name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: Great flavor, and I especially loved that we could add heat to taste. I loved the flavor of the apricots and the sweetness from the honey. I needed to cook it 7 hours on low because I went to work, but I would suggest following the directions for the best results. Thank you French Tart. Made for ZWT 6. by an Unruly Under the Influence.

name: new mexico style chili chicken casserole
review: I just stuck the cut up onion in the microwave for 3 minutes before adding in and it worked great!  I used low sodium soup and used instant salt free dry chicken bouillon and 14 oz. water in place of the chicken broth.  Delicious even with ff sour cream too!

name: baked tilapia with lots of spice
review: Very nice. I enjoyed the flavor.   I used Panko brand for the bread crumbs. I needed to use more olive oil in order to get the correct consistency for the bread crumbs to adhere to the fish.  My filets were thin so I did not need to do step 11.

name: chickpeas with spinach  greek
review: This is a delicious vegetarian dinner.  I used freshly cooked chickpeas, sun dried tomatoes and a mixture of farm fresh spinach and baby arugula.  This was served over cooked pearl barley for a heart meal.  Made for *ZWT6*

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: Very good ! Really liked the dressing I used mixed greens cause thats what I had. Made for the Queens of Quisine for ZWT 6

name: tzatziki
review: This is just outstanding Tzatziki - I have not had any better - any time any where! I used strained yoghurt and added a bit extra garlic. I used dill which made it just perfect. Thanks for a keeper recipe! Unrulies under the Influence / ZWT6 / Herculean challenge

name: company pork roast
review: Delicious glaze.  My roast dried out a bit but I will use this recipe again.  :)

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: These really earn the 5 stars!  I ate 2 huge pork chops and could have eaten another one!  Kids loved them too, so it will be repeated!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: Pretty good!  I had a bit of trouble getting my buns to cook through in the center but the taste was great.  I refridgerated the leftover dough and made pizza crust with it the following day.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I cut the potatoes into cubes, cooked this on the BBQ, but for only 1 hour. Besides that, I made this exactly as listed! LOL! Seriously though, the potatoes are terrific and the "sauce" is fabulous. My potatoes didn't brown, but I don't care - they were great! Made for ZWT6. Thanks evelyn/athens! :)

name: 7   day   soup diet recipe
review: I understand now why "the soup is the key" to this diet: you simply want to cut your tongue out after the 1st spoon-full!  I should have followed my intuition: 2 1/2 cups of tomato sauce PLUS 1/2 cup of tomato paste?!  That could NEVER work.  Yes, this will certainly make you lose weight: because you won't be able to eat it!  (And I added 3 garlic cloves, some marjoram and thyme--still, unbelievably disgusting.  I guess if you are in total desperation--which is not my case, since I only wanted to lose a couple of pounds--and are forced to do it...  I am truly sorry for my review, Mr. Sauce, but you should at least let people know this tastes horrendous.

name: double chocolate banana muffins
review: What a nice banana muffin, very different from the usual. They are def. chocolate but the banana flavour is there. They are very moist but light. They are not a dieter's friend but we all need a treat once in awhile! I know I will be using this recipe again and again. Thanks for sharing.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Moist and delicious muffin! Easy to put together, even if you are not a great baker. Definately a keeper. Thanks, KRUSTY!

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: This made my day. I am  sooo happy. When the sauce was ready, I let my son had a tiny taste of it, and he was so impatient to have the ribs baked so he can eat them. At first, I turned the oven on at 325 degrees and set the timer for 2 hours. Halfway thru baking, the ribs turned a beautiful caramel brown, shiny from the glaze. However, because I wanted to do it the way some reviewers did it, I then set the oven to 375 and baked it for a further 30 minutes. I would not do it this way next time for the ribs got slightly burnt. They were really delicious though, albeit somewhat dried out and blackened. I look forward to making them again the right way. Thank you for sharing.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Awesome to wake up to!

name: tzatziki
review: It's a great tzatziki. I used fat free thick yogurt with a little bit of sour cream cause I didn't have enough yogurt.  Next time I'll add more garlic and I'll mince it instead of a paste.  I may try with the fresh dill.  Thanks Evelyn :)  Made for the Zwizzle Chicks of ZWT

name: tzatziki
review: What can I add that over 100 haven't - this is just outstanding!  Made for ZWT6 Looney Spoon Phoodies.

name: flawless sesame chicken  restaurant style
review: I just didn't really like the sauce.  I thought it tasted too much like cornstarch.  The chicken was yummy.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: This was not watery at all!  Creamy and delicious with loads of great flavor!  How can it not with a 1/2 c. of parmesan cheese in it :)

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: I loved this!!  The only thing I didn't do was add the green pepper (personal preference), and I made the salad for one person.  I went ahead and made all the dressing though, and saved some for another salad later.  This was so good and easy to throw together -- thank you!!!

name: denny s style french toast
review: Awesome! My husband LOVED it!  Really easy and so much better than just dipping in egg.

name: kittencal s bakery buttercream  frosting icing
review: This is an excellent frosting that I have used many times.  I was just reading and read Munnumaa's review.  If it was "greasy", it certainly wouldn't be able to hold its shape, it would drip all over the place.  Maybe you should try making it again, because even from the photos you can see it's not greasy and the flavor is awesome!  Maybe you need cooking lessons!

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: Could not possibly be better!

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: My DW and I love these and so does company that comes to the house.  They quickly became well known with us!

name: chipotle roast for tacos   sandwiches
review: This was sooo good!  I allowed mine to cook overnight for about 8 hours and it was super tender!  When I took it out of the crock pot I shredded it and put in the fridge until dinner.  Then I placed the left over cooking liquid in the blender, pureed until smooth and passed it through a small strainer.  When it was time to eat I simply placed it in the skillet and reheated with some of the strained sauce. We served this in white corn tortillas and topped it with shredded cheese, sour cream, and Recipe #60137

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: Best black bean soup I have made or tasted. Well seasoned and loved the smokiness from the liquid smoke. I would say that is a key ingredient. Thanks for sharing.

name: spinach   feta stuffed chicken breast  quick   easy
review: ZWT6: VERY quick and easy - full of flavor too!! This is going to become a repeat recipe for sure!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: Excellent fish!  We have it a lot!

name: betty white s chicken wings
review: Delicious!!

name: classic baked ziti
review: Good pasta recipe.  It was very simple and tasty.  I left out the onions, but other than that followed the recipe exactly.  Thanks for the recipe.

name: tsr version of applebee s oriental chicken salad by todd wilbur
review: Really liked the dressing.  I just used plain baked chicken breasts, to save time and calories.

name: southern fried chicken
review: This was pretty good but a little on the bland side.  I will up the spices and add a few of my own next time.

name: spinach   feta stuffed chicken breast  quick   easy
review: We all liked this one and my only comment is that it took far longer to get my chicken cooked than 30 minutes...probably because I had them too close together in the pan. Otherwise delicious! I'm a Quisine Queen and made this for ZWT.

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: I'm impressed! I'm a pancake lover and these were not only very healthy, but delicious. Upon my first bite, I thought they needed some Splenda/sweetener, but then I got over it with a frew squirts of sugar-free maple syrup. I did add about 2 T. ground flax seed for extra fiber. I will enjoy these again and again!

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: I can't believe I haven't rated this one yet - I've made it several times and always get compliments from DH.  As always with a Kittencal recipe there are no disappoinments:)  Thanks so much for posting such excellent recipes.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Thank you MizzNezz for posting the best banana muffin I've ever had in my life! I made 6 without nuts and 6 with finely chopped almonds. I've never had a plate of muffins ever disappear so fast. Thanks for sharing this great recipe.

name: tzatziki
review: Loved it! Did add the dill. Made for ZWT 6 for Queens of Quisine.

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: i've never really been a fan of beef stew but i absolutely enjoyed this and even got seconds. instructions are written beautifully w/ easy to follow steps. i almost followed everything to the T except i skipped the finely minced carrots and chopped onions. i did do the finely chopped onions and regular chopped carrots w/ potatoes and they were so delicious. i did add 1 thing...the gravy was already delicious but i added a packet of sazon goya just because i wanted to finish it up before it expired. so delicious, i paired it w/ a yorkshire pudding. this is now my favorite go to beef stew and next time i'll try it on a crock pot.

name: tzatziki
review: Fantastic, and so easy to make.   Served with fresh grilled halibut and crudites!   Thanks Ev,made for ZWT #6

name: monastery lentils
review: Delicious! I don't have sherry- and can't imagine it getting any better- but will try to get some for next time.  As usual, I had to mess with this just a bit and add some garlic and cayenne.  The marjoram and thyme are perfect in this.  I'm having seconds now... and don't even feel the need to top with cheese!  Thanks so much!!

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: This wasn't a great hit with my family.  I served it over giant biscuits because the sauce, to me, tasted like a bland gravy. There was no 'cheesy' to it.  I don't know what went wrong because I followed the recipe exactly.  Maybe it's because we are accostomed to having more spice in our food?

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: This one makes me do the happy food dance!! The BEST casserole Thank You.

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: Wonderful salad. It's so much better than those limp, watery salads offered by fast food restaurants here. I used romaine lettuce and it's perfect just as it's written. The only thing I would do differently is to use green olives in deference to DD and DH's tastes but I liked it this way. Made for ZWT6 SSaSSy's

name: strawberry coffee cake
review: I made this with blackberries (with a tad bit more sugar) rather than strawberries.  It was delicious! My husband (who will rarely eat desserts) ate a piece and asked me to make it again.  It does get soggy rather quickly, but it still tastes good that way!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: Made these for dinner last night -- a total hit!  It smelled wonderful while it was baking, and tasted great when it came out.  I gave the wings a flip about halfway through the cooking time, and basted once or twice, which, I believe, contributed to a nice, even color on the wings.  Thanks for sharing, Theresa!

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: Great recipe, I loved the ratio of vinegar to oil. I didn't feel like mincing the garlic, and normally I would have just made this in the food processor (but it was otherwise occupied) so I just used 1/2 tsp. of garlic salt instead. Great and I will make again!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: These were a big hit last night! They were made just as written and there were no leftovers. Made for ZWT6 SSaSSy's.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: I know this doesn't need another 5 star rating...but oh my, it deserves it.  I am always looking for a way to cook pork chops so that they comes out moist and tender.  This recipe is flavorful, rich and creamy.  The only change I made was to use cream of chix soup as DH does not like mushrooms.  I also added some chopped onion to pan after browning the chips and caramelized them then added to the sauce.  Next time I will double the amount of the sauce as it was killer.  The chops were fall apart tender.  A keeper!

name: best apple cake
review: I reduced the sugar in the cake by 1/2c. and was tempted to reduce the sugar in the glaze by the same amount(wish I had). This cake is very good & moist (I also added cinnamon & nutmeg per other's suggestions). It is very, very sweet. I think the glaze was improved with the addition of a 1/2t. of vanilla extract. If I make again, I will reduce the sugar more. Thanks for sharing.

name: denny s style french toast
review: I made this with 2 Tsp flax seeds instead of the eggs, and served buttered and dusted with powdered sugar. It was a *huge* hit! I may add some nutmeg next time, and serve with sliced fruit as well.

name: cajun style oven fries
review: These tasted great, but as others noted, weren't very crispy.  Then again, maybe they aren't supposed to be.  Regardless, thank you for a nice variation and easy to make potato side dish.

name: flawless sesame chicken  restaurant style
review: I don't love Chinese food but my husband and I really enjoyed this dish.  I thought the flavor of the sauce was great! I took the advice of  others and used red pepper flakes (1 tsp) and only did 1/2 c. sugar for the sauce and it was plenty sweet. Also, I didn't want to buy a whole thing of sesame oil for the 2 Tbs called for in this recipe so I just ground up some sesame seeds in a spice grinder and added the powder to vegetable oil.  My only warning with this recipe is that your kitchen is kind of a mess afterwards:)  Thanks!

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: For a low calorie soup it's pretty good.  I just felt like it was missing substance.  Maybe some kidney beans or even a few more varieties of vegetables would be nice. I could see this being a nice soup to eat when you are sick and don't want much substance.

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: Thanks! This is another great keeper! I used chicken tenders and lightened it by using Light Hidden Valley Ranch, not using salt, and not using any butter (although I did spray the tops of chicken with the butter non stick cooking spray before baking.) The amounts were perfect. DH who claims to HATE ranch, LOVED this (of course he doesn't know ranch was in it ;)) and requested it again already. It's great and will be used often -- thanks again for sharing this one!

name: tzatziki
review: I liked this more than a previous recipe we've used, so glad we tried it, The boyfriend thought it needed a splash of lemon for what it's worth. Thanks for posting hun. Made for ZWT 6.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: FANTASTIC!!!  I've always shied away from cutouts because my moms were so crunchy, and I didn't realize they could be soft and delicious.  These are wonderful.  The dough was quick and easy to prepare, it rolled, cut, and baked nicely, and they taste good to boot!  And the frosting - I was scraping the bowl to lick up all that I could!  I did add a little more sugar to the dough and rolled in powdered sugar, as suggested by one reviewer.  Only problems were getting it out of the bowl (I had to scrape it out with my fingernails, even after it had been sitting out for a while) and we needed a smidge more frosting, as 3 were left naked because I ran out.  Perhaps had I not eaten so much, though.....

name: grilled cheese  diner style
review: We are in the minority here.  I made mine first and sat down with a bowl of homemade tomato soup made from Heirloom tomatoes from our garden.  I took two bites and tossed it.  DH was cooking his, one with mayo and one with butter to do a side by side.  He didn't like it either but did eat it.  We both agreed the sandwiches looked great but we also agreed the mayo changed the flavor of the sandwich.  Wish we could have joined along with all the wonderful reviews but we'll stick with butter.  Thanks for sharing!

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: I used FF half and half to make it.  We loved it spooned over our egg noodles,  It was very much enjoyed!

name: beef patties in onion gravy
review: I made these some time ago and can't believe I forgot to review them! They were very tasty! I had to make up some fresh breadcrumbs, then dry them. Like others, I also added some sliced onions while browning the patties. Everybody loved them. Thanks for posting, papergoddess.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: This is the BEST chocolate cake!! WAY BETTER than a box mix!! DH says it's "KILLER"( that means perfect!!) LOVE IT!!

name: no bake rice krispies peanut butter granola bars  lower fat
review: Wonderful and easy recipe!  I made these as a special treat for DH but I don't know, I may just keep them all to myself!  lol!  I added craisins instead of raisins, and chopped up a handful of dried pineapple and papaya along with shaved coconut, for more of a tropical granola bar.  Thanks Kitt!  Next time I'm making a double batch!

name: best grilled pork chops
review: The name says it all...these are the Best Grilled Pork Chops I've ever had! I used the full marinade for 3 boneless (thick cut) pork loin chops. These beauties grilled up so plump and juicy...full of flavor! I used Recipe #1590 . I would highly recommend making your own Lemon Pepper Seasoning Mix as I found the fresh grated lemon to add to the flavor and aroma of this awesome dish! Lastly, I used leftover marinade (boiled to reduce cross contamination) to baste the chops. Wonderful recipe which will be enjoyed many times during this grilling season (and beyond)!

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: So fresh and delicious.  The dressing was very nice.  We loved it.  Made for ZWT6.

name: meatball sub casserole
review: 3 1/2 stars!  I thought this was good but pretty darned rich!  A small portion was enough for me.  Also, it took me quite a bit longer than 15 minutes to prep this meal as stated which was unfortunate since it was a weeknight.  Surprises me since this came from a cookbook called Quick Cooking.   :)  I would reserve this meal for a night or weekend where I could prep and stick in the fridge so that I just pop it into the oven the following evening.  I substituted ground turkey easily.  I eliminated the water in this altogether.  I always do that with casserole recipes that call for it.   I find that the addition of the water makes the food........well, watery and doesn't really serve a purpose.  I baked covered in foil so that it didn't dry out.  I used Recipe #416481 as the bread in the recipe.  Thank you!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: Came out perfectly cooked ..... tender adn juicy.

name: all purpose stir fry sauce  brown garlic sauce
review: I used low sodium soy sauce with great results!  I have made this sauce many times now and each time it goes over well with whatever we have it on.

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: wow , i didnt expect that to be that good ... thanks

name: lemon tea cookies
review: WOW is all I can say....I love these and my Mother thought this the best recipe in the world! We both adore lemon and this will be added to our favorites and used again. Thank you!!! ZWT6

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: This is one sensational tagine. I used tinned chickpeas and followed the recipe, using boneless chicken thighs and a dutch oven on the stovetop. What a heavenly smell it gave my kitchen. The preserved lemon and harissa are the perfect finishing touches. Thanks so very much for posting.

name: basic sourdough bread
review: Have made this bread several times and have found that it is even better when the dough sits in the fridge overnight (per the 'zaar sourdough forum).  Also per the forum, I put a pan of water in the oven with the bread to keep it moist.  Those two fantastic 'zaar tips make this bread the perfect loaf of sourdough. 06/01/10: The bread is still in the oven and the house smells yummy!  Used the starter from Recipe#342270 #342270 to make the bread.  It rose very quickly and looks just perfect.  Thank you for posting!

name: zesty low fat chicken breasts
review: What a quick recipe to make and it tastes wonderful.  I made this for DS and I tonight for dinner and we loved it.  I did halve the recipe so we each had one and one left over to split for lunch tomorrow in a sandwich.  We both really liked the sauce, yummy.  I served this with some rice and DS liked to mix his rice with the sauce.  Thank you Bergy for sharing this great little recipe with me  and my family.  Delicious.

name: broiled tilapia with thai coconut  curry sauce
review: We are catching enough fish at present to eat it every second day and fill a freezer with the excess. I am constantly searching for recipes to keep our meals interesting and this was a great one.I used an extra teaspoon of curry paste and fish sauce rather than soy. I had to use light coconut cream, so I used half a can (will freeze the rest) and diluted that with water. I calculate this gave us just over 11g of fat in total in each serve. I could eat this again tomorrow night and am posting it to my repeatable fish recipe cookbook so that if I don't (eat it again tomorrow) I can eat it soon. We don't get tilapia in Australia, so I used Charley Court Cod, so named I've heard, because the fish and the former premier of this state both have big mouths.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: As easy as its gets and very yummy besides.  Thank you for sharing.

name: sue b s chocolate cake
review: This is the moistest cake ever! I used coconut oil and baked it in a rectangle glass pan for about 35 minutes.  It turned out great.  Thanks for sharing.

name: philly cheesesteak sandwich     authentic
review:
This is one of those recipes I can only make a few times a year due to the fact that we made total pigs out of ourselves.
I used rare deli roast beef-once the onions and peppers were cut this came together in under 5 minutes-big bonus!
I also used provolone-my Husband opted for Cheese Whiz.  He did take a bite of mine half way through the feast and was miffed-live and learn!  Served with Onion Rings.
Thank you for posting this recipe-it will be made again and again!
Di ;-)

name: easy cole slaw
review: Made this for a bunch of people at a Memorial Day motorcycle gathering.  Increased to 50 servings and it turned out great.  Had lots of compliments.  Fixing to make for lunch today.  Thanks...

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I loved the flavor of these, but I was scared that I COULD cook them too long. I reduced the recipe, for 2 huge potatoes. After 40 minutes, there was no 'white side' and I got scared that they were over cooking (even tho you say they can't be...) and I added water to the pan twice in the last 20 minutes or so. I should have reduced my oven temp; I would have not been so worried, but I was trying to follow directions, and working 3 'recipes' at once. I enjoyed the flavor of the potatoes, and I was super glad that I had used foil! I used 3 garlic cloves and lots of sea salt and fresh ground pepper. I will be making these again! Thanks for sharing, Ev! Made for ZWT.

name: mama iuliucci s famous meat a balls  italian meatballs
review: I just tried one that came out of the oven.... Fantastic!  Can't wait to try them with a spaghetti or swedish sauce.  I baked them on a cooling rack set inside a baking sheet at 450 F for about 15 minutes or until the internal temp reached 160 F.  Thanks for posting!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: Comfort food at it's best! We loved this pot pie. I made 1/2 the recipe following it as written. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 6.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Ohhhh....cinnamony goodness.  We love snickerdoodles but I've never tried to make them.  I decieded to give it a go last night and they were delicious.  Simple to prepare and took no time at all.  Thank you for sharing this recipe with us.

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: I know you don't NEED another glowing review, but I just have to say this recipe is fantastic! I made Rolls out of this dough and  they turned out wonderful. Next time I will bake a loaf of bread. Thank you for posting this winner.

name: kittencal s juicy hamburger burger
review: Once again, Kitten, BRAVO! I have been complaining that I can never seem to make a burger at home that tastes as good as the ones I get in a restaurant.... well not anymore! My hubby is going to think I'm the best cook ever because of you :) Thanks for the awesome burgers!  (p.s.  I used very lean meat and they were STILL juicy!)

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: This is indeed really good. I bake a lot of cakes and quick breads, and would say that this is between the two. It was done at one hour for me. I wasn't sure about bringing my freezer temperature down, but did follow the directions. Someone mentioned still having to cool it after 45 minutes in the freezer - mine was very cool after/the pan was frozen. I always decrease the sugar in recipes. Since many people halved the sugar in both the cake and the frosting, I quartered both of them - and it was still sweet enough for us. The walnuts are a very nice addition to this.

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: I made this with cubed tofu instead of the chicken and added a bit of crushed red pepper to the sauce. I only had to cook it about 45 minutes before the edges started to blacken. It was awesome, thanks so much!

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: It was amazing.  Made as written and it turned out moist and flavorful.  Thank you.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: I had really high hopes for this because of so many wonderful reviews. It was just okay to me. It actually tasted too sweet and I only used 1 cup of sugar. The texture was off for me as well.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Good base recipe.  My kids loved the flavor - light and sweet!  Easy to add fruit before baking or as a topping.

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: These fish and chips were very nice!  The times given for cooking were perfect, and our fish was crispy on the outside- tender and moist on the inside.  Both the fish and the chips came out a little darker than I had hoped- likely because the oil in my fryer needs to be changed.  This didn't affect the taste at all, just the color.  I also had a bit of batter left after the fish was done, so I sliced up some onions and tossed them in; they were so much better than onion rings from a fast food joint!  I served with malt vinegar and homemade tarter sauce on the side.  Thanks for another wonderful recipe!  MADE for ZWT6.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: I love salmon but DH and DD's do not.  Well, they are all out of town adn DS and I are left to ourselves.  So we made your recipe and were not dissappointed.  It was so delicious I was practically licking my plate clean.  I loved loved loved the mustard cream sauce on the fish.  I used fresh dill weed instead of the dry but otherwise followed the recipe exactly.  We can't wait for them to leave again....lol.....and we already know what we are making.  Thank  you so much for one of DS and my favorites.

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: DS loved these!  I had two pots of oil going, one for the fish and one for the potatoes.  I soaked and double fried my potatoes, so they were extra crispy and nice.  Plus, with two pots, everything came out hot at the same time!  Served with malt vinegar and tartar sauce.  I did let my batter sit for an hour before dipping the fish.  Don't know if it made a difference, but these were wonderful!

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: Took this to a graduation party, everyone loved it!  I doubled the recipe so I could keep some for me : )

name: chili s spicy garlic   lime shrimp
review: Really good!  Made as written and I wouldn't change anything.  Thank you!

name: 24k carrots
review:
UPDATE On 6/20/10: I've made these carrots so many times and can't believe I've never posted a photo. Well, I've made these again and here's the photo. And I have to say they are just as good if not better than the first time they were made. My first time to review this recipe was November 3rd,2006
I just want to say that my SO and I really enjoyed these carrots very much.I thought that the ginger and brown sugar gave the dish that "something special"that is usually missing from carrots.These will be made again,Thank you for posting.

name: basic batter waffles
review: Good basic recipe. I used 1/2 whole wheat flour and they still turned out great.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review:
I can't rate this. It basically tasted like cheese dip. Sorry.

I make soup once a week religiously and love all soups. I have actually had the Panera Broccoli Cheese and this tastes nothing like it. It was part of a topic thread, so I decided to taste it, but it is definitely not my taste. Too much carrot, cheese the combination was just NOT right at all. I did puree, but left a few pieces of broccoli, used everything to directions and I honestly just didn't want to eat it.  I gave it to a friend who is single and lives down the street and told him it was an experiment, he is single so I thought he might light it.  Who knows.  Thx for posting, but definitely something I wouldn't make again. So sorry

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: I marinated for 5.5 hours and it was tasty. Some said the lemon was overpowering, but I didn't think so.  Didn't cube meat and used boneless chicken breasts on inside grill.  Will try on tilapia or other light white fish, then pork, as suggested by others.  Thanks for sharing.

name: strawberry julius
review: My kids just devoured these!  Easy to prepare, delicious, and reminded one of my sons very much of the "real thing" he gets at the mall.  Thanks so much; what a great way to use up fresh strawberries!

name: the ultimate strawberry shortcake
review: I made this using fat free cream cheese and fat free whipped topping, but don't tell! I never mentioned it and no one could tell.  I took it to the in laws for a father's day cook out.  The plates all came back clean.  I think it's safe to say it was enjoyed by all.

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: Let me start out by saying that my daughter and I had so much fun making this together tonight! Thank you for that. :)  The directions were written perfectly and the fish and chips were just lovely. My daughter was amazed that it all looked like something from a restaurant. Both the fish and the chips were crispy on the outside and tender on the inside. Simple. Perfect. Thank you! ~Made for Zee Zany Zesty ones for the ZWT6~

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Wow! Very rich, creamy and absolutley delicious! I layered mine and froze them. I baked them @ 400, covered with foil for about an hour and half. Turned out perfect! Thanks so much.

name: chili s salsa
review: AWESOME!!! We all love this salsa!  I have made it many times as is, and thought that I would add that I have recently made it using home grown tomatoes and peppers.  I just peeled the tomatoes first, and cooked it on the stove top for 10 minutes before blending.  It tasted just the same as using canned, and helped with the overflow of fresh tomatoes.

name: kittencal s juicy hamburger burger
review: I fixed these for our Father's Day bbq.  Everyone raved about them!  My son-in-law wanted the recipe, and I consider him a very good cook, so I was flattered.  You've made me look good once again, Kitten!

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: Fabulous! Made it this morning with fresh blueberries, followed the recipe exactly.  Mine was perfecting done in 45 minutes. I dusted with powdered sugar. DH and I both loved it.  Can't wait to make it when the kids stay over!

name: glazed cinnamon rolls   bread machine
review: Per my DH's request on Father's Day, I made cinnamon rolls. This was my first attempt at them, and I followed the recipe exactly. I have no complaints other than the glaze. To me, it tasted just like powdered sugar. Would be very good with a different frosting.

name: rhubarb crisp
review: Perfect! I didn't change a thing and was really happy how it turned out. I love topping and was happy with the amount. It was crunchy on top and soft and sweet/tart underneath. Simple, and good, it's a keeper!

name: italian chopped salad in shells
review: This was ok....I made it for a family dinner - everyone agreed that it needed *something*....but no one could figure out what that *something* was....

name: honey ginger grilled salmon
review: i marinated for 2 days .. cook it on the BBQ ..... and wow that was super good ..thanks

name: strawberry julius
review: Heather this was good, but I much prefered this made with frozen sweetened strawberries. The frozen berries thicken up the strawberry julius just a bit. The last time I made this using frozen sweetened strawberries, was about 2 years ago, but I forgot to rate this recipe, and post my review. I had also added a bit more sugar, since I found my frozen berries weren't sweet enough. This was very good, and I'd like to thank you Heather for posting this recipe.

name: microwave poached eggs
review: That was so easy! Thank you so much! My mom poaches eggs in the microwave but I've never paid attention when I visited as to the how. I started with hot water and my egg was a little overdone for my taste (I like very runny) but it was not dry, so I'll try 55 seconds next time. Otherwise it was great, very easy. I microwaved a couple of slices of bacon before and had a lovely breakfast on a slice of whole wheat toast... Should get me through the whole morning for a change :). Thanks again!!

name: hamburger noodle bake
review: This was a great alterntive to lasagna.  It was really good.  I used no yolk egg noodles and I also added 2 tsp of italian seasoning to the meat mixture.  I was only able to put two layers of the meat though.  It turned out wonderful tasting.  I fixed garlic rolls and a salad to go with it.  Thanks for sharing.  Made for Zaar Cookbook tag.  June 2010

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: I made this lasagna last week and it turned out great my whole family loved it.I used ricotta cheese as I did not have any cottage cheese on hand.I will definetely be making this again.Thanks for the recipe

name: strawberries   cream bread  strawberry or blueberry
review: Great recipe.  I used strawberries that I picked that morning.

name: denny s style french toast
review: As good as fresh donuts, less hassle. We have made these for countless times by now.

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: Prettiest PB cookies I've ever made! Personally I thought they could use more oatmeal. For the final tray I added an extra palm full to the remaining mix and liked them better that way. I'm not a pb cookie person so I left the reviews to everyone else. Everyone really liked them but I didn't get RAVE reviews or requests for more. I may try them again with chunky pb and a little more oatmeal though.  Thanks for the recipe! Oh and I definitely got more like 3 dozen!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: So good! My son and I devoured these taters and wanted more! Thanks! Made for ZWT#6-Family Picks.

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: I loved this recipe! The batter was so perfect. The fish was slightly crunchy but melted in my mouth as I enjoyed every bite. The fries were just wonderful. I had homemade tartar sauce and lemon wedges to go with it. This is a definite keeper! Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 6.

name: thai coconut rice
review: Yum! Made this with brown rice, used extra ginger and Lite Coconut Milk.  Wonderful side dish! Thank you for sharing this winner Geema!

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: Excellent and a party favorite.  Thanks for sharing.

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: What a great idea to use a tortilla as a base for a pie. This quiche pie is very easy and quick, yet great tasting.

name: italian chopped salad in shells
review: We thought these were pretty good but I'm not sure if it is worth the work.  I'm sure I will make these again so thanks for something a little different.

name: eric s easy grilled chicken
review: Kudos to your brother if he came up with this combo.  Never would have thought Teriyaki and Italian together, but they totally work.  Used 2 x with skinless chicken thighs, so simple and yummy.  Usually make my own dressings, but bought a bottle of Teriyaki and Italain dressing to have on hand just for this recipe!

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: This is wonderful comfort food!

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review:
5 for a great dish
5 for flavor, but I did have to alter it to my tastes.

But a great dish, and I loved them baked.

I did use a good salsa. I do love spice, lots of it, but I cut back on the cumin and oregano.  However, I used a very flavorful good salsa, a more plain salsa or picante may require more seasoning. My salsa was a "more gourmet blend," so it had lots of seasoning already.

I did use a Mexican blend of cheeses too.

My garnish was simple a green enchilada sauce, sour cream and diced olives.

If I was home I may of served over a bed of lettuce with some fresh diced tomatoes and scallions, but I was at work (making it for co workers) so I didn't get that fancy.

I did spray with olive oil vs margarine, and they turned out golden brown.

It was easy, great taste, much healthier and I enjoyed them.  Very very good.

Black beans would be another good addition to them, but the chicken and salsa was perfect.

Thx for a great easy quick recipe.
Kim

name: simple sweet scones
review: Wonderful scones.....very light, easy to assemble.  I followed the recipe exactly but used a little less milk than called for as the dough was coming together and it didn't seem to need all it.  Turned out great. I am making this my new scone recipe!  Thanks so much for a real treat !

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: These are the best tasting salmon patties that I've ever had.  I did add some dill, lemon pepper and some hot sauce.  I saved one patty to try as a sandwich.  Looking forward to it.

name: our daily bread in a crock   weekly make and bake rustic bread
review: Unbelievable! This is both the easiest and the best baguette/boule recipe I've ever tried. Thank you thank you thank you!

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: Great tasting broccoli side here, & easy to prepare, too! I did use the fresh stuff! And the lemon juice, garlic & red pepper flakes = A great seasoning combo, always! Will be making this one again! [Made & reviewed during ZWT6 for Family Picks]

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: I used frozen broccoli and didn't add any water (frozen vegetables usually don't need any when microwaving).  I also subbed a little smoked paprika for the red pepper flakes.  A really nice way to jazz up a simple veggie.  Thanks for posting!  Made for ZWT6 Family Picks.

name: weight watchers mexican chicken breasts
review: Delicious! I left off the sour cream... we're not fans of it. It was still great!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Good stuff! I used whole wheat spaghetti and omitted the onion, minced garlic and bell pepper so the sauce wouldn't be chunky. I did use some onion and garlic powder for that flavor though. DH and I both loved the flavor of the sauce, and thought it might be fun to try this dish as a lasagna with some ricotta mixed in. We just might do that! Thanks for sharing it!

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: This is definitely more like a dessert to me.  It's good, but I found it to be too sweet to serve as a side dish accompanying a meal.  As a dessert, I think it's fine.  I have another fruit salad recipe that I usually use, but this one had such high ratings, I thought I'd give it a try.  I do think this method of dressing a fruit salad with vanilla pudding would be a great way to help out some fruit that is lacking in natural sweetness--maybe a way to salvage some overly tart grapes or some flavorless strawberries.

name: wholly guacamole
review: This may not need another 5 star review, but we just had to add our praise - this was excellent!  We made just as directed, except we halved the recipe.  Yummy!!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review:
I did not have the 4-5 hours, so I cooked the chicken, shredded it and added to the balance, and turned the crock on low. We had it over rice, so good! Thank you!

I just had to rate this again.  I did not drain the beans or corn. When I shredded the Costco chicken it soaked up the juice  Perfection. Served with flour tortillas.   Who ever invented crock pots are my hero.

name: perfect basic white rice
review: Thanks . . . guess the 'no peaking' is the trick, it was perfect! Served with Sweet & Sour Pork and Egg Rolls. Thanks for sharing.  Made again for ZWT#6 . . . love this method!

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: This was very good!  My husband loved it and he doesn't even like Minestrone soup usually.  I'm sure I'll be making this again and again. I didn't try adding red wine this time but will be sure to next time!

name: self rising flour
review: Nice recipe to have around.  Thanks for posting.

name: baked stuffed pasta shells
review: I made this for supper the other night and it was enjoyed by all.  I did have to use manicotti shells as my local grocery didn't carry the large shells.  I will look elsewhere for next time but it didn't change the flavor any.   I did all a 1/2 lb. of hamburger to the sauce for added flavor, but otherwise followed your recipe.  I served this with garlic bread and a salad, delicious meal.  Thank you for sharing this with us.

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: Very nice. I used garam masala instead of curry powder. Right amount of spiciness, and all. I left out the golden raisins and yogurt because I didn't have them, but it was still excellent. I gave it four stars instead of five, because the children didn't care for it. It must be a grown-up food in our house.

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: Thank's again Kittencal, you always come through for us. Tonight I used your Taco Seasoning Mix when preparing  "Recipe #349745" which I've made several times to great family reviews.  Being out of Taco seasoning tonight, I used this recipe as a substitute and my DH, who never says much, came to tell me that although he always likes this meal, something was different and it was just over the top!  There could never be a better review -- so much for store bought Taco seasoning mix.  This only took minutes to throw together and totally an already very good meal to the exceptional level.  This seasoning is made quickly with ingredients most of us already have on hand.  High five Kitten!!

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: I never bake pies because I've never been able to make a pie crust I was proud of.  I see myself gaining a bit of weight in the near future, because this pie crust is HEAVENLY!  Thank you so very much for sharing an absolutely wonderful recipe!

name: saltine candy   toffee
review: These were sinfully rich and delicious.  I was out of chocolate chips so subbed in white chocolate chips with no problem.  I also used walnuts and it all went together great.  Thank you for supplying us with this great yummy snack.....We love it.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: What I especially like about these is the milder taste of salmon in them.  Since I usually cook just for myself, I cut the recipe in half to use the smaller can of salmon but use the entire egg.  This makes a mixture that's impossible to make into patties, but it works fine to drop into the pan.  They're nice and moist and don't even need a sauce.  Thanks for sharing this recipe!

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: I doubled the recipe because there are 6 of us. My son who sometimes likes eggs loved these and ate two servings. They were so light and fluffy that we all liked them.

name: best low carb bread  bread machine
review: I love this bread!! my hubby bought me a bread machine a couple of month ago and our new deal is no more store bought bread; BUT,  I also don't want to turn us into two little dough boys like I did right before we got married and I went through a big baking phase-lol  so this is a fab way to make sure I keep up the deal AND stay somewhat healthy...I have made it 4 times in the past month- I do it vegan w/ energy egg re-placer and earth balance...add a pinch of salt and a sprinkle of whole flax in the mix too for texture...will be trying the chia, olive oil and coconut flours that others suggested as well...and also will try banana as the "butter" sub  too- anyhoo- LOVE IT!!- thanks!!! my favorite bread!!!

name: legal seafood style baked scallops
review: Add me to the long list of believers! This is a great recipe.....wouldn't change a thing. Thanks for posting.....I'm just sorry it took me so long to find it.

name: redneck casserole
review:
Yummy, easy, and downright delicious! I used the tiny tater tots, and Bushs' Original Baked Beans. The hardest part of this recipe is waiting to eat it... the smell alone will make your mouth water!!!
I am back to add a note- I made this tonight using the hotdogs that come stuffed with cheese- it made this even yummier!

name: quick spanish rice
review: DELICIOUS!! Compliments all around! Thank you for a great recipe!

name: creamy potato salad
review: Very good!  Thanks for the recipe.

name: moist and tender turkey  or turkey breast
review: OH MY!! How moist and delicious. I had to use Miracle Whip (was out of mayo) and I cooked 1/2 of a turkey. I had cut it in half at Christmas for the 2 of us. It browned nicely and was wonderful.  Will definitely make this again and again. I think from now on I will only buy turkey breasts--it's so moist with this recipe. I didn't make gravy with it but I could see where it would be great too.

name: veronica s easy spanish rice
review: I have been making this recipe for years and it is my favorite spanish rice recipe.  This was the first spanish rice recipe my husband really liked.  In addition to the garlic powder, I also add a couple cloves of garlic in with the onion and rice.  I add 1/2-1 tsp cumin in with all other seasonings, too.  Sometimes when I don't feel like chopping green bell pepper, I add a 4 oz can of chopped green chiles.  I love the recipe and use it often!

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: WOW! Deeeeeelicious! I doubled the recipe and we have plenty for lunch tomorrow. This recipe deserves more than 5 stars - easy recipe, easy directions, clean up a snap, and chock full of flavor! I had everything on hand, too so no need to run to the store. I used sundried tomato and basil sweet sausage. I didn't have heavy cream so I made my own (3/4 c. skim milk and 1/3 c. melted butter and 1 tsp of flour = 1 c. cream). I had Rigatoni on hand and cooked it al dente (~ 12 oz). My 6 year old ate it up and said she wants this everyday! LOL. She's getting some for lunch tomorrow, as will I. She wants me to make this when we go to Myrtle Beach next week. I think our friends are going to LOVE this too. Thanks for posting...this is a keeper!!! - Also, this recipe (doubled) easily could feed 6 to 8 people.  My serving size is 1 cup for this recipe.  Served with a nice garden salad and a side of veggies (steamed zucchini), you don't need more than a cup of this pasta (although it's too tempting not to go back for seconds.)  Just read some reviews and I'm SHOCKED people are complaining it lacked in flavor or was bland.  My DH is as picky as they get, and he oooh'd and awwww'd about the GREAT flavor this dish had.  I didn't have to make any adjustments.

name: perfect basic white rice
review: This was very good but slightly overcooked for our taste. I like the method and will make it again but cook for less time. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 6.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Talk about an easy recipe! 268 good reviews don't lie--I followed directions, but utilized comments to shorten cooking time--overnight for 12 hours and about an hour more after adding the barbeque sauce.  Turned out great.  Thanks for a foolproof recipe.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: This is the classic tuna noodle casserole that I grew up eating.  I loved all of the add ins, like the pimientos, because they added a lot of great flavors.  The only thing I did differently was to substitute bread crumbs for the crushed Ritz crackers.  Thanks for the lovely recipe!

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: Salad perfection!  Cut back heavily on the oil, you won't notice the difference.  Used more vinegar too (it's the way I like it), otherwise no changes.  Yes, of course we used lettuce!  Oops, I did add 1 stalk celery that we had too. :)

name: tortured chicken   beer can
review: I've been wanting to try one of these "beer butt chicken" recipes, and I'm glad I picked this one! Very tasty! UPDATE: I used this on the grill. I still cut the recipe in half and used it on 2 small chickens. I grilled on indirect heat for about 2 hours...fantastic!! NEWER UPDATE: Did this on the smoker....UNBELIEVABLE!!! Soooo good! I tried a different recipe once, and my family said "Never Again!" This is the only recipe I'll use!!

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: This is a very good moist loin.   We served with wild rice and peas.  Thank you

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: Definitely one of your best recipes of all time. I used light Ranch and whole wheat seasoned breadcrumbs. The chicken turned out very moist and flavorful.I melted the butter but forgot to add it until almost finished eating. I must say that even though I LOVE butter I actually preferred the chicken without it so if you consider calories and fat in your diet don't think twice about skipping it. I will be making this over and over and over again. Thank you Kittencal.

name: all purpose stir fry sauce  brown garlic sauce
review: use this sauce on a chicken and vegies stir fry and it was super good thanks

name: pronto pups aka corn dogs
review: Absolutely Delicious!!!!  Very easy too.  I will make these often!

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: Really easy and great flavors.  I served this at room temperature, I skipped the baking step. Really wonderful blending of flavors. I probably added a little more that 2 TBSP of the Parmesan, but otherwise followed the recipe exactly.  The flavors were just wonderful. I want to try it next time with some Feta, as another reviewer suggested.  Thanks

name: tzatziki
review:
perfectly yummy!
made and served with greek chicken. used half greek yogurt and half sour cream, perfection!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: Much better than I expected, will do it again with a sweet pie, I used it for a quiche and it gave a nicely crumbly result.

name: copycat lipton s onion soup mix
review: I was a little scared of this recipe because of the celery seed.  I hate celery.  But after it was mixed in with the other ingredients and added to the sour cream....oh man, I'm hooked!  I used a vegetarian beef powder substitute, and it still tastes like the real thing, but without all the nasty things they add to it--and cheaper too.  I needed some mix for a spinach recipe and decided to try this, given the good reviews. This is a real keeper, and will be used OFTEN!

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: On a lark, I tried Hidden Valley Farmhouse Originals Roasted Onion and Parmesan dressing with this instead of Ranch... I only had Italian seasoned breadcrumbs, so I omitted the seasoned salt.  Very yummy and easy, too. I did not use the butter.

name: quick soft breadsticks
review: This sure does make alot!! I froze over half of them. I used all purpose flour and it turned out fine. I added in italian seasoning to the bread, let it rise for 1 hour, sprayed with Pam butter spray, sprinkled garlic powder and into the oven. I meant to add parmesan cheese but forgot.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: Great recipe!! I used seasoned breadcrumbs instead of cornmeal, but other than that I followed the recipe exactly! Thanks!!

name: easy way lasagna
review: I was looking for a quick and easy lasagna to make for tonite's dinner.  I'm sure glad that I chose this one.  Since we like a meaty lasagna, I did add hamburger to the spaghetti sauce, along with minced garlic.  It was so easy to put together and I loved not having to cook the noodles first.  Went great with a salad and garlic bread.  We'll make this again.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: Best salmon patties ever!

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: Really good. Didn't use pepper due to allergy. Used 1 tsp. oregano, 8 cloves garlic, no salt, 1 cube bouillon, beans were fresh so used water. Very good, even my daughter that prefers not to eat beans liked it!

name: enchilada sauce
review: Very good!  I left out the garlic for my husband and just added in a little garlic pepper instead. I also cut back slightly on the chili powder for my personal taste.  Three adults and one kid enjoyed this... the other kid, thought this was too spicy (no surprise & no reflection on the recipe- I just made her enchiladas with no sauce).  We enjoyed this sauce in one of our favorite enchilada recipes: Recipe #106205 .

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: Soooo yummy!!!  I halved the recipe for the 3 of us and use cajun season salt for taste.  Really a great way to prepare cauliflower which can usually be pretty boring.  Thanks for sharing!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: I can't imagine not loving this.  It's the best!

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: This had a good flavor. I added 1 1/2 teaspoons dry Ranch seasoning mix to the crumb mixture, and I used a little more garlic powder than called for. I brushed the Ranch dressing on with a pastry brush, and I had just the right amount of crumb mixture. I didn't use butter; instead, I sprayed the pan and the chicken lightly with cooking spray. I baked them at 425 for 26 minutes, flipping once at half the time. My chicken didn't brown, but it cooked through fine and tasted good (I had mine on the middle rack - I didn't see the "setting rack to lowest position" thing until just now - lol). I served this with mac and cheese and steamed broccoli. I might do this again, next time with the oven rack set in the right place. ;) Thanks, I'm glad we tried it.

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: Super easy and the kernels were very juicy!  Can't believe I have never thought of doing this before!

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: Loved this coffee cake.  Just had a piece for breakfast.  OH YUM!  I had a ten inch springform pan and it took 45 min.

name: kittencal s extreme chocolate brownies
review: I made these for the family because everyone was dying for something chocolate.  This really satisfied our chocolate cravings, I can tell you that much!  I added 1 c. chopped walnuts and will try pecans next time.  The nuts really put them in first place and it is now our new go to brownie recipe.

name: chewy granola bars
review: Very good.  The only problem is they don't last as long as the store bought kind because we eat them faster:)  I made as called for but omitted the nuts.  I may try to add some peanut butter next time as well.  Thanks for posting!

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: I hate to give this one such low marks but we didn't like this at all.  We love all the ingredients in it but the way it came together just didn't work for us.  DH said it had too many flavors going on and I think I agree.  It did make a beautiful presentation though!  Thanks for sharing!

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: Need I even make a review?  So far, every recipe that I've tried has been great.  You are my 'iron chef' of recipezaar.

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: Made these today for my blueberry muffin-loving 14 year old son. They domed up really beautifully and I got exactly 8 muffins as the recipe said. We skipped the topping altogether and they were plenty sweet and very good without it. The dough is really thick and sticky, I was a bit worried I had done something wrong, but they turned out wonderfully perfect. Thanks for a new favorite, DebM.  *Update - made with topping and it put these over the top!  Very very good recipe....look and taste just like bakery muffins, without the "institutional" taste.  :]

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: This is an awesome recipe!  The flavor is wonderful :)  I served this with basmati rice and steamed cauliflower.  Leftovers are great!

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: Great breakfast choice and great with tea, cocoa or coffee!  We all really liked it!

name: olive garden fettuccine alfredo
review: Delicious, however I did make a few changes.  I used 1 1/2 c. half and half and 4 oz. of lite cream cheese and only 1/4 c margarine.  All other ingredients I kept the same.  Put it all in microwave for about 5 min.  So good and so easy. Next time I thinks I'll add some broccoli and chicken.

name: basic machine french bread
review: We love this bread and it has become our standard sandwich bread.  I like the fact it doesn't use oil or butter but yet still tastes good and isn't very dense.  we make it all the time!

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: With so many wonderful reviews I decided to make this, and while the taste was nice, it was just okay for me.  I even asked my boys who tried some and they said the same, it's okay.  I followed the recipe to a T and even used the egg, and I know all tastes are different, but for me, there was just no wow factor.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: I guess I had good luck because this recipe really worked out well for me.  My family thought it was great and asked me to make it again this week!

name: fusion avocado
review:
This is really good!
Try it!

name: soft batch chocolate chip cookies
review: A nice soft cookie using..who knew???  Instant vanilla pudding?  A great addition.  Thanks for a great keeper:-)

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Yummy frosting!  I made it to top your brownies that I made.  This really tasted great and I will use it again and again!

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: I made this almost exactly as written. I had to use bone in chicken as this was all I had and I baked it in the oven because I got a late start and it wouldn't have been done in time for dinner in a crock pot! The chicken was SUPER tender and falling off the bone almost! I baked it covered in a casserole dish in the oven for about an hour and left the cover off and cooked for another 15 minutes to brown up the stuffing. This was great! Very easy and tasted wonderful with mashed potatoes and asparagus. The gravy tasted very homemade and not like "canned soup"! I can't wait to make this in the crock pot. I love using my crock pot and coming home to a cooked meal! Thanks for posting Anne!

name: frizzled cabbage
review: So very good!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Oh Yum!  I, too, used montreal seasoning rather than lemon pepper seasoning.  Convected this for 20 minutes at 400!  PERFECTION!

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: Quick, easy and very tasty.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: This was good.  They were easy to make and there were no complaints at the supper table.  I may add rotel, like others, just to give them more flavor; although my kids might not eat them if they get too spicy.  Thanks for sharing.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Really good! This is how I made mine...First I marinated as directed for about 8 hours. I grilled on the Forman grill for about 6 min. While that was grilling I boiled the marinade and dipped  chicken in that once done. Then I spooned a couple Tbsp over chicken. Really great recipe! Thanks for posting this!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Perfect! I used the food processor as suggested and they came out perfect. I used a large cutter but then switched to a small one to use as much of the dough as I could without having to mess with the dough. The dough was very sticky and soft but pat out easily. My husband has been trying to make bisuits like these for a long time...they never turn out right...thanks to this recipe I got it the first try ;)

name: black bottom banana bars
review: Good, not great. It is very moist (I used 3 LARGE bananas). I also doubled the cocoa and think the recipe needs it. These are not the texture of brownies, but denser than cake.

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: I made this as directed and it turned out great! This is one of those recipe's I will be using alot. Thanks so much for posting! :)

name: lemon tea cookies
review: These are great cookies. I did have to add more flour (a little more than a cup) to make it not so sticky and more like cookie dough. I didn't refrigerate either and used my cookie press. I could have stood by the stove and just eaten the filling-spoon by spoon. It is wonderful!! And I like how the cookies seem to be more delicate than others. True winner of a lemon cookie!! Thank you for sharing-made for ZWT6 as an Xtra Hot Dish.

name: wholly guacamole
review: Excellent!  Made a 1/2 recipe of it last night for the opening game of the CFL for the hubby, there is nothing left.  Much better for him than a chips and dip. Defiantely will be making it again.

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: Delicious, indeed!  (After hundreds of glowing reviews I hardly think there is anything I can add that hasn't already been said.)  We used low fat graham crackers and Skippy peanut butter.  Also, we lined the pan with wax paper (as suggested) for easy prep n' press & cleanup.  These really do taste similar to Reese's...can't wait to make them again!

name: cheddar bar b q chicken breasts
review: Here's how I made it.  Baked frozen breasts for 50 minutes at 375 (topped with a little sauce).  Then added more sauce, bacon bits and put it back in the oven until the cheese melted.  Topped with the onion.  Served it with homemade mashed red skinned potato salad and my kids and husband loved it!

name: creamy ramen noodles
review: My kids begged me for seconds.  When I told them there were no leftovers, they begged me to buy more Ramen & make it for lunch the next day.  Overall, my kids enjoyed the chicken ramen over the beef...more flavors to be tried in the future, I'm sure!  Also, I'll experiment w/the amt of butter used, to see if i can use less w/out compromising the taste.  Thank you for a real kid pleaser!

name: brady bunch pork chops
review: Due to unforeseen circumstances and not reading the recipe carefully, my chops rested in their brine for about 24 hours, then another 48 hours or so out of the brine.  Yes, they were moister and more tender than usual.  Next time I will do a better job of following the recipe.

name: cheese tortellini pesto pasta salad
review: For all the work involved in putting this together, I expected it to be a real hit at the last company potluck.  I got zero reaction which means no one really cared for it and there was a ton of leftovers that had to be thrown out.  Pretty much tasteless was my reaction.  Sorry, will not repeat nor recommend.

name: tortured chicken   beer can
review: really good chicken

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: Great recipe! I would use less oil next time though and just cook on a cookie sheet the whole time to get them crispy, but really nice idea and I'm so glad to have tried these! Thanks for posting!

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: This is a good recipie.  I did make some changes.  I didn't use a cup of celery, carrot or onion.  I used 1 carrot, 1 stalk of clery and half an onion.  I also made my own taco seasoning.  The one thing I think this recipie lacks is lime juice.  Squeeze one juicy lime in to this soup and it will take it over the top!

name: easy pineapple upside down cake
review: Perfect! I used the juice from the can as part of the water. So yummy!

name: cheese tortellini pesto pasta salad
review: We thought this was great, we took it to our picnic and it lasted well, the salad was a hit! Thank you!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: Great brownies. I've made them twice now, and they are just delicious. This time I added toffee bits and glazed pecan chips and they were seriously amazing. This is sooooo easy too. Thanks! :-)

name: buttered egg noodles  best ever
review: Good noodles but I think that the directions are lacking a bit.  Even as a pretty experienced cook I was ready to prepare these in a tall, burner sized, metal saucepan.  Thank goodness I read some reviews first to realize that this needs to be made in a shallow, large bottomed pan such as a non-stick skillet (which is what I ended up using).  The taste delivered what I expected but to take it up a notch I snipped fresh parsley and parmesan cheese over the top before serving.

name: granny s banana cream pie
review: This pie is excellent!  So creamy and delicious.  It just takes minutes to make.   Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: the best pasta salad
review: Doubled this recipe and took to a barbecue. Only change I made was to use a variety of green, red, orange, and yellow peppers for additonal color. Easy, quick to fix, and everyone enjoyed it. Made this in the morning, tossed it all together, and didn't need to rewet with additional dressing. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: cherry pie filling bread
review: A nice option to banana, zucchini and pumpkin bread. I used 1 cup of melted butter and turned this into muffins rather than a loaf.

name: cheese and garlic drop biscuits
review: Thanks Marg!  Just got home from a trip and wanted something that I could throw together. These were great. I made as directed, except the cheese was a finely grated italian blend. Will make again.

name: basil pesto
review: I made this today so we could serve it over some low carb Dreamfield's Pasta.  I love the taste of this, it's yummy.  I used Romano cheese in mine because the zing it has better then Parmesan.  Thanks for the easy and tasty recipe.

name: easy baked potato wedges
review: These were so good! Rather than brushing each wedge with the oil mixture, I just tossed it all together in a large bowl and it seemed to work fine. I'll be making this often -- thanks for posting!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: So easy and delicious.  Cut cooking time a bit by cooking on high part of the time.

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: Easy and ooooh so decadent. I lined the pan with wax paper too. Took them to a Fourth of July celebration and it was so hot today that I had to keep moving in and out of the refrigerator. But they were a big hit.

name: lemon baked cod
review: The grown-ups loved this while the kids thought it was too lemony (is that even possible?)  I had the same problem as mamawJ with the pasty flour on the bottom.  I will try to solve this next time by only flouring the top of the fillets.  Changes made were to use black pepper and tilapia because those are what I had on hand.

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: Excellent!  Great flavor and so easy to prepare. Thanks for posting!

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: Oh wow!  This is divine!  Thank you for sharing this awesome cauliflower recipe.  My family loved it and requested it often.  Yes indeed, I will oblige....lol.

name: honey ginger grilled salmon
review: Very good!  Even my beef loving sons liked this recipe.  I followed it to the letter only substituting real garlic for the powder.  Thanks for posting.

name: perfect southern fried chicken
review: This chicken is sooooo good!  I don't know what more I can say; we just loved it!  Thank you!

name: ground beef gyros
review: that was ok

name: eric s easy grilled chicken
review: Made a double batch of these yesterday and they received rave reviews (and many 2nd helpings!) from my guests.  I used the homemade Good Seasons for the italian dressing, double the recipe and tripled the garlic.  I let it filleted chicken breasts marinate about 9 hours.  Excellent!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: huuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuummmmmmmmmmm

name: homemade rice a roni
review: Awesomw base recipe.  I added green onions, celery, grated carrots and mushrooms.  It would be delicious as written but I didn't want to make a side veggie so I put it all in the rice and it was so good.  Served with pan fried shrimp and it was a nice dinner for a very hot summer day.  Thanks for posting!!!

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: Tasty spinach pie. I made this a lower calorie and fat recipe by using 2 cups of egg whites with 2 whole eggs, soymilk, and reduced fat cheddar cheese. I enjoyed using a tortilla for the crust.  Easy to put together and cooks up beautifully. I had to cook it an extra 20 minutes for whatever reason before the middle firmed up.  I also added some sriracha and fresh basil to the eggs in step 1.  This is something I would make again. Thanks!

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: These are very sweet - but, heck who wants a cookie that isn't.  i found I couldn't fit 16 onto a full sheet - 12 worked better and they were a perfect size once baked.  Do cool them on the cookie sheet for a few minutes - otherwise they do crumble.  But, once the set they're perfect.  I'll make these again, substituting whatever dried fruit I have onhand just for variety.

name: tortured chicken   beer can
review: DS is scarred for life having to assemble this.  We cooked this on the BBQ with the lid closed.  Fantastic chicken and great cold too!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: Amazingly simple! I used Ener-G egg replacer to make these vegan, and also half spelt flour and half all-purpose. Quick, beautiful buns! Thanks! UPDATE: I just made these with Recipe #104832 for our 4th of July vegan cookout, and they were even more deliciously flavorful!

name: linda s cheesecake stuffed strawberries
review:
I'm giving this 5 stars even though I wasn't all that pleased with the end results.  However, it wasn't the fault of the recipe - the berries just weren't quite sweet enough to my liking.  A week ago they smelled divine.  Figures that when I went to make them, they weren't.  I did add just a touch of cinnamon to the cheese mixture which I thought was lovely.  Will make again, but I'll be sure that the berries are at their best.  Thanks for a lovely dessert.

Adding an addendum.  Found a cheesecake flavored cream cheese in the dairy section of the grocery store.  It's dangerously delicious in these!

name: easy pineapple upside down cake
review: I made this for the 4th of July and got several compliments on it.  Unfortunately I didn't realize you need 12 slices of pineapple to cover the cake and my can only came with 10.  I took the advice of Charmie and used pineapple juice for part of the water.  Overall this was easy to make and tasty. Thanks for posting.

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: I've had this one in my cookbook for ages and decided to make this last night!  I don't know why I waited so long to try it!  This was so easy to make and I only had to purchase  the can of refried beans.  I did up the flavor ante by adding chopped fresh garlic to the ground beef and onion mixture, as well as oregano.  I also threw in a chopped green pepper, and a can of diced green chilis.  This kind of reminds me of one of the burittos you can get here in St. Cloud by a local Mexican restaurant.  I will definately make this one again!

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: We enjoyed this.  I used worcestershire sauce instead of the fish sauce, and I had to use dry basil and ginger (not my first choice) because it was all I had on hand.  Thanks!

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: These were excellent and easy to make. Too much topping, but it's fabulous on toast! Made 9 square Wilton's silicone cupcake thingies - 18 minutes at 400.

name: hello dollies
review: this was very good. taste almost like one of our favorite deserts at chili's restaurant....the paradise pie. next time tho i will put it in an 8x8 pan instead since i'd like the bars to be thicker and i had a hard time cutting them into bars since they were pretty thin. and i may even double the graham cracker and butter since i like a thicker crust. will definitely make again. thanks!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: I made this for dinner tonite and I must say it was excellant....i added emeril's essence, and used season salt in the meat instead of regular salt.. and in place of tomato sauce I used chunky ragu tomato garlic and cheese spaghetti sauce., about 24 ounces...did not use egg and milk . Mixed spaghetti with everything , used plenty of cheese on top. Did as another reviewer did and baked 350 covered with foil 30 min then removed, increased oven temp to 425 and baked 5 min more..thanks kim for sharing ,this will be made many more times.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: This is delicious soup. I made exactly as stated and it turned out perfectly. It is a bit spicy but good. Thanks for sharing!

name: our favourite lemon loaf
review: Yum! Made exactly as written. The whole family loves it. Thank you so much for posting.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: This is an awesome soup to keep stocked in the fridge for an in-between meal snack.  Easy, quick & tasty soup.

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: Sometimes the most simple recipes are the best!! Everyone, young and old, loved this!!

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: I was pleasantly surprised by this recipe. I always grill my corn, but thought I would give this a try. Couldn't be easier, tastes just like it came off the gas grill. Love it, will make again.

name: black bottom banana bars
review:
Wow, absolutely incredible! I added chocolate chips to the plain banana layer, other than that I followed the recipe exactly. These were kind of like a cross between banana cake and banana bread. Delicious! I think next time I may cut back on the sugar by a tablespoon or two, as they are quite sweet - but YUM!!! Thank you Debster!
UPDATE - just ate some that I had frozen for 5.5 months....still moist and delicious!

name: panda express orange chicken
review: my husband really enjoyed this. i loved how crispy the chicken got. followed everything to the T except i omitted the pepper flakes. for my kids tastes i'll see what the sauce taste like w/ out the orange zests or maybe put alot less next time. my kids thought the orange flavor was overwhelming. but my husband loved it and rated it a 10 if there were 10 stars.

name: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
review: This is my daughter-in-law's favorite cake recipe.  I made it last year for her birthday, and she couldn't stop talking about it and kept saying how much she was looking forward to it again this year.  I only used 1oz of red food coloring and it came out beautiful.  I used 2  9" round cake pans, and cut in half to make a 4 layer cake.  I had to make a 2nd half batch on the frosting.  I'm not a big cake fan in genreral, but thought this cake is very good (for a chocolate ckae - my least favorite) and the frosting was out of this world!  Great recipe!

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: I have to say this dish was delish!  I didnt exactly go by the recipe because I didnt have the manicotti pasta. I planned on using penne pasta and just making it more like a baked ziti.  I just stirred the cheese mixture into the penne before layering it in the baking dish.  For the pasta sauce I used Recipe #136292.  It all went very well together and was rich and filling!  One more thing I didnt have was the ricotta so I just replaced it with more cream cheese.  I normally always in all recipes halve the spinach bc I find that I never like the full amount in recipes.  But I think in this, that I would of liked the full amount of spinach.  This also would be great with some sort of meat in it if you didnt care it being vegetarian or not.  Great recipe!  I cant wait to try it in manicotti shells!  Thanks!

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: This pasta sauce was great!  It had such a rich and bold flavor to it along with the chunkiness of the tomatoes.  I served it with Recipe #72308.  I did, at the end, add in a can of tomato sauce to thin it out a bit since it was a thicker sauce.  Thanks for the great recipe!  I will make again!

name: the best banana bread
review: In the words of my BFF "this is the best banana bread I've had in my whole life!" and I would have to agree.  =)

name: almost white castle hamburgers
review: They tasted kind of like little meatloafs!  4 year old DD loves them and that's the important part.  And these are so much cheaper than buying the frozen White Castle burgers at the grocery store.  Next time I am going to get much leaner meat. 80/20 ground beef seemed to lose too much in juices - I was only able to get about 14 patties out of this.

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: So delicous! I should have cooked the green beans a bit longer, but otherwise this was perfect. The seasonings are perfect, and they mesh well with the green beans and the tomatoes. Great recipe, thank you for posting!

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: Great bakery style cookie! I was a bit nervous about the soft batter but they turned out great. I didn't bother to roll them into balls, but dropped them using a rounded tablespoon of batter and they still came out perfectly round. I did end up with just over 3 dozen cookies. Thanks for sharing!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
