review: I think this has just the right amount of lemon to garlic and it is so easy. I used fresh broccoli and left out the red pepper flakes. I loved the ability to use fresh garlic and not get the raw garlic taste.

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: I really thought these were good, and they appealed to a dinner party of five adults and three toddlers with widely varying palates! I took the advice of others and, doubled the recipe but used only one can of pineapple. I really loved the combination of the pineapple juice and enchilada sauce. Thanks for posting! Made for Healthy Choices ABC tag.

name: quick n easy quiche crust
review: Very easy to do and I did it right in the pie pan.  I used it for quiche and it was a little soggy so maybe I should have cooked it for 10 min. like the quiche recipe stated.

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Excellent! I do not taste low-fat, just moist, flavorful and great texture. I will be making these next time the bananas get over-ripe. Thanks for sharing your recipe.

name: spicy shrimp in coconut milk
review: We really enjoyed this recipe for lunch.  Based on reviews I made several modifications with perfect results.  First, I halved the recipe (sort of) to accommodate the two of us.  I left the onion, garlic, ginger, and all spice proportions as written and this worked perfect.  In fact, we could have used even a little more cayenne.  I omitted the water to make for thicker sauce as suggested by other reviewers.  We served over jasmine rice.  We both would have this recipe again.  Thanks!

name: any fruit fast fat free cobbler
review: This is great! It's fast, tasty, and easy to put together. I used 2 cans of "No Sugar Added" sliced peaches, which turned out to be a little more than 2 cups, but that was fine. I read the review that said all types of sugars had worked well, so I used only brown sugar, and it was really sweet! I think I might cut it down to 1/3 cup next time (but that's just a preference thing). I also added 1 tsp. cinnamon to the batter, which was lovely. Thanks for this versatile, keeper recipe!

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: Great recipe.  Loved the nut topping.  Thanks for posting.

name: awesome baked ham
review: This was really a great ham, and I'm one of those who doesn't really care for ham very much!  I used a shank-half ham, and soaked it for a couple of hours to get rid of some of the salt before coating with the mustard-sugar glaze.  Since my ham was only 9 pounds, I made 1/2 the amount of glaze, and baked for 2 hours.  The whole family raved- definitely the way to do ham for the family!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: We loved these!  I added in mini-marshmallows and baked them in 9 little egg shaped foil cups.  They came out prefect in about 18 or 19 minutes.  Thanks for sharing.

name: internal detox for glowing skin
review: A keeper.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Very good!  I halved the recipe and used sweet onions instead of green (didn't have any). Tx for the recipe!

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: Absolutely delicious.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Great recipe! But alas, I don't need to tell you this...looking at all the informative reviews, this recipe will not let you down. I followed this pretty closely, except after cooking my chicken, I used my smaller food processor to  chop up the meat, the onion, and some jalapenos. Not to much! Be careful here, you don't want baby food. I just used this small chop for about 1-2 seconds, opened up, moved the contents around, and whirled about 1-2 more seconds. Warmed tortillas on non-stick with no-stick spray - and they became soft and pliable. Other then that, you're all set for a lovely dinner/lunch/or pot-luck. Go get em, Mildred....and enjoy! Thanks for posting!

name: sweet salsa dump chicken   oamc
review:
what a successful dinner tonight was, all because of this winning recipe! I used chicken breasts pounded out, and found a SFapricot jam. Delicious! Hubby was happy, and even asked if there was enough for his lunch tomorrow!
Thank you Tish, this made a moist, flavorful chicken dinner!

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Not that this recipe needs more accolades, but I'm here to give it some...I couldn't believe the crunch imparted by the boiling....I DO NOT like frying wings, so I always have to talk DH into the ones from the oven. He wants the fried ones, nonetheless, and now I can give him some that have the same crispy taste as 'fried', with none of the hassle. I may follow some other reviewer's next time, by dunking in sauce and returning to the oven, but the were great, as written. Served w/blue cheese dressing, I'm putting these in my Best of 2011 cookbook.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Very good meatballs. I halved the salt and in place of milk I had heavy cream to use up. Worked great. I baked the meatballs for 25 minutes and then cooled and froze them individually on a cookie sheet and then put them into Zip style bags in the freezer. Love the fresh parsley. Next time I think I'll use a little fresh basil, too.

name: copycat lipton s onion soup mix
review: I never buy onion soup mix because there is too much sodium.  This recipe is perfect cause there is no added salt.  I used a low sodium beef bouillon powder.  Thanks Mille :)  Made for I Recommend tag game

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: I've made these so many times and forgot to post my review. Quick and Easy!  I added more tomaotes and a dash of seasoned salt.

name: taco bell quesadillas
review: Even with the low-fat adjustments I made, including low-fat soybean based mayo, low-fat cheeses and a chicken substitute (we are vegetarians), this was very filling.  Nevertheless we each ate a whole one and my BF and I both thought the taste was great.  I only used a pinch of cayenne but thought it could have used a bit more.  I'd make this again.  An easy weeknight supper with a side of veggies or a salad.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Nice!!  This is the second time I've made this and it's a keeper. I cut back on the salt, as others have suggested.

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: I used frozen broccoli, because the fresh at my store was all wilted and limp.  I'm afraid I can't recommend this using frozen broccoli.....can't say anything about using fresh!  I followed the recipe exactly, and this just turned out sort of blah and mushy....sorry so much!  I'll try it with fresh and hopefully redo my review.  Hate to leave a bad review!

name: detweiler sloppy joe mix
review: I used your recipe as a base for my sloppy joes.  These are the changes/additions I made: minced garlic, splash of vinegar, dash of worcestershire, I didnt add the green pepper (personal taste), dash of hot sauce, yellow mustard instead of brown mustard, and salt/pepper.  This was very good and I will definitely be making it again!  Thanks for posting :)

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: So yummy.  Thanks Petunia :)  Made for I recommend tag game

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: Definitely does NOT need the extra vinegar! What a tang it had!  I went on Facebook to ask friends for a remedy before using it on my crockpot ribs recipe I was trying.  The solution was to add dark molasses and some liquid smoke.  I can still taste that sharp tang from the vinegar but at least there's more depth of flavor.  Honestly, I think the liquid smoke MAKES the recipe perfect. If I ever am in a pinch to make BBQ sauce late one night again i'd use this and just not add the vinegar then add the liquid smoke to taste.  Thanks for helping me last minute but don't think I like recipe as written.

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: Really great chocolate cake!! I loved being able to make a "from scratch" chocolate cake with ingredients I already had on hand. My cakes looked beautiful as I took them out of the oven, then each ended up sinking a bit in the middle. I'm not sure why. That is the only reason I'm giving it 4 stars. The frosting was the star. Oh my gosh, it was delicious! Thank you. :)

name: orange julius smoothies
review: At first I hadn't intended to change the recipe, but at the last minute I left out the water & added 1 small seedless orange (the entire orange!), chopped up! That added the pulp I wanted & made the whole thing a bit thicker, as well, which 2 of us thoroughly enjoyed! Thanks for posting your recipe! [Made & reviewed in Healthy Choices ABC recipe tag]

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: This is AWESOME! I used 2 cups of fat free milk (instead of half milk and half cream) and 1 1/2 cups mild cheddar and 1/2 cup Monterey Jack/Colby mix cheese with habanero, chipotle, and jalapeno chilies chopped up in it. These substitutions all worked great. The sauce was perfect - creamy, cheesy, and flavorful, without the needed addition of anything. I used whole wheat rotini (I love rotini mac and cheese, plus it was all I had, besides spaghetti), and topped it with crushed Ritz. The cooking/baking times were all right on. This will be my go-to recipe from now on for baked mac and cheese. Trying different cheeses and noodle types and shapes will be fun. Thanks for posting this!

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: This was a fast easy weeknight recipe..I used chicken tenders and cooked it for one hour...turned out perfect..I too added a can of green chopped chilies...

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: We enjoyed this, although it is more cakelike than a cobbler usually is as a reviewer already noted.  We had it with ice cream.  Just fabulous!

name: big grandma s best peanut butter cookies
review: Wow, this recipe deserves every 5-star review it's gotten!! We used 1/2   butter, 1/2 Crisco like many others did. Also skipped rolling the dough in sugar- didn't miss it! These do have wonderful texture and peanut butter taste!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review:
First off, I am a total beginner at bread making. Completely yeast phobic but with encouragement from other members I decided to give this recipe a go. I will not bore you with my trials and tribulations as they all stemmed from my complete ineptitude. For example - dissolve yeast in water. I had no idea whether ot not to stir it or just leave it. As I said - a complete dolt er...I mean beginner. The way I mishandled just about every step is almost mind boggling.

The end result was soft pillowy mouthfuls of perfection! I topped the rolls with recipe #421678 and could not be happier. What an excellent recipe for both yeastaphobes as well as more experienced bakers. Thank you so much for posting this. I'm on my way to being a breadmaker!

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Perfection!  I made the light version and added in a bit of Irish whiskey and Bailey's for an added indulgence.  It was delightful on Charishma's Recipe #9326.  Thanks for yet another beaut of a recipe....I'm quickly learning that you can't go wrong with a Kittencal recipe!

name: kittencal s technique for perfect easy peel hard boiled eggs
review: Follwed it as stated...turned out great...easy way to get a great boiled egg.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Worked.  Kids and i ate it.  Wouldn't say it is my "go to" chicken recipe or anything but I may add it to my chicken rotation.  Used Panko and I think the crunchier you can make it, the more likely the kiddos will eat it :)

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Easy and delicious. Thanks for a great recipe :)

name: parmesan crusted tilapia
review: I missed the cook covered part, but the fish was delish and perfect anyway!  Great way to cook this light, white fish! Thanks!

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: These are so rich! Lovely flavor, and would be great on a Christmas cookie tray. Made for Cookbook Tag Letter "W".

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: This was so yummy.  We really enjoyed it.  It was so simple to make.  Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: panda express orange chicken
review: I have mixed feelings about this recipe....the instructions are horrible for the first part......I made as posted and the flour/egg mix just clumped up.  Made lumpy bumps that had to be spread over the chicken.  The chicken should be dipped in the egg mixture, then tossed in the cornstarch mix.  It would save a lot of work. I loved the sauce, and agree with other posters that it should be doubled....it is sooo good!  For a beginner cook, I'm afraid this would be so confusing that they would give up, which isn't good.  This recipe is good and deserves a chance, but the instructions are so confusing that many will not make this recipe.  I can't compare this to Panda Express, as I've never had it.  But the sauce is delicious if you  can figure out how to make the first part of the recipe!!  I enjoyed this, but the instructions just aren't clear enough.I would dip in the egg first and then the cornstarch/flour mix.  Really enjoyed the finished product!  Thanks for sharing a delicious recipe.

name: frizzled cabbage
review: Simple and excellent!  Nicely sweet.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: Our daughter has Celiac Disease.  We're having the family here for Easter, so thought I'd try your recipe using Gluten Free Flour.  I did add the baking soda and salt.  I baked, as I always do when baking a pie or cake,  a small cake along with the big cake.  That way I can always sample a recipe before hand.  It turned out wonderful and very moist.  I'm guessing the crushed pineapple helped with that.  Thank you so much for your recipe.

name: sausage gravy
review: This gravy is awesome.  I followed the advice of another reviewer and removed the sausage, made the roux and then added it back when the gravy had thickened a bit.  Added the worcerstershire sauce (about a tablespoon) and found it didn't need added salt or additional spices other than the black pepper.  Easy to make and enjoyed by all.  My husband said it was the best gravy he's ever had.  Made homemade biscuits to go with it and it was over-the-top good!

name: kittencal s best deviled eggs
review: Wow... just wow!  These are so much better than the ones I've been making with sweet pickle relish.  So glad I was out of relish and went looking for a different recipe!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I liked these potatoes but I thought there was way too much oil in them.  My potatoes may not have been big enough so it might have been my fault.  I wasn't sure how the oregano would go with our dinner so I used Essence of Emeril on them.  They did taste great and I plan on trying them again.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: Guess I don't like tartar sauce on my salmon. Seems like it made healthy food unhealthy. The people in my family that don't like fish liked it. 4 4oz filets frozen solid 25 minutes.

name: simple caribbean jerk chicken
review:
This was EXCELLENT, easy, and WW pp-friendly! Winning combo! 11 YO DD said it was just a little too sweet for her taste, so I might decrease the brown sugar to 1 1/2 T next time. DH and I thought it was perfect as is!

As written, it's 4 ppv/serving for 1 1/2 lb chicken. If you use 2 lb chicken for 6 servings, it's 5 ppv. Still not bad for ALL THIS flavor!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: This was definitely easy to make, and I paired it with a coconut cream pie.  I miss the butter flavor though...

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review:
This is the almost perfect frosting recipe.The only thing I would change for the next time I make this would be to use unsalted butter.I found that I could taste the salt from the butter too much.But other than that it was easy to put togther and makes quite a bit.
Update April 2011:I didn't even realize I had already made this frosting...and this time I have no complaints...strange.Anyway,I used this recipe on Easter cupcakes I made.Check out my photo.

name: very moist banana nut bread
review: Excellent recipe!  Moist and flavorful and not too sweet.  I also made it in a Bundt pan.  I made it with buttermilk and followed the recipe exactly.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: My apologies if this review shows up twice. I wasn't signed-in the first time and I don't know if it accepted it (even though it said it did). We thought these were pretty average and they require significant extra work (cooking the garlic), so I would just stick with normal mashed potatoes unless you have lots of time on your hands to make these.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: My kids aren't done eating this and I must rate it.  I have the most picky 5 and 9 year old children in existence.  My 5 year old had a second helping and my 9 year old is finishing his.  They both like it.  It was super easy.  I made with homemade chicken stock as I had some I needed to use up.  I also added some carrots  as I had some already diced.  It is very good.  I think it will replace my usual potato soup.

name: mom s chocolate cupcakes
review: The perfect chocolate cupcake!  We frosted with a peanut butter frosting and froze to use in lunches.  They will be made permanently - no need for a box!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: The sauce was a 5-star for sure! I was worried it would be too vinegary after reading some of the reviews and smelling the sauce, but it turns out perfectly. (I even added slightly less than the whole batch of sauce, but would add all of it next time). I think the meatloaf itself is kind of boring, but it's easy and uses things I always have on hand. I think it needs garlic and some spices and then it will be perfect. Thanks!

name: easiest tastiest barbecue country style ribs  slow cooker
review: Can't leave stars. I think it was WONDERFULLY simple to do. Unfortunately my *^$&%#$%#@ crockpot tend s to overcook (dry out) meat. It had plenty of liquid and I stopped it about 1.5hrs earlier then recommended. Had it on the low setting... Still didn't cook it right. I think I give up on using the *#%#$ crockpot to cook meat. Perhaps this would work just as well in a covered pan in the regular oven on a low setting for a few hours...

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Absolutely great. Would not change anything. Even great reheated.

name: amazing white trash puff balls
review: Everyone just loved these, and so easy to make!  I cut each triangle into 4 pieces for slightly smaller bites, and used crumbled bacon instead of pepperoni.  Since I went with bacon, I added some cheddar cheese and dried fried shallots and chives.

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: Yum. I halved the recipe, served with some ketchup, devoured them.Thanks! Made for the Healthy Choices game.

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: Awesome cauliflower cheese recipe.  No lumps   yay!  I served as a side to corned beef.  Thank you for such a simple any yummy recipe

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: I really liked this!!! Next time I'll add extra cheese on top!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Picky husband enjoyed this. He even asked to put it in rotation. So I'm rating this 5 stars on his behalf. I used fresh cheese & found salt to be perfect, I could just imagine the canned prepared ones making this super salty so I'd stick w/ fresh. But even w/ the saltiness of fresh I would probably season & marinate chicken next time since I felt flavor didn't penetrate chicken. Flavor was only where I had bites of the cheese mixture topping.

name: strawberry strawberry pie from the really good food cook book
review: I know I'm in the minority here, but we didn't care for this.  The crust was soggy and the filling bland.  It's always fun to try new recipes with they turn out to be a hit or miss.  :-)

name: bakery style chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: Use butter, not margarine.  Also recommend refrigerating dough before putting it on the sheet and baking.

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: You can do so much with this recipe. I have added asparagus, minced garlic, reduced butter, omitted soy sauce/sesame oil while doubled the seasoning. I almost always double the eggs. They all came out delicious!

name: kittencal s best deviled eggs
review: Another winner Kitten!! Had them for Easter and everyone loved them.

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: Sounds like a cake I made called Triple Chocolate Cake, it's a killer of a chocolate cake. You can't get anymore chocolate packed into one little cake...........

name: split pea soup  crock pot    dairy free
review: This is a keeper. So nice to throw this in the crockpost before work and come to the house smelling like dinner is ready. I only used a teaspoon of season salt. I will use 2cups more water and stir everything together next time. I served the soup with cornbread and honey. So good! Thanks for posting.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: Just made this delicious dish.  I was so sick of Easter food I craved a casserole.  I followed the recipe exactly (which is unusual for me) and it turned out wonderful.  Rich and creamy not dry at all.  I did use 2 cans of canned chicken whitemeat as I didn't feel like running to the grocery store.  This will be made often, it is so easy to put together and a real family pleaser.  Thanks for posting!

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: Very good.  I used beef, chopped garlic instead of powder, and flour tortillas(had them on hand)which I really enjoyed.  The combination of flavors in the filling was excellent, and these were very easy to put together.  I made them the day before I wanted to serve them, and the 30 minute cooking time was right on target to heat them through.

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: Simple and tastes great!  I had mine over a salad, and my husband had his in a pita and we both really enjoyed it.

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: Perfect! Love this type of salad! YUM! Followed this exactly, added some salt and pepper, though. Even better the next day. Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: As usual, a great recipe from Kitten!  And while another review really isn't needed, I can't help it.  We have been very rushed lately, so this chicken was the star in my attempt to get us a good weekday meal for once this month!  If only the rest of my toss together dinner had been as wonderful--to quote DH "The mashed potatoes needed more milk, the broccoli was overdone, but the chicken!!!!"  A keeper and our thanks!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: This was so quick and easy.  Will use this a lot.  Thanks for posting.

name: homemade rice a roni
review: You know those people that review a recipe and then made so many changes it didn't resemble the original all that much. Well....that was me. This is more a method that is open to a huge number of possibilities that would all be amazing and reading other reviews I see I am not alone. My interpretation used orzo pasta and the last of my basmati and the last of my wild rice. I also added onions, garlic, mushrooms, toasted almonds and some fresh herbs. Rice-A-What? As somebody trying to watch our sodium intake this is PERFECT. Much better than the box because I know what is in there. A perfect vehicle for using upu the last little bits of rice that always seem to end up in my cupboard. It took more broth to get it cooked but that could be my fire was a little high. Excellent recipe I will use again and again.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: A very good base recipe.  I added blackened chicken to it and it made the dish!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Very good recipe. However, my kiddos just didn't find it cheesy enough to their little tastes, (used to Velveeta mac & chz versus cheddar flavor) so I ended up cutting back on the cheddar & cubing Velveeta & stirring it in .Voila - perfection! :)

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Perfectly delicious and perfectly simple. Since it's baked I tucked the thin tapering end of the breast under the thicker part so that it all cooked evenly and made as directed. How can you not love something this good that is also healthy!

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: This was totally awesome!  DH and The Family Circus loved it!!  Substituted Spenda Brown Sugar Blend.  I've tried Butternut Squash other ways but this is definately our favorite!  Thank you very much for this...it's a keeper!

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: I made the dough, filled, rolled and cut these and let them sit in a pan covered with plastic wrap overnight and baked in the morning.  Easier than it looks and they came out beautifully!  Next time I will definitely add pecans!  Thanks for posting!

name: amy sedaris s vanilla cupcakes
review: The frosting didn't turn out all and the cake was just average.  Save the trouble and buy a box cake mix and some store bought frosting.

name: joe s crab shack crab dip
review: Wow!  I really love this dip!  I used double the amount of minced onions and peppers.  I also used red peppers for taste preference.  Homemade tortilla chips rounded off the dip.  Thanks for posting!

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: Excellent and easy!  I used my own taco seasoning mix to cut down on the salt.

name: bev s macaroni and cheese
review: I made this for a dinner I catered and it was enjoyed by both of the ladies I cooked for. I followed this recipe exactly except that I did also add about 1/4 cup of Velveeta cheese. I've been asked to make this again and I definitely will.  Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: Delish! Thank you.

name: jello cake
review: Let me add my compliments to this recipe.  I made this using strawberry jello and frosting it with recipe #74805.  Served it with a bowl of strawberries and more whipped cream.  We enjoyed this ever so much.  Thanks Karen!

name: wonderful salsa
review: This was fantastic. I didn't use the jalepano peppers, because I live with a bunch of Gerber Mouths. I did add a little of Ancho Chilli powder to the jars. I know I did not make enough. Will definitely make more next year.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: We loved it!  I made just a few small changes.  I used pork tenderloin cut up into bite sized cubes.  I dredged them in seasoned corn flower before frying them in olive oil.  I used a 1/2 tsp. of granulated garlic (instead of the garlic salt) and added 1 1/2 tsp. of vinegar to the sauce.  Like many others, I used low sodium soy sauce which I thought was perfect.  When the pork was browned, I poured the sauce over top, mixed it around a little and baked them in the oven for 30 minutes.  They came out with a nice thickened sauce that was really delicious!  My little girl says she wants to eat this every day for the rest of her life.  She really, really liked it.  Thanks for sharing this one.  It's a winner all the way!

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review:
My turned out real salty. I even cut the salt in half. Other wise it had great flavor. A little more smoeyness would have been good.
I used a chuck roast and cooked on low for 10 hours. Melt in your mouth tender. Next time I will cut the salt to 1/2 TBS.

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: Wow, Kittencal, this will be one on my favorites from now on! I used T-Bones, and threw in some mushrooms with the marinade. I put the mushrooms on greased foil, and grilled alongside the steaks. Served with grilled asparagus and the meal was perfect! Delicious flavor, thanks!

name: best oatmeal cookies
review: These rock! Yum!

name: the best chili you will ever taste
review: Very good chili. Even subbing veggie crumbles and tvp chunks for the meat, it's still works. Cheers!

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: Very good recipe.  I was easy on the spices and used mild enchillada sauce - let every else spice it up more at the table.  Put black olives in the meat mixture and a few on top.  Also topped with some chopped green onions and used flour tortillas.  Will make again!

name: awesome baked ham
review: This truly makes an Awesome Baked Ham! Thanks so much for the super easy, budget friendly recipe!!! Will make again and again.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: My crockpot tends to cook on the hot side, so I checked the chicken after 3 hours and it was done.  I, like many others, also used Sweet Baby Ray's BBQ sauce and borrowed JOY1998's idea of adding a little liquid smoke.  Served on toasted hamburger buns along with baked oven fries, baked beans, and a salad.

name: lentil soup for people who thought they hated lentils    meat op
review: This is a really great soup.  My husband was complaining when I said that I wanted to make lentil soup because he thinks it is boring.  However, he loved it so much he had some for breakfast the next day.  It does make a lot but it does taste better the next day so the leftovers are a joy.  It is great with and without the ham and would be an nice thing to serve if you have both veggie and meat-eater guests.  I made rosemary bread to go with it.  It will be made again for sure.

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: Very good! I love that they have great flavor from the marinade and they are not heavily breaded. I omitted the butter drizzle and used a bit of olive oil.  An EZ & Tasty dinner, thanks Marie!

name: parmesan zucchini
review: I have made this a couple times because it is so easy and good.  Thanks for posting!

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: I had some challenges with this recipe.  I'm unsure if the lentils are supposed to be fully mashed and smooth, or are the lentils supposed to be left slightly lumpy for texture?  And, my lentils, which I thought were soft, actually felt too firm in the loaf after the entire cooking process.  Head's up:  I think the lentils are to be very cooked and totally soft.  Also, my loaf was really dry.  Does anyone know what I can do to make the loaf more moist?  I did enjoy the flavor, but wished it had more kick.  I'd make this again, with some adjustments or suggestions.  Thank you for posting.

name: shrimp  cocktail sauce
review: Needs a lot more horseradish for my taste.

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: WOW. This is going straight into my best of the best file. I loved the dressing!!! It was perfect with the romaine and croutons. I did use anchovy paste instead of anchovy filets. I ended up using about 1 t. of the paste. I didn't think the dressing needed any more salt. It was perfect. Thank you!

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: I didn't cut the cauliflower small, because we like cauliflower but it was really good. I could have eaten the whole dish. Yum.

name: romano s macaroni grill rosemary bread
review: We have a rosemary plant growing faster than we know what to do with it so I decided to make this bread to accompany a soup.  The bread is wonderful and aromatic.  I only used 1 tablespoon of butter and thought it was tasty as is.  It was a lot easier than I expected.  It is a great way to use up some of our rosemary and will be made again.

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: So, so good! I sauteed, carrots, onion, celery and garlic and added frozen peas and corn.I left out the potatoes and used half the amount of butter called for. I also added a teaspoon of thyme and chili powder and 1/2 a teaspoon of sage. Can't wait to make this again. Thanks so much for the recipe.

name: easy creamy sour cream chicken casserole
review: Yum, this is a down-home, kick-up your heels, and enjoy the evening kinda dish. There is nothing that I changed about this, except adding a couple of baby peas into the sour-cream/mushroom soup part. I highly recommend this for it's ease, you probably have all these items on hand, and the taste is well worth the minimal amount of time that it takes to prepare. Make it even easier using parts from a rotisserie chicken. Thanks for posting, KC!

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: I thought these were very good. I used dry buttermilk, and decreased the liquid (water) I used by 1/4 cup, both because I wanted thicker pancakes, and also because the egg I used was extra-large. They came out very nice, light and fluffy as advertised. I will increase the salt and decrease the sugar just a little next time I make them. Thank you for posting this recipe.

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review:
Easy, fast, not expensive and a good doctored up recipe for things bought in packages. Nice consistency. I used only half the chocolate chips and it was perfect.

Good one!

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: I was very easy to bring together, but the flavor is not what we expected.  I don't want to put a star rating, as I don't want to mar an otherwise popular recipe, just because it is not our tastes (darn yankees!)

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: I was looking for something different to do with broccoli, found this, made it and we loved it.  My husband is only a recent convert to broccoli and HE loved it so it's a winner in my book.  I made it as written but in the future will try some of the suggestions from other reviewers, such as garlic, red pepper, etc.  I love quick, simple, delicious and healthy recipes like this one!  Thanks for posting this Roxy :)

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: So good, said to my kids if u don't want your broccoli, give it to me, they said get you own there is no way we r sharing .

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: I made the beef version. While we did love how easy this was, we were not so excited about the beef seasoning.  Maybe we'll try again, changing the seasoning to more our tastes.  Thanks for posting!

name: crock pot ham and beans
review: Loved loved loved how it wasn't too salty!  I used more beans than called for, but also used more ham, so it all worked out.  Even my non-bean eating son tolerated this, while usually he makes a gaggy face.  I'll be making this again!

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: Yum! I made this cake over the weekend but I didn't make the frosting. I covered it with ganache--it was delicious! As some other commenters have said, it is not super sweet or rich, but it makes the perfect backdrop for a rich frosting or ganache. I like that this doesn't require baking chocolate squares since I never seem to have them on hand. It would be good with espresso or cinnamon to spice it up a bit, but for a simple chocolate cake, this is a great choice! I baked in a 9x13 glass pan and it was done in 30 minutes.***Edit to add: the cupcake pictures I posted have Recipe #454493 on them and that was fantastic as well as the ganache I usually use. This cake really is delicious and easy!

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: Sorry but I was disappointed in this.  Scaled it down for 1 chop and mixed up 1/2 the amount of crumbs and still had excess crumbs, which I find very wasteful.  After cooking as directed, my thick, boneless chop was rather dry so if I would make this again I would reduce the heat to 375 and bake for 10 minutes on each side.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: What a great and easy way to make broccoli!  Really liked the sliced stems in this too.  I thought just the salt and pepper was just right for this.  Great tasting broccoli ready in 6 minutes - can't beat that - thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: This was tasty! The sauce was a bit thin for me though; so I'd probably add some cornstarch/water into it next time. Nice change of pace from the usual red sauces. Thanks! :)

name: chinese pot stickers
review: These were fun to prep and my family really enjoyed them. I had these in soup as well but I think I preferred them lightly fried with the dipping sauce. Took no time at all to cook and we gobbled them all up. Thanks!

name: easy pizza pasta casserole  oamc
review: This was pretty good, and it is very versatile. It's a great way to use up leftover half jars of spaghetti sauce in your fridge! I didn't have any thawed sausage, so I used a 6 oz. can of mushrooms and a 4 oz. can of sliced black olives in place of it. I didn't saute the onion pieces, I just cut them small, as they are not sauteed on a regular pizza. I used turkey pepperoni, cut some into 4ths to stir into the casserole, and left some for the top of the casserole. I used mini wagon wheel pasta, and just kind of eyeballed the sauce (I used tomato-basil Classico) and seasoning. The baking time and temperature were right on. I only made 1/4 of the recipe, since I was just making it for a dinner for my husband and me, but it would be a great thing to have and freeze. I would probably make it this way (with more veggies) again, since we usually order supreme-type pizzas. Thanks!

name: one minute flax muffin   low carb
review: Mmmm! this was yummy, I used splenda as the sweetener and put a few frozen raspberries in the middle and when I cut into it the rasps were soft and mushy it was really nice, a really quick fix when you need something sweet some yogurt over the top would be perfection. Made for honor thy mother May 2011.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Great - Now I would make again I just have to find my ginger How in the world it could hide from me I don't know

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: This is a very flavorful, delicious chicken dish. I grated my own parmesan and used homemade breadcrumbs to which I added homemade Italian seasoning. The recipe was followed as written and turned out perfectly. Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: This was a very good marinara sauce.  I don't like big chunks of tomatoes in my food, so I used petite diced tomatoes.  I used red wine, but didn't like the odd, dark red color it gave it.  I did like the flavor.  Might try half red wine, half white wine next time.  I will also add some water, as suggested in the recipe.  I simmered mine quite a while and it was a little dryer than I like.  Thanks for sharing!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Excellent lasagna.  Doubled the recipe and froze one to enjoy later.  Thanks!

name: hard boiled eggs
review: I followed the recipe as written other then I only used nine eggs. They were perfect.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: This was so good!! Thanks for sharing Kittencal!

name: buttery yeast rolls
review: Really good! Dough was easy to work with, rolls were light and buttery. Look forward to trying the crescent roll variation. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: Yummy and super easy for a busy weeknight. Instead of canned soup, I used Recipe #360192. Baked for 1 hour. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: Delicious! Doubled the lemon glaze and was glad I did. Made a lovely dinner. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: This is a VERY good chicken marinade.  I used it on bone in breasts and cooked for about an hour.  Simple to make and the whole family loved the flavor and the breasts were nice and juicy.  I liked how the skin roasted to a nice golden color....and the slightly sweet taste from the brown sugar was so good with all the other ingredients.  Cold leftovers were great also!  Thank you for posting this great, easy recipe!

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: Yep! It's that good. I went with the crushed pineapple, pecans and no "extra" topping. It isn't overly sweet and soooooo moist. I had DH flip the cake onto the serving tray and waited anxiously as he removed the pan. There wasn't even in topping stuck in the pan, it all stayed beautifully on the cake. Thank you. This is definitely a keeper.

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: I did cut this recipe in half for 2 of us & also used Hormel's Real Bacon Pieces instead of frying up bacon myself! Other than that, though, the recipe was followed right on down & the salad was wonderfully satisfying! Thanks for sharing it! [Made & reviewed in I Recommend recipe tag]

name: best banana bread
review: This is fantastic!  I used applesauce instead of butter, whole wheat flour instead of white, cut the sugar in half, and doubled the recipe.  I made muffins instead of a loaf (couldn't find my loaf pan!) and they still turned out great.  I cooked the muffins for about 25 minutes, and sprayed the papers with Pam (otherwise, the crust sticks to the paper).  Even with all those changes, they came out dense but moist, with a wonderful not-too-sweet banana flavor.  Great recipe!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: We love this!! So easy and quick. It's my husband's favorite and I love being able to make it fresh for him. I usually double the sauce and use a lower sodium soy sauce. (Of course, then I've been known to add a little extra garlic salt so not sure how much good that does for us, lol.). This is definitely going to be a regular in our house.

name: kittencal s greek moussaka
review: Another great Greek recipe from Kittencal!  I impressed the in-laws with this dish.  It was delicious as written, but I think I will try adding the tsp of cinnamon next time.

name: southwestern stuffed bell peppers
review: This was good even though I used pre-cooked beef instead of raw.  I bet it would be even better if the meat cooked in the pepper and I'll try that next time.  The only problem I had was that the peppers didn't get soft enough.  Next time I'll cook the peppers a bit before adding the filling.  Thanks for sharing this recipe!

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: These were great mash potatoes.  The green onion really gave a special touch.  Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: The kids loved this "breakfast cake."  I put some whipped cream on top for them.  This took me significantly longer than 5 minutes (which I blame on myself, not Kittencal).  I used almond extract because I love the smell of almond extract, but I think I'd like the taste better with vanilla.  I will do this again.  It'll go over well with house guests.

name: cheddar bar b q chicken breasts
review: This was just okay. It was easy to make, but just didn't do a lot for us.

name: kittencal s onion patties latkes
review: anything fried is good.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: I really like the flavor of these biscuits.  UPDATE:  I made these again today and this time I brushed some butter on the biscuits before baking them  They came out so tender, soft, flakey and the flavor is awesome.

name: southern fried chicken
review: DH loves fried chicken! I break down once a year and make it for him. This was the selected recipe for this year. He just raved about it. Very easy to prepare and it was tasty. Made as posted with the exception of cutting the recipe in half. And using shortening because I didn't have peanut oil. Cooked in my electric fry pan. Thanks for posting. :)

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: Haven't had it at the Olive Garden, but this is yummy good. :)

name: crispy baked chicken leg quarters  very easy  one dish
review: This was excellent. Easy to make. will be making again Thanks

name: berry smash muffins  strawberry muffins
review: VERY good!  I had to sub baking powder in place of the baking soda but followed the rest, as stated, with all strawberries.  I cooked for 15 minutes, but would probably cook a bit less next time.  Super quick and easy.  Will definitely make again.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: This was a terrific stew!! The flavors went so well together, we loved it. I had served it over some garlic mashed potatoes....Yummy!!!!  I did do a few changes though. I had dredged the chuck roast pieces in a mixture of flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper and garlic powder. Then browned it in batches and took it out and then caramelized the onions and then put back in the beef and the rest of the ingredients, simmered on stove for about 45 minutes. Then I added in the other ingredients with some peas and popped it in the oven for about 1 hour at 350. There was no need for cornstarch because the beef was coated in flour first, so it was a perfect thickness already. Thanks so much for sharing a wonderful recipe evelyn!!

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: Very good. No need to add sugar.

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review:
I loved the cooking method. I have never made a brisket n the crock pot without adding liquid. I cut the salt down to 2 TEASPOONS and it was still too salty. If I make this again I think I'll leave the salt off all together and I'll update my review and let you know it that helps.
OK, there was a great deal on corned beef brisket so I tried this again. I trimmed the fat off and rinsed the brisket well. I followed the recipe except I didn't measure the garlic and probably had more than called for but we are garlic lovers. I also left the salt off completely this time. It turned out perfectly! Fall apart moist and oh so good. Changing my rating to five stars when you leave off the salt.

name: best banana bread
review: Oh my goodness, this may be the best banana bread I've ever made or eaten!  I did use 1/4 cup applesauce in place of half the butter and I used half white and half brown sugar and added 1/2 tsp cinnamon.  I baked it in two aluminum bread pans for 50 min.  I let them rest for 10 min. after removing them from the oven, then got them out of the pans and cooled on a rack.  I then ate half a loaf and am thinking about going back for more.  It is SO Good!!!!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: This is probably the best crock pot recipe I've ever tried using a whole chicken. It worked perfectly. The flavor is wonderful. I loved the hint of spice. The chicken is very moist. Straight into my best of the best file it goes. Thank you!

name: the perfect burger
review:
The meat tasted great, but I probably won't make this again. I followed the directions to the T and it went downhill from there. The patties shaped well, I kept them in the fridge until ready to grill, but as soon as they hit the grate, they started to fall apart. Turning them over was not an option because most of the meat ended up on the bottom of the grill. I had made one extra burger (3 of us) and had it partially frozen. So I put it on the grill and made sure to wait until it was almost done to turn it. It turned out better, but I now have a mess to clean up on my grill.
Like I said, the flavor was good.......just wish we could have eaten patties instead of scrambled hamburger.

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: Yum! I made 1/2 batch but should have made a full batch because my grandson and his friend finished these off in nothing flat. I added a little bit of cream to the chocolate and they turned out well. Thanks Karen for sharing this simple and great recipe. Made for I Recommend Tag.

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: This was a very tasty recipe. We loved the French Onion Soup in it.  Thanks for posting.

name: shredded chicken for enchiladas  tostadas  tacos
review: YOWZA!  This is amazing stuff.  So much flavor and so easy!  I did the first part (until the shredding) in the crockpot.  The whole house smelled amazing...the chicken was very tender and juicy and easy to shred; the next steps were quick and easy.   The chicken tastes better than the shredded chicken at our favorite local Mexican restaurant so this was a real find.  Thanks for sharing this fabulous recipe...love, love, love this one!

name: pork chops in onion sauce  schweinekotelett in zwiebelsosse
review: This was an easy to follow recipe with tasty results.  Thanks for a great pork chop!

name: cinnamon swirl quick bread
review: This is outrageously good!! It was worth burning my tongue on the first bite--the aroma while baking was so tantalizing and I couldn't wait til it cooled. Only by my personal preferences, I'll add just a pinch more salt with the next loaf. So moist, so tender and yet, not overly sweet. Perfect!! Thanks for sharing this treasure of a recipe.

name: copycat ihop harvest grain   nut pancakes
review: Can't thank u enough for this wonderful recipe! I made this b/c of the hearty ingredients & for a change--the nuts addition is just great! I cut the recipe by 1/3 for 2 good sized pnk but used about 5 tbsp skim milk; we didn't have buttermilk. The pnk weren't too thick or too thin, IMO. I didn't use any oil & only had chopped walnuts but almonds sound great. I added a little cinnamon & after pouring the batter--I sprinkled some mini choc chips on top for the great combo of flavors. They really worked! I topped mine w/ sliced banana & hubby had his w/ strawberry syrup. Really enjoyable recipe. Oh, and I also didn't use a blender; worked fine!

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: I made half the recipe.  I used 2 garlic cloves.  I omitted the cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.  But used the spices mentionned.  The spices were perfect with the shrimps.  And we used bread to dip in the liquid.  It was like having garlic butter bread.  Thanks Eds :)  Made for Holiday tag game

name: english muffins  bread machine method
review: This doesn't need another review.....BUT.....really youve got to make these!  They are easier to make than bagels (which I just did) and just as enjoyable.  PERFECTION!! Will freeze and enjoy for many days.  I made 15 out of this batch and size is perfect.  Thanks.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: This was actually pretty good, but next time I'll use tortilla chips instead of corn chips...but that's because hubby has a hard time digesting corn chips.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Of course, I changed the recipe but it was delicious and I have no doubt the original would be delicious.  For cheese I used feta, I replaced the margarine with olive oil.

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: Delish!  Thanks for sharing, I'll make this again.  :-)

name: zesty low fat chicken breasts
review: Our family LOVED this dish! Our picky 6 year-old even ate her entire chicken breast and that rarely happens. There's a fine line between zesty and spicy and this toed it perfectly. I did add a teaspoon of chopped garlic in water and I used spicy brown mustard instead of Dijon mustard since that's what I had on hand and it turned out great. It was also quick to assemble which is a God send for me. I also agree with dale!, I did not have to do anything to the sauce. It stayed on top of the chicken breasts and kind of caramelized while it was cooking. It was so good! Thanks so much for posting!

name: easy garlic chicken
review: This one is not for the faint at heart but I love this dish! I followed Dana U.'s suggestion and made a little bit extra 'sauce' and then served it over rice. the neighbor actually said that she could smell this cooking in her apartment and that it smelled fantastic. Thanks for a great recipe that we will be having again!

name: soft italian breadsticks  abm
review: I made this recipe on 3/10/11 to go with the Italian Meatball Soup that was being made for dinner.Except for cutting in half this recipe was made as written.Both my SO and I thought the breadsticks were pretty good. Thanks for posting and, " Keep Smiling :) "

name: kielbasa with tomatoes and white beans
review: This was awesome! My family gobbled it right up. To be honest, I thought it was just a throw-away meal, one you just pull out of your butt at the last minute ("Eh, I've got this kielbasa, but what do I do with it?"), but it was delicious. I served it over noodles and will definitely be doing so again. Thanks, Lorac!

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: Good sauce that doesn't need much marinating time.

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: I made these as stated except I used only 2pds of wings. I did turn them three times during baking, and they were delicious! I also have plenty of sauce left over to make these again, or maybe with pork ribs. Thanks for posting!

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: Great flavour! I baked the ribs at 300 for about 2 and a half hours. Thanks for a tasty recipe!

name: homemade hamburger buns  bread machine
review: Delicious, light and fluffy buns.  I do take issue with the instructions to roll the dough to 1" thickness, though.  I did this (yes I actually got out my ruler) and could only find a 3" glass to cut them out with so I thought I would get more than a dozen buns.  I only got 101/2 buns...very tall buns.  Some were 3" tall.  Next time I make these (and there will be many next times) I'll do my best to find a 31/2" cutter and I'll roll the dough to less than an inch.  All in all, a wonderful recipe, though.  Thanks Marie!

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: GREAT stuff! A great way to use up leftover tortilla chips. I lightened it up by using low-fat cheese and fat-free refried beans, but it was still super yummy. We have tacos about once a week and this was a nice change of pace! Thanks for sharing!

name: uncle bill s vegetarian minestrone soup
review: Excellent soup, Uncle Bill!  I didn't use the zucchini this time (but will next time), used regular canned, diced tomatoes, 1 can of great northern beans and added 3 chicken bouillon cubes.  I did have to cook it quite a bit longer than the time stated because my celery was still crunchy.  But I sure enjoyed this soup on a cool, rainy, dreary day.  Thanks!

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: I used chicken... and about 1/3 more cumin and cayenne pepper.  I had an emergency and ended up letting these marinate 24 hours because I couldn't make them the day I prepared them.  Because it worked out to well, I'll stick with a long marinating time!  I also salted the onions and peppers.  The final result was a fabulous fajita dinner.  I made this guacamole recipe which was also fabulous (added fresh minced garlic and subbed cayenne pepper for fresh jalapeno): http://www.food.com/recipe/guacamole-345790.  I will definitely make these again.  This was my first time trying fajitas.  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Perfect dressing. :)

name: cinnamon swirl quick bread
review: I have made this twice now and it has received rave reviews from everyone. I had a little trouble the first time portioning out the batter in thirds. The second time around I just made two layers and put the remaining cinnamon/sugar mix on the top of the loaf. It baked up crispy on the top and was excellent. I will continue to make this bread often.

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: This is the only London Broil that I have really liked.  The marinade is just excellent.  I marinated for 24 hours.  I would suggest cooking 5 to 5 1/2 minutes per side.  I did 6 minutes per side and that made it medium, I prefer medium rare.  I sliced up the left over super thin and used for steak sandwiches.

name: healthy no bake cookies
review: Made as written and was extremely disappointed. You can really taste the bitterness of the cocoa powder and I probably would have liked the original that only had a teaspoon of it. Will not bother trying again.

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: A tasty, exotic dish. I did not add the cayenne pepper and would do so next time, since this sweet dish would've been even better with a little heat. I was concerned about the large dried apricots, but they actually come apart after cooking if you smash them with your fork and are a delicious addition. I served this dish one night over rice, and the next night over pasta. It's better over rice. Thank you for posting.

name: self rising flour
review: So much cheaper than buying sefl-rising flour. I'll never buy it again. Thanks so much for posting!

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: I sure loved this recipe! It was different yet delicious b/c the oats were the predominant ingredient. I read thru ALL the reviews (whew!) to get as much help as I could. I cut the recipe into 6 for 2 pnk for me: 1/3 cup oats & skim milk (I let it sit for a few min) & added 2 tbsp whole wheat flour, 1/8 tsp cinn & 1/4 tsp baking powder. I used 1 egg white & added 1 tbsp chopped pecans & a few mini choc chips (very yum!). I do recommend preheating your griddle well since the batter is thin & the oats do tend to clump up in the middle--so mix the batter well. After I poured the batter, I used a spoon to "spread" the oats out so they'd be evenly distributed. I topped the 2 pnk w/ banana slices & sugar free syrup. They were just wonderful & I loved the texture (like I said, it was different, heartier & filling). thank u for sharing!!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Very good and incredibly moist. I did cut back on sugar in the mix (to just over 1/2 cup) and it was just right. I also added some vanilla and cinammon. Excellent reviews from my family and students alike.

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: Yummy! I made a double batch. Wish I would have made more to store in the freezer. I added wine and more garlic.This was so easy and so much better than store bought sauce. Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s juicy hamburger burger
review: These are so good and so easy.  My daughter had some friends over tonight and they wanted burgers so I found these and was confident they would be good since I like so many of Kittencal's recipes.  I was not disappointed.  The texture was just right and they were nice and juicy.  This will be my go to burger recipe from now on.

name: refreshing mojito  by the pitcher mojitos
review: Muy bien!  This was such a refreshing mojito, and we really enjoyed them.  Mojitos can be quite a labor-intensive drink to make one by one, so making a full pitcher was such a wonderful idea and time-saver.  It made it possible to actually sit and have a pleasant conversation while everyone enjoyed their lovely cocktails.  Thank you for sharing your recipe, Rita.  Made for ZWT #7.

name: crispy baked chicken leg quarters  very easy  one dish
review: The sauce was very good. Kids even liked it.

name: cheddar bar b q chicken breasts
review: YUM! This is great stuff. Left out the green onions & used low-fat cheese, but otherwise followed exactly. Thanks for sharing -- it's a keeper!

name: so it s bekah s pulled pork now
review: Very good Pulled Pork.  We enjoyed this with fresh baked beans, coleslaw and pecan bars.

name: appetizer grape jelly and chili sauce meatballs or  lil smokies
review: I used this sauce to make "worms" for Halloween... slice regular hot dogs length-wise into 4 slices and make tiny cuts sideways along each piece. When you boil them, they will curl up and look like worms!

name: banana banana bread
review: Very good, very easy and almost identical to my grandmother's recipe.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Not much I can add to 115 other reviews, but this is very good!  I will cut the breast into cutlets next time, though, as they were a bit thick.  I served plain as written, but will try them with some tomato sauce next time.  Very quick and easy, btw.

name: ground beef gyros
review: WE LUV Gyro's, so I made these for supper tonite & they were pretty tasty!. I thought the sauce was a bit weak tasting from what I'm used to at the local Greek restaurant, so I doubled the cucumber, added a tsp. of kosher salt & a few herbs...PERFECT!!! The wife isn't crazy about anything "turkey" & I couldn't find any ground lamb, so I used ground beef. I've never had lettuce on a Gyro, so I omitted that.  Other than that, 4 STARS & will DEFFO make again, but with ground lamb....I hope. THANKS for sharing!!!

name: crock pot chops that will make you eat til you pop
review:
My wife and I enjoyed this very much. I did use only 1 tbl of brown sugar after reading some of the reviews. Also, at the end I added a can of chicken broth and 2 cups of instant rice. Fantastic meal. Thanks for the keeper.

Mike

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: This is a very hearty soup and there is a ton of it for leftovers.  I am only giving it three stars, because it seemed to need a bit more seasoning for my tastes. Thank you for sharing.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Delicious, and couldn't be easier! Thank you!

name: slow cook down home pork chops and gravy
review: DH and I both enjoyed this.  I don't use my crockpot much for meats because I don't usually care for the texture but I enjoyed this one.  I used thick cut, bone-in chops and while super tender, they still had a good "chew" to them.  I didn't have the correct broth so I subbed a bouillion cube in with the water.  The gravy was rich and very flavorful.  We'll happily do this one again.  Thanks for sharing!

name: easiest tastiest barbecue country style ribs  slow cooker
review: These were a big success with our family...easy to make and very tender...this is a keeper...thanx for sharing.

name: betty white s chicken wings
review: DH and I really enjoyed these.  Followed the recipe exactly.  The only thing I may do in the future is add a little red pepper flakes because we love the heat and maybe stick them under the broiler for a bit to crisp up the skin.  Going in my "Keeper" file.  Thanks for sharing!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: These came out surprisingly well.  They were very easy to put together, and the end result was soft buns that my kids gobbled before I even sliced them.  But I think they were better as buns.  They were sturdy enough for the (veggie) burger but very soft.  I put bbq sauce on my burger and the bread was perfect for soaking in just enough sauce.  I think next time I make them, I will try adding a little onion and garlic powder, for a bit of additional flavor.  Definitely a keeper of a recipe!

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: They sure didn't taste funny to us!  They were awesome says everyone at the Halloween party I just went to!  Lovely flavor with just a little kick from the chili powder.  Great recipe and one I will use many times in the future while entertaining!  Thank you for sharing your recipe with us Sharlene!  Linda  Update:  I made these for an 80th birthday party for my aunt, and everyone went crazy for them!  I made them up ahead of time and let them marinate for about 2 hrs.  Took them out of the fridge, put them on a broiler pan and baked them for almost an hr.  The cooking time is definitely off on these. (If you want crispy bacon that is).  For any occasion these will be a hit in my family and I will make them every chance I get.  Yes, I love em and so does everyone else!  Linda

name: bread maker hamburger buns
review: very easy to make and half.  It worked great as a sandwich bread and as burger buns and my husband ate one as a roll, and said, "this bread is good!".  I usually have to ask for compliments so that's a great achievement.

name: refreshing mojito  by the pitcher mojitos
review: Perfect way to make Mojitos.  Once the gals got a taste, that pitcher was empty in record time.  I even had to snatch the pitcher away after one eager imbiber had already poured herself a mint-n-lime laden drink just to get a picture!

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: This was the first chocolate cake I made from scratch. I have to say (as did my husband and our 2 friends) that this was absolutely unbelievably delicious. I did 2 9" layer cakes with Kittencals Chocolate Frosting/Icing #89207. I served it with warmed Midsummer Swedish Strawberry Compote #235227. Fantastic recipe, can't wait for an excuse to make it again!!

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: Oh-so-good!  I can tell you right now that there will hardly be a BBQ or potluck that I attend without taking this wonderful, fresh, summery salad!  The fresh basil and black pepper let the veggies shine!  I did add a bit of aged balsamic to the leftovers and it was wonderful with that addition as well!

name: veronica s easy spanish rice
review: Quick and easy Spanish rice.  I cut the salt back to 1 teaspoon (due to dietary restrictions) and served this with chicken enchiladas and refried beans.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review:
After having this I stood up at the dinner table and applauded the recipe !!!
This one makes me do the happy food dance!!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Wow these are easy to make & really, really, really good!  I made 6 large muffins, used all the topping, added some cinnamon to the muffin mix and into the toaster oven they went (I use that in the summer rather than heat up the whole house using the oven).  Done in 18 minutes-banana muffin heaven!  Moist with a great topping!  Thanks for Posting!

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: I'm giving this only 4 stars mostly because of the recipe.  I would have preferred to have more detail about the ingredients.  Fresh lemon juice?  Or is the bottle stuff ok?  I assumed that all the herbs were meant to be whole and not ground (except for the pepper), but why not say that?  I made the recipe exactly except that I used onion instead of shallots, I didn't have any parsley, I used only 1/3 c olive oil, and I used 2.5lbs of chicken.  I used bottle lemon juice - I didn't think that the chicken was very lemony at all, so maybe fresh makes it more lemony.  I probably could have doubled the recipe seeing as I was almost doubling the amount of chicken, but it came out very nice, not a ton of flavor, but a nice, tender, juicy chicken.  I used my Tupperware marinator - the directions seemed so specific about using a glass dish, etc., that I figured I shouldn't use my usual standby of a ziplock bag.  I did end up marinating for 48 hours.  We bought some Tzatziki sauce and some pitas, and we made "giro" like sandwiches with tomato, lettuce, onion, and a little feta.  I would definitely do that again.

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: Wonderful!  Made for Zaar Cookbook Tag and what a wonderful coleslaw.  I cut the recipe in half for DH and I but wish that I had made the whole batch.  DH finished it for a snack in the evening.  Definately will make again...thank you.

name: wet burritos
review: I've had this recipe in my box forever.  The gravy kept holding me back but last week I decided to go for it.  These Burrito's were delicious.  I got distracted while cooking and accidentally added the meat to the gravy instead of putting the meat in the wraps but it didn't change the flavor, just made for skinnier Burrito's.  The gravy added a really good depth and richness to the sauce.  Moved to my "Keeper" file and will be used often.  Thanks for sharing.

name: oreo balls
review:
I made these for an upcoming baby shower at work. I made as directed except I used peppermint Oreo cookies. I also put a candy cane in the food processor and ground it until fine. The red and white blend into a pink. After I dipped the Oreo balls in white chocolate, I sprinkled them with the candy cane powder. I will update my review after the shower and let you know what everyone thought. They look so good, it will be hard to resist them until then!
Updating as promised. These were a hit at the shower. I would give them five stars based on taste alone, but deducted a star because they were so time consuming to make.

name: classic baked ziti
review: It has been said before, this is great comfort food. I omitted the chicken broth, because we like a thick sauce. Worked out well. Very easy to put together and had great result. Thanks.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: There are exactly as advertised!  What a decadent and rich treat!  I added a bit of strong coffee and cinnamon along with my m&ms which gave them a very nice Mexican Mocha flavor.  I also frosted with Recipe #43891 by Joy1996.  I can't wait to try these with other additions!  Thanks Karen!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Made this today for our lunch....so easy and delicious!  I cut the recipe in half and like some previous reviewers I used 1 Tbls. flour with 1/2 teas. arrowroot starch, added a little onion/garlic seasoning along with the salt and pepper and for the cheese I used about 3/4 cup cheddar cheese and 1/4 Velveeta for a little creamier sauce and poured over elbow macaroni.  One I will definately add to my Favorites of 2011...such comfort food!

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: Another wonderful dish from Kittencal!  I made as written only using up some left over turkey I had and I did add some red onion (that is what I had) and topped everything with the crumb mixture the when it came out of the oven with a few slivered green onions....heaven!  Thank you for a great recipe.

name: perfect pasta with no watching and no sweating
review: What a great idea!  I tried it twice.  First with elbow macaroni and then with tiny shells which took less time to cook than 15 minutes about 7-8 minutes.  I did add a little oil and salt to my water before adding the pasta and everything worked out fine.  Sure will be nice to free up a burner on busy occations.  Thank you.

name: downunder cheese puffs
review: Update: These are good and easy as a side to tomato soup both chilled and hot. Now that we homeschool I am always looking for lunch ideas. These hit the spot and the kids just love them. I love them because they are so easy. Next to a soup or salad they round out the meal. I've found mild cheeses need a little something extra...mozzarella is good but only with marinara sauce on the side to dip. We like sharp cheddar the best. This is also a quick and easy snack with some olives and other little nibbles (DH likes pepperoni or salami diced) when it's too late for lunch but too early for dinner. Origional review follows: I made these Saturday eve for a holiday cocktail party I was hosting for my neighborhood. They were very very easy to make. So easy, I wasn't sure if they would be good but they sure were. I used Kraft sharp cheddar cheese which was a nice compliment to the other items I put out and the abundance of wine that we drank lol. This is a great recipe to have at hand for spir of the moment gatherings or to keep hunger at bay if dinner will be late. Its a good thing I tasted one before I set them out otherwise I never would have, they flew off the plate so fast. Thanks for a great recipe.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: These wings are THE BEST! Loved, loved, loved them. We have found our wing recipe. Thanks so much for posting this great recipe!

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: I am going with 5 stars because this is darned good. I do think it needs a tiny bit more zip. Next time I may add some cayenne pepper (not much though) some  grated romano cheese and something to be decided. Adults praised the sauce, kids said just OK. Personally I think with minor changes (more zip) this will be my go to pizza sauce.

name: any fruit fast fat free cobbler
review:
Fantastic and will do over and over with different fruit. This time I used jarred pie cherries and a small quantity of frozen blueberries, just because they needed using. Really fast, easy and versatile. I can't wait to make it with plums.....cut into 6 which gave nice pieces, cut into four the way the recipe states would be very generous pieces!
I also added one egg and I'm happy I did.

name: i lost my noodles  low carb south beach eggplant lasagna
review: I absolutely loved this the flavour was perfect it tasted just like real lasagna. I am diabetic and can't have pasta anymore but I love lasagna and this is perfect for me. I didn't use the wine and for the meat I used ground beef. I think I made my eggplant a bit too thin and it almost melted away in the dish while cooking that's why it looks a bit muddled in the picture but the flavour was fantastic I will be making this again. I got one large dish and a smaller one and that was me cutting the recipe by half it's a great recipe for putting one in the freezer for an other day when I am short of time. Thank you so much for posting. Made for on tour with the diabetic forum. June 2011

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: Outstanding!  Supereasy, crispy crust, juicy meat.  I'll definitely make these again.  I used panko breadcrumbs.

name: bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers
review: Fantastic! We used pecorino cheese instead of cheddar as that's what we happened to have on hand, and grilled these as opposed to baking in the oven. Oh so very good!! Will get made often this summer. Thank you!

name: potato salad with chipotle peppers a man s salad
review: Great potato salad! I had to make an emergency chipotle&adobo substitute using jalopenos, ketchup and a touch of liquid smoke, and this still turned out insanely good! Liked the fact that it wasn't swimming in mayo - it was just right. So yummy! Can't wait to make again! Thank you Rita!

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: What a fabulous and easy recipe!!  I cut the recipe in half for DH and I and used canned whole tomatoes (which I pureed first), cut up a little shallot, celery and fresh garlic which I sauteed in a little olive oil/butter then I added the tomatoes, V-8 juice and I used fresh basil and heavy cream (next time I think I would use half-n-half).  Sooooo good and definately going into my Favorites of 2011.  Next time I think I would try adding fresh spinach and some tortellini like a previous review.  Thank you for submitting a great recipe.  Made for Zaar Cookbook tag game.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: From now on, this will be my "go-to" pizza crust recipe. VERY easy to make & VERY tasty!!! I forgot to buy Olive Oil when shopping the other day, so I used Canola Oil instead...still turned out GREAT!!! THANKS for sharing!!!

name: reduced fat alfredo sauce
review: Wow!  I cannot believe I made this recipe with 1% milk and not cream and it actually tasted like the full fat version!  Soooo good!!!  I doubled the recipe, used light butter, garlic powder, S&P, and at the end added in a couple ounces of fat free cream cheese just to help it to be creamier.  I still cant believe it turned out so good.  It was so thick and creamy and coated the fettuccine great.  Thanks for this great recipe and helping me find out that I can make alfredo sauce healthier and still taste delicious!

name: kittencal s milk boiled corn on the cob
review: I wanted to use this method for some not so good corn on the cob that we had.  I was hoping this recipe would add some sweetness into it and hopefully make it taste better.  The corn was justl so-so after using this method.  I still havent given up tho!  I will try this method again.  I just think the corn we had was to the "point of no return" at trying to make it taste better.  Thanks for the idea and I will be trying again.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I have made these delicious spuds multiple times and we never get tired of them.  Didn't have lemons, so subbed lemon pepper for the juice.

name: ground beef gyros
review: SAUCE: 5*****, just perfect. I thought the addition of the sugar was odd (what do I know?), but is is definitely necessary. Very tasty! Thanks for posting Cyrene

name: parmesan crusted tilapia
review: So simple to put together and the flavor was right on.  Thanks so much for sharing.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: This was easy to make and we all enjoyed it. I didn't use the onions or olives because of my families tastes. We topped ours with the tomatoes, lettuce and sour cream. Easy weeknight meal to make.

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: Good bar cookie, nothing like the flat cookie version in my opinion.  Be careful not to overcook, probably better to slightly undercook.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review:
Never in my life have I had Black Beans..until last night~how wonderful! Not that you need another rave review for this recipe, but wow, this is sooo good!
I added Laughing Cow Queso Fresco & Chipotle in place of the cream cheese..what a winner!
Thanks for sharing Jen

name: banana banana bread
review: This was made as  per recipe.  With all the bananass the bread was super mosit and even right out of the oven the bread was very flavorful.  I did add in some chopped pecans.  Thanks for posting a wonderful recipe.

name: ground beef gyros
review: These were really good.  Even DH who loves traditional Greek food said they were good.  I followed the list of ingredients but I also used the preparation method according to recipe #285900 by kneading and smashing the meat because I wanted the right texture.  I formed the meat in two small blocks and grilled them.  Once they were grilled the logs were sliced thin and put in Pita breads that were topped with thinly sliced red onion, garden fresh tomatoes and recipe #59336 by Evelyn/Athens.  Not being a lamb lover, I finally have a Gyro I can enjoy.  Thanks for posting!

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: Karen, this was very good! I did however... only used about half the pasta (9-oz. to be exact) so the pasta was nice and creamy. I cooked the pasta with 1 tsp of salt added to the boiling water, and along with a bit of vegetable oil. I used a low sodium chicken broth, 2% milk, used only 1 tsp of dried parsley flakes, an 1/8 tsp each of black pepper and red pepper flakes, plus added 1/4 tsp of dried Italian seasoning. Next time I will add some diced yellow onion when I add the minced garlic. I look forward to preparing this dish often. Thanx for the recipe Karen. It's a keeper!!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Great Muffins.  Very moist!  Thanks for posting.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: This is a very good recipe and easy to put together (though a little time consuming in assembly).  I like it with a can of Rotelle instead of the green chiles, though DH likes the plain chiles better.  I do add some garlic and 1 Tbs cumin to the chicken (as others suggested) and I do think it needs the extra flavor.  I also use a bit more chicken with 10 enriched whole wheat tortillas to really fill up my pan.  We serve this with guacamole and it is one dish where DH doesn't complain about leftovers!  Thank you for a keeper!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: Lovely; made half a recipe.  I used lemon pepper and threw about a tablespoon of butter in after the addition of the florets.  Definitely repeatable.

name: bev s macaroni and cheese
review: Easy and oh so delicious.  This was made gluten free by using gluten free flour and rice pasta.  Everyone really enjoyed it.  There were no leftovers. It is easy to see why the recipe have so many wonderful reviews.

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: Just wonderful.  Perfect in every  way.  Thanks for posting.

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: What an easy recipe to whip up--it halves easily, tastes good and the muffins look lovely.
