name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: This is great!  Super easy and super tasty.  I basted with the sauce every 20 min or so and they turned out perfectly caramelized.  Thanks for posting!

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: SO SO SO good!!!  We used turkey breast instead of chicken, because that's what they had prepared at the grocery store, and I don't like cooking chicken.  The fresh veggies we used were celery, carrots, onions, and a can each of peas and corn.  After reading reviews, we added some poultry seasoning to give it a bit more flavor.  My husband really wanted puff pastry crust for the top.  It was good, but I missed the 15 minute timer, and the puff pastry was overdone.  I will have to watch more carefully next time.  For a bottom crust, I used my MIL pie crust recipe, and it was delicious.  We made 4 cocottes and a 7x11 casserole dish.  There was a little left that didn't fit in the dish, but that's what my 4 year old ate.  She found it less offensive without the crust.  I had some as leftovers today, and I'm excited to have MORE leftovers for dinner!!!!  YUM!

name: general tso s chicken  tso chung gai
review: Loved the sauce but think I would like chicken breast better.  Will try that soon.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: We really enjoyed this.  Was worried at first as I thought cider vinegar stronger than normal white vinegar.  I used yellow mustard and garlic powder in place of cloves.  Was Delicious and will use often. Thanks.

name: long john silver s fish batter
review: Great recipe.  Thanks for posting.

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: I'm going to have to agree with everyone else, this is great!  I had to use cream of chicken in place of cream of mushroom because I disklike mushrooms.  My daughter, age 10, only gave the dish 4 stars BUT she ate this last night for supper, the gravy with mashed potatoes for breakfast AND lunch today. I as well ate all the leftovers for breakfast in place of my normal bowl of cereal.  Thank you so much for The Best Ever recipe.

name: unbelievably easy potato soup
review: Yum! I used this recipe as a base and added chopped broccoli, low-fat shredded cheese and 2 links of turkey kielbasa. I didn't peel the potatoes for the extra nutrition and color. I also used skim milk. So easy, so good and so healthy! Thanks Vina!

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review:
This dish was really lovely!
I used 3tbs of flour and butter and 2 cups of milk...because we love sauce! So I also increased the cheese and used 2 tsp of mustard powder. It was GREAT!
I served it with turkey meatloaf and brussel sprouts. YUM

name: teresa s veal  or chicken piccata
review: I was craving chicken piccata and this really fit the bill. Easy to put together and so tasty! Thanks for posting.

name: kielbasa with tomatoes and white beans
review: A sophisticated version of pork and beans for a crisp fall day!  I substituted turkey kielbasa and added 1/2 teaspoon of crushed red pepper flakes to give it just a tad of heat; other than that, followed the recipe precisely.  Some good!

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: I made this to use in Recipe #150046, a double batch. I used the larger amounts of garlic powder and cumin, and no cayenne. It certainly looked like the packaged stuff, and I always have all of these ingredients on hand. It might not necessarily be less expensive, but it is certainly healthier (lacking all of the unpronounceable chemicals). I will certainly use this often. (November 10, 2011) Edit: After using this in the recipe, I think 3 tsp. of cumin per batch is too much. It was harsh, or bitter, or some word that escapes me at the moment. Next time I will only use 2 tsp. And I will also try to curb my addiction to the word "certainly." LOL

name: shredded chicken for enchiladas  tostadas  tacos
review: Awesome recipe.  I used this recipe for my chicken enchiladas and man oh man..is it good.  Thank you for the recipe.

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: Excellent recipe Mark. I used olive oil instead of butter but the rest of the recipe remains as stated.. Thank you...

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Very Creamy!  Made Exactly As Stated!  Rich Taste.

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: I marinated this overnight, turning occasionally as suggested.  It gave a wonderful Asian flavor to the beef.  Thanks.

name: new york style pizza crust
review: Love it! Thin crust, crispy edges...perfect!

name: hello dollies
review: Yummy, yummy, yummy!  My granny used to makes these.  This is my "go to" recipe when I have company coming & have no time to make anything too time consuming.  They always turn out perfect and everyone LOVES them!  Thanks for posting.

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: Turned out great, very easy! I added some bacon wrap and let marinate for a few hours before cooking (just because I wanted to get the prep done early and have an easy dinner).  Basted every 10 minutes while cooking for about 45 minutes, at which point it registered 170 on a meat thermometer.  So I probably could have taken it out closer to 30 minutes.  Served with the sauce and a spicy Chinese style rice.  Overall I would say it is very good and I will make it again but probably tweak it by adding some pineapple for a sweet & sour flair or maybe some mustard for a honey dijon flavor.

name: best pumpkin cookies
review: These are the best ever!  Delectable little orbs of goodness!  The only change I made was to use cream cheese frosting in place of the glaze.  These are amazing, and I'll be making them again this week!  Thanks!

name: white almond sour cream wedding cake
review: Good. Mine turned out very, very dense, but then again, I changed a couple things. If I could do things over I would use 3 9x13 pans instead of 2. It makes so much cake! I will try this again for a crowd, definitely. The cake bottoms were so nice and firm for frosting.

name: harvest pumpkin apple bread
review: (OCT'11) Made w granny smith apples (2med) and 1.25 cup sugar and added walnuts. Wanted for coffee so not sweet. Very good. Muffins (11) 20 min and mini loaves (5) 32 min. Nice for giveaways too. Thx from iPhone. (NOV '11) Made w/1 GS apple, 1c raw sugar, 3/4c white sugar, no nuts... also very good. 50min was too long for mini loaves and mini bundts, but moist inside!

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: This turned out perfectly and will replace my previous chili recipe.  Thanks!

name: best twice baked potatoes
review: My mom used to make these when I was younger. I forgot how good they are! And so easy, too!

name: extremely soft white bread   bread machine
review: Oh my word. This was awesome. I'm just now learning how to make bread and use a bread machine. Up till now, almost all of my bread attempts have been too dense and have been hard on the outside. So, I know I can't take credit for how this one turned out! I was also impressed with how the holes in the bread were smaller, like store bread. I have been looking for a bread recipe that doesn't turn out too crusty so that I can make it instead of buying store-bought bread. This is the one! Thank you!

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review:
Wow!! This was one of the most amazing pastas I've had!! We don't get manicotti here so stuffed up shells with the mixture. We also don't get ricotta cheese here, so substituted half cottage cheese and half cheddar cheese for it. It was an amazing pasta and my whole family loved it!!
Thanks Kitten for yet another amazing recipe! 10 stars all the way!!

name: baked buffalo chicken breasts
review: This was good and easy to make. I doubled the sauce based on the other reviews but didn't double the celery seed. I actually didn't eat this because I don't eat hot wings but the rest of the family enjoyed this. Hubby said it was really spicy but the sauce was thin.

name: beef barley soup
review: This was a fantastic soup.  My whole family really enjoyed.  I do feel it could have had extra broth but over all it was great.  I will be using this recipe over and over again.  Thanks for posting.

name: cherry pie filling bread
review:
Sinful. Made as directed, but added choc chips and used walnuts. Will leave the choc out next.

This time made as stated, without choc chips and can't you believe it, out of nuts. . .yep, even at my house! LOL. Absolutely Wonderful, Marie, thank you for sharing.

name: bakery style chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: excellent cookies! my husband made these for me (he said he followed the recipe EXACTLY)... I believe him.

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review:
Mmm, FT, this was really, really tasty! Cheesy, creamy and delish just like promised. YUM! I had this as my main meal and it was very satisfying even though I cut the cheese by half as that's all I had on hand (I used white Irish cheddar). The crumb topping was so good, I think Ill use it on other gratins as well from now on.
THANK YOU SO MUCH for sharing this keeper with us, hon!
Made and reviewed for I Recommend Tag November 2011.

name: banana oatmeal bread
review: Good recipe.  Easy to make.  Everyone enjoyed.  Thanks.

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: This is utterly, divinely choc-o-licious, and talk about easy!!  It was a hit as dessert at a recent dinner gathering, but even better at 3 a.m. with a cold glass of milk!:):)

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: This is a really good potato soup.  I followed recipe except for adding bacon bits and a dash of garlic powder.  I found that placing the block of cream cheese on top of the lid of the pot to melt it worked well.  I just snipped off the corner of the package and squeezed it into the pot.  I am making this soup for the second time tonight and it is a must to double the recipe, as there are NO leftovers.  Thank you for a great recipe.

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: VERY good! The whole famn damily loved it, including the kids. I wish I had made 2 batches. Served with recipe#45270. The seasonings are spot on. I did sauteed the green onions in the butter for about 45 seconds to soften, let them completely cool before adding to the egg.   It will be fun to experiment with other ingredients. It's a winner, thanks Potsie!

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: Hate to be the one with such a low review, but none of us liked it. It was way too eggy.. none of the other flavours came through and I even doubled the lemon pepper. We also thought it needed a different base than just the tortilla, which was too thin and wasn't even crisp.. which may have covered up the egginess.  Sorry, but I won't be making this again.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: This was easy to put together with ingredients on hand.  It was a little bland, but made a quick meal.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Good meatloaf.  I made with 1/3 ground pork, and couldn't resist adding a little bell pepper and Worcestershire sauce.  Thank you for sharing your recipe.

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: I'm sorry but this pie crust had no flavor at all.  The recipe was easy and the dough was easy to work with  but I prefer my crust to add to the flavor profile of the dish.  It needed butter instead of shortening.

name: copycat ihop harvest grain   nut pancakes
review: I had saved this recipe a long time ago and just never got around to it.  So glad I finally did as these are some awesome pancakes and I'll be making them again.  They are my favorite at IHOP but it is so far away we rarely get to have them anymore.  These are so much like them, now I can have them whenever I want.  I made following the directions exactly and was a little worried as the batter was so much thicker than I'm used to; I didn't need to worry, they turned out perfect.  Served with warm maple syrup and hot coffee - YUM

name: kittencal s scalloped potato and ground beef casserole
review: Cheesy, saucy, and savory. Huge hit with the family and it made so much. So, we have plenty of leftovers. Very tasty casserole. May add some veggies next time to make it an all-in-one dish.

name: easy pineapple upside down cake
review: This cake was so simple to make.  It was moist and delicious.  Thanks for posting this cake mix recipe.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Let me add my five stars.  To reduce carbs, I used 1/4 cup of oat bran, used sugar free ketchup and splenda brown sugar blend and I added caramelized onions as well as garlic.  I was afraid that the meatloaf might be dry because I ground my own lean beef, but with the addition of the 1/2 and 1/2 it was moist and delicious.

name: fish tacos and cilantro coleslaw  20 minutes max
review: We enjoyed this recipe very much! I was in an extreme rush and needed it in less than 20 so I cut a couple corners: I used canned salmon (drained and then flaked), skipped the warming process, and used dried herbs. It was perfect and even easier than originally planned! I am excited at the simplicity of this recipe - I have already rolled a couple for my 3-year-old to snack on for the next couple days. Even he loved it!

name: bev s macaroni and cheese
review: Loved the creaminess and the flavors.  I had 8 oz. of Tillamook garlic white cheddar to try and just loved it.  Faint flavor of garlic that we loved.

name: cranberry orange muffins
review: I just made a batch of these this morning.  They are very very good.  In response to those who find them dry, I would say that they are right if you are comparing them to cake muffins.  so i that is what you prefer, these are not the muffins for you.  But, if you are a fan of denser muffins, then you should give these a try.  Also, INMHO, the muufin batter is adequately sweet.  The tartness is all in the cranberries.  Next time I''ll cut them in hslf do that the tartness is less concentrated in certain spots.  The only thing I changed this time was to use melted butter in place of oil.

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: This casserole was really good. I did add some salsa to the ground beef otherwise I thought it would have been too dry. I only used 5 tortillas and just half the package of taco seasoning. I always find the taco seasoning a bit overpowering so it is just personal preference. Thanks I will make this again.

name: french dip roast beef for the crock pot
review: SO GOOD! My husband loved this! I made as directed except didn't use rosemary. The sandwiches are delicious made with provolone cheese and a little butter; I served roasted cubed potatoes on the side.

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Thank you so much for sharing this easy to make dish 1Steve....delicious, absolutely delicious....I don't usually eat crisps, but your recipe has changed all that...my friend and I ate most of the crisp so I  had to make another for my dh....he loved it also.  Updated:  Six years, later and this is still my favorite apple crisp on the site. My dh would eat the whole dish by himself, if I let him. It is such a comforting dish, the spices are perfect in it.

name: weight watchers broccoli cheese soup   2 pts per cup
review: It doesn't get any easier than this!  This is a good hearty vegetable soup for low points.  I used a combination of frozen broccoli, cauliflower and carrots and pureed some with my immersion hand blender when cool. It turned out nice and thick this way. Next time I will try with just broccoli cuts and not puree and see what I think.  Also will try with petite diced tomatoes as my daughter thought it was a bit too spicy even though I used mild rotel.  I think this is a perfect lunch soup for winter.  Thanks for posting!

name: granny s slow cooker vegetarian chili
review: So delicious!!!!!  Lots of flavor!!!!!!   Passing this on to coworkers.  I use pinto beans instead of baked beans Didn't do step 1, just threw the onion , garlic, and green pepper raw into the crock pot.   Will be making this often.

name: easy creamy sour cream chicken casserole
review: This was good!  I doubled the recipe but not the butter portion.  It was fine using 1/2 c.  It was a bit rich for us, so next time I will do the following - use low fat mushroom soup, possibly light sour cream or cut down on the sour cream.  I will definitely add some vegetables to the mix just to make it a bit more substantial for us.  Very nice "quick" dinner!  Thanks!

name: harvest pumpkin cheesecake
review: This was an excellent cheesecake I made weekend before last.  DH was disappointed I wouldn't be doing an encore for Thanksgiving.  My sis is bringing the desserts.  Very good stuff.  I did not have a pan large enough to put my springform pan it for the water bath so I lowered the heat a to 325 degrees and it was okay.  I have a penchant for doing it right so I will keep looking for a large enough pan for the springform pan.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: Based on just the cake, I'd give this recipe 5 stars. I didn't bother making the frosting. With a cake this awesome, who needs it? I also really like how simple it is - a cup of this, a cup of that, and everything else is measured in teaspoons. My only complaint is how unhealthy it seems with so much oil. So, I'm planning to try substituting applesauce for some of it if I ever have any on hand when I make this again. And, no, I don't believe I'll ever need another chocolate cake recipe! Made in a bundt pan, this took 45 minutes to bake.

name: white pizza or pizza blanca
review: This is a great pizza that even my son enjoyed.  On half of the pizza I put red pepper flakes.  Thanks DragonShoes :)  Made for Cookbook tag game

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: Easy and very tasty!  I used spicy sausage and it turned out great.  This also reheats well. Thank you for sharing this recipe.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: This is quite good and requires little effort.  Think adding some sausage or other meat would help make it a heartier meal.  It reheats well also.  Thank you for sharing!

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: that was ok and super fast

name: pan fried onion dip
review: To. Die. For. Yes, too much butter and oil, but I just drained it. I used a sweet onion and a red onion. I also added 2 garlic cloves and some anchovie paste. I cut the salt in half because the anchovie paste is salty too. After the onions cooled I threw them in the food processor and then mixed. I did not feel the need to season further, it had a nice kick with the cayenne. Made it to take to Thanksgiving tomorrow and I'm so glad I doubled it because we'll be having some tonight. YUMMY!

name: uncle bill s method for cooking turkey
review: Thank you, Uncle Bill! I just got done cleaning up after our Thanksgiving Feast and I have to say I am so happy I used this recipe to cook my turkey. It was almost too simple, but it was by far the best turkey I've ever made. The water trick really does work. My husband was amazed at how the skin shrank/tightened right before our eyes. Our 12 pound turkey was very moist. I will never cook another turkey without this recipe ever again.

name: really really good candied sweet potatoes
review: Awesome! I have tried a lot of sweet potato recipes, easy to very complicated. This is one of the easiest, and definitely the best I've had. Served for Thanksgiving and topped with marshmallows just for fun. Used the amount of sauce called for and it was perfect, more would have been way too sweet. Baked the sweet potatoes the night before (350 degrees for an hour), peeled, cut up, and put in casserole dish which made prep the next day very fast. Most people would probably need to double this recipe. Thanks for sharing the recipe!!

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: Delicious marinade, I made this for a family dinner and it was gobbled up!  My only comment is to make certain you slice the meat against the grain and slice it very thin.  I know this is pretty basic advice, but my husband cut ours too thick and it was a bit tough.  Great recipe!

name: libby s famous pumpkin pie
review: Pumpkin pie doesn't get better than this!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Yummy and quick. Substituted fresh garlic and ginger for the ground. Added carrots. Super delicious and easy. A definite keeper, thanks for posting.

name: opal s pumpkin pie
review: Thanks Carol J for sharing and  Opal, wherever you are! I have always used Libby pre-seasoned pie filling but NEVER AGAIN, this rocked my world! Everyone loved it, including my husband who is not a huge fan of pumpkin pie.  Simply the best I have ever tasted and I went into this with great skepticism, silly me.

name: kittencal s best deviled eggs
review: I will NEVER make another recipe!  I tried a shortcut by using garlic salt instead of adding them separately and it over-powered the dill. They were still delicious - follow the recipe and I bet they are dynamite.

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: These were delicious, super soft and a little sweet. I have made these three times and they disappear. To have some for Thanksgiving I had to make a double batch. They freeze and thaw very well.

name: classic pie crust  idiot proof step by step photo tutorial
review: So easy and came out great! I've never had much luck making pie crust before this recipe. Thanks for posting.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Made as directed with a well cooked and seasoned roux and sharp cheddar cheese.  This is delicious and will be my go-to mac and cheese recipe.  Thanks!

name: good eats roast turkey
review: I've used this brine for the last couple of Thanksgivings and it truly makes an amazing difference in the flavor of the turkey!  I usually only do a turkey breast as there are never more than a few people here and I do it in the crock pot.  I brine overnight, then rinse and put it in the crock pot over a sliced onion, a sliced apple, a sprig of rosemary, a couple of sage leaves, and several sprigs of thyme.  I add the cinnamon stick and cook on low for 7-8 hours.  I usually use the drippings and the onions and apples to make a wonderful gravy right before serving.

name: delicious homemade egg noodles
review: DH asks for homemade noodles every year for Thanksgiving and Christmas as that's what his family always had growing up.  I'd never been brave enough to try making them until  this year.  I found this recipe that sounded exactly like the one his grandma uses, so I gave it a go. These were not at all difficult to make, even if they were time consuming.  I look at it as a labor of love :)  I dried them for 2 hours then refrigerated them overnight which worked very well.  I then simmered them in some homemade turkey stock for about an hour. DH said they were perfection!

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: Made this for our Thanksgiving meal this year and it was so good and incredibly quick and easy.  Got lots of compliments on it being the best gravy people had ever tasted!

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Worth taking my breadmaker out of storage.  Will be making this often.

name: unknownchef86 s very best dinner rolls
review: These came out great. I used and egg wash instead of butter as Chef Lil Red suggested and should have left them in the oven for just a couple minutes longer after covering with foil. The flavor and texture of these little guys are just perfect. Thanks for posting the recipe. I'll be making these again.

name: sausage gravy
review: This is how I've always made my sausage gravy.  Super good.  I use Jimmy Dean Hot Sausage.  Gives it extra flavor and isn't too hot for more tender mouths.  And of course you have to use Grands Biscuits.

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: This was so easy and delicious!  Cilantro, cheese and sour cream make a nice garnish.  It's a keeper.  Thanks!

name: traditional tamales  pork
review: I can now take making tamales off my bucket list. Your recipe is fantastic! The instructions were so easy to follow. I made the pork in the crockpot the day before and also made your red chili sauce. I let mine steam for about 90 minutes. I think next time I'll double the salt in the masa mixture. Can't wait to make these again. Thanks so much for posting this great recipe!

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: These were very easy to make and tasted pretty good as well.  I used Sweet Baby Ray's honey bbq sauce.  I'll be making again!

name: denny s style french toast
review:
Excellent French toast.
I used Recipe #408880 for the bread and Oh My!
Wonderful. DH kept saying how good it was and
loved the flavor with the cranberry.

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: These cookies are wonderful - just like it says. I didn't have to change a thing - I thought the recipe is perfect as written.  I used snowflake cookies cutters and piped royal icing on them and then dipped them in white sparkling sugar.

name: crock pot chicken taco meat
review: This really is incredible. I made this for my husband & made it again for our Thanksgiving appetizer tray. It was so easy. I used my own homemade taco seasoning & low sodium veggie broth. Chicken was fall apart tender & had great flavor AND smell. thanks for sharing!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: I followed this recipe, except I used turkey instead of chicken. It was good, but we think it needs more gravy. It also needed more seasoning.  This recipe makes a lot, it served three people for dinner and again the next day when reheated.  There was still enough left to serve us again, but I did not think it would reheat well a third time. Thank you for sharing this recipe -- I am sure I will make it again with a little tweaking.

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: I have made this recipe a lot.  I always add the green chilis, but I also use a large can of enchilada sauce so the finished product is not quite as dry.  Thanks for sharing.

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: This is most magnificiently delicious chicken ever!

name: easy creamy sour cream chicken casserole
review: I really liked this recipe but the original recipe as written just didn't seem like enough. The second time I made it I added a frozen veggie mix that I cooked ahead of time (it was corn, carrots and asparagus) and I also added some spices and seasoning to the soup/sour cream mixture (a few pinches of mild chili powder, dried onions and dill) and it was really good. I also melted the butter and mixed it with the Ritz crackers before I put them over the top to get a good even brown. I really do like how the sour cream adds a whole new taste to the boring old cream soup taste. This is really a comfort casserole at it's best! Thank you for posting! I'm pretty sure that the family will ask for this again!

name: dark chocolate cake
review: I've been making this recipe for decades (I got it from the back of a Hershey's cocoa container), and every time I make a different chocolate cake recipe, I always wish I had made this one instead. The best tip is *not* to use the full amount of boiling water - it tastes EVEN BETTER with somewhat less water! I've tried it with coffee, less oil, double-sifted cake flour ... so many ways to vary it up and still have a fantastic chocolate cake!

name: microwave poached eggs
review: These were pretty good!

name: bacardi rum cake
review: This is phenomenal! Sorry I have not reviewed before now! Can't believe I have not! I have made this several ways and each is terrific. My fave is lemon pudding and tropical rum! Freezes superbly! Thanks so much derf!

name: beth s pizza crust
review: I'm so happy to have discovered and tried this recipe because not only is it tasty, it's also quick and easy to make.  The only thing I wasn't wild about was that the bottom of the crust was a bit soggy after baking it at 450 for 15 minutes so next time I will bake it for about 5 min. before adding the toppings.  Thanks!

name: christmas rum balls or bourbon balls
review: My Dad wanted rum balls, just like Grandma use to make...and these are the ones!!  I had to skip the nuts (Dad preference) and I used Myers Rum...Delicious!! Rolled in powdered sugar...and packed to ship to California!!  Thank you Bergy!!

name: mahogany beef stew
review: Did not have wine; used beef broth instead. Agree that the flavor is rich and wonderful with the hoisin sauce. Will try with potatoes next time.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: Easy & quick but not as much flavor as id hoped.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: I have made this twice now and it is WONDERFUL!  The meat is fall off the bone tender, juicy and so flavorful!  Instead of putting onion in the bottom of the crock, I used an aluminum foil packet filled with cubed potatoes seasoned with salt, pepper and butter.  Oh my gosh, the potatoes were soooo good.  I used the leftover chicken breast to make Recipe #105202 the next day.  Yum!!!  *Update* - I've discovered if you add the bones and skin back into the liquid that was left in your crock pot, add 5-6 cups of water and whatever vegetables you have on hand (carrots, celery, onion) and cook overnight (12 hours) on LOW, it will make a WONDERFUL stock.  Filter the bones and veggies out, and store the stock in containers in the fridge.  After a few hours the fat will solidify on the top and can be removed.  The stock can then be frozen until needed.

name: chicken legs grilled
review: Mmmm...scrumptious. I doubled the olive oil for an easier distribution of the spice mixture. Great dish! Thank you.

name: utterly deadly southern pecan pie
review: I made this for Thanksgiving and it turned out amazingly well.  It reminded me of the awesome pecan pie I used to be able to get while living in Texas.  It took 55 minutes in my oven.

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: Thanks for posting this recipe! I use it all the time. I even used it to make a cake shaped like Lightning McQueen from the Cars movie!

name: split pea soup  crock pot    dairy free
review: Easy as could be and turned out great. I did have to add some broth after it sat in the fridge because it got very thick but then it was perfect again.

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: Wow..so good...I followed the recipe exactly...However, I didn't have any sour cream but it is still soooooo delicious..thanks for posting it.

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: This was excellent. I skipped the pasta and added 4 links of italian sausage for my protein obsessed hubby. He scarfed it down and I loved it too.

name: simple sweet scones
review: This was sweet and good.  Will make again.  Thanks for posting.

name: perfect turkey in an electric roaster oven
review: This was my first year making a turkey in an electric roaster and it was the best turkey we have ever had.  I had a 21 lb. turkey and I stuffed it.  It was done perfectly in exactly 4 hours and a 30 minute rest time.  The juciest breast meat I have ever tasted.

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: This was a very good coffee cake.  Moist and yummy.  Thanks for posting.

name: chocolate mint candy  fudge
review: Fantastic!  Easy! Easy!  I brought a batch of these to my dance club and everyone loved them.  The only things I did different was use white chocolate chips as other reviewers suggested and I melted my chocolate in the microwave instead of on the stove.  Chocolate melted fine.  I used 40 seconds in my microwave, but since microwaves vary this may be a little too much or not enough.  Thank you so very much for sharing.  I will definetly make this again and again and again.

name: wet burritos
review: These were a hit.   I followed the recipe as written and wouldn't change a thing.

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: Tried this tonight and don't think we'll be making again. Added some honey to the glaze right at the end to sweeten it up a bit. I found the stove top cooking method to be rather time consuming, but since this recipe is Japanese this was used since many Japanese don't have ovens. We much preferred recipe #145038.

name: chinese pot stickers
review: These were great! I've never tried making these before, and they were really good.

name: almost tortuga rum cake
review: Terrific, tender cake.  I subbed a commercial cake mix for the first part of the recipe and was out of pudding mix, so subbed cornstarch.

name: frizzled cabbage
review: This was AWESOME!   Such an easy recipe too.  Thanks!

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: Was difficult to cook as I chose to use a smaller pan so it could fit into my toaster oven.--the top was done, but the inside needed an extra 15 minutes on 325 with aluminum foil over it.  Because I'd always prefer to use my toaster oven rather than the big oven, I probably won't be making this again.

name: roast beef horseradish spirals
review: Nice make ahead appetizer. Would especially be nice in the Summer.  I would add more horseradish next time.  I like mine to have a bite!

name: scrum diddly umptious vegan brownies
review: I cannot believe this is Vegan. So good.

name: new york style pizza crust
review: Very easy. My first time not using the bread machine to mix. Had to make pizza two days in a row because all loved it. Thank you!

name: buttery yeast rolls
review: These WONDERFUL !!! rolls were made on 12/4//11 for the " Let's P-A-R-T-Y " Event in the Cooking Contests And Events Forum. I followed the recipe exactly as it was written, and was rewarded with a melt in you mouth roll.This roll recipe rates right up there with one of the best that I've ever tried.Thanks so much for posting a recipe that will be made again. " Keep Smiling :) "

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: Easy and delicious.

name: weight watchers 2 point  pumpkin muffins
review: These muffins were fantastic!  I've watched this recipe get reviewed over and over again and finally I picked up a box of spice cake mix from the store and whipped them up in mere minutes.  Mine cooked in 24 minutes.  After they cooled a bit I tasted one just to make sure they were decent and they weren't just decent- they were phenomenal!  Incredibly moist, nice pumpkin taste and were great with a tall glass of cold milk.  I can't wait to make these over and over again!

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: Love this bread!  I can't believe I haven't reviewed it before now as I've made it several times.  I usually make 2 loaves out of it and use semisweet chocolate chips instead of milk chocolate. I also use low-fat sour cream and have also used part plain yogurt before, too.  Thank you for the great recipe!

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: DH just loved this one.  I have a couple comments, don't use the seasoning packet when making the noodles.  #1 says to cook as directed on the packet. wrong.  Cook longer than the 2-3 min. to brown.  DH would like this for breakfast using ham so may try that  someday.  I did make the Cantonese brown sauce and added much to the recipe.

name: frizzled cabbage
review: The whole family loves this. I replace 1/2 the butter with olive oil. I also cover it as it cooks. It's always yummy and always perfect. Thanks for posting this recipes. I've made it 2x in 2 weeks and plan to make it more.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: These muffins are very good!  My whole family liked them.  I'm not sure they're my perfect muffin, probably because they are more cake like than true muffin texture, but they were still nice tasting and easy to make.

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: I added hot sauce in the middle of the layers and thought it was great.  Easy casserole and have a little left over for lunch tomorrow even though I made half a recipe.

name: hamburger noodle bake
review: Easy and very tasty!  If your looking for a quick dinner this is it.  I used low fat cream cheese and light sour cream and still very tasty.  Thanks for a great recipe.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: I will rate this again when I made this again.  I substituted beef stew for hamburger, I needed to use it up and even though I cut it into small pieces, it still made a different texture.  I think I added to much wine, next time I will try 1/2 cup.  With my changes, it was a 4 out of 5.

name: redneck casserole
review: I made this a couple weeks ago.  It was something fun for DH and myself to eat.  Kind of made us feel like kids again.  I bet it would be really good with a splash of BBQ sauce in the beans.  I'll put this one in my keeper file because I think there's all kinds of ways to play with this.  Thanks for sharing!

name: crock pot ham and beans
review: We made this with our leftover Thanksgiving ham bone and it was really good.  I added some diced carrots, and let it cook all day.  Thank you for sharing.

name: mashed sweet potatoes
review: Great flavor, not overly sweet, just a pleasant flavor.  I followed the recipe to a tee and wouldn't change a thing.  This is definately a company worthy dish.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: I enjoyed this (as leftovers after derby scrimmage) when my daughter finished cooking it for me. I had finished step 2 when I had to leave. All of us agreed that the sauce was a little too thick. I realize, however, that she might not have understood exactly how much cornstarch and water she still needed to add. I think I would make this again as written before trying to change it. The balance of flavors was good.

name: roast  sticky  chicken
review: I've been making this chicken for years. I found a similar recipe on another site way back when and loved it. I gave this recipe to my DD to make as her first meal for her in-laws. Even though she can't cook.....they loved her meal! :lol: Thanks C Chatwin for a winner. Made for Cookbook Tag.

name: southwestern stuffed bell peppers
review: Wonderful!  This is a simple and delicious dish and one I would serve for company.  I cut the recipe in half used recipe#76616#76616 for the taco seasoning mix and followed the instructions.  I used yellow and red peppers (but for Christmas I will use green and red) and served with sour cream, recipe#287183#287183, recipe#133436#133436 and a small green salad. Thank you for submitting the recipe.  This is going into my Favorites of 2011.  Made for Let's Party 2011.

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: Yum! This was delicious. It was also very easy to make, especially with the shortcuts that I took. I just chopped up the chicken breasts and vegetables and threw them in the pot with 4 cups of boiling chicken broth. After the chicken was cooked, I added all of the other ingredients and cooked until the gnocci was done. I left out the spinach and cornstarch and it was still really good.

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: Another wonderful recipe by Kittencal!  Used this recipe to make recipe#76043#76043 and DH said to use this recipe in ALL my Mexican cooking.  I did add about 1 1/2Tbls. of dried granulated tomato powder as you recommended.  Definately going into my Favorites of 2011.  Thank you for posting.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: This was just ok for us.  I followed the recipe but reduced the Sesame Oil out of personal preference.  I also let it marinate about 4 hours.  It was gorgeous to look at but we found the flavor kind of flat.  Not sure if I'll try this one again but thanks for posting and giving us the opportunity to try something different!

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: good pork but you gotta be careful with the breadcrumb & cheese mixture--you don't need near that much to cover the pork.

name: pumpkin cake bars with cream cheese frosting
review: Really good, my husband loved it- admittedly he likes anything with cream cheese frosting. We made it as is and it is moist, rich and decadent. THanks!

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: DH wanted green beans with dinner and this looked so pretty I decided to try it.  I used fresh green beans, but canned stewed tomatoes as that's what I had.  Pretty simple, I used fresh garlic and then followed as directed.  Very nice and enjoyed by both me and DH.  Thanks so much for posting.

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: This brisket was totally awesome.  So moist and tender.  The smoky flavor that the liquid smoke gave it was just perfect. Thanks for posting such a wonderful recipe.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: *original review 5/29/07*My friend and I made this this weekend at her house and we had to omit the sun dried tomatoes & green onion but this was SOOOO good! OMG..I loved it and will make it again!!!! ////////// 11/29/10 - I remade this tonight and included the sun dried tomatoes and green onions. Yum:) I had to use half n half but it didnt affect taste. My friend came over and really enjoyed it as well. Thanks! **Edited 12/8/11 to add stars**

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Yep, this is lip-smakin' good. Didn't change one thing, used cream - if you're gonna enjoy meatloaf, then e n j o y meatloaf. There's no cryin' in good meatloaf. Go ahead. This is the real deal.

name: the best chicken tortilla soup
review: Great recipe!  Often it's hard to find something the whole family agrees on, but everyone around the table gave it 5 stars.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: I thought the hoisin sauce made this slightly sweet; not my preference. But it was such a nice saucy stew that we enjoyed it anyway! I didn't have time to stand over the stove, so I put everything in the crockpot. I didn't even shred my beef roast- put it in whole and turned it on Low for 6 hours. Then I removed the beef and let it stand while adding the cornstarch mixture to the crockpot. (There's more liquid in crockpot cooking, so I tripled the cornstarch mixture- perfect.) I shredded the beef and put it back in the crockpot, had it on high for another hour. Perfect! Served over MASHED POTATOES! Yum!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Perfection! This is one of those recipes you save and use forever. We have no need to try another biscuit recipe. DH made these and followed your recipe on down the line. They came out light, fluffy, tasty and tall! We seved them with sausage gravy for a heavenly Saturday morning breakfat. Thanks so much for sharing this amazing recipe!

name: oreo balls
review: I can't believe I've never reviewed these. Everytime I make them they disappear. I make mine smaller only because they're so rich. I agree with others that it's best to crush the oreos either with a rolling pin or food processor, then mix with a mixer. I found using two toothpicks is the easiest way to get them covered with chocolate and then pulled out of the chocolate. They turn out so pretty. Thanks for posting this great recipe!

name: soft batch chocolate chip cookies
review:
12/11 Made them again -- forgot the salt - but they are still my go-to chip cookies !

12/10 Glad I found this !! The pudding mix certainly adds a boost to the "chewy" nature, which I have missed ! I,too, added 1 tsp salt and it was perfect. I also used 1/2 bitter-sweet bits, because I had them. Made 6 doz. perfect-sized cookies. Thanks for posting, Dawn.

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: This cookie is wonderful and the dough is amazing to work with; I made a double batch for a cookie decorating party and it made around 120 cookies of all different shapes.

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: Very good chicken salad.  I will use this recipe again.  I did add diced sweet onion and red bell pepper along with the diced celery.

name: world s best butter cookies
review:
These were good. The flavor was delicate, the texture was just right between crisp and soft. I had a hard time making my roll round, so the cookies came out a little funny, but I'm not picky.
I have made these for several years, I dip them in chocolate for gift giving.

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: This was quite a surprise!  I make my own Ranch Dressing and used panko bread crumbs, but those were the only changes I made to this recipe. This was so easy to make. Loved the fact is was so cheap on the food budget!  I served with a baked potato & steamed veggies.  Delish and will be often.

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: I had a box of cake mix left over from a product test that I never finished (oops!) and needed cookies more then a cake, so I gravitated toward this recipe. It was very easy and they turned out well. I tried to let these dry so the sugar would not absorb, but was only partially successful because I got impatient. I took mine out of the oven after 8 minutes. They probably could have gone longer, but they are still chewy so I think I like them this way.

name: oreo balls
review: Easy-peasy to make and any Oreo-type sandwich cookie will work in this recipe.  I used cookies from the dollar store.  Make sure and let them harden on waxed paper. I put them on a cake rack and they hardened to the wire mesh.  A brief time in the oven softened the chocolate enough to enable me to remove the balls to waxed paper.  I had a little trouble with the white chocolate/baggie thing as it melted the plastic.

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: So chocolatey!This is very tasty and moist.I made a 2 layer cake with 2 8 inch pans and used Frosting # 89207 instead of the glaze here.Very decadent,goes great with a glass of milk.

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: The seasonings are spot on!  I cut my potatoes like I'd normally cut fries, and for the time specified, it was too much.  I ended up with some potato chips!  But that being said, the flavor is great, and through trial and error, I'll find the right slice, temp, and time combo.  I used olive oil instead of regular oil.  Yum!

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: This is very easy to throw together and makes a very nice moist cake.  I tried it out because I found a Pineapple cake mix and had never seen one before.  I also had a case of fresh pineapples because we just got back from HI, so thought this would be perfect.  It was good, but ultimately for me, I don't think I care for the fake pineapple taste of the boxed mix.  Next time I will make a cake from scratch and just use the brown sugar/pineapple topping as it was wonderful.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: This is my new favorite fish recipe.  It is absolutely delicious, and tastes restaurant quality!!  I used simple frozen fillets, cannot imagine how outstanding it would be with fresh caught fish.  And you know what?  It is EVEN better then next day.  I microwaved our leftovers and the flavors were awesome!

name: spiced sweet roasted red pepper   feta hummus
review: My first attempt at homemade hummus and I'm sold. Can't wait to make it for friends. I did use Tahini substitute (peanut butter and sesame oil) with great results. Thanks for posting. Update: Have made several times, but just made it without the cheese and I believe it was just as good without the extra calories and expense.

name: tzatziki
review: Delicious! Made 1/2 recipe using Greek yogurt; skimped a little on the olive oil and used dried dill. Thank you Ev!

name: the perfect burger
review: Worked out nice on an indoor grill. Followed the burger part and used Cajun seasoning for stir in, but omitted the salt ingredient. Quite juicy.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: These were the best brussel sprouts I've ever eaten!  I used 4 cloves of garlic.  The parmesan would definitely put these over the top. I had to put the lid on the last couple minutes to get the tops cooked  Make sure to season with salt and pepper!!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Really good chops!  I lreally liked them, but my hubby said they were just OK.  I browned them on both sides in a oven-proof skillet with lid.  Then placed the lid ontop and baked in the oven at 350F for about 40 minutes.  My chops had the bone and were about an inch thick. I also doubled the sauce.  I served this with white rice and green beans.  I'd make again.

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: OMG....this is soooooooooooo good!!! My wife especially liked it!!! Even though it's kind of a pain peeling the squash, it is WELL worth it & the carmelization is perfect!!! I'll definately be making this again!!! THANKS for sharing!!!

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: I am going to a cookie exchange at work tomorrow and needed something to throw together fast. This was super easy, and I like the taste! I used a small ice cream scoop to scoop the dough. I scooped them out and dumped them in a bowl of powdered sugar. I rolled the dough around, generously coating them. They turned out perfect.

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: I'd love to give this higher marks because I love many of FT's recipes and photos but this one fell short on flavor for us.  It made an incredibly beautiful golden and crispy crust on our fish, onion rings and zucchini strips but the batter needs to be seasoned heavily with salt and pepper to get any flavor.  I had to make two batches to cover everything we cooked, 4 Tilapia fillets, 1 large onion, 1 regular zucchini.  The first batch I added about a teaspoon of salt so when I realized I had to whip up a second batch I added about two teaspoons and it was still bland.  I'm keeping it for future use but have to keep tweaking the seasonings.  Thanks for sharing!

name: awesome baked ham
review: I'm going to risk sounding like an idiot. I bought a pre-cooked ham (without a bone) prior to finding this recipe. Looking at the cooking time I didn't think my ham would really work so I took it back. The grocery store didn't sell "raw" hams which is what I thought I was looking for. (I don't cook a lot of ham.) The butcher suggested a pre-cooked spiral sliced bone-in ham. It did have a longer cooking time on its directions although it was only about 2 hours (it was half a ham...not 15 pounds). I cooked it for 2-3 hours at 325 (ham directions said 300 and this recipe said 350 so I compromised). It was still cold in the middle. I bumped it back up to 350 for about another hour and that was better. The end result was fabulous. So, for anyone who really hasn't dealt much with hams... I'm guessing the pre-cooked, no bone ham would have been fine with a shorter cooking time. The spiral sliced bone-in ham was fantastic as I spread each slice with the sauce before going in the oven. Anyway, I will do this recipe again. The ham/sauce is wonderful. Thank you!

name: creamy potato salad
review: I made this for work pot luck...we'll see what kind of reviews I get!  Didn't have bacon but added carrots and green pepper (chopped fine) as I like the color and the extra veg.  Looking forward to the feedback from the work crew - will post !  Thanks!

name: basic batter waffles
review: I LOVE that these waffles don't have you beating egg whites separately and that the batter can be mixed up and ready in under 5 minutes.  That said, we didn't find these very tender at all, and rather flavorless for our tastes.  The flavor can be fixed easily enough, but I'm not sure I can do much about the tenderness...I think I'll keep looking for a good, quick waffle recipe.

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: Very good.  In lieu of chili sauce and chile powder I used Siracha sauce. Sweet, tangy, and spicy made for a fabulous sauce. The only issue was the fat left in the sauce.  Next time will make ahead, chill to remove fat off the top, and then reheat.  Did that with leftovers and with that change easily 5  stars!

name: meatloaf barbecue style
review: Oh wow!  Finally I have found a successful and delicious meatloaf recipe!   I actually made small individual loaves in October and froze them.   I cooked one loaf a couple of nights ago and I have fallen in love!  I placed the small loaf in a baking dish, surrounded by sliced potatoes and onions (which I microwaved for a few minutes to give them a head start), spooned the sauce over the top of the loaf and cooked it all for about 45 minutes.  Absolutely a wonderful result, so moist and tender and the flavor is to die for, great comfort food.   I will certainly keep some in my freezer from now on.  Thanks for a keeper Bev!

name: tsr version of olive garden pasta e fagioli by todd wilbur
review: I made this recipe as stated except that I put a 46oz bottle of V-8. I also rinsed the noodles of all the starch before adding to the pot. This was a really delicious soup that I will be making again! Thank you for posting!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: I love this easy, no-fail pie crust and will not use any other.  Thank you for sharing the recipe.

name: easy garlic rice
review: It was good, but I thought it needed more flavor--I can't afford Thyme prices--probably would have made all the difference.  I'll have to follow sweetp's suggestions next time; they look like some good ideas.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: These are very good.  My DH thought they were marvelous.  Will be using this recipe a lot.  Thanks for posting.

name: cajun style oven fries
review: Good mix of seasonings. I omitted the cayenne since some of my family don't like spicy. I think I might cut them a bit thicker next time so they don't burn.

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: This does make a lot. It just fit in my crock pot. I never tasted Olive Garden's. I did freeze half of the batch. Next time, I will add the pasta separately. The pasta got soggy after it was frozen and thawed, otherwise it was delicious. I followed the recipe. Thanks ravensmith for sharing

name: chili s salsa
review: I just realized I haven't reviewed this. I've been using this for the past year at least. It's so nice that you can usually have all the ingredients on hand, except maybe the jalapeno.  The taste is surprisingly fresh with the use of canned tomatoes.  It only literally takes minutes to make, so you can whip it up in no time.  Great recipe.

name: big grandma s best peanut butter cookies
review: Wonderful peanut butter cookies.  I rolled in cinnamon/sugar mix and they were the best tasting peanut butter cookies I have ever tasted!!  Thanks for the recipe.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Made for Christmas this year, my recipe called for 400 degree oven for 8 minutes. Great tasting, look forward to them every year!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: I don't bake much because #1 hubby is diabetic and #2 high altitude adjustments are a pain.  However, I had some very ripe bananas that I needed to use up, so I gave this a try.  I did use xylitol instead of the white sugar to keep the carbs down, but stuck with the real brown sugar (a lot of that fell off the muffins anyway.)  I also doubled the cinnamon, which was just right in my opinion.  They turned out perfect and were so yummy, I'm putting these in my "favorites" folder.  They would be great even without the topping, I think.

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: Family inhaled this!  Everyone raved.  I found it easy to prepare and with great results.  What's not to love?!

name: copycat ihop harvest grain   nut pancakes
review: My batter was quite thin, even after allowing it to sit 15 minutes to allow the Oats to absorb some of the milk.  The next time, I think I'd cut the oil to 2 T. - that would help with the consistency and lower the fat content.

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: What a wonderful dish! I made it as described except I added 2 chicken breasts and 1 large local sweet onion because that's what I had on hand. I also used the saffron & skipped the optional cayenne. It was so good I was happy that we had last minute company over to enjoy it too. Will definitely make again, thanks so much French Tart! I served with garlic butter couscous (2 cups dry   4 cups water).

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: Delicious!! I subbed one third cup of the oatmeal with fine chopped coconut because I love the coconut / cranberry combination. It worked perfectly, what a great tasting cookie!

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: Excellent recipe.  I added the sauce after the crescents were cooked as I didn't want them to be soggy.  Otherwise, everything else was good as is.

name: awesome homemade crusty bread  bread machine
review: I made this today, 12/16/12 for the " Let's P-A-R-T-Y 2011 " Event. I let my bread machine do the hard work,( dough cycle )  formed into a loaf shape and placed it in a greased loaf pan.Then covered, and left to rise in a warm place for 1 hour. The loaf was baked at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. I forgot it was supposed to be a crusty loaf, and buttered the loaf as soon as it came out of the oven.And I couldn't wait for it cool off, so I cut off a small slice and buttered it. Then bit into sheer delight. The bread tastes just wonderful and thank you so much for posting. " Keep Smiling :) "

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: I made this recipe on the stovetop & actually skipped the whole pureeing step altogether. I did not have liquid smoke, but did have a smoked ham hock. I debated back and forth about adding it to the pot and I'm glad that I finally did put it in. Wow, everyone raved about it. The baby ate it, my 6 year old loved it and my hubby said to save the recipe! We finished it with a bit of sour cream which really complimented it nicely. My 6 year old also "scooped" hers with corn chips. The only other addition to the original recipe is that I added a leftover mashed up baked sweet potato & 1/2 cup quick cooking barley to the pot about 10 minutes before it was ready to serve and I simmered it for at least an hour prior to that. (I mostly did this because I only had 2 cans of black beans and 1 can dark kidney beans, this made up for at least one can of beans). Thanks for sharing, it was a great one dish meal on a cold night, served with cornbread.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: An easy and versatile step-up from traditional tuna noodle casserole.  Like other reviewers, I left out green peppers and celery and added mixed vegetables instead.  Thanks, Kittencal, for making dinner tasty and a snap.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: I made this for a work breakfast buffet this morning. Super easy to make! The topping was very tasty:)

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: I made this to  use up some veggies. It was easy and yummy!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: My husband is the fish eater in the family and he liked this. It was really easy to put together and everyone liked it.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: This recipe was made on 12/18/11 for the " Let's P-A-R-T-Y 2011 "Event and most importantly mine and my SO's dinner.I only had about 1 1/2 lbs. of red potatoes on hand,but used the full amount of oil and onion soup mix. For the amount of cheese 1/3 cup was used along with a generous amount of black pepper.Both my SO and I found the taste went very well with the steaks we had.Thanks for posting a recipe that will be made again and, " Keep Smiling :) "

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: My DH and I have decided this is officially our favorite baked Mac and cheese.  The first time we added 1/2 t of mustard powder and garlic powder and used Cheddar Jack cheese. This macaroni was a nice, thick consistency with an amazing taste. ****Update: We made again and used White Wisconsin Cheddar cheese from Trader Joe's and added green onions.  We topped with 3/4 C crushed up Ritz crackers instead of buttered breadcrumbs (Yumm!!) and upped the salt to 1t.  We didn't even need to add the mustard pwdr and garlic pwdr this time b/c it was perfect just the way it was.  We definitely like our updated version even better than the first!!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Excellent lasagna!!! I used Italian style diced tomatoes and the cottage cheese option. The sauce was a little thick so I added more water. I also added spinach to the cheese mixture. All my guests raved about how good this was. Thanks so much for sharing this true keeper.

name: amish white bread
review: Fantastic! I made this recipe for soup and sandwich night and I couldn't be happier with the result. This is a keeper recipe for sure. Thanks for posting.

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: These were really good. I would add the cinnamon to the muffins next time.

name: super peanut butter filled brownies
review: Please allow me to add my praises for this wonderfully delicious and moist brownie recipe.  Made a single batch for 4 adults coming to visit, should have doubled it as the brownies disappeared from the plate so fast and received nothing but raves from all.  Will be making these often during this holiday season.  Thank You for sharing this wonderful recipe it is greatly appreciated.

name: gingerbread  for cookies or a  gingerbread house
review: Made one batch last night and another one already today.  Made 3 houses and tons of various cookies.  I used only about 3 cups of flour per batch.  This is my first attempt at a homemade gingerbread house, and I see no need to look for another recipe.  This is perfect.  Now, time to decorate!

name: parmesan zucchini
review: I rolled the zucchini in the olive oil before sprinkling with rosemary garlic seasoning and topping with parm.  Turned out fantastic.

name: good eats roast turkey
review: Easier than it sounds. I have made my last couple turkey's this way. It cooks faster and is super moist!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: These were very good.Moist and tender. However I did make some changes to suit our needs. I use low sodium Tamari Sauce. Added grated ginger, garlic and some "Rooster sauce.I marinated them for a few hours as well. I served it with stir fried Bok Choy.Thanks for sharing.

name: sweet salsa dump chicken   oamc
review: This was yummy. My husband thought that it was a little to sweet but I thought it was really spicy.Lol it was really nice to have it in the freeze!

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: Made for Let's PARTY 2011 and we did party with this recipe...so delicious!  I did use only about 1/2 cup mayonnaise (all I had) and added fresh garlic, onion and some hot sauce to it.  Another wonderful recipe to put into my cookbook of Favorites for 2011.  Thank you for posting.

name: christmas rum balls or bourbon balls
review: I have made these to go with my Christmas gifts this year.They are very easy to make.My boyfriend loved them.I found them a little too strong for my taste,perhaps because I'm not a big rum drinker.

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: This was very good and fast, but I had an issue with the filling. Even after chilling for 45 minutes it was quite soft still. Hubby says he loves it anyways!

name: dark chocolate cake
review: A good, moist chocolate cake. Not so sweet. Not stunning, but good.

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review:
Like it needs another 5 star review, but they are great and went over very well at the Christmas Party I brought them too. Super easy to make - I brought them un-cut, and cut them when we got there since it was a 2 hour drive.
Thanks Karen!

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: Perfect Gingerbread recipe!  I didn't have molasses or lemon, but I did have lemon honey and it worked great!  Otherwise I followed the recipe exact and everything was spot on.  Baked for 7 minutes and got delicious soft cookies.  I had no problems with the spice ratio or with the texture.  I used a Kitchenaid, as suggested, left out on the counter for a few hours, and then refrigerated for a couple days.  Brought back to room temperature before rolling and needed no flour at all.  Very easy to work with...looking forward to using this for years to come.  Thanks!

name: kim s sweet potato casserole
review: We loved this recipe! It has less sugar in the sweet potato part, and you can use more or less of the topping as you please. Thanks!

name: cream cheese cinnamon crescents
review: I liked the fact that it was easy and quick to put together.  I didn't so much care for this but my son loved it. I was expecting something similar to a Danish. I think that if I make it again I am going to try about half of the cream cheese mixture and less butter and follow some of the other reviewers additions.

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: Great Recipe!  Made these cookies yesterday for the grandchildren and they make a really big batch.  So much easier than having to make pan after pan of cookies.  I baked these at 350 vs. 375 and they were still done in about 20 minutes.  Thanks for the great post!

name: cheesecake factory carrot cake cheesecake
review: This was sooo good! Too bad I underbaked it so a huge chunk of it wasn't edible. Make sure you really cook it through! I didn't even put coconut, nuts and the frosting in but it tasted great (at least the edges where it was cooked :))

name: yummy baked potato skins
review: These were just wonderful and so full of flavor because of the vegetable oil combination.  I baked at 450 and so glad I did as they were very toasted for the stated baking time.  I lost the cheese from inside when I turned them over to bake the second 8 minutes, but not sure that mattered. Loved the bacon and cheddar cheese and I added the optional green onions and DH added the optional sour cream.  Will be making these again.  Thanks for sharing.  Made for "Let's Party 2011"

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: Another great recipe, Kitten! No anchovies for us and I since I don't have a food processor (gasp!), I used a bowl and whisk with not problem. Even with just one hour resting time, the taste was superb. I used Low-Fat Hellmans, too.

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: I was really hoping for something more with this sauce. It was not what my taste buds were looking for. It was worth a try though since it had so many high reviews; however, I won't be making it again.

name: awesome baked ham
review: Excellent way to cook ham. I made as written but cooked it at 325*. Everyone raved about how tender and juicy it was. This will be my go-to recipe from now on. Thanks for sharing a true keeper.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: My computer sent my review before I was ready. These were great even though I screwed up just about every step. Can't wait to try again and do everything right! I overdid the microwave rising so was done at that point. Still worked well. Mixed butter and brown sugar/cinnamon like struesel.  Didn't have any cream cheese. Still fabulous.

name: breakfast casserole supreme
review: This came out pretty good. I'm not sure I liked the soft potatoes. I would have liked them to be a little crispy. Also,I think I would leave the tomato out next time. They were a little watery. I loved the ease of this dish and I think you could easily mix it up depending on your own tastes. Thanks for posting this recipe. I'm looking forward to making again.

name: tiny cinnamon rolls
review: I made a double batch of these Christmas morning and my family loved them!  Quick and easy when you don't have time to make from scratch; this semi-homemade version is definitely better than the canned or frozen variety!  This will be our new Christmas morning treat!

name: opal s pumpkin pie
review: This pie is excellent - perfect blend of spice/sweet/creaminess.  The only change I made was to bake it at 425 degrees for 15 minutes then lower the temperature to 350 degrees and bake for another 50 minutes.  At first I was skeptical about the amount of cinnamon, but after eating a piece I found the amount to be perfect.

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: This recipe turned out great for us.  Adjusted a few things slightly, cut back the pasta to 5 1/2 oz & abit on the milk.  Increased the beef & garlic. Sub'd 1/2 of the tomato sauce with a homemade pasta sauce I had on hand.  I was using jalapeno pepper cheese for the monterey so I cut back the chili powder abit.  The cheese browned up nicely on top & the balance of pasta vs beef/vegys was perfect for us, thanks for sharing.

name: breakfast casserole supreme
review: This was just okay for me.  I sprinkled salt and pepper on the potatoes and on the eggs and I still thought it needed more and lacked flavor.  We did find that it was a little better the next day.  I think I will be looking for a different breakfast casserole recipe.

name: unknownchef86 s very best dinner rolls
review: I followed your recipe exactly and the result was some fantastic rolls! They took a little longer in my oven. The flavor was perfect and the texture was perfect - soft and light. Everyone loved them, and I will make them often. Thanks for sharing a great recipe.

name: chocolate mint candy  fudge
review: This was sooooooooooo easy to make.  The mint tasted like York Pattys!  Made the Orange and the Raspberry....

name: opal s pumpkin pie
review: This pie is divine. The filling comes out moist and soft like a custard, so good. Only change was to use only 1/3 cup of each sugar (instead of 1/2 cup of each) for a half recipe/single pie. Pulled from the oven at 54 minutes. Thank you. ETA 12/26/11: I've made this pie 3 times now. I've found the crust turns out perfect for homemade pie dough if you refrigerate the pie plate with the rolled dough in it before baking. I put the pie plate in the fridge while I make the filling.

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: Made this gravy using turkey dripping from our Jack Daniels injected turkey. The flavor was wonderful! Thank you, Kittencal.

name: awesome baked ham
review: My husband, guests, and I think this recipe is off the charts -great:)  Recently made with 12 pounder and baked for 2 hours and 50 minutes with one hour of down time and made with 1/3 batch of glaze.

name: puppy chow or monkey munch
review: Ok, I haven't actually made this, but I have devoured it!  My sister included some in a goodie tray she gave my family for Christmas.  These are so yummy and delicious!  I can't wait to try making it myself!

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: Amazing!!  This produced the most wonderful, tender, perfectly sweet cookies I've ever had.  Made these for DH as part of Christmas dinner as his Grammy always makes sugar cookies for family dinners and we are 5000 miles away this year.  He absolutely loved them!  And he says the frosting is perfect :)

name: hello dollies
review: These are awesome. I made them ahead as part of my Christmas baskets, they froze great (I only froze them for about a week), they were so easy to make, and they tasted great! I used 6 Tablespoons of butter and mixed it with the graham crackers for the crust. Also, I used finely chopped pecans. I used a store brand of sweetened condensed milk, and it worked fine (not too runny or anything). I doubled this recipe and used an 8x8 pan for one batch and a 9x9 pan for the other, and I think I prefer the 9x9 pan - that seems perfect. Thank you, I will definitely keep this recipe!

name: new york style pizza crust
review: So, so good and so so easy to make.  This made a perfect 14" thin crust pizza.  I used it to make recipe #368535 so added additional flavors to it, but the end result was just perfect.  I'll make this one again.  Thanks.  Made for "Let's Party 2011"

name: kittencal s greek moussaka
review: I had only made the Craig Claiborne version (from the New York Times cookbook)---rave reviews, but WOW was it complicated!  This version tastes even better, and is far, far simpler to assemble.  KC, another winner!

name: southern fried chicken
review: we loved this! Double dipped was perfect. Triple dipped too much. Used a deep fryer at 350 for 6-8 min depending on size of chicken tenderloin. Not spicy at all. Just delicious!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Oh.  My.  Goodness.  This is by far the most amazing macaroni and cheese I've ever tasted.  Wonderfully creamy, decadently rich, beautiful sharp cheddar flavor.  And really not so terribly difficult to make.  Reheats beautifully in the oven.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Made this spread for garlic bread on Christmas Day.  It had the perfect combination of flavors.  Thanks for posting!

name: opal s pumpkin pie
review: This was great! Everyone commented on how flavorful it was!

name: awesome baked ham
review: I practically live for Christmas just for the baked ham.  And this recipe certainly didn't disappoint.  Moist and flavorful and oh-so-yummy.  This will definitely be my go to recipe for ham from now on.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: I was looking for a lasagna recipe that I had made before.  I forgot to save it and couldn't find it in all the lasagna recipes on here. After spending way too much time searching, I decided to make this one instead because of it's rave reviews.  While everyone thought it was good, no one went back for seconds.  It worked in a bind though.  Thanks.

name: real southern cornbread
review: This is a relly great, not too sweet cornbread! I loved the crunchy top it makes and the directions were great! Used an Enameled 10in cast iron pan i have and it worked out fine. Thanks for posting!

name: crock pot ham and beans
review: I made this exactly as written and it was absolutley Delicious! I was afraid because of someone else's review that the cloves would be too strong, but I loved the flavor it gives to this! I cooked mine the day before and rewarmed in the crockpot the next day, so good! Thanks for posting!!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: The flavors in this are awesome, but I had some trouble making sense of the directions and my coating all fell off of the steak. I wish I would have seen Bento or Bust's suggestion in the reviews first. I'll try again with those changes.

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: Made this for Christmas Eve dessert. Intense chocolate flavor and very easy to make. I'll always prefer cake made from scratch, but this is a very good alternative when you don't have the time. Thanks for posting.

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: This was great, but I was a little bummed when I read the ingredient list on the can of Swanson's veg broth after pouring it in and realized there's MSG and high fructose corn syrup in it. I am usually so anal about avoiding those two things. Oh well. The soup is good. Next time I'll make it with different veggie stock and try adding red wine. Tasted like Olive Garden, but I think wine would give it more nice depth like others suggested. Thanks!

name: kittencal s  brown sugar caramel sauce or ice cream topping
review: The biggest temptation with this sauce is to stand at the stove and eat it with a spoon before you use for anything else!  Thanks, Carole!

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: This was the first time trying anything like this before. I really loved it, but my husband said "it wasn't his thing." Owell, I froze it in portions and it was even better out of the freezer warmed up! I did make a mistake and instead of looking for the Harissa at the Specialty store i bought a jar of Tagine...well maybe next time i will try this with the Harissa. Thanks for posting!

name: cream cheese cinnamon crescents
review: We thought this was way too sugary and crunchy on top, and we also didn't like that the cresents seemed to be too soggy with the abundancy of cream cheese. Maybe with some changes we might like this, but just wasn't something I'd make again as is. Obviously everyone else seems to love it thought! Thanks for the post!

name: nutella hot chocolate
review: This is great.  It's so creamy with the nutella.  The taste of the hazelnuts from the nutella comes out.  Thanks GoKittenGo :)  Made for Holiday tag game

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: Loved this!  I reduced the sour cream to 1/2 C per reviews and it was great.  I also reduced the green onions by about half as that was all I had on hand.  Excellent recipe, will definitely make again. Thank you.

name: whole wheat honey banana muffins
review: Yummy! Followed recipe exactly..used half olive oil and half honey. Oh and threw in 1/4c of mini semi-sweet morsels. I've already eaten two of these...will freeze the remaining muffins for the kids for breakfasts on the run. Thanks for sharing!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: This was pretty good. I used about 2.5 lbs of pork, and adjusted the other ingredients accordingly. I only cooked it for 9 hours on LOW and 2 hours on HIGH, and it turned out just fine. I'll definitely make this again. Thanks for the recipe.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: Super good, considering DH and I don't care for salmon. We were given some high quality salmon from a friend who just came back from Alaska. Its such a healthy food and DH and I have really wanted to learn to like it. Your recipe is the closest we've come to loving salmon. Thanks for posting!

name: double chocolate banana muffins
review: These are simply amazing. Moist and chocolaty. I only had 2 bananas, so I didn't have quite the 1 1/3 cups. I made up the difference with sour cream. It worked wonderfully. I set aside some of the chocolate chips to sprinkle on top before baking. Gorgeous and delicious!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Enjoyed these potatoes and easy to do!! Used extra garlic of course

name: queso blanco dip
review: I could not find the white American cheese at my Walmart deli, and so settled on using monterey jack cheese. It is true that it did not melt well and was very clumpy and not at all smooth. However it still did taste good, and everyone did still eat it. I only used half the amount of the canned chilies, and it was the perfect amount for us.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: Mmmmm, such a great comfort soup, plus a great way to use up those holiday leftovers! Took me a bit longer than 30 minutes from start to finish... but maybe I was slow :)

name: crabs   garlic butter baked crab legs
review: Made this for New Years Eve 2011 and holy cow these are easy and soooooo very good!!  Did exactly as you wrote it and wouldn't change a thing!   That garlic butter is the BOMB!!!  Thank you sooo much for posting this keeper!

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: These were yummalicous!!!!! I love pancakes, and I was craving them, and no mix in the house. I will NEVER, EVER buy a box of pancake mix AGAIN. I made the whole batch. I ate 2 pancakes, and froze the rest. I will let you know how they heat up in the microwave. I now have pancakes for quick breakfasts. Thanks Nimz for this wonderful and easy recipe.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: This recipe is fantastic!!!  I made as directed and doubled the recipe.  The sun dried tomatoes are a very tasty addition.
