review: These are so tender and flavorful.  I didn't add the sauce until about an hour left of cooking.  I drained the grease out and poured the bbq sauce over.  These are great.  Thank you so much for sharing this with us, we loved it.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Everyone, but Simi, enjoyed the flavor of this chicken. The only complaint Monkey had was that I used thighs and not breasts. The only change I made was to add a few extra cloves of garlic and to let the chicken marinade for a couple of hours. The chicken came out very moist and flavorful and will be made again.

name: garlic beef enchiladas
review:
Great enchiladas. I did add black beans and salsa verde that I had open but these were great.
Used hardly any cheese but may add more next time. I made half the filling but all of the sauce so that I can do it quicker next time.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: I had high hopes for this recipe, given the long list of positive reviews, but this recipe just did not turn out for me.  The brownies were quite flat and dry in the middle, and they lacked much chocolatey-cocoa taste (and I used Girardelli premium cocoa that I've used for all my other brownie recipes with great success, so I don't think it was that).  I thought maybe it was something I had done wrong, so I made it a second time with the same result.  So I don't think I'll be making these brownies again.

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: Well, let me hop on the bandwagon and say I'm so glad you decided to share this wonderful recipe.  I made this exactly as posted (down to the Sweet Baby Ray's barbecue sauce).  This really takes no time at all to prepare and then you just put it in the oven and forget about it.  They definitely come out better than when I cook them on the grill.  Thanks for sharing this great recipe that can be enjoyed year-round.

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: These were OK for us. I followed the recipe as written other then I doubled the recipe except only made the original amount of topping. I have never put a topping on my muffins so I'm not sure if I did something wrong but like another reviewer, my toppings melted into my muffins. The topping for us was really sweet too. My muffins tasted good out of the oven but really dried out once they sat.

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: Very nice stir-fry recipe!  The sauce made the chicken quite tasty but got a little thick and clumpy after cooking.  I would probably use less cornstarch next time.  Thanks for sharing your recipe!  Made for the Best of 2011 event, recommended by Lavender Lynn

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: I tried it and this was great!  Easy and delicious.  I halfed the recipe except for the vanilla!  Delish!! Thanks for posting.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review:
Definitely five stars! This is the perfect pizza sauce. The fennel is the secret ingredient I have been searching for ages! Thanks so much for sharing this :)
Made for Healthy Hearts Find The Tags / Diabetic Forum.

name: kittencal s scalloped potato and ground beef casserole
review: Very good.  I made 1/2 the recipe as directed. DH had 4 helpings. The dish had great flavor.

name: best pumpkin cookies
review: OMG these are the best cookies.  I made these for my family this afternoon and we all loved them.  They are such moist and soft cookies, and the penuche glaze was to die for.  Yes the glaze is really sweet but it really make the cookie.  DH came home and said a buddies mom use to make these for them when they were younger as he was grabbing another cookie.  Thank you so much for this awesome cookies.

name: mashed sweet potatoes
review: These were so easy and delicious. I'm trying to incorporate more sweet potatoes into our menus since they are so good for you. For some reason, my potatoes came out a little watery, so I might decrease the amount of cream or butter next time.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: Excellent recipe as the numerous ratings show.  I added a pinch of ground red pepper and used 2/3 of a cup of hot coffee instead of water.    I baked them in tiny silicone muffin cups topping them with a dollop of Decorator Buttercream Icing.  They took only 15 minutes to bake and were a wonderful bite sized treat!

name: quick butternut squash soup
review: Very good and super easy. Used 2 lbs of diced, peeled organic butternut squash from Costco so this came together in no time. Fresh ground pepper makes a big difference in such a simple recipe. Added about a cup of chicken broth. Ate some right away and froze the rest in individual servings. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Delicious!

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: I made this soup, only adding some ground turkey to it. ( I know it doesn't make it 0 pts.) but my family eats it better with some meat.  It was really good.  I will continue to make, thankyou for sharing.

name: cherry pie filling bread
review: Really pretty colour, nice & moist old-fashioned quick bread!  Quite easy to make.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Easy to make, very tasty, nice and moist!  I don't eat frozen meatballs.  These I'll eat!  We used turkey, pork, and beef.  We plan to use these tonight in Kittencal's Appetizer Grape Jelly and Chili Sauce Meatballs or Lil Smokies.  That is, if there are any left.......

name: beef roast
review: Wow this was really good. I followed the recipe as written and we all loved it. I cooked mine for five hours at 300.It was so tendy and tasty. It smelled wonderful cooking. The gravy was wonderful too. I had made fried potatoes and we even dipped the potatoes in the gravy. We will be making again and again.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: Great cinnamon rolls! Made in the bread maker.  I think I make my rolls too small b/c I always get a lot more servings than listed. They also take a LOT more than 10 minutes to bake. Delicious, though! Thanks for posting!

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: This was good. Kids and husband thought it was really good. Myself, I'm not crazy about canned cream soups. I think next time I will use homemade cream of soup mix with much less salt and probably a little more savory spices.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: These are very good and they reheat nicely.  After they were uncovered the oven temperature was bumped up to about 425 degrees.  I used recipe #89857 for the onion soup.  I made half the recipe for the 2 of us and had enough leftovers that we enjoyed them warmed in the toaster oven for breakfast this morning.

name: lisa s swirled chocolate chip cookies
review:
The Perfect Chocolate Chip Cookie.

Hands down.

Delicious dough. Delicious cookie. Bakes up thick and delicious. THIS is what chocolate chip cookies are made of.

name: perfect rump roast
review: Really great recipe! I wasn't sure how much my roast weighed because it came from a cowshare. I cooked it for 1 hour and 20 minutes and it was perfect. I used red wine and added a little beef bouillion with the onions to make a fantastic gravy. At first we sliced the beef too thick, and then it was tough, but once we got the knack of slicing it thin it was perfect. Beautiful color and flavor. Thanks so much, this recipe is solid gold!

name: orange julius smoothies
review: i love this drink . i used powdered  milk and can use a banana also

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Boneless, skinless chicken thighs were used and cutting the cooking time to about 45 minutes.  The sesame oil and honey were both reduced somewhat.  After the chicken came out moist and tender, the sauce was placed in a pan on top of the stove and a touch of cornstarch added to thicken.  The thickened sauce was spooned over the chicken and then it was sprinkled lightly with sesame seeds.  I will be making this one again.

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: Totally agree that these are the World's Best Chocolcate Chip Cookies !  I made a batch yesterday and loved every single one that I ate.....probably way too many !  Managed to give some to my son and wife and watched as hubby gobbled them down.....I will definitely make this recipe again as I didn't change a thing.  I added the walnuts but might try without them next time.  Thanks for a real keeper!

name: allrighty then scrambled eggs   paula deen
review: Very good and creamy. I could taste the sour cream but it tasted good, like it belonged there. I used shredded Colby Jack cheese as that's all I had on hand. These were so light and fluffy. From now on I'll make a omelet out of this so the cheese doesn't melt all over the pan and stick. Made for I Recommend game.

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: Excellent! The only issue I had was that the sauce didn't caramelize even though I increased the temperature to 450 for the last 10 mins

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: (1/20/2009)This wonderfully flavorful soup can be put together in a matter of minutes.  I made as directed using 6 cups of reduced sodium chicken broth, about 1 cup of chopped onion, 1 (29 0z) can of whole tomatoes and   sausage with cheese fresh tortellini which added a lot of flavor.  This is a great recipe if you have little time to spend preparing supper.  I served with a crispy crust French bread with butter.  Thank you for posting, spatchcock! (Updated 2/13/2012) I continue making this soup.  Now I am using all organic vegetable broth and replacing the tortellini with mini spinach tortellini filled with sun-dried tomato. Super-good!!

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Oh...my...  good...  heavens...  This is amazing!!!  Fantastic flavour, meat is so moist & the coating is nice & crunchy!!  As I was adding all the garlicky ingredients, I was thinking there was no way my hubby was going to like it but he did, too!!

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: Good soup. It came together quickly.

name: soft italian breadsticks  abm
review: These are FANTASTIC!  I made them last night for our Italian dinner and we loved them.  My niece and nephew came over and they ate about 3 apiece.  Thank you for this great new food item we will make often.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: I took some of these over to my in-laws and some to work and they were a big hit with everyone.  The muffins were soft, moist and delicious.  I know what I will be doing with my overly ripe bananas from now on.  Made for February 2012 Cooking from the Pantry Challenge Game.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I made these over at my in-law's house and everyone loved them.  So easy to throw together.  I really enjoyed the taste of the lemon, garlic and oregano.  The potatoes turned out tender on the inside and slightly crispy on the outside.  Perfect!  Made for February 2012 Cooking from the Pantry Challenge Game.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: I made these over at my in-law's house and everyone loved it.  They all gave it a unanimous 5 star vote.  Very easy to make with items I always have on hand.  The pork chops were tender and the sauce was delicious.  Made for February 2012 Cooking from the Pantry Challenge Game.

name: low carb pizza
review: This is a great idea.  I made this for my family last night and we enjoyed it.  I will make again.  thank you for sharing.

name: salmon and asparagus in foil
review: I made this as directed except for adding a pat of butter to each packet. The salmon and the asparagus came out nicely cooked. Great simple recipe. I will be making this again.

name: fresh strawberry cake
review: We made this for our Valentines Day dessert.  I made the cakes in a heart shape pan and then in between the layers I put a cream cheese frosting, then I poured the strawberry glaze over the top.  Delicious.  Thank you for a great dessert.

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: This made a simple and satisfying ending to a rich Valentine's Dinner.  I just lightly dusted this with some powdered sugar and served with some fresh whipped cream.  It tasted restaurant-worthy!  It is a very moist cake and I found I really had to scrape with a spatula to lift it out of the pan without leaving cake behind.  It couldn't be easier too!

name: english muffins  bread machine method
review: These are fantastic.  The dough was very easy to work with, I just used a large glass to cut the circles which worked perfectly.  I left mine to rise for about 40 minutes after being cut on a piece of parchement.  Next time I will make sure they are off my cold granite countertop, and maybe ontop of a cookie sheet in the oven.  Thanks for posting!

name: the best ever waffles
review: The title of this recipe is no mere claim.  It is purest fact.  These waffles are absolutely positively amazing!!  Perfectly crisp on the outside, moist and full of flavor on the inside, and incredibly light.  I made them using buttermilk, but otherwise made as written using a Belgian waffler...  Heaven on a plate!

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: Very good.  Quick and easy.  Thanks for posting.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: wonderful.  I love baking chicken!  Just stick it in the oven & do whatever while it cooks without need of constant supervision!

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: Super awesome, incredibly easy, ultra flavorful.  YUMMY.  Thanks for posting.  These were the "Surf" in my "Surf and Turf" special family Valentine's Day dinner.  We'll be having these again.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: I tried it and this was fantastic! I made exactly as directed except used chicken instead of beef.  Served over brown rice - delish! It's a keeper! Thanks for posting.

name: perfect southern fried chicken
review: This is wonderfully dangerous stuff!  It produces the loveliest crispiest coating and moistest and most flavorful meat!  I used a bit of buttermilk with salt and some spices to brine in place of the water and used only drumsticks as they were on sale, but otherwise made as written for some of the tastiest fried chicken in the history of forever!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Let me voice my one objection first before I go on to praise this excellent recipe.  I doubled it but only included slightly over 2 lbs. of meat.  We like our sauce thick and meaty, but 3 lbs. would have been overkill.  I can't even fathom 4!  Other than that, the seasonings were excellent, and it was enjoyed by all.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Awesome pancakes, great texture and taste great, will be my "go to" buttermilk pancake recipe from now on. Thanks for posting!

name: paula deen crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: I won't be giving up my regular macaroni recipe, but this was SO handy to have ready when we got back from swimming tonight.  Three minutes after walking in the door, the kids were eating.  Two out of the 3 really liked it, and the third (who believes only in Velveeta) was willing to eat it if it meant she got a cupcake.  Made according to the recipe except I couldn't find ground mustard in the cabinet so I used brown mustard.  You could definitely taste the mustard, so keep that in mind.  Not all of the shredded cheddar melted nicely, so I will consider using a chunk of velveeta next time, but most of it melted just fine.  I also didn't have time to do it all on the stove top, so I started it melting in the microwave, then just stirred it all together and called it good.  I used 3 cups of macaroni, so I had one serving leftover.  It wasn't as creamy as I was hoping, but it really didn't take any more time to put together than a box of mac and cheese, and yet was so much more real, so I'll keep it in mind.  I also liked how it was a crock pot meal, but it didn't take all day to cook it.  I frequently don't figure out dinner until mid afternoon, so this really worked for me.

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: What a great combination!   It's basically artichoke dip baked over chicken, so if you love artichoke dip, you'll love this.  I doubled the (fresh) minced garlic and used skinless boneless chicken thighs in place of breasts.   This is a winner.  Thanx!

name: slow cooker macaroni   cheese
review: I won't be giving up my regular macaroni recipe, but this was SO handy to have ready when we got back from swimming tonight.  Three minutes after walking in the door, the kids were eating.  Two out of the 3 really liked it, and the third (who believes only in Velveeta) was willing to eat it if it meant she got a cupcake.  Made according to the recipe except I couldn't find ground mustard in the cabinet so I used brown mustard.  You could definitely taste the mustard, so keep that in mind.  Not all of the shredded cheddar melted nicely, so I will consider using a chunk of velveeta next time, but most of it melted just fine.  I also didn't have time to do it all on the stove top, so I started it melting in the microwave, then just stirred it all together and called it good.  I used 3 cups of macaroni, so I had one serving leftover.  It wasn't as creamy as I was hoping, but it really didn't take any more time to put together than a box of mac and cheese, and yet was so much more real, so I'll keep it in mind.  I also liked how it was a crock pot meal, but it didn't take all day to cook it.  I frequently don't figure out dinner until mid afternoon, so this really worked for me.

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: I made this dish last night using chicken pieces.  My family enjoyed this and I will continue to make this.  I think next time (if using pieces) I will let the chicken roast for the first 20 minutes without the vinegar, then drain the grease from the skin, and then pour the vinegar on for a more stronger vinegar flavor.  Anyway, we loved it and will include this recipe in our rotation.  Delicious.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: basic machine french bread
review: This made a great, basic loaf of bread!  I used 3 cups whole wheat, 1 cup white flour.  I set my bread maker to whole wheat - light setting and removed it about 15 minutes before the timer.  Perfect for sandwiches.  Update:  I made this today with 1/2 whole wheat and 1/2 regular flour.. what a difference from my first attempts at this bread!  With 3 cups of whole wheat, the bread alway sunk, what a difference with the extra cup of white flour.  Also I set my bread machine on medium crust.

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: I made this recipe as a thank you gift for an office. I used sour milk that I had on hand for some bread recipes and I grated 2 gala apples with a cheese grater right into the batter. It was so simple to do and make large amounts. This made 20 regular size muffins. I did add a little more flour to the topping to make it very crumbly. I think it is because we are at high altitude. Everyone who ate them stated they were very moist and very good. Next time I prepare and there will be a next time, I will use vinegar in milk, or lemon juice in milk as a substitute for buttermilk. This recipe is fantastic!

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: I tried it and it was delicious!! I made it exactly as is.  I love the amount heat and will increase the amount of curry next time.  I didn't top with yogurt or cilantro - personal taste. But it's definitely a keeper! Thanks for posting!

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: Easy to assemble, and tasted great as written. I think the servings are a little off, we got more like 4 main dish servings. Great with sour cream and chips.

name: chinese pot stickers
review: All I can say is YUM-O!!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Well I didn't realize how popular this recipe is, until I tagged it in PRMR Tag Game and went to review it!!!!  I made this for my lunch, so scaled it back for one.  I wasn't serving this with pasta, so I did add some marinara sauce and then topped it with some mozzarella, which I know would up the points/calories, but it was so good.  I too, used fresh shredded parmesan in place of the grated Kraft kind.  I had this with some carrot sticks, as I knew I was also going to meet my DS at the movie theater and knew I would be eating buttered popcorn and this would help keep my calories to where they should be.  Thanks for sharing a great lo-cal recipe Lainey!!!

name: crispy tilapia
review: This is so good.  Our whole family loved this.  My 4 year old nephew is living with us right now and he ate his entire filet!  (thats a big deal, as he eats like a bird).  I will most definately make these again, they were so good, and easy too!  Thank you so much for sharing this with us, we loved it.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Rated this 5 stars in 2006 with a good review but not a review of justice. I have returned to this recipe many times and double it to freeze. Freezes wonderfully! Today  I will be sharing the recipe with my daughter-n-law. Why should I take all the glory! lol My youngest son had some spaghetti the other day from somewhere else and said "how can I eat this when I have had the best, yours!" and he stopped eating. Thank you so much for making me look good! Love it and love you for sharing! <3

name: pork chops yum yum
review:
I KNEW this would be amazing.

I doubled the sauce and cut my chops into bite-sized pieces. Covered the casserole dish. Came out perfect - beyond perfect.

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: The sauce was terrific. I didn't have any pineapple juice but I don't think it needed it. It was a little bit too hot for me so next time I'll just use a dash of cayenne pepper. Over all it was a great sauce. Made for Chef Alphabet Soup.

name: auntie s delicious soft pretzels  amish recipe
review: Well, I made this back in 2008, printed it and added notes, and never reviewed it!  My notes: Spoon flour into measuring cup- dont use heaping or it will be too stiff.  Also, dont make the ropes too thick or the middle will not set.  Also, I baked at 500.  Thank you for posting this recipe!

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: Yum - great way to prepare yellow squash!  The onions caramelize a bit and add a nice flavor.  Used plenty of pepper as you suggested and really enjoyed - thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: unknownchef86 s very best dinner rolls
review: Excellent!!  These were not very pretty when they were finished but oh my do they taste good.  So soft and buttery.  I will be making them more often as they are easy to mix up.  One hint though, when you cover them with the plastic wrap tp rise please spray the plastic wrap with release spray or it will stick, I found out the hard way.

name: kittencal s technique for perfect easy peel hard boiled eggs
review: Great way to peel eggs!  The skins just come off so smoothly!  Thanks so much Kittencal for this excellent idea!

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: I tried it and this was delicious! Very rich, moist and fudgey!  Using my coffee grinder, I ground sugar in the raw and cocoa together and sifted it on top of the cake.  DELISH!  Will definitely be making this often. Thanks for sharing!

name: wonderful salsa
review: Such a great canning salsa!  We made several batches of this recipe.  We had a lot of vine ripened tomatoes to be used up.  We made the recipe exactly as stated and made one batch with extra jalapenos for a spicy batch.  Since our tomatoes were already real ripe, the sugar really didn't need to be added.  We noticed that it gave it too much of a sweet taste and hid some of the spiciness.  But after the salsa has sat in the cupboard for a couple months the sweetness finally mellowed out and the spice has shined thru!  So if you added the sugar and was afraid it made it too sweet, just give it a little while to marinate to together and mellow, it will turn out fine!  If you plan on eating it all right away, than you can decide if you want to add the sugar or not if you tomatoes are already sweet.  The ratios in this salsa are perfect for a nice mild salsa.  Thanks for this great recipe.  Im sure when we want to can salsa again we will be coming to this one!

name: potato salad with chipotle peppers a man s salad
review: I can't believe I never rated this!  I made this several years ago and thought it was delish!  I did omit the black beans.  But I need to make this again soon, and I will add them in this time.  I love trying all different kinds of potato salads.  This one is definitely unique!  It is on the top of our favorite potato salads!  Thanks for the great recipe!

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: We loved these muffins.  I used four apples, grated and was out of butter.  Served with egg, sausage scramble.

name: herbed pork tenderloin
review: Oh, this is so good.  I made this tenderloin last night and it was so flavorful that my kids didn't use ketchup!!! Thats a first....lol.  I will continue to use your recipe, it is so juicy and good I'm craving some right now.  Thank you for sharing your recipe with us.

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: Wonderful stir-fry!  I only marinated for 40 minutes, did not use red pepper flakes and added aspargus and mushrooms to chicken.  Loved it!  Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s famous coleslaw
review: Excellent coleslaw! I only used a scant 1/3 cup of sugar though as I didn't want it to be too sweet. Will make again! Thank you!

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: Awesome ! I cut the sugar by 1/2 for the topping and the bottom, althought I drzziled the apples with a bit of caramel syrup.  Great recipe, will make again.  thank you for posting.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: I frosted some Baker's One Bowl Brownies with this recipe.  The reason I am giving it 4 stars is because I think it needed just a dash of salt.  Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: Delicious! I roasted a 4.5 pound chicken for 20 min on 450 and 50 min at 400. I used salt, pepper and crushed rosemary on the outside, and injected the bird with melted butter and lemon juice. The real key was to let it sit for 15 minutes before cutting it - the chicken was tender, juicy, and crispy on the outside. Yum!! Update: I made this again using a 6 pound chicken. I cooked it for 20 min on 450 and then 60 min at 400. Again, unbelievably delicious!

name: cracker barrel green beans
review: This was pretty good. I didn't have bacon so I heated everything in some bacon grease and used bacon bits. I was leery about the sugar but after a couple bites you didn't even notice the sweetness. Made for Chef Alphabet Soup.

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: I made this sauce to use with recipe#26339.  It was perfect.  The sauce is so yummy.  Perfect balance of sweet / vinegar...  And very easy to do.  I didn't let it boil 30 minutes.  After 15 minutes, it was perfect.  Thanks Dana :)  Made for All you can cook buffet

name: cheddar bar b q chicken breasts
review: This is so yummy.  I used recipe#19023 for the bbq sauce.  Thanks Wende :)  Made for All you can cook buffet

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: I know your recipe says no substitutes with the butter but I did sub butter flavored crisco since that's what I had. I also did not use parchment paper, just baked on an ungreased cookie sheet as I would for any cookie with this amount of fat, they released perfectly  The flavor and texture of this cookie is great! Thanks for sharing

name: french dip roast beef for the crock pot
review: I cannot believe how good this recipe turned out! I followed it pretty much as written, only adding a teaspoon of dehydrated onion flakes, and it the results were unbelievable! I cooked it on low for 8 hours and while it didn't fall apart, it was still very moist and it really soaked up the seasonings. I added provolone to the sandwiches and served them on ciabatta bread (since the kids complain about harder bread). Between myself, my 3 kids and my husband, a 4 lb. roast disappeared in 20 minutes! The au jus was perfect, not too salty like some other recipes that I've had. I think next time I will try it with a top round roast to see if it gets "fall apart tender" but I will not change anything else. Thank you for the perfect French Dip recipe!

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: 1/2 whole wheat flour worked great!

name: do at home onion rings
review: And I thought making onion rings at home would be difficult! No more frozen onion rings from the store - these are so simple to make and so, SO delicious. Thank you MizzNezz!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Kind of pointless to be review #1399, but this was great. I had to dispatch a nasty rooster, about a year old, and used the breast and thigh meat. Low for 6 hours, shredded the meat, added 8 oz cream cheese until it melted, served on warmed tortillas.

name: self rising flour
review: wonderful recipe.  No need to buy self-rising flour.  It's so easy to do when we need this for a recipe.  I needed it for a cake and it was perfect.  Thanks hcopeland :)  Made for All you can cook buffet

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: This turned out to be too sweet for my tastes, but the kids loved it on their cutout cookies. I did have to add quite a bit more milk (4 tbsp) as it just would not come together without it. In the future I would probably add even more milk since it was still quite stiff and hard to pipe without excessive force.

name: basic sourdough bread
review: Fantastic sourdough bread!  This made the most gorgeously dense-yet-light loaf of bread with a crisp crust and moist interior.  I sliced it and made the most wonderful grilled ham and cheese I've ever tasted.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: This is a wonderfully comforting and creamy soup.  I used red skinned potatoes and left the skins on.  I diced them somewhat small and roasted them in the oven with some fresh rosemary and thyme, salt and pepper and olive oil.  When they were fork tender, I smashed some of them.I sauteed the onion and garlic in a bit of butter and bacon grease, then made as directed adding the potatoes with the cream cheese.  I topped each serving with shredded sharp cheddar, green onions, sour cream and crumbled bacon.

name: beef barley soup
review: I made half a recipe on the stove early in the day so when I went to reheat it, I needed to add 1 c. water.  Great flavors and very filling.

name: cajun style oven fries
review: Awesome fries! My grandson and I were fighting over them, lol. Simple and delish. Thanks Sue Lau for sharing this great keeper. Made for All You Can Cook Buffet Tag.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: Yummy! I wish I had read the review about using the rolling pin to press down the sugar/cinnamon. I will try that the next time. The taste was great!

name: chicken  shrimp and andouille jambalaya
review: Mmmmm best I've made yet! As a former 'Nawlins gal, I can say this is good stuff. I did do one full green pepper though, as that would be truer to the trinity. The baking was so much better than crock-pot versions for the rice. Perfect for Mardi Gras this year, served with Bananas Foster for dessert. Thanks for the keeper!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: This was a fabulous dish and I can't believe I hadn't tried it sooner. It got rave reviews from everyone, including our 7 year old that "hates fish." I agree with kadusey that it was just a bit too salty for me but I think it's because I used Tony Chachere's Creole Seasoning which is somewhat salty and my butter also had salt in it. I think next time I will use unsalted butter to compensate for the seasoning. When I cooked it, I screwed up and put the topping on the fish when I first put it in the oven but it turned out well. I baked it for 10 minutes and then hit it with the broiler for 7 minutes and it was very nicely browned when it was done. I wanted to take a picture but after my first bite, I devoured it before I remembered to get the camera. Thanks so much for posting! I'm sure this will be made quite a few more times.

name: honey ginger grilled salmon
review: So delicious and simple. I reduced the leftover marinade and served on the side.

name: old fashioned linguine with white clam sauce
review: This was great.  the flavor is really mild but tasty.  It was super easy, which is always great for me!  I used half chopped clams and half fancy baby clams.  I went for the baby clams because I thought it would be better.  Next time I'll stick with the chopped clams.  The chopped clams are chewier which the think the dish needs.  Overall, just a plain great dish!  Thanks Maine-iac....

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: Very rich and very delicious!!

name: lemon baked cod
review: Easy recipe. I did one fillet as in the recipe. It was very soggy on the bottom. The rest of the fillets I used panko, parm cheese, lemon zest mixture for the flour. Also I did not add the extra butter mixture to the pan. Instead of paprika I sprinkled old bay on top. With these changes our cod was YUMMY!

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: Delicious!!  I made this recipen my crockpot for dinner tonight!  It was soooo yummy!  I did use fresh diced carrots, more onion, more garlic, and double Kale and chopped zucchini, celery and fresh english peas...because I needed to use them before they spoiled.  But it was delicious and will definitely be making again!!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: tasty.  I used frozen broccoli--just got tired of steaming it.

name: beef roast
review: Very good. Made in crock pot (7 hrs on low then keep warm for 3). No mushrooms and used homemade Lipton's onion soup mix.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: So good!  I halved the recipe with no problems.  I think I might like a little more mustard mixture next time...some of my bread crumbs didn't absorb the flavors.  This is just delicious, and I'll enjoy this recipe again.  Thanks for sharing!

name: cheat n  eat vietnamese chicken soup
review: This is the best chicken noodle soup I've ever had.  And certainly head and shoulders above any I've tried to make at home.  I halved the amount of fish sauce and tripled the amount of noodles.  I LOVE the addition of the fresh herbs.  DEEEEEEEEEEEEEELISH!  Thanks for posting.  So quick, too.  THUMBS UP from our house!

name: wet burritos
review: These made a very nice looking presentation. Next time I am gonna try with shredded beef. I did add a little bit of salt to the meat too.

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Great recipe.  Made just as directed.

name: any fruit fast fat free cobbler
review: This was so easy and tasted very good!  I used 2 cans of light peaches, drained (which came to 3 cups) and made 1 1/2 times the batter amount.  I sprinkled some cinnamon on top and baked in a 11X7 pan.  I also used Splenda for some of the sugar.  Nice low-fat dessert option.  Thanks for posting!

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: This was so easy to make and tasted good. My chicken was a bit dry but tasty. I used about 1.5 pounds of chicken and used Kraft Honey BBQ sauce. We thought it could have used more bbq sauce too. Everyone enjoyed this.

name: paula deen crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: I have a new slow cooker mac and cheese now! I used 1% milk, light sour cream, 2 cups extra sharp cheddar and a 4 oz chunk of 2% Velveta and it was nice and creamy.  Also skipped the eggs. Followed the technique, but love the idea of melting the cheese and butter in the crockpot then mixing in everything else.  Made a good sized batch, had dinner tonight for 3 of us, enough for at least lunch tomorrow.  Thanks for posting, a keeper for sure.

name: basic batter waffles
review: Delicious!! I never really noticed how badly boxed waffle mix was until I made this recipe. I made waffles with the boxed mix and other ones with this recipe. After trying both, I threw the ones made from th boxed mix in the trash. Another thing I love about it is that its very liquidy so you don't need to use a spatula to spread it in the waffle iron. You can just pour it.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Very good, easy to make and turned out perfectly.  Yum!

name: slow cooker macaroni   cheese
review: I have a new slow cooker mac and cheese now! I used 1% milk, light sour cream, 2 cups extra sharp cheddar and a 4 oz chunk of 2% Velveta and it was nice and creamy.  Also skipped the eggs. Followed the technique, but love the idea of melting the cheese and butter in the crockpot then mixing in everything else.  Made a good sized batch, had dinner tonight for 3 of us, enough for at least lunch tomorrow.  Thanks for posting, a keeper for sure.

name: crock pot chicken vindaloo
review: We really enjoyed this dish.  In keeping with my new low carb life style we served this over cauli-fried rice.  We will be making this again.

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: These muffins have the most beautiful crown! This is definitely my new favorite recipe!!! They have the perfect texture and are so easy to whip up. Now I just hope they'll pass the day-old test.... I have a feeling they will. Thanks for the keeper!

name: mexican casserole   6 5 weight watcher points
review: My family seemed to like this pretty well. I did not use the reduced fat ingredients, only because we don't keep those items on hand, but I did stick to the recipe otherwise. My 2 year old son actually ate it, which is good because he does not seem to like much of anything. My husband had 2nds, and I froze the leftovers to be enjoyed again. Thanks for posting the recipe.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Wonderful!  Not greasy at all, crunchy and perfect flavor.  I made these just as written.  Thanks for sharing.

name: lemon baked cod
review: so easy .tastes great i double coated the fish  american fish is watery

name: white fish in herbed butter
review: changed slightly. used old bay, dill, butter, and lemon salt on some swai fillets. was sooo rich and yummy! will more than likely opt for garlic flavored olive oil in place of butter next time.

name: do at home onion rings
review: I was hungry for onion rings but this wasn't the one I needed.  I made half a recipe for the two of us.

name: homemade rice a roni
review: I used angel hair pasta.  I liked that there was just a little bit of butter and the taste was amazing.  Thanks Lisa :)  Made for all you can cook buffet

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: So easy and so wonderfully delicious. I can't believe I never reviewed this. I've made it twice a month for several years. We never tire of it and anyone else who tries it always asks for the recipe. Thanks for posting this.

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: I don't think I can say anything that everyone hasn't already covered. I made this just as stated. I halved the recipe, let it sit for nearly 2 hours. My son grilled the chicken. It is fabolous!! I can't wait to make this again. Great flavor! Thanks for sharing!!

name: crunchy granola
review: This is a really good granola recipe.  It is very easy and basic and not super expensive as some of the other granolas can be.  I made it just as written but drizzled a bit of honey once in the pan to help it clump a little.  It clumped enough for me!  I also added some ground flax seeds to bump up the omegas.  Thanks for the great recipe ciao!!!!

name: quick spanish rice
review: Very easy to make.  Was in a hurry to find something that required little chopping to go along with my chiles rellenos.  It did need a little more seasoning and was a tad bit dry.  The chopped green onions and cheese (we used monterey jack) definitely improved the flavor.  Thanks!

name: quick n easy quiche crust
review: Beautifully tender and flaky crust.  It is tremendously easy and wonderfully flavorful from the olive oil.  I am not particularly talented with pastry and this came out perfectly for me.  I did double the recipe and roll it out instead of patting in the pan.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: This was a wonderful recipe - easy to make and delicious flavor and appearance. Thanks for sharing.

name: neiman marcus  250 chocolate chip cookies recipe
review: Great chocolaty cookie.  I liked blending the oatmeal so it was mixed in like flour, my DSs are not fans of "chunks" in their cookies so this was I can hide a little healthiness and they will not know!  I made without the nuts for families preference.  I decreased the recipe to make 36 but ended up with 59; must have made them small...DH is happy though he LOVES chocolate chip anything!!  Made for All You Can Cook Buffet Tag.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: Love this recipe.  My only change was to put on cajun seasoning instead of the salt and pepper.  Hubby says next time we need to top with parmesan to complete.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: This was simply delicious!  I omitted the celery since my daughter doesn't like it, otherwise I made exactly as written.  It was so easy to make and cooked up very quickly.  I loved having dinner on the table in less than 30 minutes.  Definitely on my list to make again.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: Delicious!!  I made this cake for my final project for my Wilton cake decorating class, with Bavarian Cream Filling (Recipe #998) and Nutella buttercream frosting... truly decadent!!  I was a little worried about the coffee, but it doesn't taste like coffee, especially once you get the frosting on it.  We aren't coffee drinkers, but I keep packets of Starbucks instant coffee around the house for guests, so I used that.

name: grandmas sloppy joes
review: I tried it and these were great.  I halfed the recipe and omitted the mustard.  I used onion powder instead of real onion and Ragu Spaghetti sauce with mushrooms for the tomato sauce.  Delish!  Thanks for sharing!

name: the original rice krispies treats squares
review: Thanks for posting this great recipe.  I also bought Rrice Krispies with no recipe on the box.  You'd think I'd remember how after making this tons of times in the past 60 years,  but, of course, I didn't.  Anyway - yummy and as usual I had to eat the first one while it was still gooey and falling apart.  They set up  if you can wait awhile.  Great for kids and not so young kids.

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: Positively fantastic recipe.  We all really enjoyed the lovely flavors at play here.  I did coose to slice off the skin though, because my kids don't care for having the skin intact when I oven roast winter squashes.  So, to be assured my kids would actually eat it and get a serving of vegetables in, it was well worth the little extra time it took to peel my butternut squash.  Even though it's just fantastic as is, I'd still like to make this recipe again and try some of the changes suggested by other reviews, perhaps a touch of cinnamon or cayenne and maybe a handful of chopped nuts for a little extra crunch.  Thank you for sharing your recipe, Pianolady.  It was a big hit in my family.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review:
Thanks for posting Kree! This was tasty. The family enjoyed this meal. I served the sandwiches with fries and a salad as a casual weeknight dinner. I used Sweet Baby Rays Honey and Hickory sauce and shredded at the 4 -5 hour mark like Joy suggested. Definitely a keeper.
I think I may serve this on mini rolls as appetizers next event. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Loved it!

name: bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers
review: Yummy!  Simple but so good.  The only thing I didn't like was the bacon to sizzle in the oven.  But the taste is amazing.  Thanks AZRoxy :)  Made for All you can cook buffet

name: southern fried chicken
review: Turned out really good! I marinated the chicken in the egg mixture for about one hour. Came out really tasty!

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: This was good and simple. I added steamed pea pods during the last minute. Thanks!

name: bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers
review: My husband made these. As written he thought they were a bit bland but to the next batch he added some spices to the cheese mixture. He used season salt, garlic powder and pepper. They enjoyed them.

name: easy baked potato wedges
review: My husband loves baked potato wedges and these were just his thing.  We loved the spices and they went together easily.  Thanks for sharing!

name: poverty meal
review: This was good and I love that it was so economical to make.  I did make a couple of changes by adding in a small amount of paprika and about 3/4 cup of shredded cheddar.  We enjoyed it, even my picky husband.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: I will add my 5 star review to the rest. I added less sugar (about 6 tbsp) and DH is saying that he missed it. I think they are sweet enough but we are all different ;) I will for sure be making these again!

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: This was delicious thank you for sharing.

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: super delicious pizza sauce.  Couldn't stop tasting it while it cooked!  I halved the recipe and it was the perfect amount for a large pizza.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review:
Very, very good.

Next time...I'd chop the walnuts more finely. I think I'd also omit the breadcrumbs..as they seemed to be kinda gummy on the fish. Wonderful flavor.

name: best albondigas soup
review: My local market makes an excellent chorizo, which I used in this recipe. I used 4 cups commercial low-sodium broth which is still too high in sodium and so I used 2 cups of water with it. I added a chopped jalapeno to the broth. I cut off the stems from my bunch of cilantro, rinsed and tied with kitchen twine and added it to the broth - this really adds a lot of flavor. I did try frying the meatballs but won't bother next time - I had hardly any fat come out, so it was just an extra step. I also made my meatballs bigger, ended up with a dozen of them. A great soup for a cold night.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: I didn't have any sour cream or pimento, but was still really good.  Thanks for sharing such a great recipe.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: Great recipe... better than others I have tried for still tasting good after being in the fridge for a day or more.  I give it four stars... which for me means great recipe... but I'm still searching for something I like even better, that wows me like some restaurants.  : )  Thanks a bunch.

name: beef patties in onion gravy
review: Comfort food like mom used to make!  Super simple, quick and easy.  Served with mashed potatoes, of course!

name: crazy crust pizza
review: I looked up the recipe because I remembered it from when I was a kid.  I whipped this up last weekend for the kids.  What a hit!  Thanks for posting this oldie but goodie.  This is so easy to follow and has great results.  I love the sausage on this. Yum.

name: basic batter waffles
review: Great basic recipe!  We used the wheatgerm and even added some milled flax seeds which didn't weight down the batter-still light and fluffy!  The whole family enjoyed!  Thanks so much Roxygirl in Colorado...

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: DH has declared this his favorite recipe for Sloppy Joe's. He detests "store bought" mix. I think this has great flavor also!! Thanks Jude for posting.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: This was great.  I tossed the cauliflower and the garlic in a bowl - and then placed on a pan greased with a Tbl or two of cauliflower.  The garlic burnt - I'm thinking I may use garlic salt or garlic powder.  The cauliflower crisped up and was crunchy and yummy !

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: Very good! Made my own double pie crusts and had enough filling for two deep dish 9-inch pot pies. Baked one right away and froze the other for later. Added about an extra cup of chicken cause that's what I had, and used fat free milk instead of half and half. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: the best banana bread
review: This is yummy bread! Seems pretty buttery and luscious! I'd love to play around with making it healthier. My poor bread didn't come out of tin very well, but we are more than happy to eat shredded bits! Thanks for sharing! My DH loved it!!! I made it in 2 tins anad I gave it about 55mins, need to grease my tins better... added choco chips and I think I would love it with walnus too!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: I guess I need to admit I'm not wild about crockpot chicken, although I tried this recipe with high hopes based upon the other reviews.  Followed the directions precisely and did end up with a falling-off-the-bones bird, but the meat turned out stringy and a little bit flavorless.  The bright side is that I ended up with some terrific broth to make soup with the next day.  :-)

name: m   m dream bars
review: Really good! I used fat free sweetened condensed milk and natural peanut butter with great results. Will make these again! Thanks for sharing!

name: french dip roast beef for the crock pot
review:
The flavor of the meat is excellent! Just the right amount of salt and spices. I am going to saute some green peppers and onions in the juice to add to the sandwiches. Thanks for a
great recipe. Carole in Orlando

name: wholesome homemade honey whole wheat bread
review: Very tasty! I halved the recipe. Loved it!

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: Very easy to put together. I used medium salsa and the optional black beans. Yummy Tex-Mex flavor and something a beginner cook could make.  Thanks for the recipe.

name: slow cooker chicken noodle soup
review: Perfectly delicious plus easy! I used 3 chicken breasts, 6 cups broth and 2 cups of water with 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt.  Appreciate recipes that use ingredients that I have on hand. Thanks Lainey for sharing.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Delicious!!  I doubled the sauce (I used extra vegetables) and should not have because it was pretty salty.  This was my bad and not a reflection on the recipe.  Next time, I will use a 1/3 cup of either water or reduced sodium beef broth and double everything else.  I also used lots of garlic because I'm a garlic freak.   It really satisfied my craving for Asian food!  Chris, thank you for sharing your recipe!  It's a keeper!!!

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: I only used 1 chicken breast for the two of us and fresh water chestnuts.  Wow really good.  Loved the sauce and will make again soon to use up my Butter lettuce from BB.  Served with a veggie stir fry and soup.

name: no bake granola bars
review: These are so delicious.  It was hard to stop eating them..  They are perfect.  Thanks for posting.

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: Wow!  This was an awesome cooking method.  The tenderloin came out so moist and perfect that I ran to the store after dinner to pick up 3 more tenderloins while they were still on sale.  Thank you!

name: cottage cheese roast  vegetarian meatloaf
review: I wanted to like this so bad but both my husband and I didn't really care for it.  We are in the minority on this one!!

name: cracker barrel green beans
review: Tasted just like Cracker Barrel!.  DH had a craving for beans like this, and I'd never made them, so we looked up this recipe and cooked them up to go with a mid-week dinner.  Everyone enjoyed them and they'll be on the table frequently in the future.

name: brown sugar bundt cake
review: This is a great cake.  I made this for myfamily and we loved it.  I was out of pecans so I subbed in some peanuts chopped up and we will continue using them, it was yummy.  Thank you for sharing this cake recipe with us.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: This was pretty good. I sauted my veggies until they were almost done before I added the liquid. I added a little beef bouillon to my water for extra flavor.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: Great Kitten!  Used 95% ff cream of chicken soup, skim milk, low fat sour cream, nad no gr peppers or celery and used chicken, still turned out great!!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: Outstanding!

name: old widow walker s ziploc omelettes
review: Oh, this is fantastic!  I love this!!!!!  Made this evening, only adding salt, pepper and sharp cheddar cheese.  Cooked as recipe instructed.  It made a marvelous night time snack!  Thanks Pot Scrubber for sharing this delightful recipe.

name: three cup chicken
review: This is so good.  I couldn't find Thai basil so I omitted it, but we loved it anyway.  I will make again and we want to add the basil.  I love the spice in this.  Thank you so much for sharing your recipe with us.

name: quick butternut squash soup
review: This was so easy to make but it didn't have a lot of flavor to it. This was the first time I have ever had squash soup and it wasn't all that bad but it's just something I would not make again for myself. I had frozen a lot of squash last summer and was glad to find a way to use it. I also added fresh shredded Parmesan cheese to my bowl. Made for 2012 Zaar Cookbook Tag.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: Yummy and very easy! Not a traditional Alfredo (just butter, cream, Parm) but wonderful flavor from added seasoning. Mozzarella helps stabilize the sauce so it doesn't break down quickly and can even be reheated. I doubled the recipe with good results. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: amish white bread
review: Really nice flavour but found the texture to be a little dense.  It was perfect for toast, though!

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: This was good, but the pudding mixture was really runny. Next time I would put the pudding in a bowl and add the juice slowly until I got to the consistency I was looking for.

name: breakfast casserole supreme
review: Very good casserole.  My DH thought it was superb.  Will be making this again.  Thanks for posting.

name: best grilled pork chops
review: Marinated for just 3 hours, and they were delicious!  Quick and easy to put together for a  busy night!

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: These Muffins are GREAT!!, great flavor and texture, easy to make.  Enjoyed by my whole family.  Followed directions, using buttermilk, did sub carob chips for chocolate chips, tripled the recipe to have some for breakfast and to freeze some for later.  Thank You.

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: This was easy and flavorful, but a bit too salty for us. So, next time I could use more shrimp or I can cut down on the salt. Thanks for sharing!

name: granny s slow cooker vegetarian chili
review: Delicious, easy and satisfying, the baked beans were a nice touch.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: This is the Best!  My daughter and I made this together and it turned out perfect.  We used fat-free half & half, light velveeta cheese and frozen broccoli.  It was just the right thickness and flavor.  We will make a double recipe next time.  Thanks for posting!

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: This is fabulous!  I made this and we loved it.  It is so moist and flavorful.  We left our cherries whole and added a few more on top!  Thank you for a delicious dessert that we are sure to repeat!

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: Excellent recipe!!  I made as written to serve with pulled pork and decided it needed just a bit of something.  After reading other reviews, I did add some molasses and a touch of liquid smoke.  Spot on!  This made enough to completely cover 4 pounds of pulled pork and have some sauce left over to serve on the side.  I will make this again!  Thanks for sharing!

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: My kids loved this.  I, too, followed others' suggestions and used taco seasoning mix and mixed the meat with the refried beans.  Quick and easy recipe that will be a part of my regular weeknight menu rotation.

name: quick spanish rice
review: Quick, easy and most importantly DELICIOUS! I halved the recipe but did not change a thing! Thanks Sharlene!

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Loved the combination of crunchy vegetables and zesty dressing.  Tasted even better the second day. Nice recipe for gatherings

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: I enjoyed this recipe. I used the IQF fillets, which usually end up really watery even when fully thawed. I also only had one pound, but it was 6 fillets! They were really thin. I should have spaced them out into a larger pan (my mistake). After the first cooking (10 min.), I used a turkey baster to remove some excess liquid. Then I added the topping and baked an additional 5 min. They didn't really brown but they were cooked perfectly (but runny again). I enjoyed the flavor, but my fish-hating son wasn't fooled. Even so, I will probably make this again. I have a few strategies up my sleeve now if I have to use the frozen fillets again, but I would love to try fresh.

name: the original rice krispies treats squares
review: I had forgotten how much of a pain in the arse Rice Krispie treats really are. Haha. Plus, my marshmallows were ancient, so they didn't melt well. (Read the description, chefs!) However, I am pretty sure this is the original recipe, and the kids say they taste fine. I thought the recipe I used to make had vanilla in it, but it was Betty Crocker rather than back-of-the-box. So despite the rice krispies all over the kitchen and the sticky pan, thank you for posting.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: This was good and easy to make. I put my chicken on a bed of onions and used the fajita seasoning as you stated in the notes. It was easy to put together in the morning. Mine cooked up in four hours.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: This is a delicious marinade for both steak and chicken, even if you don't have alot of time to marinate your meat.  I grated the garlic and I doubled the ingredients.  Next time I'll make extra to saute the vegetables in rather than using butter or margarine.  Cooked the chicken breast and the steak separately in a cast iron skillet, then sliced both meats finely.  Sauteed the vegetables while meat was cooking.  Delicious and very light flavor perfect for summer.

name: self rising flour
review: worked wonderful and didn't have to go buy a bag for just a few uses here and there! thanks a bunch!!

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: wonderful recipe.  I used macaroni.  And I used a 28 ounce can of diced tomatoes.  I used a little bit more of each veggies (celery, pepper, onion).  And I used fresh mushrooms that I added at the same time as the previous veggies.  The mushroom soups adds a wonderful taste to the whole dish.  It gives a lot and it's perfect for the lunches at work/school.  Thanks Jellyqueen :)  Made for All you can cook buffet

name: pumpkin pie dip
review: I made this for our annual sleep over with my cousin and it was a huge hit with them and me. I love the spicy flavor and with ginger snaps it has even more zing. Great dip for any Fall event. Everyone wanted the recipe, too which makes you know it's a hit.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: These pancakes hit the spot!  I dunno if they taste like IHOP's, but nevertheless, they taste great.  My family especially enjoys having these pancakes when we have breakfast for dinner.  I never have buttermilk in the fridge, so I always use Recipe #430334 which works like a charm.  Thanks.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review:
This is more like a (cup)cake than a muffin in technique and resulting texture (light and soft), but thankfully it's not as overwhelmingly sweet as most cakes. I did not add the strudel topping, and I only used 1 3/4 cups of *very large* blueberries. At that size, I wouldn't want more blueberries!

My youngest son called these "blueberry cupcakes" and requested them for his birthday. Winner!

name: crunchy granola
review: This is my first time making granola and its fantastic.  I just used sliced almonds this time, but I want to try it with all kinds of nuts and maybe some coconut.  Thank you for this awesome recipe.  We love it.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: I made half a recipe for the two of us and it was perfect.  I used Bob Evans hot sausage and kale (from bountiful baskets) What a great soup!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: We love chicken pot pie, & I usually buy those large ones from Costco, although they are only avalable during the wintertime! Your pot pie is absolutely delicious, & I might well be serving homemade ones from now on! Wonderfully satisfying! Thanks for sharing the recipe! [Made & reviewed in Zaar Stars recipe tag]

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: Absolutely LOVED this dish. I added some potatoes as well and everything was just wonderful. This is a great way to use up extra vegetables. I probably added more spices than called for, but I like to add seasonings by eye. I forgot to add parsley but it was still great. Thanks!

name: creamy potato salad
review: Very good potato salad.  Never put bacon in potato salad before but it works!

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: Yummy! I used salted butter instead of shortening and forgot to cut down the salt. Next time I'd reduce it to 1/4-1/2 t. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: Wow what a winning recipe! I make this frequently, swapping canned green chilis for the green pepper and adding 1 tsp of coriander. The vinegar is winning. I tried jalapeno lime black beans and put cooked spinach on top today and it was over the top yum! Thanks so much for this cheap and easy regular in our house!!

name: roasted broccoli w lemon garlic   toasted pine nuts
review: Very quick and easy - and tasty. Roasted broccoli was such a great change of pace from the usual. I didn't add any nuts at the end, just out of personal preference. Thank you!

name: magnolia bakery s vanilla birthday cake and frosting
review: I made a two layer 9 inch cake with this recipe. There wasn't enough batter to make it a three layer cake. The cake was incredibly moist and delicious, however the icing was a tad too sweet for my taste. I'd definitely make the cake batter again but I think I'd pick another icing to pair with it.

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: YUMMY! the boyfriend whipped this up and added onions to it and seasoned things a little bit with Oklahoma Joe's Rib Rub #118966. absolutely fork tender and served over plain ol white rice. and everything we had on hand. Thanks for a wonderful recipe Nimz!

name: beer  n bbq braised country style pork ribs
review: Made this tonight and it was terrific!  The only problem was getting my DH to give up one of his 12oz's.   I used Sweet Baby Ray's original BBQ sauce.  The meat literally fell off of the bones!  Thanks for a great recipe.

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review:
This is so yummy!
I had to bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes. The frosting is creamy and not too sweet.
A great cake.
Justine

Update: I made this for the dessert contest at work....I beat out 23 othere recipes. This cake has got it going on!!!!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: I can't wait to try this on chicken!  I loved the sauce, it was like Duck sauce with a kick!  Thanks.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Made this dish for dinner tonight and it was very easy to make. However, I expected the sauce to thicken up and coat the chicken more than it did. I think next time I will marinate the chicken in the sauce and then bake it to see if it will absorb more of the flavor.  Will definitely try this dish again.

name: double chocolate banana muffins
review: I tried it and these are extremely good!  I used regular semi-sweet choc chips (1/2 cup) and I used my mini loaf pan.  After they cooled I sliced them in half olengthwise and spread a cream cheese frosting on some and nutella on others and put them back together.  Delish!!  Thanks for sharing!!

name: pepsi pork roast
review: I have made this recipe twice now, with fantastic results. I also used the entire package of onion soup, both times, but only because I didn't feel like having the open packet laying around. The first time I made this, I followed the recipe totally, except subbing Coke for Pepsi. I am a die-hard Coke fan, and would never have Pepsi in my house ;) It turned out great. So very tender and moist. Pork roast can sometimes be dry, and this was not at all. The second time I made this, I subbed the mushroom soup for a golden mushroom soup, and also the onion soup for a beefy onion soup packet. The second time had a rich gravy, slightly different. I think I did prefer the original version myself. There was so much nice gravy both times. I noticed it took a little more cornstarch to make it thicken, and I assume it's from the soda. Not a big deal at all, because this is worth it. The first time, we had mashed potatoes with the roast and gravy. I used the leftovers from the first batch to make a different spin on a traditional Sheppard's pie. Fantastic! The second time, I used the leftovers with wide egg noodles. All the kids liked it. Even my DD who is anti-pork. We just told her it was a regular roast beef pot roast ;) Cheers!

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: I've never made soda bread before, but do have a good reputation for making bread, so when my friends asked me to make soda bread for a St. Patrick's Day feast, I chose this one.  Lucky for all of us, I chose this recipe.  It was easy to put together although the batter took longer to come together than I anticipated.  I used a tiny bit less than the 2 T caraway seeds, and opted for light sour cream, but glad I didn't leave out the caraway seeds, as they were a nice counterpoint to the golden raisins in the bread.  Using a springform pan made it a cinch to get it out, and it was lovely.  Thanks for sharing an easy, delicious recipe, 1Steve!

name: perfect rump roast
review: Yum! This was great thanks!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Fantastic cake!  I didn't use the freezer method b/c I was worried about the pan warping and also b/c there is no room in there anyway!  I made it as a 9 inch layer cake.  I didn't make the icing, just used some cream cheese frosting that I had in the pantry.  I toasted some pecans and used them on top of each layer which made it super tasty.  Will definitely make again!

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: Really good!! I used fat free half & half and greek yogurt.  I also cooked the onion, red bell pepper and celery in the micro til tender.  I used rotisserie chicken.  Will for sure make this again.

name: hello dollies
review: Wow!!! These were so good. I was looking for recipes to help clean out my pantry, and this took care of a few things that I was looking to use up. I love SWEET, so these are just perfect. I did mix my graham cracker crumbswith the butter and then placed in 8x8 pan. I had macadamia nuts on hand so that is what I used. Even the hubby ate these and he has a strong dislike for coconut. KEEPER if I can get him to eat coconut!! I set them in the fridge to cool quicker also, since I was having a hard time waiting for them to cool! Thank you for this recipe!!

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: Delicious! We really loved this, and it was so simple and easy. We used 1.5 tablespoons of liquid smoke and it was perfect. Thanks!

name: corned beef and cabbage in guinness
review: The Guinness lends a totally different flavor to the corned beef in this dish! Everyone loved it. We served it alongside Emerald Green Punch, Dublin Coddle, Lazy Irish Beer Bread, and Nutty Irishmen. Thanks!

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Great sauce, balanced flavours all around. I used slightly less of all the tomato ingredients (due to differences in packaging sizes) but otherwise followed the recipe - using 5 garlic cloves, because we love the stuff! Thank you for a lovely recipe Bev!

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: Very good chocolate pudding! I make it stovetop over med heat.  We've been enjoying this quite often recently.

name: cracker barrel green beans
review: Great!  Used a crockpot to cook these slow and easy.  Left them in the crockpot on warm and served them for Christmas dinner.  Everyone seemed to enjoy.  Thanks so much for sharing.

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: They are so easy to do.  Easy to roll into balls.  They were great out of the oven with butter.  Thanks jean :)  Made for All you can cook buffet

name: peanut butter cup cookies  tarts
review: Delicious little bites. I made these for presents and they were the first to go. Thanks Roxy!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review:
Some of the best chops I've ever made!

Super tender, great flavor.

Next time, I'd double the sauce to spoon over potatoes. I'd also use more garlic.

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Excellent pasta salad.  I especially liked that it did not have any mayo in it.  I took it for a luncheon we were giving and it worked out fabulous...I did not have to worry about keeping it cold as it is 83 here in Traverse City MI today...which is nuts....everyone must have loved it as I tripled the recipe and have very little left....

name: cottage cheese roast  vegetarian meatloaf
review: This was really good. I cut recipe in half as there is only me. to which I added a sprinkle of johnny seasoning and a sprinkle of lemon pepper. Its consistancy was good it held together well without crumbling which I had from another recipe

name: slow cook down home pork chops and gravy
review: This was a very tasty meal.  Quick and easy to make.  Will make again soon.  Thanks for posting.

name: strawberry coffee cake
review: Awesome, will definitely be making this again!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: I made these for my husband to take to work, so I haven't actually tasted them.  He husband said they were delicious and had a wonderful texture.  He also commented that I needed to make them again very soon.  That's high praise coming from him!

name: better than sex cake iii
review: This turned out good.  Very rich and moist.  Much better than a plain chocolate cake.

name: basic batter waffles
review: Very good and easy to make.  I liked the addition of the maple extract to the batter.  This made enough for our family of 6 and we had two waffles left over.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: Inspired by your "Baklava" name for this, I wrapped this in a few layers of buttered phyllo before baking---worked great, and made for interesting dinner conversation!

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: Dear sweet lord this was incredible. Followed advice and doubled the butter beer sauce and we finished off 2 whole loaves of bread sopping it up. I used peeled and pre-cooked shrimp for simplicity but the ended up overcooked since, duh, they were cooked already and I threw them in hot butter sauce for awhile. Plus the sauce tastes best warm so I'd really suggest using raw shrimp for this.

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: for Candace my dietitian who's awesome

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review:
So easy, light , fast and delicious! I can understand why many people tried and enjoyed this recipe.
Yummy! Thanks a lot!

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: Very good soup, good for you and quick!

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: Really good beef stew.  I did as recommended and added 1 cup of red wine.  It was perfect.

name: easy cole slaw
review: Very simple and very tasty!!  I followed another posters suggestion and added about 1/2 tsp horseradish sauce.

name: the best sweet and sour sauce
review: Great! Made this to go with some egg rolls. Delicious, and no HFCS or red food coloring. Tanks for sharing the recipe!

name: beth s pizza crust
review: This was so easy that I was worried it wouldn't turn out! The crust had good flavor and the pizza disappeared. I added some granulated garlic to the dough -- yum!  I did find the dough pretty sticky and had to flour my board quite a bit. Thanks for sharing this keeper!

name: easy garlic chicken
review: This is a very easy and fast recipe for those busy weeknights. I really appreciated that last week! I thought this was very good. My garlic ended up getting a little overdone between the pan saute and the roasting. Other than that, we loved it. Thanks!

name: big grandma s best peanut butter cookies
review: I tried these peanut butter cookies in place of my usual and I am sure glad I tried them.  I love the big puffy look and the taste is perfect.  Thank you for posting this wonderful recipe.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: I tried it and this was great!  It was my first time working with yeast and dough.  Added 1 tbslpn of sugar.  I used highly active yeast so I didn't wait for anything to rise.  I also added the yeast to the dry mixture and mixed before adding the water and oil. It came out great!! Nice thin crust. I rolled out some of the leftover dough and put a teaspoon of sauce and cheese to it, rolled it up,  fried it and dipped it in the leftover pizza sauce I had!  DELISH!! Thanks for posting!!

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: My rice was soggy and the chicken was bland.

name: chicken breasts in lemon cream sauce
review: The sauce tastes bitter. So the kids do not like it.

name: crock pot stifado
review: Really good.  The feta makes a huge flavour difference.  It was good before putting that in but much better afterwards.  This was just the thing for a rainy night.  Thanks!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: What can I say that hasn't been said already. This is delicious. I was taking lunch over to my sisters yesterday. I made it in the morning and we were eating sloppy joes before 10 am. I uses Sweet Baby Ray's Sweet and Spicy Bar B Que sauce. Can't wait to have leftovers today. Thanks for posting Hey Jude.

name: wholly guacamole
review: Good good good! Cilantro is, for me, an absolute must. Made 1/2 recipe to serve with enchiladas, and the two of us polished the whole thing off in no time. Thank you!

name: no bake granola bars
review: I didn't have enough corn syrup so I had to use maple syrup.  I guess it was not enough sticky.  When I cut them in bars, they didn't hold their shape.  But they taste very good.  Thanks spatchcock :)  Made for All you can cook buffet

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: This is a great cake. I made half the recipe and baked in an 8x8 pan. It took exactly one hour in my oven. I did not put it in the freezer, it still came out moist.

name: hard boiled eggs
review: I LOVE this method. You get perfect eggs every single time. Thank you!

name: brady bunch pork chops
review: Tasty! The family gobbled these up.  Thank you!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: LOVED IT! Based on the reviews I halved the recipe for the sauce and guesstimated on the amounts.  I am glad we halved the sauce because kids wouldn't eat the sauce and we still had plenty left over. I happened to have a pineapple so I pureed a slice since I didn't have juice on hand. I was out of paprika or Cayenne pepper so I omitted but but a little extra garlic powder.  We will make again.  I am going to try to freeze left over sauce? not sure if that is a good idea?  Thanks I am glad to have this recipe now!

name: tilapia al ajillo  garlic tilapia
review: kids and my husband and I love this recipe!  My boys regularly request this fish recipe, they are 3 and 5years old.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: This really fit the bill for something quick, easy and filling and uses ingredients I always have on hand.  The only things I changed was to line the bottom and sides of a round casserole dish with a few tortilla's to provide a "shell" for the filling and instead of putting the chips on the bottom I added them to the top and covered them with cheese.  A new family favorite.  Thanks for posting!

name: mexican casserole   6 5 weight watcher points
review: I made half a recipe using 1 flour tortilla, a can of rotel and then as written.  Very filling.

name: croutons
review: Super quick, easy, and tasty. Just what we needed. Thank you!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: ohlalalalala! This was soooo good and I had soooo many thoughts about using all that Cajun seasoning. The seasonings were right on. Followed the recipe except for the sun-dried tomatoes (didn't have any). This deserves a 10  rating. What a outstanding recipe. Thank you Lorac.

name: intensely chocolate cocoa brownies
review: Very rich and fudgy brownie that is super easy to throw together.  Mine did take over 25 minutes to bake - so that is something to be very aware of with the recipe.  The flavors are outstanding though!  I used the chocolate chip addition (may be why more time was needed) this time and will try the chopped nuts the next time.  Nice addition to my quick dessert cookbook.  Tagged and made for I Recommend Tag game.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: This uses twice as much butter as my usually recipe - and it tasted so much better!  I frosted 24 cupcakes and 12 cookies with a single batch.  :D

name: easy cole slaw
review: I usually do not like cole slaw but had to make some for a gathering.  When I tasted it, it was so good :) Perfect balance in flavor.  Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: Just made this soup and yummy!  I'm trying to go the healthy road and this soup has alot of healthy goodness in it.  As others have said I didn't think I would enjoy it as much without some meat but it really had alot of flavor and that was without the parm cheese.  I did use my emulsion blender to blend it into more of a chunky soup (and to hide the beans from my husband) but that was the only change.  Thanks for a great healthy recipe.

name: easy lemon pound cake
review: Delicious! I added zest of one lemon and a bit of lemon extract. This cake is lighter and not as dense as a traditional pound cake. We all enjoyed it.

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: So delicious! Tastes so much better than store bought. Thanks!

name: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
review: I tried it and these cookies are hands down the best!  I followed the directions exactly.  I used milk chocolate chips in some of the batter.  I left the other part of the batter plain.  I let them sit on the cookie sheet once out of the oven for 2 minutes.  If you don't let them sit for at least 2 minutes they will be crumbly.  Once they set -- they were absolutely impossible to stop eating! I had three before I was able to walk away.  Off to do my workout video now -- and oh was it worth it.  Thanks for sharing with us.

name: hot german potato salad
