review: This was so good!! I love old "grandma" recipes!!

name: easy lemon pound cake
review: I tried it and this was great!!  It was like having pound cake without the extra butter!!  I tasted like a "light" pound cake to me.  I doubled the lemon based on the advice of other reviewers.  The glaze really brings it all together!  I used my 8 count mini loaf pan. Thanks for posting!

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: Very good casserole. Some people say it's bland but I just added salt and pepper to taste to the sauce like the recipe said. I covered it while it was baking.

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review: Very quick and turned out great! Thanks for posting.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: My family liked this but I didn't. I found the sauce a bit intensely flavored. I don't know what I would do different though.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: This was such a unique way to make broccoli. Followed the recipe exactly but it didn't brown. It more softened. It may be my non-stick pan though because I kept it in a bit longer and it still didn't turn color. The seasoning didn't seem strong enough for us so next time I will put in more.  It was delicious anyway though. It was a nice, light accompaniment to chicken and potatoes. We enjoyed it. Thanks for posting Roxygirl. We will make this again. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: easy biscuits
review: These biscuits got me out of a pinch.  But....I felt that they were just OK....nothing special.  There are other recipes I would try first before I would come back to this one.  Sorry!

name: granny s banana cream pie
review: Delicious and easy as pie!!! Really!

name: the best ever waffles
review: These tasted like the recipe I use but were more crisp than mine which was nice.  I don't know if it will replace my other waffle recipe but I will make these again.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: This is a great recipe. I'm not telling anyone it's WW. Thanks.

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: Terrific.  Not the best I have ever had, but the best takes a very long time, and for a quicky - this is just fabulous!  Made it up in about 20 minutes.  Used all hot curry, next time will mix 1/2 sweet curry and 1/2 hot.  Also added fresh mushrooms, which was a lovely addition.  Would highly recommend for anyone who enjoys curry.  This is simple, fast and really very good.  Thanks!  :]

name: bretzel rolls  bavarian pretzel sandwich rolls
review: These are beautiful yeast rolls but a little too sweet and too soft and fluffy to be considered "Bavarian'. Next time I will cut way back on the sugar, add some salt to the dough and use a little less yeast to make them denser. They freeze very nicely, though. I cut them in half and put them in the freezer. When I need one, I just put the two halves in the toaster then fill them with cheese slices, etc. Made and reviewed for the "More than Sauerkraut and Dumplings" event at the German Forum.

name: i lost my noodles  low carb south beach eggplant lasagna
review: This really is excellent dish for dieters and non-dieters alike!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: The family loved it! Tastes just like the original. I doubled the recipe and would highly suggest doing so. Easy to make. Thanks, Tish, for sharing the recipe!

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: Excellent pancakes Nimz.  These were awesome, big, thick, light, tender and fluffy.  The pancakes were so flavorful.  I love buttermilk pancakes and these are some of the best I have ever tried.  Garnished with some melted butter and icing sugar.  They really didn't need anything else. Thanks for sharing another recipe that has gone into my keeperbox. Made for Spring Pac 2012.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: Who Knew?  Who knew cauliflower could taste so good??!!  With all these fantastic reviews I knew I would have to give this recipe a try.  This will definitely be my "Go-To" Recipe for Cauliflower from now on!  So easy to do, so very little effort for fantastic results!  Thanks so much, Rita!!

name: hamburgers with brown gravy  total comfort food aka  meat cakes
review: Oh my gosh this was good.  Comfort food at its best.  I made these little gems for my family along with mashed potatoes and corn.  Perfect meal.  I love making these in the skillet and not the oven.  I will make again and again.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: kittencal s juicy hamburger burger
review: Oh, Kitten!  What I wouldn't give to have your brilliant culinary mind.  You have the most amazing knack for taking simple ingredients we all have on hand and making something that goes beyond just tasting good, to tasting fantastic!  These moist, juicy and delicious burgers were served with melted cheese, caramelized onions and a bit of brown sugar BBQ sauce.  And they were wonderful :)

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: Great pancakes!

name: baked ham and cheese omelet roll
review: Wow -- this was so easy to make as a brunch for a group.   I made two pans of it, and the only change I made was to saute some onions and sprinkle them on the eggs when I added my diced ham and cheese.  I had difficulty rolling it up into a neat log shape -- it tore in several places -- but I think it might have been because I just sprayed the pans with Pam.  Next time I will be sure to use a generous coating of butter in the pans!  Thanks for this recipe -- it was delicious!

name: quick butternut squash soup
review: Oh my goodness, is this soup delicious, and I love that it is healthy too.  It has a perfectly velvety smooth texture and gets a lot of flavor from the sauteed onion and garlic.  It's so easy to prepare!  Like other reviewers who didn't want to bother with peeling and chopping the squash, I chose to microwave mine (I pierced it all over using a knife, placed it on a plate, microwaved it for 5 minutes, turned it over and microwaved for another 5 minutes).  Thanks for sharing this recipe.  It's a keeper!

name: basil pesto
review: Delicious! 4 cups basil, 8 garlic cloves, zest of half a lemon, juice of 1 1/2 lemons, 3/4 c pine nuts, 1 c grated parmesan and about 1/3 cup really fruity olive oil. It did need a good one-and-a-half or two teaspoons of kosher salt. Spooned into ice cube trays (at least the part we didn't eat right out of the processor, smeared on bread) and frozen until hard, then transferred to a vacuum-seal bag for longer storage.

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: We really liked these.  Made just as written they are great!  We topped them with red hot and sour cream and they were different and yummy!  Thanks for the great recipe mrib!!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: The next best thing to real oven roast broccoli! I loved how quickly, easy, and healthy this is as well as it taste really great. I made as written. As we love broccoli and I do not always want to heat the oven this is an outstanding alterative that will be made often. Thanks for the post.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: WOWSIE was this delicious.  Easy and quick, perfect for beginner or experienced cook.  Company quality a keeper recipe.  Only changes I made were I used a pinch of cayenne pepper (out of hot sauce) & seared the fish in garlic olive oil until almost done, then transferred to baking sheet, added topping and broiled for 5-6 minutes until topping became a golden brown.  The appearance is so appetizing you can't wait to dig in!  Thanks MaMa and Crabby Cakes

name: failproof french bread  bread machine
review: Well here's review 114 and with good reason, this is such a simple, fast and wonder tasting recipe.  I'd saved it a long time ago but never got around to making it.  Yesterday needed something fast to go with dinner and pulled this out of my saved recipes.  Well; it won't take me that long to make it again - this is wonderful.  Perfect blend of flavors for that french bread flavor with a light, soft center and that wonderful crunchy crust.  When I put the loaves in the oven I did spray lightly with water every 5 minutes X3 to help with the crust I was wanting and it turned out perfect.  I was surprised it had no oil in it and was a little concerned but no need - it's perfect as is.

name: tiramisu
review:
Excellent....thank you for such clear instructions. Will be sure to make this again!
I used regular granulated sugar and Kahlua, as this is what I already had in the house. Came out terrific. Definite keeper!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: Loved the sauce and had extra even though I made this for two.  I did the salmon on the grill and 4 min. was perfect.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: Delicious. I followed the recipe as written with the exception that (after reading a few of the reviews) I subbed applesauce for half the oil, used 1/2 cup of golden raisins and 1/2 cup walnuts instead of 1 cup walnuts and used light cream cheese in the frosting. Very easy to make and smelled great coming out of the oven! Everyone loved it, thanks for posting it!

name: dark chocolate cake
review:
Wow! This cake is phenomenal. I used instant espresso in place of the water, and baked it in 2 9" rounds for my mother in law's birthday cake.
We used the mocha butter cream frosting recipe from the Joy of Cooking, and it was the perfect compliment. The outside we decorated with slivered almonds and chocolate covered espresso beans.
Everyone at the party RAVED about the cake. I will definitely be making this one again.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: I followed the recipe and halved it since I didn't need a ton of cookies. The flavor is outstanding, but we found them to be a little bit on the dry side. Maybe next time I need to roll them thicker. Overall it's a nice cookie recipe.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review:
Delicious little surprise for Easter morning! I chose this recipe because of the amount of blueberries listed. We enjoyed MORE blueberry and less muffin :) I'm not much of a baker, so I was thrilled they turned out so well!!
Thank you for a great recipe!

name: awesome baked ham
review: What a great method of baking ham!!  I used a cheap bone in ham from Aldi's and only wrapped it in foil, did not use the glaze.  The ham was delicious and moist!

name: awesome baked ham
review: I wouldn't say this was "AWESOME", but it was pretty good. I added a little ginger ale & some allspice to the brown sugar/mustard combo. I had a 9 lb. ham-half that I baked for 3 hours. A lot of success baking a ham depends on the brand of ham...some are saltier than others 7 that ruins the entitre meal IMO, I would deffo make this again, though...E-Z clean-up!!! THANKS for sharing!!!

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: We enjoyed this cake very much for Easter dinner. Have to say I couldn't find pineapple cake mix so happily went with a yellow cake. We loved the moistness of this cake. It is definitely a keeper.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Just made this recipe to frost some cupcakes.  I followed the recipe but subsituted whipping cream in place of the milk (I had it and wanted to use it).  Very smooth and creamy!  The icing piped easily onto the cupcakes (something I've never done before) and looks nice too (if I do say so myself).  Thank you for posting this recipe!  I'm sure that I'll be using this as my "go to" icing recipe from now on.

name: strawberry cheesecake trifle
review: Made for Easter dessert for a large-sized group and it was a winner. I did use half low-fat cream cheese, low fat Cool Whip and low fat sour cream...and non of the fat was missed. Also, to make ahead, I cut up and sweetened the strawberries the day before and since they released water overnight, poured that off. I made the cream cheese mixture but did not add the cake until a few hours before serving. Very tasty!

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: Great mash and just the right creamy consistency! Loved the parmesan in this: it wasn't cheesy but just added to the overall flavour. Thank you!

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review:
We liked the breaded chops, they were a great change from the usual.
The sage and parmesan flavours were a nice touch.

name: allrighty then scrambled eggs   paula deen
review: Just loved the taste of the sour cream (I used light) with the sharpness of the cheese (though I did omit the salt) and sprayed my pan with a oil spray but made a thoroughly enjoyable breakfast, thank you Sharon123 for a great recipe and catnip for the recommendation, made for I Recommend Tag game.

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: Just got done making these with my 10 yr old niece.  Followed recipe exactly, using pan size specified.  Baked 18 minutes at 375, probably should have baked at 350.  They were pretty good, but a little salty and a touch dry.  We will definitely make again though!  Thanks for the recipe!

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: I had a feeling that this was going to be an awesome choice for dinner tonight with all of the 5 star reviews and I wasn't disappointed! I halved this recipe for just my husband and me but tripled the sauce (added cornstarch) which was delicious on its own but next time I'll try the capers. The dijon mustard added outstanding flavor to the breading mix and did a great job of helping the crumbs to adhere. For those of us looking to jazz up boring chicken breasts without using a ton of butter or oil this recipe is a lifesaver. I'm adding this recipe to my permanent collection--thanks so much for posting! :)

name: awesome baked ham
review: Awesome is right!  This is fantastic and we're not exactly ham lovers.  Next time, though, I will use the wide foil or perhaps an oven bag, for I ended up with a huge mess in the bottom of my pan that took a day to clean up.  It's such a good  dish, though, it was well worth it!

name: ciabatta  italian slipper bread
review: Very good!  Breadmaking takes some effort, but I already spend a lot of time in my kitchen.  So much so, I insist you take me at my word that I've mastered the art of styling my hair with a fork and a twist-tie.

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: Very good and easy to make with things in my pantry!  Thanks for posting!

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: I love this soup - Though I am trying to cut out the wheat so I used a lot less as I used barley and barley grows a lot and since I love garlic I used 1/2 Tablespoons which is 1 1/2 teaspoons or 3 cloves garlic - Yummy made a great lunch. I love soup for lunch. Oh I added some salt to the soup before I ate it.

name: easy cole slaw
review:
Very fast, very easy... I made a few modifications based on preference (and what I had on hand), but it is good. No complaints... it is missing something, though. It isn't important enough to skip the recipe, though. Fast, easy, and good counts for something on a busy summer day.
1/3 c light mayo
1/3 c NF greek yogurt (plain)
1 T simple syrup
2 T NF milk
1.5 T white vinegar (to taste)
S&P
Add thinly sliced red onion

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: Great stew, just make sure you stir it often enough because mine burned at the bottom a bit. Thank you.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Sorry this was very disappointing.  The pork chops were very tough.

name: cream cheese cinnamon crescents
review: Oh, I'm sorry, but this was way too sweet.  I'd cut the filling and sugar in half if I ever make it again. Right now I hate that I wasted 2 packs of cresent rolls and 2 packs of cream cheese because we won't be able to finish this. Bummer.

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: Good tomato soup. I used canned crushed tomatoes, so I skipped blending it.

name: chinese pot stickers
review: These were excellent! They made a ton and took some time, but they were as good from the freezer as they were the first day! Totally worth the trouble. Now I just have to find the perfect dipping sauce....

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: Great Recipe. Added a little cumin powder and chopped green chilli just for an additional kick. Loved it. :) Fay

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Oh my gosh.  I can't believe I haven't rated this.  I make this bread ALL the time.  This is my bread of choice for paninis and for toast.  Of course, no one can resist slicing it warn out of the bread machine with butter slathered on it.

name: bev s macaroni and cheese
review: Like you need another review! But I want to keep track of the recipe, so here I am. =) I like how versatile this recipe is... made it the other night with 1/2 Vermont Sharp and 1/2 Extra Sharp (yum!) for our DD who had wisdom teeth out (owww). And last night for us... and since we can't take all that fat, I used 0% milk, and 1/2 lowfat sharp and 1/2 part skim mozzarella. Not as decadent, but certainly a wiser choice for the over 40 crowd. Since Easter just passed, we'll be having some with chopped ham for lunch! Thanks, Bev. [Oh - btw, I didn't read 235 reviews, but there is a lot more cheese sauce than fits 8 oz of macaroni... try 12 oz to avoid waste or soup when you choose not to bake it.]

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: This was good! My husband said it was like hot pockets with gravy. My  8 year old daughter and my neighbor liked it too. I only used one roll of creasent rolls and over stuffed them. Used all the gravy because I think it makes the dish. First reciepe I have tried of yours :)

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: Oh so good.  I used legs and thighs and it turned out fantastic.  I roasted them in the oven, but next time I want to grill them.....yummy.  The marinade made the chicken so flavorful and moist.  Thank you so much for sharing this with us.

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review:
My husband's favorite soup is Panera's black bean. Unfortunately we live two hours away from the closest Panera. He enjoyed this soup, and has asked for it again but does say it isn't "exactly" Panera's. It is still a tasty black bean soup. I served it with grilled turkey, tomato and cheese sandwiches and it was a wonderful winter dinner.

4/11/12 I made it again. Added more cumin, some chili powder, cayenne and it was met with even better reviews. Served it with a vegetable quesadilla and strawberry shortcake for dessert and my boys are fat and happy, but dined on healthy so it was a definite win. DH has already requested this soup in his lunchbox and how can I deny...it came from a couple cans. Delicious. My son and a friend came in this evening and DS told the friend that he needed some of what we had for dinner, it was really good. Love it

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: I tried it and these were restaurant quality delicious!  I adjusted the amounts to cook 4 lbs. of wings.  I broiled it according to the directions and they were great.  Next time I will decrease the salt.  Other than that, they were excellent.  We'll never order wings out again.  Thanks for posting.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Good! Super easy for a weeknight meal. Moist and flavorful. Even my son who doesn't care for chicken ate and enjoyed. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: chunky blue cheese salad dressing
review: An easy and excellent recipe!  Everyone liked it! I used it to go with these buffalo wings: Recipe #155021.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Made as written. Delicious!

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Loved the garlic flavor but didn't get as crisp as I thought it should.  Cooked it on a rack so maybe if I use less butter next time it would work.

name: uncle bill s green split pea with hambone soup
review: Very good soup.  It doesn't look like it needs me to say anything else about it.

name: mean s dutch babies
review: Good! Made as directed with sugar but made batter in the blender. A nice base for fruit or powdered sugar and lemon. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: I was slightly dissapointed. They were a little heavy. I would like to have had a tiny bit more imformation on the directions.like temp, app time and cooking spray or not. We still enjoyed them and will try again

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: This was fantastic!  I used the Modena glaze balsamic vinegar, added some roasted garlic from the freezer and layered the bottom of the baking dish with onions.  No skin- no bone, baked for 30 minutes at 350 degrees. I will add more than 1/2 onion next time as they were wonderful in their own right!  thank you.

name: moist and tender turkey  or turkey breast
review: Other than taking longer ( I think my oven is broken) I made this as directed and it was very moist and flavorful.  Will definitely do this again soon as it was so easy.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: Great easy recipe.  Added an extra can of tomatoes.  Fresh basil and 1/4 tsp red chili flakes.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: I had this for a family gathering.  Everyone loved it.  It was so simple to make.  Thanks for posting.

name: hot german potato salad
review: This was the best part of our meal today.  I halved the recipe and got good results. Definitely will be having these again.

name: potato salad with chipotle peppers a man s salad
review: A hose under the sink broke and started flooding the kitchen when I was in the middle of making this.  :( That's my excuse for totally forgetting to add the black beans.  Didn't seem to matter, though, since everybody agreed it was sensational.  I used 3 chipotles, seeds and all, and the heat level was actually pretty mild.  Thanks for a really top-notch recipe, Rita!  Update:  Six years and a whole lot of bowls of potato salad later, I don't think I've ever served this to anyone who didn't rave.  So many people told me at a cookout last weekend that it was THE BEST they'd ever tasted that I just had to thank you again for sharing this wonderful dish.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review:
Made exactly as suggested. Outstanding with vinegar in topping.

Next time I may add peppers to meat mixture. Will make again!

name: crispy ginger beef
review: Really good! Definitely a do-over. Everyone enjoyed it, including my kids who aren't fans of the spicy. That said, those with sensitive palates may want to cut back on the crushed red pepper. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: I made this in the microwave tonight, scaled down to one serving, in an 8 oz. coffee mug. Since it was a smaller quantity, I only nuked it for two minutes, stirring after each. By the time it was done, it had reached the top of the mug but did not overflow. I ate it right away, and it was very good. Thank you!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: These were very good biscuits. They puffed up really high. I made the buttermilk with milk and vinegar that morning. I froze the butter and grated it.

name: soft italian breadsticks  abm
review:
Just great! I used 1/3 whole wheat flour. We will definitely make these again. My kids would have eaten more than two each if I had let them. So glad to have a good breadsticks recipe.

Thanks!

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: Easy to prepare (microwave method for the squash) and delicious!

name: now don t go  eeewww    before you try this
review: I had no idea what to expect.  The fragrance of the rye wafted to my nostrils as I took it out of the toaster.  Then the peanut butter hit.  Maybe it's the tomato that brings them together.  When I bit into it I was surprised....it was good.  Can't say it will be my go to sandwich....however, it was really nice.  Interesting, it was posted in 2002 and there hasn't been a review since then...til now.

name: all purpose stir fry sauce  brown garlic sauce
review:
Restaurant quality stuff! I used 1/3 light & 1/3 dark soy so it wouldn't be overly salty for us & fried some fresh chilli with our onion, garlic & ginger...
Loads of fresh veggies, some tofu & freshly cooked rice on the side....this has knocked our regular stir-fry sauce out of rotation, with it never to be looked at again!
Thanks, Connie K, you're a stir-fry saver! :)

name: kittencal s  brown sugar caramel sauce or ice cream topping
review: I cut the recipe in half and drizzled it over a chocolate bundt cake.  It was super easy to make and way better than anything you could buy at the store.

name: crock pot thai chicken thighs
review:
I'm giving this 3 stars because of the coconut rice... that was delightful!

The chicken thighs... I couldn't eat them... maybe it is because I am pregnant and things just are weird for me right now... my husband said it was "ok" and my DD wouldn't touch it...

Keeping the rice recipe, but not the main dish...

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: I made this for my neighbors birthday. They all said it was so good. I didnt make the frosting. I bought chocolate frosting from the store. I liked it plain. No frosting. So much banana flavor. Next time I will put chopped walnuts in mix. First time making a cake that didn't come from a box. Very moist!!!!

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: I don't like mustard but went ahead and used it. Fortunately you couldn't taste it much with the finally results. I also put this under the broiler for a few minutes when it was done to brown the top. This tasted good.

name: beef patties in onion gravy
review: Finally made these and they were a hit.  Thank You!

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: Yummy! I made this to put on chili stuffed enchiladas. This is by far the best recipe for enchilada sauce I've found. I made it as written and wouldn't change a thing. Thanks for sharing.

name: crock pot thai chicken thighs
review: I've never seen cilantro salsa so I used a jar of tomatillo salsa instead.  I had 12 small thighs and there was more than enough sauce.  Yummy and easy.

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: The only thing I did different was add some lemon juice to the apples.  Delish!!!

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: After making this soup, I wanted to make it a bit heartier, plus I thought the soup didn't have enough whole black beans. With that being said, I also noticed I ran out of canned black beans, so I ended up adding a can of pinto and a can of soy beans, plus I added 2 cups of frozen corn kernels. Since I added the corn and more beans, I found I only needed to simmer the soup for 30 minutes for it to thicken up. I did want to mention... when saute'ing the vegetables in oil, I did use 2-1/2 tablespoons, plus I added a bit more carrots (2/3's cup). I saute'd the vegetables for 9 minutes before adding the garlic, and after adding the garlic, I only saute'd it for 1 more minute. I enjoyed this soup topped with shredded sharp cheddar cheese and sour cream. I do think by adding the hickory flavored liquid smoke, it gave the soup lots of flavor. My husband and I enjoyed this soup, and I will make this again, but with the modifications I made. Little Bee, thanks for sharing the recipe!!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: I was skeptical, but it was great!  Started it off in my crock pot, cooked it for about 4-5 hours, then put it in my oven to brown it.  Since my oven has a built in thermometer I used that to gauge how cooked it was.  After it was browned, I put in a dish, covered with tin foil and transfered to my lower oven to keep warm a couple of hours.

name: fabulous beef stew
review: This is great and so easy! I was out of canned tomatoes, but had half a package of dried tomatoes which I used along with 2 cups of water. A bit sweeter than using just regular tomatoes but good anyways! Thanks for sharing!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: YUMMY! and super cheap! bought some sale meat to make and didn't have to purchase anything else!! Everyone went nuts over it!! Used Bento or Bust's idea and turned out wonderful! Didnt wanna run for green onions so used some chopped celery and minced onions. Served over nice, fluffy minute rice and tossed some broccoli in the sauce. Already have a request to make it for a special little girls birthday in April of next year! THANKS TISH!!

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Wow! We were pleasantly surprised at how good this was! We'll definitely be having it often. Thanks!

name: thai chicken breasts
review: Too sour for us so I'll be using only 1/4 cup of vinegar the next time.

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: So good and so easy. I couldn't ask for a better recipe. I hate peeling the silks and this is so much easier. We will make it this way again and again. YUM!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: We baked a whole fillet with skin at 450 for approx 10 mins..........didn't have enough honey for the sauce so used cinnamon honey and it turned out awesome!! We added the sauce to each individual pc. Served with edamame and other vegies. Looks like we will have excess sauce so will be tryiing on some chicken breasts

name: wet burritos
review: This was good!  I made it to reheat another day and found the flavor intensified and was much better the second day.  The burritos were great but I wasn't totally in love with the sauce...not that it was bad, just not fantastic!  When we make it again we will do a more enchilada/taco  sauce mixture.  Thanks for the recipe Terri F.

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: I too cut the oil and sugar down to 3 tablespoons each.  Outstanding!  Bonus points for easy to follow directions-bread anything has never been my forte.  One half I topped with sauted diced onions, the other with a "everything" blend.  I won't be buying hamburger buns ever again!  Thanks for posting!

name: easy garlic chicken
review: We loved this! The taste was amazing and the simplicity was the best part. Thanks for a great recipe :)

name: classic baked spaghetti
review: Easy and delicious.

name: microwave poached egg on toast
review: I made this for my son and I for breakfast. I have to agree with others that the egg is good but my bread was too chewy. We ate the middle of the bread and left the crust as it was a bit hard to chew. You do need to play with the times for your microwave. My first egg was a bit harder then the second.

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: This is indeed an excellent way of preparing corn on the cob, especially for a large number of people.  However, for the sake of energy savings, as well as time, try doing this in the microwave.  I do mine 3mins. for one ear, 4 mins for 3, etc.  My MW is a 900W oven, yours could be 700, 900, or 1000W, so times can vary.  There are several recipes in the DB.  For six or more people a traditional oven still works wonders!  Thanks,  Chef PotPie!

name: general tso s chicken  tso chung gai
review: So good that I need to double the chicken and the sauce.

name: chipotle roast for tacos   sandwiches
review: Very easy but with great flavors.  So many ways to use the meat, great ideas.

name: awesome baked ham
review: Moist and very easy. Good basic ham. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: A keeper.

name: roast  sticky  chicken
review: Very good and easy.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Quite easy to put together and easy to make.  I had really hoped after reading all the great reviews that we would love these, too.  Roasting resulted in an okay result for us but we won't be making it again.  We weren't wild about the texture of the cooked sprouts and the aroma from the oven permeated the whole house.

name: caesar pork chops
review: Very tasty.

name: new mexico style chili chicken casserole
review: This was delicious!  It was so nice and creamy.  DH really liked it.  Will make again soon.  Thanks for posting this yummy recipe.

name: taco bell quesadillas
review: These were okay. Easy enough to make. Good for last minute supper idea.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Just wanted to add my five stars to it. A friend of mine at work's husband says meatloaf is his favorite meal, and that this is his favorite meatloaf. Thanks for the last meatloaf recipe I will ever need.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Yum! I need to remember to double this next time. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: fantastic taco casserole
review:
This was great, but a little salty. That may have been my fault though because I made homemade refried beans. Next time I'll omit the salt and might try making my own taco seasoning w/o it. I added a whole chopped green pepper to the hamburger (awesome!) and a layer of frozen very sweet corn between the meat and bean layers to balance the saltiness. I would definitely do that again, and possible add more. I am not a huge fan of chips, so the chip layer was so-so for me, but DH liked it. I think next time I might try noodles instead and maybe double the beans and 1/2 the meat. Thanks for the keeper, Leilani!

Update: I made these with Manny's Lemon Tortilla chips today and packed them into a 2 cup measuring cup today. Didn't add any cheese to the beans (can of refried black with lime), used Paul Newman's Mango salsa and added 1/4 cup cheddar to the top. it was Fabulous! And not too salty.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review:
Very good - I added peas as suggested and used part sour cream instead of all mayonnaise
UPDATE_ i think I will have to do as another suggested and pre cook bisquits or cook longer. Mine were not done until cooked longer.UPDATE This time I used cream of mushroom soup and instead of milk I used almond milk and added the green peas some thyme, cumin and oregano So yummy and not rich at all though I did not read the recipe so mixed in the cheese with the ingredients for the chicken

name: divine meatball sandwiches
review: Fabulous! The best meatball sandwich I've ever made (or eaten!) I had some 6" Bolillo rolls and recipe #443650 dunked in recipe #290736. Made half the amount of cream cheese mixture (using light mayo and Neufchatel cheese) and it was enough for four 6" sandwiches. The only change I made was using sliced provolone instead of shredded mozzarella. Thanks for sharing!

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: I made the recipe as directed, I found that overall, the dish was too dry. I baked longer to try to soften the apples and still was too dry, had to serve with milk on top. The only thing different I did was use Gala apples? I thought the flavor was good, but definitely needs something to moisten it up.

name: best twice baked potatoes
review: Delicious potatoes.   Wouldn't change a thing.

name: 24k carrots
review: It was ok.  Needed to try to thicken the sauce on the heat a bit more.

name: the best belgian waffles
review: I was looking for a recipe to use in my new Kitchenaid Pro Line waffle maker.  I chose this one because someone said that this one is so good they don't want to try any others, and that it's crisp outside and so light inside.  It's true!  I feel no need to try any other recipes, and that is unusual for me!  I used half cake flour and half white whole wheat.  I did add about a tsp of vanilla and 2 tbsp malted milk powder.  I ended up with a waffle as good as any I've had at a restaurant--where I'd pay $6-$8 for it.  The whole family was delighted, and my boys asked if I'm make them every night.  I had to say no to that but we will be making them often!!!!  I got 6 waffles from my Kitchenaid.

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: Great recipe! I made this to serve over bacon wrapped chicken and it was delish! Thx Dana!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: I cut back the sugar a little and I added 2 tsp of cinnamon to the batter. I had to cook it longer than the recipe called for, even though I had the oven set at 300F. I only made half the icing and it was plenty. The whole family loved it, so it's a keeper.

name: old widow walker s ziploc omelettes
review: Not sure why but ours did not slide out of the bag like an omelette.  We ended up scooping them out onto plates, looked more like scrambled eggs.  They tasted good, though.  If anyone can tell me what I did wrong that would be awesome.  Thanks!

name: broiled tilapia with thai coconut  curry sauce
review: Excellent dish! A great way to eat fish. I also used some fish sauce in the sauce and I would say that it is a must to serve with the lime wedge, really brings out the flavours. This sauce would be great with chicken as well.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Much, much better than any pot pie I have made with a can of cream of chicken.  Really loved the creaminess and how thick it was.  The only reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 is because it was a little bland for my taste.  I tasted the mixture before pouring it in the dish and added sage, thyme, and rosemary for some flavor.  I used a rotisserie chicken which was the perfect amount and shredded it...soooo good!!  It makes a lot.  Really tasty.

name: mama iuliucci s famous meat a balls  italian meatballs
review: Easy, and ingredients I have in my pantry every day.  Oh, and did I mention they are delicious?  Next time I'll make the sauce you recommended, because my jarred sauce didn't cut it.  I put them in the crock pot and simmered them and they got so tender.  Thanks for sharing, Karen.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: The flavor of these was great, but the texture was odd.  The middle seemed almost like a firm fudge and they did NOT cut well, we ended up getting it out of the pan best we could and eating it with ice cream.  I don't think I would make them again unless I could figure out how to get them to cut into nice squares.  I am somewhat of a picky person in that way I guess.  The taste was fabulous, though!!!

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Made without machine, omitted egg and baked them at 375 for 12 minutes, totally epic.

name: buttery shrimp and pasta
review: Wonderful blend of flavors, with a rich creamy sauce. I scaled this down for one hefty serving. Made as written using orecchiette pasta, minus the red pepper flakes and did add a white wine/cornstarch slurry at the end to really thicken the sauce, the result was a delicious evening meal. Thanks! Made for "Down on the Farm" Photo Tag May 2012!

name: frizzled cabbage
review: Fabulous!  I'm putting this into my new whole-foods, plant-based recipe recipe cycle.  Thanks for posting!  Healthy tastes good!

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: This was great! I was scared of using too much tarragon- so I used 1/2, but I think that's what gives it a great, unique, homey taste.Plus, it's made in the crockpot and NOT an all day thing!! This will be made again & again at my house!! Thank you so much!!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: We enjoyed broccoli cooked this way so much.  It was crisp -tender and it really did have a roasted flavor.  I added a little onion to the pan and cooked it for a few minutes before putting in the broccoli.  My son, who rarely makes any comments about vegetables I make said this was the best broccoli ever.  I asked him why and he said "it wasn't all mushy with no flavor like most broccoli."  It got a thumbs-up from everyone in the house -- thanks for sharing your recipe.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: Hmm- pretty good. To decrease the fat, I made a white sauce with butter, milk, and flour instead of using cream. I also used rotini pasta instead of linguine, which was not a great choice on my part! But I like how simple this recipe is. I will make it again!

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: EXCELLENT! Enuff said!!!!  Oh okay, I will say I cut down on the sugar just because that's my personal preference.  I also didn't have red wine vinegar so I used apple cider vinegar.  Super delish...will be making it more and more...thank you for sharing!!!

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: Thanks! We love chicken wings. I used your recipe more or less as it was given, but I added some turmeric extra for colour, also some brilliant seasoning spice we get here. The wings were delicious!We had it as a main meat dish with veggies for supper.

name: cinnamon swirl quick bread
review: This recipe really does not need another review but felt I had to add mine as well.  It is our all time favorite quick bread recipe and always turns out well.   Sometimes I use 2 eggs because this seems to give a better texture - taste is still the same.    Highly recommended.......

name: zesty italian crescent casserole
review: This was ok.  It was quick and easy.

name: pork chops in onion sauce  schweinekotelett in zwiebelsosse
review: Delicious! I made the recipe as directed using 2 boneless thick pork chops. DH loved the onion gravy.

name: kittencal s italian zucchini mozzarella patties
review: These are soooo good. I made a full batch and they were devoured within minutes. I'd double it if you're making it for more than 2. We dipped ours in marinara and it was an excellent complement.

name: best banana bread
review: I made 7 small loaves with this recipe for a bake sale.  I replace the butter with canola and added cinnamon, allspice and cloves.  Good texture, good bread.

name: cottage cheese roast  vegetarian meatloaf
review: I have to admit,  no one was very excited when they saw what was for dinner.  We were all pleasantly surprised. DH is a meat and potatoes guy and he had seconds!  I used low fat cottage cheese, corn flakes, and egg beaters.  I baked it for 60 minutes.  Next time I might leave it in an extra 5 minutes, but wouldn't make any other changes.  Thanks for a great meal.

name: banana banana bread
review: Made 7 of these for a bake sale using pans that equal about 2 - 2.5 regular size muffins.  I added Cinnamon and ginger.  Replaced butter with canola.  The outside forms a bit of a "crust" and the inside are moist and lovely.

name: quick and easy pizza dough
review: Lovely simple reciipe, I did mine in the breadmaker.

name: weight watchers general tso s chicken
review:
Very nice entree. I read many reviews and took ideas from all. I served it with white rice and egg rolls. I added red bell pepper, onion and garlic to the chicken as I browned it in sesame oil. I added water chestnuts just to heat and I followed other reviewers advice and cut the corn starch to 1 Tbsp and used 1 1/2 Tbsp of Splenda instead of sugar.
I will add a little more soy sauce next time for a little more depth of flavor. I too am a whimp when it comes to hot stuff so cut the red pepper flakes to 1/4 tsp. I used regular onions instead of scallions. I used skinless boneless chicken thighs and they were moist and tender. All in all a nice oriental dish and we will have it again. Thanks,
Carole in Orlando

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: My usual "no fail" chocolate cake recipe was failing me--so I needed a new one fast--and this is it!  I used an additional cup of milk instead of the coffee and thought it was still lovely, rich, and moist.  A definite keeper!  As a plus, it baked up fairly evenly for decorating (I used my own frosting, but this one does look good)!  Thank you for saving me and for the great recipe!

name: dark chocolate cake
review: Awesome Chocolate Cake recipe, was a huge success and hit. In place of the Boiling Water, I used a 1/2 Cup of Mocha Nut Espresso, it is a nice compliment to the chocolate in this recipe and adds to the depth of flavor. Super easy, and will be my "go to" for chocolate cake". Thank You Marg

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: This was amazing.  My daughter does not eat meat so this really worked for having her over for lunch and she ate two helpings.  I did read the reviews and draned my tomatoes and added about a teaspoon of taco seasoning.  I will make this again and again.

name: new york style pizza crust
review: Easy! Loved it. Going in our regular rotation. Didn't need any extra flour. Everyone devoured it. Fed just two adults and two little girls so a bigger family better plan on doubling it!

name: slow cooked bbq ribs  for crock pot
review: I made these as directed but cooked mine on high for five hours and they were perfect. We all enjoyed them.

name: easiest tastiest barbecue country style ribs  slow cooker
review: Good and easy to make. I cooked mine on high for five hours and they were perfect. I did add more sauce after I took them out of the crockpot. We all enjoyed these.

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: These were great!  Tried as is but may try with buttermilk.  I grew up on buttermilk pancakes so I have a sweet spot for them.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: My husband turned up his nose when I told him what we were having for dinner.  After he tasted it, he said I could definately make it again.  He instructed me to give it 5 stars!

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: This was good but slightly too acidic for me. Served on top of a Chicago Style pizza

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: Great pancake recipe, very simple and delicious!!

name: classic baked spaghetti
review: This was a good basic recipe. I followed the recipe as written other then I used cheddar and mozz cheese. We thought it could have used more seasonings. This was a great weeknight meal that heated up nicely for my lunches.

name: the ultimate strawberry shortcake
review: Made half a recipe and used sponge cake.  Excellent!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: This was pretty good.  I made exactly as directed.  I had trouble with the steak being tough but probably because I bought a cheaper cut of meat.

name: new york style pizza crust
review: This is great crust.  I made this last night and the only problem I had with it was, I wished I would have made two!! We loved it.  It cooked up beautifully and just the right thickness.  I didn't use a pizza pan but just a regular jelly roll pan.  We loved it, thank you for sharing this recipe with us.

name: banana banana bread
review: I used this recipe to teach my 10 yr old DGD how to bake.  She did all the mixing, measuring, and baking.  I just stood by and gave her specific instructions for each step given.  She did a wonderful job and I am proud of her.  This banana bread was very good.  I personally look like the bread if it were a little bit sweeter since I enjoy banana bread that way the best.  Next time I will increase the brown sugar to 1 cup instead of the 3/4 cup listed.  I'm not penalizing the chef for my desire to have it be sweeter since that is a personal choice...especially since everything else about the recipe is perfect.

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: Great cake.  I used a yellow cake mix and cooked in two round pans for 40 minutes.

name: veronica s easy spanish rice
review: Good, but not over the top for me.  I added some oregano and 1 T of chipotle sauce to kick it up a bit.  Will use this tonight in some 7 layer burritos.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: I'm not giving this any stars.  It was WAY too salty (and I love salt), and not sure whether it was that I had a fairly small head of cauliflower, or the recipe just calls for too much salt.  I'm going to grab another head this weekend and try again.  As is, I would give it a 3-4*--very good, but just needs less salt.

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: I only added a dash of cayenne and omitted the crushed red pepper, I just personal preference.  Very good flavor, nice blend of spices.

name: parmesan crusted tilapia
review: Great tilapia.  Served with Baked Parmesan Tomatoes from eating well and both were baked at the same time.  Easy and filling meal.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: Very good flavor, but I was so surprised at how thin it was~~even after trying to thicken it up with corn starch.  Next time, I will definitely add more potatoes to the initial soup.  For now, I've sent my husband to the store to buy some frozen cubed hash browns that I can whip up and add to the leftover soup I have.  Thanks for posting!  Love the cream cheese twist!

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: This was super terrific.  Can't say anything else about this - made it exactly as shown (which I rarely do....) and it was great.  Can't wait to taste it as left overs, cold.  I bet it will be great that way too!  Thanks!!!!

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: The name of this recipe says it all as this is The Ultimate Greek Salad!  This makes a nice large family salad that was enjoyed by all. I made one small change in that I cut the olive oil in half as my lettuce was still fairly moist from washing, other than that made as written. We thought the garlic and oregano were the perfectly proportion to the other ingredients and DH who quite often does not like the stronger flavored onions thought the soaking did a nice job taking the edge off.  Thanks for the post.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: Due to a lack of communication, we had multiple rotisserie chickens in the fridge. 1.5x'd this to serve 5. Used Silver Palate Gazpacho salsa and 4 cheese Mexican cheese. Served with chopped tomatoes, avocado chunks, and sour cream. Never had 'real' chimichangas so can't compare, but these were great!

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: I'll add one more review.  My issues were with the ounces and the packages I got at my small market, and I think I used too much of something, BUT it was excellent.  My roast was a tad overdone cooking it 7 hours, so I will reduce the cooking time next time.  I will also add the potatoes and carrots long before I did this time.  We had to nuke those so we could eat.  New crockpot; new recipe.  This, like so many other reviewers, will be my standard recipe now for roasts.  I will get more packets and make sure I have everything but the roast on hand when I want a good meal.  Excellent.

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: Fabulous marinade.  Grilled it to  perfection, and even great leftover.

name: all purpose stir fry sauce  brown garlic sauce
review: I wish I had read Connie's comments before making the recipe.  It was indeed salty!  It has great potential...next time.  I will pencil in a reminder to reduce the soy sauce.  Other than that, a great all-purpose sauce.

name: wholly guacamole
review: Best guacamole I have made yet.  Thanks for the recipe!!!

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: A delightful sandwich that received mixed reviews. Those who grew up eating Sloppy Joe's loved this and said it was outstanding. Then there were those whom grew up eating something similar to this but without the sugar and with the addition of Worcestershire sauce who enjoyed but not as much as the Sloppy Joe eaters. I did make this as written right down to using a cast iron pan and traditional yellow mustard with some really good dill pickle slices. This was received well enough that I will be making it again, thanks for the post.

name: ginger me up chicken  low fat honey   ginger chicken breasts
review: I like the combination of ingredients in this sauce! But hubby is not fond of ginger, so I can only use about 1/2-1 tsp of ground ginger.

name: lemon baked cod
review:
i used gluten free flour and put in fridge an hour before baking wonderful recipe
.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: The taste of these pork chops was great, but even after keeping them covered, they still turned out dry. Also, by covering the pan, I wasn't able to get any of the liquids in the sauce to evaporate. To have moist chops and a great sauce would've made this a 5 star review from me. Still tasty nonetheless and I'm sure I'll make it again, but let it marinate for a bit before cooking. UPDATE: I originally posted the above in 12/10 and I recently made these again. I browned them then followed other reviewers suggestions and covered them and removed the foil for the last 10 minutes. This time, though, I only cooked them for a half hour and (20 minutes covered, 10 minutes uncovered) and they were still dried out. I think I will try this on the stove top next time to see if it helps. But on a side note, I did get the sauce that I had trouble getting the last time.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: This was really good but the there should not be a layer of noodles on top. It should have had sauce then cheese. The noodles got super hard and the cheese became one with the noodles so you lost the ooey gooey effect. Great flavor, but missed the mark with the execution.

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: Nice chop recipe. I used a rib end cut. Loved what the lemon zest brings to the flavor. Forgot to add the Parmesan to the crumbs, so added it on top at the end. Oven temp. and time baked was spot on. :)

name: cream cheese cinnamon crescents
review: Very good and rich!  Made 1/2 the recipe and used the crescent sheet which I cut in half.  Only had 6 oz of cream cheese but was plenty.  Will be making this again!  Made for Down on the Farm Tag.

name: weight watchers general tso s chicken
review: Not ever having the real thing before I can't compare it but this recipe has a great taste.  I changed the sweetness because I'm not a fan of sweet and sour.  I doubled the recipe but not the chicken.  Added some chopped mushrooms and asparagus, cut on the diagonal to replace the chicken amount.  Used a whole can of chicken broth and decreased the corn starch to 3 level tablespoons.  I used 1 teaspoon of vinegar and 1/2 t. sugar.  Per serving I only used 1/2 c. rice and 1 c. of the chicken and sauce.  I didn't figure out the calories but it has to be a lot less than the nutritional information for this recipe.  Delicious!!  I foresee making this many times in the future.  Thanks for posting!!

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: This fruit salad was very good. I was asked to make it again next time, so it must have passed. I did not add the sugar. I used french vanilla pudding. I'm not sure the banana is necessary, but if it's important to you, you might use 2 or 3 bananas. One was very little. Also, I mixed the fruit juices a little at a time until the pudding seemed to be the right consistency, so not all of the juice was used.

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: Excellent recipe! I did drain and rinse the black beans, using vegetable broth to soften the sauteed onion and garlic.  I served with brown rice with lime.  The seasoning was perfect.  I will definitely serve this delicious recipe again.  Thank you for sharing your recipe!

name: detweiler sloppy joe mix
review:
I made this for lunch today and my 10 yr old really enjoyed these.
I had to omit the peppers but that was it. Loved the brown sugar!

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: This was delicious. Everyone loved it. I added a little Beau Monde and Herbes de Provence.

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: This was good and easy to make. I did change it up though. I made this in a pan on the grill. I used six boneless skinless chicken breasts, a can of cream of chicken, a can of cheddar cheese soup, garlic powder and pepper. I cooked these for 30 minutes. We all enjoyed this with the changes made.

name: french bread rolls to die for
review: They were so easy to make and so delicious and beautiful - high and rounded like bakery French rolls.  I made 24 smaller rolls for a buffet supper and everyone loved them.  Delicious hot, but equally good and substantial at room temperature for small party sandwich rolls.   These freeze well as soon as they are cooled, and will keep for about 1 month in freezer.  Next, I'm going to try freezing the rolls BEFORE baking; defrost, let rise, and then bake.  Will update review after this trial.

name: rhubarb crisp
review: I doubled the rhubarb and reduced the white sugar to 3/4c and it turned out to be the perfect proportions - sweet and tangy. I I also subbed the flour for Bob's Gluten Free Flour mix for  a GF guest.  t got rave reviews at the party I took it to.

name: linda s cheesecake stuffed strawberries
review: Made these for my grandtwins 1st birthday party - everyone loved them including the birthday boy & girl.  Thanks for posting Linda!

name: zesty italian crescent casserole
review: Very good recipe.  I made this and we really liked it.  Its a good base recipe and anything can be added with it.  Thank you for sharing with great recipe with us.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Delicious!  I halved the recipe for 2 chicken breasts.. I didn't have a fresh lemon and lime, but I used 3 tbsp bottled lemon juice (for half the recipe) and it was perfect.  I marinaded it for about 3 hours, part of the time the breasts were still partially frozen.. worked great but next time I'll try to do it the night before!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: We have both meat eaters and vegetarians in our family.  I used Quorn naked cutlets for the vegetarians and boneless skinless chicken breasts for the meat eaters.  I also used a light mayo.  But other than that followed the recipe.  It was enjoyed by everyone, which is rare in our house.  The chicken took longer than 45 minutes to cook but the breasts were on the larger side.  The Quorn only took 20-25 minutes and I did not defrost the cutlets before baking.  The only thing I may do differently is reduce the amount of seasoned salt next time.  It was just a little on the strong side.  I will be adding this to my cook book for sure. Thanks!!

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Delicious way to eat cauliflower!

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: Can't go wrong with this recipe! Yummy!! The only thing I did differently was to omit the dill. We loved the flavor and crispyness of these potatoes and onions. Note: I sliced my onions thin but they tended to burn. Next time I will slice the onions thicker. Thanks!

name: berry smash muffins  strawberry muffins
review:
I decided to give this a shot, and I think I've made it 4 times since then... I just couldn't stop making it! I actually used raspberries (frozen, defrosted) instead of strawberries and baked it as a bread instead of muffins. Really good flavor, moist, and very easy to make!

Thanks! :)

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Love these - have made them a few times so thought I should go ahead and add another review, as if it needs another one!  I used panko bread crumbs and the cutlets came out nice and crunchy. Make great leftovers as well. Will be making again, thanks!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: We don't have PF Chang here in Ontario so I cannot speak to how closely it resembles the original but it is an excellent dish!  Made more or less as directed - I made 50% more sauce but did not increase the sugar.  I was using a Prime Rib Steak so I didn't cook it as long in the sauce as suggested.  Served with steamed rice and stir fried vegertables it was a hit at my table.  Thanks for posting!

name: basic batter waffles
review: OmG best waffles ever!!!   And so simple to make!!!  No more mixes for me!!

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: These were good and easy to make. Next time I would cut back on how many potatoes I use (I did follow the recipe exactly as written) because some potatoes had good flavor and others didn't have any at all. I cooked these on the grill for 50 minutes. We enjoyed them but wish each piece had more flavor.

name: banana oatmeal bread
review: Sorry, out of 15 people, only one liked the oatmeal in this. I made this as recipe states. Everyone said the bread was too tough. The one who liked it just liked the taste of raw oatmeal in it. Sorry, this was a fail here.

name: old fashioned linguine with white clam sauce
review: Just wanted to add my 5 stars to the rating.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Another 5 star review to rack up your total to 428.  There's nothing I can add that has not already been said.  Really easy to make-came together great-ingredients that most folks have on hand....oh yeah, and it was really, really YUMMY!  Thanks for posting, Di ;-)

name: panda express orange chicken
review: The directions are a bit confusing, I had to read it 3-4 times before I understood it. For me there was way too much vinegar in it, I broke out coughing every time I tried to taste it. I had to add more sugar. For me there was enough sauce.  Made for Chef Alphabet Soup

name: crock pot chili pork chops     a must try
review: What a great chop recipe.  I loved the sauce in this.  Thanks for a great recipe.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: It was great! I didn't get as good of a char on mine as in the picture, but maybe next time I will. Thank you!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: This was delicious. DH said it looked liked a picture out of a book. I think next time I will add some salsa to the sauce with the chillies. Yum

name: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
review: I took this to an end of the year party at work.  When we have to bring a dish to pass, I am always asked to bring desserts.  I always come home with an empty plate and have started taking a copy of the recipe for what ever dessert I make, because someone always asks for it.  Well, I came home with 2/3 of the cake.  So disappointed.  It wasn't over done, the texture and flavor were good but it was dry.  Sorry, I won't be making this again.

name: thai chicken breasts
review: Wonderful recipe. I used white balsamic vinegar as I was out of white wine vinegar. I double the sauce ingredients and added extra red pepper flakes. Everyone raved about the chicken all through the meal and ate every bit of it. When they ask when will you make it again while they are still eating, you know you have a hit! I served it with Calrose rice and steamed broccoli. Thanks for sharing such a delicious and easy recipe.

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: This was delicious.  I used just one tablespoon of butter for three small squash.  I cooked it until it was nice and browned.  My son, who hates every kind of squash, ate it without complaint, and my husband and I loved it.  Thanks for posting.

name: steel cut oatmeal for the crock pot
review: Originally Reviewed March 2011.  Edited May 2012 to add stars (how did I forget?)  Excellent!  Made with only a pinch of salt in a small crock.  Stirred in cinnamon, maple syrup, craisins, and some powdered milk when cooking was finished.  I usually make oatmeal with milk instead of water, but didn't want to have milk cooking overnight in a crock because I was afraid it would curdle or scorch.  The powdered milk worked perfectly.  My whole family loved it.  The first recipe I've tried for steel cut oats, and it was delicious!  I have successfully doubled the recipe in a larger crockpot.  With my husband and I and three young children who love oatmeal, we rarely have more than 1 serving left over!

name: yummy crispy baked fish
review: We really liked this fish. The tilapia was nice and crisp on the outside and had great flavor. The only thing I will try differently next time is to sprtiz the top of the fish coating with Pam so it doesn't get too dry. Loved the flavor and it was nice and healthy, too! Thanks. :)  Made for the Healthy Choices tag game.

name: spinach   feta stuffed chicken breast  quick   easy
review: This is a very flavorful and easy to make recipe. We all loved it and I have made it twice so far, with no changes to your recipe. It's perfect just as you wrote it. Thanks for sharing!

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Not our preference, I guess. Husband really doesn't like strongly acidic tastes, and I thought this was very vinegary. I discovered this after it sat for several hours in fridge; I made it palatable for him by adding more sugar and salt to cut the acid, but now it just lacks flavor. I read elsewhere that one should emulsify oil and vinegar for a pasta salad, otherwise the vinegar soaks into the pasta (resulting in strong flavor) while the oil clings. But others like it...!

name: awesome baked ham
review: Yum! I recently learned from an Amish friend that the way to have delicious, super-soft ham is simply to roast for hours in the oven like this recipe! But it's too hot to have the oven on that long, so I did this in the crockpot on Low for 5 hours. (no foil) Delicious!

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: I have virtually this same recipe in a Milk calendar from way back in the 80's.  My recipe calls for 1-1/2 c. oats, melted butter or margarine instead of the oil, and adds 1/2 tsp. cinnamon.  DEEEELISH!

name: strawberries   cream bread  strawberry or blueberry
review: so good as muffins!

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: What a great idea!!  It was good enough to make my cauliflower-hatin' husband eat it!  I just thought the sour cream flavour was stronger than anything else.  Next time I will try with fat free ranch dressing or less of the fat free sour cream.

name: peanut butter cup cookies  tarts
review: I've been meaning to try this recipe for a long time but had it in my head that they would be too time- consuming & finicky - NOT SO!  So, so easy & so delicious!!  I made them to take to a housewarming party & they were gobbled up first!  I didn't even bother rolling into balls - I just dropped by teaspoon into the muffin tins & they formed beautifully into tart shells.  I also used the really mini Reese's pb cups that are already unwrapped so that saved time.  I managed to get 4 dozen cookies out of this recipe & there were more than enough pb cups in one bag.

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: LOVED this.  It was so easy to make (even despite my aversion to mayo)!  I used the olive oil mayo in this recipe and found it super easy to assemble and bake up.  I even enjoyed leftovers up to 2 days later crisped up in the toaster oven!  Thanks so much for an simple, tasty dish.  Would love to try this for eggplant parmesan dish.

name: chicken stroganoff   crock pot
review: Super quick and easy.  I used cream of chicken soup, since that's what I had on hand.  I meant to put in an onion, but forgot.  It was a very "white" meal served over rice.  Perhaps some peas and carrots would help with that.  Cooked on low about 3 hours and high for an hour and a half.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: These were easy to make and tastes great. Thanks for the recipe.

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: These are wonderful. I made them thick so they were soft and chewy. My family loved them. Thanks for the recipe

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: 5 stars for being the easiest chicken Ive ever made and it tasted good too!  halved the recipe using 1 can cream of mushroom and 1 can cheddar soup.  put breasts in frozen for 4 hours on low and they were perfect.  threw some broccoli in at the end.

name: brown sugar bundt cake
review: So my daughter came home from school and told me that she needed a cake that would represent the 1930's. After a bit of research I found that round cakes were all the rage back then.  I am not sure they had cake mixes back then, but with the last minute notice from my daughter, I figured no one would know the difference. This is so easy to make. My daughter brought home the leftovers and my boys practically inhaled what was left. One kept commenting on how moist the cake was. Thank you for a hit at school and at home.

name: poverty meal
review: Delicious!  I like using diced canned tomatoes, sharp cheddar cheese, and a can of drained corn with this recipe.    I often freeze this and give it to working gals to have on hand when they need a quick dinner.  Thanks for posting and reminding us of the  old-timey economical goulash-type recipes.

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: Totally fattening, but so yummy and moist! A sweet indulgence!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Wow! This was really good! I don't think you really needed another review however, it was sooo delish...I just had too! I used fresh minced garlic and marinated with Chinese 5 Spice seasoning instead of ginger! Will for sure make this again! Thanks for posting such an easy recipe...also...tried it with chicken...that was really good too!

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: This was mixed in less than 5 minutes and resulted in a cake everyone in the house loved. I added 1 c semisweet chocolate chips on top before baking. Thanks for sharing a recipe that I will make again and again.

name: black bottom banana bars
review: Oh gosh. I made these tonight and haven't been able to stop snacking on it since! I made a few changes: for the 1/2 cup of butter, I used 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup plain yogurt (which seems to have definitely upped the moistness of the bars. They almost melt in my mouth!) I also used less than a cup of sugar; maybe about 3/4 though I might try it with 1/2 cup next time as I like less sweet desserts. I also doubled the vanilla, used a very full 1/3 cup of cocoa (the base became very chocolatey and delicious) and added some cinnamon to the batter as well. Yum yum yum! Mine ended up baking for just under 30 minutes and it is so delicious! Thanks so much!

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: My daughter made this for me for Mother's Day by my request.  I have had this recipe saved in my "Want to Try" cookbook for a long time and was waiting for the right occasion to try it.  I must say that it turned out perfect!  She loaded it up with lots of granny smith apples and added the topping and it was beautiful.  And the taste lived up to my expectations of how good it would be.  The filling was just the right sweetness and the streusel topping was fantastic.  I loved it so much that I have requested it for my birthday too, which is tomorrow.  This is by far my favorite apple pie.  Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: So good and easy to make! I also added fennel seed. Thanks for posting. Your recipes are always great!!

name: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
review:
Yummy, soft cookies ... unfortunately irresistible!

I did add a splash of vanilla, and I agree that the sugar could be reduced. Salt would help if you use natural peanut butter without salt. I had to bake them for an extra 6 minutes, and they are still soft (not crispy) cookies.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Quick, easy and yummy.....thinking these will be a winner with my son's last day of school party!

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: These were so good (advise you have a finger bowl and lots of napkins handy).  Has we don't get Louisiana hot sauce here I made up a hot sauce of 3/4 cup of tomato sauce/ketchup, a dash of hot ground chilli and a good dash of tobasco sauce and I also coated the wings in the sauce and cooked in the oven at 175C for 30 minutes.  I think it was a stroke of genius to simmer the wings in water with cayenne pepper, crushed red pepper flakes and salt.  Thanks for a fantastic recipe WhoDat and to breezermom for the recommendation, made for I Recommend tag game.

name: kittencal s beef or pork marinade and tenderizer
review: A wonderful basic marinade! I only had time to marinate for 6 hours but the pork still turned out so tender and flavourful. Would use a touch less honey the next time to keep things decidedly savoury. Thank you for the recipe!

name: lasagna supremo  the best lasagna ever
review: Wonderful flavors in this lasagna.  I made half a recipe in a 9X9, used fresh pasta and it was wonderful.

name: microwave chocolate mug brownie
review: Used milk instead of water.  Delicious!

name: mahogany beef stew
review: Great to mop up with crusty bread! I dredged the meat and browned it, cooked the onions with the meat and then put all the ingredients in it and put it in the oven at 300 degrees for about 4 hours. Just make sure you make your meat chunks very large so they don't get dry like mine did, but the veggies were perfect and I didn't need to thicken the sauce since I dredged the meat in flour.

name: cajun style oven fries
review: pretty good.

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: Great method - this made a delicious and simple meal tonight.  Thanks!

name: funky chicken with sesame noodles
review: ****Rating is for noodles alone, with modifications***** First, I think it is very important to use low sodium soy sauce, second, reduce both the sugar & the sesame oil by at least half (that would be 1/8 c., maximum of sesame oil).  Sesame oil is a very nice flavor , however, a heavy hand can ruin the dish. Since I didn't make chicken in the recipe (made breaded, baked chicken breast tenders instead), I added some ground ginger & garlic powder with just a pinch of cayenne pepper to my sauce. I also steamed some broccoli and mixed it altogether with the noodles to complete the meal. Overall, it was received very well by my one year old, 7 year old and hubby. There were plenty of noodles left over (a pound is a lot around here), so I'm thinking about some cold noodles tomorrow for lunch with maybe a few sliced onions & sugar snap peas for crunch! Thanks for sharing

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: Good Grief !!  Makes a TON !!  I used a 10X10 inch casserole, piled to the top !  There are just 2 of us, so after the second night, remains went to the critters.  It was very tasty, and I think serving OVER the chips on a plate makes good sense !  This would be a hit with teen DGKs -- and would be good appy for a crowd.  Thanks for posting !

name: mexican stuffed shells  oamc
review: These were simple and really good. My grandson devoured these. I used a Mexican 4-blend cheese and added a few jalapenos on the side. Thanks for sharing. Made for Cookbook Tag.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: This was amazing!  I doubled the recipe to 8 servings.  It called for 2 c. of milk & 2. of cream.  I didn't have cream so I used (1) 12 oz. can of evaporated milk, which came out to be 1.5 c, and 2.5 c. of milk.  It was perfect!!

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Really good salad.  Will make often!!

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: Prepared for DH and myself last evening, followed the recipe as posted with the exception of seasoning the chicken breast with white pepper & poultry seasoning in addition to the salt. Very simple recipe which was quite tasty, I had prepared to cook both chicken breast halves, however, when I finished pounding the breasts out I found that one was plenty for our dinner so I froze the second one and look forward to having an even easier meal next time I prepare this.   The only thing I will do differently next time is turn the chicken over half way thru the broiling time so the bacon on the bottom will crisp up as the top did. Thank you Tish for posting.

name: chili s spicy garlic   lime shrimp
review: Some of the best tasting shrimp I have ever had, but there's definitely too much salt. I won't go over 1/4 teaspoon next time. Thank you.

name: the best sweet and sour sauce
review: Not quite the right color, but the taste is great if you increase the brown sugar a bit.  Desperately needed this recipe when I found a recipe that called for sweet and sour sauce.  This recipe saved the day.  May decrease the cornstarch a bit...but it was a lifesaver!

name: linda s cheesecake stuffed strawberries
review: Strawberries are in season right now in NJ and this was an outstanding way to use them.  I could eat these yummy little treats every day!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: As requested by family, I left out the garlic and still it was delicious.  The next time I may add some sauce to the spaghetti before baking.  I will be using this recipe again and again. Thank you for a family friendly recipe that all would eat!

name: funky chicken with sesame noodles
review:
We very much enjoyed this. I made a few slight modifications- a few tablespoons of sesame oil as opposed to the whole amount, I cut the chicken in strips before sautee'ing, and sautee'd in the marinade, adding some fresh broccolli at the end.
It was delicious, and my family definately inhaled it! This is a keeper, and will go into the regular rotation.
I also used a garlic-ginger paste that I get at the Indian food store, and it eliminates the need for chopping and buying fresh ginger and garlic.

name: excellent carrot cake
review: This was a wonderful cake recipe.  It was so moist.  It melted in ours mouths.  Thanks for this recipe.

name: addictive mexican stew
review: Absolutely delicious -- and so quick and easy to make too.  Wonderful for a busy night.  I didn't even had to cook any chicken -- I used leftover rotisserie chicken that was part of a chicken dinner meal I purchased the day before at the supermarket.  I did sprinkle a little cheddar cheese on top of the individual servings since I had some in the fridge. Everyone loved it -- it's something I'll definitely be making again and again.  Thanks for sharing this recipe!

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: Quick, easy and very moist.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: OMG This is delicious! I even cheated and used diced hash brown potatoes instead of peeling and cutting my own! Why didn't I think of that before?! I will never peel another potato again! I was afraid the cream cheese would make it too creamy, but it's perfect! I added some chives, and kept everything else the same. Definitely a keeper!

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: Well done, barb63!  Utterly delicious marinade. I used boneless breasts cut into chunks, and skewered onto kebabs with tri-color peppers and onions.  What a hit with our company, served with fried brown rice and grilled pineapple slices.  Hint to others:  make a triple amount of this sauce, and keep in a big jar, so that next time you're in the mood for this dish, you just pour!  I always end up throwing a lot of cilantro away because it's so hard to use up all at once, and this would be a good use for it.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: This was delicious! I made some changes based on reviews. I used a little less than a pound of crumbled hot Italian sausage, and 2 thick-cut slices of bacon. I used 6 small russet potatoes, unpeeled, 4 cloves of garlic, and an entire bunch of kale. I used 6 and a half cups of water with 5 teaspoons of chicken bouillon. I also used only 1/3 cup of heavy cream. It was so good! My husband and I both used to work at the Olive Garden, and we both think it was just as good as the Olive Garden's version, if not better!

name: classic baked ziti
review: Very yum, although I prefer my pasta casseroles with a little more sauce.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: This was excellent.  I used the "parmesan" in the green can--too lazy to grate fresh.  I might just sprinkle the salt/Old Bay on the fish directly next time.  I may take the advice of another reviewer and add some lemon zest next time.  Thanks for a lovely recipe.

name: refreshing mojito  by the pitcher mojitos
review: This is so yummy.  Great flavor from the lime and mint.  But just a bit too sweet for us.  So next time I'll use less sugar.  But very good and refreshing.  Thanks Rita :)  Made for Holiday tag game

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
