review: Scaled the recipe back to serve two. Omitted the hot sauce and added the lemon zest along with the juice. Don't like wasting expensive lemons. Delicious. :)

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: I made these up as written, and we really enjoyed them!  Just dropped them into the sauce and let them simmer for 3 hours.  My guests really enjoyed them!  Thanks for the posting

name: panda express orange chicken
review: So I made this recipe two ways. . .one with baked chicken and one with tofu.  As per the recommendations of others, I doubled the amt of sauce and used fresh squeezed OJ with a couple splashes of white vinegar.  I also added some steamed broccoli, frozen peas, a thinly sliced carrot and a little  onion.  I think the sauce was definitely good, but not restaurant quality.  The neighbor thought it was pretty yummy.

name: the ultimate strawberry shortcake
review: I made this for a ladies luncheon I catered and everyone really enjoyed it.  The angel food cake mixture was divine.  I'll definitely make it again.  Its a perfect summertime dessert.

name: blueberry oatmeal muffins
review: Fab muffins! Didn't have enough oatmeal so topped up with coconut and ground almonds. Delicious and will be making again. Thanks!

name: authentic italian tomato sauce
review: I had made some changes while I prepared this sauce.  I had fresh tomatoes on hand that I wanted to use up...used 4 garlic instead of 2...and added about 1 T of hot chili paste. The sauce turned out quite thick, so I added water to make a better consistency.  The cloves imparted a unique taste that I quite enjoyed.  I added a parmesan rind for flavor.  To prevent the onions and garlic sticking, I sprayed my Dutch oven with Pam and cooked them at a lower heat and had no problems with burning.  Next time, I would probably use fresh basil for a fresher taste. I used your recipe for meatballs and just plopped them in the Dutch oven, let them cook for  about 10 minutes, then stirred them around...then simmering them for 3 hours.  This is not the "run of the mill" type of sauce and turned out something quite unique.  The cloves do make a difference, but you have to like the taste in the first place!  This was a very easy recipe to put together, and I would do this one again!

name: outback steakhouse style steak
review:
This was pefect. I omitted the tumeric and coriander...I didn't have them and went lighter on the salt (4 teaspoons). Otherwise these made a PERFECT rub for our Porterhouse steaks. Will use again and again.
Update--use as rub on our london broil--it was the best we ever had tasted. Served with hrseradish/sour cream mixture. *****

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: Great recipe - a nice change from my usual. I used sweet potatoes and fresh snipped chives from our garden for the mash - they were great! Thanks for the keeper!

name: addictive mexican stew
review: Love this recipe! So easy and so good! I cut the recipe in half and used my 3-qt. crockpot- just put everything in on high for 6 hours. I used home frozen corn (thawed, drained) and refried beans instead of black beans, which added great flavor and thickened the stew. So I omitted the cornstarch. The two of us ate all of it for dinner, with cornbread!

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: While the marinade does impart a tender moist piece of chicken (I used boneless,skinless breasts), I didn't find the flavor particularly "wow-ing". I used fresh garlic, 1/2 t. salt and half the oil called for, this should've in no way compromised the flavor. I made this to go with Cheesy Chicken and Asparagus Bundles, which I thought would make them even more flavorful. Chicken itself was just ok.

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: I love the speed and simplicity of this recipe.  I found that we did not have enough sauce so I would double that part next time.  Also, after draining the marinade I brought it to a boil and simmered it before adding it back to the cooked chicken, just to be safe.  I skipped the red pepper flakes as we don't like spicy food.  All in all, a great recipe that I will be sure to repeat. Thanks CoffeeMom!

name: buttery shrimp and pasta
review: I made this for dinner tonight. Very tasty shrimp but the sauce on the pasta was a bit bland. I had to add some seasoning. Super simple to make however. Thx for sharing!

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: I threw in some carrots and potatoes for a simple meal.

name: easy garlic rice
review: Excellent and quick to prepare. I didn't have parsley or bay leaf...didn't miss them. The finished rice was flavorful and not overly garlicy. I really minced my onion and garlic fine. Cooking times were right on. Made with recipe #15580 & recipe #55173.

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: I really don't know how many times I have made this and forgotten to review it! I love the flavor, and I usually have the ingredients on hand. A keeper!

name: one minute flax muffin   low carb
review: This is definately wonderful. I add a packet of stevia type sweetner, and cacao powder, as well as fresh fruit either in the muffin itself or on top when it is done. But, since I need it a little sweeter, I also add sugar free maple syrup on top when it is done. So, kind of a pancake muffin for me. I used earth balance instead of oil, but next time I will try coconut oil as another reviewer suggested.

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: 5 stars for the easiest way to make corn on the cob!  WooHoo!

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Excellent soup.  I used a homemade sausage and ground bacon up in the sausage instead of bacon bits.  I also used chinese cabbage instead of kale and milk instead of cream.  The milk gave it a lighter refreshing feel, though I am sure the cream would have made it more indulgent and yummy.  Thank you for the great recipe!

name: blackberry cobbler
review: Good! Really buttery and rich. Used huge, just-picked blackberries and had plenty of liquid in the finished cobbler. Baked until the edges got slightly crunchy, which was perfect with vanilla ice cream. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: This marinade gave a great taste to the steak.  The steaks were tender.  Very yummy.  Thanks KJK :)  Made for I recommend tag game

name: roasted tomato soup
review: I won't rate this recipe as I did not have all the ingredients available, but I did use this recipe a  guideline.  I had all the ingredients but the fresh herbs....so used dried basil and thyme, salt and pepper.  I finished it off with a little hot chili paste and about 2 T cream. We enjoyed the final dish.  Thanks for the idea!!!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: These were delicious! Made exactly as posted, except I doubled the sauce. And the sauce... Oh My, it's heavenly! Going to try it with baked chicken also, something tells me it will be equally as tasty! Thanks, Yooper!

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: I've been looking for a crisp chocolate chip cookie, and this is it.  Thank you for your recipe.

name: blackberry cobbler
review: Good and Easy!! I often use this with one can of pie filling--blackberry, cherry, peach, blueberry, etc. and don't need all the sugar. We eat it topped with ice cream or milk.  Thanks for posting.  I love quick recipes that are so tasty!

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: These were soooo good! I used a chopped onion. I used margarine to brush the tops and bottoms with and they turned out nice and crispy. I cut them in half to eat. I put sour cream with chives and some more cheddar cheese on top of them and ate them like a sandwich. Yummmm! A keeper for sure.

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: I used the temperature and time you suggested for a chicken leg quarter recipe which i came up with... was perfect.. referring to the doneness of the chicken. I will stick to this temp time always. I am eager to try your simple recipe as it seems it will yield a similar tasting dish to mine. Mine had hoisin, sugar, garlic. Will try just soya and garlic as you have done...so easy and quick and i always have those ingredients in the house...

name: banana banana bread
review: Delicious. I've made this several times. It's my favourite recipe to use up over-ripe bananas. Thanks!

name: spicy shrimp in coconut milk
review: Oh WOW!!  Talk about a super easy, very delicious supper this was for us tonight.  After having the day from (well, you know where), the hardest part was peeling the shrimps.  Everything just flowed together and this inhaled!  I will make this again and again and again!  Thanks for posting!!

name: nutella hot chocolate
review: I was looking for something to use up the milk before it turned and stumbled on this.  It is now a favorite of my guys!  Thanks for sharing!

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: Absolutely beautiful, thank you for the recipe! It had great flavour, and the chicken and vegies were lovely and tender.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: This method really gives the broccoli a great nutty flavor. Well loved by us all.

name: doctored up vanilla pudding casserole
review: I use this recipe all the time...it's awesome!  I live low carb so I use sugar-free/fat-free everything except the cookies (can't skimp on those).  I also make my own condensed milk with Splenda (#412496)...I know it cuts the sugar content in this desert!  And no one is the wiser!!  It gets rave reviews always...then they're surprised when I tell them...hehehe.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: I replace the green pepper for jalapeno and it was great. Thanks for that good, eazy and fast recipe

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: Yum!   I made this with leftover turkey breast.  I left out the pimientos (don't like 'em), and used 8 oz. fat free sour cream and skim milk rather than 1/2 and 1/2.  I cooked it covered to keep it from getting dry.

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: Made these for Father's Day weekend and they came out great! Like others, I omitted the white sugar and since I did not have celery salt, used kosher salt instead. I baked mine for 2.5 hours on 300 degrees and basted every half hour. Delicious!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: I'll admit I was a little disappointed in this dish after all the rave reviews. I prepared it exactly as written, and while it was good, it wasn't great. The chicken was tender, but I thought it was also quite greasy. The sauce had a good flavor. I think I would definitely make the sauce again, but perhaps use boneless, skinless chicken breasts next time. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: chinese pot stickers
review: I am not a novice cook by any means, so this recipe suprised me on so many levels.  There was no way I was going to get 2 tsp pork/shrimp mixture in that wrapper.  That took me about 4 wrapper duds to figure that one out!!  I could only find square wrappers, so that made them all that more fragile!  Second, I had partial froze the wrappers, but was in a rush so ended up putting them all together in a Tupperware and when I went to use them, they were one solid block.  I did a trial run with DH and took out about 12 wrappers.  They were thawed out before they went into the skillet, but even with the oil in the skillet and the broth afterwards, they ended up sticking so badly, the finished product was not very appealing! With my style of cooking,  I probably wouldn't use them as an appitizer, as I don't like doing last minute cooking before my guests and having to worry about the extra clean up!!!  Now with all that negative comments being said, here is the postive.  They tasted really great!  I decided to use the leftovers in a won ton soup!  I seasoned the chicen broth with sesame oil and soy sauce, brought the broth to a boil and added the frozen wrappers and cooked them for 2 minutes or until they all floated to the surface.  As I have 50  wrappers leftover, next time, I will add tofu, some chopped green onions and maybe some bean sprouts!  If I was to make the wrappers all over again, I would freeze them individually and place them flat with a layer of parchment or waxed paper in between.  I would definately consider omitting the cabbage, as it was more of a pain to get it in the wrappers and it was hardly noticed in the taste!  You have to have enough time to play around with these....I figured they took me 2-1/2 hours to complete them.  They were something interesting to do, and I might do them again if I am doing a Chinese theme type of dinner

name: microwave chocolate mug brownie
review: 4 Stars for taste when right out of the oven, wonderful chocolaty richness, but after setting for awhile got so hard we couldn't eat it and that was a real shame as we loved it.  I'll make it again but will make sure we eat it straight out of the micro.  A very nice, fast treat when you are craving just a single serving (don't want to much sitting around)

name: kittencal s  brown sugar caramel sauce or ice cream topping
review: I didn't have any heavy cream so used a can of reddi-whip that had lost its oomph. Since it was already sweetened I only used 1/2 the sugar. Turned out perfect.

name: roasted tomato soup
review: This was really a great and fresh way to use tomatoes from the farmers market that were a day or two past their prime!  I forgot the onion and it was still terrific.  I did mix in a bit of fresh basil into the soup before the puree step and I added a bit of cream (!) and skim milk for a creamier texture.  Super yummo.  Reminded me of my favorite roasted butternut squash recipe from this site.  Put into oven, dollop with EVOO, include onions and garlic, mix, mash, add chicken stock and whammo supper yummo soup!  Thanks for posting.

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: So easy to put together with things I always have in my pantry.  And the taste; yum!!  Chocolate and PB, couldn't ask for any better.  Cut these small cause they are rich, but they won't last long, at least not in my house.  A perfect after dinner desert to serve with coffee or milk.  All the kids in my family voted them 2 thumbs up.

name: overnight french toast casserole
review: Simply and TASTY!  Followed this one to the letter to make for this morning's Father's Day Breakfast.  Loved by all!  I used challah bread for this recipe and it was perfect!  Love how simple it was to prepare the night before!

name: basic batter waffles
review: We thought these were really good.  Batter had a good flavor (I used both vanilla and maple extract) and very easy to mix up. They were super tender inside, but we would have liked them a little crispier.  I left them in the iron for a long time and they just didn't crisp up as much as I wanted, but still very tasty.  I subbed 1/4 cup of Flax Meal for flour, so maybe that is what caused this.  My DH and DD really liked them for Father's Day breakfast.  Thank you for posting!

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Very Very Good! No more bottled sauce for me. I cut back one tablespoon of brown sugar.

name: overnight french toast casserole
review: Made this for a big Father's Day brunch and had grown-ups and kids both say that they loved it.  I cut the bread diagonally so it would go farther and used wheat bread.  So easy to make!!  Thanks for posting!

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: My dh wanted ribs for Father's Day.  So I choose this recipe to try.  So glad that I did.  We really enjoyed the ribs prepared this way.  I baked them in the oven for 3 hours.  They were perfect, tender and fall apart delicious.  The sauce was to die for, sweet, hot and spircy..  Thanks for sharing this lovely recipe.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: Thanks for posting Yooper! DH loved it and it was gone in a flash. I made completely as written except I halved it as that was the only roast size I could get at the market. It was tender and juicy and not salty at all. It was seasoned well. The only problem was the packets are now sized differently so it was hard to get it to match up but I did it. I used Good Seasons Italian, Hidden Valley Ranch Original and Buttermilk and generic gravy mix. I served it with egg noodles and green salad. The packets were expensive where I live. I spent $10 in packets. Next time I might try it with vegetables thrown in. It was great as written though. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: berry smash muffins  strawberry muffins
review:
These are awesome, very moist. I had the worst tasting strawberries to begin with and they came out perfect.
Thanks for posting

name: strawberry coffee cake
review: We made this for Fathers Day and everyone loved it.  I had some fresh strawberries that I wanted to use up and this fit the bill perfectly.  Its a nice texture for coffee cake (sometimes they can be gritty).  thank you for sharing this recipe with us.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: So moist and rich.  Yummy.  I didn't use your frosting recipe because with opted to top it was ice cream and hot fudge.....omg so good.  The cake is very moist.  I'm glad you added in the instructions that the batter would be runny cuz I would have been worried.  This baked up so nice.  I have found our "go to" chocolate cake recipe.  Thank yo for posting you recipe.  So good. Edited to add:  DD made the frosting this time for the wonderful moist cake and it was fantastic.  So creamy and just the right amount of sweetness.  This cake is a winner from start to finish.

name: sweet salsa dump chicken   oamc
review: This worked well putting frozen chicken breasts in the crock pot with the ingredients, then cooking on low for about 6 hrs. DH really liked it, so this one's a keeper. Went well with brown rice and beans. Even my 4 yo, who hates spicy food, ate up her chicken (I left the sauce off of hers, but the meat still had the flavor).

name: amish white bread
review: Lovely recipe, I usded F.com to cut it to one loaf as there's only 2 of us right now and it made one lovely, large and very soft loaf of bread, with a slightly sweet taste that we enjoyed with butter.  Think it's going to make great toast for todays breakfast too.  Our only problem is it's almost too soft (if that's possible) when it comes to using for sandwiches - I did add a tablespoon of flax seeds to it, just my attempt at getting something healthy in my picky eater nephew that is visiting.

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: I've made this twice.  Both time I substituted blackberries for blueberries (because that's what we have growing right now).  It is definitely important to cream the butter and sugar for a few minutes! The first time I just hand mixed them together for about a minute.  The cake came out dry. The second time I made it I used a hand-held mixer and creamed the butter and sugar for about 4 minutes. The cake turned out much lighter and was not as dry.  I also added some orange zest, which added a nice complementary flavor.  I made this in a bundt pan.  I added about half the batter, then the struesal topping, and then the remaining batter. Delicious! I will make this again.

name: easy baked potato wedges
review:
seasonings were good, but overall the potatoes weren't raveable to me. They were easy yes, but I like crispiness & I didn't get any crunch at all with these.

On second try, I cut them thinner and was more happy with the result

name: the best pasta salad
review: I take this salad everywhere I go for potlucks, especially in the summer months.  It's always a huge hit!  Our favorite combo is cucumbers, peppers, red onion, olives, feta cheese, and pepperoni with a greek dressing...but it is fabulous as written too.

name: double chocolate banana muffins
review: Easy to prepare and very tasty.  These muffins look so beautiful when baked.  Huge, soft muffins.  I held back some of the chips to sprinkle on top before baking.

name: whole wheat honey banana muffins
review: Delicious! I made some mini muffins for my 12 month old.  Had to use regular white flour since I was out of whole wheat and didn't have quite enough honey.  Will make wonderful snacks or breakfast for him out of the freezer.  And yummy for us too!

name: quick cinnamon rolls   no yeast
review: These were really good! I used white sugar instead of brown sugar, which did not give these cinnamon rolls the typical brownish look that brown sugar does. But these were so good! I also find that if there are leftovers, it is best to microwave it to make it warm, because it tastes better all warmed up.

name: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
review: Cake like, chewy, awesome!!!

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: good coffee cake. I followed the recipe except used splenda for white and brown sugar.I will make this again using reg sugar.

name: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
review: So good! I used my tablespoon cookie scoop and baked for 13 minutes - not going to last long at my house.

name: wonderful salsa
review: 10 Stars!  With 411 winning reviews, we need to start up a Camp Fooddotcom...and have winners and stuff like that.  [To the batch, I added the juice of 1 lime after turning off the fire and before processing.]

name: buttery yeast rolls
review: Very good.  I used an 11 by 8 pan, & they were pretty crammed in there & needed longer than 20 minutes.  I'll space em out more next time.  I'll probably also dip the rolls in butter rather than rubbing cuz I love the flavor.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: I really hate giving bad reviews but this meal was not liked very much by myself or my family. I made it expecting what was in the picture and wound up with some kind of soupy mush of half-boiled/half-mashed potatoes, kielbasa and chopped vegetables. I followed the instructions up until I realized that the water was not going to evaporate. After that, I removed the lid and let it cook for the rest of the time (9 minutes), stirring occasionally to cook all of the potatoes. I wound up ladling out some of the soupy stuff so it would evaporate and I ended up with potatoes that turned (almost) to mush. We also found it pretty bland and we all doused it with ketchup to eat it. I really wish I would have taken a picture of the look that was exchanged between my son and husband when I sat the plates in front of them. The first thing out of my husband's mouth was, "That doesn't look like the picture on the recipe card." And he is completely right. Many people try a recipe based on the picture. I really wish the picture that is posted as the main photo would be taken to illustrate a recipe that isn't altered so much that it winds up looking nothing like the way it is supposed to turn out. Overall, the picture difference was bad but I would have had the same review of this recipe if the picture would have matched whatever I wound up with. I will definitely NOT be making this again. I will also post a picture of what mine looked like since I've seen quite a few reviews describing something similar to what I had.

name: sweet salsa dump chicken   oamc
review: I used this with pork chops, and it was wonderful!  I put a few chops in a foil pack and into my slowcooker which kept them moist & seemed to help the flavors come together without marinading.

name: flawless sesame chicken  restaurant style
review: Very good sesame chicken! It was a bit of an experiment as I did try and follow the advice of other reviewers as well as getting it to work with my pantry. I didn't have chile paste or sesame oil so I used chile oil instead which worked really well. In addition, I lightly fried this in a skillet with a couple tablespoons of olive oil which gave them a similar texture with a little more work. All in all, I recipe I will be hanging on to as everyone loved them.

name: sue b s chocolate cake
review: Not sure what I did wrong. The flavor wasn't as chocolatey as  I thought it would be. I baked in 2 nine inch layers.  They didn't rise at all and the texture was a little chewy.

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: So good! This was quick, simple, and tasty. Chicken was moist on the inside and crispy on the outside. Thanks for sharing this nice keeper. Made for Zaar Chef Alphabet Soup Tag.

name: zesty italian crescent casserole
review: This was a great recipe. I followed the advice of other reviewers and seasoned the ground beef with garlic powder and seasoned salt while that and the onions (I used a whole, chopped onion) were cooking. I also used a bit more sour cream to get the cheese mixture to a consistency that I could spread. After seeing the main picture for the casserole, I also added pepperonis to the top before baking. It reminded me of a really wonderful pizza sloppy joe. It got great reviews across the board from our family. The only thing that was misleading was that this was described as "zesty" and I found nothing in the ingredients to create that zestiness. I wound up adding somewhere between 1/4 and 1/2 tsp of crushed red pepper flakes and it turned out great. Thanks for posting! It's a keeper!

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: Perfect! I received some squash from a co-worker and whipped this up. Nice to have everything I needed.

name: weight watchers 2 point  pumpkin muffins
review: We ate them plain and they were very good, especially considering they aren't bad for you.  However, we had some cream cheese icing that we added to half and they were delicious, but not very good for you I'm sure.  These were easy enough for DD to make by herself. I'm sure we'll be making these again.

name: shirley s perfect rare roast beef
review: This makes the perfect roast.  I have it in the oven again for the second time in less then a month.  I love that it comes out pink in the middle and reminds me of my mom's roast.  Thanks for posting.

name: kittencal s italian zucchini mozzarella patties
review: Aaaahhhhhmazing!! These were so dang good! We have a bounty of zucchini this year.  Trying to come up with different things to do with the zucchini can be a challenge! Fried in oil last night and used green onion and they were so crispy and tasty. Might make them again tonight! You're right, after the crop is gone, I will still be going to the market for zucchini for these. Thank you soooo much!!

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: This is a very tasty soup.  Will make again soon.  Thanks for posting.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Lovely light tilapia and easy to fix.  Next time think I'll do it in the broiler to get that toasty brown color without over cooking the fish.  I liked others idea about adding some lemon zest to the top too but still wonderful as I made it.  Enjoyed this wonderful blend of flavors without over powering the tilapia itself.

name: roast beef horseradish spirals
review: I like it.  I was afraid it wouldn't hold, but it worked out great.

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: I made up a batch of this a while back to go over some leftover pork loin.  I added a dash of liquid smoke and thought the sauce was quite tasty.  Thanks for posting Dana.

name: ground beef gyros
review: Loved it! Used Recipe #79388 for the pita.

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: The seasonings are good, but I highly recommend finishing these on the grill instead of broiling.....much better taste that way.  Very tender and falling off the bone ribs!  Thanks!

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: Very good, I warmed the milk & butter in the microwave in a glass liquid measuring cup, stirred in the beaten egg and went from there. Very nice muffin. Made 1 dozen large & 1 dozen mini muffins, I added more blueberries too!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: Great base recipe.  My BF thought it needed more to it but this is an excellent place to start and the add more flavor that you want to come through.  This was a kid pleaser as is.

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: Great recipe.  A friend of tours used to make this same pound cake and would not reveal the recipe....  "Family Secret".  Thank you for posting, now I'm in the know!  Am taking this to a new neigh bor tomorow.  I  made 2 loaf cakes instead 1 lg cake.  Cooked about 70 minutes.   Note to self:  added a teasoon or so of coconut, rum, butter, vanilla and almonf extract to the batter.

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: This was excellent. I think next time I'll try thighs. Thanks

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Amazing!  Made a huge cake!!  Halved the icing which was perfect.  The banana cake was super moist and flavourful.

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: Where have I been?  I can't believe I'm reviewer #332!  Better late than never, especially when it comes to such a tasty salad.  Made as directed, and it's perfection.  Thanks, Kittencal.  This will be made weekly from now on.

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: This recipe caught my eye as I was trying to use items I have in freezer & pantry.  I thought I would try to fix it in the crock pot (due to the extreme heat) and it does work.  I wasn't sure how long to cook it, but 4 hours on HI for 4 breasts (2.25 lbs) was too long.  The chicken was dry and the rice over cooked.  Next time I will go for 3 to 3-1/2 hours and increase the water (may sub out low sodium chicken broth) by 1/4 cup.  I think it would also be good to add in a poblano or green pepper & maybe a can of chopped green chilies for a little extra "zip".  Over all, very nice, EASY recipe that I will make again.  Thanks for posting and I will re-review when I make again.  :)

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: This was delish!  Didn't have thyme, so I sub'ed some Mrs. Dash...  Perfect! Thanks so much!

name: denny s style french toast
review: Great! For no lumps, mix dry ingredients, add milk and vanilla and mix until smooth. Mix in eggs last. The kids gobbled this up. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: Good, good, gooood, according to my thigh-lovin' husband.  I did this as directed, but put the thighs on a rack so that the fat could drip off.  Even with skin removed, these little babes still have a lot of fat!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: This recipe is all about technique.  It is so simple yet the end results is wonderful.  I used chicken stock for added flavor and would most definitely make this recipe again.  Thanks Roxy for sharing.

name: bretzel rolls  bavarian pretzel sandwich rolls
review: After seeing the photos and reading the reviews I couldn't wait to try these rolls.  Made them for our 4th of July party and followed the recipe exactly.  They are awesome and keep disappearing off the table so don't know if they'll even make it to the party.  They taste just like a soft pretzel.  Only trouble I had is when I tried to cut the cross on the top (loved the look of the photo) mine didn't stay; but they still taste awesome.  I'll be making these often and I'm sure my technique will get better.  By the way, thanks for the tip on adding the soda to cold water.

name: minado s perfect sushi rice
review: Unbelievably tasty, and perfect technique.  So good that I kept eating spoonfuls right out of the bowl, so that I almost didn't have enough to finish my sushi project!  I had no mirin, so subbed white wine, and that was fine.

name: my no roll pie crust
review: very good!! and super simple!!

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: Really delicious. Everyone loved it. I will be making this often.

name: kittencal s greek moussaka
review: Oh my goodness.  I wasn't sure what to expect ith this dish, but I was very happy with it.  My kids weren't sure either but I was wanting something different tonight.  I was so happy that we all loved it.  The parmesan cheese sauce is amazing.  The kids couldn't taste the eggplant so they liked it alot too.  Thank you  Kittencal for sharing with us.

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: Quick and easy.  I used a combination of beef and chicken broth instead of water and boullion.  I did not add the salt it called for and those served added what they felt it needed at the table.  Delicous; will definitely make again!

name: mean s dutch babies
review: We really liked these.  I topped ours with strawberries and bananas.  We didn't add any syrup or powdered sugar.  We didn't need too.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: These were probably the best ribs I've ever made. Fall off the bone good!!!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Pretty good

name: big thicket chicken and dumplings
review: Excellent

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review:
Been wanting to try this recipe out for yrs and finally i did for 4th of July. Delicious! I doubled the sauce because I had double the meat, but it was not neccesary. I had way too much left over. Next time I will only make 1 batch of the sauce for 6-7 pounds of ribs. I finished these off on the grill (about 10 minutes) to get a grilled taste.

I made the mistake and bought pork ribs, not baby back pork ribs and they were fatty. Will definately make these again with baby back ribs.

name: appetizer grape jelly and chili sauce meatballs or  lil smokies
review: Liked them.

name: sweet salsa dump chicken   oamc
review: Very good. I made the recipe as directed. It was very tasty.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Loved it. Could not be any better.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: This was good. Made it as posted and everyone liked it. Thanks.

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: Frosting is delicious.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: I absolutely love the raw garlic addition which cooks from from the heat of potatoes so it's not the harsh raw garlic taste that some people might find overpowering but it's distinct enough to separate these mashed potatoes from the "boring" kind, and the Parmesan just takes it over the top. Thank you.

name: kittencal s best deviled eggs
review: These were ok for us.  Most deviled egg recipes I have had include vinegar and/or sugar so I guess that is my own fault that they weren't my favorite.  Everyone ate them, many said they needed sugar.  Thanks for sharing your recipe though!

name: three cup chicken
review:
DEFINATELY the Thai basil is the way to go, TRUE!
Honestly? Initially was worried about using 20 GARLICS too!
Used 20 spoonfulls jarred garlic, 10 spoonfulls jarred ginger as has on handy today!
SAVES HEAPS OF TIME and makes little difference okay?
This was restaurant quality,
Of course, I added three heaping pinchfulls of chili!!! LOL
ONLY thing I did was thicken the sauce, might be personal taste for me,
Used 2 heaping teaspoons of cornstarch and thickening I did see!
WHAT A GREAT RECIPE!!! SO glad I did do,
Nothing best the best rating for this recipe will do!
Thanks! DEFINITELY the Thai basil is the way to go, TRUE!
Honestly? Initially was worried about using 20 GARLIC too!
Used 20 spoonfuls jarred garlic, 10 spoonfuls jarred ginger as has on handy today!
SAVES HEAPS OF TIME and makes little difference okay?
This was restaurant quality,
Of course, I added three heaping pinch fulls of chili!!! LOL
ONLY thing I did was thicken the sauce, might be personal taste for me,
Used 2 heaping teaspoons of cornstarch and thickening I did see!
WHAT A GREAT RECIPE!!! SO glad I did do,
Nothing best the best rating for this recipe will do!
Thanks!
***UPDATE Made it again today and was EVEN BETTER (as IF that were possible) Added finely diced bok choy and mushrooms; this time instead of waiting the 30 minutes, my bite size chicken was done so added about a tsp or two of Chinese cornstarch dissolved in water to the mix and VOILA!! GREAT again too!

name: the ultimate strawberry shortcake
review: Pretty strawberries and delicious cake.  I had a hard time trying to make it cut into squares.  Made for Photo Forum Circus.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: Fresh, light and healthy. Perfect for Summer. I didn't have fresh basil, so I used dried and thought it came out great! Thanks for posting this recipe. I'm sure I'll be making it often.

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: Just perfect.

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: Served with stir fry frozen veggies (sugar peas, water chestnuts, edamame, mushrooms).  I made using 2 whole chicken breasts and the as written amounts for the rest of the ingredients.  Had plenty of flavorful sauce and it was just thick enough to hold it all together.  What a wonderful treat for me!  There is more than enough left over for 2 lunches this week.  Thanks for such a wonderful and easy recipe.  Tip I found for slicing the thin strips of meat for stir fry, slice while still slightly frozen!

name: kittencal s juicy hamburger burger
review: Only made two burgers but they were very good.  Served with corn on the cob and baked beans.

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Didn't like it this time, but I made some modifications so I can't blame the recipe.  Next time I'll try trading out the half cup of flour for some corn meal then coating the pan with olive oil so the crust will absorb the flavor.  I'll drop the sugar--didn't like that sweet taste, and put more garlic/onion/italian flavoring.

name: bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers
review:
I'm not going to assign stars to this because I never got to actually eat these - they were gone too quickly! I guess they were a hit ...

Followed the advice of others below and mixed the shredded cheese with the cream cheese and also chopped up some green onions for the mixture. Be careful not to overstuff the peppers because the cheese does ooze out while baking. Prep time was longer than stated above but still quite easy. I did each step at a time - cut/seeded all the jalapenos, then stuffed all the jalapenos, then wrapped all the jalapenos in bacon. Definitely try to wear gloves because manhandling jalapenos for 30 minutes will burn your skin.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: These are very good.  I used ground turkey and omitted the milk.  The meatballs were formed and dropped into rapid boiling water for a few minutes to firm up.  They were carefully transferred to a baking sheet and baked for about 20 to 25 minutes.  After cooling the meatballs were frozen for later use.  This is something I will be making again.  Thank you for sharing.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: This is perfect for the garlic lover! I didn't quite use as many garlic cloves, maybe half as much, but the garlic still flavoured the cauliflower beautifully. Pllus roasted garlic is so delicious already. I used dry rosemary instead of fresh and it worked out well. I'd definitely make this again; thanks!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: I loved this recipe for the simplicity of it!  I had a small roaster that I had taken out of the freezer last night.  It was still partially frozen when I put it in the crock pot this morning and cooked it on low for about 6 hours.  Since the weather has changed and it got hot, I will serve the meat cold with some pasta salads.  The meat turned out nice and tender.   I would definately do this one again!  Thanks for the posting!

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: You know I wasn't wild about this recipe at first, but the leftovers tasted great.  I kept the pot in the fridge and put it back on very low heat in the morning, and by the second day the flavors really picked up.  I followed the recipe exactly, but I forgot to buy dried apricots unfortunately...  That seemed like a big mistake, because the dish could have really used them.

name: frizzled cabbage
review: We love cabbage and this recipe made us love it even more. This would be a great noodle replacement if low-carbing. I'll be making this recipe often. Thanks for posting.

name: minado s perfect sushi rice
review: Great recipe! We like our sushi rice a little softer, so I only used 1.5 cups of uncooked rice (cooked in a rice cooker) and it was perfect. So easy to spread on the nori and very flavourful. Thanks for a great and easy recipe!

name: crazy crust pizza
review: Awesome idea! Certainly tastes different to a regular pizza crust but I actually preferred the slightly less 'doughy' flavor and it's a breeze to make without kneading and rolling.I was using a fairly large pizza tray so found 15 minutes of initial baking was spot on. Not only did it taste great but I finally managed to make a perfectly round pizza!

name: parmesan zucchini
review: Sorry.  Forgot that stars thing.  You get all five of them.

name: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
review:
Beautiful, delicious cake. I will pass by the box mixed red velvet cakes for ever more. DH baked for my Birthday :)
Thanks for posting!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Simple and delicious.  I just wanted something fast and easy, and it's too hot to deal with the oven right now.  I subbed in gluten free flour and pasta and used 1% milk and 2% sharp cheddar.  It tasted great and had a nice creamy texture.  Thanks for sharing!

name: chicken  shrimp and andouille jambalaya
review: Like a lot of others, I had to adjust the liquids the first time this came out of the oven, adding 2 more cans of tomatoes with juice and about a cup and a half of broth.  But the basic recipe is just exceptional!  Thanks so much for posting, Sue.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: I saved this recipe so long ago I'd almost forgotten about it.  Finally got around to trying it and it won't take me this long to make it again, and again.  So easy to make, and love that I can freeze them and have them ready for anytime to pull out and serve.  The taste is perfect and goes so well with spagetti but would also be great served on their own, maybe as a sub, so many options and always on the ready in the fridge.  These are going to be a regular in my fridge and always a batch on the ready.

name: breakfast burritos  once a month cooking
review: This was my first oamc recipe that I tried, and I love it.  It's a very convenient breakfast idea.  I like having fiber in the morning, so I added a drained can of black beans and used whole wheat tortillas.  The amount of servings in the recipe seems to be a bit off though; I increased all the ingredients by 50%, but still only had enough filling for 24 tortillas.  So if people really want to make sure they end up with 24 burritos, they should use 18 eggs, a pound and a half of sausage, and increase the rest of the ingredients accordingly :)

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: This is a great recipe.  My DH wants me to make it again soon.  Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: ginger me up chicken  low fat honey   ginger chicken breasts
review: Great recipe!  As soon as you mix up the sauce, the smell is going to intoxicate you.  SO fragrant.  However, I ended up using ground ginger instead of fresh, and you can really taste the difference; the ground ginger makes the dish more bitter than it should be.  I'd urge people to use fresh grated ginger whenever possible.

name: hard boiled eggs
review: No grey ring and easy to peel. Perfect! Thanks for posting your technique.

name: zesty low fat chicken breasts
review:
I'd make this again, but not as written. I made it as written for my first try.

I used mild salsa, one of my favorites. I think the sweetness from the ketchup, and from the honey was too much for the dish. As another reviewer suggested, I think I'd replace ketchup with tomato paste on the next go-round.

I'd cut back the honey atleast by half, if not more. Think I'd also dice jalapenos, onions, and garlic and mix in.

Good recipe and will be made again, with modifications.

Could be good sprinkled with lime juice, too.

name: fajita seasoning mix
review: This is a delicious blend of spices.  I made beef fajitas the other day and used your seasoning.  Perfect.  I'm going to make a big batch and split it between myself and DIL.  THank you so much for sharing with us.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review:
This made an unctuous, this sauce--the kind that seems to come on macaroni and cheese purchased at a deli. Thanks to some helpful reviewers, we knew to cook the flour for a while before adding the milk, and to take the pan off the heat before adding the cheese. Thus, the sauce wasn't floury or pasty; nor was it greasy and broken.

We did change the recipe a little--we added mustard, paprika, garlic salt and a little cayenne. I think it would be a little dull without these additions. We also used far less butter.

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: These are soooo great.. These have become our families favorite rolls. I've made these a few times now and my family just loves  them.  Thank you for a quick and easy recipe for dinner rolls, these are excellent. A Keeper.  Update just saw that the stars didn't show up when I posted  -sorry

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I made these potatoes for the first time (I've been meaning to for a long time!) this week for my new family - I just relocated from Toronto to Winnipeg for love.  I needed something that was simple and delicious, and would go with my fabulous souvlaki - and wow, did this to the trick!  The only change I made was to use baby potatoes as that's what Harry had on hand (used 5 baby potatoes per large potato, probably could have used 6 or 7).  I cut the potatoes in half to soak in the wonderful juices, popped them in the oven as directed, and was rewarded with the best potatoes with the least effort I've ever had!  Thanks, Evelyn, for sharing this garlicky, lip-smacking, dish - reminiscent of my trip to Santorini years ago with my Mom.  This will be my go-to Greek potato dish from now on!

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: Easy and delicious.  I skipped the lemon this time as I didn't have any on hand.  Will try it the next time.  Wonderful with some corn bread or rice.  Keeper recipe.

name: kittencal s italian zucchini mozzarella patties
review: These were getting snatched up and devoured as fast as I could fry them.  Simply wonderful!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Not much I can add to 143 other reviews, so I will just say "DELICIOUS!"  This is a keeper.

name: gluten free french bread
review: This was pretty good.  It definitely satisfied my craving for sandwiches and I didn't want to cave and use regular bread.  I used rice flour and potato starch because that is what I had on hand.  I also used reular yeast.  I put all the ingredients in my bread maker to knead and rise and then put it in the oven to bake.  i might try using the tapioca flour next time.  It tasted a little yeasty.

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: Loved this chicken! Sadly, my cilantro had gone bad so made do by adding 1 tsp ground coriander. Marinaded for probably 2 hours, which was enough to infuse the meat with all the great flavors. Terrific cooked out on the grill next to thick slices of eggplant. Thanks for posting.

name: easy lemon pound cake
review:
what I loved about it was that it was easy...one bowl & no buttermilk. I used it to get to another product I'd seen on food.com without all the steps. In essence, I added two cups of frozen triple berry blend. I put a tablespoon of flour and a little sugar in with the berries & mixed them prior to adding in. And I added them right before stirring in the milk. That made the mixture purple, but the cake came out a good color.

I really didn't like the glaze step because it had me fearful of sogginess--which my husband complained of. He also complained of too much lemon flavor. I thought the opposite--not enough, but he got the edge piece so that's probably why. Anyway, due to those complaints, I'll follow other reviewer's suggestions and either put more lemon juice into the cake--trading 1/4 cup of milk out for 1/4 cup of it then not add the glaze. Or I'll use POWDERED sugar, rather than normal sugar, in the glaze to thicken it.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: I "cheated" and added a touch of olive oil and red wine vinegar.  Delicious!

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: This worked so well for me. I am terrible at making pie crust and this one was easy and turned out great.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: Worked well! Doubled the recipe, made two pizzas (one was recipe #70951) and froze two balls of dough for later. Next time I'll remember to prebake the crust when using a 12 inch pizza pan. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: We loved this - my DH who doesn't like mayo said it was damn good.  I thought it would get a little more crispy on the outside, but didn't matter - the flavor was so good.  Like one other reviewer I think there was enough sauce for six pieces of chicken.   We were a little concerned about reheating but this was just as good second time around.  Thanks for a great recipe.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Superb .. we relished the wings..the best part was the simplicity of the recipe and the fact that they weren't deep fried. They certainly tasted deep fried though. I will broil for less time when I next make these. Will also try coating other sauces although I doubt it would turn out half as good.. the hot sauce, butter and cider vinegar (as one of the reviewers suggested) was spot on!. I wonder if they would be good with tenders. I am sure those would not require the boil/broil method and would probably require a bit of breading... Whodat thanks for this excellent recipe. No idea why I am unable to give you the 5 stars I want to.  I've tried everything -- FIVE STARS .. there!

name: fish tacos and cilantro coleslaw  20 minutes max
review: Made the cabbage slaw only and loved it! Super quicky, easy and incredibly fresh tasting and flavorful. I chopped up a few hot jarred jalapeno rings since the quantity needed was so small and it worked out great. Made with roasted chickpea tacos in both corn and flour tortillas.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: I made this once as written. After a search for a real good recipes to do. And with resulted in other similar recipes, I decided I wanted to create something unique a great base recipe and easy to modify depending on your tastes.. It may be a stretch to call my creation, but the result was a meal the whole family will liked. MY was Not better, not worse, just different! I've will added this to my recipe book "AS IS" and with my additions TOO. I have two way to do it!! THANK YOU!! I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! 7 Stars

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: Fantastic!  I took chicken tenders and cut them on the diagonal in about 2" sized pieces and cooked for 2 hours.  I substituted 1/2 cup white wine for the water.  I then removed the chicken chunks and whisked in the cream cheese in the hot liquid.  Then I added the soup, but no mushrooms because my kids don't like them.  Everyone gave this 2 thumbs up.  There wasn't even a tablespoon leftover.

name: easy garlic chicken
review: I selected this recipe after seeing Derf's photos.  This was quick & easy which is always appreciated.  I liked the flavor~ nothing overpowering or terribly bold so it pleased everyone.  I did line the pan with foil & reduce the oven temp based on reviews so had a good result.  thank you for sharing the recipe!

name: flawless sesame chicken  restaurant style
review: I'd rate the chicken marinade highly.  Those taste-tested good right out of the oil.  The sauce quantity comes no where near the proportions & the taste is a bit off.  I'll just make the sauce with a different recipe next time.

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: I'm sure I'll will be make it again. Before attempting this again, I'll have to figure out what seasonings to use, by reading all of the review, and see that will work for others, and than for me, to make it more flavorful or lot better for me to do! Anyway, excellent to do a SCRATCH on recipes. The more I play with my food, the more I love cooking, to make a recipe that will work for me, that is!! Than I can do the happy food dance!! I've will added this to my recipe book with my additions. THANK YOU!!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: I made this tonight for something different and everyone really liked it.  I halved the recipe and used light mayo, less than 1 tblsp. of soft butter and no salt and it still turned out great.  Also added some garlic powder and sprinkled a few seasoned breadcrumbs on top before broiling.  I cooked the (frozen) fish about 15-20 minutes before adding the topping.  It browned up perfectly and looked beautiful.  Thanks for posting!

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: A genuine pizza sauce !! I will not play with this recipe. I've will added this to my recipe book "AS IS" THANK YOU!! I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! THANK YOU!! 30 Stars!!!!!!

name: paula deen crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: Very cheesy! In my crockpot it was done to perfection in 2.5 hours.

name: slow cooker macaroni   cheese
review: Very cheesy! In my crockpot it was done to perfection in 2.5 hours.

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: Nice recipe.  I have never put my chicken in a food processor before and that worked out great. Next time I might add something for a little bit of kick.  Thanks for the recipe ellie.

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: Used can of sliced peaches, can of sliced  pears, blueberries, banana, sweet cherries, and cantaloupe. The sweet cherries were a mistake - turned it all a lovely shade of purple. Used 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup cornstarch in place of pudding mix.

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: These taste great.  I added a teaspoon of agave syrup and a bit of cinnamon, and they ended up tasting too good to be true.  With all the protein and fiber in these and the small amount of calories, these really make a perfect breakfast.  Thanks for sharing :)

name: low carb pizza
review: My favorite low carb recipe so far! Really satisfies the pizza cravings! I added red and green peppers, onions, mushrooms and black olives. Thanks!

name: crock pot ravioli
review: This was really good.  The raviolis got a little mushy for my taste but the flavors were excellent.

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: I made this for dinner for guests last night and it was great!  I had to cook a little longer than stated for it to thicken up to a syrup consistency.  I then put in the refrigerator for a while before dinner and it got even thicker.  Before serving, I reheated it in the microwave and it got thin again.  So next time, I will just keep at room temperature so I don't have to reheat.  The flavor was great though for salmon.  I used less pepper and only a pinch of cayenne and it was just right for our tastes.  Will definitely make again.  Thanks for posting!

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: These were so good!  I made mine with shredded chicken, and it just tasted fantastic.  If anyone is apprehensive about making this because it's vegetarian- don't worry, you can add meat like I did and you will love it.

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: This is definitely worth the extra effort to make, as it's so much better than store-bought enchilada sauce.  Thanks for sharing- this made my enchiladas taste great :)

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: I have used this method for roasting corn several times now.  It's so easy to prepare, and I like how the silks come off easily after roasting.  My kids think it's fun to eat corn with the husk peeled back.  It's great with a little butter and seasoned salt.  I highly recommend this recipe.

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: Marvelous!  I cooked this on the stovetop as there was no way my little crockpot could hold all of it.  I chose not to add the pasta as we are watching our carbs but other than that I followed the recipe exactly.  The next time I make this I will add a bit of garlic because we love garlic.  I have never eaten at Olive Garden so I can't say whether it tastes like their soup, but who cares?  This stuff is great!  Thanks for sharing this recipe.

name: kittencal s italian zucchini mozzarella patties
review: This was a great basic recipe.  I also baked  the mixture in a casserole dish and cut squares to serve.  thanks

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Kittencal, your recipes never disappoint! This garlic bread was soo delicious! I halved the recipe for a small batch of garlic bread and still have some extra garlic butter for tomorrow, though man, I'm craving more already. Thank you for a great recipe, and for the epic and delicious garlic breath :)

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Really surprisingly good for a low-fat muffin. I did add more chocolate chips because I can't help it. Thanks for the keeper!

name: french bread rolls to die for
review: These rolls were so good! I used my bread machine with this recipe, placed it on the dough setting, and the dough rose so much it pushed open the lid! That proved to be an impressive recipe already! My rolls browned nicely though it didn't seem quite as crusty as other French bread I've had, but regardless, these were delicious and tender inside. I didn't have bread flour and substituted with regular AP flour mixed with wheat gluten (1 TB gluten per cup of flour.) I made 16 oval shaped rolls and they also turned into amazing garlic bread after! I froze the majority of the batch and can't wait to have lots of fresh bread in the future. Thanks so much!

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: we ALL loved this chicken!! other than what the recipe said i used a jalapeno for the minced chili. baked in a pan with onions, celery, and zucchini. will make more next time and really, really want to grill it!!! :)

name: sugar cookie icing
review: Perfect as written!!

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: I liked it.  Very nice flavor.  I might add a little salt though for more.

name: chunky blue cheese salad dressing
review: Perfect dressing, Luby. You did a great job on making this~ the only change I made was not having buttermilk, I used 1 tsp. vinegar to the amount of milk. Boy, this is perfection over nice, cold, lettuce leaves. Thanks for posting!

name: spiced sweet roasted red pepper   feta hummus
review: I love this! I finally broke down and bought a bottle of tahini; I always balked at the cost considering I'd use so little of it for homemade hummus. But I now see it is worth the price because I will make this OFTEN! I'm making my second batch tonight! I only used 1/4 tsp cayenne because I don't like things too hot. Thank you for posting; I've been using it on my turkey sandwiches with lettuce!

name: chicken legs grilled
review: These were just fantastic!  Will make these a lot.  Thanks for posting such a wonderful recipe.

name: utterly deadly southern pecan pie
review: I made this for my husband's birthday (it's his favorite) and it was fantastic!  Thanks so much for posting this!

name: strawberries   cream bread  strawberry or blueberry
review: This bread was very moist. My husband liked it a lot. My first bite made me think of the Berry Special K. I only sprinkled a little bit of brown sugar. I only had dark. Not sweet at all. Better the next day coming out of the fridge.

name: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
review: Fantastic Cookie!  I used about 3/4 of cup sugar between the two sugars instead of the one cup the recipe called for and the cookie was plenty sweet.  I brought it to my Friday night line dance and everyone raved how good they were.  I willl make tham again.  Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: WOW, Kittencal!  I don't know how I missed this one!  This smelled sooooooooooo good!  I have changed up my diet to  Nutritarian, so left out Oil, Salt, Wine (replaced with 2 T Red Wine vinagar).  I have already cheated and put over my zucchini squash, I had prepared with my Spirooli , yummmmmmm.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: These were just ok for us. I cooked mine in the oven and covered with foil but they still turned out very dry and I only cooked them for 40 minutes. I used chili sauce instead of ketchup. The taste was good... just very dry chops.

name: easy peezy pizza dough  bread machine pizza dough
review: This is my new love!  I used this pizza dough recipe for the crust of a Bobby Flay pizza recipe that we grilled with wood chips giving it a smokey flavor.  I love how the dough is thin and crispy; more like a flat bread.  This made enough for 2 pizzas so I just rolled out the second one, wrapped it in parchment paper, rolled up, stuck in a freezer bag in the freezer for later.  When I went to use the second one, all I had to do was unwrap it as it thawed, then roll out a little.  It tasted as good as the first one.  Now THAT was easy peezy!

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Good!  Did it's job to make tender meat, and was yummy, but I was left thinking it needed some herbs or something...

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: Tasty and easy, I wanted dessert but I was out of eggs.  This is just tasty as any cake with eggs and I love the idea there is only the cake pan to clean up afterwards.  I didn't use icing because it was good enough without it.  Thanks for sharing!

name: 24k carrots
review: Very sweet and tasty.

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Made this for Summer on the Porch Diabetic Forum and what a wonderful and tasty salad.  I added some celery and used turkey pepperoni and the salad made a delicious meal on a hot evening with some french bread.  Definately a keeper!

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: This was a hit with my family!

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: So good! Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: I am the latest review (128) and still felt the need to tell you how god it is. I bought 4 steaks and marinaded for almost 24 hours in this delicious marinade. I made it as written.  It softened the meat, brought out flavor and was tasty. For my DH that loves seasonings he added Montreal Steak Seasoning as written and then again tableside. The key to this is using high quality ingredients. We used brewed balsamic vinegar and it proved to be well worth the pricey tag. Fresh garlic and high quality Dijon are important too. My family doesn't like Dijon but you can't taste it in this. We will make this again and again. It even got a non-steakeater to gobble it down. Thanks for posing Kittencalskitchen.Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: I made this for dinner tonight, and it was really good. I made half the recipe, and now I have lunch for tomorrow! Definitely a keeper. Thanks for posting it.

name: baked tilapia with lots of spice
review: Cut the recipe down for three and used 1/2 t. salt.  Cooked in a skillet rather than the oven so was very quick.  Served in thin buns for a sandwich.  Very good.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: I only had garlic powder, so I used that and Cavenders greek seasoning salt, and I used a splash if white Basal mic vinegar. Very refreshing!

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: Very very good! I used Splenda for half of the sugar, I had mostly raspberries with just a few blue berries.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: I made this and  it was delcious. Most everyone had seconds. The way the ingredients on the recipe were written for the seasoning it appeared dry minced onion belonged in the seasoning. So I put the minced onion in that mix but then it said to cook the minced onion with the meat. I did both. It cooked for 8 hours and was wonderful. As a previous poster did I added one can of refried beans in for one can of the kidney beans blended as I didn't have a working blender and it was great. This is a less chunky chili so if you prefer more chunks add some bell pepper, more beans or chunks of onion or even chunks of beef. If not enjoy it's smooth texture. Served with bowls of cheese, white raw onion, avocado etc for toppings. Thanks Debbie. Enjoy! Chef DLH

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review: Extremely simple and delicious!   I made my own blend of Italian seasoning,  and made exactly as directed.   So nice!!!!   I served it with recipe#41167,  and they complemented each other well.  We enjoyed this recipe for the Great Barbie Challenge,  ZWT 8, thank you Rita!!

name: kittencal s onion patties latkes
review: I'm not going to rate stars for this. I cannot seem to get over the baking powder.

name: simple caribbean jerk chicken
review: This chicken had wonderful flavor.  It was so quick and easy to fix.  DH just loved it.  Thanks for posting.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: YUM!!  I loved this and will definitely make it again.  Thanks!!  UPDATE:  I make this all the time, and like Geema, I omit the cheese and final broiling.  This is my favorite way to prepare salmon!  Thanks again!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: We enjoyed this dish -- it was a nice change of pace and I was looking for a flavorful recipe for the slow cooker.  I did not use frozen chicken breasts, but instead browned chicken thighs and used them instead.  It did make a lot of sauce; however, I served the chicken over rice and it worked great.  I'll bet the leftovers will really be even better.  Next time I might add additional black beans and corn -- just my preference.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: When you are right, you are right and you are so right about this being Healthy, Easy and very Tasty! I made two of these one with basil and one without basil, both were equally good. This was so easy, yummy and healthy that it going to become a summer staple in our home. Thanks for the post.

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: My daughter made this cake for our family vacation. She used a 9x13 pan and it turned out perfect. Great dense texture and rich buttery flavor. The ideal poundcake. I'm sure we'll make again. It's not healthy, but pretty much worth every darn calorie. Thanks for posting.

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: Sensational! Our good friend mummamills made these for us for dinner last night-I can't believe how simple, tasty and healthy your method of cooking is. Thanks for posting.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: We had these for dinner the other night-mummamills cooked them for us and I was so impressed. The recipe seemed VERY easy to put together, and the result was a delicious meal for us.

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review:
Made for the Australian BBq challenge What a wonderful explosion of taste. Thank you for posting
Made for the World tour 8

name: chicken legs grilled
review: This was good and easy to make. I followed the recipe as written other then I only used half the pepper. I lined my grill with foil but the chicken still really burnt. I put it in a roasting pan and then the chicken cooked better.

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: Add me onto the 5 star list!  I made it with 1 can of Amy's Lentil Soup (like a couple other reviewers suggested), about 1 cup of grated and saut?ed veggies- onion, garlic, carrots, mushrooms, zucchini (like how many reviewers suggested), shredded cheese, 1 egg, 1 scant cup old fashioned oats, and all bbq sauce with extra on top.  It took about 45 minutes, and it was perfect!  I really didn't notice the cheese when eating it, so I think I'll leave that out to save on calories next time.  My husband really loved this, too!  Using the soup made it so easy!

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review: Great Shrimp recipe.  Easy and quick to make.   Made a great dinner with some beer batter fish.  Made for ZWT8.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: thanks you! I made spaghetti and meatballs for 50 years, but I  am 70 now, and don't cook like that anymore. I use to make wonderful meatballs, with no recipe. You know the old saying,"use it or lose it?" Your recipe fascinated me, because it sounded exactly the way MY recipes used to read. they were wonderful! thank you so much for helping an old lady cook like she used to!

name: wholly guacamole
review: Very good! First time I've made Guacamole myself but it was much better than any I've been served before.

name: impossible peanut butter cookies
review:
I made these cookies this morning. Seemed easy enough. I used Jif creamy peanut butter and white sugar.. one large egg. I couldn't 'drop' onto cookie sheet. The mixture was just too crumbly. I had to squish it into my palms into a greasy little disk.. then I pressed into white sugar.. pressed with fork and baked. Maybe another egg would have helped.. not sure.
I got 17 cookies out of the mixture. The cookies are very delicate and crumbly.

UPDATED the very same day. I had to give it one more star because people said they tasted good and one lady wanted the recipe.

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: Oh wow, this was so good.  I only had three chicken breasts - wish I would have had more.  Next time, for sure, I will.  I didn't have chedder cheese soup, so used cream of mushroom and added some shredded sharp chedder cheese and a little milk.  Yummy sauce.

name: southwestern stuffed bell peppers
review: OK - so I LOOVED this recipe.  Super good.  Thanks for posting.  I did make some changes...added water to the canned tomatoes as recommended - also added a small can of green chili's to the tomatoes.  I used the taco seasoning mix here on this site - http://www.food.com/recipe/taco-seasoning-budget-friendly-seasoning-for-tacos-burritos-166030 and used Quinoa as a sub for the rice.  I also mixed some of the cheese into the meat mixture.  It was super good.  I'm going to make this again soon.  I sure hope the CSA keeps the peppers coming!  :)

name: basic batter waffles
review: They came out perfect.

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: This sauce is so much better than canned!  Used for recipe#224280 and it was a great addition.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Super easy!  Loved it.

name: real southern cornbread
review: Good cornbread.  I'm from the south and putting sugar in cornbread was always a northern thing. However, a cast iron skillet and buttermilk is always called for in a good recipe for southern cornbread.  I enjoyed, but some of the older folks still don't want the sugar added. Thanks for sharing your version.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: I doubled the spices, but still wanted more flavor.  My husband said it was good though.  I appreciated the ease of making it.  I'm sure I'll make this again.

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: FINALLY!  An enchilada recipe that my Mexican-food snob liked.  However, the tweaks that I did was to omit the tomato sauce, and just use a can of enchilada sauce and a couple tablespoons of brown sugar, and some salt to bring out the flavors.  Since we're chili-heads, I also used some pequin peppers with the meat, and some of the heat went with the discarded grease, but it still had a bit of zip for us.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: Not that this recipe needs another review... but this is awesome. The whole family loved it, including the kid-teens.  I found the directions a bit confusing but it all worked out. I had more "special sauce" than we needed so that could easily be halved or do what I did and add it to the chicken mixture.  I poured 2/3 of the special sauce over the chicken mixture and heated it through. Served it on romaine leaves. My son suggested crunchy chow main noodles on top, so I'll give that a go next time. Thanks for sharing, it's a keeper.

name: big grandma s best peanut butter cookies
review: This will be my go-to peanut butter cookie from now on!!  Very easy, especially if the grandkids get involved on the rolling!  I didn't have Butter Crisco so I made it the way my mom used do when I was a kid.  She would do 1/2 margarine (not the spread kind but a good brand in the stick form) and 1/2 Crisco.  We doubled this recipe and we have dough coming out our ears.  Thought I would freeze some but doubt they make it there, they are so good.  Making a note that my review will be number 248 just to see how far this recipe goes years from now.  Thanks for posting!!  Sooo good!!

name: quick spanish rice
review: Such an easy and delicious rice dish.  My Mother stated that it was the best she had ever eaten!  I failed to add the oregano by accident, but I don't feel that the taste was significantly altered.  Cooked for 25 minutes and the rice on the bottom of the pan was starting to burn, so next time I will only cook for 20 minutes.  Very nice recipe and thanks for posting Sharlene W.

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: What a quick, tasty and filling dinner. I used ground turkey and added a bell pepper and jalapeno while cooking, used 4 tortillas and added some fresh salsa when layering. I'm looking forward to the leftovers. Thanks for posting.

name: unknownchef86 s very best dinner rolls
review: Pretty good.  I just tossed all my ingredients into the bread machine, saving lots of trouble. Light & fluffy.

name: crock pot chili pork chops     a must try
review: Simple, yummy and flavorful. The pork chops (mine were thin) basically fell apart (tender). I would love to try this again with thick cut pork chops. I too placed unpeeled whole baby red potatoes, a whole vadallia onion and the garlic in the bottom of the pot, placed the pork chops atop the vegetables and topped with the sauce.  Probably used half of the amount of the water called for, doubled the cumin & chili powder, lastly adding a dash of cinnamon. This was a keeper. I may try a little lime juice in the sauce next time for that chili-lime flavor. Served with steamed broccoli. Thanks for sharing an inspiring recipe!

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Excellent!  Next time I would probably decrease the sugar by 1/2.  I used these as the foundation for a breakfast for dinner sandwich with egg, ham and cheese and it was absolutely delicious!

name: no bake rice krispies peanut butter granola bars  lower fat
review: These were really delicious. I used 1 3/4 cups rice krispies, agave nectar and dried cranberries. They came out great. Although, I think next time, and there will be a next time, I'll use less sugar, no chocolate, more peanut butter or almond, and mix in a bunch of extra healthy goodies. I'm trying to cut back on sugar. Thanks so much for posting this extremely flexible recipe.

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review: The taste is so good.  The seasonings are great.  My son also liked it since it was not spicy.  But it would also be great with red pepper flakes.  Thanks Rita :)  Made for ZWT8 for Diners, Winers and Chives

name: mexican stuffed shells  oamc
review: I had some leftover taco meat to use up and tried your recipe.  It was delicious!  I made as written except fried up the onions a bit in oil then added the leftover meat and salsa.  It worked like a charm and my family was none the wiser!!!!  Thank you for sharing this great recipe, I plan on using it again when I need something quick.

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: Yummy, easy and healthy...that means 5 stars from me!  Only thing I do differently is add a handful of green olives. Yum!  thanks for the great recipe Carol.....

name: uncle bill s vegetarian minestrone soup
review: Delicious and very simple to prepare.  Following the recipe to a "T", however adding in 3 teaspoons "Better Than Vegetable Bouillon" Vegetable Base and also 2 links of Tofurky Kielbasa, cut into small pieces.  I would not change a thing!  We really enjoyed this soup and will look forward to having it again.  Thanks so much for sharing all your wonderful recipes with us Uncle Bill!!

name: copycat ihop harvest grain   nut pancakes
review: Incredible!  I was introduced to these pancakes, looking for a healthier alternative at IHOP.  I made this recipe pretty much as directed.  I used the blender to process the oatmeal, then pulsed the walnuts and almonds a few times. I replaced the buttermilk with almond coconut milk, which turned out to be fabulous.  I used coconut oil on the skillet.  Real Canadian Maple Syrup and sliced bananas to top for an incredible experience I will look forward to again!  Thanks so much for sharing, JustaQT!

name: basil pesto
review: I had an abundance of basil in my garden this year. Unfortunately, it was the only herb that did any good this summer. I had no idea what to do with all of it, and one of my coworkers suggested making pesto. I've always liked pesto, but I didn't even know what was in it! This is delicious! So quick and easy to make! And cheap, too! I may try the walnut version next time. The pine nuts were expensive and hard to find. Thanks!

name: kittencal s italian zucchini mozzarella patties
review: These were good. Different than I expected somehow. I LOVE fried zucchini and thought this would be a stepped up version of that. It wasn't, it was more like a potato pancake. Thanks for posting the recipe!

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: DD was less than thrilled with the idea of eating a soup filled with beans and spinach.  But she was more than willing to give it a try once she got a whiff of it cooking.  "That smells sooooo good!"  Well I guess it didn't disappoint.  Everyone in my family gave it 4 or 5 stars, which is excellent coming from this crew.  Thanks so much for a wonderful recipe.

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: These were yummy! Tender, fluffy and cheesy and so easy to make. I got 12 perfect sized biscuits! Thanks for posting :)

name: chocolate eclair dessert
review:
Very good! I don't care for the container frosting, so I used Recipe #351946 (just the frosting). Worked great!
I give 4 stars because I was disappointed in the taste with the graham crackers. I'm sure I had this growing up, and I knew the crackers would be soggy... but they didn't even taste like graham crackers; it was almost like soggy wheat bread! I'd probably have to blame Honey Maid for changing their product. If I make it again, I might try vanilla wafers or some other cookie...

name: the best snickerdoodles i have ever eaten
review: These are good with lots of cinnamon flavor.  Thanks for sharing.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: Delicious! I added a sprinkling of almonds and they were a nice additional crunch!

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: Incredible! The best chocolate cake ever! I made a triple layer cake with your frosting and it is to die for... thanks for posting!!

name: general tso s chicken  tso chung gai
review: a lot of work. and the flavor was just ok. I'll look elsewhere for chinese food in the future.

name: self rising flour
review: Went to make recipe#429494 and didn't have self rising flour - used this and it worked perfect - I'll be using it from now on whenever the need arises.

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: I made this yesterday. I added two banana, walnuts, and cinnamon. I also used lemon zest because I didn't have an orange. I think I would of preferred them better without the zest.
