I smashed the raspberries and bananas up. You could not taste any of the banana. I liked them better coming out of the fridge, cold.

name: the best belgian waffles
review: This is an awesome waffle recipe. I've made this recipe both in a traditional Belgian waffle maker and in a square waffle machine--it turned out great both times. This is going to be my go to waffle recipe from now on, they are just delicious!!

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: I've made many variations of  chocolate cake, but this recipe seems to be a cake that all chocolate likers will eat.  I think it's the well balanced combination of ingredients that make it so well received--not too much chocolate or too much sugar.  If you're cooking for family or guests who like chocolate, it may not be their favorite chocolate cake, but it's a cake they will all like and eat. You won't be wasting your time and effort making this cake.Thanks for posting the recipe and its variations.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Why put water in something just to reduce it?  Good anyway.

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: It's perfect. Easy. Tastes amazing. Good on everything. Definitely keeping this recipe at my fingertips. Thank you!

name: banana banana bread
review: I had 2 bananas so I made a half batch - delicious!  It baked a little quicker as it was only half as big.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This was simply fantastic!  I had no idea that something so easy, and so few ingredients, could take on such a wonderful taste of its own.  It also accepts the flavor of cilantro very well. Enjoyed with recipe#485580.  Thanks Jen Santiago for posting.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: very good recipe.

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: If you're looking for a light and fluffy pancake, this in not the recipe for you. But, if you're looking for a pancake recipe that will fill you up and keep you full, look no further. I added a little bit of cinnamon to the mix and mixed up the batter the night before. We liked the flavor and texture. Thanks for posting.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: Flavor will totally depend on the quality of your bbq sauce.  But this recipe gets 5 stars for when I got ease.  I took my chicken breast right from the freezer and tossed them in the crock pot with the sauce and onion. The house smelled wonderful when I got home from work. I shredded the chicken because it was falling apart.  Next time I may shred it a little sooner so it can really soak up the sauce.

name: zucchini lasagna  lasagne    low carb
review: This recipe is a really nice change form regular heavy lasagna. I didn't miss the noodles at all. The sauce was too mild for us, so I doubled and tripled some the seasoning and garlic and I think it was still too mild. I'm looking forward to making it again and really tinkering with the sauce to suite our tastes. Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: moist chocolate cupcakes  super easy  budget
review: Wonderful! Love that there is no egg and it isn't too sweet. I added chocolate chips and paired with Recipe #481319 for a fabulous combination!

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: What a hit!! Easy to do and yummy! I broiled a few minutes at the end to crisp up the bacon a bit. I didn't have toothpicks in the house, so just laid them seam side down on the pan. Based on other reviews, I also lined the bottom of the broiler pan with foil. A definite repeat. Why not use chicken tenders and make it a main meal?

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: Colleagues loved this - only problem is people are asking me to bring pie in all the time! Really couldn't be easier either....

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: Very good. I made the recipe as directed using bone in chicken breasts, fresh off the cob corn and 1 cup of black beans. The chicken was cooked perfectly and the rice was yummy.

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: I can't believe this recipe gets such wonderful reviews.   First it is overly sweet and secondly they dry out in a short time.  Guess they would be fine if eaten same day as made.  Sorry.........

name: cheese and garlic drop biscuits
review: These turned out pretty good. I have never bought a box of Bisquick and never plan to. I want to make them again, when I do I think I'll substitute real butter for the shortening as I think it was missing the buttery flavor. Likewise, I'll double the garlic as my DH stated he couldn't taste it at all and missed it. The prep, texture and baking times were right on, I ended up with 9 medium sized biscuits, just enough to go with our Chicken Pot Pie tonight for dinner. Thanks for sharing.

name: reduced fat alfredo sauce
review: I made this and it  was fantastic and perfect for my Baked pasta.

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: Perfect! Extra hot chili powder was all I had on hand, so it was kick'n, but tasty just the same. Thanks so much!

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review:
TERRIFIC is all we can say,
Remember TGIF's...this soup MADE MY DAY!
Quick, delicious, healthy too!
HIGHLY recommended to you too!
For those in Australia, found black beans at Asian Grocery, TRUE!...vacuumed packed or dry, is up to YOU!
UPDATE: Made this again today! Got the WHOO HOO again is what I can say!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: I did think it was too salty and my dough was crumbly but greasy at the same time.  Not sure what went wrong.

name: perfect pasta salad
review: First off, the dressing was perfect us. I used my favorite olive oil and red wine vinegar, so don't let the recommendations stop you from trying this amazing recipe, use what you have on hand. Think of this as a fantastic base recipe. After the pasta and dressing make it your own and add whatever your family likes. I did emulsify the dressing with my stick blender. Great stuff Mrs. Jaye! Thank you for posting.

name: low carb pizza
review: What a delicious surprise.  I made mine with pesto and chicken sausage, omitting the tomato sauce.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: This was a hit tonight.  I served it with crusty french bread (#101476) with olive oil and herbs and it was delicious.  Great meal.  I ended up using 1 lb ground beef and 1 lb italian sausage.  Other than that everything remained the same.  I had enough cheese mixture and meat sauce left to cover the top layer of noodles with more of both and then topped with mozzarella.  Lasagna is a great meal that just takes so much time, but it is worth it in the end.

name: crock pot garlic brown sugar chicken
review: I am so sorry, but this recipe didn't work for us... I cooked this for 6 hours on LOW, and came home to black overcooked chicken. It smelled AMAZING and probably is, but I might try cooking it for 4 hours next time?

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: doesnt really need another review does it :) Best crumble ever! I did sub some demera sugar, for some of the brown, and it gives the crumble an even better CRUNCH!

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: This recipe is not only great, it is easy and would be an ideal dish to serve guests because it looks and tastes as you have been slaving away in the kitchen for hours.   I usually don't like cooked salmon as much as the raw stuff (mmm... sushi), but this could convert me to cooked salmon.   My DH said it is a must make again and soon rather than later, which is a very high compliment from him.

name: world s best cinnamon raisin bread  not bread machine
review: I cut the recipe down for just 1 loaf but my is it good.  Love it toasted in the morning.  May make some honey butter to go with it.

name: cake batter ice cream
review: This ice cream is fabulous!!  I absolutely loved it.

name: chocolate mint candy  fudge
review: Very good mint candy.  We made this for family and friends last year for the holidays and I forgot to ratre it.  It melted in your mouth.  Perfect for gift giving.  Thanks for sharing the recipe with us.

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: Delicious! Since the batter was thin I made them smaller and cooked on a hot griddle which worked well. Served with recipe #17086 for a very yummy breakfast. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: These were very easy to make and tasted great!  My son was amazed at how thick they were...they passed his test.  Thank you for sharing!

name: bacardi rum cake
review: This cake has been around for so many years but still very popular.   Over time I have made a few changes (to suit our tastes) and now use a French Vanilla cake mix and substitute 1/2 cup melted and unsalted butter for the oil.  I do add a few tablespoons of oil just to ensure extra moistness.   Any way that it is made alsways a hit.

name: buttery shrimp and pasta
review: Fantastic!!!  I added a few extra ingredients due to the reviews I read.  I added mushrooms, chopped broccoli and a little mozerella cheese to thicken the sauce.  Otherwise I followed the recipe as written.  My husband couldn't get enough.  Thanks so much for sharing.

name: parmesan zucchini
review: Wow...loved it!  I had chopped up some zucchini for a stir fry and then changed my dinner plans.  I was able to pop this in the oven alongside the  Recipe #22126 and enjoy a simple, yet delicious meal.  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: I'm not a fan of creamed soup recipes, but since it was posted by yooper, who has many  other delicious recipes, I thought I'd give this a whirl.  Easy, tasty and a change of pace from ordinary pork chops.  I had very thick chops, so timing worked out well, although I turned the oven temp down to 325.  Thanks, yooper, for yet another good recipe.

name: crunchy granola
review: Pretty simple.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: pretty good.  I don't think I crushed enough of the potatoes to release the starch and thicken the soup.  Be sure to do that if you don't want a chunky watery soup.

name: banana banana bread
review: Just took this out of the oven and it is delicious!  I did lay foil over it to prevent it from browning as my oven does have a tendency to do that.  It took about 50 minutes to cook.  Excellent!!!

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: We loved the rich, deep flavour of this taco seasoning mix, which really helped us out in a pinch when the store was closed! The recipe made a lot and we used about half in a pound of beef to make taco burgers and found the flavour to be just right. Thanks for another winner Kittencal!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: I made this for dinner tonight and really enjoyed it.  I used pangasius fillets, halved the butter and subbed greek yogurt for the mayo. Definitely a keeper recipe.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Sure was tasty and quick, thank you!

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Great flavors in this dish.  I served it at room temp. and added a little cotija cheese.  Served with Recipe #21935.

name: low carb pizza
review: I have tried several low carb pizzas & this one is by far the best. I used 1 less egg in the crust because mine were huge. I also followed the other reviewer's suggestion & baked the cheese 1st for 5 minutes before adding the egg mixture. Very hearty & delicious, thanks.

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: This is a very easy but tasty recipe.  I added some tofu at the last 5 minutes.

name: simple tomato sandwich
review: I prefer mine untoasted (fresh and white as rice) and with Hellman's and S&P.  Just a matter of taste and what we grew up on.   I could eat these 3x's a day.

name: hot german potato salad
review: I made this tonight to go with some fresh made German Brats.  Why oh why haven't I made this before!  This was easy to make and I followed the recipe exactly as written.  Upon tasting, it did need an extra little "something" so I gave another good pinch of the cayenne.  DELISH and I will make this again!! Thank you for sharing your family heirloom recipe!!

name: stove top tamale pie
review: Good recipe!  I tossed in some chili powder, cumin, onion powder, garlic & seasoning salt instead of the taco seasoning, used black beans and added some corn to the beef mixture at someone else's suggestion.  Everyone liked it & I appreciated how fast this came together!

name: caesar pork chops
review: They were ok.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: This was a very simple and tasty sauce. I served with it over spaghetti and topped with meatballs. I only used a 1/2 lb. of pasta, but made the full recipe for the sauce.Thanks for posting.

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: This was great, scaled it down to fit our family.  Thank you!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: I x4 the recipe to use 1 lb of pasta. I also used roasted red pepper instead of sun dried tomatoes. Was great!!!

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: This was a simple, flavorful way to bake chicken. Thanks for posting!

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: was good and easy.  Not great.

name: parmesan zucchini
review: This was a really nice, light and tasty side dish. Couldn't have been any easier. Thanks for posting.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: This recipe is perfect!  It would be great served in soft tacos with a bit of guacamole as a meal.  I will make this recipe often, Barb!  Thank you!

name: chunky blue cheese salad dressing
review: This was too sweet for me.  Thanks for sharing, though!

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: This tasted great and it was so easy to put together.  Thank you!

name: jello cake
review: Loved this.  I used pineapple cake and pineapple jello.  When I poured the jello liquid over the cake I thought wow that is too soggy but it soaked up nicely after refrigeration.

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: I made this one day, tasted it, fell in love with it, and the following day made a quadruple batch to serve on ice cream at a birthday party.  It got rave reviews all around.  I followed the recipe except for increasing the amount of vanilla to 1/2 tsp.  Used the full amount of butter.  Will never again buy chocolate sauce...

name: cranberry feta pinwheels
review: Oops - forgot to review these....made these for our Christmas Party.  Everyone loved them!

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: Without a doubt, this is the best pizza crust I have ever made!  (I have tried probably over 100 different recipes over 31 years of marriage -- no joke).  It was the perfect amount of dough for my 14" perforated Chicago Metallic pan.  I like cracker crust pizza and my husband likes his more like the Pizza Hut hand-tossed variety.  This was the perfect compromise for both of us!   I did pre-bake it for five minutes and may bake a little longer next time; we were hungry last night.  It actually got a bit crisper after coming out of the oven.  Next time, I won't be so lazy and will try it out on my Lodge iron pizza pan.  Unknownchef86, thank you so very much for the rescued recipe!  It is a keeper!!

name: olive garden fettuccine alfredo
review: The best Alfredo ever! I did use 8 oz cream cheese, as suggested by Barry Barton. Unbelievably good!

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: This was very easy and so delicious.  Everyone in my family liked it.  My son even ate it as dip the next day.  Will definitely make again.  Thanks for posting!

name: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
review: I recently read that using shortening improved the texture of cookies, so I was intrigued by the shortening/butter mix here.  I used butter crisco.  I love soft cookies and usually bake less than the stated time, but I left these all in for 9 1/2 to 10 minutes, until they didn't look wet.  Now a day later, they have kept their lovely soft texture.  They were kind of thin, but not at all runny.  I used my cookie scoop and got 66 beautiful cookies.  I probably would have gotten the full 6 dozen had I not eaten so much dough :)  I will try dropping the temp a bit and using convection next time, to save some time.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: So delicious, so easy!  When I first got married, my grandma was horrified that I fed my husband brownies from a box.  She would be so happy now!  I've made these twice.  I had to substitute real butter for shortening once, and it was fine.  I do not believe in nuts in brownies, but I DO believe in chocolate chips :)  These were still warm when we cut in to them last night.  There were 9 kids and 6 adults there and we had the pan empty in minutes.  These are a winner!!!

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: This recipes is very easy to make.  I did not have dill seed so used dill weed.  I cut the chicken into large pieces, just because I like the look better.  Made for Please Review My Recipe

name: copycat applebee s hot artichoke and spinach dip
review: 5 stars from every member of the family!! Now that's a great recipe.  I did add some extra garlic, just because we always do.  I doubled the recipe and baked in a 8 x 13 pyrex pan for the regular time listed.  Turned out perfect.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Very good.  I mixed everything and placed in a bag and marinated for 2 hours.  Cooked as directed.  When it was done I removed the chicken from the pan and added a bit of cornstarch to the liquid.  I cooked that on the stove-top until it was thick and served with the chicken.  (It didn't need it, but the kids loved adding to their rice).  Very good and moist chicken.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: Good.  Thanks for sharing.

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: This was so good.  We had an abundance of yellow heirloom tomatoes and used them in this recipe.  I should have read the reviews about hot liquid and blenders but I did discover that about three ladels full of tomatoes worked fine in the blender.  I used whole milk because I had that and I wouldn't know the difference because I haven't had this soup out and we will be making this again and again.

name: classic baked spaghetti
review: Let me start by saying that my husband declared this one of the best pasta dishes he has ever eaten.  He had two helpings, added some of the leftovers to his eggs in the morning (gross, I know), and took the last of the leftovers for lunch today.  It was really a great meal, and I think the key is the spaghetti sauce.  I used a homemade sauce that I threw together when I realized I didn't have any jarred sauce and I took the advice of other reviewers and added another 15 oz can of crushed tomatoes to the recipe. I also used turkey instead of beef and whole wheat spaghetti. I didn't have enough cheddar cheese for the whole casserole so I used a blend of cheddar, Italian blend and Parmesan.  I also added some dehydrated onions when I cooked the turkey for some extra yum.  I layered everything in my Pampered Chef deep covered baker, baked for 15 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.  The result was a perfectly cooked casserole that I could eat once a week.  Thank you for posting such a great recipe that is so easily adapted!  We will make this one quite often.

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: Fast and easy and yummy and moist too!  What a smart recipe.  We skipped the frosting and dusted with powdered sugar.  I actually made two 8 by 8 cakes instead of the 9 by 13.  One for us and one for my parents.  I halved the recipe for each pan.  Adjusted to 1/2 tsp. salt, 1/4 cup applesauce and 1/4 cup oil in each pan.  Turned out great!

name: cake batter ice cream
review: WOW!!!!  I used 1 cup vanilla soymilk and 2 cups Silk original coffee creamer in place of the dairy ingredients and used 1/2 c sugar and 3/4 cup confetti cake mix and... it is literally the best soy ice cream I've ever made (and I've made some pretty dang good soy ice cream).  Will be repeating... probably weekly.

name: blue ridge mountains chocolate chip cookies
review: Delicious!  I used the extra flour and they turned out great, didn't get flat.  Next time, would add some nuts, but didn't have any handy this time.

name: kittencal s  brown sugar caramel sauce or ice cream topping
review: Caramel sauce perfection! Thanks for posting.

name: vegetarian lasagna
review: I thought this was absolutely excellent!  I am trying a vegetarian diet this month and this recipe really made me happy.  :)  My family didn't rave about it like I did but they did eat it w/o any complaints.  That's huge since it was filled with veggies.  Thanks for posting.

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: I'm so happy to have found this recipe!  I halved the recipe and got enough for a plate-sized pancake two days in a row that were not only very good tasting but also filling.  And better for me than regular pancakes.  I used my favorite Log Cabin syrup on them.  I'll definitely be making these again.  Thanks, Mom of Five!

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: Not sure how you can go wrong with this one. At it's "worst" it's a chopped fresh veggie medley - fresh cucumbers and basil always are a winner - and it appears to be nearly impossible to mess up. I could have added more garlic salt and pepper but too quickly threw the dish out on the table when people arrived so by the time I tasted it the salad was mostly gone. Very versatile and, as I said, impossible to go wrong!

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: This is a wonderful classic recipe that I've been making for years.  The  recipe I received years ago indicated a 9x13 pan and that's what I've always used baking at 350 for about 27 min.  I follow the recipe exactly, but sometimes add an additional 1/4 c. of chips. Anyone who likes chocolate should like these pan cookies. The idea of adding peanut butter or M&Ms seems like fun. Thanks for sharing.

name: chili s salsa
review: Mmmmmmmmm so good. I used a small serano chili, 1/2 lime juiced & cilantro. So easy and will be my go to recipe from now on. Thanks!

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: I served this tonight over noodles with steamed broccoli on the side.  I felt it could use a little more seasoning, but all in all, we enjoyed it.  Even put the sauce on the broccoli!  Super easy to throw together and the family gave it four stars.

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: Love these!  I've made them twice now, and both times I've skipped the soaking step and used the parchment paper method, allowing me to use the entire turn table in the microwave to place the potatoes on (the only microwave safe dishes I have are much smaller, so would limit the number of chips I can cook at a time).  I re-spray the parchment each batch, and definitely reduce the number of minutes to cook each batch.  First batch took 10 minutes, down to about 6 minutes for the 5th or 6th batch.  I just used salt and pepper.  I was considering making them for a BBQ tomorrow, but I think it would take way too long to cook enough batches for 15 people (I can eat almost 2 whole potatoes worth just by myself if I'm not careful!).  Potato chips are one of my weaknesses, so I'm really happy to have an almost guilt free way to eat them!  Thank you!

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: This really exceeded my expectations, even with all the great reviews.  It was SO delicious.  The girls in my family especially couldn't seem to get enough.  It was so moist and tender.  With only the caraway seeds and raisins (which we plumped in whiskey) to really provide flavor, I was surprised at how much flavor this bread had.  We ate it as a side to an Irish stew.  We ate half of the loaf, and I'm interested to see if it stays moist when we have leftovers in a day or two.

name: saltine candy   toffee
review: Tastes like a skor bar!!  My favourite!  Skipped the nuts... DELISH!

name: best baked potato
review: Just like those delicious baked potatoes you get in restaurants!  This was fabuous and I will be using this recipe from now on!  Followed the recipe exactly.

name: brown rice and lentil casserole
review: I've put off making this because it looks bland in the photo, but I finally made it tonight when DH is working and it's pretty good! I added a handful of chopped mushrooms, peas, and two grated carrots, more garlic powder too as suggested. Also added 1 cup of mixed italian cheese blend from Aldi which worked well with the spice. I think the mushrooms really made it. Will make this cheapy cheap, healthy meal again. Thanks!

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review:
Wanted a quick muffin recipe to make for my girls' school lunches - something other than the standard PB&J. This definitely fits the bill. Both girls raved about them. Will definitely keep this one around.
Thanks for posting!!

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: This was great!  The whole family loved it!  No changes needed but you can add a topping (BBQ or something) if you are feeling adventurous.  Thanks SaraFish.......

name: softest ever bread machine bread
review: Hands down a clear winner for best, tastiest, and softest bread in existence! Can't get much easier, unless you go to the store and buy it. You will LOVE this bread. I prefer to make in bread machine and finish off in oven, just for own personal preference. This is indeed everything that it suggests. Excellent! Thanks, K!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: Eh

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Excellent soup.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Great flavor and smelled so good we could smell it outside!  Thanks!!

name: the easiest  bestest focaccia bread ever
review: I baked this up for our game day snacks.  Once it cooled, we split it down the middle and filled it with sandwich ingredients.  We used ham, turkey, lettuce, onions, tomatoes, alfalfa sprouts and green onion mayo.  This is delicious.  I have never made focaccia before and DD want to use it as a pizza crust too.  Thank you for this delicious recipe.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: So wonderful and yet, couldn't be more simple to prepare.  A definite keeper!  Thanks as always, MizzNezz.  : )

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: Great Stack-Up.  Very easy to do, great flavors and very Filling meal.

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: My oven only goes to 500 degrees so set it for that; also my tenderloin was a little over 1 pound so I cooked it for 9 minutes and then turned it off and left the oven closed.  My tenderloin was a little too rare for our liking; not sure if it was under cooked or cooked perfectly but looked under cooked based on how we usually cook it (we may just over cook it usually).  Was very tender and juicy and I just sauteed the slices in a pan for a couple minutes on each side to be sure it was cooked through.  Will use this method again; even with cooking the tenderloin slices afterwards it still turned out more moist and tender than any other way we have cooked it.  Made for Help A Naked Recipe Tag in the Photo Forum.

name: quick spanish rice
review: Good, but a little dry.  Added about 3/4 cup of V8 juice.  I too agree with Pippy, I love meals that turn into meals~~and I had some leftover from the stuffed peppers I made.  Let's see....

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: Loved this dish!  Probably should have waited until it was 20 below zero to make it--but it was delicious even in 90 degree heat!!  I used 2% velveeta and turkey sausage with no compromise to taste or texture.  The hardest part was scrubbing and boiling the potatos!!  I might consider adding a little spinach or kale next time--please try this, you won't be disappointed!!

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: Really good. I used diced cooked chicken that I had frozen previously from a roast chicken dinner. We don't like onions, so I subbed three green onions instead, and my mushroom soup didn't have garlic so I added some jarred minced garlic. Cooked on low for 8 hours. Delicious! Served five for supper with just enough left for two lunches tomorrow.

name: microwave poached eggs
review: Worked perfectly - 77 seconds !! No explosions thankfully - thanks to all the warnings !!

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: The pineapple cake mix definitely spoils this cake and, as others have mentioned, it gives an aritificial pineapple cake.   Made with a yellow or white cake mix is a big improvement  - atleast for our tastebuds.   Thanks for the recipe tho because with these changes it is great.

name: crock pot ham and beans
review: This is good but I could really detect a strong flavor of cloves.  I had trouble getting past that taste, so I probably won't make again, unless I leave the cloves out.

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: This recipe gets 5 stars because my DH and the kids thought it was 5 stars and because it made the house smell good. I gave it 4 stars for taste and 5 stars for ease of prep so in the end 5 it is. It is super easy to make and the sauce is good. I made it as written but next time will do some add ins like peas, mushrooms and/or onions. It is comfort food. I couldn't really taste either of the soups but they complement each other nicely. The lack of seasoning was a problem for me but the guys loved it that way. I served it on top of egg noodles and along side vegetables. Good meal. Thanks for posting Kathleen Traylor. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: crock pot thai chicken thighs
review:
I did as some other reviewers and tweaked this a little bit. I don't like crock pot cooking so I used the dutch oven method (90 minutes at 350) and the chicken thighs were cooked perfectly. I also added the rest of the coconut milk (1 can minus the 1 cup for the rice) and used medium fresh salsa from the grocery store. I put limes in my cart at the store but somewhere along the way my 2 year old ejected them and I didn't notice. So I substituted white vinegar for acidity. I'm sure this took away from the flavor of the dish though.
Overall we liked the flavors a lot, but the texture, between the rice and the sauce, was a little gummy. This is where some fresh lime juice right before serving would have come in really handy; I think it would have cut the thickness of the sauce beautifully. So next time, and there will be a next time, I will make sure to have the limes at the ready.
My 2 and 3 1/2 year old daughters and husband enjoyed the meal, but my 6 and 7 year old sons were not that thrilled with it. The peanut garnish helped them get through it though!
Thanks for posting. This is a really easy and quick (in the dutch oven anyway) way to cook chicken thighs that's a nice break from the norm.

name: cajun sauteed shrimp
review: I used 8 Prawns and 1/2 the seasoning. It was yummy, but I think in future less seasoning for that amount of prawns!! Thanks for sharing your recipe.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Very tasty. Easy to make. I would make this again for sure.

name: chicken garlic bites
review: Great recipe! I added some salt to marinade and Italian seasoning to the crumbs. The four of us didn't take long to finish these off.

name: panda express orange chicken
review: Mmmm, hmmmm...pretty freakin' awesome despite the confusing directions!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: This was a bit sweet but definently a winner!

name: banana oatmeal bread
review: I made it with Rye flour.  Very good.

name: queso blanco dip
review: Wow, this is excellent.  You definitely have to use the white american cheese as it really makes it.  I tried Velveeta also and it is just not the same.  Easy and very very good.

name: kittencal s extreme chocolate brownies
review: We enjoyed these brownies.  I followed recipe as written.   I first gave them four stars because I thought they were a little cakey, but when I gave them to my family they did not agree with me and thought they were fantastic brownies and not cakey, so I changed my review to 5 stars three against one they won out.  I cooked them 35 minutes.  The edges were fine.  I used dark chocolate chips.  The taste was very good.

name: aloo gobi
review: Pretty tasty.  It really needs time to sit and absorb all the flavors though, so don't make this right before dinner.  Even better- try putting it serving-size containers and sticking it in the freezer and you'll have a great Indian side dish whenever you need it, and it tastes great.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: Wow, all these reviews made me think this was going to be perfect.  Really, it was decent, but kind of bland.  It's easy to tweak though and change to your liking.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: This was excellent! If you are looking for a very light meal but full on flavor this one is for you. I used egg substitute to "glue" the bread crumbs to the chicken rather than the mayo some reviewers suggested.

name: weight watchers mexican chicken breasts
review: Loaded with flavor and super-quick easy to make.  Thanks for sharing

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: The best beans I've ever eaten.  I'm not a vegetarian, but I could eat this on top of cilantro lime rice every day and not get sick of it.  What really brings everything together is the red wine vinegar.  Thanks for sharing.

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: This is a decent curry, especially for how quick and easy it is to make.  It is better to double the amount of curry powder though, and even then the flavors aren't as strong as in your usual curry.  Ultimately, I'm going to stick with my favorite curry recipes even though the cooking times are longer, but this recipe is a great option for people who are strapped for time.

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review:
Very good and so easy to make. I used country style spareribs which turn out so tender and meaty. I spread some liquid smoke on the ribs before I rubbed it with the seasoning mixture.
I also used smoked paprika and yes I did use a little ground red pepper. When I put them under the broiler I used Sweet Baby Ray's Hickory and Brown Sugar barbecue sauce. There was very little clean up work by using the tin foil.

name: classic pie crust  idiot proof step by step photo tutorial
review: Easier than a butter crust. I have never weighed ingredients before but the end result was great. Used for apple pie will make again!

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: This was good. Next time I would used crushed pineapple.

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Very easy, very delicious!! Will for sure make this again.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: I had some leftover cilantro lime rice so I mixed in the beans I had which were black eyed peas then pretty much followed the rest of the ingredients ..... really enjoyed this recipe and very colorful

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: Soooo good! I left out the cilantro but otherwise made as directed. DH is disappointed that I'm holding off on serving up the leftovers tonight.

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: My family gobbled it all up! This marinade is delicious. My husband went on and on about how tasty it was. I marinated chicken tenderloins for about 90 minutes, then the rains came. I was not able to grill them for over 24 hours > it was still yummy & and not overly marinated (I did pour off the excess marinade before storing). Thanks!

name: kittencal s scalloped potato and ground beef casserole
review: Made ahead for dinner using low fat/ reduced fat ingredients and veggie grounds instead of ground beef.  Popped it in the oven tonight for an hour covered and 30 minutes uncovered. We all enjoyed it.  It was a little on the spicy side for DD, so she requested less crushed pepper next time, but it didn't stop her from asking for seconds.  Served with steamed broccoli, made a delicious meal.

name: chicken legs grilled
review:
The flavor of this chicken is outstanding. I cooked it over indirect heat then browned over direct heat. However, I found this is more of a rub than a marinade. I mixed all the ingredients in a small bowl and slathered it on the chicken. I refrigerated on a plate covered with plastic wrap. This recipe goes into my hard copy "Family Favorites" cookbook. Thank you Rita, for posting this.

UPDATE: Since I started using this recipe in 2007, the powers that be decided that injecting chicken with a "flavor enhancing solution", was the way to go. I finally figured out why my grilled chicken was no longer getting crispy! I now buy only organic chicken for the grill and am again enjoying Rita's fantastic recipe.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: I made this (almost) exactly as written, except I used pico de gallo instead of regular salsa.  I couldn't believe how good it was!  I shredded the chicken before I added the cream cheese and gave everyone the option of folding it up in soft taco shells or serving it over rice.  It was delicious both ways.  Kudos for posting a simple, cheap and tasty recipe!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Awesome sauce!  Yes, I am a recipe tweaker, but hear my case...it was just what I was looking for, like a needle in a haystack...a recipe without creamed condensed soups. Well, I started with a recipe that did call for a creamed soup and came across this one for inspriation.  I cooked the chicken breasts in a crock pot with 3 stalks of celery and 1 whole, chopped onion, seasoned with pepper & Adobo garlic salt. I let that cook until done. Set the chicken aside, and took all the veggies, juice from crock pot & a can of chopped green chiles and pureed adding broth to that to equal the amount called for in the recipe. Made the roux...and the rest of the recipe as follows. Loved it. Kids all but licked their plates (unknowingly eating onions, celery and onions). Served with my black beans and rice. Thanks for saving me from a creamed soup compliation! We will definetly be making this one again. For the enchiladas I used onc side of the the dish pepperjack; the other 1/2 sharp cheddar (for the kids). YUM!

name: best baked potato
review: I agree..it's the best baked potato.  I used olive oil because I prefer the taste.

name: the cheesecake factory pumpkin cheesecake by todd wilbur
review: YUM! I've made this a few times, especially around this time of year :) I've made it both as written and subbing Splenda for the sugar.  Regular graham crust and gingersnap crust.  Came out beautifully both times.  Recently, made this for my BF who had never had a pumpkin cheesecake.  That's right, never had a pumpking cheesecake and he loved it.  I doubled the cinnamon (thanks, Sean!) and added some maple sugar to the crust (which I got from Spice House in Chicago). Beautiful! Thanks for posting!

name: nutella hot chocolate
review: Mmmm... so good! The bestest, simpleist ever!

name: best albondigas soup
review: I always order this soup when at restaurants, but have never attempted to make it at home.  Until tonight.  BF had never even heard of it before, but loved it!  This is spot on what albondigas should taste like.  And super easy too! Thanks for sharing, will be making this often!

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: Previously, I rated this poorly, and I'm updating to apologize!  Yes, the meat falls apart to the point that it's more of a stew-in-gravy than a pot roast. However, my husband has BEGGED me to make this at least once a month- and that's reason enough to rate it as a five-star recipe!  Because it falls apart so completely, I simply stir to make a meat-in-gravy sauce and pour over pasta or rice :)  As a pot roast, this is two stars. As a creamy meaty sauce, it's 6 stars! (Just don't add salt... it's quite salty on its own)

name: banana banana bread
review: Very good banana bread. The banana is definitely the star here, as it should be! I loved that it was so easy to put together. I checked mine after 55 minutes and it was just staring to get too well done. It probably could have been pulled out after 50 minutes. Thanks for posting this yummy, easy recipe! Made for the I Recommend Tag in the Cooking Tag Games forums.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review:
This pizza sauce is fantastic! The texture was perfect, and the flavor was outstanding.

I did make a few changes by reducing the oil to 1 tbs. and omitted the butter and salt. The first time I made it, I didn't have fennel and it was very good. After tasting the sauce, I decided to add 1 more tsp. each of basil and oregano, as we like these flavors a lot.

10-3-10 Second time I made this sauce I added 1/8 tsp. fennel and that changed a very good sauce into an EXCELLENT one...so much better than store-bought sauce or sauce served on deli pizzas. I always quadruple the recipe, and it makes 2 quarts - enough for the freezer!

Thanks for sharing an outstanding pizza sauce recipe. This is the BEST!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: This is a wonderful chicken recipe...I use chicken leg quarters (3 each) & there was enough sauce to cover it all.

name: carb free cloud bread
review: Awesome.  Guilt-free!  With PB an J, you don't notice it's not true bread.  Made this a dozen times already.  Thanks for posting.

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: These were lovely muffins.  So tender!  Made as directed but didn't have quite enough blueberries so I made a few of them with chopped up strawberries.  They were very good as well just not quite the flavour of the blueberry ones.  I also thought (after the fact) that I would have been fine with the one cup of blueberries that I did have.  They vanished within 36 hours and I'm embarrassed to say that there are only two of us in the house.

name: szechuan noodles with spicy beef sauce
review: Sure was good! I followed to the letter but found that this was a good place to decrease red meat. I split my meat in two thus using only a 1/4 lbs. and it was not missed in the least! Thanks for a great and easy recipe...this is a keeper.

name: garlic panko chicken strips
review: These are really good chicken strips.  They are very flavorful and so easy to fix.  Thanks for posting.

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: This is really good!  Makes a lot of sauce.  You can easily add something else (red peppers, broccoli, whatever) and not worry about it being too dry.  Thanks Stacky5.....

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: Whole family raved!  Definitely not quick, but extremely easy and delicious.  As I have posted before, I have one son who is very picky about Tex-Mex dishes.  He loves the flavors but detests the 'sameness' of so many of them.  He gave this one two thumbs up and asked to take the leftovers with him.  Huge compliment from a guy with a very discerning palate, Breezermom!!

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Awesome, Fabulous, delicious - perfect texture, mouth feel and flavor. Keeper recipe! TY Kittencal - post this one prominently on your new site!

name: the best ever waffles
review: I asked my husband to make this for my daughter and I because he is the waffle maker in our house. They were truely the best waffles I have ever had. He put the teaspoon of vanilla like everyone suggested. He said they are very time consuming but I said they are worth it. I suggested that we make a batch and freeze. Forget Eggos!!!! He said yes, but we would need to borrow another waffle maker to make it go by faster. I made my daughter one with syrup and another with light whip cream. She said she liked the whip cream better but she is 8. Light syrup was fine by me. Thanks for recipe!! Update: we added a banana to the batter. Very good!!!

name: spicy shrimp in coconut milk
review: Such an easy quick and delicious recipe,  a really special meal put together in half an hour, we loved this.   Served over steamed white rice,   made a fabulous dinner and I'm already looking forward to having it again :)   Thank you, MizzNezz,   super recipe!!!!

name: real southern cornbread
review: Wonderful! Loved this cornbread and will definitely make again. Cast iron skillet is a must, the outside edges get crisp and buttery while the inside is moist with a nice crumb. Not too sweet. Unfortunately, I did not read the directions so missed the step about mixing buttermilk and baking soda. Turned out well, but will definitely give that a try next time. Thanks for sharing the recipe! UPDATE: This time I mixed the buttermilk and baking soda. This cornbread is SO good! Thanks!

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: This was so easy and delicious! I will definitely be making this again... soon! Thanks!

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: We really enjoyed this tasty and hearty meal, breezermom. All the flavors and textures blended together so well...just perfect. Thank you for posting.

name: kittencal s technique for perfect easy peel hard boiled eggs
review: Perfect!!  I only had new eggs and those don't usually peel well....but these did!!  Thank you!!  This will be the only way I will boil them in the future!

name: meatball sub casserole
review: We really liked this casserole and like some of the other reviewers, I made a double batch of meatballs.

name: thai coconut rice
review: I made half a recipe for the 2 of us and served it with Recipe #480070.  A delicious combination.  I did not have crystallized ginger but did add in sliced almonds.  Will have to make this one again.

name: white fish in herbed butter
review: This was delicious!!!!  I cut the recipe in half and used tilapia and followed the rest of the instructions...One that is going into my Favorites of 2012 for ease and deliciousness!!  Thank you MizzNezz.  Made for the Cook-A-Thon for MizzNezz.

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: This was a great movie-night dinner! Quick to make, filling and tasty. I loved the cream cheese in the meat mixture, and DH loved that it had corn tortillas instead of the typical flour ones. Sorry, I didn't get a photo because DH wanted to eat this while it was still all hot and melty (and he wanted to start the movie, lol). Definitely a keeper for Tex-Mex nights, thanks for posting!

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Incredibly delish is right! Super simple and taaaaaaaasty! I added a little parsley to the mix and devoured.  Thanks for posting!

name: white fish in herbed butter
review: Surprised to see I've never reviewed this fantastic tasting recipe.  I've used it for both cod and tilapia with good results.  If I have lemon on hand, I also love to sautee some lemon slices to go with this.  This is a super good, quick and easy recipe.  Thanks, MizzNezz!

name: pork chops in onion sauce  schweinekotelett in zwiebelsosse
review: Turned out good.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: We are big garlic lovers in our house so, like I do with every recipe, I doubled the garlic.  Even with that change my family didn't find it had enough flavor.  They gave it three stars. They liked it better when we added additional garlic salt with parsley, fresh cracked pepper, and topped it off with additional fresh grated parm.   I served it with steamed broccoli.

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: These pancakes were easy to make and yummy, my lil's gobbled them up, thank you!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: Really good!!! And really not hard to make.

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: We used apples from our tree whatever they are - they look like a granny smith.!! I could have eaten this raw but it had to cook and go to the dessert table at a charity supper so I will have to make it again for our own meal.

name: saltine candy   toffee
review: Oh these are so good and so easy - what could be better than that.

name: spiced pumpkin waffles
review: It's now fall and had to celebrate with these waffles.  They were great just ate them with butter my kids liked them.  I froze the extras and thought they were better than the day of, thank you!

name: white fish in herbed butter
review: Very flavorful and easy to do.  I used whitefish fillets.  Will make again.

name: easiest beef enchiladas ever
review: Really good recipe!  I used a 10oz. can of enchilada sauce to pour over the top and for the beef filling I used some taco sauce I had on hand, probably about 1 cup.  I  wound up with 10 enchiladas and served them with sour cream.  Thanks for posting!

name: roasted tomato soup
review: I pumped this up per reviewer suggestions. I doubled the onion, added a hot pepper, a jalapeno and 1/2 a green pepper. YUM

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: This makes a nice refreshing and light meal. Easy to put together. I was able to easily substitute kidney beans for black and lemon juice for lime since that is what I had on hand. Fresh corn was great in this dish. Will definitely make this again. Thanks.

name: apple or pear cake
review: We had some pears that needed to be used up.  Our family friend has a pear tree and gave up a big bucket full.  I was looking for something to use some up with and chose your recipe.  It was so rich and delicious. The pears are perfect for this cake, and the sauce....omg, to die for.  Thank you for sharing with us.  I can't wait for next year for the abundance of pears again, we will be making this delicious cake again.

name: hamburger noodle bake
review: Easy and delicious, comfort food at its best.  I was generous with the onion, added some herbs,  used a small shell pasta to cup the delicious sauces, yum, one of those dishes where you can make a lot because the leftovers are even better!!  I added a small amount of zucchini cooked in spicy tomato sauce that I had in the fridge,  added a touch of pizzazz :)   Thank you, loved this!!!

name: grandma s soft sugar cookies
review: I used your recipe for the "crust" of our fruit pizza.  It was perfect.  I will use this from now on.  DD wants to make the cookies for her play cast party.  We loved the texture of this reicpe.  Thank you for sharing.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: The flavor is wonderful! I doubled the sauce and am glad I did. This would be great served over rice, I think. I used the oven method, but found that the pork chops were too dry after only about 35 minutes of cooking. I wish I would have checked them even earlier. This recipe is worth making again and experimenting on the timing. Thank you for posting. Made for Cookbook Tag game in the Cooking Tag Games forums.

name: best cream of broccoli soup
review: I found this to be a very comforting soup.  I made this for our dinner the other night and served it with paninis.  I pureed half the broccoli in this and left the other half whole.  I lovedthis.  Thank you for sharing this with us.

name: peanut butter cup cookies  tarts
review: Wow, what a fun cookie.  DS needed two dozen cookies to take to his football practice and I chose your recipe.  These didn't last long, they were the first cookie to be gone out of probably 20 different types.  I love how easy they are to make and they are too cute.  thank youf or sharing with us.

name: blue ridge mountains chocolate chip cookies
review: We made these for DD's sleep over and they were so good.  The almond extract in these takes them over the top.  I loved it and so did the girls.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: Delish! Omitted the butter and used two bacon slices per roll (more bacon!!). Thanks for sharing, Tish, this will get made again (and again)!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: I made this the other night and the whole family thoroughly enjoyed it. I didn't realize how much, until my DH told me last night that after I went to bed, he stayed up and ran off the recipe to hand out at work!! Thanks so much for sharing your wonderful, EASY recipe!

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: Worked VERY well.  Nice and crunchy.  I used a mandolin to slice - definately less than 1/16"...almost as thin as Lay's..  At 5 minutes they were too dark.  4 minutes still pretty dark.  Used waffle bottom silicone so no added oil at all!  I have to admit I was skeptical.  Love the crunch!

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: Delicious way to eat cauliflower! I didn't have to cook as long as recipe said...about 15 min. Will be making this again. Thanks!

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: Delicious and easy! My family really liked the coating.  Since we like our food sweet, I added an extra tablespoon of honey and I substituted graham cracker crumbs for the breadcrumbs.

name: croutons
review: These are perfect.  I made these using only the seasoned salt and veg. oil and they were great.  I will add some other spices next time, but you don't need too, they are great as is.  Thank youf or sharing this with us, what a $$$$ saver!  And a great way to use up leftover buns.

name: do at home onion rings
review:
Look no further, this batter is perfection! It's light, tender, tasty, crunchy and actually adheres to the onion!
I made one batch as written and one batch with Old Bay Seasoning. Both were excellent.
Made for MizzNezz-Cook-a-Thon. Stay strong GF.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: Yummm!  This was so good that I made it two days in a row!

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: I made this according to recipe and it was pretty good. The gravy is slightly sweet and tangy, probably the ketchup, but very tasty. I felt like the meat needed something, but I'm not quite sure what it is. Maybe some herbs? I'll probably experiment with this one because it's a keeper.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Of all the fancy pulled pork recipes, this has to be the easiest and tastiest.  I make it as directed but I use CattleBoys Barbecue sauce

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review:
Don't listen to the purists! This cooking method is no fail and really good! In my 40 years of cooking, I've had grills of all types and only one that cooked ribs to perfection. I'm tired of trying to do them "right" and am now doing them FANTASTIC!
I used my own rub and roasted foil wrapped, on a cookie sheet, for 2 hours.
I browned them on the grill for about 5 minutes per side, mopping with Teriyaki Baste and Glaze.
You'll never have tough ribs again if you follow this method...the experts aren't alway's right.

name: french toast sticks   oamc
review: I cut the recipe in half as I only had two eggs but followed the recipe as written. I did use Splenda instead of sugar though. I didn't even get to try this as my husband and son ate it as soon as it came out of the oven. They both said they liked them. I didn't cut mine like someone else suggested. I will have to make these again so I can try them.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review:
I did not refrigerate the chicken but followed the recipe as written, otherwise. I put the
chicken on a square of cheese cloth and tied the corners together and in the cp it went.
When the chicken was done, it was fall-off-the-bone tender, but I lifted it
out quite neatly and laid it on a sheet pan to remove the cheese cloth.
It was delicious and so was the broth.

name: big grandma s best peanut butter cookies
review: Perfect. Followed recipe as written, ended up with the best peanut butter cookies we've ever had. Thanks for sharing!

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: Wowza!!! This was crazy good! I admit, I made lots of adjustments, as I had lots of veggies that I wanted to use up,  but I imagine the recipe is great as written. I sauteed the chicken chunks in a little butter and oil, adding poultry seasoning and thyme, removed it from the pan and sauteed onions, celery, garlic, jalapeno, and cabbage until tender, then mixed it with the other ingredients, except, the pimento, as directed.  I refrigerated the mixture until ready to bake, It came out perfect. I can't wait to make this again on a cold snowy day. This is a keeper for sure. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: corned beef in beer  crock pot
review: Delicious.  We really liked this.  The potatoes and veggies were so full of flavor, and the meat, DS couldn't get enough.  I loved how easy this is to prepare.  I plan on using your recipe again, as we really like corned beef.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: This was AWESOME!  DH loved it so much he went back for thirds...  Thanks for making me look like a star in the kitchen!

name: kittencal s  brown sugar caramel sauce or ice cream topping
review: This was so good. I served it with apple crisp and it was perfect.

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: This was ok... Took almost 1.5 hours before it was no longer soup...  still had to add plenty of cheese to thicken it up... maybe my pan wasn't shallow enough??

name: easy garlic chicken
review: Great chicken!  A little sweet ut not overpowering.  I used thin-sliced b/s chicken breasts so decreased the cooking time a little.  Made for Cookbook Tag.

name: i lost my noodles  low carb south beach eggplant lasagna
review: I am not going to rate stars. I made this for four people. Two liked it. I did not think that it was all that for the amount of work. However, I am not on a limited diet. I, merely, wanted to make something that was good but was healthier.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Delish! I used leftover chicken and light cheese and light sour cream. I also used whole wheat tortillas -- delish and easy to make these lighter changes. Thanks for sharing!

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: I didn't make the final topping, just the pie and the crumb topping - still, insanely good! A wonderful apple pie even when you take the caramel part out of the equation, but rest assured, I will try the full version too!

name: denny s style french toast
review: Not quite Denny's but decent.

name: unbelievably easy potato soup
review: Surprisingly good to be so simple!  I added some leftover ham I had in the freezer and a couple of carrots, and I used fat-free half and half.  I wish I had gone with the lesser amount of half and half, but it was still delicious.  It really hit the spot on a cool fall night.  Thanks for posting; this one is a keeper!

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: POTSCRUBBER... This is unbelievably Delicious!  Yes, pure comfort food.  So nice to make a meal where everyone wants not just 2nds but 3rds!!!  The empty casserole dish bought JOY to my heart.  I only made few changes--added 1/2 c. sour cream, no pimentos or red peppers, subbed monterey jack cheese for cheddar and used onion powder ( for my picky eaters).  I used the Grands flaky biscuits and the eight in there were perfect for my 11x7 dish.  Thank you, this is going in the keeper folder for sure!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: Fantastic soup!  Don't know if it tastes like Panera, but it is delicious nonetheless.  Even the toddler ate his vegetables! : )  I didn't have half and half, but used one cup evaporated milk and one cup skim milk.  I really enjoyed this recipe and it reheated pretty well also.  Will make again; might be my go-to broccoli cheese soup.  I like to add a little cooked rice in my soup also.

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review: Pretty tasty! I was wanting something different for dinner and saw some cube steaks at the store, so came back and found this recipe.  Had never made cube steaks before, but they turned out so tender and the gravy was delicious!  I added some cut up onion and cooked for 2 hours on high, then down to low for another 2.  Perfect served with mashed potatoes for the extra gravy.  Mushrooms would make a great addition (but unfortunately, DH doesn't like them).  Edited 10/12: Have made this multiple times and is always delicious!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: Ever so easy! The recipe didn't make quite enough for a deep pie dish though so the crust was very thin. Will try 1.5 x recipe the next time for the deep dish! Thank you for sharing!

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Omg..i will add this to the family recipe box top be passed on. I used baby spinach instead beause its what i had. Delicious.

name: thick and creamy new england clam chowder
review: Best clam chowder ever, this is a wonderfup recipe!

name: spiced pumpkin waffles
review: These waffles rock! used buttermilk (low on regular) so had to add a bit more.  Crispy on the outside & full of flavor that is complemented with maple syrup, sausages, bacon & sweet butter.  TY for a keeper recipe!

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review: This was delicious!! I baked it in the oven at 350 for 2 hours and it was just perfect.  Will make often.  Thanks for the wonderful recipe!!

name: white chili   football soup
review:
10/7/12 update: I have been working on this and now make a few changes; I do not add the oregano because it seems to just float to the top and looks unappelaing. I take about 3/4 cup of the chicken broth and dissolve about 2 tablespoons of cornstarch to make this more like chili. After these changes this is now one of our favorite meals.

Great soup - DD thought it was a little too spicy and said to reduce the green chilis to one can but I thought it was great. I did add about one extra cup of cheese. I thought this would be thicker than it was but that's okay - it is delicious!

name: crabs   garlic butter baked crab legs
review:
I will never steam crab legs again! What a great easy and so not as messy recipe..
the sauce was great for dipping legs into after cooking!

name: bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers
review: my son james loves these  he cooks them on the grill

name: delicious homemade egg noodles
review: My recipe is similar, but I wanted to try yours because of the egg yolks instead of all whole eggs.  My family was nervous, but in the end they couldn't tell the difference.  I even made it all by hand, per instructions, instead of using the mixer.  :)  Thanks for sharing your recipe, kindcook.  I'll be using it again!  I used the basic method for my Recipe #280784 (Mom's Easy Chicken & Homemade Noodles) and used your noodles and Recipe #55282 (Crock Pot Chicken or Turkey Stock by Pets'R'Us).  Probably the best comfort food ever!  :)

name: easy garlic rice
review: This was a nice and flavourful rice. Slightly heavy and salty, so for future times, i'll hold back a bit on the broth and poss. thyme? Thanks for sharing, it went well with the rest of the meal!

name: brady bunch pork chops
review: No wonder you have all these reviews.  This has to be the best pork chops I've ever made.  I followed the recipe, marinading over night.  The flavors in this are right on, with a perfect blend of spices and the chops came out so moist - not dry at all.  Not all that healthy with the fat content - but hey, an occassional splurge is nice.  I used the 1/2 inch boneless chops and couldn't have been any happier with the results.  A true 5 star recipe.

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: This was a great recipe, I didn't add stars because I made some adjustments due to time restraints and ingredients.  I used vegetable broth, home made cream soup, sauteed the onions and celery also baked at 400 for 30 mins.  I really liked the mayo in this, it gave it some tang.  Thank you for this recipe, it was easy.

name: pan release  professional pan coating  better than pam spray
review: This stuff is AMAZING!  I have been baking in all my "less than favorite" pans just to find one that it didn't work in and guess what....it had worked in ALL of them!  Even the Nordicware fancy bundt pans..yep the cakes just slide right out!  Love it!  Thanks Kittencal!  I love love love this stuff!  Sometimes I make it with butter flavored Crisco and I love it that way too!  UPDATE: This is so perfect in my Pampered Chef Stoneware!  I always had a problem with the bundt pan...well cuz frankly I am too impatient and turned the pan over too quickly...not a problem now..the cake just falls right out!  I LOVE this stuff!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: I have made this several times and it always turns out great!  Thanks for a great "no fail" recipe!

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: Delicious stack ups!!!  I made this as written although scaled back to serve one for my lunch the other day.  I get ground beef on sale and then take 2 lbs  home and cook it with a large diced onion, then I make several smaller freezer bags full of the mixture to use later in recipes such as this recipe.  The only change I made was to use dark red kidney beans in place of the black as I had some that were leftover and frozen from a previous Taco Salad.  This is pure Tex/Mex heaven on a plate!!!  It is very filling, next time I might just use two tortillas!!  Thanks for sharing the recipe.  Made for Holiday Tag Game.

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: These muffins were delicious.  I one and a halved the recipe and got 24 muffins.  Although I one and a halved most of the ingredients, I did not add extra sugar or topping.  I also used whole wheat flour and 2/3 c applesauce and only 1/3 c oil.  They were moist and delicious and I will definitely make again.

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: Breezer, thank you for sharing a wonderful recipe!  My kind of food. Loved the seasonings. Easy to put together. Attractive too.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: All 3 of my kids loved this meal.  I added peas for a vegetable and used onion instead of shallots.

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: Seriously yummy dressing!

name: interesting crock pot chicken
review: This is reallly good!  I made this and it is so comforting.  The chicken was so tender and the mixture of ingredients was divine.  I served this on white rice and we loved it.  Thank you for sharing this with us.  delicious.

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: These ARE the best! I made these exactly as written. I was skeptical of the dough (it was very wet) and skeptical that they would slump down into cookie shapes, but sure enough they did! Will definitely make these again. Thanks!

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: We really enjoyed this recipe!  As some of the reviewers suggested, I laid the chicken atop half of a sliced red onion and three large crushed cloves of garlic.  Also used skinless, boneless thighs (the husband is weird about both skin and bones).  Cooked for about an hour at 350 (our oven is a bit unreliable).  Served with a green salad and baked then mashed winter squash, this was a lovely dinner for a chilly fall evening.  Thanks for posting!

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: What can I say that hasn't already been said.  To sum it up - absolutely delish!  Had these tonight for dinner and they really hit the spot.  Going into my Best of 2012 cookbook as this recipe will be used often.  Such a great idea and these stack-ups have everything I love in Tex-Mex cooking.  Made for Everyday is a Holiday, October, 2012.

name: quick and easy pizza dough
review: Really easy, great result. thanks!

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: So good!!  Moist, flavourful & delicious!  I grated the apple as suggested by another reviewer & liked the results.

name: strawberry shortcake a la treebeard s
review: This was excellent!  The only change I made was in using peaches instead of strawberries.  The shortcakes came out sort of large so next time (and there definately will be a next time) I'll make them a little smaller so there will be more!  Everyone loved the whipped cream too!  Thank you for posting this recipe!

name: crock pot stifado
review: Delicious! This was a nice change of pace from our usual stew. I used a can of diced tomatoes in place of tomato sauce. I prepped everything the night before, put it in the crockpot in the early am, went out and played all day and came home to a delicious meal. I served the stew over mashed potatoes. Thanks for posting.

name: beef barley soup
review: Nice easy tasty soup

name: easy peezy pizza dough  bread machine pizza dough
review: This dough rose beautifully and looked great in the pan but after the pizza was cooked, the crust was very thick. As for flavour, it tasted much like the one I usually use, just average.

name: shirley s perfect rare roast beef
review: Perfect!

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: The flavor was good, but the apples turned to mush, almost like applesauce.  Could have been my apples?  I used Granny Smith.

name: impossible peanut butter cookies
review: These are super easy to make, but as some others mentioned, very sweet!  I doubled the recipe and used 3/4 brown sugar and 1/4 white.  I used a 1 tbsp scoop to make the cookes then flattened with a fork and sprinkled just a pinch of sugar on each.  I think next time, I'll use much less sugar and a pinch of salt.  I made these for DH, and he hasn't tried them yet, but I'll bet he loves them!  Thank you!

name: hard boiled eggs
review: The yolks turned out perfect, but peeling these eggs didn't work too well.  Too much of the whites came off.

name: taco bell quesadillas
review: These were quite good for us. We found them a bit sweet in the end, tho'. Thanks for sharing!

name: kale chips
review: I've been making kale chips for years, but never used vinegar on them.  Great addition, thanks!

name: big thicket chicken and dumplings
review: This makes a lot of dumplings.  I only cooked half because I was afraid I wouldn't have enough broth once I added my chicken back in.  I probably could have made more than I did.  This recipe was good and could probably serve more than it states, but that's ok, it just means more leftovers for us.  A great rainy day meal.

name: good eats roast turkey
review: This turkey was awesome! Used chicken broth instead and used 1 1/2 tbsp candie ginger by mistake. Made incredible soup afterwards!

name: pumpkin gooey butter cake   paula deen
review: I hesitated to even rate this, because I really don't like giving negative feedback.  But As I don't know Paula Deen personally, and care not if I offend her, I have to say...ugh.  Instant Type II diabetes on a plate,  The only reason I gave it any stars at all is that I served it to a group of ladies (bridge club) who DID love it---but, frankly, these darlin' gals would eat sugar right out of the sack, so...hmmm.  This is the last time I ever make a recipe with "Gooey" in the title. (Actually, this may have been the FIRST time I ever did!)

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: Simply delicious!!  I used a mix of yellow and green squash and added a couple teaspoons minced garlic.  I couldn't believe how fast and easy this is.  It's not much more effort than opening a can of veggies, it just takes more time.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: Excellent!!  Made as directed.  I added a cup of rice the last 1/2 an hour of cooking as another reviewer suggested.  DH couldn't get enough, lovely blend with the broth, mushrooms and rice.  The one thing I will do differently next time is to remove some of the oil that accumulates from the chicken before I add the rice.  It will definitely be in my rotation, thanks for posting!

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: This soup was the answer to a cold Fall day and is TDF.  I baked the potatoes and then peeled and cubed them.  I blended the cream cheese with some of the broth and added some fresh rosemary.  I followed the recipe as stated and topped it with some shredded cheddar cheese and copped bacon.  I will use this a base for other dishes like clam chowder or ham chowder and add shredded carrots and leeks.

name: magnolia bakery s vanilla birthday cake and frosting
review: Delicious!  The best white/vanilla cake recipe I've ever made.  I used this recipe to make Recipe #126930 and they were a huge hit at my 4th of July party.  The flavor was outstanding and this will be my go-to recipe from now on.  Thank you Marie for posting!

name: redneck casserole
review: Here is deal, I was skeptical and thought my husband looked interested turned out I liked it and he was like OK I will eat this because you made it.  Sort of funny, I probably would not make it again because of that reason.  He said if you made hot dogs, baked beans and tater tots on the side I would love it.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review:
Absolutely wonderful combination of flavors! I did alter recipe somewhat - omitted green peppers (they don't like our tummies)and cut back on the cheese (used all I had in fridge). My potatoes created enough water I didn't need to add any but this was just wonderful. I served with steamed carrots, corn bread and blackberry cobbler for dessert. Thanks for posting - we'll be making this again and again!!

1/5/08 I have made this several times since my original edit. This last time I did make with the green peppers - they add incredible flavor (even if we do suffer a little after)! I added 1 cup pale wheat beer and OMG! This has quickly become an often requested supper dish that I am more than glad to make upon request. Thank you again for an awesome recipe!!

1/17/2012 - Made this again for MizzNess Cook Bake-a-thon. This is now a standard in our house and DH almost has recipe memorized. love, Love, LOVE this awesome recipe!

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: Perfect didn't make the icing since I made it into an ice cream cake and put a chocolate sauce between and topped with whip cream. For a birthday! Made 2 days ahead based on comments and reduced the salt. Thanks can't wait to make again!

name: interesting crock pot chicken
review: So surprised. After the great 5 star reviews I thought this was going to be a hands down winner. This was ok.  Everyone ate it but no one wanted seconds. I had issues some of the other posters have noted. The "sauce" was runny like soup and not creamy. Next time I would have to omit some liquid. The cream cheese didn't dissolve in the last hour properly. I think I will warm it with the soups then add it in if I made it again. Not as easy as this states but would be creamier. The color was plain and the flavor was a tad bland. I would need to find a seasoning mix of herbs to jazz it up. The plus of the recipe was the chicken was falling apart and not dried out. It was easy and fast. Definitely add more mushrooms. This was made as written. We served it atop a choice of egg noodles or rice. Thanks for posting. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: quick yellow cake
review: A wonderful light cake that was easy to make!  I made this for my own birthday cake and was thrilled!  I used 2-9" round cake pans and baked for 24 minutes.  Next time I will use the 8".  There is nothing else to add that hasn't already been said, but THANKS for posting a wonderful "scratch" cake recipe!  Made this again using some tips recently shared by another member and again had stellar results.  Made for MizzNezz Cook Bake-a-thon!

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: This was excellent. I used bell pepper instead of celery because that's what I had on hand, and I made it from memory and forgot the worcestershire sauce. I also added some cracked black pepper. Made delicious sandwiches on toasted white bread.  Will be making again!

name: panda express orange chicken
review:
First I need to say that I agree that this recipe is written in a more complicated way than required. After reading the reviews I made some adjustments to the method as well as ingredients. I have never had the Panda Express version so wasn't likely to be disappointed. :)
First I made the sauce in a small saucepan, choosing to saute the ginger and garlic at that point rather than adding it to the wok prior to cooking the chicken. I included the cornstarch so it was ready to go. I tripled the sauce and was glad I did.
Along with some other reviewers I dipped the chicken in the egg mixture and then dredged it with flour before frying it in a wok with the chili peppers and green onions etc. This streamlined the process as I was not required to set aside the chicken other than to wipe out the pan. Tossed in the sauce and 5 minutes later we were eating. This is definitely a Five Star tasting recipe but in fairness I can only give it four for all the adjustments I thought necessary. Thanks for posting this yummy chicken dish. We will be enjoying it for many years to come.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: I'm knee deep in the midst of making these meatballs of yours along with your ground beef sauce.  Dinner is hours away and my husband and I can't keep our hands off either of these recipes!  I consider myself a very experienced cook and have been making my own homemade meatballs and "gravy" passed down from my husband's Italian family.  These 2 recipes BLOW THEM AWAY!!  I baked the meatballs and plan to freeze them in ziploc's to drop in to quick meals for my toddlers.  I used extra meat in these meatballs, added crushed red peppers, garli garni seasoning and lots more garlic. I also chose to bake these rather than drop in the sauce since I was saving 1/2 of them for future meals.   The recipe is sheer perfection!!  Thank you so much!  I'll now be looking at all your other recipes for more wonderful treats.

name: light and fluffy pumpkin pancakes
review: My family really enjoyed the pancakes. I even read the recipe wrong and added three times the amount of butter that they recipe called for and it worked out just fine. Thanks for sharing.

name: chicken stroganoff   crock pot
review: Mmmmmm....so good.  I have a confession to make though.  I forgot to get these started in the crockpot, so I made this on the stovetop.  Didn't hurt the recipe at all, it was still very flavorful and delicious.  We served ontop of buttered and parsley noodles with some corn.  We really loved this.  Thank you for sharing this with us.  I will make this alot, using both the crockpot and the stovetop.

name: pumpkin cake bars with cream cheese frosting
review: Delicious!!!!!  I would definitely call this a cake, not a bar, but who cares when it tastes so darn good!  Made this for my sister's birthday and everyone fought over who was going to get the last 6 pieces to take home!  Will make again for sure!

name: lentil soup for people who thought they hated lentils    meat op
review: Excellent soup and so flexible.  Thanks!

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: Love the roasted cauliflower but my garlic was burnt.  Will leave the skin on and cook them that way.

name: hot german potato salad
review: This is worthy of a bazillion stars! This was, by far,  the easiest hot German Potato salad I have ever made. I halved the recipe, cut large cubes of potatoes and cooked. It took about 10 minutes for the potatoes, in the mean time, I fried up the bacon. Once the bacon was nearly done, I added diced onion and fried until near caramelized. The only change to the recipe, I grabbed the apple cider vinegar by mistake. Threw it all together and we are in hog heaven. I served with BBQ brisket sandwiches. Lali, I cannot thank you enough for sharing you gramma's recipe. You're a peach!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: This was delicious!  I had to do some modifications based on what I had on hand.  I added roasted red bell peppers chopped up to the cooked chicken mix.
