review: Everyone liked the cupcakes I made with your recipe.  The only change I made was to use butter in place of the shortening.  I got 21 cupcakes, though I think I could have made it into 22 easily.  I baked then for 20 minutes, but they were slightly dry so I could have called them done at 18-19 minutes.  When I first took them out of the oven they smelled extremely eggy, but the smell faded away and they weren't eggy tasting at all.  I did notice on the two cups cakes I overfilled, that once I took them out of the oven they fell a bit, so I wouldn't recommend this recipe to someone looking for a high crest.  I loved that it was so easy to make with ingredients I always have on hand.  And all made in one bowl!  Can't beat that!!  Thanks. :)

name: big thicket chicken and dumplings
review:
This was excellent! I had never made rolled dumplings before and the dough was wonderful to work with. I added a little milk at the end as we prefer a creamy sauce with our chicken & dumplings but otherwise, I made as directed. Thanks for a great recipe that I will make again!
12.13.12 Updated - Made this many, many times now. It's still a great recipe. This last time I used split chicken breasts that I roasted in the oven. Roasted at 400? for 30 minutes to crisp up the skin then put into the pot of water with the pan dripping. I must say, it really made for a richer, deeper chicken flavor. Did everything as written and the family just ate and moaned (with delight). Thanks again for a wonderful recipe that I make quite often!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: This works perfectly for us every time. Test it with a thermometer and it's done. Have used pre-seasoned as well as seasoned on my own. They all turn out great. Thank you!

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: Down home cooking!  Reminded me of my grandmother.  We all enjoyed this very much.  Thanks for sharing!

name: delicious homemade egg noodles
review: Very good!  I also used my KitchenAid, super, super easy!  This will be my go to recipe for egg noodles.  Thanks for sharing.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: Excellent brownies! I've been making these since 2009, but I didn't realize that I hadn't reviewed them.  This is one of my go-to recipes!  I use coconut oil/butter mix instead of shortening to make it healthier, too.

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: This is the first time I made ribs in the Crock Pot - I did not know what to expect and was a little apprehensive - no need to be! I modified the recipe slightly by adding paprika to the flour and used soy sauce instead of Worcestershire sauce but followed the rest of the recipe. I only had 1 1/2 pound of ribs so it cooked faster and was done in 6 hours, even on low. The ribs where sooo delicious, so moist, the meat fell off the bones and the sauce was fabulous! I served it over yellow rice, it was a totally wonderful meal! I emailed the recipe and picture to a friend in Austria who just got her first "Crocky", as she calls it, she can't wait to make it! Thanks for posting, MizzNezz!

name: the best sweet and sour sauce
review: This was easy and excellent! Won't change a thing next time!

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Awesome!  Thanks for the great recipe!  I was able to make two thin crust pizzas with this recipe.  I baked one for 5 minutes before topping, and the other I topped and popped in.  The pre-baked one turned out more the way I like it, but different strokes for different folks ;)

name: healthy no bake cookies
review: These are very good.  I'm one of those people who likes a little something sweet after a meal and these healthy, flavorful little gems are perfect.  The whole family likes them, though some aren't huge fans of the texture.  Thanks for posting.  I plan on making these regularly.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: I used the frosting portion of this recipe for icing my Christmas sugar cookie cut-outs yesterday.  I was searching for a frosting that hardens and allows for easier, neater cookie storage.  Only after making many modifications, the frosting turned out.  Like other reviewers, I felt the instructions for the frosting were unclear in terms of the amount of milk.  Far more than 1 tbs. is needed to achieve the right consistency, so I would suggest indicating the exact amount (or an amount closer than just 1 tbs.) would be much more helpful.  Plus once I finally reached the right consistency, I realized the flavor was lacking.  I ended up whipping 2 tbs. butter, 1/2 tsp. lemon extract and 1/2 tsp. salt into the mixture for more flavor and less tacky texture.  The frosted cookies did harden, as the recipe title promises.  The trick must be the addition of corn syrup.  Next time, I think I'll just add corn syrup to my standard butter-based frosting recipe.  Thanks for sharing your recipe!  Although it didn't completely work out for me, I did learn a new trick in the process, so thank you for that!

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: Adding my voice to the masses here to say how much we LOVE these little squares!  Thanks so much for posting.  I'll be making them often.

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: Loved this!  I've been trying to go primarily vegetarian and so I especially love this because it works as an entree for me and a side dish (with salsa chicken or something similar) for my family.  Then the leftovers make for a tasty lunch the next day.  We all really enjoy this one. Thanks for posting!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Delicious! Lots of flavor, and easy to pull together. I used half the amount of sesame oil called for and used skinless thigh, just to cut back on fat. We're looking forward to the leftovers. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: easy cole slaw
review: This will be my go-to recipe for cole slaw from now on! I used low fat mayonaise, Splenda , 1% milk, rice wine vinegar and added about 1/4 to 1/2 cup finely minced yellow onion. Absolutely delicious!! Even my hubby commented on how good it was! Thanks for posting this- it's a keeper!

name: roasted tomato soup
review: Wow! This soup is amazing. It was so easy to make and the taste and texture is perfect. It tastes like there is cream in it but is much healthier without. I didn't have any garlic or fresh herbs so just sprinked some dry spices on the tomatoes and onion before roasting. I will make often!

name: puppy chow or monkey munch
review: I gave this recipe 5 stars! OMG! These taste just like the store brand Chex Mix Muddy Buddy's! Just delicious! My family loved these! I made these for guys I take care of as a special treat! I'm hoping they enjoy them! Thanks for posting! Christine

name: buttery yeast rolls
review: Delicious rolls. Mine took about 2 hours to rise. Very easy to make in the bread machine. I baked half the dough the first night, and kept rest in fridge to bake off another night. Mine took about 25 minutes to bake.

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: First time I made this I didn't quite care for it, but my mom made this again and it was like eating chicken cheesecake and soo yummy!  I would definitely add veggies or extra chicken to give it more substance in the future, though.

name: harvest pumpkin apple bread
review: This bread is awesome, and what is even better is that you get 2 full loaves!  It is moist and flavorful.  I reduced the sugar to 2 cups and added an extra apple for a total of 2 chopped apples.  I topped mine with a simple glaze.  This would make wonderful gifts for the Christmas and Thanksgiving season.  The glaze I made was 1 c powdered sugar, 3 tbsp whipping cream, and 1/2 tsp vanilla.  The I put it in a ziplock bag with the corner trimmed and piped it on.  This was delicious and I will be making again.

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: I got 19 regular sized muffins (and baked them for 12 minutes). But this is very good.

name: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
review: The perfect recipe. Thanks!

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: This was awesome! I used skinless boneless chicken thighs instead of breasts. I omitted the cilantro and raisins, and I just used a pinch of cayenne to keep the heat down. I also stirred the yogurt into the curry when it was done. And as others suggested, doubling the curry powder did make it great.

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: These are so easy to work with. A keeper!

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: This was a great marinara to make. I found the heat a bit much, so I'll cut down next time. Also would maybe thin it out a wee bit more. But it was yummy and I wanted it on spaghetti right away, but was using it on the four cheese spinach manicotti recipe. I actually didn't love it on the manicotti, think I would have preferred it just on pasta, nice and fresh! But will definitely make again. Used white wine, which was nice. Thank you!!

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: This was definitely great! The spinach filling was sooo good! All I could find was oven- ready canelloni shells. So, they were good b/c they were firm to fill, but their texture wasn't good. I will hunt out manicotti next time. I really liked this, but I didn't love it. Used the marinara recipe too. Thanks for sharing yet another great recipe!

name: szechuan noodles with spicy beef sauce
review: Made a good, quick dinner. Served with edamame. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: hamburger noodle bake
review: Made for Zaar Cookbook tag game...this was an easy and tasty dinner.  I did cut the recipe in half and added more garlic, chopped onions and mushrooms.  I also combined all the ingredients and put in a dish to bake.  The grandkids gobbled this down with no complaints.  Thank you for posting.

name: fresh strawberry cake
review: Very good. We'll be making this again.

name: best banana bread
review: I had 2 very large bananas and needed to make something. This was an easy recipe and I just added about 1/3 cup of nuts and 1/4 cup of chocolate chips. This was wonderful and made the house smell delicious. Thank you this will be the go to recipe for sure.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: Oh what a delicious recipe.  I wanted something easy to make and use up some frozen cooked turkey and we chose your recipe.  I made exactly as written and we loved it.  My kids wouldn't want the added veggies into it so I served some on the side (they don't like alot mixed together).  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: peppermint candy cane bark
review: 5 stars for ease, 4 stars for taste.  Such a simple treat to make.  Perfect way to use up the extra candy canes and make a tasty addition to the Christmas goodies we give to friends.  Merry Christmas!

name: sugar cookie icing
review: Used this on recipe#11345 in my Holiday cookie tray and it was easy and so yummy.  I didn't have any food coloring (couldn't find it in all of Trinidad) so just left it white and sprinkled with pearl sugar - it's lovely and not to sweet.

name: grandma s soft sugar cookies
review: Just finished baking this for my Holiday tray and frosted with recipe#64015 and they turned out great.  Wish I'd had some colorful food dye or at least sprinkles but had to stick with white.  But they are soft, and taste great without being too sweet.  Everyone loves them.

name: big grandma s best peanut butter cookies
review: Really delicious cookies! I'm gonna try them again with chunky peanut butter as they weren't quite peanuty enough for me/as much as some others. I used an egg sub to keep mine vegan and they went off without a hitch. Probably the prettiest PB cookies I've ever seen   easiest dough to work with!

name: pork chops in onion sauce  schweinekotelett in zwiebelsosse
review: Very good, easy to do.  I served with scalloped potatoes.  Nice meal.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: You can't get much easier than this! I had all the ingredients at home and threw everything together in a few minutes. We had a yummy bbq aroma all day and the end result was so tasty. This is a keeper for a quick dinner that will please. Thank you!

name: microwave chocolate mug brownie
review: This was really easy and tasty quick treat!  I liked it a bit better than the cake in a mug recipes. Thanks for posting!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Simple, quick, and oh so good.

name: mexican stuffed shells  oamc
review: These were interesting - didn't have a strong Mexican taste to me but it was a nice variation on the traditional Italian style shells. We made ours vegan by crumbling up some Gimme Lean fake Sausage in place of the ground beef and using a soy cheese medley.

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: A tempting delicious likeness of the wonderful biscuits that are served at my favorite eating establishment.  Enjoyed these with MizzNezz's recipe#20755.  Thanks for sharing Heather'sKitchen

name: roast turkey
review: I've only roasted a turkey a handful of times, and have never done anything other than pull the turkey from the packing and stick it in a plastic turkey bag. This time I I wanted to have it well seasoned and know I picked the right recipe. I still used the turkey bag, so I followed the instructions other than putting the chicken broth in the bottom and doing the last few steps. The turkey came out juicy and tasty, and I got quite a few compliments at dinner. The only reason that I'm giving it 4 stars instead of 5 is that I found the butter/seasoning mixture really hard to spread over the turkey. It ended up in clumps that didn't melt during cooking because there was way too much seasonings for the amount of butter. I also wasn't sure if I was supposed to put the full amount in the butter plus sprinkle them over the top, which is what I did even though I thought it might be too much. Based on the results, next time I think I'll just add the onion and garlic to the butter and then sprinkle the rest on top. I think the butter will melt better that way and I won't end up with almost black clumps that ended up not soaking into the bird. I also didn't have tarragon but I didn't miss it at all with all of the other seasonings packing a punch!

name: white pizza or pizza blanca
review: I made two of these pizzas for my christmas party last night. I sauteed baby bella sliced mushrooms and bacon pieces with the onions and garlic. I also added some fresh spinach leaves on the top before adding the cheeses. I debated adding some alfredo sauce but am glad I didn't as it wasn't needed. I also used pre-baked thin pizza crust and made them several hours before the party. It turned out very flavorful and they were gone quickly. I am going to make again for christmas eve. Thanks for posting!

name: super peanut butter filled brownies
review: Wow, what a rich decadent dessert.  I printed this recipe out a long time ago and just now got around to making it.  What a mistake.  This was fantastic.  My family devoured these, although one piece was enough per sitting.  Rich rich rich.  Thank you for sharing with us, they are delicious brownies.

name: really really good candied sweet potatoes
review: Turned out great with halved sugar and syrup, just a personal preference for us. Yum.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: This recipe is AMAZING!  I came home from Christmas shopping and the house smelled so good and when it came time to eat everyone had seconds including my 6 y.o. DS and my 2 y.o. DS who are very picky.  There was plenty of gravy to mix in potatoes and carrots before serving.  Will definitely make this again!

name: sticky pork chops
review: Delicious and tender chops! This was a quick recipe, yielding lots of flavor. I added some fresh grated ginger, other than that followed the recipe down the line. Thanks for posting.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: A great sugar cookie recipe.  The icing really makes this cookie.

name: crock pot chicken taco meat
review: This is awesome! I found it cooked much faster than the suggested time in low, but maybe my crock pot runs warm. So simple and easy. It's worth it to use high quality taco seasoning. I use a blend I bought from an upscale spice store here in Chicago. Make your own if you have to - with such few ingredients you will absolutely taste the difference in the spice mix.

name: broiled tilapia with thai coconut  curry sauce
review: This was delicous.  I made exactly as written and my family loved it.  I'm always on the lookout for more fish recipes that my family agrees with and your makes the cut.  DS loved it and almost went for seconds but was too full....lol.  Thank you so much for this delicious recipe.  We loved it.

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: This Christmas is the first time in about 20 years that my branch of the family was called upon to make and bring the turkey to the big meal at my inlaws' house (my mother in law or sister in law usually do the meats and I do the bread/sides, etc.)  My adult daughter had brined and set up the turkey in a roasting pan so all I had to do was stick it in the oven after she left for work.  While it was roasting I made yeast rolls, stuffing and side dishes, and was REALLY getting nervous about having to make gravy to feed all these people.  Naturally, I turned to Recipezaar and was so relieved to find a No-Fail Turkey Gravy recipe from a chef whose recipes I have used many times before!  I skimmed the fat from the pan drippings and added enough canned chicken broth to make the 4 cups.  Followed the directions and it turned out PERFECT.  My only comment would be that on an electric cooktop like mine I had to up the heat a little bit to get it to thicken, but once it did, I tasted it and it was delicious (no "raw flour" taste at all). Transferred to a small crock pot to keep warm until it can be transported to the inlaws' house in a  couple of hours.  I am sure it will be a hit!  THANK you for saving me again with a terrific recipe!  ~ Zew

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: This was delicious.  I used 1/2 cup butter for about 3/4 of a large loaf of Italian bread.  My butter melted too much, so I mixed in the parmesan and sprinkled mozzarella on top.  Baked for about 8 minutes at 450, then turned on the broiler to brown the top a little bit more.  Served with stuffed shells.  My son said "You did a good job with the garlic bread!"  High praise from an 11 year old.  Thanks for sharing.

name: overnight french toast casserole
review: Love this recipe!  I assembled it last night and cooked it this morning for a Christmas Eve brunch.  Everyone raved about it and ate it up!! Some used syrup and some ate it without syrup.  Everyone loved it!  Thanks for posting this keeper recipe!!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: This chicken turned out very juicy and tender.  The sauce got a little dark, but didn't taste burnt; however made a horrific mess on my pan.  Next time I will wrap it in foil...Made for I Recommend Holiday Tag.

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: I wouldn't say that these were crispy but we liked them. We dipped them in hot sauce once they reached the table.  Next time I would reduce the butter and I would drain the fat part way through the cook time, then I think they would be crispier. Thanks Marie.

name: awesome baked ham
review: Easy & delicious. Everyone was gushing about this ham.  My friends & family want to have ham more often.  Thank you

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: Great soup. I did not add the cornstarch, since I liked the thickness, but otherwise made as directed. Thanks for the super healthy and tasty keeper.

name: easy baked potato wedges
review: I made these today for Christmas to go with some ham sandwiches and it was a nice side dish.  I did end up putting them back in the oven at 425 for about 30 minutes to get them more crispy.  I would suggest cutting them pretty small if you want them crunchy on the outside.  I think Cajun spice would work well on these too!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: Laurie, you have restored my confidence in making pie crusts! For whatever reason, the darn things scare the flour out of me, but this was so easy it's impossible to mess up. I made the crust for a Dutch Apple Pie and it was perfect. Thank you!

name: sticken chicken
review: This was good! I did a short cut for time, 40 mins at 350. found it a bit sweet, but just put a bit of soy sauce on my rice, and all was good. I think had it been cooked properly, we may have had more of a crisper outside. Ours wasn`t underdone, but it was kinda soft through. Anyway, thanks fro sharing!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Yep! It's the best lasagna ever! I think we have a new tradition for Christmas dinner. I assembled it yesterday. I used 1lb. of ground turkey and 1lb. of spicy pork sausage, cottage cheese and added a little more seasoning to that mixture, crushed tomatoes instead of whole. I only had one can of tomato paste, and used no boil noodles. I added about a up and a half of water to the sauce as per the directions on noodle package . I like sauce on the top, so I just saved some to use on top. I baked it covered for 1/2 hour and uncovered for 15 mins. It came out PERFECT! Thanks for sharing this fantastic recipe.

name: awesome baked ham
review: This ham was ok.  I followed the recipe to a T and the ham turned out way to sweet.  I will not be using this recipe again.

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: I decided to make this for our Christmas Day dinner and the family loved it.  I did use canned green beans but the fresh tomatoes, garlic, basil and butter and yes - sugar?!?!  made for a delightful fresh bright flavor.  It was perfect side dish to all the heavy dishes that normally accompany the ham.  I can't wait to try this again with fresh green beans!  Thanks for a wonderful, quick dish we'll be making often!

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: this was a nice change of pace for a vegetarian. we used red lentils, my favorite, and served it with marinara sauce on top. I did find the loaf a bit soggy - perhaps i needed to cook it more? I think this would also be great as a veggie burger.

name: legal seafood style baked scallops
review: I halved this recipe....big mistake!  These were devoured!  Will be added to our Christmas Eve Seafood Fest from now on.  I did sub milk   lemon joice in place of the buttermilk.  Seemed to work fine.  Next time I think I will reduce butter/crumb mixture.  While delicous as written and prepared, shaving off a few calories would be better for my thighs.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: This was awesome. Everyone loved it.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: It was okay but lacked flavor. I think I would put much less broth and much more milk in it. It just wasn't that creamy flavor I was looking for.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Excellent basic pot pie!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: This soup was very good!  Thanks for posting!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Made this as posted last evening for my DH and I - what a wonderful flavor and oh so simple to prepare - I did marinate the chicken for about two hours based on other reviewers and will do so when I prepare this again, soon :)  I think this would also be very tasty on pork which I'll try in the near future. I will also double the sauce in the future to serve over the rice, just wasn't enough since I cut the recipe in half. Thank you for posting Petunia, this will be a regular in my rotation.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Whole family really enjoyed this!  We shredded the chicken and served with tortilla chips.  Yum.  Thanks Jen Santiago....

name: lemon tea cookies
review: Really pretty little cookie!  Nice & tender but I would prefer the actual dough to be a little sweeter.

name: allrighty then scrambled eggs   paula deen
review: Really nice fluffy way to make eggs - the cheese is a nice touch.  This recipe was part of our Christmas morning brunch this year.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: I have served this to my family for the past 2 Christmases and they have already asked for it next year.  Simple easy and delicious!  Definitely a keeper :)  Thanks Rhonda!

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Fabulous!  Really tender & flavourful!  I pre-baked & then kept warm in pizza sauce in the crockpot - served as an appetizer at our Christmas Eve Open House.  All 4 dozen meatballs I made were gobbled up!

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: I had a heap of roast chicken left which I left over which had been well flavoured by the stuffing and the seasoning so just mixed int he the celery and the parsley and then I mixed the mayonnnaise, lemon juice and dill together and then mixed into the chicken (of which I used 2 halve breasts and the meat from 2 thighes) and used about just under 3/4 cups of mayonnaise which was plenty to moisten the chicken for us.  Served with a side salad as a main dish with a dinner roll on the side.  Thank you ellie_, made for I Recommend Tag game and recommended by pammyowl.

name: kittencal s perfect prime rib roast beef
review: I actually couldn't bring myself to eat this because the meat was so rare and fatty...  but everyone else said it was a perfect roast.  So I'm passing on their five-star reviews to you!  I will say, however, that the au jus was awesome and tasted great with the Yorkshire puddings I made :)

name: mean s dutch babies
review: I'm surprised I haven't reviewed this recipe yet. I have made it several times. I'd never had Dutch Babies before. But my girls and I love them! Just fixed it this morning for my mom who is visiting and she said it's better than regular pancakes. I bake in a cast iron skillet for about 22 minutes. We like it with powdered sugar, berries and real maple syrup on top. Unfortunately, no berries today - out of season. But still great anyway!

name: baked ham and cheese omelet roll
review: It stuck to the pan but once I got it released it rolled real good. I did not care for the texture and if I would decide to make this again I would not use the flour.

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: Hi Sherri. Awesome recipe! I've tried it with many different fruits... apples, raisins, Craisins and red seedless grapes. All are wonderful. I do, however, cut the celery down to 1/4 c (just because I don't care for it) and only use about 1/3 c of diced onion (because I like to leave it sit overnight, and then the onion really takes over). I also add just a pinch of mustard (because that's how I've been making it for 40  years. I too love "Miracle Whip"!!! Thanks so much for dressing up a classic go-to sandwich (croisants rock!). P.S. I skip the nuts altogether... they don't work welll with false teeth! LOL. :-)

name: crock pot whole chicken
review:
First Delicious!

Very moist tender, falling apart goodness. Now, I knew I wasn't going to eat the skin, so I didn't care. It made it for sandwiches and for leftovers in the freezer. But it would be equally good for dinner; the skin just didn't that golden brown crisp which I like. But I knew it wouldn't.

The seasoning was good, but I cut back on the salt; I tend to go light on the salt personally.

No pop up timer, but I know my crock pot pretty well. Also, I had a smaller chicken - 5 hours on low and it was perfect. I also have a larger pot. If I would of used a large chicken, 6-7 would of been the right amount of time.

Easy and came out very very good.

name: treebeard s red beans  and rice
review: Delicious red beans and rice!  Surprised my DH with these wonderful red beans today and he loved them.  I have eaten at Treebeard's restaurant many times over the years and these red beans are a favorite on the menu.  I used Burton's jalapeno sausage and it was a really nice addition - reduced the cayenne a tad.  Served these beans with rice and some delicious hot rolls.  Will definitely make this dish again!

name: banana banana bread
review: Good

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: While I was a bit care free with the seasonings, using Creole seasoning instead of the seasoning salt and cayenne, this was absolutely the best roast chicken I have ever made!  I used a vertical roaster and cut the lemons up into quarters not cutting quite to the separation point and put 1 semi-separated lemon in the chicken and one in the cup of the roaster.  I surrounded the bird with potatoes (which I cooked from the beginning) and carrots and rutabaga (cut into chunks) which I rolled in olive oil and seasoning and added at the last 40 min. cooking stage.  My chicken was still a bit frozen, so I had to cook it longer, but the end result of all ingredients was GREAT!!!

name: tzatziki
review: I made this yesterday to go with your Souvlaki recipe.  I did use a smaller cuke than I wanted to-DH has "issues", even with the burpless kind.  I added some fresh parsley as well as the dill, and opted for yogurt over sour cream.  Loved it!

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: First time making pot pie and the family loved it.  Only used one pie crust.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Wow! What a fantastic cookie.  Followed recepie as written.  Thanks for sharing.

name: blueberry oatmeal muffins
review: Great muffins! I used beaters to mix the butter, vanilla yogurt, egg, and brown sugar, then folded in remaining ingredients. The kids loved them. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: almost white castle hamburgers
review: Made these to have during the football game today.....they were NOTHING like the original & that's a GOOD THING, cuz we can't stand White Castle!!! I did forget the egg, but they turned out real good anyway. I made them in the oven the night before & kept them in the fridge until just before gametime.....chopped up & sauteed' some fresh onion & served them on mini-buns....EXCELLANT!!!! will definately make thse again...THANKS for sharing!!! (I gave only 4 stars, because I thought that 10 minutes was a little short...I added another 10 minutes)

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: my mom made this and it was awesome.  only downside is it is quite expensive to make.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Love them!

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: Used 2 boxes of the dried hashbrowns (looks like a 1 pint milk carton), reconstituted, 1 cup sour cream. dried onions and the rest the same. On the stove 1/2 hour, 375 15 minutes because I was using the oven for the meat. Excellent.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: This was really good and easy.  I cooked the chicken & onion in the crock pot and shredded it.  I used light sour cream.  I also tossed some sliced green onions on top of the melted cheese.  The only other things I would do differently:  1) add another can of chiles or some diced jalepenos to the chicken; 2) wait until the last few minutes to add the cheese (it got a little overcooked after 20 minutes).

name: brown sugar meatloaf
review: Moist and delicious.  I only used 1/4 cup of sugar and it was perfect. Also, the next time, I would put the sugar/ketchup on top of the mealoaf instead of being on the bottom.  Other than that, this is a keeper recipe.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: This was super simple, but just like any other cheater chicken, barbecue sauce, onion recipe.  Not outstanding at all.

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: this was okay, we found it a bit sweet for us.

name: gingerbread  for cookies or a  gingerbread house
review: I made one batch of this recipe (I didn't have allspice or cloves so I bumped up the ginger and cinnamon a bit) and it made one large gingerbread house (the roof pieces were 10" by 4", the walls were 9" by 6" and the end pieces were 9" by 4.5"). I had enough dough left over to make a couple snowmen and Christmas trees to decorate with. I LOVED that this was a one pot recipe and that the dough didn't have to chill. I was afraid that it wouldn't all come together, but when I kneaded it on the counter the dough did finally come together smoothly. Next year I'll be doubling the batch to make two houses and we'll have a friendly competition over who can decorate theirs the best! I did roll out half the dough on the baking pan (and cut away the parts I didn't need) and half of it on the counter. Rolling on the pan was really worth it to me because those pieces were much less wonky once they were baked than the ones I transfered.

name: kittencal s technique for perfect easy peel hard boiled eggs
review:
If you rating is a one or two stars, you went wrong since and you didn't followed the directions. ""ALWAYS READ THE RECIPE IN FULL BEFORE YOU START"" This would receive the Nobel Pie Prize if such an accolade existed. lot better than my OLD one I did ! Anyway, excellent to do a SCRATCH on recipes. I've will added this to my recipe book and the OLD one is out. THANK YOU!! I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! I can't leave anything alone! THANK YOU So!! 7 Stars There are some great chefs here on Zaar, and she's one of the best!
Note: A little salt in the water will keep eggs from cracking when boiling. Add a little vinegar to the water if or when an egg did cracks during boiling. It will help seal the egg. Someone suggest you start by putting the eggs in room temperature water and then bring to a boil, A pinhole in the tip of the egg will keep the shell from cracking due to trapped air. If you put an egg in already boiling water you stand a good chance of the egg cracking, especially if the egg just came out of the refrigerator.

name: the best chili you will ever taste
review: This is so sweet!  Tooth-achingly sweet! I made according to the recipe, although I only used 2 cans of beans...the poster actually said she cut the bean amount, so I felt that was okay on my first try on this recipe.  Maybe the extra beans take away from the sweetness, but I have always enjoyed a "meat" chili, not a "bean" chili, so tried for that. I enjoyed the mix of cubed sirloin and ground meat.....that is what I usually use.  I also do not use chili powder, basically making my own.  However, this chili is extremely sweet.  I can't say it is awful, but my mouth recoiled when I took a bite....it was expecting "chili", not candied baked beans.  This recipe is edible....but it doesn't taste like chili to me.  I'm giving this a 3 star, because it doesn't taste horrible, just not what you expect from chili.  I'm sad, because this is the first "new" chili recipe I've tried in years.....going back to my own tried and true recipe.***Letting this chili sit overnight lets the heat increase and temper the sweetness.  So I'm changing my rating from 3 to 4 stars.

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: This dish was prepared by our daughter for New Years Dinner and I believe she followed the recipe as is and it was spectacular.  Will be making again for sure

name: easy garlic chicken
review: I watched over the cooking to make sure the chicken didn't dry out in the 500 degree oven, which it did not.  After 18 minutes, it was nice & moist & tender.  However, I expected a nice glaze on the top, which I did not get.  I ended up with some browned garlic bits on top, no glaze, and a lot of liquid in the bottom of the pan.  Also, not a lot of flavor - what flavor there was was too sweet for my taste.  Will not make again

name: granny s slow cooker vegetarian chili
review: This totally hit the spot on a cold Winter day. I used chile beans instead of baked beans and refrigerated it overnight before serving. I'm glad I did because I thought the flavor really improved with time. I wasn't sure if I would like the garbanzo beans, but they added a unique texture to the chile. This was a very hearty meal and we never missed the meat. Thanks for posting the recipe.

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: This is a great soup!  It is very thick and hearty, tasty, and was not difficult to make. I made on the stovetop in my Dutch oven.  I only had 3 cans of black beans so for the fourth can I used Pinto beans, which seemed to work out fine.  I used a vegetarian-friendly substitute called "No Chicken Broth" for the chicken broth, and I ran out of regular chile powder before I had 2 tsp, so I subbed some ancho chile powder to make up the difference.  These modifications worked out fine.  I enjoyed topped with green onion and Monterey Jack cheese as suggested.  I'll be making this again.  Thanks!

name: christina s killer dip
review: Creamy, tasty dip.  It doesn't have any zip, but that's fine by me. Others may want to try to give it some zing.  We baked and then put in a mini crockpot.  It did get a bit juicy at the bottom of the crockpot, but it tasted great to the end.  Doesn't warm up quite as well, but if you don't have lots of other food out, it'll be gone anyway and how it warms up won't even matter :)  The ladies at our party really enjoyed this.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: I made this chili last night and my family loved it!  I didn't have time for the crockpot, so just cooked on top of the stove for about an hour instead.  I left out the tomatoes since the kids don't like to see them in their chili and just added a little water to compensate.  I love the texture that is created by blending one can of beans - makes it more saucy.  I also liked the spice combination.  Will definitely make this again.  Thanks for posting!

name: doctored up vanilla pudding casserole
review: Terrific recipe!  Everyone loved it.  Next time I will brush my banana slices with lemon juice, that is the only thing I would change!

name: easy peezy pizza dough  bread machine pizza dough
review: worked great... even though SOMEONE dropped the bread machine on the floor. thanks for a keeper!!

name: fabulous beef stew
review: This stew was amazing!  The only change I made was using 1/2 the amount of tomatoes since DH is not a big fan.  This was so easy to put together, will be making this again.  Made for I Recommend Holiday Tag.

name: chicken fried steak w cream gravy
review: Excellent recipe!  I made 4 cutlets and used only 1 cup of flour, 1 egg, and 2/3 c milk and there was still plenty of all left over.  The gravy was excellent and there was a TON of it.  We ate it over our steaks and potatoes and I still have plenty of that, too.  Next time I will halve the amount of gravy and it will probably be perfect.  Such an easy recipe and the whole family LOVED it!!!

name: garlic panko chicken strips
review: I really enjoyed this recipe.  I love to cook with panko, such an interesting texture.  I did have to put them under the broiler for a bit to brown them which gave them great eye appeal.  Thanks for the recipe.

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: This delicious soup really hit the spot on this chilly day.  The egg noodles were a great addition to this creamy soup.  Made as directed except that I added some seasoning from a Knorr vegetable soup mix.  It really gave the soup a nice flavor and I served it along with some cornbread.  This is comfort food at it's best!  Made for PRMR, January, 2013.

name: ground turkey chili for people who hate ground turkey
review: I am very happy with how this turned out.  I took the advice of several reviewers and doubled the amount of spices.  I also added about 1/8 t. ground cayenne pepper.  I also subbed black beans for the kidney beans.  Very good.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Awesome recipe, I added peas cause DH said pot pie always has them. I used a top and bottom crust, but it doesn't need it and next time I will go with the top crust alone. This could be a grat make ahead recipe for company and camping, will make again.

name: magnolia bakery s vanilla birthday cake and frosting
review: Cake and icing turned out great, as expected. I halved the cake recipe and baked it in 1 cake. Baked for about 1 hr. Cut in 3 layers, filled and iced with half the frosting. BTW, I didn't use nearly all of the sugar for the frosting and it turned out nice and fluffy and not overly sweet at all.

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review:
5 stars for the soup, but only 3 for the recipe. I found it confusing. I read many of the reviews, and it seems like the recipe has been updated since it was published in 1999, which is good, but I wish it mentioned that so you could know to ignore some of the comments. I still found it confusing - cup measurements for the onion, celery, etc., but ounces for the chicken (fyi, 12 oz of chicken turned out to be 3 cups in my kitchen). Also, what size tortillas? If you buy the little ones vs. the 8 or 10" ones, it can make a big difference. I was also confused by the direction to break them into pieces - tear maybe, but my tortillas were too soft to "break". Is the can of tomatoes optional? Or the dicing? It would have helped to have these things clarified.

That said, I did follow the recipe except where I made the following changes to make it a little healthier: cut oil down to 1T, used McCormick's Low Sodium taco seasonings, only used 4, 8" corn tortillas, only used 4oz of cheese in soup, used skim milk. For the chicken, I bought a rotissery chicken from the grocery, and I used every spec of chicken on it for the 3 cups. I think I agree with the reviewers who mentioned adding raw chicken to the 1st step as a savings - although it might not break down as much in the soup.

My tortillas took a LONG time to break down, and some pieces remained. I don't agree with some reviewers who said this was quick - with over an hour of cooking time (where you have to watch and stir), and multi-step prep, this was a weekend project for me. It did make a lot, though, I got 10, 1 cup servings from it, and I froze some for lunches. I would make this again, but I think I would try the massa harina instead of the tortillas, it just took too long and stressed me out.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Great!  That is pretty much it!  I did have 1 bit of trouble though.  Because the chicken was cold, when I added it to the butter it hardened.  I threw it in the microwave for a few seconds and it worked out OK.  The flavor turned out great!  Thanks for another great one Kittencal....

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: I doubled the recipe (using just under 2 cups of cream).   Next time I will not add the salt as I think the cajun seasoning had enough and it seemed a bit salty.  Also, the sauce seemed a bit runny so instead of adding the parmesan to the top I melted it into the sauce before I removed it from the heat.  This helped the sauce to thicken up nicely.  Very nice and QUICK dinner.

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: I make blueberry muffins all the time for my kids. I decided to treat them again this morning. I cannot wait for them to wake up already! :D I successfully halved the recipe and got 8 regular size muffins, baked for 17 minutes. I warmed the milk and butter in the microwave for 30 seconds , long enough to let the butter soften (not boil). I used lemon zest and canned blueberries that I had on hand. I sprinkled Sugar in the Raw on top the muffins before baking but it sunk into the batter while baking. I wish they would have browned up more on the tops, though.  The flavor is perfect and found them to be perfectly sweet, just right. I think anyone who disliked these or found the texture off, IMO  it was "pilot error".  You cannot add extra ingredients (bananas, etc) and expect an ideal end result.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Quick and easy to prepare and tastes wonderful.

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: Made this for dinner last night, my boyfriend loved it! We doubled the 'sauce' componant since he's crazy about sauce. It was great.

name: basic batter waffles
review: Great Easy and Tastey Waffle  I really liked the fact that I did not have to seperate the eggs and beat the whites and still have the waffle come out great.  I followed the recipe as written.  Thanks so much for sharing.

name: baked tilapia with lots of spice
review: This was really easy and tasty!  I made exactly as is and the fish came out perfect. Thanks!!

name: easy garlic chicken
review: DH and I really enjoyed this dish. As per other reviews, I took some advice. I added some diced onions and chili flakes to the oil with the garlic. I flattened out my chicken breasts to promote even cooking. I salt and peppered the chicken breasts before I poured on the brown sugar mixture. I baked at a lower temperature, but I understand why it was a higher temp. I rounded out the meal with garlic mashed red-skin potatoes, and steamed edamame. Lovely meal. Thanks ElleFirebrand for posting this great recipe.

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: The cheese in this recipe really makes the dish. I am not a big bean fan and would use chicken or something else next time (or at least very few beans). It turned into more of a pasta dish with a little sauce/soup which I really enjoyed with a very generous amount of parmesan cheese.

name: quick yellow cake
review: Excellent cake!  Cut down the baking time by about 15 minutes to avoid cornbread texture.  I used to always use cake mix, but this recipe gives me the confidence to bake from scratch!!  I sub oil for shortening, and that makes mixing so much easier, too.  The cake is light, tasty, spongy, and moist.  It makes great cupcakes, too.  This is now my go-to recipe!  Thanks for sharing!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: These were THE best biscuits I have ever made!  The ease of using the food processor, the detailed instructions, and they were the lightest, tastiest biscuits to ever come out of my oven.  This is a recipe I will not be losing anytime soon!  Thanks for sharing.  :)

name: crock pot chicken vindaloo
review: Really quite good.  I'm glad I added the brown sugar, as I couldn't imagine the dish tasting as good without it.  Next time I might use a little less cardamom and cloves, as it was a bit overpowering for my tastes.  Thanks for sharing.

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: Since I have never tried kale I wanted to make a recipe that was tried and true.  I processed the veggies in the food processor until fine and added 1 can of white kidney beans (all I had) so I added about 1/2 C of pot barley to help thicken the soup.  Mine is much thicker than the photos linked to the recipe.  Like another reviewer I added my parmesan rinds to flavour the soup instead of topping it on the soup.  As much as I enjoyed this soup, I found that 2 tsp of Italian seasoning may be too much for my taste otherwise it was a solid recipe.  Thanks for posting Barbara.

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: This was really good.  I scaled it down to 4 chicken breasts and put 3 bacon strips on each breast.  My husband REALLY loved this and my 3 picky kids and I all liked it too.  This is definitely staying in my recipe box.  Thank you Tish.

name: parmesan crusted tilapia
review: Yummy. We used Italian seasoned Panko and it was delish. No, we did not cover it- and it turned out moist, juicy, and perfect. Great, easy weeknight recipe!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Excellent recipe!  Loved how quick and easy it was.  Made half a recipe and still have enough for another night.  Used Anaheim pepper for the green.

name: perfect rump roast
review: Excellent!  I had a 2 1/2 lb. rump roast....I didn't add the garlic (husband doesn't like it) and used Montreal seasoning in place of the salt, pepper, garlic.  After reading some of the reviews, I used beef broth in place of the water and sliced my onion into quarters....the onions got all browned and delicious!  I roasted the beef until it reached 150 degrees, removed it from the pan and kept it warm, then poured out the juices and added some veg oil to the pan and browned a couple of tablespoons of flour right in the pan over low heat.  I added enough water to the juices to make about 1 1/2 to 2 cups of liquid and poured that back into the pan and whisked with the browned flour.  What a delicious gravy that was!!  This is really a great, simple recipe and I'll definitely use it again the next time rump roast goes on sale as it did today!  Thanks so much for posting this recipe :)

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review:
Very good. I doubled this recipe. The white sauce ended up being to thick, I had to thin it with about a cup of water. The kids don't like bread crumbs on their casseroles, so I cubed some cooked ham and sprinkled that over the top, then I sprinkled French fried onions over the top.
Very filling and there was even some left for my lunch tomorrow.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: The sauciest, best shepherd's pie ever! Seems a basic recipe, but it is fab!

name: cherry pie filling bread
review: We loved this bread. My cherry pie filling can was a bit smaller then called for but not a problem.  It still turned out nice and moist and flavorful.  I made this to send with DH to work for the guys and they all loved it.  5*'s all around.  thank you for sharing with us.

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: This is really good!  I made this for company and it was devoured by all.  I really liked the slightly sweet glaze for this meat.  I did let it get a bit too done, (not alot) so I spooned the liquid from the pan onto the sliced meat.  Perfect.  I then sliced the leftovers up in thin slices and served them to DH for sandwiches in his lunch.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: tilapia al ajillo  garlic tilapia
review: Easy to make and awesome flavor!  Everyone loved it!  Paired with Herb Cheese Sauce for Fish-Recipe #251802 and Greek-Style Oven-Roasted Lemon-Butter Parmesan Potatoes-Recipe #137331.  The sauce was great with the potatoes too!!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: Lovely, tasty soup. Made with full fat milk, boiled the veggies from the start with the soup, so halved the cooking time. Would leave carrots out next time and increase broccoli.

name: chicken fried steak w cream gravy
review: Good Lord Mark!  This was awesome!!  I sized the recipe down for two-which was easy.  I used half flour, half panko for the "crust" which worked out to be a very good experiment!  Loved the gravy-my Husband raved and yes, I will make this again, just not often as I do have some goals for spring, one of them being able to wear my cute capris ;-)  Thank you for posting this recipe.  It's now printed and in my Food Bible,  just in case the grid goes down and I have to kill a cow, I want to be able to make this again.

name: really really good candied sweet potatoes
review: So sweet and sticky.....yummy.  I made this with a pork loin roast and it went perfectly.  Our guests like the difference from what they are used too (w/ the marshmallows on top).  I was really pleased with how they turned out, thank you for sharing this recipe with us....its a keeper.

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: I didn't read the other reviews before I made this or I would have known to double (or triple) the sauce. Other than that, it was wonderful. I had a bag of Meyer lemons so I used one for this recipe. I used Panko breadcrumbs; I also added capers. Very, very good; I will definitely make this again, increasing the sauce. Loved the flavor and the crispness of the chicken.

name: jalapeo bites
review: We needed something quick to take to a get together this afternoon and had everything to make this (including panko) and was surprised how easy this went together and how good they tasted - full of flavor and really not so spicy they would burn.  Mine took about 20 minutes to brown nicely, they didn't stay round for me, kind of flattened on the bottom, but hey; who cares about that.  Wish I'd followed fwgal's idea and doubled these to freeze half to have on hand when unexpected company come around.  Thanks for posting and sharing this winner.

name: the best belgian waffles
review: I have given a few recipes on this site a try...hubby bought a professional waffle maker...I guess he likes waffles...anyway...this is awesome...I have made it at least a dozen times now...still trying to prefect the amount needed for my maker...either liquid spills out...or I have cute little ends...but the taste never varies...and here is someone who can't get egg whites to whip...but I can now...thanks for posting this delicious recipe...:)

name: the best chili you will ever taste
review: We love this recipe.  The only change I make is to reduce the amount of brown sugar by half.

name: grandma s soft sugar cookies
review: Very good cookies.  Thank you.

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: No need for take-out with a Chinese/Japanese recipe this easy and this good.  My husband thinks it tastes just like the mushrooms & chicken he gets at our favorite Chinese restaurant.  Definitely a keeper!  Thanks JustJanS.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Chicken was moist and flavorful.  The only thing I did different was to use paremesan cheese in place of some of the bread crumbs (I did not have enough bread crumbs.)  Thanks for sharing.

name: pizza dough and sauce
review: Pizza is one of those foods that everyone has their favorite type.  Unfortunately, this one was not ours.  If you like a thick hearty crust, this will be right up your ally.  For the sauce I used splenda for the sugar. Instead of using red wine OR water, I used a combination of both. I used up what I had left of the red wine and it wasn't quite enough so I added the water to get the needed amount.  This reminded both myself and DH of the type of pizza my in laws would like, but it's not our favorite.

name: the easiest  bestest focaccia bread ever
review: It was good, but tasted too much like pizza dough for me.

name: moist chocolate cupcakes  super easy  budget
review: Terrific cake recipe! We really wanted chocolate cake but had very little in the kitchen. I went looking for a recipe that used oil and found this one! And joy of joys it's already vegan! Didn't have to fuss with any subs! Already wrote this down in the book. Thanks bunches!

name: 24k carrots
review:
IF I could give this a 10 I would.. perfectly balanced sweetness and the ginger is SO perfect here!

Will use for tonight - St. Patrick's with our corned beef.

1/2013 Adding that these canned so well!!!!
a

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: I'm surprised that I haven't made this before now since I have tried lots of different marinara recipes on this site.  I made it today for meatball sandwiches and it turned out really well.  Very easy to make and the flavor was really good.  I had to add a fair amount of water to thin it to the right consistency as it cooked, but it didn't take away from the flavor.  Simmered turkey meatballs in it after cooking for about 2 hours.  Then served on baguettes with melted provolone cheese.  Everyone in the family really like them.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: This made a restaurant quality meal that my whole family loved.  It taste just like something we would get from our local Mexican restaurant.  I pared it with Spanish Rice, lettuce, tomato, sour cream, guacamole and refried beans.  Thanks for a great recipe Miss Annie.

name: interesting crock pot chicken
review: This was very good.  My chicken was so tender after 4 hours it fell apart as I tried to take it out of the crockpot so I shredded it and added it back to the broth.  I heated the soups and cream cheese on the stovetop then added it to the chicken.  I also added a little milk.  This was great over noodles.  Thanks for the recipe!

name: caesar pork chops
review: Really good - super easy! Thanks for posting.

name: healthy no bake cookies
review: We really liked these.  I made them exactly as written but doubled the recipe and I did use regular oats, not the quick ones.  I thought they were great and will make them again and again.  Thanks for the great recipe ShaGun.....

name: mexican casserole   6 5 weight watcher points
review: Really good and very easy. Mine wasn't as light as the recipe (light sour cream, regular cheddar) but still very healthy. Used a can of tomatoes rather than fresh and frozen corn. Baking covered helps the corn tortillas soften up. Served with a green salad for an easy weeknight dinner. Will definitely make again! Thanks for sharing!

name: salmon and asparagus in foil
review: Lovely way to prepare salmon. Clean, fresh flavors and super simple prep. Also very healthy. Loved it, Paula. Thanks.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Good but the sauce is too vinegary for us.  Made for I recommend.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Tasty pork chops.  Everyone loved these.  I decreased the bake time to 35 minutes as an hour would have been too long.  I also made another double batch of the "sauce" and poured them over fresh mushrooms and baked alongside the pork chops.  The mushrooms were even more delicious than the pork, highly recommend trying.  Thanks Brad!

name: brown rice and lentil casserole
review: This was good and easy to put together. I used vegetable broth. After reading the other reviews I decided to not add the italian seasoning. I also used a teaspoon of minced garlic instead of garlic powder. I also used 1/4 teaspoon of pepper and sprinkled with some salt. I also used Velveeta shredded cheese. I cooked it at 350 because I was also making meatloaf. It still took an hour and 15 minutes to cook. We liked it.

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: The meat mixture had a great flavor, I found that the flavor didn't go down into the  noodles at all and they were bland.  Next time I will double the meat/sauce mixture and mix half into the noodles.  Also, we love cheese, so I used a whole 12 oz bag on Monterey Jack cheese and 1 cup of Cheddar.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Great soup! I enjoyed the variety of veggies, the ease of preparation and the flavor. Most of all, I loved the health factor. I did find that I needed to add about 1 more cup of liquid. Thanks so much for posting!

name: amazing chicken tortilla soup
review: This was a great soup!  I would definitely make this again!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: Excellent sloppy joes!  I use extra lean meat and it's delicious every time!  Thank you for sharing this recipe!

name: cinnamon sugar bread  bread machine
review: A five star winner for sure! I loved the cinnamon/sugar flavor of this bread. It makes delicious toast as well. Thanks!

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: This was very simple, but I will definitely stick with the Traditional Eggplant Parmigiana that I normally make from now on.  The breadcrumbs tasted gritty and were unappealing.

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: This is very different, and very yummy! I used ground turkey and fat free soup/beans. I thought it was really good, but needed a little more "kick". Maybe next time I'll try using pepper jack cheese or add some green chiles or sliced jalapenos. I will definitely make it again! Thanks for sharing!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: Excellent.  Just as a personal preference, I would use less nutmeg next time.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: updating review: Made these again with small sprouts. Turned out great! (again... liked them the first time too.) They are carmelized and crispy on the outside and buttery soft on the inside. I was amazed that my 6 yr old daughter kept on asking for more and oozing of enthusiasm for them. Wow... that says alot!

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: Great oven baked fries!  Followed recipe as written.  Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: Fantastic! Make that 474 5***** ratings! My family could not praise it enough. I roasted a 8# bird (2.5 hours) and it was amazing and moist. The gravy was delicious. Thanks for posting Kitten!

name: vegetarian  meatballs
review: FANTASTIC!  I'm vegetarian and LOVE these meatballs!  I use my blender to finely crush the walnuts and also use half an envelope of Ranch powdered dressing, instead of the onion soup mix (can't stand onion).  I love these right out of the oven, brown and crispy, and also think they are awesome when cooked in the broth!  I use two vegetarian bouillon cubes with two cups water. I love them plain, with mushroom gravy and mashed potatoes!  These are awesome (and pretty cheap for me)!

name: do at home onion rings
review: I will add my voice to the chorus of yums. Super easy and very tasty. Like several other reviewers I added a touch more salt and some cayenne. Definitely a hit.

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: Excellent flavors and oh-so-easy to prepare makes this dish a 5  star winner. I improvised and used 4tsp of Garam Masala in place of the Mas mix, works perfectly. I used only one can of chickpeas because I'm not a huge fan, added the cayenne because I am a fan. Also I did add the apricots which lose their sweetness into the dish, very good taste. I will use thighs next time so the chicken is moist, breasts tend to dry out. I served over couscous cooked in chicken broth with golden raisins and topped all with chopped cilantro; some warm Naan and an arugula salad with cucumbers. Fantastic!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: My wife makes really good Sloppy Joes & this recipe is just as good, if not better...even she agrees!!! Didn't have any tomato sauce, so I used chili sauce instead. will most definately make this again...THANKS for sharing!!! :D

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: Oh... I made this last night... delicious! I mixed EVOO, butter, lemon juice with smashed garlic cloves and micro-waved it for 30 seconds to make it "garlic infused". Then added season salt & pepper to the garlic oil mix. I not only rubbed it inside & outside, but used my injector to put some directly into the meat. Yummy!!! I baked at 475 for 20 minutes, lowered to 400 about an hour. Update Jan 19, 2013: I'm so sorry KittenCal... I forgot to add those dang "5 stars" on my 1st review. Again I say... "delicious"! Thanks.

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: This is the best black bean soup. Use the canned beans....    they make a much heartier soup. I've had both versions... using dried beans from scratch and using canned beans. Canned beans make a huge difference. This is a good protein source for me. Thanks for the recipe. I like to add freshly chopped cilantro to this soup. ...    along with a jalapeno pepper.

name: cranberry orange muffins
review: Good muffins!  Needed to use up some oranges, so I juiced them, rehydrated my cranberries and these turned out good. DDIL really liked them as did DGS#2.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: I am surprised I have never reviewed this!  It's almost a staple at our home.  Making it today, I always add fresh basil, and oregano, and I use different tortellini's.  My family prefers the sausage tortellini's.  Today, I am trying something different as I could not find the sausage tortellini from buitoni, I am going to try some Italian Sausage Ravioli in the broth, along with some Chicken and Prosciutto Tortelloni....love that broth!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: WOW....was this ever tasty!!! E-Z to make & a little messy, but well worth it!!! I'll bet this would be excellant on baked fish, too!!! I used reduced fat mayo made with olive oil....forgot the garlic powder, but that's OK 'cause we're not big on garlic. THANKS so much for sharing...will DEFINATELY be making this again!!!

name: cinnamon raisin bread for the bread machine
review: Very good! I did as others suggested and used 1 teaspoon salt and 2 teaspoons cinnamon...and 2 teaspoons yeast. I used the white sugar, but brown would be good too.  I also soaked about 1 cup raisins in rum. Thanks for a great recipe!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: Just finished making this. Boy, is it good, lip-smakin' in fact! After reading the reviews, I decided a couple of changes...I used boneless/skinless chicken thighs cut into pieces, and dredged in some cornstarch. (1 tablespoon = 2 thighs) I boiled down the sauce a bit before adding the chicken (approx. 15 minutes), and once I added chicken it cooked very quickly. (20 minutes). Other then that, I did everything else the same and it was Awesome with a capital "A".

name: general tso s chicken  tso chung gai
review: This is one of the best recipes I've tasted here on food/zaar.com. I don't think I'll EVER go out for General Tso's again!  This was a bit more time consuming than the recipe stated, but then again.....I was watching tv and enjoying a glass of wine....so maybe I wasn't really diligent!  I couldn't find small dried red peppers, and used larger ones.  Just reduced them down to 6 instead of 8.  But will probably leave it at 8 next time because I ran out of peppers when enjoying this wonderful meal.  This is absolutely fabulous, and I'll enjoy this often!  Thanks for sharing!  Can't wait to make it for my daughter.....I guarantee she'll take the recipe back home. Super delicious!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Very good and easy.  We all enjoyed this flavorful and moist chicken.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: Perfect thickness and creaminess.  Loved it.  Put mine in the blender and served with Russian Black bread.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: This soup is really good.  I followed the recipe as written except I added crushed red pepper.  Will make again.  Thanks!

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: This dressing is off-the-chart yummy! I make all my own dressings and this will be my balsamic dressing forever more. I make a double batch, and would make a triple if I had a bottle big enough to put it in. We go through a double batch in about two weeks and it has always kept well in the cupboard. No need to refrigerate. Thanks to you and your mum for this fantastic recipe.

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: A very nice and easy recipe. I cut way down on the cayenne, just used the pepper flakes. I admit to adding some cream to the sauce, to increase it (I should have read the reviews first), and also to cut down on the heat (find for me but not for DH!). I should also add that fresh prawns/shrimps seldom get peeled here in the southern parts of Africa -- we prefer it shell on. Thanks!

name: best baked potato
review: A really good baked potato!

name: panda express orange chicken
review: If I had to rate this on taste alone, I would give 5 stars. I do agree the directions were a tad confusing, however after reading reviews I made some adjustments and it turned out perfect. First key is that the flour / cornstarch / egg mixutre is a WET batter. I increased to 2 eggs and a splash of water to get a thin pancake like batter consistency. I also coated the chicken pieces (I used cut up chicken breast tenderloins) in cornstarch first for about 10 minutes so the wet batter would stick to the chicken when I fried it. Second key is to use PEANUT oil if at all possible for frying. It really does make a difference in flavor. I used a wok and about a half inch of oil and the chicken turned out nice and golden brown. If you are frying in small batches, keep the fried chicken in the oven on warm on a wire rack and it won't get soggy. Third key is to use fresh ingrediants (ginger, sesame oil, etc.). I also adjusted the sauce (yes, double it!) to using a combination of white and brown sugars and reduced the vinegar by half, substituting the remaining vinegar with the juice of the orange. The zest is a must. I made the sauce in a separate sauce pot and let it reduce while the chicken was frying. I also added a cornstarch / water slurry to thicken the sauce just before I tossed it with the chicken. I will say this recipe is probably not best suited for the first time cook, however if you have the passion and the time, anyone can make it and is worth the effort.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: These were really good.  We made these exactly as directed.  I pared this with scalloped potatoes, Pan Roasted Broccoli and Frizzled Cabbage.  This was a delicious, wholesome meal.

name: leftover mashed potato pancakes
review:
Great recipe! I love potato skins, though I never know what to do with the leftover potato...
I added garlic powder, snipped green onions and leftover bacon bits-YUMMY!! I cooked these in a nonstick pan that was sprayed with butter flavored cooking spray. I chilled the mixture prior to cooking and I noticed the second batch I made didn't hold up as well since the mixture was more room temperature rather than from the 'fridge

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Very good chops!  Only change I made was I used pork steaks rather than chops.  Perfect amount of sweet and salty.  Made for I Recommend Tag.

name: ground beef gyros
review: I've made this before but I see that I had not reviewed it. I think it is a great short-cut recipe. The oregano really makes the difference. Today I am trying it with ground turkey and using the tip left in other reviews to knead the meat. (a little strange!) I also am baking it in the oven like a meatloaf. Tonight the oven works best but I think it will taste great either way. I'm interested to see how the texture comes out with the kneading. As written it had the texture of a hamburger.

name: one minute flax muffin   low carb
review: Great recipe. Really like having two small to medium sized muffins or one of the monster ones. I used 1/4 c egg white rather than a whole egg and grape seed oil to save on bad fats. Also upped the cinnamon a bit, added ginger and cardamom. Nuked this in a ceramic mini loaf pan and it was perfect at one minute. Does not taste or feel like a low carb muffin. Thanks for sharing!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: Everyone who can eat bread and had these liked them. I didn't like that there was 2 TBS yeast for only 4 cups of flour. Also, after letting them rise 5 minutes, I pressed them down so they were more disc shaped then let them rise 10 minutes before baking. I made these due to time constraint. In a crunch I might make these again.

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: This is a wonderful soup!! All who tried it raved. I made exactly as the recipe was written with one exception, I used fat free half and half. It turned out wonderful. Thank you Anne for posting this recipe!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: This is a really great technique for cooking broccoli. We love broccoli and eat it frequently.

name: frizzled cabbage
review: We love cabbage and use it in recipes often or as side dishes, but this is probably the best way we've ever eaten it.  Thank you.

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Wow. I am shocked how easy and fast this was. And good! It was my daughter's 100th day of school today so we shaped the dough into three pieces to look like "100." Added Italian seasoning, too. Both kids helped me spread the sauce and cheese. She thought it was great. I think we'll have pizza night every week and use this dough. DH was impressed, too. Thanks!

name: baked ham and cheese omelet roll
review: I had so much fun with this recipe and made it more for the technique than the recipe.  I've never been able to make a pretty rolled omelet, they always fall apart on me and doing this it came out "perfect" I did cut it in half for the 2 of us and used eggbeaters with only one real egg, then added sauteed onions, peppers and tomatoes to it when adding the cheese and ham.  Used an Italian Blend of cheeses as that's what I had on hand.  Served with a slice of homemade bread, and fried potatoes and hot coffee - a great, filling breakfast.  This is one I can't wait to share with my DGS's who enjoy making breakfast.  It would be a wonderful way to make breakfast for a crowd.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: I really liked this and my kids all ate it without complaint.  I made as directed, adding a bag of frozen broccoli stir-fry to the sauce and cooking about 5 minutes.  This was very easy and I will make again.

name: 7   day   soup diet recipe
review: This so-called diet is extremely unsafe. It is woefully inadequate in most major nutrients, and far too high in sodium. Following this diet as directed can lead to irreversible kidney and heart damage in susceptible individuals. I have seen this diet ascribed to half-a-dozen different "major hospitals;" all have disavowed it. It is an urban myth and not to be followed. You will lose water weight and dehydrate yourself; you will gain it all back as soon as the 7-day-cycle ends. I beg of you, for your own health, avoid this "diet." If you need to lose weight, go see your physician.

name: basic pancake mix
review: This is a fantastic basic pancake recipe. I usually look for healthier pancake recipes with a little more umph to get through the day. But, today I was in the mood for a nice, light, traditional pancake. This fit the bill perfectly. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: old fashioned corn and potato chowder
review: This was SO good - total comfort food. It was even more delicious the next day. Very easy to make using ingredients I normally have on hand. I used frozen kernel corn and added 1/2 chopped green pepper. Thanks so much for posting a recipe that I will be making often.

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: This was pretty good, it definitely needed some onion or something.  It is incredibly rich too, I couldn't eat much of it.  Thanks for sharing :)

name: low fat banana bread
review: This was a nice, moist banana bread and very easy to make. I did sprinkle a small handful of chocolate chips into the batter just because I love them. :-) Thanks so much for posting!

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: I loved these!  I halved the parmesan.  I liked how they had flavor, but weren't totally cayenne fries.  I did the soak in ice water thing too & they ended up nice and crispy.

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review:
Excellent! We loved the taste. I added the veggies to the black beans and broth when I blended it.
I cooked it a little longer to make it thicker, but did not change the recipe. Can't wait to have the leftovers! Carole in Orlando

name: old fashioned corn and potato chowder
review: I don't think I will make this again.  It is very bland.  I will search for a recipe that uses a flavored broth instead of water and has more seasonings.

name: beef patties in onion gravy
review: I added onions as other reviewers suggested.  Also for the 1/2 cup of water and flour I used red wine.  I think using beef broth would make it too salty because it's borderline salty as it is.  Overall pretty yummy and easy.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: This is an excellent recipe.  I cannot compare it to Panera as making it by this recipe is the only way I have experienced this soup.  I made it healthier by using Earth Balance in place of butter, using Better than Bouillon (vegetarian no chicken base) with water instead of chicken stock.  I also used my immersion blender to cream the soup after the vegetables were tender.  The flavor  and texture of this soup is perfect for our taste!  Thank you so much for sharing!  I will definitely make again!

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Yum, what can I say that hasn't been said? This was great. Made to use on cupcakes and DH took to work, of course, the guys loved them. Super easy and very good! Thanks Kitten.

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: This is delicious!  After cooking everything for an hour, I took some of the soup out and pureed it with my immersion blender.  Then I returned the pureed soup to the pot.  This soup is a keeper!

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: This certainly was easy to do.  I only had 6 oz of cream cheese but that was more than enough for us as this dish is quite rich.  I did a taste test about a half hour before serving and decided it needed some colour so I threw in 3/4 C of peas. I also drained off about half of the cooking liquid before I added the soup mixture because there seemed to be quite alot of liquid in the crockpot and I didn't want the sauce to be too thin.  My picky teenage son liked this so that is a good thing. Thx Mille!

name: crock pot potato chowder
review: This was a good base recipe but my husband and I both felt like it was missing something.  I added shredded carrots, bacon, garlic powder and pepper about an hour before serving and that helped a little but we still felt like something was missing compared to the potato chowders we get in restaurants.  I will have to fuss with this a little to find the perfect combination for our family.  Thanks stacylu for a good start.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: This was a great and tasty chili. I like to try different chilis and I loved that this one was supposed to be made in the crock pot. I cooked it on low for about 12 hours (that's how long I ended up being out of the house) and the meat was tender and the flavor was fantastic. I used a little extra of the spice mix (yay for not reading the recipe very well) and I used Penzy's ground chipotle pepper instead of chili powder and it was quite spicy, but not TOO hot--and quite smoky, too. I threw in some red bell peppers I had on hand as well as most of a large onion (instead of the tablespoon) and I only had 1 lb of ground beef. Obviously this recipe is made to tinker with! Thanks once again, I had it for lunch a day or two later and it only got better with time!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: This is on my menu for game day!  I made this the other day and everyone really loved it.  Changes?  I used a lean pork roast, 1/2 a bottle of sauce and cooked it on low for about 5 to 6 hours.  After the pork was pulled the additional 1/2 bottle sauce and about 1 cup of the cooking liquid was poured over the meat and finished the cooking process.  So simple and so utterly yummy.

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: Wonderfully delicious!  Loved the use of the mustard to dredge the chicken in before breading it with the panko bread crumbs.  I used chicken breasts that were halved which made this chicken so much more tender.  Served this dish with a mustard/lemon based sauteed asparagus.  What a wonderful meal!

name: skillet parmesan chicken
review: This was delicious! We served with broccoli over spelt linguine. Thanks!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: what more can I add? Tasty and moist and good!  Thanks for sharing!!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: Did the pizza Joe's.  Very good, quick easy and simple.

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: Good and spicy.  Will cut thinner next time.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: I haven't been able to branch out from Panera's broccoli cheddar soup, so I have no idea if this is really the same.
