What I do know is my 7 and 5 year olds both loved it, so it's a winner in my book!  We did double the season salt, just because  potato soup can be bland.  It certainly had flavor.  I used a package of thawed hash brown potatoes to cut the work down.  This was a snap to put together.  We grated cheddar on top and cooked some turkey bacon to crumble on top as well.  Our soon used his bacon as his spoon :)

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Wow, so awesome! I love that this is super quick and easy and they come out so brown and crispy and delicious. I used fresh brussels sprouts (I can't imagine it would work well with frozen). I didn't measure the oil, but probably got away with halving it. 35 minutes seemed to be perfect for whole brussels sprouts. I can see why this went into someone's best of the year cookbook!

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: Excellent, easy and looked great to boot! 'll be making these again. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: This was tasty,I had too much BBQ sauce in with it and it overpowered the chicken unfortunately.

name: poverty meal
review: This was really good. It reminds me of a healthier version of Hamburger Helper.  I paired it with garlic bread and a salad and had dinner ready in about 25 minutes. Great for a stressed out, crazy mom like myself.  UPDATE 2/1/13: I made this again tonight and added a can of Cream Style Corn that I accidentally bought and it turned out great again.  I had to spice it up a little because the corn made it bland.  Again I paired it with a salad and garlic bread and had dinner ready in a hurry.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: I've been using this for over 5 years -- can't believe I haven't reviewed it.  It's wonderful, and very, very easy.  I add Italian herbs to the dough -- makes it even better.  Great recipe!

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: I knew I couldn't go wrong with a Kittencal recipe.  I made Amazing White Trash Puff Balls and used this pizza sauce for dipping - yummy combination.  I made them for our weekly Mexican Train/Spinners game night.  They were a big hit.  Best thing is I have lots of leftover sauce so am off to make a pizza.

name: amazing white trash puff balls
review: These were very good, although mine weren't exactly attractive.  I may use the whole crescent triangle next time - just make them bigger.  I did make Kittencal's pizza sauce  for dipping.  Yummy.

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: FANTASTIC! So easy, ingredients I always have on hand, and fry up on a flat top with bacon grease...YUM! As close to Cracker Barrel pancakes as I've found. Perfect texture & flavor. THANKS!!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Made this last night for dinner and it was GREAT.  Loved the sticky, thick glaze that ended up on the chicken and the ease of just popping it in the oven and letting it bake.  Taste like something you really worked on.  The only thing I changed was to cut the recipe in half for the two of us and marinade the chicken with the sauce in the fridge for about 4 hours prior to baking, and I wouldn't change a thing otherwise.  The thighs came out moist and flavorful.  This is going in my Best of 2013

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: I have made this over and over, but never rated.  I love these.  They are a perfect work night meal.  I use leftover chicken, turkey, or even cornish hens.   I sometimes top with a pepperjack cheese sauce, which kicks them up a bit.  I too use olive oil instead of margarine.

name: fusion avocado
review: This was good! A change from my half avocado with sprinkle of salt.

name: cheesecake factory cheesecake
review: This is the best cheesecake I have ever made,so creamy and the taste is amazing!I also added strawberry sauce to the batter to give it that swirl effect,it was ok but I think I like the plain cheesecake better.It makes a nice high cheesecake.Great tasting crust too.Excellent!

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: Wow, this was so good.  I actually made it for an ingredient in spinach artichoke dip and it made it so rich and creamy. Can't wait to try it with pasta next time.

name: lisa s swirled chocolate chip cookies
review: My only chocolate chip cookie recipe from now on. Thank you so much for the new keeper.

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Tasty!  The method sounds daunting but it really is easy to do.  Nice presentation!

name: wholly guacamole
review: Loved the intro and the recipe! Made this for the Superbowl but I couldn't resist trying some early, a very good traditional guacamole. Thanks for posting!

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: Ribs were tender and sweet.   Too sweet for me  I would leave out the honey and white sugar next time.  Made for best of 2012.

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: As I did not have Old Bay seasoning or celery salt, I left them out, but otherwise made as written. My family loved them. Thanks for an easy dinner.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: These were good! Made with a side of refried beans. I marinated for a couple hours. I didn't taste a whole lot of marinade. Maybe I need to double it. I used a green, red, and yellow pepper. Added avocado, salsa, and sour cream.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Very nice frosting.  I had rave reviews from my family.  Thanks for posting.

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: Really hearty and good! 4 men DD1 (5 years old), DD2 (15 months), and I say so. This recipe works well with all sorts of modifications, additional vegetables etc. I first put the stewing beef in a few tbs vinegar and Motts Tomato Juice for 35 minutes to help them become tender and give it some extra flavour. After I drained them and began the recipe. I used white rice flour instead of regular flour to be gluten free. Before I added the big pieces of vegetables I cooked the meat for approximately 40 minutes longer than called for in recipe#206712 instead of beef broth as I could make it easier. I used 3 medium carrots in all, cut into big chunks rather than diced or chopped fine for more heartiness. I used one less onion than called for, though my onions were pretty big. I exchanged the thyme to marjoram due to personal preference. In addition to the called for vegetables I added some chunks of butter nut squash one time (wouldnt do it again), a large handful of fried okra one time which was a good addition, and about 1/3 cup frozen baby peas near the end of cooking time both times. I served it with quinoa macaroni if wished. I would make again during the winter for a warming lunch or dinner.

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: 10 stars!  These are so unbelievable good!!  We have a drive up diner in town that serves loose meat sandwiches and these taste just like them.  They are called "zip burgers"!  I always get a cheese zip with ketchup and pickle.  They close Nov-March, so now we can get our zip fix in the dead of winter.  Thank you so much for posting!

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: Nice, easy recipe that had a full bodied flavour!  Instead of adding the sugar, I added abut 1/8 to 1/4 tsp cinnamon which gave it a nice touch.  I made this recipe primarily to added to other dishes that called for marinara sauce, so I am looking forward to seeing how they turned out.  Going by the taste of this marinara sauce,  they should be excellent!!!  Kudos on a great posting!!

name: the best chicken tortilla soup
review: Good and spicy, we loved it.  Served with quesadillas.YUM.

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: I'm giving this recipe 5 stars because the flavors were very good & I liked the idea of baking, not frying.  I think the butter is overkill with Sat. Fat and will try it with Vegetable Oil or Canola next time to see if the crispness comes out better.  They didn't crisp up as much as I would have liked with the butter.  Also, I think I'll save a step and use Kentucky Kernal Flour next time, it has the same spices except the cayenne.

name: self rising flour
review: I used this for some sweet potato muffins that called for self-rising flour.  The muffins came out great.

name: low   slow oven baked ribs   super simple
review: Great method! Can experiment with different BBQ sauces and rubs with this recipe.

name: tsr version of olive garden pasta e fagioli by todd wilbur
review: My guys loved this soup.  DS thought it was like a goulash and chili soup mixed together.  He loved it.  DH did too.  They thought the leftovers the next day were just as good if not better.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: treebeard s red beans  and rice
review: What a WINNER of a recipe.  We loved this dish.  I did add 2 lbs. of smoked sausage but otherwise followed your instructions.  My house smelled heavenly while this was cooking.  DH liked it so much he took the leftover out of town with him to eat at his job site!!!  Thank you so much for sharing with us your recipe.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: We don't eat chicken thighs often, but they frequently go on sale at the grocery store.  This recipe is a good way to take advantage of cheaper chicken cuts, yet enjoy a flavorful meal.  Thanks, Petunia, I didn't change a thing and our family enjoyed every bite.

name: southwestern stuffed bell peppers
review: I made this for my family and not only was it a tasty dish, it was beautiful too!  I left some of the filling out and put in a small casserole for DS whom doesn't like peppers.  They all loved it.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: easiest beef enchiladas ever
review: This was a simple enchilada recipe.  I used ground meat and cheddar cheese.  I also used some homemade sauce I had in my freezer.  Thanks for the quick meal.  We served this with spanish rice and refried beans.

name: one minute flax muffin   low carb
review: It is really strange how this resembles the look of bread/ muffins and yet there is no flour in the recipe.  I was a bit surprised by how much this puffed up in the mug.  I added blueberries and diced strawberries to mine.  I think next time I will try apple bits and some walnuts.  This is a great recipe for the South Beach Dieter. Thanks for posting!

name: crock pot potato chowder
review: Such a forgiving recipe!  and a great way to use up potatoes!  I made quite a few changes, but my version was 5 stars indeed.  I used veggie broth instead of chicken.  I used half red potatoes and half russet.  I took recommendations of others... Threw in a can of creamed corn, added the corn kernels off one cob, added 2 T of diced red bell pepper, and 2 thinly sliced small carrots.  I also added white pepper and basil.  Lastly, instead of the cream cheese (which I promise I will do next time) I added some instant potato flakes.  Yummy stuff!  Mine took 1 Huron high followed by 7 hrs on low.  Crock pot was full!

name: szechuan noodles with spicy beef sauce
review: I can't believe I have not reviewed this recipe. I make it at least once a month and we love it. I have also made it for  company and it is always a big hit. I make it exactly as posted except for adding a splash of oyster sauce. I prefer making it with whole grain spaghetti, but will make it with any spaghetti I have in the house. Easy to make and very delicous to eat. Thanks for this great recipe Sharon123.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: This was great. I didn't change anything. Served with wild rice and veggies.

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: Made this for a ladies luncheon I catered and it was a big hit!  You need a really big crockpot for this as I had to cook the noodles separately, put them in the serving bowls, and ladle the soup over the top.  Even with the omission of the noodles in my crockpot, it was close to overflowing.  One of the ladies reheated this for a couple of days following her lunch and said it got even better with time.  I will definitely be making this again in the future.  Thank you for posting!

name: wholly guacamole
review: Love the intro, and the dish. It was my first time making guacamole, and it turned out really tasty. Thank you.

name: taco bell quesadillas
review: Wowee!!!!  What a great recipe.  The sauce is spectacular and is a great condiment for many a Mexican dish.  I did though increase the amount of the cumin, garlic powder, and paprika.  I also added chili powder a dash of hot sauce and very little cayenne due to my girls dislike for very hot food.  Instead of salt I added Goya adobo seasoning mix.  Didn't add the jalepeno's  or the jalepeno juice because I didn't have any but I've used a touch of vinegar and at another time I've added lime juice.  How my kids adore this recipe, even hubbie, son and daughter who declare to hate mayonnaise!  What they don't know won't hurt them:)   They like to use it as a dipping sauce for quesadillas and plain tortilla shells.  Thanks 89240 for posting a WINNER!

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: Lovely to look at! Delicous. Simple to make...appreciate recipes where you do not spend hours in kitchen. I used dried basil, unfortunately I did not measure. Did use 1/4 t. garlic salt, 1/8 t. Pepper, and 2 t. Lemon juice.  The other beauty of recipe is versality.  Served with my chicken enchilada. Had a similar salad at Wisdom's in Tumacaori with tamales so knew I would love it.  Thanks Marliah for posting.

name: shrimp  cocktail sauce
review: My family is attempting to use fewer commercially prepared items, and I was needing some cocktail sauce for later this evening. I literally just finished making this, and it couldn't have been any easier. It tastes so much fresher and cleaner than the supermarket variety; I can't believe I didn't try making this earlier. I made this using ketchup recipe #343611.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: This was good, just found that the flavour was fairly mild even after marinating overnight.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Great method!  Since I have a new oven and am not used to all its quirks yet, I stood by the whole broiling time to keep an eye on it.  I broiled on the lowest shelf, 10 minutes on one side and 5 on the other.  It came out nice and crispy.  I used Frank's Red Hot for the sauce part, but agree with the others who said this method would work great with any type of sauce you were in the mood for.  Thanks for sharing!

name: tsr version of applebee s oriental chicken salad by todd wilbur
review: I've never tried the Applebee's Salad but this was really good! I didn't have corn Flakes so I sub'd corn Chex. I will be making this salad again for sure. Thanks for the post!

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: Dear Kittencal, I know you don't need another review but you are getting it anyway! This is truly the best whole roasted chicken I have ever made, as good as the Rotisserie Chicken at Publix. Crispy skin and moist meat = delicious! I put 2 half lemons, some rosemary and plenty of salt and garlic in the cavity, the chicken tasted faintly of lemon and garlic but not overpowering. This will be my only blasted whole chicken going forward! Thank you!

name: weight watchers 2 point  pumpkin muffins
review: I used a whole wheat gingerbread mix and pumpkin that I roasted myself (and had in the freezer) after Halloween.  I added 1/2 cup of oatmeal per the other reviewers to decrease the moisture and next time I will add a full cup.  Super moist and delish and healthy!  With the gingerbread flavor the pumpkin went undetected.  Will make this again!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: Add me to the list...creamy, zesty, hearty and good! Not for the nights you want to eat lighter, but when you're ready to indulge, this is IT!

name: interesting crock pot chicken
review: February 12, 2013 - Update - Made this for supper tonight.  The whole family loved it.  I would however, cut back a little on the the dry ranch as we thought it was a little salty and I would also half the recipe...there is alot of sauce.  We will definitely be making this again.  Thanks for sharing!

name: wholly guacamole
review: Wholly Yummy!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Cooking is both art and science. As a science, the kitchen becomes a laboratory, the setting for discoveries that work so well they become classics, or fail so abysmally that they are lessons in what to not do. As science, food becomes cuisine. Cooks learn to add a 'pinch' of a favorite spice to enhance flavor. Scientists maintain the rigor of exactitude. Cooks weigh and measure to produce a finished result that is consistent. AND THEN THE FUN BEGINS. We decorate around food, making our tables beautiful, honoring community with flowers. *ALWAYS READ THE RECIPE IN FULL BEFORE YOU START, then read the reviews. I give 5 Stars! FOR the reviews : Will I GIVE 7 Stars to the reviews. "ALWAYS READ THE RECIPE IN FULL BEFORE YOU START". THANK YOU!! I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! I can't leave anything alone! THANK YOU!! 8 Stars.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: I didn't care for these at all. I tried a couple before adding any sauce & they were tough & tasteless. Doubt if I'll make 'em this way again.

name: jalapeo bites
review: Loved this idea. Got great comments all around. I had a bit of trouble with the shape holding too. I used panko breadcrumbs and half cheddar.

name: blender quiche   or whatever you have in your kitchen leftover
review: Delicious! Made with zucchini, onion and garlic as well as some leftover chicken and the last of the lunchmeat in the fridge.  Great use of leftover bits!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Yummm. Even DH liked it, that's a big compliment coming from a meat and taters guy. Made pretty much as outlined, I did dip the chicken in some 1% buttermilk before breading. Cooked quicker than expected. Will certainly make again, oh did I say quick and easy with minimum clean up. Thanks for sharing.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: This was really good.  I am sick so my husband made this for Valentine's Day dinner and it was restaurant quality.  I couldn't find Cajun seasoning so he used soul seasoning instead.  We both agree that next time it would be better with more sun-dried tomatoes, wilted spinach and mushrooms.  We served it with salad and garlic bread for a delicious meal.

name: chicken pasta milano
review: Mmmmm, this is really good.  I made as written and we enjoyed very much.  I served with roasted broccoli and garlic bread.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: Yummy.  I did make a couple changes.  I used 1% milk and Velveeta cheese and added a little garlic.  I think the nutmeg adds a lot.  In any case, I will be making this lots.  My DH who doesn't eat cooked broccoli even had a dish and said it was good.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: I agree with the title. I will never need to use a different recipe again! Very moist, intense chocolate flavour, but well balanced and not overly sweet. Unlike my other chocolate cake recipe which is also delicious, this one holds up well and is not too crumbly. I halved the recipe and used a tall 6 inch round pan and it took about 1 hour for it to cook through.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: These are very, very decadent brownies.  We made these with 1 1/2 cups of milk chocolate chips folded in.  These are simple and only take a few more steps than a box mix to make.  Next time I want to try to do a layer of the brownie batter, a layer of raspberry preserves and then another layer of brownie batter.  There truly are an infinite number of possibilities with this recipe.  Thanks Karen!

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: Delicious and so easy.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: I made a half batch but used 2 heads of garlic. It was perfect!

name: the best chicken tortilla soup
review: Absolutely wonderful!  This soup had just the right amount of heat and complex flavor.  I made it on Sunday and ate it on Wednesday.  It definitely got better with age.  Also, I used several different types of hot peppers and chilies %u2013 not sure if they were those that were intended but it worked out fine.  I roasted a couple of chicken legs and thighs that were perfect for the soup %u2013 no prepared rotisserie for me.  This could become a staple in my home.  Thanks so much for posting

name: breakfast burritos  once a month cooking
review: Awesome.  I added about 2 cups of frozen hash browns (browned), a cup of sliced mushrooms and a cup of frozen diced onions.  What a great way to get some protein in my husband on a hectic morning.  I did find from a total frozen state, it took 3minutes in the microwave--but I do have a lower wattage micro. Good idea to wrap the burritos in a damp paper towel to keep them from drying out. Thanks.**update 02/15/13~~I make these quite often so I felt like I needed to revise my comment.  This does not make 24 burritos unless you want all carb, too much tortilla burrito.  I make an even 10 burritos, without splitting the tortillas.  I'm not adding a ton more ingredients as far as what's listed.  Still 12 eggs, 1/2 pound turkey sausage, then 2 cups cubed potatoes.  Another cool trick is to reduce the salsa, helps to avoid the burrito being too wet.

name: treebeard s red beans  and rice
review: I made this in the crockpot.  The only substitution I made is to use Soy Chorizo so the vegetarians coud eat it too.  Everyone seemed  to enjoy it.  Thanks for a great meal on a cold winter day.

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: Delicious! I added 1 lb cooked chicken sausage and a handful of rice. Loved it!

name: slow cooker macaroni   cheese
review: This is good...not to die for.  I had 2, 2 year olds that loved it but I wasn't over the moon.  Made it as written but next time will leave out the eggs and see how that works...I wonder if they made it temperamental?  Anyway, thanks for the recipe GiddyUpGo and Paula...

name: best ever  and most versatile  muffins
review: I think the recipe is good, but I'm not an independent enough baker to come up with a good filling combo.  I didn't have any fresh fruit around so I tossed in a teaspoon of cinnamon & a teaspoon of vanilla plus a fourth a cup of chocolate chips & 1/2 cup of brown sugra.  Hardly tasted the cinnamon, and if the brown sugar added anything I would have been really disappointed without it.  I also added instant coffee--sprinkled some in, and a spoonful of nutella to half of the muffins.  The flavors didn't stand out at all.  Guess I need to be more bold next time.  Also, the muffins weren't moist. I can possibly blame over stirring for that--though I was anxious the whole time about all that others had warned about, I stirred in my added ingredients AFTER the milk/egg mixture & maybe that's what overdid it.  Or maybe I baked it too long--20 minutes as opposed to the 25.  But if either of those things were to blame, I wish the recipe would have been more specific to prevent though issues.  Still, it was an easy--nearly one bowl recipe.  I'll probably be returning to it.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: Yum, this is delicious!  I don' t know if I had a smaller cauliflower or if we just got addicted and ate a lot (very possible), but it was 4 servings here.  This was so easy too - I just prepped and put in the oven and was able to make the rest of dinner.  Wonderful.  Thanks for sharing!  Veggie Swap 55

name: paula deen crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: This is good...not to die for.  I had 2, 2 year olds that loved it but I wasn't over the moon.  Made it as written but next time will leave out the eggs and see how that works...I wonder if they made it temperamental?  Anyway, thanks for the recipe GiddyUpGo and Paula...

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: I was disappointed after reading all the good reviews. We followed the recipe as written but found the chicken to be bland. It needed more seasoning.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: This was quite good. It wasn't like most carrot cakes I've had before, but it tasted good and got even better after sitting for a day.  I loved the icing but my husband said that was where he thought it was lacking.  Next time, I'll sub a cup of brown sugar instead of 1 3/4 cup white sugar, and skip the coconut, and maybe add raisins. I thought the coconut made it very chewy and didn't add to the overall flavor. I'll also add some extra spice; nutmeg and clove, perhaps, as other reviewers have suggested.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: The kids love this. It is delicious. We have no leftovers for a family of 5.

name: baked tilapia with lots of spice
review: 4 stars because it itoo salty. definitely reduce salt.

name: oatmeal chocolate chip lactation cookies by noel trujillo
review: These are delicious! I just ate my first few so I can't speak to their effectiveness yet, but I'm sick and noticed a drop in my supply so I'm hoping these will do the trick!

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: Delicious. followed recipe as written.

name: how i got my family to eat spinach  spinach casserole
review: I great, quick-to-make spinach recipe.  It was a bit too salty for me, but otherwise it tasted quite good.  I used saltines instead of croutons and it worked well for me.  Thanks for sharing.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: I have made this many, many times.  It is tasty, comforting, and healthy.  I make it with homemade chicken broth which makes me like it even more!

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: Super easy, fast and full of flavor! Served it with barbequed chicken and brown rice. Perfect weeknight dinner. Made for Healthy Choices tag.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: These were good... not great. Maybe I used the wrong wings. I didn't cut up fresh wings from the supermarket. I used the IQF (Individually quick frozen) Tyson wings from Sam's Club. They weren't cooked wings..   they were raw.  I defrosted them first and then made this recipe with them. They were a lot of work for the end result. A big pot to wash... a broil pan to wash...   bowl and tongs... sink to wash out after draining the boiled wings and spices.  I'm just not as thrilled with this recipe as much as others are.

name: chipotle roast for tacos   sandwiches
review: This was good! Followed directions exactly. Everyone loved it! I made it as tacos with queso fresco and avocado slices.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: Very good soup. I didn't bother to peel the potatoes. Next time I think I'll cut back on the seasoning salt, but other than that, it was perfect.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: This is a great little recipe.  Word to the wise, unless you like very spicy food DO NOT use 2 lbs of hot sausage.   We did this and it is really spicy.  We still liked it, but next time I will definitely sub in Sweet Italian Sausage.  Thanks for a great recipe Sharlene!

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: This was so easy to make & enjoyed by the whole family with the exception of the fussy almost 3 year old..I added some grated carrot & zucchini & chopped tomatoes to the mince mixture for added vegie content and it made enough that we have leftovers to freeze. We topped with guacomole & sour cream and chopped grape tomatoes. Thanks for posting!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Delightfully moist and tender... Simply gorgeous. Hubby says it's a keeper!

name: individual cream cheese danish
review: Yummy!  Super Easy, and tasted so similar to a danish!  The filling was spot on!  Thanks for the recipe idea!

name: vegetarian lasagna
review: Quite tasty!  I used baby portabella mushrooms so they'd hold up better when cooked.  I cut back on the sauce, using about 2/3 of the recommended amount, saving the extra sauce for serving.  I also doubled the amount of mushrooms and zucchini because I have extra on hand; and that was a good choice.  Next time I want to try using fresh spinach instead of frozen.

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: Excellent! I made a half recipe us this in an 8x8 square baking pan since it is just the two of us tonight. Came out wonderfully. Thanks for sharing-

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: Made this up to go with recipe#194375#194375 and used recipe#89857#89857 for the lipton onion soup mix....this was delicious!  I will definately make this again DH ate most of them so there was no leftovers.  Defiinately a favorite and going into my Favorites of 2013.  Next time I might try to cut the oil back just a little.  Thank you for posting.

name: kale chips
review: These were delicious. I ueed fresh kale from the garden. This didn't need ANYwhere near the salt called for in the recipe as far as I am concerned. {{2 tablespoons of salt would do a whole basket of kale}}. Please use your discretion when adding salt for your own taste. I am amazed that as Roosie {another reviewer} stated ... they turn out like lightly baked potato chips. ...  oh.. just tooo tooooooo delicious. Thanks for a tasty recipe!... and a healthy one to boot!  UPDATE 02/21/2013..  These are still terrific for a snack. Your kale needs to be DRY BEFORE BAKING it. So.. what I do is: the night before I make them I wash and spin dry the kale. I then put it into a new large mesh bag (the ones that you use for laundry or lingerie) and put it in my refrigerator overnight. When morning comes around your kale is nice and dry. I also bake these longer on a much lower temperature to reduce overbowning. I bake them on 275 degrees F  and check them after 10-11 minutes and take the crisp ones off while allowing the others to remain on the cookie sheet to be baked a little longer.

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: On top of recipe#462758 with extra sliced organic bananas on top. Wowie. Like my mom used to make for the ice cream dessert we ate all to often. I made ours a bit healthier using organic cane sugar, organic fair-trade cocoa powder, sea salt, light tasting extra virgin olive oil to be dairy free, & alcohol free vanilla from the health food store. I will make this again for DH to try those pancakes! Made for Healthy Choices Tag Game 2013.

name: easiest beef enchiladas ever
review: I made these tonight using recipe#42094 for the sauce and left over chuck roast.  DH & I loved them!  I did add a can of chopped green chilies (personal tastes).  This was my first time ever making beef enchiladas and I knew MizzNezz would not let me down.  I will make these again and again - next time with ground beef! :)  Thank you for posting a super easy recipe to make that is worthy of any guests or special occasion!

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Delicious! I make a very similar tasting recipe to this, but mine uses a lot more butter. That's why I'm putting this recipe into my best of the best file - it tastes like our favorite wing recipe but it uses much less butter! That's a winner in my book.

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: I made this with a slight change for our own personal tastes.  I used 1 cup low sodium beef broth and reduced the water accordingly, and only used 3 teaspoons chili powder.  So very easy and the enchiladas were to die for!  Thanks for saving me tons of money as I'll never again buy enchilada sauce!

name: pizza dough and sauce
review: Our new go-to pizza recipe! Easy to prepare, and the family loves it!

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: Not that you need any more reviews!! <wink!>  But this was just what I needed tonight -- with cauliflower in abundance, and tired of the same old, same old ... I did not tweak your recipe, but I used a container (1 cup, 250 ml) of creme fraiche instead of sour cream. Oh well, it's actually the same thing, only creme fraiche is thicker. I crisped the bacon under the oven grill. I did use up a small piece of Grana Padano cheese with the cheddar. Yes, it is rich, but I am a woman who happens to love "rich", and it has never made me fat! <wink!> I also appreciated that your ingredients and directions were spot on. In fact, I accidentally over-baked the dish by 5 mins. Thanks for a keeper!!

name: denny s style french toast
review: I forgot the cinnamon... don't forget the cinnamon!  But I thought it was a good french toast recipe and I liked the texture.  Thanks.

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Fantastic and so easy!  We like thinner crusts, so we made this into 2 pizzas. We'll be making our own from now on!

name: drunken garlic crock pot roast
review: Had to break from my normal crock pot roast beef since I didn't realize I was out of half the ingredients!  Decided to try this and it was delicious!  I only had one head of garlic, so added in some garlic powder and had to use a cheap beer but was still great!  I think we will add this to the rotation in addition to our regular recipe.  Thanks for posting!!

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: This was an okay dish, good if you consider the ease of preparation. There was just too much of that canned soup taste to be completely enjoyable.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Everyone at work loved it.

name: mexican casserole   6 5 weight watcher points
review: This was a delicious and quick dinner!!  I replaced the beef with tofu but otherwise made as listed everyone really liked it!  Will be making this again! Thanks for a great recipe!

name: best pumpkin cookies
review: Good recipe! I turned the cookies upside down and dipped the top in the glaze. It was faster that way, as the glaze gets hard quickly.

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: A good cookie recipe.  It is not the family favorite just because they like a softer chocolate chip cookie and these ended up pretty crispy the next day.  Followed your hint to chill the dough before baking and the only slight change was to skip the nuts.  Good flavor - really more of a texture thing for us - I even tried baking them less but all the cookies were "dunkers" the next day which is fine with me in a cup of coffee!  Thanks Karen for posting.

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: Loved this recipe for being quick and easy to put together.  I followed the recipe exactly, except I used my own dry Italian seasoning mix (# 63812) which I found on this site, and folded pre-cooked noodles into the mixture instead of serving it spooned on top of the noodles.

name: cream cheese cinnamon crescents
review: We enjoyed and ENJOYED  !!!  Made these and took to the hospital to share with the other volunteers. And in no tome they were gone.  I did make these as posted except used fat-free cream cheese.  This is one not to worry about the calories. Worth trying.  Made for Best of 2012.

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: This was a simple, very good sloppy sandwich.  My husband ate 3 and I had two.  The only person who didn't really enjoy this was my picky 2-year-old.  I will make again.

name: wholly guacamole
review: I like a bit more garlic but this is a nice version of guacamole. I used prefect avocados and I loved the crushing with a big spoon and the texture it gave the final product. I used the greater amount of organic garlic, sorry but I used less than half a lemon which I love generally adding even more, plum tomato, regular onion, sea salt and the optional cilantro (a small hand full, would add more next time) for it's detoxing of heavy metals and just love it anyway! Made for Healthy Choices Tag Game 2013%u200F.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: I made this once as written. After a search for a real good recipes to do. And with resulted in other similar recipes, I decided I wanted to create something unique a great base recipe and easy to modify depending on your tastes.. It may be a stretch to call my creation, but the result was a meal the whole family will liked. MY was Not better, not worse, just different ! I've will added this to my recipe book "AS IS" and with my additions TOO. I have two way to do it!! THANK YOU!! I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! I can't leave anything alone! THANK YOU!! ALWAYS READ THE RECIPE IN FULL BEFORE YOU START, then read the reviews. I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! You get good Tips and Hints or two, to Note there. There are some great chefs here on Zaar, and she's one of the best! See Chicken Spinach Tortellini Soup or Chicken Soup for more tip's.

name: crispy ginger beef
review: This was really tasty. I only used half the amount of sugar and it was still plenty sweet. For some reason my beef didn't get crispy, but it was still tender and flavorful. I would say it was restaurant quality. I usually go for a healthier stir fry, but this was made as a treat, choosing not to look at the nutritional values. Thanks for sharing the recipe, we really enjoyed it.

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Pretty good!  The cumin makes the dish taste just different enough to not be boring old spaghetti, which I enjoyed.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: Fantastic!  I used pecans and I'll try the walnuts next time.  This was just so delicious I can't stand it.  I kid you not...our 21-YO cat stared at us while we ate with drool coming out of his mouth so we just had to save a chunk for him.  He wolfed it down and is now snoring, LOL.  I love making everyone happy!  My husband and I really loved the combination of flavors and textures in this salmon recipe.  This is going into our 'favorites' folder!  Thanks for sharing this recipe Tigerjo :)

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: YUMMY!!!  I made just as directed with one small change.... I used evaporated skim milk instead of the half and half and it was DELICIOUS!!  Even my kids liked it alot!!  Thanks for a yummy AND EASY recipe, not to mention quick!

name: fabulous beef stew
review: Family liked this. Maybe a tiny bit to much tomatoe but fine. I added an onion an an extra clove of garlic.  Peas would have been nice but none on hand. I cooked 5.5 hrs on high and added potatoes and celery after an hour or 2 of cooking and added carrots 45min before done added the corn starch mixture with only 30min left. Will make again might reduce tomatoes? Great comfort food for the snow storm we had!

name: soft peanut butter cookies
review:
Light and fluffy doesn't even begin to describe these! They literally melt/fall apart in your mouth. My mom used to make peanut butter cookies when I was growing up and hers were always dense and tasted so peanut butter-y, like you were eating a mouthful of peanut butter.
These are more cookie-like, and the flavors of the butter and sugar are prominent also. Very very good.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: Such a simple recipe to have on hand when you want a tasty dinner to come home to without a lot of assembly time. I used bone-in skinless thighs and  served with coleslaw and we really enjoyed it. I'm looking forward to trying it with skinless breasts. Thanks for posting the recipe.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: This is wonderful soup, probably the best I've made.  Subbed dried onion, about a tablespoon and a half since I was out of fresh.  Threw in some proscuitto (sp?) because I had some, but I think it would be equally good without.  I also had to use bouillon cubes and water since I'm out of broth...  shopping day is coming up.  Even with all the subs, this is fantastic...  Will double the recipe next time to have leftovers! Update:  We make this all the time now, and every time I have company they request the recipe.  Changes I've made: I add enough potatoes to just be covered by broth, so I don't measure.  I don't peel the potatoes, just cut into pieces.  I use Johnny's seasoning salt, which is wonderful.  After stirring in the cream cheese, I blend this with an immersion blender to break up the potatoes and mix the cream cheese all the way thru, then bring it back up to serving temp.  Garnish with shredded cheese, sour cream, bacon bits, and green onion as needed.  It's great with and without garnish.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: Delicious and easy!

name: blueberry oatmeal muffins
review: These muffins were very flavorful, but didn't hardly look like muffins.  They had a different texture than the usual muffin, but were good for being healthy.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: This was great! I was surprised that there was broth remaining, but it was so delicious! Very easy to make and a wonderful one-dish meal for a cold winter night.  Thanks for posting!

name: kale chips
review: Love the addition of vinegar.  Thankj you for posting.  I agree- 1-2 teaspoons of salt is quite alot and really not necessary.

name: double chocolate banana muffins
review: These muffins are EXCELLENT---MOIST and FLAVORFUL!!!  We loved them.  I did make a few changes, such as using only one cup of flour and adding 1/2 cup of rolled oats.  I also cut the sugar in half and cut the oil in half and replaced the other half with applesauce.  I did not use the chocolate chips, but instead put in diced dried plums.  I added some vanilla, too.  I also did as one reviewer suggested and put all liquid ingredients in the blender.  I will definitely make this again.

name: monterey chicken rolls
review: Really good, as all these reviews say.  The family love it!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Quick, easy, and delicious! I made it exactly as directed, and it turned out great! Both of my kids loved it. I bet it would be good with hamburger added, too! Thanks for the recipe!

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: Made for Zaar Cookbook tag game and what an tasty dish!   I did add a few bean spouts but otherwise followed the instructions.  The two pan method worked for me and I did use the oriental flavor ramen noodles.  Going into my Favorites of 2013.  P.S.  I did make recipe#45270#45270 to top the noodles.

name: healthy honey oatmeal cookies
review: This is a great cookie!  I volunteer at a Christian Academy and made these cookies to share with the kids. They all loved them!  I live in Costa Rica, so it's always very warm - I didn't get out the mixer but just let the butter come to room temp and used a spoon for the whole process. Easy!!!  Like other reviewers, I did cut back on the brown sugar and only used about 1/4 cup - they were plenty sweet. However, I rolled the cookies in cinnamon sugar before  placing on the cookie sheet and flattening slightly with a glass. Used raisins as the add-in.  Next time, will try substituting half the honey with agave syrup and will use craisins instead of raisins.  Thanks for posting such a versatile recipe - it's going in my favorites!

name: lemon baked cod
review: The sauce was really nice.  However, the flour coating just ended up like paste while baking in the oven in the lemon butter sauce.

name: tilapia
review: I did not have lemon juice maybe a 1 teaspoon vinegar OR 1 teaspoon white wine OR 1 teaspoon lime juice or 1 tablespoon other citrus juice, Pineapple will work too. I went ahead and made it to recipe anyway, and it turned out fine. I did it With Pineapple juice. Prep time was less than 5 minutes . THANK YOU for the a fine recipe !!!

name: best baked potato
review: OMG!  That was soooooo easy!  And they were delicious!  I never make baked potatoes in the oven because they always seemed so involved with the foil and all....so I always just did the microwave version.....NEVER again!!  These were sooooo good and soooooo easy!  Thank you for posting!  This is AWESOME!!!!

name: big thicket chicken and dumplings
review: The chicken and gravy in this were delicious, but the dumplings were really doughy and heavy.  I will make this again but use mini biscuits instead.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: I let the pork cook overnight and in the morning added my favourite homemade BBQ sauce and let cook another 2 hours. Delicious and couldn't be easier. Thanks for sharing!

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: Good but a little dry. Next time I would double the sauce (but not quite double the beans). Easy and quicky vegetarian dinner, thanks!

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Make this rave review #890. These were absolutely fantastic. And now I'm a convert to the 'make your own meatballs' crowd. I'm not sure why I wasn't before. I think it's because I was subconsciously holding out for this recipe. I followed it to the letter, with the minor exception of adding in about 6 large leaves of fresh basil that I chopped up (I LOVE fresh basil). I started them in the oven for about 20 minutes and then finished them off simmering in the sauce. Thanks for the recipe. I'll be making this again, and again, and again. The leftovers will be for meatball sandwiches later this week.

name: fabulous beef stew
review: Super recipe...quick to put together and fabulous taste...I used the smaller can of tomatoes as suggested by some of the other reviewers...we didn't have any leftovers...thanks for sharing this...it's a keeper.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Yummy yummy! I used ditali pasta and instead of buttered bread crumbs I just sprayed non-cook spray over the top of the bread crumbs after I put them on and they browned nicely.

name: classic pie crust  idiot proof step by step photo tutorial
review: I made this pie crust using all butter.  I was using it for the top of a chicken pot pie and did not have time to let it get cold before rolling it out.  In this case it still worked out wonderfully and tasted delicious.  I look forward to trying it for an actual pie next.

name: slow cook down home pork chops and gravy
review: My hubby put this together before we left for work this morning.  When he came home for lunch and checked on the crock pot, he was surprised to find the chops already pretty much done.  So by the time I came home four hours later, they were definitely off-the-bone tender.  Due to our needing to cook these longer than the recipe indicates, I needed to add a little water to loosen up the the gravy; as it was a little too thick.  I served these chops with brown rice and baby peas.  This was definitely a country-style, hearty meal.  :)  I can certainly understand why this recipe is so highly rated and has had so many reviews.  We will be enjoying this recipe many more times, I'm sure.  Thanks for sharing your recipe, Buttercup!

name: tzatziki
review: Great recipe!  I used a bit less olive oil, and it was just right.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: 2/2/13 Crazy good and so easy. I used Frank's Red Hot Original hot sauce. Thanks for posting WhoDat. Made for Best of 2012. UPDATE: 2/19/13 Made a 2nd time and decided that we will make using drumettes next time. Still loving this!  I boiled the ahead of time and stuck them back in the fridge until dinner time. Snipped the wing tips off so they would not burn under the broiler. Brushed the Frank's hot sauce on each win rather than dipping. Got a photo this time too :D   Made for Best of 2012 Tag game!

name: vanilla scented granola
review: Very good.  Made as written.  The kids have been eating this with yogurt.  Great after school snack.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: EXCELLENT meal!  This was my first time making pot pie and it was so worth it!  I had to stop myself from eating seconds and thirds.  We had meat from a pork roast we had smoked and that is the meat I used.  I also made a homemade pie crust (recipe # 26205) to put on top.  Other than that, I made as directed.  I will make this again and again.  Thank you for an awesome recipe.

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: Definitely a keeper. I will use tinfoil over the dish, as it dried out a bit, removing the foil about 15 minutes before the end of cooking time. Thank you for sharing.

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: Wonderful, wonderful! I used refried beans instead of black beans. Probably didn't look as nice, but still delicious! (omitted the cilantro)

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: Thanks for the recipe... I loved the texture.  I used 1/4 tsp baking powder and my husband detected an "odd flavor".  I'm going to try again using 1/8 tsp... then I'll rate again.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: I have only one comment.. yuck!

name: lentil soup for people who thought they hated lentils    meat op
review: Fantastic flavour and so easy. I made this by using a 19oz can of spicy tomatoes and ommitted the fresh tomato and tomato paste. As I was out of mushrooms, I left them out too, but my goodness this was good and it made so much. What a wonderful soup so packed full of flavour. Thank you for the recipe.

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review: This was really good! I didn't have onion gravy mix so I used a packet of onion soup mix (Lipton's), and it was delicious! The meat was so tender you could cut it with a fork. Served over wide rgg noodles. Thanks for posting!

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: This soup is delicious and easy to make.  I made a few changes because I didn't have some of the ingredients--such as subbing okra for green beans--but I left it mostly the same.  I am looking forward to eating it for lunch tomorrow.

name: pumpkin cake bars with cream cheese frosting
review: Nice pumpkin bars!!!  I made this as a dessert when DD and her friend were home from college for a long weekend and for my DS's girlfriend's Birthday.  I did add some ginger and cloves to the cake mix and then added 1/2 tsp of cinnamon to the cream cheese frosting, yummy!!!  Thanks for sharing the recipe.  Made for "Best of 2012" Tag game.

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: Wanted a fast and easy ground beef recipe...this fit the bill...am very glad we tried this...it was really a pleasant surprise and we all enjoyed it...thanks for sharing.

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: After following the directions precisely, these were delicious and my husband won't stop raving about them!  The only change I would make is to follow reviewer Greg's suggestions of partially cooking, then draining the fat before adding the sauce.  Be very careful not to overcook; the first time I made them I overcooked the sauce and it was inedible! Made properly, this sauce would be great over many different types of foods.

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: Beyond amazing!  Perfectly tender, juicy and phenomenal flavor. I added some garlic because I love it and used fresh thyme, sage and rosemary.  This is company worthy but so easy!

name: awesome slow cooker pot roast
review: This is similar to a pot roast I made many years ago, wrapped in foil and slow cooked in the oven.  This recipe lends itself well to that method, only using the crockpot which makes it even easier.  First I lined my slow cooker with heavy duty foil, leaving enough overhang to seal after the liquids are added.  I used dry red wine instead of water, and microwaved it for about 5 minutes on high to  burn off much of the alcohol, then dissolved one can of golden mushroom soup, the dry onion soup mix, and about a teaspoon of Better than Bouillon Au Jus Base, which I then poured on top of the roast and sealed the foil tightly.  I slow cooked on high for one hour, then turned it down to low for 7-8 hours.

name: beef barley soup
review: This is one of the BEST things that has ever come out of my crock pot!  I replaced the frozen veggies with some turnip and mushrooms, and dissolved all the tasty fond from the skillet into the water before adding it in.  I didn't have time to do the extra-slow cooking, so I set it at high and hoped for the best.  It was ready to eat in 3 hours and both the pearl barley and beef were well cooked and tender.  DH told me to hold on to this recipe... sure sign of a real success!

name: the ultimate strawberry shortcake
review: Yes please!  This is most certainly the ultimate shortcake. I used homemade pound cake in place of angel food but otherwise made as directed. This ones going in the keeper file.

name: ww 5 can soup
review: This was good! We had it for Lent. I added some Parmesan Cheese and sir racha in it.

name: 100  whole grain wheat bread
review: This made 2 beautiful light loaves.  I was worried after the first rising as it didn't look like any dough I have ever used before but turned out great.

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: Lovely flavor and they were fairly crispy.  A bit overdone at 30 minutes plus 10.

name: garlic panko chicken strips
review: Delicious tenders!  Meal prep was so simple...love it when I can cook a nice, hot meal for my family with little fuss and great taste.  These tenders taste great on their own - no sauce needed.    Like other reviewers, I had trouble getting them to brown, but this was not a deal breaker, as I would mos def make these again.  I served with Recipe #83524 and mac n' cheese.  Awesome lunch - thank you!

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: So good and easy.  I will cut back on the Dijon next time as I felt it was a little strong but other than that it was perfection!!  Thanks,

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Oh these were good!  I used red potatoes since that's what I had but they're softer so I think next time I'll use russets so they'll crisp up more.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review:
It was a little too sweet for us, but had a good flavor.
Update: made again, and used only 3 C powdered sugar and 1 T 1/2 and 1/2. Turned out great!

name: roasted broccoli w lemon garlic   toasted pine nuts
review: Good but lemon is not that great on broccoli for us. | used frozen organic broccoli florets, light tasting extra virgin olive oil, sea salt, no butter to be dairy free just additional olive oil, organic garlic clove, good quality (fresh tasting) walnuts I toasted in a dry frying pan instead of pine nuts as that is what I had on hand (loved them), plus the rest of the ingredients, although possibly no pepper as I may not have had it when I made this recipe and the problem with this site is my reviews were not showing so I didn't write this immediately afterwards. Made for Healthy Choices Tag Game 2013.

name: my no roll pie crust
review: I tried it and this was fabulous.  Easy and not messy.  Thanks for sharing.

name: thai chicken breasts
review: I love this chicken!  The sauce is perfect, and the sliced snow peas are a perfect, refreshing garnish.

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: This was super easy to make in my Kitchenaid mixer. The bread rose well and looked beautiful when baked. The texture was perfect - a good crust and soft and airy on the inside. The only issue I had was that it did not have a lot of flavour, as another reviewer has pointed out. Maybe more sugar or salt is needed?

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review:
Because I am not a wing eater, I will give you my DH's take on this recipe. He proclaimed this 5 stars all the way. While he felt that the wings could have a little more kick in the spice department, it was certainly not a deal breaker (or a review star taker). In his words, "They are juicy and awesome and a definite DO AGAIN!"*** (**Must add that DH reviewed these after having warmed them up in the microwave the day after I baked them. He never tried them fresh out of the oven--so I imagine that these are even more fantastic freshly prepared.)

Now, as a wing maker, I can tell you that this could not be easier to make and I found that the wings crisped up very nicely under the broiler. The sauce was easy peasy to make as well. After it cooled down slightly from the microwave, I simply dumped the sauce and wings into a ziploc and shook to coat. Thanks for a great go-to wing recipe.

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: This is exactly what we want in a chocolate chip cookie. Perfect tasting and perfect looking. Thanks so much for sharing this keeper recipe!

name: reduced fat alfredo sauce
review: I've made this twice now. The first time, I let the milk mixture thicken too much, which made the "sauce" pretty floury and almost, stiff, for lack of a better word. This time, with that experience to work on, I barely let the milk sit at all before adding the cheese. (This could have something to do with the fact that I'm cooking on a gas stove.) Now that I know how to do it right, this recipe is really easy, simple, and tasty. Thank you!

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: I didn't have any problems with the reduction as many reported, it turned out very nice. Served with scalloped potatoes and steamed asparagus.  My 7 year old took some of the extra sauce and put it on her aspargus, she really liked it a lot! Thanks for sharing.

name: croutons
review: My husband and I made these tonight. They were really easy and came out really well. Thank you!

name: poverty meal
review: This was a staple when I was in college. We always used canned whole tomatoes, though, which we crushed by hand; a good bit more garlic; and some herbs for a little more flavor. Probably made this once a week. So good!

name: uncle bill s green split pea with hambone soup
review: 5 stars all the way around the table!  I have always prided myself in my split pea soup (our ingredients are near identical) but this method will now replace mine.  I am convinced that soaking the dried peas in the hot water for 1 hour (w/o seasonings) makes a HUGE difference. This soup is much smoother in consistency than any other split pea soup I have had or made.  I used chicken broth, more thyme as pinches can vary, no beef bouillon cuz I forgot, and a smoked butt. I have always used a stick blender at the end, that said, this soup blended up smoother, no kidding! My husband could not stop praising this soup. I'm so glad we have some leftover for lunch today. YUM!  My recipe is now out the window and this recipe is replacing it. Thanks for sharing this gem, Uncle Bill!

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: Very nice marinade.  Everyone enjoyed it.  Used far less oil.

name: thai chicken breasts
review: We really enjoyed this dish!  Full of great flavor... I will be making again!  Thanks for sharing!

name: impossible peanut butter cookies
review: These cookies are so easy to do.  And the taste is so good.  It's hard to eat just one.  Thanks Mysterygirl :)  Made for Holiday tag game

name: lemon tea cookies
review: I made this once as written. After a search for a real good recipes to do. And with resulted in other similar recipes, I decided I wanted to create something unique a great base recipe and easy to modify depending on your tastes.. It may be a stretch to call my creation, but the result was a meal the whole family will liked. MY was Not better, not worse, just different ! I've will added this to my recipe book "AS IS" and with my additions TOO. I have two way to do it!! THANK YOU!! I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! I can't leave anything alone! THANK YOU!! ALWAYS READ THE RECIPE IN FULL BEFORE YOU START, then read the reviews. I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! You get good Tips and Hints or two, to Note there. There are some great chefs here on Zaar, and she's one of the best!  O Yes I use jelly bean, like jelly belly, put 2-3 bean in the center and have a Gourmet cookie, I love these cookies I make them every the kids come over.

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: A cinch to prepare.  I did not eat this, but my son who LOVES salmon wolfed it down and said it tasted like a dish you'd find in a 5 star restaurant.  Served w/ couscous and braised spinach.    I did not have pineapple so I subbed fresh juiced orange in place of.  <br/>Might add a touch of ginger next time. One more thing--I baked this in a 400 overn for approx 10-15 minutes (without turning).  I just made the sauce as directed and poured over salmon in a baking dish.

name: tilapia al ajillo  garlic tilapia
review: Delicious!  I was surprised at the depth of flavor I got from such an easy, uncomplicated dish.  I really watched my garlic and put it on top of the fish as suggested once it was golden brown, and really enjoyed this.  I'll definitely make this recipe again.  Thanks for sharing!  Made for Zaar Cookbook Tag.

name: ciabatta  italian slipper bread
review: This was easy to make, although time consuming while waiting for the dough to rise. I thought the taste was pretty good, though mine wasn't as airy as other people's.

name: poverty meal
review: Made as is. Even my picky children ate it.

name: vanilla scented granola
review: This granola is AWESOME!  I love the vanilla flavor.  I used whole almonds since I didn't have sliced ones.  I also added raisins to the dry mixture.  I used 1/4 tsp cinnamon (instead of 1/8) and 2 tbsp vanilla (instead of 4 tsp).  It was delicious and I will definitely make it again and again and again.

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: Great technique, they really did crisp up. Thanks!

name: orange julius smoothies
review: Edible, but not good.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: This was pretty good but I would have liked a precise measurement for the salt, as I had no idea how much I should use, and as a result, my cauliflower wasn't terribly flavourful.

name: corned beef and cabbage in guinness
review: Excellent.  Followed recipe as written.  The Guinness and soaking and rinsing the beef made this dish!  The spices were just perfect.

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: This chicken was so, so easy to make!  I made two chicken leg quarters and sprinkled very generously with garlic salt before adding Kikoman's soy sauce.  I had to bake my leg quarters for 1 1/2 hours at 350° to get them cooked all the way through.  I also poked the chicken all over with a fork before placing the garlic and soy sauce.  My husband and I both enjoyed this and it will be my go to quick chicken recipe from now on.  I made this for Zaar Alphabet Soup Tag.

name: kittencal s  brown sugar caramel sauce or ice cream topping
review: Delicious and easy!  I made this to top a tres leches cake and it was wonderful.  My husband said it tasted just like mexican caramel.

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: Well this recipe, does not need any more reviews....but I had to put my 2 cents in.  Outstanding!  Best soda bread I have ever had!  It sure beats the recipe I have used for years.....I was out of caraway seeds, darn it.  This will be made often!

name: amy sedaris s vanilla cupcakes
review: My daughter made these cup cakes and they were outstanding, some of the best I have ever tasted! She opted to make a different icing, so I can't comment on icing, but for sure we will be making the cup cakes again.

name: n  y  c  corned beef and cabbage
review: Two things. First, love the addition of Harp as it truly tenderized the meat. This was the first time ever I could eat corned beef without a knife. Second, the twist on the potatoes was fantastic! Everyone commented on how good they were, so thank you very much.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: I made this and it was gone in a flash, so much so that I wasn't able to photo it. It was really good. The family says this is not a 4 person meal for a normal serving. They vote you double it. I will next time. TIP:  I used an 8x8 pan and it was perfectly layered. The ingredients were fresh and flavorful. I used a fresh salsa instead of a jar. TIP: when you take the meat mixture out of the pan after mixing with water and taco seasoning drain the meat to make the layer and later no soggy chips! I served with a mexican salad on the side. Thanks for posting Leilani. This Taste of Home recipe hit the spot. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Fabulous recipe! Made tonight to go with Greek Chicken Kabobs, yum! Used redskins, extra garlic and the mediteranian oregano. Definitely a keeper recipe to be made often.

name: utterly deadly southern pecan pie
review: Absolutely the best pecan pie recipe I've ever used. Not too sweet and sets up perfectly. I've made it many times now, and not once had a single issue. Make sure to strain the filling mixture. It's very difficult to stop the eggs from cooking when you first start tempering them. You'll be much more pleased with the end result if you don't skip that step. Thanks so much, PCrocker!

name: bread machine cinnamon buns
review: Huge hit in our house!  Thank you!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: Easy and fast.  However, it's very similar to the Costco chickens and that' even easier.

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: I really enjoyed these cookies. I made each cookie 1.1 ounces and baked them for 12 minutes in a convection oven.  I will make these again.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Keeper recipe and so easy to do.  Mine only needed 30 minutes in the oven and they were perfect.  Thank you for sharing this recipe.

name: strawberries   cream bread  strawberry or blueberry
review: I made this with blueberries and it was moist and delicious.  I used all applesauce in place of the butter to save calories and fat, but other than that made as directed.  It was wonderful and I cannot wait to make it again.  Thanks for sharing.

name: the best banana bread
review: Great banana bread, I just didn't see the note to adjust the time down when making two loaves. So mine were a little brown. Otherwise they would have been really stellar.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Good not great. I covered and baked for 45 minutes, still were a little dry. And I would prefer a sauce that is thicker than water.

name: mile high cabbage pie  5fix
review: I was disappointed  after reading all the great reviews. The simply Potatoes were under cooked . If there is ne thing I hate it's half raw potatoes. I think the dish could use a little liquid of some kind.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Fantastic!  My husband took one bite and declared this "miracle chicken!  I'm not sure what you did to it, but it's so juicy and you should always make it like this."  I'm not sure what that says about all the other ways I make chicken, so I'm on the fence whether to be flattered or offended.  ;-)  My almost 5 year old ate this and actually moaned with every bite, so it's a winner here.  I used a homemade mayo that was mostly olive oil based (too strong for spreading, but great in recipes to my tastes), and probably had a little less than a cup in the bowl.  After mixing this up, I just dumped it in a bowl with my chicken and coated it before putting it in a pan and topping with the remaining mayo mixture.  Cooked up perfectly in my convection oven set 50' under temp, but running the full time in the recipe.  Thanks for sharing. UPDATE:  This is also fantastic on catfish.

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: I used this recipe as a base. Husband loved this and asked me to write down what I did so there is hope to make it again... If you hate when people do this - stop reading.  If you want ideas ... I cooked 1lb ground beef with a medium onion diced, 1 large seeded and deveined jalapeno.  I then added 7 tsp taco seasoning (recipe fr this site) and 3/4 C water.  Boiled a bit to get most of the water out and flavor in.  Then added a large can green chile's (6 oz?) and a mostly drained can of Rotel tomatoes and chile's.  I then added about 1/2 the bag of low fat cheese to the meat mixture - took it off the heat.  I used microwaved flour tortillas (about 10 sec 4 times - flipping and splitting the tortillas ea time) 1/2 the green enchilada sauce on bottom of pan (NOTE:  spray pan with EVOO or pam before beginning next time) and 1/2 can on top of enchiladas and then rest (1/2) of low fat cheese on the top.  Bake for 20 min and then add arugula and lf sour cream on top.

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: good coleslaw!!<br/>Easy recipe and tasty!! Will use this as my go-to recipe.

name: company pork roast
review: I made this exactly as written and it smelled marvellous while cooking.  The flavour was okay but the meat really dried out even though I basted it every 25 minutes or so. I would double the sauce if I was to make it again and reduce the pepper a bit. Thanks.

name: funky chicken with sesame noodles
review: Awesome! Halved the recipe, used angel hair pasta. Made with leftover rabbit. Made noodles and let sit. Mixed up marinade and put in chopped up meat, let sit out about 30 minutes, then heated to boiling. Poured off marinade. Heated up noodles a little in the microwave and served.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I covered these before baking - seared them first.  Very tender!  It was a little sweet for us - maybe cut back on the honey next time.  I doubled the sauce.

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: Delicious, and a hit at our supper club recently.  Only changes:  I subbed a yellow bell pepper, both for extra color, and because I'm not a big fan of the green kind.  Also threw in some chopped marinated artichoke hearts.

name: chinese pot stickers
review: yummy!!!!! Had the 10 year old ask what potstickers were.... she took a bite and I said they're pretty good aren't they? She replied with NO! They're awesome!! Whole family loved better than the chinese restaurant. Only difference we had was used some of the ginger from a tube. Worked out great! Can't wait until leftover time!! :)

name: lucky sweet and sour sauce
review: Pretty good! may puree some pineapple up and add it to sauce next time. just for a little more of a sweet taste. thanks!

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: Definately a yummy recipe.  I do wish there was a more specific measurement on the potatoes, as they can really vary in size.  I used 3 large russets and that seemed like plenty to me.  Also when it was finished there was still a lot of water in the bottom of the skillet which I drained off.  Next time I will use less.  I left the skins on the potatoes, subbed in a Mediterranean Herb Chedder that we had and served with fried eggs and toast for a breakfasty type supper.

name: mexican stack up  rsc
review: I made this for dinner tonight, trying to use up things in the fridge. I used reduced fat cheeses, a pack of veggie grounds of the ground beef, sweet onion for the green onion, canned corn, and a whole can of black beans.I also didn't have chives, so I had to leave them off  The only problem had was with the foil. It didn't stay tented and the cheese ended up sticking to it.  When I uncovered the dish I got as much cheese off of the foil as I could and just set it back on top before putting it back in the oven.  The entire family enjoyed this.  It was very filling, enough for two meals! I served it with the rest of the can of corn and re-fried beans.

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Loved these, and really love that they are low fat. I actually couldn't believe there was no oil or butter in the recipe.  They are moist and very banana-y (yes I made that word up). These were cooked at the 24 minute mark in my oven so watch carefully.  Thanks Manda!

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: Love the flavorful BBQ sauce - I could see this being great in a slow-cooker too.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: This soup is so delicious.  We loved the addition of the ham.  Thanks for posting this wonderful recipe.

name: low fat banana bread
review: Absolutely delicious, moist and wonderful.  This is just as good (if not better) than my regular recipe which has a lot more calories and fat.  Great banana flavour and it is still moist three days after I made it.  I did add a few choc chips for my son but other than that, followed as written. Thanks a bunch.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: Delicious! Everything about this recipe was great. The cookie by itself was soft and great tasting. The icing was easy to put together and was nice to work with. Shiny finish, dries hard, smooth surface. I loved this recipe. The bake time was perfect, the cookies rolled out great. This is a keeper. Thanks so much!

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: I gave this recipe 5 stars just because it's easy, it's forgiving (if you don't alter the given cooking technique).  I prepared this for last night's dinner, and had plenty to have again tonight.  I didn't use the rub to slow cook them in.  I used the barbeque sauce I was going to end with.  While baking in foil, I did include the rub ingredients in with the BBQ sauce.  Of course, by the time you have completed the cooking in the foil packets, you have essentially boiled the ribs anyway, and the rub/bbq sauce has permeated the meat.  I drained them after cooking, lined another pan with heavy duty aluminum foil anb proceeded under the broiler.  This really made the ribs.  They were tender, easy to separate to eat, and were just saucy enough to kinda make a mess.  I loved them!  And, I have a few left over to put into the freezer for another quick meal!  I am very pleased with how this method turned out, and will definitely use it again.

name: mile high cabbage pie  5fix
review: I had to make this recipe as it seems like there is a new review for it almost every day!  It was pretty good, but I was hoping for more based on the other 100+ great reviews.  I think this needs more liquid of some type, definitely some seasonings, and my potatoes were only half-cooked, so that was a bit disappointing.  Otherwise we enjoyed the recipe and would try it again with modifications.  Thanks for posting your recipe!

name: perfect rump roast
review: While rump roast is generally a pretty dry and unappealing thing, I bought one because it was on sale.  I gave this cooking method a try and was pleasantly surprised.  The low cooking temp made the majority of the interior stay nicely pink - medium rare - while the exterior was nicely crusty.  That's the way we like it.  I only let my roast sit out about 1 hour, so it was not quite room temperature, but I don't think that affected the outcome too much.  I seasoned my roast with a spice mixture called Essence (by Emeril).  I skipped putting anything except the garlic in the slits, being unsure about how to get the seasoning into the slits.  I think just salt and pepper would have been fine, but you could really use any seasoning you like.  I did use  low sodium beef broth and added the leftover broth plus onions into a jar of canned gravy, and it really made that a tasty addition to the meat.

name: the best chili you will ever taste
review: I'm sorry, but I honestly don't understand the number of good reviews for this recipe. I expected a lot from it, but to me it tastes exactly like it started as canned pork and beans. It is just too sweet. I used only half the brown sugar called for because we were worried that would be the case, but it is still way too sweet from the brown sugar, chili sauce( which is glorified ketchup), and tomato paste. If you have a sweet tooth, this is definitely the recipe for you. If you want a rich, authentic chile flavor, find a more traditional recipe that uses toasted and pureed chile peppers, which will have the flavor notes of coffee and beer. This recipe also makes a huge amount, much more than 6 or 8 servings, so now I have a freezer full of it. Sorry, but it doesn't work for me.

name: beef patties in onion gravy
review: This is a very good recipe and so easy to fix.  It is great served with mashed potatoes. Thanks for posting.

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Used for a lasagna recipe. Thank you!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This is a good base recipe, but it definitely needs tweaked to be made more to our liking.  I followed the recipe to the letter this time and we found that it was very, very bland.  If I make this again, I will definitely spice the chicken up and use hot salsa.  Also I will add canned chiles.  It was a decent recipe, just not a favorite in our household.  UPDATE: Made again 2/13/13 and used a 24 oz jar of Great Value Hot Salsa and stirred in cooked rice just before serving and this tasted much better.  Our family likes things a little spicy, so the hot salsa and the extra quantity really helped to make this something we can enjoy often.  Thanks Jen.<br/>UPDATE: Made for a third time on 3/30/13 and used a homemade salsa from this site ( Recipe #485128 ) and the recipe was sooooooo much better.  I am even bumping the star rating from 3 to 4.  I want to love this recipe so much because it is so easy, but it still needs a little more work.  I will continue to tweak it on days when I need crock pot meals.  Thanks again Jen.

name: jalapeo bites
review: My son made these for Easter and they were awesome!!! We used panko crumbs too!

name: awesome baked ham
review: Awesome! The ham was so moist! I baked mine in a roaster. Worked great and freed up the oven!

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: This was good, but I had a problem with lumps too.  I mixed the flour into a water slurry too.  I will continue to try until I get it right because the flavor was great.  I made mine using beef broth.

name: easy cole slaw
review: Good and very easy. I'm not a dressing fan, so would use 1 1/2-2 times cabbage next time. Make sure to make a little ahead. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: I don't know why, but I followed the directions to a T and ours came out with a metallic taste.  I baked it in a glass 9x13 baking dish, so I know it wasn't a taste from the pan.  Also all of my ingredients were new, so it wasn't because of old products.  I had such high hopes for this cake, but it just didn't fill the bill.  I hope others continue to have better luck than I did with this cake.

name: kittencal s best deviled eggs
review: Loved the flavor of these deviled eggs.  I made half a dozen eggs and just modified the recipe accordingly.  I admit these eggs are more for adult tastes -- but you can still make a batch for the kids the way they like them -- laden with pickle relish, etc.  Will definitely make this recipe again.  Thanks for the post.

name: world s best cinnamon raisin bread  not bread machine
review: Wow! I have to say this is awesome. BUT...  first... I have to mention that I used JUMBO eggs....  so then needed to add more flour. My dough was really sticky and I really wondered if I'd made a mistake. Well....    this bread turned out really well...   I mean.. GREAT....  I added some almond extract and vanilla to the dough...  and the extra sugar/ brown sugar and more salt as others have suggested. ... Plus... I doubled the raisins. It's really a great recipe. Thanks so much Lydia Holton. I started another batch this morning only using two jumbo eggs and using Craisins.  UPDATE: The two jumbo eggs and Craisins turned out wonderful. Oh ... can't wait to try other variations! Maybe some orange zest and nuts? ... or how about strawberry preserves in the filling with a streusel topping?

name: emeril s essence
