review: On 4/1/13 I was making Recipe #170376 by Sandi (From CA),and didn't have any Essence.I did a quick search and found this recipe and decided to try it.Now I've never tried the original Essence,so I can't really compare it. But it added a very good taste to the hash.Thanks for posting a recipe that will find its way into many of my recipes. " Keep Smiling :) "

name: neiman marcus  250 chocolate chip cookies recipe
review: I made these to take on our vacation with us.  These were a big hit with all the kids.  I made them into big cookies, but they were cooked perfectly.  I loved them, as did all who tried them.  Thank you for sharing with us.  Delicious.

name: thick  soft  and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: What a delicious cookie recipe.  I made these for our vacation and my family gobbled them up.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: olive garden garlic alfredo sauce
review: Very creamy and delicious.  I served this with grilled chicken and a salad.  Thank you for this easy sauce recipe.

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: This is hearty tasty soup.  I did add some mild Italian sausage to this and it was delicious.  I served this with some crusty French bread.  thank you for sharing with us.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: Although I made some substantial changes based on personal preferences and suggestions from other reviewers, this was definitely the best and most moist carrot cake I've ever had. I reduced the oil to 1/2 cup and added a cup of apple sauce. I removed the pineapple and replaced it with 2 heaping tablespoons of marmelade. I replaced the walnuts with pecans. I also reduced the sugar to 1 cup. I baked it in one round cake pound for 45 minutes and it was just right. The frosting was perfect although I did have a little excess.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: For a carrot cake I am sure it's 5 star but as for just a cake I am giving it 4stars. It's good but I am not dying for more. I omitted the nuts since it was for my one year olds birthday cake.  I reduced then sugar to 1&1/4 cups. I added 1/2tsp nutmeg and 1/8of all spice. I did add 1/2 cup of tea soaked golden raisins soaked for 15min or so. I soaked the coconut in hot water for about the same.  I used half the oil 1/2 cup apple sauce. The icing I added 1/2tsp vanilla and zested a small orange. If I make again I will not do raisins not a big fan. I loved the orange zest in the icing!

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Perfect and easy in a pinch. . .when a recipe calls for Teriyaki and you have none in the fridge!!!  I made it as written except I subbed out stevia for the sugar.  YUM!  UPDATE:  I just used up the rest of the sauce atop grilled salmon and it was DY-NO-MITE!  A keeper for sure.  My husband said, "Don't put any of that sauce on my salmon.  I don't normally like Teriyaki" and then he proceeded to put a dollop on each bite of fish. . . .hummm. .. I think he liked it!

name: excellent carrot cake
review: This is amazing.  The glaze adds so much richness to the cake, its so good.  We could have eaten it with the glaze only, but, why not add the frosting.  Thank you for sharing this with us, its a wonderful addition to anyones files.

name: homemade hamburger buns  bread machine
review: This has been my go-to hamburger bun recipe! So easy to put together, and the buns come out beautifully: soft on the inside, yet nice and sturdy. I used AP flour mixed with wheat gluten to substitute the bread flour. (#416294 is a great substitute) I use a little less sugar than called for, and I don't use a cutter; I just divide the dough by hand and usually out with around 12-14 good sized buns. Mine usually take around 15-18 minutes at 350. It's good to keep an eye on them. Wonderful recipe; thanks so much!

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: Good dish!  I made as written but also threw some avocado chunks on top.  This was great for me to make and leave for my husband to throw in the oven when he was alone with the kids for dinner.  Thanks Leilani....

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: I love this!  Most of the chicken breading comes off when you try to flip the chicken, but I LOVE the breading.  May be better with no capers, and the sauce doesn't translate great to a pasta sauce--probably best to just pour it over the chicken.

name: thai coconut rice
review: Not amazing, but edible.

name: banana oatmeal bread
review: I used 4 bananas in this. I made it for my family and they all loved it. Just the right amount of sweetness.

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: Delicious! Definitely the best if you take them out of the oven while still a little jiggly; (browned top). They cool to a firm but chewy bar- not crisp.

name: jalapeno popper burgers
review: This was good. Next time I'll bump up the seasonings. I cooked them nice and slow on the grill and they were perfectly cooked.

name: vanilla scented granola
review: Delicious! I didn't stir at all until it had cooled for about 5 minutes and I got some great chunks of granola (my favourite part of granola!). Tastes great and so easy to make. I did use about a cup of shredded coconut instead of some of the oats, but otherwise stuck to the recipe.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: Very delicious soup.  I try to eat less carb so I skipped the tortellini but I followed the rest of the recipe exactly.  My family loves this too. Thank you Spatchcock.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Excellent.  I chose this recipe because I wanted to bring a dish to Easter that could be eaten by everyone including people with a milk allergy and/or wheat allergy.  Everyone really enjoyed it.  Thanks for posting. I will be making it again!

name: moist and tender turkey  or turkey breast
review: The meat was very moist and flavourful but the skin didn't crisp up for me which was a bit disappointing.  I turned the heat up as indicated when I thought the meat would be almost done, but I had to increase the temp yet again, as it still didn't reach the correct internal temperature. So I upped it more and cooked another 20 minutes til it was done. I would try this again but start out with a higher temperature and see if I get a crispy skin.  I know you shouldn't eat the skin but let's face it, it is the best part.  Thanks for the recipe!

name: strawberry shortcake a la treebeard s
review: The shortcakes were very good (though I made them by hand and not in the food processor) and they strawverry filling was great (though I ended up slicing all of the strawberries and not following the directions).  Where I had issues was the amount of filling.  I made a half batch of the shortcake as four cakes and a full batch of the strawberries--and I really only had enough strawberries for three shortcakes.  I think I will make this again, but for me, it will be with half again as many berries for half of the shortcake.  Thanks for a good recipe!

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: Loved it!

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: We used your marinade recipe on some T-bones we had the other day.  This marinade makes them even more tender and delicious.  We used our normal steak seasoning on them and grilled for a delicious dinner.  Thank you very much Kittencal for this great recipe.  I loved the balsalmic vinegar in this.

name: vanilla scented granola
review: I made this for brunch yesterday and it made the house smell heavenly while baking.  We served this with some milk but I'm going to top some yogurt today with us.  Its flavorful and delicious.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: jalapeno popper burgers
review: Pretty good, although I had to broil mine as we do not have a grill (and it's cold in Chicago anyway!)  The burgers also leaked a lot of cheese out, but I probably overstuffed them.  I topped the patties with pico de gallo and diced avocados- quie tasty.

name: all purpose stir fry sauce  brown garlic sauce
review: This is so good.  I made this to top some fried chicken chunks and fried rice.  It was so good.  The flavor was outstanding.  We will use this for all kinds of dishes.  thank you for sharing with us.

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: These were excellent.  I made them in the morning and got ready to grill and realized we were out of charcoal.  I then broiled them and they turned out nice.  These stay juicy and are full of flavor.  I served them with some Thai rice and a veggie.  Thank you for this great recipe, I can't  wait to try them on the grill.

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: What a hearty filling meal this was.  The flavor was spot on to what I expect from stew.  My family loved it, I will add this to my list of regulars.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: Wonderful flavor & so quick & easy! Modified slightly based on what I had on hand. Used only 2 T. of butter, used 1 c. of milk instead of 2 c. of cream & so added 1/4 c. cream cheese. It tasted so good after adding the parmesan, that we didn't even stir in the mozzarella! We tossed in sauteed mushrooms & peas. Everyone loved it! Thank you!

name: perfect rump roast
review: Oh yum.  I made this and it turned out perfect.  It was cooked just the way I love it.  By adding the s&p and garlic cloves it flavored the meat so good.  Thank you for sharing with us your recipe.  We loved it.

name: mexican casserole   6 5 weight watcher points
review: Delicious casserole.  I served this with some spanich rice and a salad.  Thank you for sharing with us.  We loved this, good flavor.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: This is a nice and thick chili.  I used all the seasoning mix in ours but otherwise followed your recipe.  We loved it.  I served it on top of bowls of fritos, topped with sour cream, cheddar cheese and chopped onions.  Delicious.  We then took the leftovers and served them on hot dogs the next day.  thank you so much for this chili recipe, we love a good thick chili, this was perfect.

name: reduced fat alfredo sauce
review: Very good sauce! I avoid alfredo sauce because it's so unhealthy and I never feel good after eating it. I thought I would give this a try and it turned out rich and creamy without it leaving me feeling weighed down. Looking forward to trying it to top spaghetti squash. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: Very nice sauce and easy too - loved the spiciness from the chili powder and the smokiness of the cumin.  Due to a gluten intolerance, I used 1 tablespoon of cornstarch instead of the 2 tablespoons of flour.  Thanks for posting this - will definitely use this again.

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: I read a lot of reviews and then looked at the photos of the recipe. I then miraculously managed to make this recipe exactly as I wanted it and looking like Jenny Sanders' photo. I used raw lentils and boiled them for 45 minutes until they were soft enough, I chopped my oats in a small chopper so that they were smaller pieces as they were not instant oats and I was worried about them cooking properly. Finally I added grated carrot, celery and lots of parsley and a bit of ketchup. The result was absolutely delicious but my kids wouldn't touch it so I felt I couldn't give the recipe 5 stars no matter how much I wanted to. This is a great recipe to play around with and adapt to your tastes and maybe when the kids are older I'll be able to convince them that this is awesome. :-)

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: pretty quick and super yummy! Baked chicken breasts and seasoned with mccormicks grill mates garlic and onion medley. seasoned with cracked black pepper and the garlic onion medley. usually have all ingredients on hand. thanks!! kids loved!!

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: The broth/gravy was thick and rich and had great flavour.  I added a touch of garlic when the minced onions were added. I also added about 1/2 C red wine and a dash of marjoram.  Great recipe that I will definitely make again.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Wonderful!  I used a can of tomatoes since I was out of fresh.  I also used a 4 oz can diced chiles in place of the jalapeno and a one pound bag of frozen corn that I cooked on the stove.  I omitted the olive oil because I didn't think it was needed.  I also cooked the brown rice with some coconut oil so I figured that was a good healthy fat.  I added a chopped avocado as I was serving it.  Delicious and easy!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: Best pork chops recipe so far! Great flavor! Frying time is much less than 5min per side; 3 minutes and they were too black for me. Also, I baked them less than the allotted time and still felt the pork was a little tough; not sure if it needed to be cooked longer or shorter...

name: company pork roast
review: Very nice recipe although I did think it was a bit salty. I did use less than half the salt <br/>for a double recipe. The meat is very flavorful and juicy and for that gave it 5 stars. The salt can be easily adjusted. I will make this one again with this very minor adjustment. Thanks for sharing your recipe.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: Outstanding!

name: best grilled pork chops
review: Great pork chops! I marinated 2 thick-cut chops in half of this recipe for about a day and a half. We grilled them, and even had to throw them back on the grill a few times, and they were still very juicy! We will be making these again! Thank you!

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: I guess I am in the minority here.  I just wasn't bowled over by this dish.  First off, I have nothing to compare it to, being I live in MX and the tortilla soup is totally different.  I omitted the carrot...had none and went with the optional tomato and otherwise followed the recipe.  I found it bland (Mexico's fault) and thought of re-naming it Chicken Tomato Tortilla Soup.   I do appreciate that the soup does not contain beans nor corn.....as the other recipes have.  I do want to thank you for the recipe. I did like the tortillas boiled in the broth!   I will take the boiled tortilla method and run with it!!!

name: olive garden garlic alfredo sauce
review: What's not to love? If you want a fattening fest this is the recipe for you! It was delicious, and like most of the reviewers we stepped up the cream cheese a lot. ( we added half a block). It still has that authentic taste, but was a LOT creamier than other alfredo's I have tried or made.

name: no bake granola bars
review: These are delicious!! I decided to try them out with 1/4 C. mini m & m's and 1/4 C. mini chocolate chips instead of raisins. I also subbed honey for the corn syrup and reduced the brown sugar to 1/3 C. packed. They were so simple and quick to make. My 3-year old loves to help me bake and cook so this was perfect for us!! Thanks for posting.

name: best low carb bread  bread machine
review: Wow!  A great recipe!  I doubled it for my 2# bread machine and substituted King Arthur's Organic Bread flour for the soy flour, otherwise made as directed.  The crust was chewy and insides soft. It had a kinda nutty flavor going on.   I toasted it and used in a Canadian Bacon, egg, and cheese sandwich.  Very tasty and filling.  I would highly recommend this for those craving bread and/or sandwiches yet still watching carbs.

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: My daughter made these for dinner and they were delicious!!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: This was great served with rice and a nice green veggie! Have made more than once. For two pork chops, I used a glass dish that was maybe 6x6 so I had great coverage. Be sure to serve with cooking sauce, yum is right.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: My 4.5 lb. chicken cooked in about 5.5 hours.  The rub imparted a good flavor to the meat.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: Made this with chicken- very good and easy.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Thanks for posting Sharlene! It was tasty and very well received. Absolutely all had seconds. I was wondering if the portions were spot on? Reason being that it serves 10-14 it says as of today and there is only one lb of pasta called for. I had to make another pound to serve that many but didn't need to make more sauce. So next time 2 lbs of spaghetti and this sauce as written. The slow simmer is great. The water is too much but I will likely do 1 cup or none next time. I simmered for 2.5-3 hours and there were watery plates. BUT it was so delicious. It got raves and raves.  You have a winner here. Thanks for sharing. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: This is a good recipe, and following it to exact, I can see that the mozzarella addition was grand, however, made it kinda gloppy. I had to keep it very warm and serve it right away so the cheesy factor (stringy) didn't mess with the dish. **(I might add no cheese or much less next time.) Thanks for posting delish dish!

name: turkey breakfast sausage patties
review: Very good.  I was surprised that the texture was so similar to breakfast sausage, and the flavor was definitely there as well.  I used 1 teaspoon of sage instead of 2 though.

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: These may be the best scrambled eggs I have ever eaten.  I loved how fluffy they were and the salt and pepper content was perfect.  I made 6 servings and served alongside sausage and Pancakes by Ellen Brody for dinner tonight.  Thank you for another great, easy recipe Kittencal.  UPDATE 4/15/13- I made these again tonight for dinner and they turned out really well again.  Last time I didn't have any cheddar cheese so I omitted that.  This time I had the cheese and everyone enjoyed them even more.  Many more thanks for this recipe Kittencal!

name: denny s style french toast
review: This french toast was awesome!  I am surprised that my kids didn't rave over it as much as I did.  It was plenty sweet; in fact it didn't need any extra powdered sugar or syrup in my opinion.  Very delicious!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Just made these tonight and they were delish!  I must be getting old because I didn't use the food processor, just did it the old-fashioned way. I also freeze my butter and grate it on the largest holes. My sis had hers with butter and honey, I had 1 with country gravy, then another with butter and preserves. (my dessert)  Thanks for posting!

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: Great recipe! DH Loves it and it makes a nice veg-based starch. I make it often with good aged cheddar and Colman's mustard. I use 1 1/4 cups of milk and 2 cups of sharp cheddar, 3 Tbs butter and flour, 1/4 cup bread crumbs (the conversion function on this site is terrible, so this is for future reference :) Thanks French Tart, your recipes are all FAB!

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: In my opinion this has too much liquid which resulted in a rather soupy consistency.  I actually used less liquid than it called for too as I reduced the amount of wine to about 1/3 C as that is all I had left.  After I reduced the gravy down I tasted it and decided it needed more spices, so I added more thyme and a small clove of minced garlic.  Because it was so soupy, the gravy part flooded over the potatoes as it cooked so I drained some of the gravy off and then continued cooking.  Nice flavour though, so I will try again with some alterations. Thanks for the recipe.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: Kathy - I'm so impressed with this chicken...moist, juicy and bursting with flavor from the top down!  Mine took 6 1/2 hours in my crockpot but I had a larger sized chicken.  Really a great way to prepare a roasted chicken without the oven.  Loved coming home tonight to this meal and so did the hubby and son!  Thanks so much!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Outstanding. I grated fresh ginger and garlic, otherwise followed recipe exactly. This is so tasty and satisfying. No MSG and Gluten Free. LOVE IT!

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: The entire family enjoyed these!  They are easy to make and wonderfully tasty.  Thanks so much for posting this recipe - it is fantastic! :)

name: very moist banana nut bread
review: This is a very simple, easy recipe to put together and  the best I have ever made!  This will be my go to recipe for Banana Bread from now on.  Thanks so much for posting!

name: bacon lattice tomato muffins  rsc
review: Oh my goodness, this is rich and tasty.  I made these to go along with some soup for dinner and we loved them.  I really liked the filling....yummy.  Thank you for sharing with us, its a perfect addition for those cold soup nights.

name: mile high cabbage pie  5fix
review: This is so good.  I made this for my family and they loved it.  They said it tasted just like a runza.  I did screw up a bit from the recipe.  I forgot to add the soup mixture to the meat and cabbage before I put it on the bottom crust, so I just added it to the top of the meat mixture and then but the top crust on.  it turned out perfect.  My family didn't know any different and they loved the recipe.  Thank you for sharing, this is so much easier then making all the individual runzas.  You are a life saver!

name: cajun style oven fries
review: Delicious! I made thin wedges and they turned out great. I'd keep an eye on them; mine did take longer than 35 minutes, but they are totally worth the wait! Thanks!

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: These are really good eggs.  I made this to go along with some hash browns and sausage.  My family loved them.  I liked the addition of cheese in them, took them over the top.  Thank you so much for this egg recipe.  We will use often.

name: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
review: Ok, first let me say we loved your recipe.  DH ate and ate and ate.  The only thing is I didn't use raisins, I subbed in butterscotch chips instead.  This cookie is soft and moist and full of flavor.  We will use the raisins next go round but I had a half bag of chips to use up.  THank you for such a wonderful cookie recipe.  Everyone should try these, they are that good.

name: chocolate eclair dessert
review: Oh yummy!  I made this for some friends that came to town and we all loved it.  I actually was using up some graham crackers I had open so for the first two layers I used regular graham crackers but for the top layer I used chocolate graham crackers and it worked perfectly.  I also used Fudge frosting and it set up so nice.  :This is a repeat recipe for sure.  Its easy, its cheap and it soooo good.  THank you for sharing with us.

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: My kids could have make a meal off of these.  They were so flavorful and moist.  I will make again when we are serving seafood.  Perfect addition to any meal.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: the best snickerdoodles i have ever eaten
review: These are heavenly.  I had to let them bake a couple minutes more but they were so worth it.  They were soft and chewy, yet sweet and tasty.  So good.  These are definitely making their way into my Christmas trays this year.  Thank you for sharing.

name: kittencal s salisbury steak
review: I made this for my family and they loved it.  We served mashed potatoes, corn and biscuits with this.  What a comforting meal.  I really like how the loaves held up nice an firm.  The gravy that goes with this is rich and flavorful.  This is a keeper, thanks for sharing with us.  I love trying your recipes.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: This is a really comforting soup.  Its really simple to prepare and it tastes like more work then it was.  Thank you for sharing with us.  We sprinkled celery salt on top...mmmmmm.

name: legal seafood style baked scallops
review: I had printed this recipe out so long ago and just now made it.  BIG mistake to wait so long.  It was delicious.  I loved the tangy buttermilk mixed with the scallops and buttery crackers.  Oh my goodness, so good.  I served this with a lemony rice pilaf and asparagus, perfect meal.  Thank you for sharing with us, I just wish I didn't wait so long before trying it.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: OMG YUM!!! I used this sauce with recipe/italian-saucy-sausage-sub-20037 and recipe/weight-watchers-pita-pizza-230254. This pizza sauce will be my family's "go-to" pizza sauce from now on! Thanks for sharing.

name: tzatziki
review: Delicious! I used Greek yoghurt and it's the first time I've used vinegar in a Tzatziki but it added a nice little extra tang.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Excellent. I was almost tempted to add a little more salt, maybe next time. This tinted & frosted one 8" round & 12 regular sized cupcakes beautifully. Definitely recommend with recipe #94886. This was probably the best cake I've made in a while, thanks for sharing!

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: Wonderful pie! The flavor is tart and refreshing; texture thick and creamy. I used fat-free condensed milk, which was undetectable. The filling did not fill my extra-large Keebler pie crust, so I used the egg whites to make a meringue for the top. I had to bake it for 20 min. for the meringue, and the lime part survived that just fine.

name: lucky sweet and sour sauce
review: Easy and good.  Thanks for sharing!

name: amish white bread
review: I've been experimenting a lot lately with yeast breads after years of being afraid of them.  This is by far the best I've made.  It's delicious by itself, not ever requiring butter.The directions were perfect. This will be my go to white bread from now on.

name: best grilled pork chops
review: My entire family loves this recipe.  I marinated them over night.  The chops came out moist and tender.  Very good recipe. Thank you for sharing it.

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: These were amazing baked pork chops - wish I had read the part about freezing the leftover crumbs before I dumped them out because I'm looking forward to making them again!

name: fish tacos and cilantro coleslaw  20 minutes max
review: Best fish taco recipe we've tried yet! Excellent- thanks!

name: microwave chocolate mug brownie
review: Oh dear lord!  This is sinful!  Can't wait to try out many variations...peanut butter, cherry flavoring nuts etc etc.....and put in mason jars with a Just add water for co-workers.....oh my...

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: very good.  rubbed a very little amount of mayo on it before dipping.  The only thing we thought it needed was a little salt.  Will make again!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: This recipe is excellent. I followed the recipe except that  I added in chopped carrots and they came out even better than the potatoes IMHO.  The carrots picked up the lemon flavor more.  I will definitely be using this recipe often.  Thanks evelyn/athens.

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: Mmmmm....nothing better than a good chocolate cake that's super quick and easy to make. The only issue I had was that it took about 45 mins. to bake. The sides baked up find, but the center took forever to cook through and by the time the center was done, the edges were a little dry.  I have an unreliable oven right now, so that was probably the reason. Thanks for posting this easy , tasty recipe!

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: Excellent!  I used mainly fresh fruits, which was very time consuming, but well worth it.  The entire bowl was G O N E in less than 10 minutes.  Did not add sugar.  Thank you!!

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: a good starting point.  I like the cooking method--easy. not too complicated, but even though I added rosemary, thyme, & sage, onions & celery, I still wanted more flavor & wasn't a big fan of what was there.

name: detweiler sloppy joe mix
review: Made last night - very good.  I added a bit of garlic and worcestershire sauce (personal taste).  Thanks for a quick and easy dinner!

name: famous challah
review: Made a big, beautiful loaf.  I halved the recipe.  Easy in the bread machine.  I added raisins.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: After making this again yesterday, I'm now revising my previous review from 2 stars to 4.  I think the reason I didn't like it the first time I made it is that I had followed the instructions and cooked my garlic much too long..I suppose it burned, which gave the entire soup a bad taste.  This time I sauteed onion and carrots in extra virgin olive oil for about 5 minutes, THEN added the garlic and cooked only til the garlic was fragrant.  Otherwise, I followed the recipe using the beef broth and it turned out to be quite good, as well as quick, easy and very nutritious.   And the next day, it was even tastier.   I'm so glad I gave this soup another chance...I'll definitely be making it regularly.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: I keep having people say how much they loved your meatballs.  ANOTHER winner Kitten :)

name: new mexico style chili chicken casserole
review: This was very good. I halved the recipe and used "hot" green chilies.  Even so, this wasn't very spicy.  So it would be good for a family feeding children who are sensitive to spices.  If you want it hotter, I'd sub jalapenos for the chilies. I added chopped fresh cilantro when serving.  Thanks for sharing!

name: easy way lasagna
review: This is really good and easy.  I was sure the noodles wouldn't come out right...but they did!  Next time I'll add more of the cottage cheese because I felt like it was a little skimpy.  Thanks for the great recipe MizzNezz....

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: I loved the flavor, so will definately be making this again.  However, 45 minutes made my chicken breasts overdone.  I'd recommend starting out at 30 min. and check for doneness then.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: I made this for dinner tonight using cheese tortellini. I also used a bag of fresh spinach.  It was a little smaller than what the recipe called for but it seemed to be perfect.  The fresh grated parm. at the end was a must for us.  It really made the soup.  I had a Italian seasoning grinder on the table that some of us added to the soup as well.  No one in my picky family gave this anything lower than four stars.  Wow! That doesn't happen often!  I served this with Bada Big Betty's Tuscan Portabella Melt (193692)  These two wonderful recipes compliment each other well.  Made for a delicious meal!

name: cha ching  carrot spice muffins
review: These are really good.  I made this half with raisins and half without.  you  would never know these are healthy for you.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: roasted tomato soup
review: Oh yum!  I made this last night for my kids with some grilled cheese sandwiches.  This is so good, and healthy.  DH isn't a fan of canned tomato soup so I can't wait for him to try this recipe.  He will love it.  Its such an easy recipe to make too.  Roasting the veggies gives them so much flavor.  Great recipe, thank you for sharing with us.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Easy and delicious!

name: sweet potato curry with spinach and chickpeas
review: I love curry, but never thought to use sweet potatoes.  We liked this a lot.  Thank you for sharing this recipe.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Made this as written for the most part. I didn't realize my scale was off by an ounce so only used 7 ounces of pasta. We used Tillamook cheddar and real butter. Again, the key to white sauce is to cook it long enough so the sauce doesn't taste like flour. This was super yummy! LOVED how saucy it was, almost all of my family of 9 liked it!!  Thank you, we will be adding this to our menu!  UPDATE:  I have one child who requests this daily!!  But with the price of cheese I just can't do it. BUT we have had it about 3 times in a month as it is so easy and yummy.<br/>Update 5-3-13: you have to use REAL cheese. Not marble, not pre-shredded.. The preshredded stuff has rice flour added to it so it doesn't stick so your space will be grainy. Also, you need to cook your flour in the butter for a minute and then when you add your milk make sure to bring your sauce to almost a boil or even to a boil, then remove from heat and add your cheese then. This is NOT Kraft Mac and cheese, this is real food, dump and stir doesn't work. You do have to put some effort into it, but so worth it.<br/>We have used Tillamook cheddar, Tillamook white cheddar, cheap cheddar, sharp cheddar.. The key is CHEDDAR, and shred it yourself

name: crispy baked chicken leg quarters  very easy  one dish
review: Nice flavorful chicken. This recipe was simple to make and turned out very well. The skin was crispy, and the meat was tender and moist. Thanks for sharing this nice keeper. Made for Zaar Chef Alphabet Soup tag.

name: kittencal s extreme chocolate brownies
review: Oh my goodness... What a wonderful recipe! I just made these for a gathering of women and their children for this afternoon, and I'm almost afraid to take them. :) I doubled the batch and used 4 - 8x8 disposable, aluminum cake pans (one pan to keep for hubby and I). After they cooled, (before tasting), I went ahead and sifted powdered sugar over the top of all pans... YIKES!!! The mom's are gonna kill me for serving this to their kids! Soooo rich, but delicious!!! I wouldn't change a thing to this recipe. Mine looked very thin, separated into the 4 pans at the start, but baked up beautifully (and I'm not a good baker). Thank you for posting this awesome recipe. (Made for "Name That Ingredient" tag game). P.S. I did not use any nuts, for fear that some of the children may be allergic.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: I used butter instead of margarine and used 1 cup of butter and 12 garlic cloves which I put through the garlic press  and omitted the parmesan chees (sorry my mob refer parmesan cheese it as SPEW/VOMIT cheese when it is cooked so used 1 1/4 cups of a sharp cheddar) but otherwise cooked as directed - taking nearly 20 minutes on 225C fan forced  (could possibly have done with a minute or 2 less for perfection) but the end result was oh so good cheesy garlic bread which we all enjoyed immensily.  Thank you SaraFish, made fopr Name that Ingredient tag game.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Wow! amazing and easy!  the recipe was so easy to follow!  My husband moaned or groaned... well made in unpleasant sound when he saw them on the table.  A few minutes later he tried them and said, wow that's the best Brussels sprout I have ever tasted!!!!  Yea!  Now my 3 and 5 year old were not fond of them they ate equivalent to 1.5 of them, but oh well... I LOVE them! This is a keeper and we will make again!  It was my first time making them but it wont be my last!

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: Very good. Perfect for a cold, rainy Sunday. I used a small jar of pimentos and added garlic salt, and dried Basil. It was perfect. Next time I might double the sauce, the biscuits soaked up a lot of it. I made noodles to go along side this, thinking they would go nicely with the sauce, but they were not needed. Just a nice green salad would have been perfect. This will go in my regular weeknight rotation.

name: weight watchers mexican chicken breasts
review: I'm always looking for easy recipes for those days when I just don't have a lot of time to spend in the kitchen, and it's a major plus when it's a Weight Watchers recipe.  I used chicken tenders and baked for 20 minutes.  Loved the addition of the salsa and sour cream.

name: caesar pork chops
review: Unfortunately this rating is 100% from my hubby - I had to run out to attend to a family emergency while they were still in the oven & then I took my chop in my lunch the next day & proceeded to melt the Tupperware that I was reheating it in.  He said he enjoyed the flavour but didn't like the texture of the flour coating on the meat.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Yum!! We followed the recipe exactly and these made for such a wonderful breakfast! I agree with everyone-they're very light and fluffy and the taste is fantastic! Thanks for the great recipe!

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: This is really good. I made this for my family the other night and we all enjoyed it.  I liked the slightly sweet flavor with the garlic.  I served this with fried rice, egg drop soup and chicken wings.  Thank you for sharing.

name: breakfast burritos  once a month cooking
review: Only made two to eat right away but they were so good.  Added crisp hash browns and green onion.  Will make many time again.

name: microwave poached egg on toast
review: For the egg I would give a five but the cooking process in the microwave turns the toast to being rubbery not at all crisp, would consider doing this recipe again by greasing a plate and cracking the egg onto it and microwaving it and then puting it onto the CRISP buttered toast which could be cooking while the egg is cooking.  Thank you Trisha W for a great quick breakfast idea, made for Name that Ingredient and tag game.

name: tilapia al ajillo  garlic tilapia
review: So quick, easy and fresh tasting!  I decreased the oil to just a little drizzle since I used a non-stick pan.  Seasoned the tilapia with lemon pepper and salt and left out the lemon juice.  I loved the toasted garlic and parsley that topped this dish.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: What a quick and easy way to make a light-tasting broccoli dish.  I mixed some garlic powder in with the salt, pepper and water and then topped the finished dish with Mrs. Dash-Onion and Herb seasoning.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Really great bread spread with the perfect amount (for us) of garlic and cheese - loved it.  I used butter instead of margarine, slathered it on French bread and baked for 9 minutes.  YUM!

name: stove top tamale pie
review: DH and DD loved this recipe.  I was gone so didn't get to try but they thought it was really good.  I served this with some lime cilantro rice and they were both gone.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: the best ever waffles
review: So good!  I liked the crisp on the outside and they got a little dark but were still moist and fluffy on the inside.  I used my hand mixer for the egg whites to make sure they were stiff enough to not break down completely when they were folded in.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: Very easy, good, and filling.  I made as directed except used applesauce in place of oil and whole wheat flour.  My kids liked them, too.  <br/>Update: This time I put all ingredients in my vitamix (blender) and blended it all up with some chocolate chips.  It was even better this way!  We LOVED them!

name: vegetarian lasagna
review: Tasty. I omitted the zucchini and added extra mushrooms. Thanks for posting.

name: crock pot chicken taco meat
review: So simple, and so delicious. A must do for everyone. Thank you.

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Moist and Delicious, cream cheese frosting is terrific per DH.  We didn't use the freezer method and it turned out great.  I also put my oven on 350 and it also turned out fine.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: whole wheat honey banana muffins
review: These are terrific. Made mine with white whole wheat flour (instead of the traditional red whole wheat), 2 large ripe bananas, and coconut oil. I just ate one still warm from the oven, and they taste great-- no spreads or additions needed, but I bet these will be awesome with some hazelnut butter (or macadamia nut butter) in the morning. Thanks for posting.

name: tsr version of carrabba s bread dipping spice by todd wilbur
review: Loved this dipping sauce.  I can't compare it to Carrabba's since I've never eaten there (and have no intention of driving to another state just so I can eat at Carrabba's).  Served with slices of French bread and it was delicious.

name: easy lemon pound cake
review: I made this for my family with the intent to put strawberries and whipped cream on top.  BUT, it didn't last that long.  They all dug in as soon as I took it out of the pan.  Since I was going to do the strawberry thing, I opted to not but he glaze on top.  Next time I will add the glaze since I know my family likes it just as the cake.  Thank you for such an easy cake to whip up.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: I scaled down the recipe and enjoyed on whole grain toast. Thanks!

name: tsr version of starbucks pumpkin scones by todd wilbur
review: These scones were delicious, not dry at all.  I did bake them on a stone cookie sheet so I think that helped.  I also mixed up the spiced glaze using the leftover first glaze by just mixing in the spices.  Excellent dipped in my coffee and so easy to make!

name: quick yellow cake
review: I have made cakes from scratch for years and thought I would give this one a try because of how easy it was--I must agree with others that the texture was very similar to corn bread and I don't know as though I will make this one again (though I thought the flavor was good--I did use butter flavored shortening because it was what I had).  I served it with sliced sweetened strawberries and it made a good base to what essentially became strawberry shortcake.  Thanks for the easy dessert!

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: How much dry noodles needed to make 6 oz of cooked noodles?  I shouldn't have to do research in order to finish following a recipe.  As it was, I cooked up 2 cups of dry noodles but could have used more.  Taste is very good and it was easy to put together.

name: best oatmeal cookies
review: This recipe has become my goto recipe for oatmeal cookies.  I don't know about "best", but these are a tasty oatmeal cookie. I am trying to make my cookies a little more nutritious so substituted 1 cup of white flour for 1 cup of whole wheat and 1 cup of sugar w/1 cup of Splenda. No one could tell the difference!   Also, i make my cookies a little bigger I guess because I only get 48 cookies.  Thanks for sharing a great recipe!

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: What an awesome side dish and so easy to make.  We will be making this again.

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: Wonderful!  Thank you for sharing this.

name: strawberry strawberry pie from the really good food cook book
review: This went over well in my house. I used some of the suggestions I read in other reviews. I cut the water down to 1 1/4 cup and I also mixed the liquid and strawberry's together in a bowl before I added it to the pie crust. I used a store bought shortbread crust and my ingredients almost fit perfectly. I had just a touch left over.

name: unbelievably easy potato soup
review: I adjusted this slightly, added some leftover potato casserole and also some carrot along with the celery, onion & potatoes. Once cooked down & mashed I added a small handful cheese along with a little crumbled bacon, was very hearty & delicious and yes unbelievably easy...:)

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: Fantastic!!  Easy and delicious!  Went well with our grilled burgers tonight.  Thanks!

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: This recipe has 264 reviews so it hardly needs mine but here goes. Good solid sauce. As with another poster, I made the vegetarian version and it turned out well. It tastes even better the next day when the leftovers are reheated so make more than you need. If you find it acidic add a bit of sugar, if you find it too bland add some more seasonings, if you don't eat red meat add some ground turkey, remove the bay leaf but make it your own. This sauce is a good base for it all. The family ate it happily. Thanks for posting Bev. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: skillet parmesan chicken
review: Delicious. We'll be making this again.

name: easy taco stew
review: I made this last night using some leftovers I had in the fridge.  We had nachos the other day, so I used our leftover hamburger meat from that.  I had some leftover corn, so I used that.  This was really good, plus it cleaned out my fridge.  I served this with corn chips, sour cream, shredded cheese and some veggies I had leftover from the nachos (tomatoes, onions, black olives and avocados)  Thank you for sharing your recipe with us.

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: These were terrific!  A definite keeper that we will have again and again... thanks so much for posting this winner! :)

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: The first time I made this I didn't enjoy it as much. I remember the worcestershire was too much for me. The second time I halved the worcestershire and it was much better. A lovely, comforting and enjoyable dish, thank you.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: The rolls were delicious. The icing tasted like thick, sweet margarine. I would do this again but I'd use softened real butter in the icing and reduce the amount of it, increasing the cream cheese to compensate. I also might take the suggestion of others and add a second rising.

name: new mexico style chili chicken casserole
review: Very good and easy dish.  Only made enough for two and turned out great.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Garlic lovers would unite and though I loved as per recipe 2 of our other diners thought it could have done without the cheese in the crumb mix and just sprinkle over top in the  last 5 minutes of cooking (I did both so may have overpowered and only used sharp cheddar cheese as my mob hate parmesan when cooked, they refer to it as spew cheese).  Thank you Kittencalskitchen made for I Recommend tag game and recommended by Breezermom.

name: chicken pesto
review: This recipe was so easy to make and so tasty that my husband (who despises baked chicken) said it was the best chicken he has ever had... he loved it so much he had the leftovers for lunch today!  Made this exactly as written and it turned out perfectly.  Thanks for posting! :)

name: red lobster cheddar bay biscuits copycat
review: In January 2010 I had made this yummy recipe a few months ago and forgot to rate it. The biscuits didn't last long after taking out of the oven. Everyone loved them. Thanks for posting.<br/>May 2013- I have made these a number of times, with everyone that tastes them rates highly. If this recipe come from a Bisquick box, I am not bothered.  Red Lobster probably uses Bisquick too!  I am not disappointed in the taste, and, isn't that what is the bottom line?  It is for me.  Thanks for posting this recipe ThatJodiGirl

name: strawberry shortcake a la treebeard s
review: We really enjoyed these strawberry shortcakes.  Easy to make and sooo delicious.  DH really enjoyed them too.  We used to order a similar dish at a restaurant that is now no longer in business.  So glad to have this recipe handy since I have access to freshly picked strawberries at a local Farmer's Market.  Made for Name That Ingredient tag, May, 2013.

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: These shrimps are so yummy.  I cooked plain shrimps for our son and then we cooked these shrimps for me and DH.  We liked them so much.  Montreal steak seasoning is great with the shrimps.  I misread the direction and chopped the garlic so I didn't have to leave it in the skillet.  DH liked that the garlic was with the shrimps.  The lemon zest and juice was also great in it.  Thanks Chippie :)  Made for Holiday tag game

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This was pretty good. I coated my defrosted chicken in salsa seasoning before I put it in. I had 2 different kinds of salsa along with frozen corn. I cooked on low and this turned out really great with tortilla chips. I also shredded the chicken. It took about 6 hrs on low, but I only had 2 chicken breasts.

name: chewy granola bars
review: I made these last night for DD to take to a lacrosse game for her and her friends.  These are excellent.  I wrapped them up in waxed paper and they are a great take along treat.  I didn't use the raisins and subbed butterscotch chips for the chocolate ones.  Delicious.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: balsamic chicken thighs
review: Only made two and wish I would have made more as it is so good.  Served with Creamy  Italian Orzo (153994)  Will make these all the time.

name: amazing white trash puff balls
review: I used two 8 oz. tubes of croissants and cut the triangles in two, as I found it difficult to wrap it if cut into thirds. I think this would be great if crab were used in place of the pepperoni.

name: refreshing mojito  by the pitcher mojitos
review: Very delicious... and I even used tonic in place of the club. Such a refreshing drink!! I just went out and planted more mint. My poor mint plants won't last long now that I've found this recipe. Between myself and my friends, I'll need a mint field!!

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: This is great. Packaged stuff is expensive and this is way more convenient.

name: no bake rice krispies peanut butter granola bars  lower fat
review: Delicious!!! I have made this twice in the last week and we all love it. So fast to make and I love that I can add whatever I like. It is also a great way to use up Rice Krispies. My chocolate chips melted a bit the first time, so this last time, I let the bars cool a little, then gently pushed the chocolate chips on top. Much better results but delicious either way!

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: I added spinach to this.  It was easy and tasty.  The pasta I used was a little funky, I did not use penne.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: so good but you need foil on the pan otherwise it does burn right away

name: quick n easy quiche crust
review: Worked great- quick and easy!

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: This is another hit by Kittencal!  So easy and so delicious.  I used fresh parsley and probably a little more parmesan.  Served on rolls one night with recipe#99870#99870 and another night on some sourdough bread.  Thank you for posting.  Made for Zaar Chef Alphabet Soup ~ Jan-June 2013 tag game.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Good, not extraordinary. I didn't think the long marinating made much difference. Served with bbq sauce, and used leftover chicken in a salad.

name: ground beef gyros
review: Very easy and tasty weekday meal.  I cheated and made them more like ground beef tacos, so I am not rating on meat consistency, but flavor.  I found them a tad too peppery and might cut it in half next time.  The sauce does help cool down the spiciness though.  Will definitely make these again!

name: orange julius smoothies
review: yum yum....used kefir milk for added healthy benefits

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Fantastic flavor!  I made according to directions except used a slightly smaller container of ricotta than called for.  Next time I'll use a larger container.

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: We really liked this but I did make some changes. With reading the other reviews I did double the sauce but wasn't sure if I really needed too. I used Italian seasoning instead of oregano, basil and thyme as that is all I had. I also used old bay instead of the cayenne and red pepper flakes. I forgot to double the salt and pepper. I ate some on brown rice but everyone else ate them plain. We all really enjoyed these with the changes made.

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: This was just ok. I used panko bread crumbs and I did not measure anything but eyeballed it. I like the patties themselves but did not care for the sauce. I thought it was way to sweet, which i think was from the ketchup, I hate ketchup meatloaves and fear that is why this tasted so strange for me. Thanks for posting

name: pan release  professional pan coating  better than pam spray
review: Fabulous!

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: This was so good that hubby even declared it tasty! You know that's a winner when your other half speaks up. I used black grapes, walnuts and mayonnaise. Delicious!

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: I honestly can not say how wonderful this recipe turned out.  What a simple full flavored sandwich!  I made it exactly as directed (even the steamed bun!) and these were true belly poppers!  The hubby was still talking about them this morning - we will certainly have this again and again.  He did want me to say next time we will toast the buns as you do because you clearly have great tastes, so we will try it your way! Thanks so much for posting this recipe, it will be enjoyed at out house again and again! :)

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Delicious and tender.

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: This was 'different', but we really enjoyed it. Will be making again....

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: Great seasoning/marinade!  Not too spicy which is what I like.  I made these with chicken and used red and yellow peppers.  I marinated the chicken for approx. 8 hours and it gave the meat a great flavor.  Will be making these again, it was so quick and easy!  Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: This dish is so incredibly good!  We love chicken pot pies, but I always purchased them in the past -- shame on me!  Now I can make them at home and control the ingredients -- and there is enough for a second helping for DH.  Great comfort food.  Made for Everyday is a Holiday tag, May, 2013.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: This was good as written. The next time I didn't have enough butter, so I improvised.<br/>1/4 cup butter, 4 ounces cream cheese, and 1/2 cup palm oil shortening, NO milk. Also I used 2-3 tsp vanilla extract and 1 tsp peppermint extract to make a vanilla mint frosting.  Yummy and perfect!

name: mile high cabbage pie  5fix
review: Very good, filling and easy! I used a great deal of pepper as we like spicy and some worcestershire sauce. Other than that followed exactly and enjoyed. Congrats!

name: chili s spicy garlic   lime shrimp
review: These were yummy! I just cut back on the salt, maybe even to 1/2 (could still do bit  less), and that seemed great!. Put them on a tangy caesar salad, and would be happy to do that again! Thx for sharing!

name: easy cole slaw
review: Nice and easy.  Always turns out good for me.  I agree with the previous reviewer--it could use a bit of kick & I've added horseradish for some extra spice too.  I also think it get's too juicy.  I'm considering reducing the milk & vinegar by a tablespoon each, but hope that won't affect the flavor.

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: I loved the idea of this dish but the flavours didn't really come through too much. Maybe my pan was too large? The red onion and garlic that I added like some other reviewers was the best part.

name: classic baked ziti
review: I made this exactly as directed and wouldn't change a thing. Okay I added more garlic but I add extra garlic to everything.  This was flavorful but great for those who don't want heat or spice. A total keeper.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: Made recipe as stated. We used lamb. Everyone loved it. Next time I might make a puff pastry top as requested by the kids. Like we have with our Scottish meat pies.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: We didn't add the parmesan, and it was still delicious! Will be making this often...Thank you for sharing!

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: I was apprehensive about trying this recipe because of the lack of butter or oil in the ingredients list despite the reviews.  I was so tempted to just add a little oil (as per the cake mix's instructions).  I made this cake according to the instructions without adding any oil and the cake was devoured!  One person ate 3 pieces!!!  Lots of sighs and moans and a couple of people even asked to take some home for later.  Thank you for posting this recipe!!!

name: beer  n bbq braised country style pork ribs
review: Wonderful ribs! I used Redd's Apple Ale and Garland Jack's Secret Six BBQ sauce. The ribs were so tender, they fell apart just lifting them out of the pan. Thanks!

name: homemade hamburger buns  bread machine
review: Good tasting but I wish that they would have raised more.  I let them raise for 2 hours but they still did not raise as much as I would have liked.

name: banana banana bread
review: Terrific banana bread recipe...no frills, just great banana flavor.  I've made this recipe several times.  Sometimes as written, sometimes with half whole wheat/half AP flour, sometimes all whole wheat.  It's good all kinds of ways!  :-)

name: the ultimate strawberry shortcake
review: This is a great, light summery dessert. I followed directions given, only I used a smaller pan so it would be thicker. Came out great! Mine cut perfectly into squares. My kids made a flag pattern on the top using strawberries and blueberries.

name: baked stuffed pasta shells
review: These were really great!! I added about 5 or 6 Italian sausage links, removed from their casings and browned, to the ricotta mixture and used The Silver Palate tomato basil sauce to top these with. I also added a little extra shredded mozzarella on top. Everyone loved them and they freeze really well too. Thanks for posting this yummy recipe!

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: These ARE the best ever!! Made them for breakfast this morning(Sunday), and was asked by the family to wrap the rest individually so they can bring them to work and school! I'm always asked to make recipe#87925 for class parties, but DD said this could become "the NEW brownie"! LOL Thanks so much for sharing-

name: reduced fat alfredo sauce
review: We started out with every intention of making this low-fat. Then we bought some goat's milk to make cheese and found that it was ultra-pasteurized and couldn't be used to make cheese. So we used it for this recipe and, while it was not low-fat, it was DELICIOUS!!! We used this in a lobster lasagna recipe that was just fabulous. Thanks so much for posting this. I'll never buy bottled alfredo sauce again!

name: poverty meal
review: A quick, easy, inexpensive and pleasant meal that can be on the table in now time and only dirty one pot; great for those nights when you just don't want to spend a lot of time in the kitchen but still want that home made dinner.  It was a little bland for our taste so added 2 teaspoons of chili powder and 1 teaspoons of crushed red pepper and that seemed to work great for us.

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: While the flavor of this dish was decent, the amount of oil that accumulated in the slow cooker was very off-putting.  It looked to be almost halfway filled with oil.  This is probably unavoidable when cooking the ribs in a crock pot, so next time I think I'll just go with broiling or grilling.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Such a simple cake but it sure didn t do anything for us......dry and followed recipe exactly. I guess our tastes are all different.     Wish it had been a success because of the simplicity but afraid not.

name: ground turkey chili for people who hate ground turkey
review: This is delicious.  We don't hate ground turkey, but we love this.  I served this with some corn chips, shredded cheese and sour cream.  My family "dolled" it up, but I ate it as is.  So good.  Thank you for sharing with us.  We loved this.

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: OMG. That's all I can say. OMG. :)  THANK YOU FOR SHARING~

name: wholesome homemade honey whole wheat bread
review: Oh my gosh, I am so proud of myself with this recipe.  I have never baked bread with out using a bread machine.  This was really easy to follow the directions and my bread turned out so moist and light.  Thank you so much for helping me overcome my fear of homemade bread.  I will make many times, we all loved it.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: This cauliflower is really delicious!  I made it as written and it came out perfect....my husband and I ate nearly the entire large head of cauliflower.  Thanks Julesong for this wonderful recipe!

name: kittencal s beef or pork marinade and tenderizer
review: We used this on pork steaks and this sweet marinade is perfect for pork.  I haven't tried it on beef YET but we will soon.  I think this is my go to marinade for pork steaks.  We like them but sometimes they come out blah, not anymore.  This marinade is very flavorful, thank you for helping us out in that area.

name: slow cook down home pork chops and gravy
review: This is so easy and very tasty too!  Made as written and just added a little fresh cracked pepper to the finished product.  Served with brown rice, green beans and breadsticks.  Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: I'll admit I wasn't thrilled when my daughter chose this recipe to make for dinner. I usually do not like anything cajun. But, since it was her night to cook, I let her. I'm so glad I did because this dish is fantastic!! She used Mirj's Recipe #14190 as recommended. The only changes she made was to use light whipping cream and to cook twice as much pasta since she was serving 4 of us. (The 2 chicken breasts we had were huge so no need to double those.) We all loved it and agreed it needed to become part of the regular rotation. Thanks, Lorac!

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: A nice muffin. We preferred them with the sugar decreased some and the chocolate chips and walnuts doubled. The buttermilk adds a nice tang to them.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Great marinade! Flavor is good but no overpowering! I increased the garlic by a hair but other than that followed the recipe! Thx!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: This is a good meatloaf recipe, I just do not think it is the best I have had.  I liked the sweet-tangy sauce on top, it is a nice change from just ketchup, but the meatloaf itself needed more flavor.  Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: These were fantastic, I couldn't believe how tender they were. I will def make them again. Thanks!

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: Made half a recipe but each batch took 71/2 min. as I had used my food processor to slice the potatoes.  It is 2mm, I believe.  May have to get a different blade so they are thinner.  Serving with Recipe #34683 later today.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: I hate to say it that I am not a huge fan of this sugar cookie.  They cooked very well and kept their shape, but they were not sweet at all (and I put icing on them) and they didn't have much flavor.  I will keep looking for a different recipe.

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: We marinated for 4 hours.  This was great on the barbeque.  Made for Name That Ingredient.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: This recipe was made for mine and my SO's dinner on 5/30/13.Except for using legs & thighs the recipe was made as it was written. To help prevent sticking, non stick aluminum foil was also used.<br/>There was " A LOT " of sauce so if I make this again, the amount of sauce will be cut in half.<br/>The chicken was baked at 350 degrees for an hour and 15 minutes. I personally don't like dark meat,but this was very good. Thank you for posting and, " Keep Smiling :) "

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: These were delicious and so easy! I made them with chicken, and I let them marinate in the fridge for about an hour and a half. I used 2 onions and one bell pepper, and next time I think I would use even more onions. This is going in my regular rotation. Thank you!

name: moist and tender turkey  or turkey breast
review: I had two turkey breasts in the freezer just waiting for a way to cook them. I found this recipe and have a family full of happy campers. I used half the first breast for a Turkey Caesar salad, so much better than chicken. The next day turned cold & wet so I grabbed the broth, some veggies, rice and the other half of the turkey breast and made dh & ds some hot turkey soup for when they got home from work. The second breast is being used in lunch sandwiches and the guys are loving it. The turkey is full of flavour and so moist. Thanks so much for the excellent recipe, it will be my goto for making turkey & chicken breasts for salads & sandwiches. Ps. I used Earth Balance in place of the butter as turns out I'm allergic to dairy :(

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Used 1.5 boxes of pasta and kept other ratios including dressing the same and it was perfect!

name: sweet potato curry with spinach and chickpeas
review: Very yummy and easy, put spinach in last so it was less wilty.

name: kittencal s salisbury steak
review: Really delicious! I have never made Salisbury steak, so was pleasantly surprised with this recipe. Made a half recipe and used leftover gravy plus only a quarter of the recipe's gravy. This was tender and delicious. Ate with mashed potatoes smothered in gravy. Used half package total of the Lipton Onion Soup Mix. Thanks for giving something else to make for supper.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Wonderful!!

name: softest ever bread machine bread
review: This bread is really soft and so yummy.  I used the dough setting and let it rise at least 30 minutes.  Thanks Dine & Dish :)  Made for Name that ingredient tag game

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: This was good and easy to make. I followed the recipe other then I used 1/2 teaspoon of pepper and used Velveeta cheese. My family enjoyed this and I did not have any issues with the amount of flour.

name: corned beef in beer  crock pot
review: This is good and easy, but the vegetables were mushed.  I've made it several times and only put the potatoes and cabbage in an hour before serving.  Thank you

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: We are salmon lovers but usually only on the grill with limited amount of seasoning.  This is not the norm for us but it is for a very special treat and loved it.  This topping also works with haddock or cod........so versatile.    We do like the cheddar on top.....

name: pork chops yum yum
review: The sauce was good.  Not too sweet. I used chopped garlic instead of garlic salt.  I used fairly thin pork chops and cooked them on the stove, covered, after browning.  They were a bit dried out after 20 minutes and the sauce wasn't reduced at all.  It tasted good though.  Thanks for posting.

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: Excellent and easy recipe that was perfect for my busy day.  The sauce was so delicious and rich.  I put ours over rice and it was so amazing.

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: No reason to buy a mix - this is quick and easy to put together.  There are no issues with the baking powder, I checked my other recipe and this is essentially a "doubled" recipe of the one I have used before.  Great pancakes - added some fresh blueberries and a touch of vanilla.

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: Soo good. I actually doubled the black beans alongside a 15 oz can of pineapple. Next time I think I'll stick to the recipe as written. I was worried it would be too sweet yet I found myself wanted more pineapple in each bite with the added beans. Served with Spanish Rice. With the extra filling I plan to make Black Bean and Pineapple Quesadillas! Thank you, mrib! [Made for Name That Ingredient]

name: ginger me up chicken  low fat honey   ginger chicken breasts
review: The ginger flavor was perfect, we loved this recipe! I decided to experiment and baked one and pan fried one. I much preferred the pan fried one, it had caramelization and just plain looked better, the oven baked one was pale and unappetizing looking, although it was very good. Thanks for sharing!

name: balsamic chicken thighs
review: Sorry, this didn't turn out well. Maybe there are different kinds of balsamic vinegar. It was way too strong.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Delicious and so easy. Moist, tasty and loved by all.

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: Very bland and surprisingly "heavy". Not my cup of tea - sorry.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: This is a great tasting muffin.  The reason for the 4 star rating is that since I don't use paper muffin cup, my muffins stuck to the tins even after generously coating them with butter!  Will make this again but am now aware of the sticking situation.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Mine didn't come out as golden as some of the others pictured, but that doesn't mean they weren't absolutely delicious...and I'm still trying to figure out a polite way of asking for your leftovers!

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: Add me to the list of fans of this sandwich. I've never been to Iowa, so never had the real thing. My husband has raved about loosemeat sandwiches for years and I remember their appearance on "Roseanne". Followed the recipe exactly and used a cast-iron skillet. Toasted the buns, spread with mustard, topped the meat with dill pickle slices. Everyone raved. Thanks for sharing this recipe. Already have requests to make it again.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Delicious!!  I cut 1 large organic chicken breast into 4 pieces and pounded them thin before breading them.  I also used whole wheat panko in place of regular bread crumbs.  I also cooked them in a pan on the stovetop in a little bit of coconut oil.  They were delicious!!  Everyone LOVED them!!  Thanks for a quick and easy recipe!!

name: reduced fat alfredo sauce
review: This was really good and easy to make. I followed the recipe as written other then I went a bit heavier with the parmesan cheese. I also used 2% milk instead of 1% as that is what I buy. We all enjoyed this. I used this in Recipe #239830

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: I made this chicken salad for my son but he didn't like it.  Too bad for him.  I'm the one lucky to eat it.  And it's so yummy.  Thanks ellie :)  Made for Name that ingredient tag game

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Really good!  I used fat free Greek yogurt instead of mayo.

name: chicken with fettuccine alfredo
review: This was fantastic!  I am not a big chicken fan but thought this had delicious flavor and very simple to make!  I used chicken breast tenders and after I browned them in the skillet I put them in the oven to finish baking.  I thought the sauce would be to thin because I used part regular milk too but it coated the noodles and chicken very well.

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: I mixed this up to use in Recipe #17598. It tasted good in the recipe (which has quite a lot going on) but I didn't like the flavor alone. I thought it was too sweet and lacked depth. However, I did use some leftover dumpling dipping sauce instead of soy sauce, which would have completely altered the flavor profile. Although I usually make Recipe #55859, it calls for fresh ginger, which requires planning. So I will probably try this recipe again using soy sauce and very carefully measuring the brown sugar and honey.

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: These were really tasty! I made a half recipe using chicken tenders. Use regular bread crumbs but baked on a cooling rack on top of a baking pan which helped keep it from getting soggy on the bottom. These will be made again! Thanks for sharing.

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: I'm rating this on sheer genious and flavor alone. Although mine were not as crispy as I had hoped, they did work well. (It could have been my crappy microwave). I used my mandolin to slice thin, and just made season salted. I served them with our brats (burnt on the grill... "thanks hubby"). I thank you for posting a quick and easy chip recipe. I will definately make these again. (Made for Alphabet Soup tag)

name: cranberry orange muffins
review: Perfect. I had been using the recipe on the back of the Ocean Spray fresh cranberries bag, this recipe is almost identical.Doubled the baking powder as suggested, they rose up perfectly. I didn't have any zest (which is fabulous btw, and worth the effort). I reduced the sugar slightly & added a few extra cranberries. These are my DD's favorite,  They freeze beautifully, just pull out and pop in the microwave for a few seconds for a quick breakfast (topped with cream chesse). Thanks for sharing, this one is a keeper.

name: carb free cloud bread
review: These turned out pretty good.  Sort of a cross in texture between sponge cake and bread.  I'm going to try adding ground flax to the egg yolk mixture to get a bit more texture, but other than that I was pleasantly surprised.  I did spread these a bit thinner to get 10 "buns" but think I'll go for 8 thicker ones next time.  I think mine got a bit too soft overnight in the container so I have the lid cracked now to try to dry them out a bit.  We'll see how it goes.  Instructions were easy to follow, and I'll definitely be making this one often, as this has a much lighter hamburger bun texture than the flax bread I usually make.  I did bake mine on parchment to avoid any sticking issues and it worked great.  Thanks for sharing!

name: strawberry strawberry pie from the really good food cook book
review: Oh, this was just okay. I won't give it stars because I probably played around with the glaze too much. I sliced the berries thickly, and put maybe 2 1/2 cups into the pie. The glaze did seem too sweet, so I added some lemon without measuring. I only cooked the glaze with the one cup of hot water, then added an unmeasured amount of ice water before refrigerating, to thicken it before I poured it on the pie. I didn't use all of it on the pie, but it did seem like the pie was not full enough- of berries or glaze.<br/>I'll keep looking for the perfect recipe...

name: carb free cloud bread
review: This is a follow-up to my previous review in case someone has the problem I did: I took the very sticky "buns" out of the plastic bag and just let them air for several hours.  Then when they ceased to be so sticky, I bagged them again, refrigerated them overnight, and now have the more bread-like "buns".  <br/> Ok, I followed the recipe and directions exactly and used full fat cream cheese, but I'm sure disappointed in these.  First of all, they had to bake for 38 minutes before they were golden brown.  I ate one right away and kind of liked the flavored air. (Mine were not crumbly at all) But then after being cooled and bagged and left overnight, they are terribly sticky and not at all as predicted.   It was fun trying, though.  <br/>It's quite humid here due to lots and lots of rain this spring, so I wonder if that would make a difference.

name: stove top tamale pie
review: I was very pleasantly surprised by this.  I was just looking for something quick and easy that wouldn't require a trip to the store and decided to give this a try based on the number of positive review.  But truthfully, I had fairly low expectations.  However, I really enjoyed this and will probably make it again often. Of course, that's depending on how the left overs are since this really isn't something my kids would be into so it's just two of us eating it.  I added a can of corn because I like the crunch and because I decided that if I pretend corn is a vegetable I can make this a one dish meal.  I think next time I might add a second can of tomatoe sauce but other than those changes I would keep it the same.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: Easy, quick and delicious. We used wings.  Made for Name that Ingredient.

name: breakfast burritos  once a month cooking
review: Delicious OAMC breakfast! My DH really likes them as do I. I use the reduced fat sausage which is 12 oz and always add in the hash browns. This time, used frozen hashbrowns, which made prep a lot easier! I cook some onion in with the sausage and use whole wheat tortillas. So great to have in the freezer for a quick hearty breakfast. I used some larger burrito size tortillas this time, so made about 16 or 17 instead of 24. Have made now for the 2nd time and will be making again as a staple in our freezer! Thanks for the idea!

name: easy way lasagna
review: I don't know if I did something wrong, but this was the worst lasagna I've ever had. (This came as a total shock to me since I consider MizzNezz to be one of the biggest names on Food.com.)

name: creamy ramen noodles
review: I made this as written, but doubling the recipe making it for 2, and using whole milk, chicken flavored Ramen Noodles, and adding both packets of the seasonings, and it was delish. I also made this using the Roasted Beef Ramen Noodles, and my husband said they were his favorite. I have also used 1-packet of the Creamy Chicken along with 1-packet of the Picante Chicken, and they were very good. I bet the Roasted Beef and Picante Beef cooked together, would be good too! The other day I used 2 packets of the Creamy Chicken, and adding in 3 individual wrapped slices of Velveeta cheese, to make it Mac 'N Cheese, and boy was that ever delicious! It tasted better than the blue box mac 'n cheese. I'm sure kiddies would prefer that over the stuff that comes in the blue box. Thank you ms-bold for posting this recipe. It definitely is a keeper!!

name: basic batter waffles
review: These are tasty and so easy and quick! They are a perfect spur-of-the-moment waffle, thanks so much for sharing this easy (no melted butter or whipped egg whites!!) recipe! I know I'll use it again and again.

name: lemon baked cod
review: I took someone's review of subbing flour with Ritz crackers and even added some to the bottom(crushed) as a bed for the cod to sit on.  Nothing soggy about this dish.  The leftover lemon and butter I poured  over the fish before baking.  Perfectly done at 30 minutes.  Will make again!

name: crock pot garlic brown sugar chicken
review: This was wonderful! I used a whole cut-up chicken - skin, bones and all. Instead of the 7-up, I used 1 teaspoon lemon juice. Like most crock pot chicken recipes, I liked the dark pieces of meat the best. They were the most tender and moist. But really, all of the pieces of chicken were fall-off-the-bone tender! This made A LOT of sauce, so I ladled some out of the crock pot and put it in a saucepan on the stove. I added a slurry of 1 Tbsp. cornstarch to 1 Tbsp. water and simmered. Then I just kept adding more slurry to get the consistency I wanted. I served it over rice. A very easy and delicious dish!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Easy and Delicious!  Everyone in my family loved this chicken, including 5 children.  It is often hard to please ALL 5 children!  My son who doesn't like mayo even liked it---of course, I did not tell him that it was smothered in mayo.  Make it; you won't be sorry.

name: steel cut oatmeal for the crock pot
