review: This is certainly different than other oatmeals, but we liked it a lot.  The texture is different, but appealing and it cooked perfectly.  I served it with some stewed peaches.  Delicious.  Thank you for sharing this amazing breakfast with us.

name: buttery farm biscuits
review: These are delicious.  And I have to say they are easy, my DS (11 yr old) made these for our Fathers Day breakfast.  They turned out great!  Thank you for sharing, we loved them and I loved seeing my DS so proud of his baking.  What a great day!

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: I made dinner rolls and used 1/8 cup of sugar.  I didn't want them too sweet.  They have a light texture.  Great taste.  Thanks DDW :)  Made for Name that ingredient tag game

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: My kids are loving this coffee cake!  It is moist and delicious.  The only change I made was to add a splash of vanilla.  I also didn't think it needed the extra dusting of powdered sugar; it was delicious on its own.  This would be a great coffee cake to take to a breakfast or brunch as it is pretty as well as delicious!

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: These muffins are so yummy.  I used 1/4 cup sugar instead of 1/2 cup.  Thanks Manda :)  Made for Name that ingredient tag game

name: hawaiian chicken kabobs
review: These chicken kabobs were a big success.  The chicken was in the marinade overnight.  The taste was so good.  The chicken was tender.  Thanks MizzNezz :)  Made for Cookbook tag game

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Great flavor - used boneless chicken thighs, baked at 375 for 35 min, then flipped for an additional 10 min. Used fresh garlic and ginger in the sauce - plenty of flavor without marinating. Served over rice - amazing!

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: This was really delicious. The chicken was cooked perfectly and very moist. A definite go to recipe. Thanks!

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: Great fish recipe.  It was very easy and quick.  Will make this many times again as I loved the sauce on the fish.  It really added an extra flavor.  May try  on tilapia.

name: parmesan zucchini
review: We loved this quick and easy way of preparing zucchini! I combined 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/2 tsp. seasoned salt, & 1/2 tsp. garlic powder in a pie plate.  I rolled the zucchini wedges in some olive oil and dredged them in the cheese mixture.  After putting them in the baking dish, I sprinkled any remaining cheese mixture over the tops of the squash. I baked them until the cheese started to brown...yummy!!  I will be preparing this recipe often to use up the over abundance of zucchini that my garden produces each year.  Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper!!

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: Leave it to me to fail at a "no fail pie crust"!  I used this to make recipe#128566 128566 since I usually use store-bought crust...I didn't add enough of the water/egg mixture so it was a little dry going into the fridge; I thought it would be fine, but rolling it out it fell apart.  It did not make a pretty crust, but it still tasted good.  I will be making this again and add more liquid.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: This is a great soup!  I have never had black bean soup so this is a great first try!  I made 1/2 the recipe since it was just me eating it (still have lots of leftovers), I used a red pepper instead of green and left out the cayenne.  Was very filling and not too spicy for me.  I topped it with cheddar cheese and green onions; will be making this in the winter time often.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: Definitely 5 stars for this one!!!!  I love it and I know it would be wonderful without the changes I had to make in order to use what I had on hand:  1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce for 1/2 cup of the butter, plain Greek yogurt for the sour cream, and semi-sweet chocolate chips in place of the milk chocolate ones.  The only thing I will do differently next time is to mash my bananas up better than I did.  I had some visible banana chunks in mine which I would have preferred not to have, but that's not the fault of the recipe.  Thanks so much for this delicious recipe!

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Really good and very easy! I increased the recipe, used the individually frozen wings from Costco (unthawed), enough to fill my stock pot, then placed on a foil-lined sheet pan sprayed with oil, and broiled at 425 in the middle of the oven for 15 minutes on each side. Then just tossed in a bowl with Franks Buffalo Wings sauce. They were perfectly cooked. Next time I would make two sheet pans worth, these were gone in no time. Definitely better and better for you than purchased wings. I'll try BBQ and other wing sauces, too. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: wholesome homemade honey whole wheat bread
review: Hands down the best wheat bread I have ever made.  Despite being more than 50% whole wheat, this made a really soft and fluffy loaf of bread.  After spending a lot of time and too many valuable ingredients making brick after brick of wheat sandwich bread, I am very happy to finally have a winning product.  Thanks for posting this recipe!  Note:  I cut the recipe down to make one loaf and did not alter anything else.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: This is very reminiscent of how my mother use to make these when I was growing up.  The recipe was reduced in half and made 3 nice patties which is perfect for the 2 of us.  I did add in some chopped green pepper.  The patties were served with Recipe #428248 and Recipe #16533 for a very nice meal.  This is something I will make again.  Thanks for posting.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: We loved this - used diet ginger ale but other wise followed the recipe as written -- only cooked for 8 hours before shredding on adding bq sauce and cooked for another 4 1/2 hours or so. My butt roast was 4 1/2 pounds which was on sale and this was the perfect way to use it! Thanks for sharing!

name: amy sedaris s vanilla cupcakes
review: Excellent cupcake!  (I didn't make the icing)  Usually I am not a big fan of vanilla cupcakes because they taste dry - not this one.  I highly recommend these!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: Perfect summer patio dinner.  Thanks so much.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Loved it!  The only thing I added was fresh cilantro, and these were so good.  So easy to make too!  Thanks for sharing.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: We just finished with dinner tonight. Hubby and I both liked these, but they are just not what we are use to. I rated this just on the recipe itself. It could use some tweaking, but I did not. I wanted to stay true to the original recipe. We still prefer the way I normally make them (yes... I  use condensed cream of chicken soup, picante sauce and some cream cheese, etc). Thank you for posting. (Made for" Name That Ingreient" tag)

name: jalapeno popper burgers
review: Wonderful recipe. I happened to have some jalapeno cream cheese in the fridge, so it worked out perfectly. Thank you.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Loved this marinade.  We used boneless, skinless, thighs.  Defiinitely will be making this again.   Made for Name that Ingredient.

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: Had a bunch of my kids' friends over hanging out. They all wanted sloppy joes, so tried this out on them. Added just a little prepared mustard, cause couldn't taste the dry. Also would decrease celery to one rib. Easy to prepare and we enjoyed it. Thanks.

name: kittencal s juicy hamburger burger
review: I had between 2 and 2.5 lbs of ground beef. So, I used the whole pack of onion soup mix, a little more minced garlic than called for, italian breadcrumbs with a couple of crumbled saltines added and homemade hot (and I mean hot) hot sauce.  They were very wet, so I was a little concerned, but I guess it was unfounded.  DH loved them!  We grilled them and served them with fresh corn on the cob and baby red potatoes with rosemary, garlic butter.  This recipe is a keeper!!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: My husband loved these, but I thought they were missing a zing of something.  I think I'll go with granulated garlic next time to see if that's it.  I cheated a bit to not heat up the house so much by pre-cooking my wings in the crock pot, then I poured the glaze over and cooked it on in about 20 minutes in the oven with convection and finishing up with broiler, turning once to coat as the sauce thickened.  I love how this sauce thickened and coated everything, and liked it more after it sat a bit as far as flavor.  I'll definitely try it again, even tho the carb count kept me from eating many, which my husband had no complaints over, either.  ;-)  Thanks for sharing.

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: I loved this, as did my non spaghetti squash eating husband, so high praise!  I used half of a huge squash, so the amounts were probably the same, but cooked in the microwave to save prep time.  I added some extra veg, sauteed onion, celery, and garlic, since I only had mild Ro-tel tomatoes.  Also added sliced black olives.  I was worried about the liquid since the can of tomato was smaller, but it still had a bit of standing liquid in the bottom after baking so I think it was all good.  I used a shredded pepper jack, rather than plain jack cheese, and garnished with sour cream before serving.  Will definitely make this again.  Leftovers reheated very well the next day.  Thanks for sharing!

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: This was delicious, delicate flavours. Omitted the bacon since I will not eat it and used turkey stock in place of chicken stock as that is what I had on hand. Just gorgeous. Got 6 meals from this. Thanks for a lovely dinner.

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: That bread was wonderful! I used half whole wheat flower and half all purpose flower and added some seeds, the bread had just the right consistency, not too dense but not spongy either. Makes great toast! This is my new "go to" recipe!

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: This was great.  I baked on a non-stick cookie sheet and needed no spray at all.  I think panko would be a great substitute for the breadcrumbs, which I'll probably try next time.  We served ours on ciabatta rolls with lettuce and tomato for a yummy sandwich!

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: These are really good.  So easy to do in advance and then when ready just heat in the oven.  I made half the recipe for the 3 of us and we had leftovers.  Thanks Helping Hands :)  Made for Name that ingredient tag game

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: So good! This is definitely my favorite way of cooking brussels sprouts. I added a drizzle of balsamic at the end but otherwise followed the recipe!

name: baked ham and cheese omelet roll
review: I made this for dinner tonight.  It was fairly simple to make.  It didn't want to stay rolled up so I would probably just fold it next time.  DD didn't like it at all. I ate the small slice on my plate but I really felt that the flower taste was just too strong. DH, however, thought that it was just right. I great basic recipe that I will adjust  more to our tastes if I make it again.  Served with Timberlodge's Lumberjack Hash Browns.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: As everyone else says, "fall off the  bone tender". The broth was fantastic!  Thanks

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: These cookies are amazing!  So simple and yet people think you worked hard at them!  I live in a very humid country, so we went with the white sugar coating.  They're beautiful!  Next time I'll try adding the vanilla, but I think they're perfect as-is.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: I made this 90% as written. I had some leftover roast lamb that I also threw in just to use it up. The wine I used was a shiraz. Only change to method was at the end I was too hungry to wait so cut the last two cooking steps in half. I also used fresh herbs rather than dried since I have them handy. Served with some mashed potatos. I really like this stew, it's beautiful and rich and was quite easy to make. Thanks for sharing.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: Best Garlic Mashed Potatoes I ever made!  Based on Chef #669074's recommendation, I sliced off the top off the whole head of garlic before sprinkling with olive oil, and baked for 40 minutes.  Based on several reviews, I used 2 heads of garlic for 4 people, and even then the garlic did not overpower.  My new go-to recipe!

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: Wonderful! I tented with tinfoil near the end and used purple cauliflower. The dish was very good, thanks.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: Really nice flavour but didn't get crispy.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Very good! Tons of blueberries. I used frozen wild berries and topped with natural sugar rather than the nutmeg mixture. Made 18 regular-sized muffins. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: enchilada sauce
review: I made this to go with Kittencal's Recipe #172232 and it was really good!! I liked that it was mild so my grandkids would eat it. I doubled it and froze 1/2 for another time. Thanks for posting..this one is a keeper!

name: roasted broccoli w lemon garlic   toasted pine nuts
review: Great broccoli!!  I made as directed and it came out perfect.  I like the flavor of lemon and broccoli, but not a ton of lemon flavoring.  Will definitely be making this again!  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: lentil soup for people who thought they hated lentils    meat op
review: Yummy and versatile. I used what I had on hand. Instead if vegetable stock I used home-made lamb stock with the addition of water, extra organic garlic, organic onion, no red capsicum, carrots or celery but I did add one organic Swiss chard stock cut up, organic spinach from our weekly local organic produce basket, no tomatoes, just organic tomato paste, no leek but I put organic garlic whistles also from the CSA basket in place of the green beans which added some extra flavour, chopped zucchini instead of mushroom, organic fresh flat leaf parsley, dried oregano in a lesser amount, the fresh basil, grey sea salt, a perfect salt, a bit of home-made garlic whistle and spinach pesto made with Romano cheese, ate right when cooked with a square of organic butter on top and recipe#275175 served on the side.

name: no bake rice krispies peanut butter granola bars  lower fat
review: Made these for DD#2 camping trip and they were delicious.  I didn't chill the mini chips and they melted in my bars, but no matter they were still very good.  They held together nicely (unlike some others Ive tried) and withstood the heat outside.  A big thank you for sharing with us your recipe.

name: light and fluffy pumpkin pancakes
review: Oh my are these good.  I made these for breakfast the other day and my kids and I loved them.  The spices really stood out in these and combined with maple syrup.....yummmmm.  Thank you for sharing with us, I plan on making these our Thanksgiving breakfast from now on.  So good.

name: crock pot ham and beans
review: This is delicious and easy to make. Because we try not to eat pork(because of health and religious reasons) I use smoked turkey wings or drumsticks. I throw in a package of onion soup and a shot of liquid smoke to the recipe. Thanks Sue.

name: denny s style french toast
review: Delicious! I added 2 tbls of sugar rather than 1/4 cup. We served this with homemade maple syrup and it got completely eaten up. Thank you!

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: It was so easy to do at the last minute.  So yummy.  Thanks ratherbeswimmin :)  Made for Name that ingredient tag game

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: These were yummy. I made them with chicken and black beans. I added some cilantro to the marinade and served with guacamole rather than sour cream.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: Hey Carol, this is definitely a 5 STAR recipe! My husband and I so enjoyed it. I didn't think this was dry as others have stated, it was very creamy. I did add 1 (12 oz.) can of tuna, plus I added 1 tsp. garlic powder, 3 Tbsp. of parmesan cheese, 3/4 cup of sour cream, 1/2 tsp. each seasoned salt & pepper, and a (2 oz.) jar of pimiento(s). I didn't have any celery or green peppers, so I added about (8 oz.) of slightly cooked peas & carrots, as they were from a frozen bag. I did not add the 2 Tbsp. of butter to the noodles, cause I already added 1 Tbsp. of butter to the boiling water when I cooked the noodles. I topped the casserole with 15 (generic) ritz crackers, and topped the crushed crackers with 2 Tbsp. of melted butter. I think this dish would taste great using other canned soups, such as: cream of chicken with herbs, or cream of chicken & mushroom soup. I plan on substituting other vegetables for the celery & green peppers, such as: either corn or canned mushrooms. Thank you Carol for sharing this recipe. This recipe is definitely a keeper!!

name: cake batter ice cream
review: Wow is this sweet... but it sure is good. Will definitely make again but with less sugar.

name: patti labelle s macaroni and cheese
review: This was really good! Made it with gluten-free macaroni and it worked well. The only changes I would make would be to cut the Velveeta into much smaller chunks so it gets more evenly distributed and also to add more seasoning salt.

name: ground beef gyros
review: Delicious! Since a lot of reviewers were complaining about the hamburger taste, I added half of a ground zucchini to the meat. It turned out great! I also made homemade flour tortillas #204109, which are better than pitas any store bought tortillas. For the sauce, I used recipe # 129930 since I had all of its ingredients on hand. The only other change I made was to add feta cheese. It came together well! Next time I'll add banana peppers and kalamata olives. Thanks!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Really good! I omitted nuts in topping, otherwise made as stated. Only change I'd make next time would be to make 15 muffins. With 12, the topping spilled out onto the pan. Maybe my bananas were larger than normal? Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: Very tasty!  I used my husbands homemade salsa from the garden, 3/4 teaspoon chili powder, 1 teaspoon cumin.  I left the corn and the beans out and used chicken thighs.  My whole family liked it.  I had enough to take for lunch tomorrow.  Thanks for posting!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Very yummy - I used just 2 potatoes with the regular amount of  and it turned out well. Although next time I'll cook for longer as they didnt brown as much as I would have liked.

name: crock pot chops that will make you eat til you pop
review: My hubby really liked this dish and it was so simple to prepare. I used four pork chops, but cut all of the rest of the ingredients in half. This seemed to create just the right amount of topping. Really good with rice and the chops were so tender!

name: easy cole slaw
review: Yum!<br/>This was the first time I've made cole slaw and it turned out amazing. I used 1/2 head of green cabbage, 2 carrots and kept all of the other measurements the same. I split the sugar between white and raw, just because I ran out of white. This was so delicious, I'm looking forward to experimenting with it. Thanks for posting!

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: I really don't know why I'm posting my review here...there are so many great ones already...I guess I just want to be able to know I've made this delicious dish...I prepared it using chicken tenderloins and cooking them on skewers...I marinaded the meat for 48 hours and it came out so tender and moist...we loved the flavors...thanks for posting it =)

name: company pork roast
review: Delicious! I used a Hormel Pork Tenderloin, pure maple syrup instead of honey, and white wine vinegar. Make sure you use a small pan so the sauce doesn't spread out and burn. And be sure to baste!

name: copycat  green giant niblets corn in butter sauce
review: This was very good,  Will make again for sure!  Thanks for the recipe!

name: hot german potato salad
review: Excellent --Made it for the 4th of July!!

name: blender quiche   or whatever you have in your kitchen leftover
review: I've made this several times now and it always comes out great. Love that it is so versatile. Thanks, Tish.

name: sugar cookie icing
review: Stays glossy but firms up nicely. Used 2t more corn syrup and a touch more milk for spreadable consistency. Used vanilla in red and blue colored icing and almond extract (clear) in white icing. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: This was really good stuff. I used 2 boxes of Stove Top stuffing mix and left out the cheese. We really enjoyed it and I'm sad there are no more leftovers.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: Great, refreshing recipe. I did not have basil on hand, so I used dried cilantro. I also left out the garlic salt, substituting in table salt instead. I added chopped avocado for an additional flavor to the salad and the dish was gobbled up. Thanks for sharing!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: I agree with everyone that this is a fabulous banana cake.  I'm not a big fan of banana loaf but enjoy this cake because it's moist & fluffy, not to mention tasty.  I thought the oven temperature was low also so I bumped it to 300 F.  It cooked up nicely but only ended up ending cooking time 5 mins earlier.  I did the freezer trick, but only did is 30 mins.  We also aren't big fans of frosting, the cake was delicious without it.  Thanks for sharing.

name: lemon tea cookies
review: Oh My !! I haven't had cookies this good in such a long time. I don't usually make many cookies anymore. These were absolutely worth it. I must of made them a bit bigger because I only came out with 29 cookies, and I suppose that is why they took a few extra minutes in the oven. I too made my thumbprint in them again as soon as they came out of the oven. Made for a nicer indent for that delicious lemon filling. It was the perfect amount of lemony taste. This is definitely a make again recipe. Thanks so much for the recipe post Lavender Lynn. Made for the Comfort Cafe '09<br/><br/>UPDATE: I have made these so many more times since '09 and just wanted to mention since I didn't go back to update before that to be sure to use real lemon zest off of a fresh lemon or the color will not be a bright yellow. Also I used a Melon ball scoop to get the right size and made 35 each time. But it definitely takes a good extra 5 minutes in the oven. I have to keep mine in for 15 minutes. So you just may want to watch this when you make them. I just did another batch this week to bring to work and they all raved about how delicious they were and they all want the recipe. Just want to say thanks again for sharing.

name: easy way lasagna
review: The first time I made this I didn't expect much.  I wondered how good it could be with just basic ingredients, no extra seasonings, meat or veggies. I even put a Italian seasoning grinder on when I set the table, just in case.  Well, no one needed it.  A basic but terrific lasagna.  UPDATE: When I made it tonight I altered it a little because my fridge/freezer went out and I needed to use things up. I probably used more of some ingredients than called for. My cottage cheese was low fat. I had about 1/4 of a green bell pepper, and a couple of slices of sweet onion that I diced and sauteed. I added them to some veggie crumbles I had left over and put them in the center layer of the lasagna.  It still made a great lasagna, everyone went back for seconds!  DD even asked if we could have it again this week.  Served with garlic bread and salad.

name: strawberry shortcake a la treebeard s
review: Didn't make the cream but was wonderful.

name: very moist banana nut bread
review: Very tasty Banana Nut Bread.  It was so moist and yummy.  Thanks for posting.

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: I made this recipe for dinner Friday night, and all I can say is "Awesome"! I didn't change a thing, other than I used my compound butter (which has garlic, chive & scallion in it). I did not use the optional marjorum (I don't keep that in my cupboard). I love the tang from the sour cream and cream cheese. I served these with a meatloaf and also Recipe #415550, and it made a truely delightful meal. I will be making these again. Thank you for posting this recipe. (Made for Name That Ingredient tag)

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: These ribs turned out great! I brushed with a very small amount of liquid smoke, but next time will leave it out.

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: This is a beautiful dish indeed and also so easy.    To make it even more attractive I roasted some red peppers, cut them in strips and added before serving. Just a suggestion......  irregardless it is lovely.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: These were good, but next time would shred the chicken instead of cubing it. I sauteed it with some seasoning. Liked the sauce with the green chilies, but when making for us again, would add in extra for more spice. These went over well with us and our company. Makes quite a bit, will try putting some in the freezer.

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: This bakes up really beautiful.  We loved it.  I like the fact the the bread machine does most of the work.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: As if this recipe needed another 5 star review! This was a hit in our house. I doubled the recipe as I used the pudding to make a pie. I poured the pudding into a chocolate pie crust, layered it with bananas, and spread white chocolate shavings on top. Also to make this recipe nearly sugar-free I used 20 packets of Equal to sweeten the pudding instead of sugar. If you do decide to use artificial sweetener, make sure to stir it into the pudding AFTER cooking. This recipe is so easy that I'll never use the packaged version again. Thanks for posting!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: This spaghetti sauce is so good.  I used spicy italian sausages and merlot red wine.  Thanks Sharlene :)  Made for Name that ingredient tag game

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: Very flavorful.  Just the right balance of lemon and herbs.  Will make extra next time as I didn't have any left over for lunch the next day.

name: kittencal s extreme chocolate brownies
review: AMAZING! Kept well sitting out for a couple days, too. Our goto brownie recipe! My only caveat is that the edges cook WELL before the center. I read on here this may be because of the chocolate chips. I will need to try with melting them all, next time, to see if that helps. Keep an eye on 'em in the oven and if anyone has any suggestions for a more even cooking, please let me know. (I DID try to cover them while cooking, but it didn't help.)<br/><br/>Edited to add: I've made these several times since. Here are my thoughts:<br/><br/>1. Don't over cook or cook until they look "done." If you do that, it will end up like a very dry cake with all of your chocolate chips on the bottom somewhat dry and slightly burned.<br/><br/>2. Instead, cook the brownies in a LARGE pan (they really rise from all those eggs!) until they no longer shake like jelly in the middle when you shake the pan. Once it's firm enough not to shake, leave them in another minute or two and then take them out! THEY WILL NOT LOOK DONE! But, once they cool, they will firm up into very fudgy ooey gooey brownies that are absolutely heavenly.<br/><br/>3. Enjoy!

name: wet burritos
review: Five stars!!! It is because of recipes like this that I love to try new foods.  These were amazing, I have never had a "wet" burrito before and I can guarantee you, I will be enjoying them again and again.  I couldn't find Mexican Oregano (Australia has limited Mexican food items) other than that made as written.  Thank you for posting!

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: I have made this a couple of times now, and it is delicious. Just like Thanksgiving in a pot. I forgot to use the milk in the soup and it still turned out wonderful. I think the swiss cheese really makes this especially good. I served it with a side of cranberry sauce. All I can say is YUM!

name: dark chocolate cake
review: My daughter used this recipe to make cupcakes for my son's graduation party.  The texture and flavor were perfect.  She frosted them with chocolate ganache.  So good!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Like other reviewers, I used 1/2 italian sausage and 1/2 ground chuck.  Drained the fat off before adding the onions.  I kept reading over the recipe looking for the oregano...LOL.  I made it exactly as posted and we really enjoyed it.  Didn't miss the oregano at all.  I did add a splash more wine.  I simmered for 4 hours....its even better the next day.  Thanks for sharing!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: For us this was perfect! We have never had Tilapia before,we will again though.Thanks

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: This was easy and awesome! I used my own home made mixes because I can't get them here in Germany and also needed a gluten free gravy mix. It worked so well, the meat came out tender and moist, so delicious! I mixed in some mixed vegetables at the end of the cooking process (45 minutes before serving) which was the perfect addition. Thanks for posting this!<br/>Made for Eating Well While Staying Cool / Diabetes Forum

name: chicken pasta milano
review: Love it and no changes necessary for us.;  Had to cut in half for two but that makes no difference.   Thanks for a great pasta recipe and one fit for company.

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: Almost never give a recipe here for Irish soda bread a 5 rating but this one is exceptional. Granted it is very rich and not one I would make on a regular basis but certainly worth a top rating.

name: mini tacos
review: Great finger food. The only thing I did differently was to bake the wonton wrappers for about 5 minutes before putting in the filling/cheese-- then baked 5-8 minutes more.(at 350 degrees because there was something else in the oven) This helps the bottom of the taco bite not get soggy. Thanks!

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Great pancakes !! I've made them twice this month for guests & they were well-rec'd both times. On the 1st occasion, they were made exactly as written. For the 2nd occasion, they were also made as written .. BUT I added a homemade gingerbread spice blend to the batter & swooned over the outcome. These babies are now my go-to recipe of choice for pancakes. Thx for sharing this recipe w/us. :-)

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: Wonderful muffins.  Made as written except using lemon zest and frozen blueberries.  Got 17 regular sized muffins to enjoy.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: I would have been daft to not try a cake with so many wonderful reviews! This really is an awesome carrot cake. I doubt I'll ever need another recipe! I made a few small changes. I subbed tofu for the eggs to keep things vegan, added a smidge of nutmeg, and used part brown sugar, and used pecans. My feather (lifelong carrot cake nut) said it was the best ever!

name: copycat recipe for carrabba s chicken marsala
review: What a simple and delicious recipe.  We loved it and will certainly make it again.

name: easiest beef enchiladas ever
review: I have made these at least a half a dozen times and my family really digs 'em!  Great recipe & oh so fast!

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: Good! A cakey cobbler, best served with ice cream. Used frozen wild blueberries, and may use 1/2 cup more next time. Quick to fix and gone in a flash. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: Amazing shrimp! Definitely spicy, but not overly so. The lemon and parsley did a nice job of balancing the dish out. I added a splash of white wine with the lemon juice, but otherwise followed the recipe. Served as a main dish with herb rice and fresh salad as sides.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: Another 5 star review? Yeah, well, I figure I need to pay tribute. I have made this twice and both times there was nary a crumb left, except for the skin and the cat made short work of that. A definite keeper -- thank you for sharing!!!

name: easy garlic chicken
review: This was average.  Nothing bad about it.....nothing great.  If I was in a jam and didn't have a lot in the house, I might throw it together, but I wouldn't go out of my way to make it a regular part of our dinner rotation.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Yummy

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: We enjoyed this recipe.  Quick & easy to make.  Enjoyed the addition of the lemon pepper & nice variation for the tortilla vs a quiche bottom.  Increased the bacon & added one more egg and it was perfect for us, thanks for sharing.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: I some how forgot to rate this and have been making it for over 12 months!  Fabulous and easy, great to cook a chook for meals that require coked and shredded chicken or to have shredded chicken in the freezer.  If I am making this for that nights dinner, I always add small new potatoes on the bottom.  Such a great recipe!!!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Great!  I was hesitant to try it because of the mayonaise, but I am sure glad I decided to go ahead and give it a try.  The chicken had a nice flavor and was moist.  Thanks for sharing.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Yummy lasagna! I did use regular spaghetti sauce instead of making it, though. Next time, I'll put it in a bigger pan because I didn't have room for everything in my 9x13. Thanks!

name: parmesan zucchini
review: Most of the parm ended up on the pan after baking (even after dredging) .  I suggest cutting the tips off of the wedges to create more surface area on top.  The wedges I experimented with turned out much better that way.

name: treebeard s red beans  and rice
review: Close to being too hot for us but OMG SOO GOOD!!  And very easy.  It just takes time.  Delicious!!  Made for ZWT9 for Mike & the Appliance Killers for the HolyTrinity Challenge. Thank you!

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Great pancakes.  Just perfect to flip.  Served with homemade chokecherry syrup and sausage.  YUM.

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Great tasting crust! Not my favorite because I prefer a thinner, crispier crust, but this was very good. It would make great breadsticks. Thanks!

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: So simple and SO good!

name: self rising flour
review: Thank you! I needed self rising flour for recipe#503604, which I am making for ZWT9, but only have AP flour in the house.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: This was ok but a bit bland. I used 1 tsp salt but would use a bit more next time. I did love how fast and easy this was, though.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: I use this recipe all the time and it always turns out great.  Can believe how easy it is to make a tasty pot roast!  This a keeper and one of my favorite recipes on this site.  It's so easy!  I cook the roast all day, then skim the fat off the juices and thicken the juices to make gravy.

name: mean guy s general tso s chicken
review: This is definitely a good General Tso's recipe....not the best I've found but very good.  I halved the amount of chicken but left the sauce amount alone.  I wanted some sauce for my steamed broccoli. I also increased the pepper to chicken amount, but I like things spicy.  Served over jasmine rice, and this was a very good dinner!! Thanks for sharing your adopted recipe.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: Whole family loved these!  Thanks Dari....

name: cajun sauteed shrimp
review: Love these...easy and so flavorful! Made for ZWT #9.

name: cheese tortellini pesto pasta salad
review: I loved the flavor of this dish and to boot, no mayo.  I omitted the mozzarella and rotini as I was serving 4 people.  I know that I'll be making it often this summer because it is such a flexible dish.

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: We really enjoyed this recipe!  It was by far the best sloppy joes I've ever made. I served them on big, soft bakery hamburger buns.  They were such a huge hit.  Thank you!

name: thai coconut rice
review: This was a great recipe!  I made as written only I didn't used the ginger (didn't have any) and I toasted the almonds.  I used jasmine rice and served this with recipe#480070#480070 and a tomato, onion, cucumber and celery salad.  DH and I had a great dinner.  Going into my Favorites of 2013.  Thank you for posting.

name: super peanut butter filled brownies
review: Oh, my!  Those are some incredible brownies!  The peanut butter filling tastes like the center of a Buckeye Ball candy or a Reese's.  Chocolate and peanut butter, how can you go wrong?  Made these without the mixer and they turned out fine and much less mess to clean up. It was hard to get the filling on the brownie because everyone wanted to keep "taste testing" the filling!  Thanks for posting!

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: I thought I had reviewed this recipe already - I have used it several times in the past.  This week I used this recipe to make meat pies, and Recipe #60976.  It always comes together quickly, and is much easier to work with than the crisco, flour and ice water recipe that used to be my standby crust. :)

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: I have made these about a dozen times now without reviewing them.  1165 reviews seemed like plenty of feedback lol BUT I can find the recipe so much faster if I review them. :)<br/>As evidenced by making them a dozen times in 6 months we think they are wonderful.  I keep it fairly simple and just add walnuts to the batter.  For a glaze or icing I sprinkled chocolate chips on the top for the last 6 or 7 minutes of baking.  After a few minutes out of the oven the chocolate is very spreadable.  Definitely my 'go to' brownie recipe.  Thanks for sharing!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: As if this recipe needs another great review, but there is a reason there are so many. These were simply awesome.. The DS repeatedly said "Honey, did I tell you how great dinner was".. Based on other reviews, I made only minor "tweaks". Since our preference is to shred the chicken first, I used 2 large bone in split chicken breasts. Seasoned them with garlic powder, onion powder, cumin, Mexican oregano, salt and pepper. Roasted them in the over for an hour. I also made sure I used the pan drippings in the sauce. I sprinkled the leftover seasoning mix on the chicken after shredding. For the cheese in the filling, I crumbled queso fresco cheese, then used the cheddar / jack blend for the top (I mean really, why not have more cheese!). Other than that, I made as stated. Although next time I make these (and there will be a next time!) I wonder if I should add some black olives... hmmm..

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: My husband recently joined WW so I fixed this tonight to go with broccoli and corn on the cob with V8 juice.  We both thought it is good and was very moist.  I did brush a little olive oil on the pan because I did not use a nonstick baking sheet.  Thanks for the recipe.<br/><br/>07/20/13  I forgot to add that I turned them over after 10 minutes baking and used a spatula to pick up what fell off and placed what fell off on top.

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: Excellent cookies! Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: Great bread, I made this for something different to do with my left over bananas and it sure was different.  Almost like a "brownie Bread" I made it into mini loaves as we usually don't finish a large one but have to tell you - TWO of them were gone almost before they finished cooling.  I also used semi sweet mini chips and glad I did.  Loved the moist texture and know we'll be using this one again.

name: perfect pasta salad
review: We liked this pasta salad but I would probably cut the onion down a bit next time. It was good but I'll be on the look out for a better go-to salad.

name: teresa s veal  or chicken piccata
review: Delicious and easy!  Love the capers, so I added just a tad more.  Served with angel hair pasta with a parmesan cream sauce and spinach.  Delicious! Thanks for posting.

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: Fabulous!  My family loved this for dessert, and since I doubled it we had enough for a decadent breakfast the next morning.  I added a bit more blueberries, and slightly decreased the sugar sprinkled on top.  YUM.

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: A great pot of soup!  I only used one can of cream soup, and I liked it.  Bonus point for how tweakable this recipe is, although it tastes delicious & comforting as is.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: I discovered our mayo was way past date, so I ended up using miracle whip.  I think I got it too thick because it didn't make the "crust" like it was supposed to.  But we just didn't eat the excess sauce and it was good.  It did taste "miracle whippy" but I like that flavor, so it was fine.  I would think with mayo, the seasonings used would come through more.   I ate the leftovers a couple of days later and it was still moist.  My 6 and 8 year olds gobbled it up and I was able to bribe my 2 year old to eat it, so that makes this recipe a winner :). Five stars especially because of how easy this was.  I don't like to touch chicken, so I used 6 of the schwans unbreaded chicken breast fillets.  Mixing the ingredients up was super quick.  In fact it took me longer to look for new mayo than to do the rest of the prep!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Great flavor, easy to make, very moist.  I really enjoyed this!

name: mexican stuffed shells  oamc
review: You know a recipe is fantastic when you make it once, then can't stop thinking about making it again. These were great! As long as you don't mind getting your hands messy when stuffing the shells, they were easy to make too. Thanks!!!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: Dh loves this recipe! Have even made twice. Second time I tripled and had in crockpot for three hours-- celery came out with a bit of texture which we like. For us,  the celery amount is fine. I did reduce catsup, barbecue sauce, and sugar a bit.  Thanks for sharing your wonderful recipe with us.

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: Found a recipe I wanted to try,  recipe #17586, that called for enchilada sauce so I decided to try this.  So glad I did.  I really enjoyed it on my enchiladas and will use it whenever  I  make them from now on.  This sauce was so easy to put together and didn't take much time at all.  The only thing I changed was to cut the recipe in half for a half recipe of enchiladas.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: A good, basic marinade for grilling chicken, reminiscent of the American Legion barbecued chicken I had every summer as a kid. We had pretty large leg quarters, and knew it would take longer, lower heat to cook them, so we cut the sugar in half so it wouldn't burn. Also, my husband thought "whole grain" mustard meant ground mustard seeds, but thankfully he he put in only 1 1/2 tablespoons of ground mustard seeds instead of prepared mustard. Very tasty!

name: easiest beef enchiladas ever
review: Believe it or not, in all my 67 years, I haven't had an enchilada...not until today, that is.  And I so enjoyed it.  Except for cutting the recipe in half, I followed it closely and found it both simple and easy to put together.  Also,  I like that it called for  basic ingredients that I already had on hand.     For the sauce, I used recipe #42094, and that's what I plan on using when I make these again.  Great recipe, MizzNezz!  Thanks for sharing it.

name: chewy granola bars
review: Per the other reviews, I used omitted the white sugar.  We are allergic to nuts so I substituted Grape Nut cereal for the almonds, and whole wheat flour.  Tasted like a cookie, very sweet.  Next time I will reduce the amount of brown sugar to 3/4 cup and up the rice crispie cereal to 2 cups because that adds a little airy crunch.  We had it for a dessert after dinner.  I suggested reducing the amount of chocolate chips but the kids said NO.  Thank you for a great recipe.

name: perfect pasta salad
review: We enjoyed it.

name: cajun sauteed shrimp
review: I liked that these weren't cooked in tons of butter; however, I do like the taste of butter on shrimp so I use 1/2 Tbs butter and 1/2 Tbs olive oil to cook these.  They have a nice bite to them, but not overpowering.  Made for ZWT9.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Add another 5 stars for me! These are awesome!! Love the chilling of the baking sheets! My grandkids loved these! We greased the pan because they were hard to get off. Thanks for sharing!!

name: roast  sticky  chicken
review: Very good! I didn't bother with the bag; just covered the pan of chicken wi/ plastic wrap while marinating. We needed to eat earlier than I expected and the chicken was done nicely, at 4.25 hours baking time.<br/>**Made it again, but it's too hot for the oven! I put it in the crockpot, on high for 2 hours and low for 2 hours- WONDERFUL! Even the breast was moist!!

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: Yum! I love this type of salad, and this did not disappoint. The only thing I changed was the olives, I used garlic stuffed green instead of kalamata. Thanks for sharing! <br/><br/><br/>made for ZWT9

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: Nice batter! We used a dark ale (as that's what I had on hand). Yes, the batter turned a brown color, but it was the beer! Yum. Will make again.

name: kittencal s bakery buttercream  frosting icing
review: Your recipes are spot on though so turn to them. added my changes for recipe and my gall bladder requirements. Used for an  almond cake I had filled with lemon pie filling so used some of the pie filling, halved the margarine only used butter and for Crisco halved that but used butter flavored Crisco. since added the pie filling had to increase the confectioners sugar but all and all it was wonderful and people love the recipes I glean from you.

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: I can't say I've ever had Taco Bells Mexican Pizza, so my review is not based on closeness of the original or copycat recipe. I was looking for something different with Mexican flavors and this hit the spot! Family loved it (including the kiddos). Thanks for sharing!

name: cajun sauteed shrimp
review: I made this shrimps for me and DH.  They were spicy and yummy.  So easy to do.  Thanks PanNan :) Made for ZWt9

name: homemade hamburger buns  bread machine
review: These were pretty good and the rolling and cutting out made them pretty uniform. I prefer a very light and airy bun; however, this one is a bit more dense and perhaps a bit sweeter than I would like.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Made this last night and the whole family loved it - including a very picky eater nephew who declared it "the best" it was so easy that even that 6 year old nephew made most of it with only a little supervision.  I made as directed with only one small change - adding an extra 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese as that finished off what I had on hand.  It made a lot and that's good as we'll be having the left overs today.  Had the wonderful, creamy, cheesy goodness we love, and looked pretty too - who could ask for more.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Wish I could rate this higher.  I had high hopes for this, given all the great reviews.  Probably just a matter of personal preferences, but my family and I did not enjoy this.  I'm afraid it might have been the gross pink color that was so off-putting.  It's hard to give it a fair chance on how it tastes when it looks so icky to begin with.

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: Fantastic coffee cake!!! Light and fluffy and just plain good.  Easily converted to gluten free using my favorite gluten free flour - Gluten Free Mama's Almond Blend.  Thanks for posting Katie!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Great recipe. The only change I made was choice of steak. We used ribeye because they looked really fresh at the meat counter! Other than that, made as posted and just as good as any restaurant. Thanks for sharing!

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: This was a great sauce.    Thanks for sharing.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: This was my first time to ever eat brussels sprouts.  They were good and my kids ate them.  A friend came over and she said she has never liked brussels sprouts before but she really liked this recipe.  I did use coconut oil in place of olive oil, salt, and black pepper.  I will try them again.

name: company pork roast
review: My entire family loved this.  My husband said I could make this any time...and he hopes to see it often!  Very flavorful, tender roast and so easy to prepare!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Another great review!!!  I made half of this recipe using ground beef and Italian turkey sausage less water and followed the rest of the ingredients.  DH was in heaven!  We had enough left over for another meal.  Definately a keeper.  I did cook the sauce on low also for 4 1/2 to 5 hours served over spaghetti and served with a green salad (with Italian dressing) and garlic bread.  Thank you for posting the recipe.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This is an easy recipe. The combination of salsa and cream cheese is  good and there is no effort involved to make this. The last time I made it, it was a home run, this time not so much. Same ingredients, same crock pot, same reviewers, different conclusion.

name: brady bunch pork chops
review: Very good, nice and tender pork chops. I let the chops thaw in the milk mixture in the refrigerator about 6 hours. Half the crumb mixture was enough for 8 chops. Cooked over medium heat in a cast iron skillet. Used breadcrumbs from my freezer (leftover bread, toasted in oven, and run through the food processor). Will make again. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: This was easy and I liked that aspect of it, but I didn't think it was great.  To me it still seemed a little dry.  All I did was put a seasoning for pork and chicken on it and then followed the directions.  Maybe I am just not a fan of pork tenderloin???

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: Really delicious cookies!  My 11 yr old granddaughter and I made these over the weekend and used Betty Crocker dark chocolate cake mix.  Actually, she made them, I just assisted.  It was nice that we didn't need a lot of ingredients, and that she could mix it all with a spoon rather than having to dig out the mixer.  I helped her roll them into balls and then in the powdered sugar since that was a bit time consuming.  We got 2  large trays of cookies, totaling about 36 cookies.  Ours came out rather flat so next time I'll try making them a bit larger.  Also, most of the powdered sugar disappeared, so next time I'll do as Karen suggested and let them "dry" a bit before rolling them.  Nevertheless, they were chewy and SO delicious!

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: easy and yummy

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: Easy and delicious! I put baby carrots, red potatoes, celery and onions into my crock pot first and then put a 3.5 lb roast on top of it. The veggies turned out perfect and I didn't think the gravy was too salty.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: This frosting was great. I needed to add more milk to make it the right consistency. We then split it into bowls and added coloring. It was a big hit at the frost your own cupcakes part of the birthday party.

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: I really didn't like these at all.  The one thing I did like was the way they were just one step away from using ready made cookie dough.  Aside from that--too fluffy, not sweet, salty flavor and the cooking time needed maybe another 5 minutes.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: In response to a previous reviewer, here are the proportions I used.  One 10 3/4 oz, can Campbell's Cream of Mushroom soup, one 10 oz. can of Rotel, 16 oz. chicken broth, and one pound of cooked chicken breast cut into bite-size pieces.  Yesterday was a typical summer day in Huntsville, Texas and I didn't want to turn the oven on.  I cooked the pasta in a six quart pan, drained it and added all of the other ingredients and put it on the stove top and cooked on low until everything was hot, bubbly and melted.  It was rather "soupy", but I think it will thicken upon setting from the starch in the pasta.  If you want your version drier, use less broth.  I think a typical can of broth is about 14 1/2 ounces.  I purchase the 32 oz. cartons of broth.  I was extremely happy with the result!!!   This will probably be my usual method of assembling this unless I take it to a function.  One pan to wash made my day!  Miss Anita, thank you for your excellent recipe!   PS - By the time we got around to eating dinner, all of the extra liquid had been soaked up.  It was creamy and delicious!

name: healthy honey oatmeal cookies
review: Great recipe.  I like other users replaced the butter with 3 tablespoons of Vanilla Yogurt and cut the brown sugar and salt in half.  I added a 1/2 cup of butterscotch chips. Yum!  Thanks for sharing.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: This is a great chocolate cake - very light yet moist.  Took this to work for a co-workers birthday frosted with peanut butter frosting - it was gone in no-time.  My new go-to chocolate cake.  Easily converted to gluten free using my favorite gluten free flour. I also added 2 T of ground flax seed and used buttermilk instead of milk as is my standard practice for converting recipes.  Thanks for posting this Marg.

name: roast turkey
review: I haven't cooked very many turkeys in my life, but this recipe was fairly easy. I too found the butter mixture difficult to spread, having too many seasonings for the amount of butter. Also, it was way too salty for our taste. This recipe has potential and I love the blend of herbs, so I would consider making it again. Next time I would cut all of the seasonings and herbs in half, then take half of those and mix with the butter to make it easier to spread. The other half I would sprinkle on top of the bird.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: Amazing potatoes! Creamy and flavorful, with surprisingly little butter.

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: I was looking for a quick recipe for Italian bread that would go with my lasagna and came across this.  I doubled it and mixed it up in my bread machine but had to take it out to rise because it was overflowing.  It turned out just like the picture, two nice large loaves.  It tasted so good!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: I liked this for it's convenience.  I thought it could have had a little more flavor and maybe next time I will play around with it.  Maybe add some cilantro or something.  I added a small dollop of sour cream to my plate.  I would make again.

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: We really enjoyed this casserole.  Usually the tortillas get soggy in this type of casserole and we don't enjoy it then, but I think by breaking up the tortillas instead of leaving them whole we didn't notice it as much.  I made the whole recipe even though there are only 3 of us and we enjoyed it for leftovers too.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Very good, but I did change one thing. I used minced garlic instead of powdered. Made for Name that Ingredient tag game, 2013

name: soft batch chocolate chip cookies
review: My nephew is visiting and needed something for a party he was going to and picked this recipe out from all the others I'd saved.  Made two batches, one with vanilla pudding and chocolate chips and one with chocolate pudding and white chocolate chips.  They are both great.  Left out the nuts as I don't send those to parties with kids for fear of possible allergies but bet they'd be even better with them.  Will are soft, chewy and delicious.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Very good! I discovered that I only had half the amount of parmesan, but I don't know that it mattered.

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: Another winner!!!  Made this for our dinner cutting down on the chicken and using chicken tenderloins pounded down and left the sauce at the same amount.  I did use some panko crumbs with the breadcrumbs and added some capers.  (I breaded the chicken and like PaulaG I let them sit for about 15 minutes).  The chicken turned out to be so tender and DH loved this dish.  Definately an easy and quick dish on a hot summer night.  Served with fresh stirfry of broccoli, cauliflower, mushroooms and onions.  Wonderful.  Thank you for posting.  Going into my Favorites of 2013.

name: crunchy granola
review: I used this as a basic recipe to make a delicious granola we enjoyed with unhomoginised organic yogurt. I used some organic cane sugar and molasses as that was the only type of sugar I had on hand. It worked well. We got chunks of granola which we like. I used a little less water because of using molasses, alcohol free vanilla from the health food shop, less sea salt, wheat free organic oats, a bit of sliced almonds, but mostly walnuts in place of pecans, for the dried fruit which is very important to add only after cooking I added organic raisins, organic dried apricots, and dates. I will use this recipe again inshallah Allah. In fact I already bought more oats for it!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Very good!  Very easy!  Very low-maintenance way to entertain.<br/>Thanks for the great recipe.

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: Just made these for the second time for a family get-together after receiving a phone call asking me to bring "those awesome potatoes".   The first time making them, someone had only supplied me with the list of ingredients, so I just mixed everything up in a bowl and stored them in the refrig till ready to serve.  Then we just nuked them till hot and served.  They were wonderful!  <br/>So then then next time I made them, I followed the full instructions of baking them for 25 minutes before serving.  To be honest, I'm not sure there was any difference between the baked ones and the nuked ones.  Regardless, they are so tasty, we completely cleaned the baking dish in one sitting.  I did think the onion taste was stronger than needed, so I'll only use the 1/2 cup green onions next time instead of the full 1 cup.  And I used plain Greek yogurt in place of sour cream and we couldn't really tell any difference.  Thanks for sharing this keeper!!!

name: beer  n bbq braised country style pork ribs
review: Wonderful recipe.  My pork was thinner (about 1 inch) so this cooked much quicker.  After 1 hour I checked and it was starting to burn so took it out of the oven to rest until just before time to eat.  Put on the BBQ sauce (Recipe #502451) and back to the oven for 30 min. at 300 deg.  Amazing.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Delicious! I used this frosting on both vanilla and chocolate cupcakes, and it was great! Thank you for sharing!

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: I scaled this back for 4 serves and thought I would have enough for 6 but it was so delicious that we ate up the lot.  I did have an oops moment in that I mixed the bacon into the mashed potatoes instead of saving to sprinkle on when serving, also I omitted the onion powder due to dietary needs and I had no chives to put in otherwise made as per recipe.  Thank you Helping Hands, made for Name that Ingredient tag game.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: Really tasty!  Next time, though, I will cook a bit more pasta, as I found the ratio between the pasta and chicken not quite in balance.  I had a LOT of chicken from two breasts and hardly any pasta, so have sauce left over.  For us, one cup of cream made enough sauce.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Sorry but this just was not great. I added more vegetables and a bit more spice but it was bland. We don't like spicy btw. I used an organic beef vegetable broth, organic garlic, organic tomato paste, organic green cabbage, organic yellow onion, grated organic carrots, organic yellow beans instead if green, no zucchini as I had none on hand but added half an organic green pepper, fresh organic green peas in the pod, dried basil, organic fresh marjoram in place of oregano in a greater amount, a dash of cayenne pepper powder, sea salt & freshly ground black pepper. This may be a bit better the second day but I don't think we will finish it! DD1 (6 years old) loves soup but said this was only ok. I made a similar recipe before which had more flavour if I want this type of soup I will look for my review.

name: copycat lipton s onion soup mix
review: I love,love,LOVE this recipe! I didn't use celery seed, and it still adds waaaay more flavor!! I'm going to make a batch for my mom~ she will love it! Thanks so much~

name: our daily bread in a crock   weekly make and bake rustic bread
review: This is awesome.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: My husband retains his childhood fondness for good ol' tuna casserole, and this is a nice twist on that "school cafeteria classic"!  I chopped up some leftover grilled yellow bell peppers and subbed these for the pimiento/green pepper combo, and used the golden mushroom/roasted garlic canned soup.  And the resident overgrown "little boy" insists on a can of sweet green peas added to the mix...good old-fashioned recipe, KC!

name: jello cake
review: The kids loved this - I think any colour Jelly would work great.  Thanks for posting!

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: We enjoyed this recipe.  Left out the shallots but followed otherwise.

name: croutons
review: These are the best homemade croutons that I have ever tasted.  They are so light.  Will be using this recipe from now on.  Thanks for posting.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: I can't believe I have not posted a review yet, this is my go-to pizza sauce.  I follow the directions exactly....perfect every time.  I use this dough.. recipe #352152.  I have topped this with many things, family loves it.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: I make a lot of cakes and therefore have tried lots of frosting recipes. This one  is my new favorite vanilla buttercream recipe!! The best I have tried by far!!

name: bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers
review: I guess I should have read the reviews before I made these.  The cheddar melted off the popper, the bacon didn't crisp properly and the cream cheese needed something to add to the flavor.  Luckily we have lots of jalapenos in the garden.  So I will make these again using the suggestions in Raquel Grinnell's review. I will update review when I do.  I think this could be a great recipe with some tweaking.

name: hot dog hamburger buns rolls cinnamon buns dough cycle a b m
review: I cannot praise this recipe enough; I would certainly give it more than 5 stars if I could. I very recently purchased a bread machine, and wanted to make some hot dog buns. This was the first recipe I tried for the machined dough, and I do not need to search further.<br/>These buns came out beautifully! The texture was incredible, the flavor was delicious. I used 1% milk instead of skim (that's what we keep on hand), I used the 1/4 cup of the sugar, and I did add 1 teaspoon of vital wheat gluten per cup of all purpose flour.<br/>I will most definitely be using this recipe again, and can't wait to try it for hamburger buns and cinnamon rolls. Thanks so much for posting!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Excellent & EZ! I halved the recipe and baked in a 8" pie plate. Makes for a nice presentation. <br/>I used a heaping measure of chili powder, oregano, and cumin also a dash of cayenne. Subbed red bell pepper and some minced serrano chili pepper for heat. A mix of sharp cheddar and pepper jack cheeses. We really loved this! Thanks Kim D.

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: I think I might follow another reviewer and add some veggies. Alone, it needed "something". Served with Recipe #65287 & Recipe #83203 (which is wonderful, btw) & steamed broccoli. Thanks for sharing, with a few tweaks, we might have a repeat.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: I used reduced sodium soy sauce & 1 T. sesame oil (trust the other reviewer that stated too much sesame oil will ruin a dish) & bone in chicken thighs. This was so tender & delicious. I let it marinate in a freezer bag overnight, used sliced vidalia onion (which carmalized beautifully while baking). This will be a repeat in our house for sure. Note: I baked, covered with foil for about 45 minutes and then removed cover for an additional 20 minutes. Kids all but licked their plates. Served with Recipe #133513 (which we thought was just ok) & Recipe #65287 (which was a wonderful side with the chicken), lastly, I had steamed broccoli on the side. Thanks for sharing, this one's a keeper!

name: so it s bekah s pulled pork now
review: Amazing recipe! I reviewed this earlier and I remember being the 100th reviewer, but unfortunately it was never posted. Anyway hope that this review is posted. I used 5.7 lbs of boneless pork. It took about 6 hours for it to reach the stage where I could cut it in perfect slices. In the past when I baked it for about 8 hours, it was delicious too - perfect pulled pork (shredded easily). Both ways are great for sandwiches. However I am always baffled by the large quantities of pepper and mustard in the recipe. Thought it was a typo at first, but decided to use half the quantity for the size of pork I had. Thanks Mean Chef<br/>8/8/13 :I have to thank Bekah who has inherited this wonderful recipe.. This recipe is still a winner at our home. I have even made it with thick pork loin tips 3lbs in a covered pyrex dish. 375 degrees at 20 mins per pound - you're right .. it doesn't turn into pulled pork but delicious sliceable chunks of pork for sandwiches. I used only 1/8 cup of pepper and 1/8 cup of paprika, 1 tsp of red chilli powder (cayenne) and it was perfect.

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: Delicious and so easy.  I subbed fresh tomato for the canned but otherwise made as written.  The rosemary makes this dish, already looking forward to having it again.  When time permits I will try this with my own veg stock and home cooked beans to further lower the sodium.  Also, we got 3 servings, though, not 4 as noted in the recipe.

name: best ever pumpkin pie
review: A very good pie, but a little too sweet and rich for my taste. I like a lighter pumpkin pie, but everyone else seemed to enjoy it! I covered the crust edge with aluminum foil the first 30 minutes or so of baking so the crust didn't get too brown.

name: cajun sauteed shrimp
review: Made this for Zaar Chef Alphabet Soup 2013 tag game and DH and I really enjoyed them.  I did cut down on the cayenne pepper a little and used some butter along with the oil.  At the end I added a little white wine for more of a sauce and served this with brown rice, French bread and a green salad.  Thank you for a wonderful dish!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: This is a great recipe! Used pork loin as it was all I could find and Stubbs BBQ sauce. Cooked on high for 7 hours, added the sauce, cooked on high for another 3... Served with hoagie rolls and broccoli slaw. Yummmmmmmmmm!<br/>Freezing 1/2 for a quick meal in the future. Thanks!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Wonderful! Loved the large wedges. Potatoes were nice and brown on the edges. Used my large Calphalon roasting pan which was perfect. Would suggest making more than you think you need, these kept disappearing from the pan even before dinner was served. Served with pork souvlaki, homemade pita, and tzatziki sauce. Will make again! Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: sweet bacon wrapped venison tenderloin
review: This is really good.  I had a tenderloin to use up and followed your recipe.  We sliced it up and served with white rice.  We all enjoyed this and the kids thought it took some of the "gamey" flavor away.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: unknownchef86 s very best dinner rolls
review: OMG, I loved these rolls.  I have always been afraid to try homemade rolls but no more.  These were simple to make and they are soooo good.  thank you for sharing with us.

name: cinnamon raisin bread for the bread machine
review: This bread baked up so nice.  I used it for some "carrot cake" tea sandwiches.  My family loved it.  DS toasted some the next morning and said it was sooooo good.  Thank you for sharing with us and saving us some money by making it on our own.

name: uncle bill s whipped shortbread cookies
review: So easy and so good!  My teen son gave it his approval!  I made mine with a thumbprints full of raspberry jam.  One thing I didn't realize is that these cookies will spread out quite a bit when they cook so make sure and give some room.

name: hard boiled eggs
review: As an update - I continue to use this method and it's never failed me.  Love it!!<br/>Had to add my rating for this great tip on hard boiling eggs.  I followed the instructions exactly letting mine (farm fresh medium to large sized eggs) sit for 18 min as they where of varing sizes.  Came out so nice with no green around the edges.  Peeled easier than most fresh eggs and I was very pleased with the outcome.  I used this method to make my own recipe for Smoked salmon deviled eggs and I can't thank you enough for posting this recipe

name: no bake granola bars
review: This is a good base recipe.  I like to experiment with adding in different things.  This time I used honey in place of the corn syrup and added in wheat germ, white choc. chips and sunflower kernels. Much better than the store bought bars.

name: french dip roast beef for the crock pot
review: This was delicious, the meat was very flavorful.  It would've been helpful for the butcher to make thin slices to cut cooking time down.  Thank you for a great crock pot recipe.

name: wonderful salsa
review: Excellent! Doubled the recipe, left the skins on, left out the sugar, halved the cumin, added 2 teaspoons of chili powder, 2 tablespoons of cayenne, 1/2 cup of chopped cilantro. So easy and looks great in the jars. Thanks for sharing this terrific keeper, recipe!

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: I substituted red wine vinegar for the balsamic as I didn't have any and cut back a little on the garlic but kept the rest of the ingredients the same. I marinated some rump steak for around 24 hours in the fridge before bringing it to room temperature as suggested. It was the best steak I have ever made. Thanks Kitten!

name: funky chicken with sesame noodles
review: I wasn't crazy about the noodles. I found them a bit too sweet.  But I really enjoyed the chicken.  This is very easy to make, which is also a plus.  Thanks for sharing!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Good, fast, basic recipe.  Makes too much sauce for the quantity of pasta.  I saved the extra to mix with broccoli.  Needed a little extra spice, I used dry mustard, even with very sharp cheddar.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: PLEASE READ THIS REVIEW!!  I get extremely annoyed at those members who post these horrible reviews and then don't even bother to complete their pages.  As far as I'm concerned, they just "hit and run".  This recipe was featured the other day and I saved it to try.  I have just now completed it and it is delicious!  The only change I made was to use a Mexican style blend cheese, because that's what I had.  It is not grainy, gritty or disgusting.  Remember, the  cheese you select to use will dictate the taste of the dish.  I have no burned flour taste.  I completely melted the butter, whisked in the flour, whisked in the milk and then kept whisking until it was thickened to my satisfaction.  I left it a bit runny, because the starch from the pasta will cause it to "draw" up.  Removed from the heat, stirred in the cheese until it was melted and creamy, then stirred in the elbows.  Pure mac and cheese heaven!  This is a classic recipe and not to be confused with a boxed mix or that made with Velveeta.  Velveeta isn't even classified as real cheese (and I still love it!).  Marie, thank you again for another wonderful recipe.  This is a keeper and I will use it often because it's such a fast meal.  To those of you who left rotten reviews, "LEARN TO COOK" before you post such nonsense.  Also, if a man leaves you because you flopped a dish--men are like streetcars--another one will come along shortly.

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: I liked the idea of these, but I could taste the baking powder, so I only gave it a four, sorry. I used 1/8 tsp. for four eggs. Thanks for sharing! Made for name that ingredient, 2013

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: Delicious!

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: To start with, I do not eat shrimp. So why make this recipe? Well, when I read the ingredients for the sauce DH said that it would be nice to try with codfish. OK, tried that and it was a hit. Made just as stated (with the codfish instead of shrimp) with the exception of, as another reviewer suggested, decreasing the cayenne pepper to just 1/4 teaspoon and it was plenty. Next time I will also decrease the thyme to 3/4 teaspoon as it was a little overpowering. We had enough sauce to save for the next day when we tossed it with spaghetti. Delicious! Thanks for posting.

name: linda s cheesecake stuffed strawberries
review: Made these with my mom today! Someone at her work made them and she wanted to do make them. Only change was 3/4 cup sugar and no nuts. I think it needed the crunch of the nuts so I will try it next time. Or dip them in chocolate and then put cream cheese. Everyone still loved them.

name: emeril s essence
review: Very versatile spice.  Originally I reviewed #14372 but it was duplicated to this recipe.  I found this one impossible to scale to 1/4 cup and found some ingredients out of whack to the original.  I found one posted directly from Emeril's cookbook and it perfectly matches the version I use.

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: Just as others stated....quick, easy & delicious!!!

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: I liked this, but I also made changes.  Otherwise I think it would have been terribly bland.  I added 2 tsp chili powder and 1 tsp cumin.  We liked it and I will make again.

name: simple tomato sandwich
review: Have always loved tomato sandwiches made this way!!

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: These are very good and super easy.  I make mine with coconut sugar and coconut oil (instead of butter).  I also add some vanilla.   You can make many variations with this basic recipe by adding various ingredients, such as cinnamon, chocolate chips, banana, or apples. These pancakes rise well and are delicious.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: I loved this! Marinated 2 thighs, skin on overnight and then threw in some skinless breasts about an hour before cooking because my girlfriend revealed she prefers white meat. I actually preferred the breasts - despite not being marinated for as long they were super tender and very flavorful. I actually thought the thighs were a bit too salty --- I think they marinated too long. I'd make this again in a heartbeat, but with chicken breasts!

name: baked ham and cheese omelet roll
review: This was very good and so easy.  I sprayed pan and lined with parchment paper, also sprayed with Pam and used the paper to roll up the omelet.  I sauted ham, onions and red pepper and added with the cheese the last 5 minutes.  This is a keeper - so easy to use whatever meat and veggies you have on hand.  Thanks for sharing.  Update - didn't have parchment paper so used waxed paper - big mistake - it really stuck.  Next time I will either use parchment paper or just put it in the pan with Pam and butter.  DD was here and she loved it too.  Can't believe I've gone so long without making it again.

name: pan fried onion dip
review: that was ok

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: This was amazing and so delicious!  I used it on tilapia.  I think even if you aren't a big fish lover you would like this topping on your fish.  It is very cheesy and full of flavor.

name: tortured chicken   beer can
review: This was the best chicken I have ever tasted!!  So moist and the flavor was wonderful!

name: yummy creamy rice pudding
review: My daughter made this using leftover brown rice. It was REALLY good! The kids thought it would be better with white rice, so we'll try that next time. It took longer to cook than called for, but other than that, it turned out great. Thanks!

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: I used up 1/2 a chicken I had (already cooked) shredded it and left out the onion.  Mixed the chicken with the beans (added kidney beans too) and made as written.  I made this earlier and popped it in the fridge until needed.  I doubled the cooking time as it was cold when the cooking process started - it turned out great.  Thanks for posting

name: denny s style french toast
review: This was a good recipe, however it wasn't much different than my own recipe which does not have flour in and therefore doesn't clump up.  I do like french toast using the texas toast.

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: This is my goto recipe for chocolate pudding since I found it on this site.  I prefer the taste of cooked puddings, so this was one I glommed right onto.  It's easy to prepare, 5 and a half minutes in my microwave with a stir every couple of minutes, cool in freezer or refrigerator (depending on how desperate you are for your chocolate fix!) and voila!  It's ready!

name: best apple cake
