review: Very good!  I omitted the choco chips, & these were good, but I think they would be excellent with them.

name: garlic beef enchiladas
review: Excellent.  The sauce is good.  I made the sauce one day then put them together the next which saved time. I have used canned sauce and it just is not as good as these.  Delicious and worth the effort.

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: Very good. Easy, fast, and made with things I usually have on hand.  However, I didn't have the red pepper this time and substituted a diced carrot and some green pepper.  It was good but I'll try it as you have written next time.  I'm sure it will be even better.  Waited to add the salt and found I was happy without it.  Ate it with a dollop of sour cream atop.  Mmmm!

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Another recipe I've been using and haven't rated!  I'm famous at DS's class parties for this frosting.  I do add a teaspoon of vanilla though.    Thank you!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: I really wanted this to work, but perhaps my oven just retains heat really well because my 2lb loin was reeeally well done after turning off the 500F oven and letting it stay for about 50 minutes. It was still a little juicy but oh what it could have been! Thankfully the rub I used gave it a great flavour. I may try it again sometime and cut the time down, or invest in a thermometer that I can leave in the oven.

name: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
review: I used half butter, half margarine. My daughter requested soft pb cookies. It's a good thing she came and got them, as I had a hard time stopping putting them in my belly! I managed to hide some in the freezer, lol. Thanks for yummy cookies! Oh, I did leave out the chocolate chips.

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: I have a new favorite recipe!  I could just eat that glaze with a spoon.  Super simple and delicious, I will definitely be making this again and again.

name: basic pancake mix
review: If pancakes can be stunning - well these are for sure!  The addition of the vanilla really makes this recipe tops!  Nice light, fluffy and large pancakes (used a 1/2 cup measure) which even filled up my teenage son.   Thanks for sharing.

name: copycat recipe for carrabba s chicken marsala
review: Made this for dinner tonight. DD didn't like it at all. DH thought it was just ok. I really liked it.  We served it over fresh spinach fettuccini. Going with 3 stars as an average for our family.

name: super peanut butter filled brownies
review: There is another recipe (or two) that are posted here on Food.com very similar.  A fabulous pb brownie recipe!!!  Very rich, so you don't need to cut them very big.  Yum Yum!!!

name: crunchy granola
review: Great granola recipe.  I pretty much followed your recipe, but did add in 1/2 cup of ground flax meal.  Dates, almonds and pecans rounded out this yummy recipe!!!

name: beef patties in onion gravy
review: Great recipe.  A great go-to recipe for an easy week-night meal.

name: olive garden fettuccine alfredo
review: Loved this! I used 2 TB of cream cheese as the recipe directs, and it was perfect. I mixed the sauce with penne pasta and served grilled chicken on top. Kids loved it.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: With all the great reviews, I was expecting something more. I added broccoli and this ended up tasting just like plain old beef and broccoli.  It was OK, but I probably won't make again.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Wonderful dinner and really love the fact that I did not have to sacrifice flavour to save calories

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Excellent. The only thing I did different was to use all chicken broth, instead of any water.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: This was a SIMPLE recipe, and I loved the result! I had a left-over sirloin steak (from one of those gigantic packages of steak, so I could get it inexpensively) and had no idea what to do with it. This recipe allowed me to stretch out the steak (it was a big one) for a meal and nobody noticed they were eating a bunch of veggies. I added a sliced zucchini to my onions and peppers because it was in the refrigerator and it needed to be used. I followed the recipe exactly, other than the addition of the zucchini. The spiciness was just right for us -- some might want to adjust for their level of heat (with the crushed red peppers).

name: white chili   football soup
review: This was very good and don't know if I should rate it because I cooked it in the crockpot.  It had great flavor and DH loved it.  Thank you!

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Delicious cookies that are soft and easy to make.  Thank you!

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: didn't work for me.  I timed the boiling one minute, but it was hard when I put it on my ice cream...and I really tasted no significant flavor either.

name: queso blanco dip
review: This recipe has spoiled me - I'm a little disappointed by other quesos I'm served at restaurants now!<br/>This is super creamy and delicious, not to mention so easy to make.  Added diced pickled jalapenos for some kick.

name: cauliflower cheddar soup
review: This is a wonderful tasting soup.  Loved the cheese.  Thanks for posting.

name: oven fried garlic chicken
review: Excellent flavor and crunch. I used about half the amount of parmesan cheese (because I ran out!) and cooked chicken legs for about 45 minutes vs 60 minutes. The chicken was delicious. The garlic flavor hit just the right notes. The chicken was crispy on the outside and tender on the inside. I highly recommend this recipe. Thank you!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: After 6 hours, mine came out a bit dry and tasteless. Definitely couldn't taste the spices and it needed more salt (I used 2 tsp). Fortunately, I just put everything back in the crockpot with water and a couple bay leaves and made soup, which saved the chicken!

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Very very easy and very yummy! Honeycrisp apples and homemade sweetened whipped cream pushed it over the top.  Thanks for posting!

name: so it s bekah s pulled pork now
review: I am only rating method and spice rub.  FANTASTIC!!   I used my family's favourite BBQ sauce instead.  Very easy recipe.

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Excellent sauce. Usexd onion powder and garlic powder- did not use mushrooms. Great taste and will use this recipe!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: These were good but a little tough so I will decrease the cooking time next time. Thanks!

name: croutons
review: Oh my goodness!!  These are THE BOMB!!  I got a loaf of sourdough bread (marked down and perfect for croutons) and seasoned simple with the seasoning salt and little fresh ground pepper.  THESE ARE TO DIE FOR!!  Even the hub that normally doesn't like croutons fell head over heels for these! Thanks for posting!  Count me in with never buying croutons again!

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: This alfredo sauce was really good.  However, looking at the nutritional information, I think it will have to be a special treat to have once in a blue moon.  This one is a diet buster for sure!

name: copycat  green giant niblets corn in butter sauce
review: Tried to cut this down for two but didn't come out right.  Too salty and never did thicken up.  Probably better just to make the entire recipe.

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: This was great and very easy.  I used a hand-held mixer to combine everything, so that was quite easy.  I missed the buttery taste, so next time I'll make sure to use butter-flavored Crisco.

name: easy garlic chicken
review: Thanks for posting Elle. This was pretty good and interesting. We made it as written. It now shows 450 degrees to cook it at. We did it at that temp and on the bottom rack with good results but beware the sugar mixture still smoked. The garlic was a sharp flavor in this and was a little potent despite picking normal sized cloves so don't use big ones. The foil lined pan is a MUST! We doubled the sauce and still it doesn't adhere or remain on the chicken fully. The meat was juicy and moist however. The outside of the chicken was tougher and was where the flavor was. It definitely is a tame recipe seasoning wise so next time I will season it up.  I agree with other posters that it is pretty easy, takes two pans to clean, and is a recipe I would make, but not on regular rotation. Enjoy! ChefDLH.

name: low   slow oven baked ribs   super simple
review: Super simple is right! Had I known how easy it was to make ribs, I would have made them sooner. You really can't mess this recipe up. Serve with extra BBQ sauce!

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: Excellent soup - will most definitely make this again!

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: This was delicious!!  Taking the advice of a couple other reviewers, I used Crisco and flour and heavily coated my pan.  I also left it to cool in the pan for about 10 minutes, and probably could have left it another five or so.  I followed the recipe exactly and it turned out perfect!  I would like to suggest that those that had issues used too much flour.  You must fluff the flour and then lightly spoon it into your measuring cup and lightly level off.  If you use the dipping method, you will end up with too much flour.  Also, in my experience, you cannot over beat the fats.  If your butter starts to separate, throw it out and start all over.  Pound cakes are tricky and I think these are the two main causes of failure.  This is extremely high fat.  If you worry about fat calories and grams, this would not be the recipe for you!  Please do not try to make it healthy.  Jeff, thank you for the recipe!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: Easy to prepare and tastes awesome!  I doubled the recipe to feed 8, had some leftovers but they didn't last very long.  I used leg quarters separated and Splenda Blend Brown Sugar in place of sugar.  Dh, kids and grands loved this!  Definitely will make this again.  Served with Sesame Noodles Recipe #244524 and Garden Peas.  My 5 yo grandson ate 4 pieces and wanted more!  Still haven't figured out where he put it...lol.  Thank you for sharing!!

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: I made this using recipe as a guideline yet tried to use up produce I had on hand.  I sauteed one large shallot with four celery stalks chopped and four red skin potatoes with their skins still on but chopped into large pieces.  Only sauteed above for about 4 minutes then added five sliced cremini mushrooms and two serrano chilis which I minced finely in addition to five cloves of garlic which I grated.  Let that cook for 2 minutes then added the flour and stirred well.  Added Better than Boullon chicken flavor with two cups of water and heavy cream, brought up to a boil to thicken.  Then added 1/4 cup chopped italian parsley and salt and pepper.  Added about 1/4 tsp. of cayenne pepper and 1/4 cup dry white wine.  Needed a bit more flavor for our taste, so I added 1 tsp. of thyme and two packets of Swanson's Flavor boost, chicken flavor.  Added the rotisserie chicken pieces then and poured all into a Pam sprayed 9x12 casserole dish.  Topped with one package of Pillsbury Crescent rolls, which covered the whole filling(had to stretch it a little to reach the corners) and then I baked it at 375 for 45 minutes.  Really easy and tasted great!!!! Made again but used sherry instead of wine, used pearl onions, green beans (cut into 1" pieces), 4 carrots, one bell pepper, 4 Serrano chiles and I used one pkg. of crescent rolls for the bottom crust and I used two pkgs. crescent rolls for the top crust. Those were the additions I used in addition to the veggies I wrote down in my first try at this recipe.

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: Very tasty!  Was loved by DH, kids and grands!  Increased this to serve 8 but other than that prepared as posted.  Thank you for sharing!

name: fajita seasoning mix
review: This was easy and I had everything I needed on my spice/herb shelf.  I skipped the chili and cayenne (little ones don't like it).  Made one batch with chicken bouillon and the second with beef bouillon.  I used the dry packets that I get in the Mexican food section.  Everyone loved it!  I'll never by store fajita mix again.  Thank you for sharing!

name: peanut butter no bake cookies
review: Delish! I made 2 batches of these over 3 days - the 2nd batch because they were devoured so quickly! lol. The first batch, I cut the sugar back to 1 1/2 cups and 2 1/2 cups of oats. They tasted great but were a bit soft and fell apart easily. The 2nd batch, I followed the recipe to a T and they were wonderful. I cheated a little bit on both batches by nuking the ingredients rather than boiling them. I nuked them for 2 minutes, then stirred, then nuked for an additional minute. In our minds they were absolute perfection. The 2nd batch was perfect and held together really well. Thanks Impera_Magna for sharing a real winner that we will make repeatedly! Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: oven fried garlic chicken
review: Wonderful and easy chicken recipe.  All I had in the freezer were bone-in chicken breasts and they were quite large so I had to bake for an extra 20 minutes before the juices ran clear.  Chicken was very moist and tender, and the coating is yummy. Can't wait to make this again!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Amazing, made for the holidays this year and everyone enjoyed.

name: fajita seasoning mix
review: I made chicken fajitas using your spice mixture and they tasted just like fajitas from our local Mexican restaurant.  This will be my go to spice from now on as I normally spend a whooping $2.98 a package for seasoning that only tastes half as good as this.  Thank you so much for the great recipe Kathy at Food.com!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: OMG, I can't believe I made something so good from scratch. I don't think my family will ever go back to frozen! I followed the recipe mostly, using Ricotta cheese. My only change was to use ground venison rather than beef. Made my own lasagna noodles from the low carb pasta recipe on this site and it was great. I think this is closer to 12 servings tho, as my family of 4 barely ate more than a quarter of this. With my low carb noodles I counted this out around 10 carbs each with 12 servings. Delicious! Thanks for sharing.

name: grandmas sloppy joes
review: Quick easy dinner for us.  We added green peppers.  Made for Name that Ingredient.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: I have made this so many times, I couldn't count!  It is just the best recipe...period!  Look no further!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: These were GREAT! I just pan-fried my chops and added the sauce at the end and caramelized it. This is my new go-to sauce to make pork chops shine. My kids devoured them -- I live for this recipe!

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: This was great soup and so easy to throw together. It had great flavor! I used 1 1/4 lbs of ground turkey and it still worked out beautifully. Other than that, I kept the recipe the same. Yummy!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: I can't believe I have not reviewed this recipe yet!  I have made this recipe about 12 times now.  Actually it is the only meatloaf recipe I make.  I use 2 lbs of lean ground beef, 2 slices of bread and 1/2 cup of milk.  Perfect every time.  We love it!  I always double up on the sauce because we like to use it on top of the mash potatoes I server it with.  By far the BEST and a KEEPER.  tyvm

name: wonderful salsa
review: Made a batch tonight - tastes just like Pace picante sauce. I like more depth and heat, but this is a good one to have on hand for when my east-coast friends come to visit!

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: Yum!  I didn't have any problems with any soggy crust at all.  It was flavorful and moist.  The panko really makes a nice crispy crust.

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review: Simple, tender, & delicious! I did use brown gravy instead of onion gravy. I love cube steak but I haven't made it for years. It takes forever to cook it to tenderness. I never thought about putting it in the crockpot. Thanks for a new way to make an old favorite.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: So simple, yet a perfect way to cook broccoli! Delicious!

name: crock pot chili pork chops     a must try
review: These were very good pork chops and so easy to make.  I made them with baked mashed potatoes.

name: breakfast casserole supreme
review: This was good, but just another breakfast casserole.  I used bacon for my meat and did not have tomatoes so omitted them.

name: easy cole slaw
review: This was exactly what I was going for in a nice creamy slaw.  I made Crockpot Cola Barbeque Pork Roast Recipe #43186.  This cole slaw went excellent with it.

name: pineapple upside down cake
review: Loved this..I used a yellow cake mix as others suggested.  Very moist.  changing my go to recipe to this one!  Thank you!

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: OMG!  Why did I wait so long to finally try this amazing recipe!!  LUV IT!

name: beef barley soup
review: This was great!  I had two soup bones that had a good amount of meat on them so I used that.  I also didn't have any diced tomatoes and so I used a 14 oz. can of tomato sauce instead.  I kept the liquid the same, but I think next time I will add some extra because it was more like a stew.  I cooked this on high for 5 hours while we were at church and came home to a wonderful smell when we walked in the door.

name: bestest hamburger soup
review: Loved this. I used beef broth instead of water and it really had a great flavor. Since the pasta absorbs liquid, I did add water on the next day. Thanks for posting.

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: OMG!!! This is the best bread I've ever made and I make a lot of bread! The taste is authentically Italian. I made this into 2 loaves and baked them on an overturned cookie sheet with a pan of warm water below them on the bottom shelf. They were perfectly browned in 20 minutes. I can't wait to try this recipe as pizza crusts and rolls. Follow this recipe and impress your family and friends.

name: angel food cake   homemade
review: So flavorful I had to give it five stars.  For some reason my cake did not come out as light as I would have liked.  I'm wondering if I didn't beat the egg whites enough.  The only thing I did different was to add a half of teaspoon more of vanilla and almond extract.  We ate it plain and loved it.  Thanks for sharing.

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review: This is delightful! I also accidentally used a different mix--brown gravy mix as opposed to the onion, but it tasted wonderful nonetheless. I've made recipes combining cream of mushroom soup with onion soup mix, and I think I like this one better! The gravy had wonderful flavor, and the cube steaks were very tender. I did do a few things differently--I browned the steaks in a large skillet with some sliced fresh mushrooms, foregoing the crock pot only because I had lots of dishes already, and didn't want to make more. Lol  While they were browning, I combined the soup with the gravy mix and water, and upon noticing it wasn't onion gravy, added a few tablespoons of dried minced onions. When the steaks were browned, I poured the gravy mixture into the skillet, covered it, set it to "simmer", and then let it do its thing for about 2 hours. The result was yummy! I also only had a pound of cube steaks, but prepared and used the entire amount of gravy. (Recommended.) Or, if you do have the two pounds, you may want to double the sauce if you're serving with mashed potatoes, noodles, dumplings, or fries, etc. I served ours with American cheese and potato pierogies, ladling the luscious gravy over all. But we could have used even more, since as it cooks, the gravy tends to thicken, and reduce to some extent. Next time I'll try it with the onion gravy mix, and transfer the cube steaks to the crock pot. Thank you Southern Chef, for sharing your recipe! This is a definite keeper!

name: tsr version of applebee s oriental chicken salad by todd wilbur
review: I truly enjoy Applebee's Oriental Chicken Salad and this recipe is spot on!  The amount of chicken listed is confusing.  I used one chicken breast per person since I was making four salads.  The breading ingredients didn't need to be doubled.  Love it.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Very good mac 'n cheese!

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: We love lettuce wraps and this version is very tasty.  I also just minced up the chicken breast (after cooking it - as per instructions) as I don't like buying ground chicken.  I did change up the sauce based upon some of the reviewer comments and the outcome was quite good.  Made for Name That Ingredient tag, January, 2014.

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: An other great bread recipe.  I love baking bread there is just nothing like it.  This was amazing!  Thank you for the recipe.  Will make it again for sure.

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: We liked these a lot. The butter does make a difference. I did have to use more butter mixture to brush on top.

name: beef barley soup
review: Beef Barley soup has always been my husband's favorite soup.  I am now a hero because of this recipe.  I halved the recipe.  I browned the meat in a couple of tablespoons of oil and then when I removed the pieces from the skillet, I added a couple of teaspoons of chopped garlic and cooked that until fragrant.  I accidentally left the soup in the crockpot for over 12 hours but it did no harm.  The consistency was perfect.

name: spinach salad with honey bacon dressing
review: How many times do I need to review this before reviewing?  This is my go to recipe for spinach salad.  Very tasty as a main dish salad.  The last couple of days I have made it has a main dish wish a cup of soup on the side.  If there is extra dressing just refrigerate for later.  Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Looooooove the meatballs and the sauce!!! This recipe yielded 25 meatballs for me and a ton of delicious sauce to go with pasta! These meatballs did taste a little mushy but the flavor was excellent. Next time, I will take other commenters' advice to broil or brown them first before simmering. Thank you for this awesome recipe!

name: the best chicken tortilla soup
review: Absolutely wonderful!!! The ingredients for garnishing stated in the recipe are crucial, making a delightful topping to go with the savory soup. Followed the recipe exactly except that I used a couple drops of Ghost Pepper sauce instead of Tabasco. It was a very nice kick! Will make it again for sure!

name: crock pot ravioli
review: This was good!  Certainly easy for a weeknight meal!  The pasta came out kind of gummy from the slow cooking but not terrible.  Overall a great option for those quick slow cooked dinner nights.  Thanks Bekah

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Delicious! I used crushed tomatoes and added 1-2 tbsp butter at the end.

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: This was very flavourful and super quick. Thanks for the recipe!

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: A delicious classic!

name: chicken stroganoff   crock pot
review: DD didn't care for this at all and opted to have plain buttered noodles instead. Everyone else felt it was ok. I had a few mushrooms left over from another recipe, so I added them to it.  I served this over tri-colored fettuccine.

name: crazy crust pizza
review: I really like this recipe; thanks for sharing! When really hungry for 'normal' pizza, this probably won't cut it. But when trying to eat healthy and still wanting pizza, this is marvelous! The crust is thin and soft- not quite able to eat with your hands. I want to record my changes for when I make it again (I have made it twice this month): Cut the salt to 1/2 tsp in the crust. Bake the crust for 10-15 mins alone. Top partially-baked crust with 7oz. pizza sauce, shredded zucchini, shredded carrot, diced bell pepper, diced onion, diced sun-dried tomatoes, then the cheese and some turkey pepperoni. Bake for 10 mins before serving.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: I occasionally (probably not often enough!) cook and deliver casseroles to my elderly neighbors, and to my husband's parents, and am always alert for things like this, that are not "strange" or fussy, but that have just a bit of kick.  This fit the bill nicely.  I used a store-brand queso white cheese melt bar instead of Velveeta, and added a can of drained English peas.  Enjoyed by all my "peeps"!

name: grandmas sloppy joes
review: Great sloppy joes! I half it and skip the vinegar and it's great! Thanks for the keeper!

name: yummy crispy baked fish
review: We give this only a 3 star rating, sorry.  Flavor wise everyone loved it!  But crispy?  Not so much.  They were more on the gritty side than crispy because of the cornmeal.  Next time I will use planko in the mix, cornflakes or maybe stuffing as someone else posted.  <br/><br/>I omitted the pepper and cayenne for the grands but other than that followed this as written multiplied by 4.  I have 8 in my household at the moment and we all love fish.  I should have read more of the reviews before hand.  Had a problem with the coating coming off when flipping them..maybe add an egg?  I don't know.  Everyone said the flavor was awesome!  So maybe with a few tweeks it will get a higher rating from me.  Thanks for sharing!

name: garlic beef enchiladas
review: Very good recipe. Love the chili powder kick. I followed this recipe to make some turkey enchiladas and brought them to a picnic in the park. Every one loved these so much! Will definitely make them again.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: These were just ok. They were a very flat brownie.   I have other brownie recipes that I prefer,

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: Couldn't make it any better! Hubby said who needs takeout anymore? I froze in little baggies since we don't like a lot of sauce on our pizza and am going to make one for Super Bowl Sunday. Thanks so much!

name: quick butternut squash soup
review: This was very good.  I used pre-prepped squash that I got from Walmart because I wasn't feeling well today.  It was a heavy soup that was filling and good for a sick day in our house.  I served it alongside Recipe #192896 for a well rounded meal.  Thank you erinBOberrin.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Fabulous!  Only comment as people came back for thirds was "they are kinda bland".  What??  Next time, I will add more garlic, and maybe try stock instead of water.  I didn't peel my potatoes, so it was a very easy recipe.  Served with roast pork but would compliment any entree.  Thanks for a keeper!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: I've always hated sloppy joes.  I've hated the recipes that I've prepared myself, and I've especially hated the canned variety of sloppy joes.  This recipe here made me a sloppy joe believer.  Very tasty and easily tweakable for your own tastes.

name: denny s style french toast
review: YUMMY!!!!  I used half the amount of sugar (trying to rid that from the diet), and put all the ingredients in my blender to blend them together.  I even melted my butter and put it in the blender with the rest of the ingredients.  Result:  A smooth creamy liquid with ZERO lumps!!  Turned my griddle up to 325, and cooked them up!  The Child said it was the best french toast I've made, as did her friend that spent the night.  This is a keeper!!  Thanks!!

name: the best chili you will ever taste
review: I thought this was a great recipe.  I made venison chili, with ground venison, braised backstrap chunks, and smoked venison sausage.  I upped the heat by using hot Rotel vice diced tomatoes and added extra cayenne.   I too cut back on the sugar (used a ¼ cup).  The coffee and coca were a perfect match for the venison.  I entered this chili in the office chili cook off and won 1st place, so I?m not too sure about all the really negative reviews.   Chili recipes are like opinions?everyone  thinks theirs is best.

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: Sooooo good & it was ingredients I already had in my pantry!

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: This turned out pretty bland.  The sauce was pretty thin, and it didn't taste like much more than noodles.  =/

name: lentil soup for people who thought they hated lentils    meat op
review: A delicious soup! I didn't add a couple of vegetables. I first sauted the onion, carrots, celery, leek and garlic before adding the lentils and broth. Also, added extra fresh parsley and 1 tsp. dried basil and oregano. I added some sauted mushrooms and the spinach at the end. Will make this again.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: Yum, goody good. Made for Best of 2013 game.

name: almost white castle hamburgers
review: These were delicious.  I have never had White Castle Burgers, they just don't have them in our area, but my husband has and says these are better than the restaurant's burgers.  I love how easy they were to make and that I already had everything on hand to make them.  These will definitely be a go to when we need a quick delicious meal.  Thank you Chef Doozer!

name: eric s easy grilled chicken
review: Excellent! Very moist and I loved the combination of flavors.

name: eric s easy grilled chicken
review: Our chicken came out very tender--although I wasn't able to grill it because we don't have an indoor grill, and it was twenty-something degrees outside! A shame, because when I cooked it in the skillet, the "browned" areas were very tasty. I used Kraft House Italian dressing and Kikkoman Teriyaki Baste & Glaze. I'm refraining from giving any stars because I didn't use the suggested method of cooking, and it seems in this recipe that would make quite a substantial difference. I will try it again when the weather warms up--and on the grill this time!

name: oven fried garlic chicken
review: I used what we call a Maryland cut (thigh and leg kept intact) and prepared as per recipe though I used sharp cheddar cheese instead of parmesan (otherwise I would have had a revolt on my hands as I the only one in the family that really likes parmesan) and baked at 175C for 60 minutes on a tray lined with baking paper as I find this easier for clean up than alfoil and the chicken does not stick as it sometimes does with alfoil) and microwaved by butter and garlic, thank you SilentCricket for a delicious recipe that delivers some lovely flavours and was thoroughly enjoyed by us all, made for Name that Ingredient tag game.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: The best Salmon Patty EVER!  I will use this recipe from now on when making these...scouts honor!  Easy to prepare, moist and delish.  I only added some Dijon mustard, personal preference.  Served with Orzo with Parmesan and Basil #79431 they went well together.  Thank you for sharing!

name: panda express orange chicken
review: Yummy! Decided not to thicken it up and it was great.

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: Simple and good! I used my food processor to chop everything including chicken and veggies. I also halve the mayo. Tasted quite good.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Delicious! I used the tilapia and the rest of the ingredients as listed but subbed oregano for the basil. Served with broiled tomatoes and grapes.

name: low carb pizza
review: Dh and I have been doing the Low Carb diet for quite some time so it was really nice to have "pizza" for dinner.  We enjoyed the taste of this, but we both found it very rich.  That's not necessarily a bad thing though, as you tend to eat less.  I'll definitely be making this again and will play around with it a bit.  I'd like to try using 3 eggs as another reviewer indicated. Thanks for the great recipe.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: This was so easy and quick to prepare, I was suspicious that it wouldn't taste very good.  What a pleasant surprise - it was delicious!  I used low sodium soy sauce (trying to keep sodium under control) and otherwise followed the recipe.  There was not too much sesame oil flavor nor was the soy sauce overpowering, as it can be.  This is a keeper for sure!

name: easy garlic rice
review: Wonderful! Loved the flavors and the ease of preparation. The rice turned out perfectly. Thanks for sharing.

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: What can I say tat 268 other reviewers have not already? The combination of raisins and caraway (I used anise) just gave it a tremendous depth of flavour. Served with a pot roast with lots of gravy.<br/>Superb!

name: m   m dream bars
review: These bars are really great! I love the peanut butter layer and the M&M's.  There will definitely be a repeat of this one.

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: This was a nice easy dinner.  I did add a small can of green chilis and doubled the garlic.  I think it might have been too bland otherwise.  I also used kidney beans since I was out of black beans. Everyone liked it and will definitely be making this again!  Thanks for a quick, easy and healthy dinner recipe.

name: angel food cake   homemade
review: Perfect! Thank you for the wonderful directions. I'm so glad you mentioned cracking each egg separately. I had no idea that I was that bad at separating eggs. Loved the texture and flavor. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: LOVED THIS!  It was amazingly delicious and really, very easy to make.  I used fresh cauliflower that I steamed before baking.  I made this to go along with a spinach stuffed chicken and steamed baby carrots for a rather healthy and low carb dinner.  I used the measurements listed and got enough to make 6 side dish portions.  Will be making this time and again I am sure.  Thank you Helping Hands.

name: jalapeno popper burgers
review: I made these burgers for my family tonight to eat while watching the Super Bowl XLVIII, (Great job Sea Hawks!), and they were a hit.  I made a whole recipe, but used 2 whole small jalapenos and Hot Shot seasoning instead of the Ancho Chile Pepper Seasoning.  These were slightly spicy, but not bad, even my three year old ate some. Also, February in Pennsylvania is not grilling weather and the broiling thing scared me a little, so I made these in a frying pan set on medium-low temp and let them cook for 6 minutes per side and used the recommendation to only flip them once then I finished them off by placing two slices of bacon and then the shredded cheddar and placing them under the broiler for 2 minutes to melt the cheese.  Served them alongside garlic fries for a great Super Bowl dinner.  These are sure to be made again in the summer!  Thanks Julesong.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: 5 stars from this family!  I used the KitchenAid to mix this up.  These were enjoyed with a bowl of chili. Thank you!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: My family devoured these! Used local beef and subbed marinara sauce for the tomato sauce and ketchup. The homemade BBQ I used had all the remaining ingredients in your recipe: brown sugar, mustard, etc. so I skipped adding those ingredients. The mixture was served over dinner rolls I picked up at a local bakery. Served with a tossed salad. Very good and very easy! Made for Best of 2013.

name: panda express orange chicken
review: So awesome I don't even know where to begin!  I didn't think anything of the directions until half the reviewers were squaking about it!  It was totally understandable if you have medium knowledge of cooking.  Anyways, I have to say prep time was kinda significant, but oh so worth it!  I used 1/2 juice of the zested orange and 1/2 the vinegar.  I did some extra minced ginger and added a tiny bit of jalapeno I had kickin around.  This was awesome!  Oh, I also split the sugar half brown half cane.  Thanks a TON for posting this flume!!!!!

name: chipotle roast for tacos   sandwiches
review: While we liked the flavor of this, most of my family found this too spicy.  Of course when using peppers, they vary in size, and therefore the heat will also vary.  It was super easy to throw together and the house smelled fantastic when we got home from work.  If I made this again I would have to play with the ingredients and amounts for my family, trying to keep flavor but decrease the heat.

name: homemade pie crust
review: Thank you for sharing your wonderful recipe.  The pie crust was wonderful, flaky, light, tender and very tasty.  It was quick and easy, perfect with the mixed berries I filled it with.  I'll be making this again.  Made for Name That Ingredient Tag Game.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: These were really yummy! I did brown them first as a matter of preference but didn't change anything else.  I loved the flavor and the moistness and they were better the next day as leftovers. Thanks!

name: best twice baked potatoes
review: The taste on these is magnificent.  I however apparently don't have the knack for taking apart baked potatoes and putting them back together.  My potatoes kept breaking and after about two potatoes I gave up and diced them and then mixed them in the potato stuffing ingredients and baked them in a casserole dish.  I'm going to try to go threw all of the reviews and see if I can get some tips on how to properly make these, because I think they would be very well received in our family.  Thank you for a yummy tasting dish LorenLou.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: I found that the soup just wasn't flavorful enough for me.  I ended up adding Italian seasoning, Italian sausage, red pepper flakes, and a can of tomato paste.  Thank you for giving me a great base recipe.

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: Nice and simple recipe for sloppy joes!!!  I scaled this back to 1/4 of the recipe, but followed as written for the recipe.  I just bought some celery the day before, it was very fresh and green and even after simmering for 45 mins., it was still crunchy when I ate my lunch, but that isn't the fault of the recipe but rather the super freshness of the celery.  My recipe is very similar but includes green pepper, which I did miss and would add it next time.  I used "Montgomery Inn" bbq sauce so it had a little kick which was nice.  Thanks for sharing the recipe.  Made for "Best of 2013 Tag Game".

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: This is delicious  -  our new favorite soup!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Delish! Super easy and very flavorful. I just love roasted Brussels sprouts and this recipe was a winner. Thank you!

name: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
review: I have made these 4 times now, and I LOVE them!  Oatmeal Raisin Cookies are my favorite and this is one of the best recipes I've found.  It's very dependable and always turns out well.  I even upped the recipe to make 500 cookies for our church picnic and they turned out amazingly, even with the abundant amount of cookie dough that we got out of them.  These will be my go to "sweet tooth" healer from now on.  Thank you so much for such a great recipe Dale Goodman!

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: This sounded like the perfect dinner for a cold night.  I made it with tomato juice and left out the optional lemon juice. We all felt it was ok but weren't as wowed as all the other reviewers seem to be.  Next time I may use the broth option with the tomato juice and add the optional lemon juice. Hopefully these will add the flavors to wow us.  I will update my review and make necessary changes to the star ratings when I make it again.

name: soft batch chocolate chip cookies
review: I always turn to this recipe whenever I'm preparing a care package. The cookies stay softer so much longer than my usual recipe. (My husband isn't very fond of the pudding flavor, which is why I don't use this recipe all the time.) It is also fun to use M&M's instead of chocolate chips if they are for a party.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: As if this needs another 5* review!  Delicious!  Made one for us and another to take to a sick friend and her family.  Thanks.

name: mom s chocolate cupcakes
review: Moist and chocolatey! This recipe made exactly 12 cupcakes.

name: chocolate eclair dessert
review: I can't believe I have not reviewed this recipe!  It is always a hit with my family or pot lucks.  The only thing I do that's different is I beat up some heavy whipping cream (1 pint) add about 4 or 5 T of powered sugar to it as it is beating and replace the cool whip with the whipping cream.  Yummy.  When I am really ambitious, I make the pudding from scratch using this  Recipe #148727.  Thank you Pear for a wonderful recipe.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: So good.  Had two baked potatoes to use and added about 1/2 c. soup and sour cream.  No butter but cheese on top.  YUM.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: I think I rolled mine too thin but the flavor and icing turned out great.  Made half a recipe and got 8 of the large 7 inch snowflake cookies.

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: I made this appetizer tonight.  The prep time for me was longer because I used boneless chicken thighs and I had to trim all of the fat and gook off of the pieces.  I probably should have started prepping this last Thursday (just kidding!).  Because it took me longer to prep the chicken, I wanted to save time on clean-up so I put the pieces on non-stick foil instead of on a rack.  If I had drained the fat off of the foil midway during cooking time, the bacon would have been crisper.  The people that ate it didn't mind it at all but next time (and there will be a next time) I will.  Thank you for posting this recipe!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: Good with domestic rabbit. Added spices to 1/4 olive oil and rub on skinless meat. Done in 7 hours on low.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: I reduced to one egg to make more chewy. I added a bag of chocolate chips and 1/2 cup walnuts. I think that was too many chips. I will reduce a bit next time.

name: neiman marcus  250 chocolate chip cookies recipe
review: WARNING: DO NOT USE A Silpat Matt to bake cookies on!  My first 2 batches  of cookies flattened out and ran together. I had to cut them apart with a pizza cutter. For the 2nd two batch, I used parchment paper with better & more ideal results. I love the slight texture the oatmeal adds to the cookies. The overall flavor is great, no sweeter than any other chocolate chip cookie I have ever eaten. Baking for 10 minutes results in a chewy cookie. I baked 5 minutes longer for a crispier cookie. Batch 2 still "fell" and flattened out but did not spread quit as much. Since this was too unpredictable, I am giving a 3 star rating for taste. I may try making them again one day to determine if it was pilot error or the recipe itself, and report back.

name: new mexico style chili chicken casserole
review: I omitted the onion and salt. And I used flour tortillas. This was good, especially for my wife who doesn't like things spicy. I had to put some hot sauce on mine but it was still good. Just very mild. It was very runny, even though I let it sit for about 15 minutes before cutting it. I will make it again, but I think I'll cut the chicken broth in half, in hopes that it won't be as runny next time.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Wow, wow, wow Sharon.  I am not a huge fan of Brussel sprouts, but I may be now.  These little sprouts were oh so lovely, soft, tender, slightly sweet with a nice dark outer skin that had a great bite.   Made exactly as written wouldn't change a thing. They were so quick and easy to make, I know that we will be enjoying these again.  Made for the Best of 2013, Kudos to you for making it into my Best of Cookbook for 2014.

name: crock pot thai chicken thighs
review: Thanks for posting this easy recipe.  The flavors were nice together.  The salsa that I used had a big kick to it, but the peanut butter tamed it.  It is a recipe that I will bookmark and make again.  Thanks for posting, KelBel!

name: awesome slow cooker pot roast
review: This is very good! I threw in some carrots and ate it with corn and red mashed potatoes. Simply but delicious.

name: double chocolate banana muffins
review: I made these last night as part of a "breakfast for dinner" meal.  The only minor change I made was to use chocolate chunks instead of chips because that is what I had on hand.  It was a great way to use up some bananas that had turned to dark to eat plain.  I got 14 very large muffins out of your recipe.  Thank you for a new go-to muffin recipe Charishma_Ramchandani!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Pretty good. Just a little bland.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Yum! Simple recipe - roasted cauliflower - but a great reminder of how delicious this veggie can be.

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: Wow, is this ever good! I am making it in 2 batches of 40 portions each for an event tomorrow. I used crushed tomatoes and did not have to use the immersion blender. And because I was making so much I combined a couple steps by pureeing the basil with a little of the soup in the blender and then adding back to the soup. Delicious. Simple. Wonderful. Thank you so much for sharing!

name: famous challah
review: Made half the recipe for one loaf, turned out beautifully.

name: veronica s easy spanish rice
review: Very delicious and super easy.  I substituted the tomato sauce with undrained diced tomatoes because it is what I had on hand, and what I have always used in Spanish rice.  I don't think it really changed the outcome much.  I love that this recipe was completed on the stove-top, which made it so much easier and quicker than other recipes I've tried.  I served this alongside Recipe #8595 for a very satisfying meal.  Thank you for a great side dish Trixyinaz!

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: My husband said these were hands-down the best sugar cookies he's ever tasted!  I especially love how the icing had a nice gloss to it but hardened completely so I could package them into plastic bags for gifts!  Perfect cookie!

name: crock pot stifado
review: This turned out really good.  I have been wanting to try this for awhile and I'm glad I finally did. It was very easy to make and cooked quickly. I served on angel hair pasta. I only used one onion as that seemed like a lot, but next time I will add another as it wasn't overpowering at all. It was nice to make something different.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Our daughter and son-in-law reported that these were the best pancakes they have tried so far, but they aren't sure this is just like IHOP (and they go there frequently).  LOL!  Who cares if they are the SAME; it's okay with me if they are better!  Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: my no roll pie crust
review: I needed a pie crust today for a coconut cream pie so decided to try this one.  It was very easy and tasted a lot like shortbread. I could taste the salt though so would cut that in half next time. Glad to know how to make this.  It will definitely come in handy.

name: roast beef horseradish spirals
review: Got to love them!

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: Thanks for sharing this recipe! I put 6 eggs, 3 Table. milk, 1/4 tsp. baking powder, salt and pepper in a food processor and turned the food processor on high for about 30 seconds. I next heated 1 Table. butter in a nonstick frying pan and added 1 sliced green onion and a handful of baby spinach. When the spinach had wilted, I pulsed the egg mixture again for 5 seconds and then quickly poured them into the pan and sprinkled a handful of cheese on top. I started stirring everything and the eggs were fluffy and delicious just like they were supposed to be.

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: This bread is the BEST!!  I only used 1/4 cup cocoa and I will do that next time I make it, too.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: I can?t believe I haven?t rated this yet as it has become my favorite chicken pot pie recipe.  I make it in two pie dishes.  I don?t find it all that time consuming to make, although I take a shortcut and use store-bought pie crusts. It?s a recipe worthy of all of the 5 star ratings!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Sharlene~~<br/>  I wish I could give you a thousand stars, for that's what it's worth! This is the best spaghetti sauce I have ever had, restaurant or home. What a fabulous consistency! I have a freezer loaded with this sauce and I use it regularly. Everyone I serve this to just raves about it, and I've sent many a guest home with some along with your recipe. Thank you so very much for making so many people happy.

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: Great! The whole family loved it and I'll definitely make again. Soaking the red onion made a huge difference and I'm wondering why I never tried that before! Delicious fresh dressing, next time I'll double it so we have leftovers. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: potato salad with chipotle peppers a man s salad
review: I am giving this 4 stars based on DH rating.  He is the only one who ate it.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: This is a lovely recipe, we did enjoyed the chicken.  I used bone and skin on thighs. Unfortunately the temperature was too high and our chicken burned. It still tasted good and had nice texture, but there was no sauce to speak of....and we peeled off the burnt skin.  I love all the ingredients in the sauce and will make this again, but at a much lower temperature.  Thanks for sharing your recipe. Made for Best of 2013.

name: nutella hot chocolate
review: This is so easy and freaking good!!! Love the rich flavor of chocolate and hazelnut. The thickness and smoothness were just prefect for me. I might reduce the Nutella amount by a little next time and sprinkle some cinnamon. I think I will never buy instant hot chocolate from the store from now on since I found this awesome recipe! Thank you for posting!

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: I was scared there would not be enough seasoning but these tasted great! I used red potatoes. I also took Angie's advice and friend them first without the lid. I'll definitely make these again!

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: So enjoyed this Sarafish! Thanks for posting. Easy to throw together and tastes divine. We used butter (1cup) for taste as we dislike margarine. It was a good substitution. We used hotdog buns for the bread and the spread and it was terrific. You need some sort of bread with thickness or a crust because the spread it heavy and could get soggy. The rolls, french bread, crusty bread, buns etc make the bottoms not burn due to being a thicker bread. We served it with spaghetti, meatballs and salad and felt the bread's taste was just as good or much better as premade garlic bread sold in stores. It was identical to garlic cheese bread we have had at restaurants too. The cheddar makes it kid friendy too. We will make again and again because it is so good. As #226 you don't really need my review but I want to urge people to try it. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: This was just so good.  I decreased the salt and pepper to 2 tsps each and the liquid smoke to 1 tsp adding some Worcestershire sauce instead.  I would further decrease the salt next time.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: So, so good!  Good enough to convert the haters to lovers!  The only thing I would caution is to check the ingredient list on your lemon-pepper seasoning to make sure it doesn't contain salt.  I didn't realize that what I happened to have did.  Luckily I caught it, or I would have had some salty sprouts!

name: lemon baked cod
review: Nice, nice! Instead of flour, I used up some seasoned breading mix, and broiled instead of baked. Not soggy at all! Served over collard greens with a side of brown rice, and what a healthy supper.

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: Great recipe for light and fluffy pancakes.  Served with maple syrup - yummy!  I halved the recipe and made 7 pancakes.

name: oven fried garlic chicken
review: Wonderful recipe.  Chicken came out very moist.  I ran out of parmesan cheese so I made it without and it still turned out great.  Thanks for sharing!

name: vanilla scented granola
review: Very very good recipe.  I added in some giant flakes of unsweetened coconut and subbed coconut oil for the veg oil.  Thanks for posting!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Fabulous and very easy!  Made just as written (except I threw in a handful of sliced mushrooms that needed to be used up - good!).  Next time I might squeeze in a teaspoon or so of scrirracha sauce into the soy sauce/water/cornstarch mixture just for a little added heat and interest.  Loved this recipe.  Thanks.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Yummy! Added a teaspoon of cumin, stirred it all together and served as a side dish with salsa lime chicken. Looking forward to the leftovers for lunch tomorrow. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: easy garlic chicken
review: I made this for dinner, but I only had 3 chicken breasts (a total of 1-1/4 lbs.). I used the 4 cloves of garlic (minced), but now wished I had only used 3. Also used the entire 4 tablespoons of brown sugar (but used dark brown sugar), and this was enough coating for just the 3 chicken breasts. If I were to make again using 4 chicken breasts, I would suggest adding 2 more tablespoons of the brown sugar. I baked this for 30 minutes in a 400º oven, but the chicken was a bit dry, so next time I'll reduce the baking time to 25 minutes. I can't see baking the chicken at a higher temp, not if you want burnt, dried-out chicken. I ended up dipping the chicken in a honey mustard sauce which I got from Hardees (hamburger restaurant), and boy did it make the chicken taste even better! Not a bad recipe, and will make again, but with the modifications I had stated, and that includes dipping the chicken in a honey mustard sauce.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: Absolutely loved this!

name: olive garden garlic alfredo sauce
review: Perfect post periodontal surgery recovery meal - 3 days out and ready for savoury - this with angel hair pasta and some slivered chicken breast was awesome. TY for posting! Will use again for guests when I am recovered - in the meantime it is heaven!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: Very delicious! I've roasted broccoli in the oven before, and this has a similar flavor, but I liked this better. Next time I may add some garlic to roast as others suggested. Thank you for sharing this!

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: This was SO much more delicious than I expected. Based on ingredients, I kind of thought this would turn out something similar to a meatloaf with the kind of ketchup/Worcestershire sauce I put on stuffed green peppers (which has yet another similar meat mixture). Sure, the meat was a little like that, but it was better somehow, and I'm convinced that some kind of magic happened in that last 20 minutes in the pan when it went from "meh, this will be OK," to "oh my gosh, this is actually fairly amazing." Thank you so much for sharing this!<br/><br/>I served this with Pan-Roasted Broccoli (http://www.food.com/recipe/pan-roasted-broccoli-155018) and Roasted Garlic Mashed Potatoes (http://www.food.com/recipe/roasted-garlic-mashed-potatoes-the-best-youve-ever-had-68159).

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: Wonderful and easy recipe - and foolproof, too!  I'd realized part way through the bread machine cycle that the loaf wasn't rising and that I'd forgotten the yeast.  So I reset the machine, added the yeast, and let it run again.  It turned out beautiful!  I probably should have left it in the oven for five more minutes to brown it a wee bit more, and I chose not to add the egg white (more lazyness than anything).  I will make this one often!  Thanks, andypandy!

name: baked tilapia with lots of spice
review: I didn't use the salt, or the bread crumbs. I basically used the spice mix as a dry rub, and let the filets sit in the fridge for several hours. Then sprayed baking dish, added filets, drizzled with olive oil, and proceeded. Fantastic spice blend that will find it's way into other recipes. Thanks for the keeper.

name: hot dog hamburger buns rolls cinnamon buns dough cycle a b m
review: I am rating this for the cinnamon rolls.  My daughter is allergic to eggs and soy, and I was looking for a hamburger bun recipe suitable for her.  I saw this recipe and while I am going to make the hamburger buns, I immediately wanted to make the cinnamon rolls.  I had previously been unsuccessful in finding a cinnamon roll recipe that didn't have eggs (that I felt compelled to make).  I got my bread machine out last night as my husband was cooking dinner.  I warmed the milk to about 110 degrees and then proceeded with adding the rest of the ingredients.  90 minute later I was rolling out my rectangle of dough (and very excited).  I spread a half a stick of butter (maybe a little less) over the dough and then I spread 1 cup of brown sugar mixed with 2 1/2 tablespoons of cinnamon over the butter.  Patted it down and very gently put my rolling pin over the surface.  I rolled them tightly and cut them at least 1 3/4 inches (I tried dental floss cutting, but went with my sushi knife instead).  I placed them cut side down in two round foil pans.  One pan got wrapped and put in the freezer.  The other pan I wrapped and put in the refrigerator.  Before I went to bad, I turned on the oven light and set the pan of cinnamon rolls in the oven (do NOT turn on oven).  This morning, they were ready to bake when I got up.  I put together a frosting (2 oz cream cheese, 7 tbls butter, 2 tablespoons milk, 1/2 tsp vanilla, 1/4 tsp salt and 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar).  These were AMAZING.  My daughter is over the moon happy (which makes me happy) and my husband said they were awesome as well!

name: amazing white trash puff balls
review: Lacked flavor SO my kids and I experimented and finally got the right combination of flavors and we renamed our new dish,.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: I scaled back for 2 serves and there was plenty for 3 of us.  For the garlic I used some garlic paste that I had made and stored in the fridge, otherwise made as per recipe, thank you Mimi Bobeck, mad for Best of 2013 tag game and recommended by KaeL.

name: world s best cinnamon raisin bread  not bread machine
review: Wow! This bread is so delicious! I did as suggested by another reviewer, and used 2 tablespoons melted butter instead of the milk. I also used 2/3 cup white sugar, 2/3 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup of cinnamon for the filling. I will be sure to make this when my family comes home for Easter. Thanks!

name: the best ever waffles
review: Perfect waffles!  I added cinnamon to the batter.

name: big thicket chicken and dumplings
review: Very satisfying on a cold winter evening.  I did cook the chicken the night before, also skimmed the fat off the broth. This was great because of all the dumplings.  Thank you!

name: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
review: I didn't have raisins, and I never use margarine (butter only) other than that I stuck to the recipe. It didn't turn out too bad, but I'm still searching for the perfect oatmeal cookie recipe.

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Excellent, kids loved them!  I added a bit of ground cayenne pepper, but otherwise, very quick to put together & will be a repeat. Served with angel hair pasta & garlic cheese bread. Thanks for sharing.

name: hard boiled eggs
review: Perfect!

name: crock pot   style loaded baked potato soup
review: This is delicious and super easy!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Easy and tasty recipe.  Next time I would decrease the amount of pasta, and perhaps replace it with beans.  I topped with cilantro and homemade guacamole.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: FANTASTIC cake! I divided the cake mixture into 2 9-inch cake pans and made a double-layered one (baking time was 40 minutes)! After reading the reviews, I substitutes the white sugar with brown sugar and also decreased the amount to 1 cup; used 1/2 cup oil and 1/2 cup apple sauce; chopped pecans instead of walnuts. The result - it was soft, moist, and full of greatness. I especially liked the frosting. Lennie was right. The frosting mentioned in this recipe was so much better than store-bought ones. I doubled the frosting recipe for my double-layered cake! It was GREAT!

name: zucchini chocolate cake
review: My husband took this cake to work and it got good reviews. People said it was moist and tasty. I think it could probably use more cocoa, however.

name: olive garden garlic alfredo sauce
review: I used a combination of half and half and heavy cream. I also used the low fat cream cheese.  I had to add extra cream cheese because it was too thin otherwise.  The flavor was fantastic.

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: Very good. I love the glaze......and very easy to do.

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: By far the best greek salad I've ever had.  However, I could not imagine using an entire cup of oil.  I did not use 3/4 cup, or even 1/4 cup.  I only used 1 tablespoon.  Also, since I wanted to keep the calories down, I added fewer olives and less cheese.  This reduced the fat even further.  I added maybe half a carrot for extra vitamin A and some quartered artichoke hearts because I like them.  No changes at all, otherwise.  Also, I was unclear whether I was supposed to add all of the dressing to the salad.  I did, but it seemed excessive so I poured off most of it.  As per Scotch Bob, I did marinate most of the veggies in the fridge with the dressing before putting everything over the lettuce and adding olives and cheese.  I did include some parmesan cheese.  I was not concerned about it's being authentic Greek or not.  I would definitely make this again.

name: best cream of broccoli soup
review: amazing soup

name: black bottom banana bars
review: great recipe! Quick and easy. I did it all in my standing mixer (except final bit where you separate). I sprinkled small bittersweet chips on top too.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: Delicious potatoes and the roasted garlic really makes this dish.  I could just eat the roasted garlic all by itself (and I did), but saved the majority for the potatoes : )  These potatoes make such a wonderful side dish to any meal.  Made for Best of 2013 Cookbook tag, March 1, 2014.

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: What a wonderful and easy pie to make.  We thoroughly enjoyed this! Thanks for sharing. Made for Best of 2013 tag.

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: This was good.  I added a decent amount of pepper and extra salt.  I still felt like it was missing something..... maybe fresh garlic?  I'm not sure, but it was a great base to work with, thank you!

name: refreshing mojito  by the pitcher mojitos
review: Simple and delicious! First time I made Mojitos and I will look no further for alternate recipe. A great recipe!

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: 5 stars from this family!  This was so good and easy to prepare, also it wasn't over the top sweet.     Thank you!

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: I am not an expert at cooking fish and especially salmon.  This came out perfect!  I made it for my DH for Valentine's Day. He loved it, though he preferred it without the glaze. I really enjoyed the glaze.

name: weight watchers broccoli cheese soup   2 pts per cup
review: Wow! I very much liked this. Great taste with so few ingredients. The right amount of heat and good broccoli taste. So low in calories that I will be making this a lot. Thanks a thousand times.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: I made these for a Valentine's meal with salmon.  They were so good and easy!  I will definitely make again!

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: This cooking technique makes a very tender, flavorful roast. I cooked a ~3 lb rump roast and it was fork tender. For our taste, will reduce the salt to 1 T and the pepper to 1 1/2 T. I also like the suggestion from other reviewers to add Worcestershire sauce w/ the liquid smoke and will try that next time. Thanks for sharing this recipe.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Made this frosting today.  It was delicious.  I didn't let my butter soften and it was a bit difficult on my hand mixer, but still delicious.  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: lemon baked cod
review: This recipe was quick and easy.  Taste was good.  Followed recipe as written.  Thanks for sharing.

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Great crust!  This was super easy to make and tasted great.  Thinking about making calzones with it.  Thank You!

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: Great taste, felt guilty for not squeezing a bag of key limes... for a few seconds.  But to convince someone that I actually made the pie, next time I would need to make my own graham cracker crust.  Recently I made a key lime pie authentically and made my own coconut crust, but it was no better than this!  Okay, no more swearing at a stack of limes!  Made for I Recommend tag game based on the recommendation by WiGal (who added it to her Best of 2013 cookbook!).

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: I have never had Brussels Sprouts before, but these get a five star rating for my husbands reaction. I quote, "These are probably the best Brussels Sprouts I've ever had; you have to eat 'regular' Brussels Sprouts to know what I am talking about". They were enjoyed by all.  DH also remarked that this recipe needs to go into the A rotation. Thanks for sharing. Made for Best of 2014 tag.

name: baked ham and cheese omelet roll
review: I have house guests who stay up to seven days and this is part of my planning along with a couple of other favorites including my quiche from freezer and croissant breakfast that I need to review. Breakfast is not my thing so I need easy.   Reminds me of egg filling in McDonalds breakfast which have not had in years but you can jazz this recipe up very easily to your own preferences and that is the beauty of this recipe- make it suit you and yours.  Hints from many other reviewers that I also do  -- Line pan with parchment paper.  Change order a bit-- start with flour and THEN add milk and then eggs to avoid flour balls. Use HALF of suggested flour and salt. Sometimes I vary by sautéing onions and bacon instead of ham depends upon what I made other mornings. Cooks much quicker than 15 minutes, remove after 9 min add stuff, wait for cheese to melt, roll, add more cheese, and put back in until it melts. Serve with coffee cake and fruit.

name: easy baked potato wedges
review: My family loved these... they are like fried wedges at a favorite restaurants, but much healthier!  I used extra virgin olive oil because of it's great flavor.  <br/><br/>Also, I was afraid they weren't going to turn out.  I washed and cut the potatoes and added all the seasonings before church, then finished them 3 1/2 hours later.  I didn't realize potatoes have a lot of moisture that I guess was drawn out (maybe because of the salt).  I had at least a cup of juice at the bottom of the bowl and could not get it to "stick" as I tried to remix it.  So the watery spice mixture was on the bottom of the pan as well as poured on top of the potatoes.  Surprisingly they still turned out great.  Next time I'll add the spices right before I bake them.<br/><br/>Also, I made 1 1/2 times the amount (except I didn't increase the oil), and it was the perfect amount for 7 people (3 adults, 4 children)... we ate every last one.<br/><br/>Thanks for a great recipe.

name: crock pot garlic brown sugar chicken
review: Delicious moist chicken! My DD made this for us when we came to dinner. She used a whole chicken witch she broke down. My whole family loved it however, I thought it was on the verge of being too sweet. Majority rules and that is why my review is 5 stars.

name: all purpose stir fry sauce  brown garlic sauce
review: I had always been told rice wine is rice vinegar. Not true. I added more sweetness to compensate. I added more sesame oil because I like that. also added sweet chili sauce and crushed red pepper and honey and sesame seed. I reduced the amount of soy sauce to 1/2 cup but could handle more. I changed this recipe a lot so probably shouldn't review but I know no one is going to read this review due to the number of reviews but I wrote this for myself for reference. Hi Dixe--you liked this and do did Kyle.

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: My DD made this recipe for when we came to dinner! It was so delicious! Of course she used my favorite aged reserved extra sharp cheddar cheese. Not only does it enhance the flavor of the cauliflower it melts perfectly to form the perfect cheese sauce. FT you have out done yourself with this true comfort food. :D

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: This cake is amazing!  We've never had banana cake, so I can't really say whether it is the best in the world, but it's really darn good.  I followed the directions precisely and it resulted in a super moist and sweet cake.  The frosting was also very delicious and I could definitely use it on other cakes as well.  Thank you for a delicious dessert that I'm sure will be made frequently in our home.  Thanks Rhonda *J*!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: WOW this is awesome!! I used Old Bay for the seasoning and broiled mine. It came out very moist and the cheesy, buttery topping is To Die For!! Thanks for sharing the recipe MaMa and Crabbycakes!!

name: grilled cheese  diner style
review: These sandwiches are good and I agree that the mayonnaise is easier to work with than butter.  I missed the butter flavor that grilled cheese usually has.  This will be good for my son when I need a quick lunch for him.  Thanks for something different tonight Dawnab.

name: cinnamon raisin bread for the bread machine
review: The texture and crust of this bread were fine. We thought it lacked flavor. Needs more spice and definitely more raisins.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: I have tried the original WW soup and had to force myself to eat it. This was a much tastier version - you are right, BEEF broth is better! I sautéed my cabbage and used spinach and diced mushrooms in place of the carrots and zucchini. I am not a huge fan of oregano, so next time I might try a little thyme, sage and/or rosemary. Thanks for posting!!

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: And Kittencal hits another one out of the park. I sliced the breasts in half and I used granulated garlic instead of powdered. I cooked until the chicken had and internal temp of 161 and then carried it over to 165 degrees and I cooked them on a rack. They were moist and crunchy. My son was cutting them with a fork (I taught him better, really I did. It was garlicy and I like it that way. Yum. I served with mushroom risotto. It is a meal I would have gladly paid for in a restaurant.

name: best banana bread
review: This was good but I think a little too sweet. Next time I will try 3/4 cup of sugar.

name: crock pot garlic brown sugar chicken
review: Made this on one of our busy nights and it turned out great.  I added broccoli on top.  Next time I'd like to add quartered onions and maybe some red pepper.  I thickened with cornstarch and served it over steamed rice.  Nice meal.

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: Very good and very easy to make.

name: tiramisu
review: What an excellent recipe - I don't like tiramisu, however, my SIL loves it, so for a special family dinner I decided to make this.  My SIL likes to rate meals using a rating of fail, satisfactory and outstanding - he gave the entire meal an outstanding + due mostly to this recipe.  I must say that I have never tasted a tiramisu I cared for, both due to texture and flavor, the flavor in this was amazing, the only part of it I didn't care for was the texture - I've got to find a way to put some crunch in there in the future.  That being said I will make this again even if I'm not able to find that crunch factor :)  Thank you Sassy Syrah for posting this.

name: grandmas sloppy joes
review: This was yummy! I bought manwich at the store and guess it didn't make it home so when I went to add it, it wasn't there!!  Looked this up and had everything on hand... it was GREAT! and easy!<br/>Might not be buying the Manwich...

name: the ultimate lemon meringue pie
review: I had too many lemons to use up, and had just gotten some eggs from a friend's farm, so I decided to try this recipe.  I didn't use a graham cracker crust, but a regular pastry crust.  This recipe is now down as a favorite for my husband -- the filling was tart, and the meringue was fluffy but had a lot of body.  Absolutely perfect!!

name: the best belgian waffles
review: WOW best waffles that I have ever made.  Got 20 waffles so have lots leftover for breakfast this week.  Made a berry syrup to go with them and served with sausage patties.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Love all of your recipes so decided to give this a try.  It was so easy & very good.  I placed mine on a rack over the pan to bake & this gave a lovely crisp coating with no mushy bottom.  Followed your suggestion of topping with marinara sauce & mozzarella cheese in the last few minutes.  Served over fettuccine noodles & served with a fresh garden salad.  Lovely dinner in a short amount of time

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: These are the best enchiladas I've ever made and my family agreed!!  Love that it doesn't use a canned soup and it is still quick to prepare!

name: banana banana bread
review: Very delicious bread. I am making a third time today and have decided to add nuts, vanilla and a little spice to it.

name: divine meatball sandwiches
review: Proud to be review 101 for this delicious meatball sandwich recipe. As the previous posters have said, the sauce makes this recipe. The spread is creamy, flavorful and glues the sandwich together. This sandwich is super messy but tasty. Grab the paper towel roll and dig in. Used bakery fresh baked soft bread and made as written. Next time we will add another dash of garlic powder. Kids and adults loved it. Perfect for a dinner or a party. Thanks for posting Jamie Renee. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: quick yellow cake
review: Very quick, very moist. Excellent with a good fudge frosting. Made it for my 2 year olds birthday. Only reason it is getting 4 stars is because the flavor was a bit mealy...not soft and sweet. It was a bit like a Moroccan cake, porous, and semolina tasting. A bit of grit, if you will, even though the actual consistency of the cake was fluffy and moist. This is purely a taste issue. I would make this again, just with different expectations. Thanks!

name: homemade rice a roni
review: Made this for supper tonight and it was a big hit.  I used Knorr's Chicken Bouillon (powder) for the broth.  I don't normally like it as a broth but it did really well in this recipe and I was able to almost duplicate Rice-a-Roni.  Thanks for sharing this recipe.

name: tsr version of chili s chicken enchilada soup by todd wilbur
review: This got good reviews. I like the idea of using the masa harina to thicken it. This would be a great use for leftover rotisserie chicken.

name: hamburgers with brown gravy  total comfort food aka  meat cakes
review: Hubby approved of this recipe! Comfort food for sure.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Delicious easy to make basic macaroni and cheese. I used recipe #30358 to cook the macaroni while I was making the sauce. Also added a couple tablespoons minced green pepper (from the garden), 1/4 teaspoon dry mustard, and a few shakes of Parmesan cheese. Served with slices of leftover cooked ham, pickled beets, and bread and butter.

name: failproof french bread  bread machine
review: Great recipe. I didn't realize I should cut them before rising, so I cut after but it didn't have the right effect. Regardless it was delicious with chicken and noodles. I'm using the second loaf for blueberry bread pudding. Thanks!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: I can't believe I forgot to rate these! Add another 5 stars from my family. A keeper for sure!

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: Made this yesterday! Added a can of pinto beans and half a can of corn. Just added a dollop of sour cream and cheese to the top. My husband liked it. I thought it was ok! Smelled delicious though.

name: awesome baked ham
review: I cut the recipe in half for a ham half the size.  While the ham was good, the sauce was not a hit.   All you could taste is the mustard, and my daughter hated it.  I guess I'm accustomed to some sort of spice in the sauce.  The recipe is good and in the future I may add some sort of spice to the sauce and cut the mustard a tad.  Thank you!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Another 5 stars from this family.  I'm glad it only made 12 otherwise I would have been snacking on these all night.  I used a cheese grater on frozen butter, seemed to be easier, with great fluffy results.  Thank you!

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: I received compliments from my husband on this dish, all thanks to you!  This is great comfort food and will be put in the the "again" file.  Thank you again!

name: unbelievably easy potato soup
review: I was pleasantly surprised at the ease of this recipe.  I added in some other things (sliced carrots, garlic, rosemary, dried onions, and a bit of vegetable Better Than Bouillon) and it was really delicious.  Also, I didn't end up smashing my potatoes at all; the smaller bits kind-of melted into the pot as I stirred then I added a splash of half and half at the end to loosen it up a bit at the end.  Yummy!

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: Soooooo good. We loved this. Made as written. It takes a lot more than 7 minutes to prep but well worth it. The golden raisins were a sweet tidbit in a savory sauce. The entire family inhaled it. Served over rice. We will make again and again. Thanks for posting Sue! Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: This is outstanding! But do NOT substitute for the sesame oil. I tried it, and it just wasn't even close. Use the sesame oil, and I suggest garnishing with some toasted sesame seeds as well.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
