name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Updating my previous review -<br/>    5-stars instead of my original 2 stars.  I think it must be the quality of the ingredients I used this time compared to the first time I made this. I started with a loaf of fresh, homemade Italian bread.  I used unsalted butter instead of margarine.  The cheddar cheese I used was labelled 'Seriously Sharp White Cheddar'.  <br/><br/>With nearly 200 5 star ratings, I feel weird giving it 2 stars but for me it was just fair.  The cheddar cheese seemed out of place on garlic bread. I couldn't really taste the garlic or the parmesan cheese. I did like how baking, rather than broiling, the bread resulted in a crispy top and bottom.

name: mashed sweet potatoes
review: Was surprised that the recipe didn't call for the potatoes to be cooked first. But it was delicious.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: this is really good.  Its simple to prepare and when you mix it all up after cooking its nice and creamy.  My family really liked this.  thanks for sharing.

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: I liked it but no one else in the family does :(

name: kittencal s greek moussaka
review: added sliced parboiled potatoes on base then the eggplant, minced lamb tomato sauce,eggplant,bechamel sauce......very very very good!!

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: Really good!  This is the easiest potato soup I've ever made!  (Made just as written.)  Thanks.

name: meatball sub casserole
review: We loved this! All the flavours from one of my favourite sandwiches in a casserole, which made it OK to eat for dinner! I love homemade meatballs and with the sauce and bread base as well it was delicious. Even though the bread was a little soggy, we didn't mind at all. I followed the recipe exactly and would make this again.

name: low   slow oven baked ribs   super simple
review: These oven baked ribs were really delicious.  Although they do fall off the bone, they are tender and moist and your fingers stay clean since you can use your fork : )  This recipe is so easy and I liked the idea that I could just leave them in the oven and they required very little attention until the end.  Served these delicious ribs for my New Year's dinner along with my Southern blackeyed peas, cabbage, potato salad and cornbread.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: I cannot believe I haven't posted a review of this amazing recipe before - I've made this at least a dozen times.  Of all the ways I prepare pork chops this is my DH and my favorite.  Very easy to pull together and the chops are amazingly tender - the sauce is very good over rice or noodles.  Thanks so much for posting Yooper:)

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: This was definitely easy because I didn't have to chop garlic or ginger or wait for the beef to marinate.  Since I am vegan I used substitute "beef tips" instead of real meat.  Also, I didn't have enough broccoli so I added a chopped green squash along with the broccoli I had.  We both finished up a half recipe in one sitting.

name: the best ever waffles
review: The butter content is too high for the ratio of dry ingredients making for a very thin batter and a rubbery waffle. I think if you halve the amount of butter (and even replace with canola oil), it would probably be an outstanding waffle. The flavor was good, just the texture wasn't what we'd hoped it'd be.

name: thick and creamy new england clam chowder
review: This is a great recipe--and while I usually don't like using canned soup, I am glad I tried this! I did make a couple of changes based on other reviews: I did not add the bacon (I didn't miss it at all) and used a couple Tbs of butter instead. I also used 1 10 oz can of baby clams, 1 6.5 oz can of chopped clams, and 1 6.5 oz can of minced clams. I cut back to two Russet potatoes (plenty!), minced two ribs of celery that I cooked with the onion, and then used cream of potato soup. I also added some parsley, subbed some thyme for the dill, and added 1/2 Tbs of sherry. It tasted great and I will definitely make this again!

name: best banana bread
review: Made just as directed, and it was amazing.  Definitely will be my go-to banana bread now!

name: cottage cheese roast  vegetarian meatloaf
review: My husband and I did not care for this meatloaf. It seem to lack flavor, and it didn't even come close to tasting like a meatloaf.! We ended up topping our slices with Sweet Baby Ray's Sweet 'n Spicy Barbecue Sauce, which was the only thing that gave this meatloaf flavor. We did eat 2 slices, but ended up throwing out the rest. Guess we much prefer our meatloaf made with real beef.

name: 24k carrots
review: Really good. Super fast and easy to fix. Thanks for the recipe!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: I've made this twice without substitutions. The first time I made it I used the Sweet Baby Ray Barbecue Sauce and found it just a bit bland. But then the second time I made it with Jack Daniels Barbecue Sauce, and it was fantastic. I'm giving it five stars because the recipe calls for "favorite barbecue sauce" rather than a specific brand, so allows for "each to one's own taste"! Also, the second time I had to use what was labelled a 4-lb center-cut port roast; I'm assuming this means it's a shoulder cut but I'm not sure. Anyway I slow-cooked it on low 9 hours before adding the barbecue sauce, and it came out falling apart tender and easy to pull apart. I then cooked it another hour and was all set.

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: Made this sauce tonight for chicken and fell in love!  I did add a pinch of salt and had to use garlic powder and dehydrated onions.  I can only imagine the taste with fresh onions and garlic!  Thanks.

name: copycat  green giant niblets corn in butter sauce
review: The corn was so delicious prepared this way.  It was sweet and tender surrounded in a lovely, silky butter sauce.  It was perfect served over saffron rice.  Thank you for sharing a recipe that I will make again.  Made for What's on the Menu Tag Game 2015.

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: Wow....delicious! So few ingredients, so little time and so tasty.  Winner! I used evaporated milk instead of cream and half the butter called for . Total keeper recipe! Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: easy lemon pound cake
review: Delightfully moist and light and very lemony.

name: milk free  egg free pancakes
review: We were out of milk and my kids wanted pancakes. These were really great! We used the egg in the recipe. Will make again, even if I do have milk in the house. Thanks!

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: Such an easy-fix & no sml wonder that your recipe has a nearly perfect rating after so many reviews. It quite simply deserves every single star it has gotten & then some. I made it exactly as written, but reduced the temp & cooked it a bit longer than stated. Then I turned off the oven & let it sit there while I finished the rest of our meal. It only got better! I love this recipe! Thx for sharing it w/us. :-)

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Been wanting to try this for quite some time & was VERY disappointed. The sauce was terrible!!! Won't be making this again...sorry!!!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: Excellent!  I did what other reviewers did and cooked for 15 minutes then draining the fat/juice prior to adding the sauce. Also, for the sauce, I subbed 2T of BBQ sauce for the ketchup and added more minced garlic. I lined my pan with tin foil for easy clean-up. There was an abundance of sauce, so I only poured about 1/2 on the wings, I will save the rest for something else. Thanks for posting!

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: Loved how easy and such good flavors.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: Yummy! I froze leftover mashed potatoes with this in mind and am glad I did. Made it exactly as written except with canned vs. frozen peas because I could buy a smaller amount of them (didn't want any left over since DH doesn't really like them.)  I used ketchup instead of paste. Might have overcooked as the gravy wasn't as plentiful as I'd like (Suns game went into double OT!). Don't overcook!

name: simple baked chicken drumsticks
review: So simple, so delicious. Surely you can change up the seasoning as you wish.

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Missing something...don't know what. Orange rind, maybe? Was good, though. Will tinker with it.

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: YUMMY!!!! I made the pasta separately and just added it to the bowls as my kids eat at a different time than my husband and I do and I didn't want soggy noodles. Definitely making this again.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: I tried this recipe last night as a change of pace from our usual soy sauce based marinade for salmon. I loved it. What more can I say? Light. Did not cover up the salmon....thanks for the great recipe.

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: Loved the flavor in this soup!  This one pushed out my previous recipe for Tortilla soup.  Thanks!

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: These were super easy. I used 2 whole eggs instead of 4 egg whites. They were a little bland alone but once I poured on some maple syrup my kids gobbled them up!

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Nice batter. Got a nice smooth batter by putting my bananas through a potato ricer. Be warned: baking for 30 minutes is WAY too long! I checked mine at 21 minutes and they were too dark. I'd say 18 minutes would be a better recommendation. I'm going to add a dash of cinnamon next time.

name: weight watchers broccoli cheese soup   2 pts per cup
review: This was quite good.  I cooked some carrots first then added the other things.  My kids couldn't even tell that there were diced tomatoes in this...they thought they were red peppers (bwahahaha)!

name: best oatmeal cookies
review: Perfect texture! Crunchy on the outside, soft and chewey on the inside!

name: 100  whole grain wheat bread
review: We made this for my grandson who is allergic to eggs and dairy products.  We all were very pleased with the texture and taste.  Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: This made a lovely, rich, thick sauce and we really liked the flavour. I left out the red wine and crushed red pepper flakes as our toddler was having some but it still had a good flavour to it. Really easy to make too! I didn't feel the need to add sugar and cut the oil to 2tbsp so it was Weight Watcher friendly too. A good all-rounder!

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: We really enjoyed it.  The pot was very nearly too small.  I used a "cheesy" pasta sauce, which I think added a dimension to the flavor.  I'll add more vegetables next time, but otherwise we'll make this again, and again.<br/><br/>Top with Romano, and some toasted bread on the side.  Divine.

name: copycat recipe for carrabba s chicken marsala
review: Fantastic and so easy to make! I didn't use very much shallots, since I'm sensitive, but it still was very flavorful.

name: 24k carrots
review: We really enjoyed this recipe.  I have made it twice now, first with brown sugar and the second time with maple syrup sugar!  Both were a hit with everyone.  Thanks.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: I made these to take over to a friend who just had a baby. I ended up folding them all, securing with toothpicks and freezing so she could pop one in the oven whenever she needed. The toothpicks can stay in while baking to hold the shape. It worked really well and she absolutely loved them! Thanks for the recipel

name: crazy crust pizza
review: This is the weirdest recipe I have ever seen but it worked! Made when my 3 older grandkids were over and it was very tasty. It fed 5 of us and I think they would have eaten more if there had been any extra. Even my husband went back for 2nd's and he doesn't even like pizza. Will make this again. Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Very good. We reduced the amount of parmesan for our taste.

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: The meat was dry even though I followed the instructions exactly.

name: kale chips
review: Oh my gosh, these are so good!! I used the prepackaged kale and probably only used 1 bunch. I took them out before they were all completely crisped up because I loved the taste. I didn't salt them in the bowl but shook out some kosher salt trying not to overdue it. Was still pretty salty for me, so next time I will just sprinkle a small amount over the pan after I spread it out. A keeper!! Thanks so much for posting!

name: easy cole slaw
review: Not having much of a sweet tooth, I used about a teaspoon of sugar (and don't think I even needed to add that).  I think I would halve the dressing ingredients the next time as there was a tad too much dressing for my tastes.  Great tasting though!

name: christmas rum balls or bourbon balls
review: I finally made these.  I had bought the vanilla wafers before Christmas to make these for the cookie trays but didn't have time to make them.  I didn't have any spiced rum so I used half Bacardi and half Rum Chata.  The dough is very sticky to work with so I used my small scoop to make the balls.  Using the scoop, I made 48 balls.  I used quite a bit more powdered sugar (probably at least half a cup) because I didn't want them to stick to each other.  I already tasted one and it was very good.  I think that the Rum Chata might be less potent than regular rum.  That's okay, I'll just eat two instead of one.  :)  Thank you for posting this recipe!  I'll make sure that I make them for the cookie trays next year!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Rhonda J: I'm breaking my review into two units-1) reviewing how you wrote the recipe, and 2) the end results. First, 1) Your recipe has to be one of the finest, best written and most detailed recipes I've ever had the pleasure of reading!!! How I wish EVERY recipe was this thorough! Not only did you mention bowl size (major props on that point!) but also repeated the ingredients in each step, as cookbooks of old, did. I write out my recipes the exact same way so I truly appreciate the detail and time it took you to post this. 2) End results? Perfect! Incredible! BEST banana cake I've EVER eaten!!!! Followed everything to the letter (did sneak in 1 tsp of Vietnamese Cinnamon). NEVER had over-flow from 9" x 13" pan; mine was done, to perfection in one hour flat! Had no room in freezer but breezeway was at 38 degrees so I set the pan out there, to cool.Used a modified version of your cream cheese frosting; only 2 cups of powdered sugar vs. the amount you posted. Makes for a less sweet frosting and more "cream cheesey". My friends and family were over-the-moon for this cake, so I thank YOU for posting it! Job well done, Rhonda J!!!!

name: parmesan crusted tilapia
review: Loved it, and the parm crispies were a nice bonus.

name: bacardi rum cake
review: What can I say that hasn't been said. Truly yummie. I made 5 cakes. I gave 4 away as gifts. I used  pecans and Bacardi Gold Rum. It was very good. I plan on making this cake every Christman from now on. I also use a Duncun Hines yellow cake mix and added the pudding.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: The first time I made these I didn't like the lemon  pepper. I made these again without recalling I had made them before and by some stroke of luck forgot the lemon pepper totally, and felt they were perfect with just salt and black pepper. So if someone doesn't like the lemon pepper, try it again without and I'm sure you will love it!

name: crispy ginger beef
review: My boyfriend made this recipe for our dinner.  He made it as written and normally cooks quite well.<br/><br/>I took two bites and my stomach is still aching from the overuse of ginger and crushed red pepper.  It went into the trash.  <br/><br/>I hate that we wasted good beef on this.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Definitely a keeper. Super easy. Super tasty. The ginger and the brown sugar really make this dish stand out. I added a little water to make it more saucy.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I made the recipe as directed and was really disappointed.  The pork chops were inedible until we grabbed a bottle of barbecue sauce for dipping.  The pork chops were REALLY dry.  The sauce did not stick to the chops.  The sauce was thin and watery and pooled in the bottom of the baking dish. I would not make the recipe again without some of the tweaks suggested in the reviews.  Next time I will try covering it in the oven, or pan frying  I also like the idea of some way to thicken the sauce.  My advice is, don't make as the recipe directs but instead follow some of the suggestions in the reviews.

name: monastery lentils
review: Loved this for meatless Mon.  Added about 2/3 c. brown and wild rice I already had as a leftover.<br/>Served with rye bread and Farmers Market Kale salad.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Great flavour, overall a beautiful warming, hearty meal.

name: chicago italian beef
review: BOMB!!! This recipe is great for sandwiches and beef goes so well with rice too! I cooked the beef for 12 hours and it's already fork tender and so so delicious! I made two small changes - 1) I used fresh carrots, broccoli and mushrooms instead of giardiniera; 2) Sweet green pepper was substituted by mini sweet pepper. I wish I could give this recipe 10 stars! The juice softened my french bread. I am not a big sandwich fan, but I devoured this one!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: The day I made this, the flavor was really good, but the next day the leftovers tasted AMAZING! From now on, if serving this for entertaining, I'll make the day before and reheat.

name: strawberry cheesecake trifle
review: I used low fat versions of the cream cheese and sour cream and used some stevia to replace half of the sugar. I also had to use white cake.  Even with all of these substitutions, it still turned out fantastic.  My only suggestion is not to make this ahead of time.  The cake can get soggy and isn't nearly as good.

name: french bread rolls to die for
review: Fantastic!!!  So easy!!!!  Great taste!!!  I will never buy store bought rolls again.  Thank you for sharing.  A side note - 1 1/2 cups water in microwave for one minute brings water to the right temp to activate the yeast.

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: Enjoyed by the family, great tasting glaze, however a bit time consuming waiting for it to caremalise.

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: We made this for breakfast yesterday and we have had it for 3 meals with just 2 of us.  I have really craving potatoes and onions.  These were great!  Made for Favorites of 2014.

name: yummy crispy baked fish
review: The coating is wonderful - really sticks well. I didn't have any trouble turning it over. I ran out of cayenne, and it really needed it. We ended up needing some tartar sauce.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Super yummy and easy to make.   We made it using just hot Italian sausages and it was still super meaty and decadent.   I used no boil lasagna noodles and it turned out perfect.

name: ground turkey chili for people who hate ground turkey
review: This was OK.  Just not my favorite.  To be fair, I'm not a ground turkey fan to begin with but the title gave me hope.  Sorry.

name: crazy crust pizza
review: I was skeptical that this could be any good, especially after putting the uncooked batter in the oven,  but I was so wrong. It tasted great to me. We did a veggie pizza and after reading some of the other reviews I decided to par-bake the crust for 5 mins before putting the veggies on, cooked for 20 mins, topped with 1 cup of homemade thick sauce and baked about another 10 mins. I baked mine on a foil lined tin and wont use foil next time. The edges were nice and crisp, but the center was still a little soft . It's not pizza crust, but with the toppings it has all the flavors and you can eat it like pizza. I love that I didn't feel grossly full after eating three slices. Thanks for sharing this fun recipe, I'll be making it again.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: These were really delicious and super easy!  I used a full 2 lbs of ground beef (because I'm cheap) and used fresh grated parmesan but followed all of the other ingredients as written.  When it came time to cook the meatball I opted for the oven method and layered in Ragu sauce with the meatballs and baked for 35 minutes.  The came out perfectly cooked and still so moist after cooking.  We used your wonderful meatball recipe to make meatball subs and I plan to use the sauce left in the bottom of the pan to make baked spaghetti casserole tomorrow night.  Thanks for a keep Kittencal!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Now I understand why this recipe has so many 5 star reviews. WOW. This is really great. I used small sprouts so I didn't cut them in half the way I normally do, and I only shook the pan once about 2/3 into the cooking time. I loved the almost burned spots that gave the sprouts so much flavor. I didn't add any extra kosher salt at the end as they were plenty salty already. I would definitely taste them first before adding it or even cut down the salt in half if you don't love salt. Will definitely make this one again!

name: easy cole slaw
review: Great recipe.  I use about 1 1/2 pounds cabbage/carrots for a less "soupy" texture.  It's also great with a combination of red cabbage and carrots... to get your nutrition filled colorful veggies in!  I add about 2 T Beaver hot cream horseradish for a bite... but not too spicy... yummmm!  This is the first time I ever made cole slaw and it's delicious and something I'll be making more in the future.  I was striving for something like Famous Dave's cole slaw... and with the horseradish, I think it's just about as good... and that's saying a lot!  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: olive garden garlic alfredo sauce
review: Nice sauce.  Made half a recipe to use in Recipe #154640.  Still have some left so will serve with pasta.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: Excellent recipe - prepared exactly as written - the only thing I would do different next time is skin the legs, neither my DH nor I care for chicken skin, and marinate for several hours to allow the deliciousness of the sauce to permeate the meat.  Thank you djmastermum for an excellent recipe.  We will be enjoying this for years to come.

name: baked tilapia with lots of spice
review: This was a very easy alternative to fried fish.  I had read the reviews prior to cooking this and made one small change.  I completely omitted the salt, as it would be easy to salt at the table if need be.  The taste was phenomenal without salt, so that is how I will make it from now on.  I have a hard time eating fish, as I just don't normally like the taste of it, but with this recipe I will be able to start rotating it into our diet more often.  Even my 1O, 8 and 4 year old children loved it.  My 8 year old daughter wanted more, but alas there wasn't any leftover.  Thank you for a great new way to eat fish ladypit!

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: I seem to use this every couple of months--it's so delicious and simple. I just keep a mixture on hand of 1 part each  brown gravy mix, Italian dressing mix and ranch dressing mix and rub it on when ever i'm preparing to slow cook a new roast. Definitely one of my top go-to recipes!

name: easy creamy sour cream chicken casserole
review: This gets top scores for ease of preparation, and is pretty tasty too.  It lends itself well to variations and tweaking, as evidenced by all the alterations in previous reviews.  I did not want to boil the chicken, so I simply seasoned it with garlic powder, salt, pepper, and a little poultry seasoning and baked at 350 until done.  I then cubed and prepared the recipe as directed.  I really wanted to use the cream of chicken soup, but realized I only had cream of mushrooms.  I did find garlic butter Ritz crackers, though!  All in all, this is simple, quick and appealing to most palates.  Thanks for sharing.

name: mini tacos
review: We have both meat eaters and vegetarians in our house. So I made these with veggie grounds, just like I do when we have regular tacos.  I also used a Mexican blend for the cheese.  They were easy to grab and go for a quick dinner on the run.

name: neiman marcus  250 chocolate chip cookies recipe
review: Very yum!

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Super, but not health food.

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: Delicious and so simple! Thanks so much for sharing the keeper recipe.

name: panda express orange chicken
review: Delicious!!. I froze the left overs. I will let you know how it freezes. I followed the recipe exactly.

name: jalapeo bites
review: These didn't crisp up as much as I would have liked, so I think next time I will use panko crumbs. I may also try and spritz them with cooking spray before popping them in the oven or flipping them over so they will bake on both sides. The flavor was good and everyone enjoyed them. They went well with the burgers we grilled up.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Made these for dinner tonight and had to hide enough for the meal.  They are very light and flavorful, guess they floated off the plate?!  thanks

name: best apple cake
review: This was delicious!... soooo good!  And it definitely serves more than 12... 5 rows of 3... 15 pieces brings the calories down to 507 (and if you're counting calories, you can have 1/2 a piece without too much guilt).<br/><br/>I used freshly ground whole wheat flour (I like to try whole wheat flour and wasn't sure how that would work... it was great!).  The caramel sauce was amazing.  I'm so excited to find this recipe.  I had lost my favorite apple cake recipe and am so glad I found this.<br/><br/>Thanks!

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: I didn't put the chips on the bottom.  That way there was no chance of soggy chips if there were any leftovers.  Other than that, I followed the recipe and we scooped it out onto our chips on the plate.  We topped it off with sour cream and some added hot sauce.  Quick and easy to make.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: It seems next time I make these, I will have to make an extra batch just for my daughter! Recipe works beautifully, biscuits were light and tender and flavorful. Thanks for posting.

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: I softened the cranberries as others did and they were nice and moist. Thanks for sharing.

name: crock pot   style loaded baked potato soup
review: delicious!!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Nice and moist. Taste like my mom's used to. Thanks for posting!

name: auntie s delicious soft pretzels  amish recipe
review: great recipe! very soft. i throw all the ingredients in the bread maker for the dough cycle and bake in oven. i do like to add salt in the dough.

name: easy pizza pasta casserole  oamc
review: My family really didn't care for this dish and said that it isn't a repeat.  I have an entire pan left over that I will pass on to another family.  May be that I added some sausage and bell pepper???  Or maybe the Italian season I used??? Or maybe the brand of spaghetti sauce???  Who knows?  Thank you for the recipe though!

name: beer  n bbq braised country style pork ribs
review: Awesome! I never eat ribs, but I actually tried these. I realized that I never poured the beer off while we were eating them, but I don't think there was really much (if any) left in the pan when I went to pour the BBQ sauce over the ribs. I browned the ribs in a large deep cast iron skillet on the stovetop and then put the whole thing in the oven and followed the rest of the recipe as directed. My family said they were some of the best ribs they'd ever had (after the got over the fact that I had actually made and subsequently eaten ribs)! Thanks for sharing!

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: Yes, I strongly agree!!  This will be my only sugar cookie recipe from now on!!  Only thing I can add is that I made these with my 2 and 4 year old so we (unintentionally) got varying thicknesses.  The ones that were more like 1/4 inch were the best because you could get a little of the chew as well as the crispy.  But in the end, they were all awesome.  Thanks once again Kittencal.....

name: basic batter waffles
review: Left out the vanilla & maple. Excellent, thanks for sharing!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: I added some Rotel tomatoes and black olives. Pretty tasty recipe. I think I will spice it up more next time.

name: best twice baked potatoes
review: These were the BEST twice-baked potatoes I have ever had! Made these for a family gathering and everyone was so impressed on how good they were. I sprinkled some dried tarragon leaves on top before serving. Will try to make them with bacon bits inside next time. This recipe deserves the word "BEST". Thanks so much for posting!

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: Such a great soup! I used boneless chicken thighs, adding them fresh, uncut and shredding them before adding the noodles. There was too much broth (no room for noodles) and it wasn't very creamy so next time I'll skip one of the cans of chicken broth.  I would also add the peas when boiling the noodles so that they taste fresh.

name: the best chicken tortilla soup
review: Excellent soup.  I added corn and beans but it didn't need them.  Really good  and really easy.  Nice heat to it too.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Great stuff!! Thanks for sharing! This is a definite keeper - & easy, too!!

name: uncle bill s vegetarian minestrone soup
review: Made half a recipe and it was perfect for us.  Loved it for meatless Mon.

name: brown sugar bundt cake
review: Quick and easy hit!  I personally thought it was a bit too sweet but it was inhaled by all the others.  Thanks for posting!

name: chicken pot pie with 2 crusts
review: Simple and easy.  The possibilities are endless!  Update 1 suggestions:  We enjoy this on a regular basis.  I usually peel, cube and fry (covered) two potatoes in a skillet until tender.  Leftover baked potatoes work well.  We've substituted turkey for chicken and added 3-4 cups of freshly sautéed kale when the potatoes were nearly done.  That's a good one.  Update 2 suggestions:  Another tried variation: 4 cups chicken, no potatoes and 6 strips crumbled bacon.  1/2 teaspoon poultry seasoning is a great addition to the salt and pepper.  This is a family favorite now.

name: basil pesto
review: I substituted walnuts for pine nuts.  Freezes well.  This recipe has inspired me to triple our basil crop next season.  I've added a photo of our favorite way to eat it.  My kids say it's perfect - baked Italian loaf, pesto, sliced roma tomatoes and mozzarella.

name: jello cookies
review: A cookie scoop was helpful since the dough was so sticky.  We decided to roll the balls in white sugar and put them on a greased cookie sheet.  That made it so much easier.  We chose cherry lemonade.  Yummy!  The endless color and flavor options make this recipe a serious keeper.

name: chicken pesto
review: I can't believe after all the years I have been making this recipe, I have never left a review! This is a favorite in our household. The only changes that I make (occasionally) are adding sliced black olives and swapping the provolone for crumbled feta. My family loves this and I am happy to serve them something that tastes good AND isn't too hard on the waistline. Thanks for posting! Sorry it took so long to give this the 5-star review it deserves.

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: A great Apple crisp! I used a total of 5 apples. We loved this warm with vanilla ice cream.

name: granny s slow cooker vegetarian chili
review: My son gave up meat for Lent and I was craving chili.  I made this on my stove top and took about an hour from start to finish.  We all enjoyed this chili--all of my 5 children and that is saying something.  For those of us eating meat, I made some ground beef and had it on the side.  I ended up using 2 cans of 29 oz crushed tomatoes to make more for our large family.  I adjusted the seasonings by adding a total of 2 tbsp chili powder and 1 tbsp cumin along with all the other seasonings.  I also used carrots in place of the zucchini.  We served with fritos, sour cream, tabasco, and jalapenos on top.

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: I little too sweet and could have used some veggies besides onion.  Next time I will add carrots, peppers, maybe celery.  This was really good over mashed potatoes.  Thanks. I will make this again.  So easy.

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: These pancakes are so good and fluffy.  They remind me of why buttermilk is superior to milk in a pancake recipe.  I make pancakes about twice a week so trust me when I say I have tried many recipes!  If I don't have buttermilk, Pete's Scratch Pancakes is my other favorite recipe.

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: These were really good.  I did add extra chili powder and added cayenne pepper.  I like the sweetness followed by a bit of a bite.  I prepared these with the intent to cook them immediately, but then I had to leave, so they remained in the fridge overnight.  The sugar does become wet and drip off.  But still, all turned out well.  Thank you for the recipe.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: This is my new favorite way to have cauliflower.  I LOVED it.  The garlic was amazing, too.  I also added carrots to the mix, which was okay, but the carrots are a different density and cook at a different pace so they weren't as soft.  If I do that again, I will cut the carrots into smaller chunks.  I made this a second time and put grape tomatoes in with the cauliflower.  AMAZING!  So sweet and juicy.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: This is a fairly easy to make wonderful chicken casserole. I halved the recipe and also made some changes: 1) sautéed onion, chopped red bell pepper and chicken in melted butter. Seasoned with salt and pepper; 2) reduced mayo amount and added sour cream as the recipe suggests; 3) totally forgot to put milk in. The casserole turned out delicious, creamy and satisfying. Thanks for posting!

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: Wow, wow, wow.  We really enjoyed the chicken wings prepared this way.  So quick and easy to make.  So delicious.  They were perfectly cooked, tender and juicy with a crisp outer skin, spiced perfectly.  Thanks so much for sharing a recipe that I will make again and again.  Made for Whats on the Menu? Tag Game 2015.

name: quick soft breadsticks
review: My family loved them... I used 2 cups whole wheat flour.  Thanks!

name: sticken chicken
review: Simply fabulous. We made the whole batch for just the two of us and then shredded the leftovers for sandwiches later in the week! Loved all the flavours, the slight hint of ginger was just great. Lovely, moist and sweet!

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: Made with Recipe #199612.  Perfect!!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Substituted cod for tilapia.  Served with garlic bread and Recipe #125463 by Crabbycakes.

name: awesome slow cooker pot roast
review: Awesome flavor!  I used a 3 lb shoulder roast, 1.4oz pkg of Knorr French Onion Recipe Mix, 8oz beef broth (less liquid which was recommend by others) and two cans of cream of mushroom soup.  It slow cooked on low for 6 hours.  The meat was tender and flavorful and everyone fought over the gravy!  The gravy was still quite thin.  Next time I'll use 6 oz of broth because I don't want to mess with corn starch.  Update: 6 oz works great.  I've made this about six times.  Lipton's Recipe Secrets Onion Soup & Dip Mix (2 oz) works well too - just increase to 7 oz of broth.  If using a 23 oz family size soup, increase broth to 9 oz.

name: low   slow oven baked ribs   super simple
review: The house smelled amazing and we couldn't wait to eat.  I was not disappointed!  Great recipe.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: I usually turn my nose up at cauliflower, yuck.  But this is delicious!!  Five stars from my very picky family!!

name: garlic panko chicken strips
review: Love love love. Thank you Lennie!

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: Excellent...I've been making this dish for years...except not with the dill...that add a nice new flavor...I used yukon gold potatoes...yum...made for Best of 2014 tag game...

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: A keeper of a recipe!  Thank you for sharing this delicious and easy recipe.  I used a honey lime jelly in place of the honey and avocado oil for the oil. I recommend turning the wings about halfway through so that one side isn't overdone. I think next time I will cut the sweetener by half and substitute with a spicy sauce.

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: 152 reviews!  Well, looks like every review that I couldn't think up has been taken.  Great bread.

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: I didn't add any milk and they were a little thinner than we usually like our mashed potatoes.  But the flavor made up for it!  We used light sour cream and reduced fat cream cheese and it didn't take away from it at all.  I had green onions to use up so I am sure I had close to a cup, next time I will stick with have a cup as it was almost too much. I say almost because no one else mentioned it as they gobbled up second (or third!!) helpings!

name: 24k carrots
review: I made these for DH, as is the only one who likes cooked carrots in our house. He gave them 3 stars. He said they were "okay" and "not bad, but not his favorite." Lots of leftovers.

name: chili s salsa
review: So easy!  My family loves this!  I add a handful of fresh cilantro.  I added extra salt, which was a mistake, as the chips are salty.  Don't be tempted to add extra salt!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: While I did not have any of this, I did make it for my family, who all rated it between 4 and 5 stars.  They really enjoyed it. My only complaint is the messy clean up.  Next time I may try the crock pot method that another reviewer posted and see if my family likes it that way as well.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Great sauce recipe! I slow cooked my pork and served with white rice and broccoli.

name: angel food cake   homemade
review: My 2nd time making angel food cake and this one came out beautifully. Perhaps a tad too sweet though, as I served it with a vanilla glaze and fresh strawberries. This recipe is definitely a keeper!

name: banana banana bread
review: It's a pretty good darn sign when a recipe receives 860 ratings, and most are positive, that this is a keeper.  This one is no exception.  I had to "bake" the bananas I had, because they were not ripe enough.  This made them squishy and perfect.  I could not wait for the recipe to cool, and I don't think I gave it enough time, but the first slice was heaven!!!  I put it back in the oven for an extra 10 min. (inside was "oozy") and that was perfect.  This was dinner last nite, and breakfast this morning.  An absolutely keeper.

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: UPDATE:  I make this ALL the time!!  Add extra jalepeno and pablano reguarly and use low fat cheese and skim milk.  Add cilantro right at the end.  Just awesome.  We love this soup!   Wow - enjoyed this very much.  Changes I made include adding 2 mostly seeded jalepenos to the vegetable mix.  I also added 1C white wine to the broth.  I like my soup thick so I added about 15 tortillas (had extra liquid) and used my immersion blender to mix it all up.  MOST EXCELLENT SOUP!

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: I have never had RL biscuits before so I can't compare them, but I can say they were delicious!  Like others, I freeze the butter. I also grate it into the flour mix on the largest grate hole possible.  I can't remember where I learned that trick, but it works well!  Thanks for posting Heather!

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review:
This is a really great recipe, the only reason I give it 4 stars instead of 5 is that it was a big glob of dough in the middle... it needs to be checked every 5 minutes at the end with a knife or a toothpick.

I'm happy to have discovered Soda Bread... it's my first time both making it and eating it.  It reminds me of cake without so many sugar calories!  Cant wait to make it again, and it works great in a springform pan.  Thanks!

name: chicken pesto
review: Made the http://www.food.com/recipe/speedy-spinach-pesto-176624 recipe from this site (which is excellent, btw) and used it in this dish. I left out the breadcrumbs completely (low carb) and followed the recipe with the addition  of purchased fresh 3 cheese ravioli, a little wine, chicken stock and placed in the same skillet in the oven, covered for about an hour. I was delicious and one pan clean up made it that much better!

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: Delicious but quite a bit too salty for me.  Will try with DIY soup mixes.

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: I suggest doubling sauce ingredients and serving the pan juices over brown rice with an Asian veggie medley.  My family of five rated this a five star meal.

name: quick yellow cake
review: My son needed to make a cake for a school project.  This turned out perfectly despite some errors in the order in which we added the ingredients.  It turned out fluffy and delicious.

name: real southern cornbread
review: I liked that this was made in a cast iron skillet, but it had absolutely no flavor.  It was light, fluffy, and moist, but utterly flavorless. I would do the same method of cooking in a cast iron skillet, but I would use a more flavorful recipe.  I did follow the recipe exactly; my kids and husband didn't go back for seconds which is unheard of with cornbread in our house.  One of my children didn't even finish his first serving.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Yum. Everything I was looking for in a pot pie. I did add some peas and would have added corn if I had had some. Bellywarming for sure

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: Come on over, I've got a chicken just coming out of the crockpot. I'm just itching to have someone over for dinner. We can party? Yes??

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: This was so easy and quick.  It turned out almost identical to my grandma's fried potatoes, which is a big bonus in my book.  Nothing seems to be made the same way that my grandmother's generation and generations before that used to make things.  Sometimes, even though it isn't necessarily the most healthy way to cook, you just need some good old comfort food.  This hit the ticket on a day when I wasn't feeling great and just wanted some good ole home cooking.  I made this with Southern Fried Chicken and Asparagus for a great country dinner that my whole family really loved.  Thank you Uncle Bill!

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: Delicious! I made a half recipe but made as is. Hoping my kids would like it. One did, one didn't but I enjoyed it!

name: m   m dream bars
review: These are soooo good!  I didn't change a thing and they were fantastic!  Gooey and rich and yummy.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Thank you for sharing this fantastic and easy recipe!  I have used it on chicken also with good results

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Wow, this was amazing soup!  With the ww title I was skeptical on how good it could be, but this one is going in my keeper file.  Thank you for sharing!

name: beef barley soup
review: Thank you for sharing this excellent and easy recipe.  I used venison and it turned out amazing!  I did not use the bouillon cubes and I think it was fine without it. This freezes well too FYI.

name: skylike chili   skyline chili copycat
review: This was delicious. We don't get Skyline here in the UK, so I was just looking forward to a really great chili! I've heard so much about putting chocolate in chili and I've been meaning to try it for ages, I hadn't got round to it until I made this, but now I have I'm converted! It gives a real depth of flavour and richness! I used very lean ground beef, so there was no need to skim the fat, but I still couldn't stop tasting bits as it cooked! We served ours with rice and it went down a treat. Will definitely be making this again!

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: Only ok for us. Maybe it's because we used chicken thighs? The flavor never got into the meat.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: These are well named!  Thank you for sharing this recipe--they double well too!

name: kittencal s best deviled eggs
review: These were great!  I did accidentally double the seasonings for the filling (for some reason, I thought the recipe was for 6 eggs...) and I don't think they suffered for it at all--I might even double the seasonings on purpose next time.  Thank you, Kitten!

name: kittencal s perfect prime rib roast beef
review: The beef was very good, but I didn't care for the jus.

name: healthy honey oatmeal cookies
review: I don't want to be a downer with all the rave reviews but I followed the directions exactly, adding pecans to mine. Although the taste wasn't bad, my dough was wet and sticky, and the cookies were so flat that I could hardly get them off the cookie sheet (I did spray the pan generously with cookie spray). After reading some of the reviews, I saw that some others added more flour or oats or used some other variations that they preferred. Maybe someday I will experiment with this recipe.

name: basic batter waffles
review: Excellent, fast and easy! Easily halved, which made 3 large waffles. Thank you!

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: Excellent!  Made just as directed, however we only marinaded for three hours.  We also grilled on a lower heat, which resulted in nice moist chicken, and an excellent glaze on the outside.  Will definitely make again often!

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: Cut the oil back to 2/3 cup ...let onion sit for 2 hours in oil and spices ...sprinkled salt on the tomatoes to let them drain ...did not use the romaine lettuce or green pepper (just a preference).  My family enjoyed this recipe

name: frizzled cabbage
review: Cabbage helps rhythms of the body. ;-) Ok, now let's get back to the spirit of cooking.  What's wrong with ya'll?

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: OK - stop reading reviews and MAKE THIS.  Seriously 20 stars!!!!  The first time I made this - I doubled everything - for 1.5 lbs boneless skinless chicken thighs.  Hubby grilled them outside.  AMAZING.  My new favorite - with rice and veg on the side.  (note - I used serrano - for the chile and it has a bit of a kick!)  Also used thai basil - instead of italian basil.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: I made up 3 chicken breast ...used my own BBQ sauce and found that the chicken got way to watery and diluted the sauce.  I ended up shredding the chicken and served to DH for lunches!   This is OK, but not worth the 5 star rating

name: grilled cauliflower
review: Simple and delicious!  I made your original recipe and it was fantastic.  I made it a second time and changed it.  I used some bacon fat (not something I often do) instead of butter and I used Simply Organic Citrus A Peel seasoning (I love this stuff on grilled veggies or grilled chicken).  Again fantastic.  Glad you won for this.

name: pork chops yum yum
review:
My rating is for the sauce.  Next time I make it I will follow other reviewers suggestion to simmer it right in the pan for a shorter period of time.  I baked it as instructions state, but only 50 minutes instead of one hour, and it was still overdone by a few minutes.  I may also try what others have suggested to brine it in water and salt... I'll experiment to make it more tender.

The sauce is absolutely delicious, and although some reviewers say to make more, the amount in the recipe was just about right for my family... maybe I would  1 1/2 times it or double it (since it's always better to have too much than not enough).

Thank you for a great recipe!

name: basic pancake mix
review:
I added about two tablespoons of ground flax seed, and used 1 cup whole wheat flour and 1/4 cup white. I also added a couple of handfulls of chocolate chips into the batter. Was the perfect consistancy. Delicious. Just perfect. A standard, good, dependable pancake. Thank you! I'd been trying all of these fancy recipes for pancakes, when the one I wanted was so "basic". :)

Edited to add, made as directed using olive oil and vanilla. Very fluffy. Batter burns easily, so keep an eye out.

name: chicken pot pie with 2 crusts
review: Very good and very easy to make.  I added celery with the onion, decreased the milk to 1/2, increased the broth to one can, and used canned carrot and potato instead of frozen veges.  I also used 3 cups of chicken.

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: When all is said and done, these are fantastic! But I had to remove a star because of the confusing instructions. When you mix all of the ingredients together, it does NOT make a "semi-dry paste." It is a sauce. So I just ignored that little bit and baked the ribs in the sauce. I actually only made half a recipe of sauce. I baked covered at 375, then uncovered and baked another 30 minutes, turning over and basting occasionally. This thickened up the sauce nicely and browned the ribs. We had very sticky fingers and faces when we were done eating, but it was worth it!

name: skylike chili   skyline chili copycat
review: I was a bit skeptical of this recipe, but I liked that it didn't have beans. Turns out we loved it! The blend of cocoa and spices is perfect. I served it on gluten-free spaghetti with shredded cheddar and green onions piled on top. I plan on making this one again!

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: I don't normally like artichokes, but decided to give this a try and I'm so glad I did, it was DELICIOUS!! Slightly tart, yet lovely and tender with a flavour explosion going on in my mouth! I served it with Bulgur Wheat and it disappeared in minutes!

name: the best belgian waffles
review: Wow, 5 stars all the way Marie.  These wonderful little treats were indeed  super crisp on the outside and light as a feather inside and so scrumptious! They were so quick and easy to make.  Great flavor and excellent texture. I enjoyed them very much.  Garnished mine with a little icing  sugar for a delicious meal.  Made for What's on the Menu? Tag Game 2015.

name: perfect rump roast
review: This is a great recipe. I sliced it with an electric slicer and I had the best roast beef sandwich meat ever! I have also made this as a dinner roast also. Thanks for a great recipe.

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: This is EXACTLY what I've been craving!  Most pork tenderloin recipes have sweet spices and sugar added...This was savory and soooo easy and delicious!  Thanks for posting what is now my go to recipe for Pork Roast!

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: These are amazing!  Even better,  DH can have potato chips despite having to watch his cholesterol.  I like them with salt,  pepper,  and smoked paprika.  They're also great with coarse salt and a touch of malt vinegar.  Thanks!

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: This was the moistest pork recipe I have ever cooked.  It was delicious and I will definitely make again.  The sauce did not thicken much and remained runny like broth.  I would have preferred a thicker or more gravy-type texture to the sauce.

name: soft peanut butter cookies
review: This is my go-to peanut butter cookie recipe.  It is easily halved and produces perfectly moist and chewy cookies.  I used soy nut butter due to an allergy and no one suspected the difference.

name: fusion avocado
review: So simple and soooo delicious!

name: honey roasted pork loin
review: So simple to make, had all the ingredients on hand.  The family LOVED this, that is quite a compliment.....the glaze over the pork was perfect, not to sweet.  Thank you for posting.

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: I wouldn't say that the tortilla was crunchy but no matter...I thought this recipe had great flavor and I will definitely be making it again. I used a spinach tortilla, feta, cherry tomatoes and parmesan on top. I also used garlic powder but the thought of roasted garlic sounds delicious!Thanks for posting!!

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: Num, num, num, num, did I say num yet? We followed the recipe exactly (except we had to heat ours longer) and it was as close as I can imagine to the real thing at Cracker Barrel! Amazing! Thank you very much for the great recipe!

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: Pretty good way to cook cauliflower and easy too.  I was the only one who ate it (no surprise there, though).  Was hoping the toddler would it eat, but maybe next time!  Thanks for posting.  I will make it again! 4/25: Yay! This time he said "Yummy!" and "Thank you for more cauliflower, mommy." Woohoo!

name: best banana bread
review: Wonderful banana bread recipe. I used 1/2 a cup of sugar and 1/2 a cup of Splenda with excellent results. Next time I will try all Splenda in place of the sugar. Also, I addes 1/2 tsp. cinnamon to the recipe.

name: mama iuliucci s famous meat a balls  italian meatballs
review: Excellent meatballs for a party!  I made these as directed, they held together perfectly.  I used a cookie scoop to shape them and I put them on cookie sheets to bake.  I did not make my own sauce this time as I was crunched for time but I would like to try that.

name: best banana bread
review: I just wanted a quick and easy banana recipe and this one was perfect! I threw it together in no time and it turned out delicious. I added largely chopped pecans. Will be a favorite from now on. Thanks for posting.

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: We really enjoyed these bell peppers. I precooked the rice and while the mixture simmered, I simply added about a 1/2 cup of water to keep it moist. It all worked out perfectly. My husband isn't a fan of cheese, so sometimes cooking gets a bit creative in our home. In this case, I filled his peppers before adding the cheese to the rest of the filling and everybody was happy.

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: Ditto to all the comments!  Used crumbs from the end of a homemade potato bread and forgo the butter as it was not needed!  Delicious!

name: ground beef gyros
review:
I love the challenge of a new recipe...staying busy, plotting and planning.
It makes me forget that I'm growing older.  Speaking of older, where was I...ohhh the gyro...this one's a real keeper!

name: angel food cake   homemade
review: Great cake--thanks!

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: This was a great recipe and the first time I made chicken pot pie.  I added in thyme and rosemary as another reviewer suggested as well as a 1/4 cup extra liquid (next time I'll add more extra liquid).  I also added peas.  Very yummy and versatile... you could customize your own veggie mix based on what you like... I'm thinking broccoli and mushrooms would be great too.  Thanks!

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: So simple to make and tasted wonderful. Hubby LOVED it. Thank you

name: creamed ground beef sos
review: Delicious. My picky children ate all of it.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: Oh my gosh was this delicious. I made this with legs and can't wait until I make it with wings. It was delicious. I had some sauce left in the pan. I saved it and put it on pork chops the next day. Yummy!! Thanks for such a wonderful recipe. I will make this often.

name: southwestern stuffed bell peppers
review: Awesome! I doubled the tomatoes and I covered it with tin foil while baking so that the steam could help soften the peppers.

name: basic pancake mix
review: This is a great pancake that we enjoyed for breakfast.  It made more than enough so I froze the leftovers.  Thank you!

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: Outstanding! We used Famous Dave's Sweet & Zesty BBQ Sauce and followed the recipe exactly. The sandwiches were pleasing to the eye, tender, and very flavorful and we'll definitely be revisiting this one again soon. Thank you very much!

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: DH made this and gave it 3 stars.  He said it was good, but didn't have a whole lot of flavor to it.

name: rhubarb crisp
review: It was really the best like I used to make. I did add double the rhubarb cause that's what I had, cut down to 3/4 c white sugar, 1/2c brown sugar and 1/3 c melted butter. I don't like it too sweet.  Served with vanilla ice cream. This is a keeper; thanks.

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: great

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: They were great. My husband used whole wheat flour and flax seed meal for the white flour. He also only used 1/3 cup of both the brown and white sugar and they were plenty sweet enough. The kids scarfed these up, yummy.

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: These were good but I would like to fiddle with the recipe to get them just how we like them. I soaked the cranberries in hot water before using. I will cut the sugar next time because they were a little too sweet. They also spread out very thin so I will add more flour too.

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: Great! Made as is, except only had 2 bananas. Delicious!!

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: Why have I tried all the other recipes for Shepherds Pie???  Made as written and it's such a sinfully simple and wonderfully tasty dish!  Thank you for posting!  I wouldn't change a thing and will make this again and again!

name: chicken legs grilled
review: Loved it...used Splenda in place of sugar.  DH preferred the chicken made with chucks chicken juice 38399 (only reason gave it 4 stars over 5), but I would definitely make this again.  Thanks!

name: homemade pie crust
review: Used this for a ham, ricotta zucchini tart.

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: This is yummy grilling goodness at its best. I am adding this to my low carb arsenal.  We used chicken, but can't wait to try it with lamb as well.  And, as stated...yes, it is awesome cold on salads!

name: pork chops in onion sauce  schweinekotelett in zwiebelsosse
review: Easy. Pork chops came out tender and flavorful!

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: We got some red potatoes in our farm box. I didn't have any fresh garlic, so I added some Trader Joe's crushed garlic to the potatoes after I drained them.  I also used buttermilk instead of milk.  Everyone in my family liked them and gave them between 4 and 5 stars, a true complement from my sometimes picky eaters!

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: Awesome and easy to make.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: When trying this frosting right out of the bowl, we weren't crazy about the flavor. But when we tried it on some scraps I had trimmed off the cake, we all liked it.  I had to make it twice to have enough for a 2 layer 9inch round cake.  Which worked out well, because the first time the texture was way too soft. So the second time as I was mixing I left out the cream. Instead I alternated between adding powdered sugar and the soft frosting of my original batch.  Still not the perfect texture for piping, but useable. Lucky for me it was for my own family and not someone else, so it was fine.

name: spiced pumpkin waffles
review: Tasted great, but a little wet which meant we had really soft, wet waffles. I don't like dry waffles, but I do think these were a little too wet. Next time I will reduce the milk, but the pumpkin/spice ratio is just right!

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: Very good. I crushed up hard shell tortillas for the bottom.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Very tasty pancakes. Thanks for the recipe!

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: This is a very very good chicken salad recipe. I used light mayo, green seedless grapes and walnuts for this recipe, finished with a dash of black pepper and paprika. Great for summer.

name: moist chocolate cupcakes  super easy  budget
review: Excellent and moist cupcakes.  Really quick to whip together and they look delicious.  They only made 18 cupcakes for me.  I would make these again!

name: easy lemon pound cake
review: We enjoyed this last night. I added the zest of one lemon and was glad that I did because the lemon is very subtle. My cake didn't rise... Although I made as instructed.  It still tasted good. Next time I'll be more careful when putting it together

name: queso blanco dip
review: This was so yummy! We found the Land O'Lakes white American at Giant Eagle, but as others have mentioned, any good-quality white American cheese would do. Next time, though, I think I'll use half and half cream or whole milk in lieu of the heavy cream, as it was very RICH! I added a few dashes of salt, and may add a little diced jalapeno for kick next time, too. We used it on loaded nachos which consisted of Tostitos Cantina Style tortilla chips, Southwest-seasoned ground beef (compliments of McCormick), this wonderful queso, and Southwest Guacamole. ("Viva Mexico Guacamole" recipe with fire-roasted corn--also from Giant Eagle--in the frozen section, and black beans added to it.) They were delicious . . . better than any restaurant's nachos, and thoroughly enjoyed in the privacy of our patio alongside less-pricey beers! ;-) This queso would surely be awesome as just a dip, but is certainly versatile enough to also be used on tacos, burritos, French fries, grilled chicken or steak, burgers, etc. Thank you so much for sharing this recipe! :-)

name: bakery style chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: We bake a lot in our house. Therefore, we have tried a lot of different cookie recipes.  Everyone agreed that this one is a favorite.  We did chill the dough. We also used a combination of chips to use up things in the pantry. This batch had mini M&M's, white chocolate, and chocolate chips.

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: Excellent!  Made just as directed and toasted the buns.  Will definitely make again!

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review:
Excellent. I subbed 1 c. wheat flour for 1 c. of the APF and no one noticed! This will be my go to crust recipe from now on. Nice thin crust pizza; quick & easy to put together. Thanks for sharing!
***Update*** I made this dough to take with us camping and we loved it. I made the dough at home and placed in a Ziploc bag (double batch; froze one and chilled the other). Brought pepperoni, shredded pizza cheese & purchased pizza sauce. Placed a pizza stone on the grill until hot (lid closed), rolled out dough, placed on stone & topped as you normally would, closed lid and waited for perfection. We had this 2 nights for dinner (out of the 3 nights we stayed). Will definitely make this again and again. I also want to try making it into cinnamon buns or some kind of yummy breakfast pastry. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: My family wasn't crazy about all the water left in the pot.  I tried draining some of it off.  Next time I may cook the potatoes in the water first until almost done. Drain the water off.  Then brown everything up in the oil.

name: chewy double chocolate chip cookies
review: Perfect recipe! I used spelt flour, turned out just right.

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: Enjoyed by the family, easy, and  nice flavour.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: I don't eat a lot of fish, but this was pretty good. I did not use tilapia, as we can't really get that here (or it may be called something else) but I just used a mild, white fish from the fish shop.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: This turned out very well. Lovely flavour, not too difficult and DH enjoyed it. I like the suggestion of putting the meat in the freezer for 15 minutes to make it easier to slice thinly.

name: homemade hamburger buns  bread machine
review: Excellent recipe for buns. Only change in recipe was to use 2 1/4 tsp. rapid rise yeast (one packet) in stead of the 1 1/4 tsp. listed. I also divided the dough into 12 balls when dough was completed- then flattened them slightly and baked them in my non stick hamburger bun pan. Will definately add this recipe to our "faves" for breads and rolls !

name: classic baked ziti
review: This was quite good.  I used penne instead of ziti and made my own sauce.  There is no amount given for the mozzarella.  Near as I can tell, you need 3 cups.

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: Great recipe! I have people who are on a no-carb diet in the house, so I completely omitted the rice, which resulted in less cooking time on the stove. (If you choose to do the same, no need to add water into the filling.) I used more Worcestershire sauce and sprinkled extra cheddar cheese on top of the stuffed peppers prior to baking. That's an easy and great main course right there! Five stars!

name: stove top tamale pie
review: We love this recipe.  Since we are a large family (8 people), I use 2 lb of meat, 2 cans of black or kidney beans, 1 15-oz can of tomato sauce, and 1 cup of water.  I find the 1 c of water is necessary or the meat mixture gets too dry while waiting for the cornbread to cook.  For seasoning, I use Kittencal's Taco Seasoning (76616), but I DO NOT double the seasoning as I did everything else.  Trust me.  For the cornbread, I use Corn Bread (397920).  This is a great one pot meal.

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: I have used this twice now in taco soup and it is great.  I made the soup for a friend and she told me it was better than hers and that I must do something different.  I told her I made my own seasoning mix and didn't use a packet.  I also made tacos with this, too, and they were delicious but a little too salty.  Next time I plan to cut the seasoning salt down to 1/2 tsp.  I have now started using smoked paprika in this mix and it adds a delicious flavor.  I also add a pinch of ground chipotle pepper instead of cayenne pepper.

name: jambalaya for the crock pot
review: This recipe is delicious and so easy to make! We don't like spicy that much, so I skipped the tabasco and only added about 1/8 teaspoon cayenne. Perfect amount of spicy for us!

name: kielbasa with tomatoes and white beans
review: The flavoring of this dish was too much like spagetti sauce for my taste.  There was very little sauce, and it was super thin.  It was easy to make, but I just didn't think it made the most of the kielbasa or those wonderful beans.  Sorry to be going against the grain on this one.  It's just one opinion of many.

name: balsamic chicken thighs
review: Really easy and delicious! I love the fact that this recipe only calls for very few ingredients but the result is amazing! Will definitely make it again!

name: simple caribbean jerk chicken
review: The sauce was so so good, but when I grilled the chicken drumsticks according to this recipe, most of the sauce was left on the grill. Next time, I'll try to cut up a few lines on the chicken for the flavor to get into the chicken a bit more. Overall, the recipe is great! Thanks for posting!

name: microwave poached eggs
review: My first egg turned out over done at 50 seconds, I like a really runny yolk.  40-45 seconds is just about perfect for me.  Served it over an English muffin, melted mozzarella cheese a slice of tomato then topped with some home made pesto...yummy!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: Fabulous!  Added red bell pepper, onion, and fresh chopped garlic while sauteing chicken.  Used one cup cream and thickened with about one T flour.  This is on the regular rotation.  Thanks, Lorac!

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: This was the first time I made Salisbury steak and it was AWESOME!!! I served it with sweet peas and hash brown casserole. My family loved it! Thanks so much for the recipe. I will certainly make it again.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: I used 3/4 lb skirt steak to make this recipe. Added more cumin after the fajita fillings were done. Served it with a homemade green salsa, shredded cheddar cheese and sour cream. Very good! Thanks for the recipe!

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: Amazing, amazing, amazing!!! I let the dough chill in the fridge overnight and brought it to room temperature before handling it. It was a bit sticky, but with more flour, it worked fine for me. I mainly used a gingerbread-man shape cookie cutter. These little men totally made my day! They were delicious! Would totally make them again. Thanks so much for the recipe!

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: This was absolutely delicious!!! So good It's something I won't make often or I'll eat all of it. Everyone in my family loved it. Followed directions and a few tips as far as greasing and flouring my pan and folding the flower in by hand, not with a mixer.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: What else can be said about this recipe??  Every bite was tender and delicious!

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: Oh wow this was amazing! My new favourite gravy and so easy to make! I honestly wanted to just eat it out of the pan with a spoon, so good!!

name: easy crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: I didn't really care for the texture. It was pretty gummy. I used some minced onion that I sauteed a little before adding the other ingredients. I also upped the cheese b/c I didn't think that 1 cup would be enough. Thought I would give it a try, but probably won't make again. Didn't leave stars since I made some changes.

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Easy and tasty! I think I am going to go back to this recipe every time I need spaghetti sauce. It was so much better than a regular bottled one from a store. I served this sauce with some homemade gnocchi. It was amazing! Thanks for the wonderful recipe!

name: minado s perfect sushi rice
review: Perfect sushi rice. Seems like not enough water for cooking, but it absorbs the vinegar mixture and is perfect.

name: easy stir fry sauce
review: This is a good base - agree with others --much less sugar - maybe 1-2 TBL max.  Then you have to add some heat.  Pepper flakes or hot garlic sauce.  Will try again and see what else I add to it..  Did save and will be adjusting and updating my notes.  Thanks!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: The people at church liked these, but it did seem as though two cups of blueberries would have been enough.  I got 19 muffins from this.

name: tiramisu
review: Ok, I've made tiramisu many times before, and everyone raves about it, but I was looking for a recipe that had a lighter cream layer (for anyone interested, my benchmark best ever tiramisu is at the Cafe Vitorio in the North End in Boston).  So, I decided to try this recipe.  I doubled it because I was bringing it to a pot luck and because I bought the large tub of marscapone.  I also didn't know what caster sugar was, but going on one of the reviews, I used powdered sugar - and it worked fine.  I also only made the 2 cups of coffee, but I used about 1/4 cup.  I can't imagine using so much liquid in the recipe.  I very quickly dipped the lady fingers so that they were barely wet with the coffee.  The recipe came out excellent.  I think tiramisu is all about ingredients (use marscapone, good lady fingers, and good liqueur - I used Kahlua and brandy) AND technique - the whipping of egg whites and folding, and not soaking the lady fingers are key to a good tiramisu.  My original recipe called for some of the coffee/liqueur mixture in the marcapone mixture - I'm not sure if this recipe needs it or not, but it wouldn't hurt either.  I will definitely make this again - it will be my new standard.

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: These tasted good, but they didn't rise as much as I thought they would.  Also, they browned quickly, but I had to leave them in the oven because they weren't done.  So they were a bit tough on top.  Still, I would make them again.  I'm not sure what happened this time.

name: wonderful salsa
review: I intended on canning this and made this before going to the store for both the tomato sauce and paste (and cilantro which I always love in salsa). We however, loved this so much that there wasn't enough left to even bother jarring. I used lime juice instead of vinegar (personal preference). This was so fresh and delicious, I will make it again as instructed (reducing the sugar by half) and then one more time; making half with mango and half a little hotter. Great way to use up the jalapenos, onions, and tomatoes in the garden. This is such a flavorful and excellent recipe. Thanks for sharing!

name: the best ever waffles
review: I followed this recipe exactly and, while the waffles were good, they weren't fluffy at all. I thought that maybe it was something I had done wrong until I read how many other reviewers had the same problem. I will say the taste was really good--I did add vanilla and cinnamon. My daughters thought these waffles tasted like regular pancakes. The measurements in this recipe seem off--it calls for a lot of baking powder, a lot of butter, and the flour-to-milk ratio also seems off, resulting in a very thin batter.  In any event, these flat waffles tasted good with the addition of vanilla and cinnamon, and they were gobbled up in our home. Thank you for posting.

name: basic batter waffles
review: This is a great and versatile recipe. You can easily add blueberries, chocolate chips, cinnamon, etc. I doubled the recipe because cleaning the waffle iron is such a chore, and then I added a tablespoon of cinnamon and three teaspoons of vanilla. That yielded 14 fluffy waffles and I think the added cinnamon and extra vanilla gave the waffles an added flavor that we would have missed if omitted. To make the waffles extra fluffy, I poured the batter into the waffle iron and left the lid up for a minute so the bottom portion of the waffle could rise. I then closed the lid and let the entire waffle cook through. My family and I ate five of the waffles for breakfast and I froze the rest. I will be thawing the waffles and popping them into the toaster oven when the kids, my hubby, or I want waffles for breakfast!

name: uncle bill s method for cooking turkey
review: This is as good a turkey recipe as any! I loved seeing the skin "shrink-wrap" when I poured the boiling water on top. The meat came out moist and flavorful.

name: brown sugar bundt cake
review: This cake is AMAZING! It's moist, perfectly sweet, and beautiful looking. Just wonderful! I didn't add the chopped nuts (I used walnuts) into the cake batter. Instead, I made an easy caramel sauce and poured over the cake, then sprinkled chopped nuts on top. My family loved it! Thank you for the great recipe! Definitely a keeper!

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Loved this dageret, I followed the direction exactly (except for Zucchini as I had none) and it was great for lunch, then I decided to try it for a base for dinner and added a potatoe with some left over port - still healthy and low in fat and it was great.  Served it with my sage rolls and it made for a hearty, warm and satisfying dinner.  I can imagine a lot of things could be added, but I like it just as written for when those HUNGRIES strike.  Update: August, 2015.  Continue to use this just as written, though I do double it then freeze in batches to handle those times when hunger strikes or just a a lovely fall dinner with a slice of home made bread and a class of red wine - Yum and not bad on the calorie side

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Great base for Mac and cheese!  IMO, you need a stronger flavor of cheese or add more spices; it was bland for me.  I would made this again but kick up the spices.  The recipe was doubled with no changes.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: Absolutely perfect, as is. Did not need to add or change a thing. I did have a rind from a chunk of Parmesan that was begging to be used... So I threw it in. The added flavor was ridiculously delicious. Amazingly perfect, simple and fresh tasting recipe. LOVE it.

name: chunky blue cheese salad dressing
review: DH said it best. This may be the best blue cheese dressing I've ever tasted! I used light mayo and light sour cream. Thanks for sharing!

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: Good recipe. You can't go wrong with Kittencal's recipes. She's been a part of our kitchen for some time now, even though I don't know her. :-)  I made this recipe exactly as directed, with 1/2 tsp. of white salt. However, I found it needed a little extra salt--1/4 tsp. extra--for our taste. I also added a 28 oz. of tomato sauce to the meat. The taco seasoning was beautiful. Keep in mind that if the seasoning comes out too spicy for your taste, you can balance out the heat with some added sugar. Thank you for posting.

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review:
I rarely cook salmon well. I don't know what it is about this type of fish that eludes me, but I've learned to steer clear of salmon because, although I love it, I botch salmon recipes time and again. The fish market had a sale on wild-caught salmon, so I picked up a fillet. I don't like baking salmon because of the way it makes the house smell, so I looked up a grilled salmon recipe on good ol' Food.com/ex-Recipezaar.com and found this recipe. It was so, so simple to grill this salmon this way and make it taste delicious. I started by patting the salmon dry with paper towels. I don't know if this removes some of the "fishiness" that cooked salmon tends to end up with, but it has made salmon less fishy-tasting for us in the past. I coated the fillet with olive oil on either side, added salt and pepper to taste, and then grilled for 6 minutes per side over medium-high heat for an average-sized salmon fillet. That's all I did and the salmon tasted great before I even added this wonderful sauce. 

The sauce is involved, with many ingredients, but utterly worth it. This sauce made the salmon taste even better. I will say that I used orange juice instead of pineapple, a dash of red pepper flakes instead of the cayenne, and I used half the amount of sugar listed in the recipe. The sauce was sweet enough and would've been too sweet if I had used the full amount of sugar, and too spicy had I used the cayenne pepper. I made double the amount of sauce and have frozen it in batches to use on future fish or chicken dishes. Thanks for making me less scared of cooking salmon! Be well.
