name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: DELICIOUS! I'm always after the perfect fluffy pancake recipe and this is definitely it! My fiancé and I polished these off for brunch very quickly!

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: This is a great way of cooking brussels sprouts. It's delicious! I usually roast them in the oven after a quick sear on the cut side in the pan with butter and olive oil, but leaving them in the pan to cook slowly definitely worked just fine! I had 1 lb brussels sprouts, so I decided to cook them all. As a result, I increased olive oil and butter to 2 tablespoons. I also used minced garlic and left it in the pan for the whole time. Sprinkled freshly ground pepper and salt when the brussels sprouts were cooking. I did have to cook them a little longer than the recipe states, but they came out great! Parmesan cheese was definitely an essential touch for this recipe! Thanks for posting! I will make this again.

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review:
**This is a revised review as I now must revise all recipes to be gluten free as I've been diagnosed with Celiac disease a few years back. 
The GOOD thing is that it is super simple to modify this recipe to eliminate the dreaded gluten. I used Scha brand GF bread crumbs- but I also love Aleia's and Ian's- each of which provide a super crispy, yummy crust. 
I also prefer to buy thin cut, bone-in pork chops to eliminate the oven step and simply pan fry them. It's an easy meal that tastes out of this world with a simple green salad. We also like to serve zucchini muffins or cauliflower biscuits with these delectable chops. SUCH a great recipe! (The sage and parm combo is really out of this world!)

name: baked ziti
review: Ok, so I wasn't impressed by this but my family really enjoyed it.  So they beat me out for a 4 star rating.  I guess I am just used to my mom's recipe for baked ziti.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: My son wanted chocolate cake for his fifth birthday and this is the one I chose to make.  It was easy to make into cupcakes and tasted great. Thank you!

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: Wonderful!!!!  I brought this to my dance and everyone loved it.  I received so many complements.  I made some with chocolate chips and someone with out.  Either way the cookies received great reviews.  I followed the directions as written and found them easy to make. Thanks so much for sharing.

name: poverty meal
review: Great recipe and base for similar meals. I tweaked and made this for one of our Meatless Friday dinners. In place of the ground beef, I used 16 oz. of mushrooms (8 oz. of bella mushrooms and 8 oz. of white mushrooms). I also added a diced green pepper. Since mushrooms cook down and release so much water, I added a 12 oz. cup of water to the dish instead of the recommended 16 oz. Based on several of the prior reviews, I also added oregano to the dish, and was liberal with the black pepper, since the recipe as provided would have been a bit bland for our taste. My last change was to use a 14.5 oz. can of diced tomatoes and a 14.5 oz can of tomato sauce in place of the two 16 oz. cans of stewed tomatoes. We loved this dish as tweaked and will be having left-overs tomorrow. Thanks!

name: cream cheese cinnamon crescents
review: I have made something like this before, but without the topping.  I made this for a holiday party and it was gone in a flash.  So easy and delicious.

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review:
We really, really enjoyed this.  I've taken it to a cookout, where it was also raved about and I was asked for the recipe a few times.

I don't do Miracle Whip, that was my only change.  Just Hellmans, instead.

name: romano s macaroni grill rosemary bread
review: 263 reviews!!  You review hogger, you!  Well deserved.

name: joe s crab shack crab dip
review: This was delicious! Instead of green pepper, I used two pepperoncini peppers. I also substitute onion with 1 tsp onion powder.  Very easy and taste great!

name: redneck casserole
review: Easy and delicious! My son helped make it and eat it. :)

name: awesome slow cooker pot roast
review: Very nice! The whole family loved it! Cooked for 4 hours on high, plus 30 minutes on low and the result was tender and delicious. Per reviews, we tried it with golden mushroom soup (yum, just cut down a bit on the water) and added diced potatoes, carrots, celery, and onions. Great flavor!

name: mexican casserole   6 5 weight watcher points
review: We love this recipe. It freezes well. I have also made it leaving the tortillas off the top. Thanks for sharing.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: Not giving it a star rating since I didn't follow the recipe exactly, but this really wasn't that good to us. We aren't really casserole people, so I'm not surprised, but I was hopeful after all the positive reviews. I subbed cheddar for the velveeta, and put green onions on top to add some color and flavor. Just meh to us.

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: Made this exactly as the recipe says. It was super yummy. I served it with corn chips in the afternoon. During dinner, my DH ate it with some pan-fried fish. It was surprisingly good with seafood. Thanks for the recipe!

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: So good! I made this mashed potatoes the night before. Before serving, I dot it with butter and then microwaved it for 1 minute. It was delicious!

name: uncle bill s whipped shortbread cookies
review: These are pretty awesome!  I left the butter sit out overnight so it would be soft all through.  I whipped the butter in my stand mixer for about five minutes while getting everything else out and cutting the cherries.  I opted for almond extract to compliment the cherries.  My kitchen was warm, about 75 degrees when I started and once the oven was running it got up over 80, but I decided against refrigerating the dough as I wanted to try the recipe as is, so glad I did.  The batter texture was like fluff, it is awesome.  I didn't touch the batter at all until the very last cookie, pretty sure any additional heat would melt the butter in the batter.  I used a tablespoon and got a little carried away with heaping tablespoon size.  So my cookies were huge and some broke when transferring to the cooling rack.  I did not get even 24 cookies.  Totally my fault though.  Next time I would stick with the teaspoon, and make it a heaping teaspoon.  I put a powdered sugar/water drizzle over them inspired by the gorgeous pictures other members have taken.  The cookies do melt in your mouth, no chewing required!  This will be my go to recipe for shortbread cookies from now on.

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: So, so good! I'm really glad we tried this perfect gravy. We did cut back on the butter by about half and it was perfect for us. Thanks so much for posting! Update: made a veggie version using veggie broth added a tiny bit of poultry seasoning and some white pepper. Loved it! Thanks!

name: paula deen crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: I only added one egg do to other reviews and this was very good and I would make again for sure

name: amazing chicken tortilla soup
review: I made this using the wine option and substituting fresh diced tomatoes for the canned.  I was told to add liquid to the tomatoes to make up for the liquid in the canned tomatoes. I had never done that before, and I don't think I will do it again.  The soup was a little thin, and that was probably the cause.  I think without, this recipe would be a close second to our favorite chicken tortilla soup.

name: quick butternut squash soup
review: You certainly don't need more 5-star reviews, but I need to be able to find this recipe again!  So delicious!  My butternut was closer to 1 lb. so I threw a chopped up zucchini in there with it.  Also, I subbed veggie broth for the chicken.  The soup turned out with a smoky-like flavor, almost like there was bacon in it!  I also stirred in a couple of spoonfuls of plain greek yogurt to help with the creaminess.  Thanks for a quick, healthy, delicious recipe!

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: DH had this cooking when I came home, it smelled so good!  It tasted good too.  Thank you!

name: opal s pumpkin pie
review: My first time making Pumpkin Pie and it was great! Love the creamy texture and the spicy/sweet balance was just right. We don't get particularly deep pie shells here, so I had a bit leftover, but it still turned out great. I wish we did get deeper shells, so I could have had more of the yummy filling!!

name: world s best cinnamon raisin bread  not bread machine
review: Yummmmm....great directions and the bread looked beautiful. I would add a bit more salt next time. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: cheese enchilada chowder
review: I substituted fresh diced tomatoes for the canned and I used 2 ten ounce cans of mild green enchilada sauce.  Even with these changes, my picky family really liked this.  Perfect for a cold, dreary, rainy fall day.  I loved that I could throw everything in the crock pot in the morning, and dinner was ready when I came home.  The house smelled terrific too!

name: kittencal s bakery buttercream  frosting icing
review: What a wonderful recipe!  This frosting is easy to make, spreads and decorates easily, and tastes great.  Only change I made was to use butter flavoring in place of the almond.  Thanks for my new favorite buttercream recipe!  Fantastic!

name: flawless sesame chicken  restaurant style
review: Yummy sauce.  Not bad for homemade take-out!

name: treebeard s red beans  and rice
review: This was an easy and good recipe but there's something missing. I will be making this again and, when I do, I will saute the onion, celery, pepper, and sausage together first, and then add to the beans, as one of the other reviewers recommended. My husband and I enjoyed this dish but thought it might have been better if the onion was allowed to caramelize with the rest of the veggies and the sausage. I used Andouille sausage with quite a kick already, so we skipped adding the cayenne. Thanks.

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: Way too easy to taste so good, but it is!  Thanks

name: mashed sweet potatoes
review: Easy and great! I added a sprinkle of cinnamon. Nice to be able to skip the boiling step.

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Made this as directed, except used 1 tsp garlic powder in place of fresh garlic.  Delicious!  I put mine on an Italian loaf and served with Lasagna Soup.  Yum!

name: corned beef in beer  crock pot
review: I made this using baby carrots cut in half and red potatoes.  I forgot how awful cabbage smells when it is cooking. I walked in from work and the smell smacked me in the face.  Luckily, it was a beautiful day so the windows all went up.  My house still stinks the following day. Just not as stongly. Beyond the smell, my family loved the corned beef! I was worried they wouldn't like the potatoes. They sometime don't care for them if they've cooked with something else. But, they liked these and DD even liked the carrots and she's normally not a fan. Unfortunately, no one liked the cabbage.  It's the only thing that kept me from giving this five stars.

name: easy fried rice
review: Great recipe and so simple.  The only thing I did differently was  use coconut aminos instead of soy sauce.  It is suppose to be better for you then soy sauce.  Thank you so much for sharing.

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: I thought this was wonderful!  Cauliflower and cheese has always been one of my favorites and I will make this often!  (Though I will admit to using extra cheese on the top and also using two 12 oz bags of frozen garlic cauliflower in place of fresh.)  Thank you for a classic!

name: old widow walker s ziploc omelettes
review: unique way to serve eggs

name: overnight french toast casserole
review: Yum. I made this for breakfast when my daughter and her family stayed for the weekend. It was a hit with everyone. Easy to make and very good. Thanks for sharing. Made for What's on the Menu tag.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Very good. I definitely will use the low sodium soy sauce next time. I took the suggestions of other reviewers and made the sauce first, added a pinch of red pepper flakes, and marinated the steak pieces in the sauce for an hour. I then made as directed for the rest of the recipe, adding only an additional 1/2 tablespoon of minced garlic at the end, as the rest of the ingredients simmered. I can't wait to make this again with the low sodium soy sauce. I think we'll enjoy this dish even more.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: I made these to take into work, and they were very popular! I made them with chopped Mars bars. So, so good. Chewy, moist, flavourful and too easy.

name: best oatmeal cookies
review: Flavor was good, left out the nuts due to allergies and doubled the raisins.  The dough was extremely crumbly and dry. Next time I may add another egg in hope this will help bind the dough together better.

name: healthy honey oatmeal cookies
review: We liked these a lot. They taste healthy, but that's not a bad thing to us. Followed the recipe pretty closely but used sucanat (dehydrated cane juice) instead of brown sugar. Love the honey flavor! Also added cranberries and pistachios.

name: crock pot   style loaded baked potato soup
review: Made exactly as written and this was easy and YUMMY!  I used heavy cream because I had it.  I also used an immersion blender to mush up most of the potatoes, though I did leave some chunks.  This is a definite keeper!!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Outstanding mac and cheese.  The sauce was the height of velvet deliciousness, and there was plenty of sauce.    I used lowfat milk, full-fat cheddar and real butter.    I took the perfectionist route and sprinkled in the flour (not having Wondra on hand), and I couldn't believe the texture.   I did have to add a little flour because I lost some to my fingers and countertop while sprinkling.   NEVER have I had a better texture in a cheese sauce.  NOTES FOR SUCCESS:   The flour needs to be added very slowly, stirring all the while.   It will clump if added quickly.   Just resign yourself to the zen of it, and enjoy creating a masterpiece.   The flour mixture needs to be cooked long enough for it to thicken.  If you've never made a roux or white sauce, try to find a video online.   That cooks out the flour taste and is also what thickens the sauce.   The cheese should not be packaged, pre-grated cheese.   The latter is coated with something to keep the strands separate, and it WILL effect the final outcome.   Lastly, if your heat is low enough, the cheese can be added in only two or three batches as long as you're constantly stirring.

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: Fantastic recipe! My husband and so enjoyed the chicken! Unfortunately I only had 2 lbs. of chicken on hand to use in this recipe, and after my husband and I ate the 2 lbs., I wished I'd of had the 3 lbs. of chicken. When I was mixing the ingredients, I used a low sodium soy sauce which I purchased at Festival Foods. The brand was Essential Everyday, and it only had 580 mg of sodium in it. I didn't add any salt, but I did use 2 cloves of garlic (minced). I did lightly grease the baking pan, before adding the chicken and the sauce, and I baked the chicken for 30 minutes, then flipped it over, and continued baking for another 30 minutes. And it was perfectly done and caramelized within the hour. I would bake as per the instructions, but just be sure to turn the chicken over after the first 30 minutes of baking. By the way I wanted to mention, while the chicken was baking away in the oven, my whole house smelled absolutely wonderful, kind'a like Chicken Teriyaki. I will definitely be making this chicken again! Thank you Theresa/Thunderbird for sharing this recipe. It's definitely a keeper!!

name: best albondigas soup
review: Very good, with all the expected flavors.  Love the meatballs with the combo of beef and chorizo - so flavorful.  It does make a lot, but that's not a problem as now we have leftovers for another night.  I made as directed right down to topping with cooked rice.  great soup for the cold evenings

name: alton brown s baked brown rice
review: Seems foolproof!  Worked the first time, perfectly done.  Brown Rice is easy to mess up and get undercooked... I'll definitely di it this way again.  Thanks!

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: These were wonderful, soft, chewy and tender.  Loved the flavor.  I made these for my grandson's dedication.  They were enjoyed by everyone, young and old alike.  Thank you for sharing this quick and easy to make recipe.  Made for What's on the Menu?  Tag Game.

name: grandma s soft sugar cookies
review: These were really easy to make.  the dough was easy to work with.  I rolled them in colored sugar before baking.  But the cookies themselves were bland and I don't think I would make them again.

name: buttery yeast rolls
review: Scrumptious! Thanks!

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: I can't believe that I forgot to rate this. It is one of my favorites! I made a Mexican version using undrained Mexican chili beans in place of the cannelini beans. Instead of saving some back to thicken, I used a can of refried beans pureed with a little of the tomatoes. I sauteed the carrots to soften with the onions and garlic. Added 2 T. chili powder and 1/2 - 1 t. cumin with the veggies before adding the liquid to release some of their oils. I used a Kale Medley mix that I get at Sam's Club, that has spinach, chard and carrots added to it.  I have used low sodium beef broth and I have added diced chicken or turkey that I had leftover from the freezer. I have added a little taco blend cheese right before serving. Delicious!! I keep this one handy at all times!

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: Awesome! I doubled the cumin and increased the chili powder. I'm going to save this recipe and I'll probably never buy canned enchilada sauce again.

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: I made these with beef and mostly followed the recipe. I left out the onions because my husband won't eat them and I added about 5 jalapeños in with the meat and topped the enchiladas with more sliced jalapeños. I also made my own enchilada sauce instead of buying canned sauce

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: I don't have a dutch oven, so I just cooked this dish in a large saucepan by adding 1 cup of water. Let it boil; uncover and simmer for 20 minutes to allow the water evaporate. The result was probably not as good as a dutch oven, but the flavor was excellent.  I used both American cheese and cheddar cheese. There was a bit of liquid left in the bottom of the saucepan, which was very much like a potato chowder. Very yummy!

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: I just realized I haven't rated this yet.  I've made it several times and it has never failed.  I use the carcass to make Kittencal's Best Chicken Stock Broth.  Cook a 5 pound chicken in under 2 hours.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review:
I am reviewing the recipe two ways.  One as written and one with a variation suggested by Doug MC.  Both reviews are for the pulled pork itself and its juices, not the pulled pork with the BBQ sauce since that would be totally subjective based on the type and brand of sauce preferred by each chef and a not good review of the recipe itself.  Also, I made the variation one first as I forgot the ginger ale, but had apples and apple cider vinegar on hand.

"As Is"  - 4 Stars:  Prepared as directed.  It was good and had I made this BEFORE the variation, I would have given it 5 stars as I've never made pulled pork and wouldn't know any different.  The recipe was easy and delicious, but lacked some flavor and didn't WOW me like the variation recipe.  I used Pork Shoulder Butt (that's what the packaging said that I purchased from Kroger).  I couldn't find a 4 pound roast so I bought an 8 pounder and doubled the recipe.  I'm not sure what flavoring the ginger ale gave it, but I couldn't taste it.  I cooked on low for 11 hours and the meat shredded easily, was super tender and juicy.  Like the variation recipe, we also took out the onions after cooking/shredding.  Also, we did not add the BBQ sauce to the meat and simmer in the crockpot.  Instead, I put the shredded pork back in the crockpot with its juices and let it soak it up on Warm.  Adding BBQ sauce to the meat and simmering is just not how my husband eats it in the south.  Plus, if I had eaten it using my husband?s sauce mixed throughout, I would have given it 2 stars.  I don?t like his sauce.  LOL.  Served for Thanksgiving Dinner with mashed potatoes, gravy from the pulled pork juices, and roasted asparagus.  My husband definitely gives this a thumbs up and likes it so this is a keeper.

"Variation" -  5 Stars:  Instead of the ginger ale, I wanted to try Doug?s recommendation of 1 cup apple juice and 1 cup apple cider since I had that on hand ? did not have smoke flavor and did not use it.  Everything else in the  original recipe stayed the same.  I have a juicer so I juiced a Granny Smith apple for fresh apple juice.  I also used Braggs Organic Apple Cider.  I Poured in 1 cup of each.  I put mine in the crockpot when I left for work around 6:30 am with onions on top and on the bottom.  By time I came home at 4:30 pm, the meat was falling off the bone.  I turned it off and pulled the pork with a fork.  It was so tender and juicy.  I couldn?t help myself and ate some without the BBQ Sauce.  It had a nice tang to it?.maybe the vinegar did that, I don?t know or the apples, but it had a different flavor than just the ginger ale recipe.  It was still amazing.  I gave some to my husband, but he didn?t like the onions because ?that?s not how they do it in the south where he?s from?, so I removed the onions and put the meat back in the crockpot and into the juices.  Since he is from the South and usually is served his pulled pork plain with the sauce on the side so he can pour it over the meat on his sandwich, that is exactly how I served it for dinner.   I heated the BBQ Sauce.  He used Famous Dave?s Devils Spit Sauce.  He has always HATED everything I have ever cooked in the crockpot so he wasn?t hopeful that it would be good.  On the contrary, he LOVED IT!!!!  Instead of a traditional Thanksgiving dinner this year, he asked for pulled pork ? MADE IN THE CROCKPOT!  Excellent variation to the original recipe.  Will definitely will be making this again.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: UPDATE:  Added 3/4 C white wine and a couple of tbl of fresh herbs (sage / rosemary / thyme)  Added the herbs after putting in the broth and half and half.  Seems perfect this way.  Original:   I made this last night.  Everyone liked it.  Thanks to the other reviewers got some ideas and added some poultry seasoning, thyme, and rosemary to the chicken and then baked it.  My husband said I should have also added a bit more of the same seasoning to the pot pie mixture.  Will do that next time.  One other reviewer also said a bit more liquid is good - and she used white wine.  I am FOR SURE doing that next time too.  We used homemade crusts - also from this site.  I will for sure make this many times again.  Thanks for posting!  PS -- be extra sure to add extra liquid if you are going to have left overs.  Our left overs had very little sauce and was very thick...

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: I bought bone-in ribs for this recipe and the bones were just detached from the meat after 9 hours of slow cooking. The tenderness and taste were excellent. I did add some mushrooms and peppers according to other reviewers recommendations. We had some sauce left, so I threw some leftover meatballs in the sauce, and it was such a hit! Thanks for this amazing recipe!

name: gumbo
review: Oh my goodness, this was so good! I've never made Gumbo before and now I have no idea why because it's fantastic! I used a mixture of shrimp and sausage and we both loved it! Just delicious! :)

name: traditional tamales  pork
review: Worth the work! You should also make extra sauce for drizzling on before serving.

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: Perfect. Only change I made was to use soft white whole wheat flour, and line the pan with parchment.

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: This was a very good soup. I had never bought, prepared, nor tasted gnocchi.  I ran across a package and decided to go for it using this recipe. I took advice from the reviewers to add the cream last and I had no problem with separation.  I had to use a Mexican cream and thickening was not an issue. And only half the amount was sufficient.  Husband gave the dish 4.5 stars...and it's very rare he likes new dishes.   Thank you for the recipe.

name: the perfect burger
review: I couldn't believe how juicy the burger turned out. But I have to say, don't bother to turn the patties while grilling. I tried to turn one pattie after 8 minutes, but it immediately fell apart. So I left the other three patties untouched until they reached to 160F. The result was amazing! In terms of flavor, I stirred in bbq sauce, oregano, and curry powder. Very very good!

name: soft and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: Wow! This is a really good chocolate chip cookie.  The main thing in my opinion to remember is only cook them for 8 minutes.  Let them cool on the pan.  They turn out perfect.  Thanks for sharing.

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: Excellent!  I was looking for a an oven rib recipe and found this and glad I did cause it was so tasty!  My son loves ribs and I have never cooked or grilled bone in ribs before.  I had about 4 lbs of country style, bone in ribs, about 1 to 1/4 inch thick.  I had, on hand, Pampered Chef Smoky BBQ Rub which included the same rub ingredients mentioned here and I added that generously to each side of ribs.  I wrapped in the foil and refrigerated for about 3 hours. Pulled them out of fridge, sprinkled on some Liquid Smoke and added some sea salt and baked them at 300 degrees for about 2 hours 15 minutes.  Pulled out (very tender and falling off bone) and basted on Baby Ray's BBQ sauce (our fav too) and broiled as directed to get the sauce nicely caramelized.  We used forks, as my ribs were country style and not a rack; but it was tender and flavorful.  My son is not one to go looking for leftovers the next day but did with these ribs and luckily I had a few leftover.  I served this with a cheesy potato casserole and some green beans.  Clean up was a breeze with the foil; the baking sheet was not even soiled.  Will definitely make again for sure; thanks for posting!

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: So easy and yummy! I added some mushrooms and diced jalapenos in the filling. Delicious!

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: I used salted butter and skipped the salt. This was SO perfect! I like really simple cupcakes, so I just added some of the vanilla bean seeds I got for Christmas into the frosting to make it look a little fancier.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: So good, so easy. I used a New York steak since we had a bunch of those. Sliced thinly with my meat slicer while it was frozen. Other than that followed the recipe exactly.

name: rustic italian bread abm
review: Very nice abm recipe. Will try upping salt amount or adding other spices as well next time.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: I live in California :(  No Cracker Barrel's here, however, everytime we travel we route by a Cracker Barrel!  For me, it's this hashbrown casserole!  it's to die for.  Since we don't get to visit a Cracker Barrel all the time, my memory, is that this is sure darn close!  I have made this several times exactly as written and it's wonderful!  Today I just changed it up a bit, just for fun and thought I would share.  I used idahoan dehydrated hash browns from smart and final (3 cups) I had some bacon bits (the good kind from Costco) and added them, no idea how much, just added them, and I omitted the butter (that was hard to do, I add butter to everything) used jack and cheddar mixed (I shred my own....I think it tastes better than pre shredded, thank you food processor) and I swapped out the onion to 1 C of my Hubbys Onion Mixture  our home NEVER is without this in the fridge  Recipe 474468.  Oh and tried out the cream of mushroom soup.  So good!  As written or add stuff, Rhonda, this is a keeper, Thank you!

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Yummy! I'd never heard of or tried this combination of ingredients before, but it's delicious!! Made it exactly as the recipe stated and it turned out great. And the next day the leftovers were delicious for lunch too!

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: What a great soup recipe! I'm always on the lookout for new homemade soups as I love them and find them so comforting. This was just perfect after the excess of Christmas! We both loved it here and will definitely make it again!

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: This is an excellent recipe! I really love the fact that there's no processed food in this recipe. It tasted amazing! Other than adding a pinch of salt in the filling, I followed the recipe exactly! Will certainly make again! Thanks for sharing!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: I thought this was fabulous!  I didn't have any half and half so I used 2% milk and it thickened up nicely, but I did go a tad heavy on the flour to compensate.  Husband raved and raved over it, it's a keeper :)

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: This is now my favorite way to make brussels sprouts!!  They are delicious!!

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: Excellent! I don't even want to know how many calories or how much fat this cake contains. Who cares?! It's delish! I halved the recipe except for the vanilla and baked in a loaf pan tented with foil for the first hour and then uncovered for 40 mins. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: This is only ok. I liked the old fashioned from scratch soup. This can stuff is just not the same

name: perfect basic white rice
review: I had always used a rice cooker to make rice, which we eat three times a week. Then my trusty rice cooker that had been with me for over a decade broke. Money is tight so I decided to try and make rice on the stove for the first time. As in, in my life. I tried using the same rice-to-water ratio in a pot that I had used for my rice cooker. The rice came out sticky--too much water. Then I tried Martha Stewart's recipe. The rice came out dry--too little water. (I have little luck with Martha Stewart recipes. I should have known better.) And then I tried your recipe. Perfect rice! My husband and kids said they didn't notice any difference between this rice and the rice cooker rice I had been making for so long. Thank you for saving me the expense of buying a new rice cooker! *Note: my husband is lactose-intolerant, so I coat the bottom of the pan with a thin layer of olive oil and skip the butter. This also keeps the rice from sticking since you don't stir the rice as it cooks.

name: easy pizza pasta casserole  oamc
review: This was a big hit here and I love that there is another casserole waiting in the freezer.  I used 1 lb ground beef, 1 lb Italian pork sausage, reduced the pepperoni to 7 oz (two of which I diced and mixed into the casserole), added about 5 oz sliced baby bella mushrooms which were sauteed with the onion, and reduced the mozzarella to 4 cups - spreading two cups on top of each casserole and not mixing any in.

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: Pure comfort food! What a delicious dinner. I'd never had this before, but couldn't believe how good it was. The chicken was completely fall apart tender, just amazing!

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: Made exactly as recipe stated and this was amazing!!! What a wonderful, hearty soup recipe. It tastes utterly divine! Can't wait to make it again!

name: shirley s perfect rare roast beef
review: I followed the recipe exactly, cooking my beef for 15 minutes (as per cooking instructions for 5 mins per pound) and then leaving it in the oven for an hour. It wasn't that rare though... a little pink, but not really rare as I know rare beef. Unless, it wasn't meant to be really pink? Don't know if I did something wrong? I definitely didn't open the oven, I didn't over cook it, I let it stand for 15 minutes... still tasted great though, so will try it again!

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: Snow day! Freezing rain and ice turned a typically crazy week day morning into a stay in your jammies snow day.  No where to go and the family all home together called for a warm delicious breakfast.  With real homemade maple syrup on hand and buttermilk in the fridge, this recipe is the one that won out.  So glad it did.  I prefer waffles over pancakes, but these cooked up perfectly golden brown, light and fluffy.  I even substituted 3/4 cup of the flour with whole wheat pastry flour and you would have never known.  Pure pancake perfection!

name: cinnamon swirl quick bread
review: I had buttermilk to use up and was on the search for a recipe.  I came across this and am so glad I did.  Everyone in my picky family gave this five stars.  Boy, that doesn't happen often!  I baked it for 45 minutes and my tester came out clean but I should have left it in a bit longer as it was still a little gooey in the center of the loaf. Next time I will bake a touch longer, because I know there will most definitely be a next time. I also recommend spraying the loaf pan with joy baking spray. I didn't have any problem with the bread sticking.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: These are so good!!!  My husband claimed them the best biscuits he's ever had :) :)!  Not sure if he was just being nice though lol.  But they were delicious, wish they would have gotten a little bit taller rise, but they sure did beat out some pretty flat biscuits I've made in the past by far.  It's a keeper!!!

name: no bake rice krispies peanut butter granola bars  lower fat
review:
I love this recipe!  I can't believe I haven't reviewed it yet for as often as I make it.  I use 2 cups of puffed rice cereal (not Rice Krispies, but the plain ol' puffed rice with a single ingredient of brown rice), 1/4 cup of brown sugar, and sometimes molasses instead of corn syrup.  Sometimes I use almond butter instead of peanut butter, so it could be made quite allergy-friendly.  As recommended, I mix everything except the mini chocolate chips (I tried full-size, and mini are better), let it cool slightly, then add the mini chips.  Oh yum yum yum!  It's still quite sweet, so I've been playing with it, and I can replace some of the syrup/molasses with water with acceptable results.

The trick to good results is to PRESS the bars into the pan.  PRESS HARD.  The less air, the more likely it is to stay in bar form!  I use a piece of waxed paper to keep my hands (or lid) clean while pressing.  Next I pop the pan in the freezer to make the bars easier to slice.  I usually slice into 12 bars instead of 16 (too yummy to skimp) and wrap each one with press-n-seal (I've been happiest with that for this).  Then I store the bars in the freezer until I need a snack.  And when I remember I have these in the freezer, I can feel the need to snack building up!  At least it's healthier (and cheaper) than so many other snack choices.

I'm a huge fan of recipes that are flexible, meaning they can be used as a starting point to make something different.  Other dried fruit, nuts, coconut ... just imagine this with chopped almonds and coconut instead of raisins!  I'm sure that would be awesome too!  This is the best kind of flexible recipe because I only measure the dry ingredients (fewer dishes to wash, and I just rinse after dry stuff), and I get good results eyeballing the sticky stuff.

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: Made this 2X.  First followed directions - using 1TBL anchovy paste. and 2 cloves garlic.  Second time used much more garlic and used about 5-6 flat anchovies out of a can.  Put in fridge to meld.  Will update if I make any further changes.  Thanks!! So delicious.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: When schools were closed for a snow day, meetings were cancelled and DH gt to work from home, replacing our crazy, hectic weekday morning with a yummy breakfast just sounded like the thing to do. We had buttermilk that needed to be used up so I searched the recipes for one we hadn't tried yet and this is what we came up with. Served them with either powdered sugar or real maple syrup. These are very close to IHOP pancakes.  DD said all we needed was IHOP's strawberry syrup (her favorite) and they would be perfect.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: Chicken drumsticks were on sale this week and I had everything else on hand.  This was really easy to put together and the baking time gave me plenty of time to get sides together, set the table, etc. while it was baking.  When the family walked in the door they all remarked on how good it smelled. Everyone enjoyed this. In fact everyone started putting the extra sauce on their rice too! ( I served with seasoned brown rice and broccoli. )

name: cheese and garlic drop biscuits
review: I made these as a side to go with our pasta dinner tonight.  The biscuit itself was great.  They were very light and fluffy, not heavy at all like some other biscuits we've tried.  However, my family didn't think the garlic or cheese flavors were very noticeable.  For that reason, they only rated the recipe as written, 3 stars.  Next time I will increase both the garlic and cheese and see how it effects their rating.

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: I made these expecting some really good flavor, but they were  very bland...about like the frozen ones I bought in the freezer case.  I have a better recipe and will continue to use that. I probably will not make these again.

name: simple tomato sandwich
review: There is definitely something special about the simple tomato sandwich. I remember being introduced in my childhood while over at my neighbours house for lunch. I came across this recipe and decided to revive the old favourite and tried it as written. It is absolutely important to use home grown or the best quality tomatoes you can find in the store that are still on the vine. I used the miracle whip option but I must say I wasn't impressed. I'm not really a mayo fan either (personal taste). For me, I like my tomato sandwich on fresh, untoasted buttered bread and a bit of salt and freshly ground pepper. I'm not giving stars as my preference is too different from the original recipe, but thanks for reminding me of an old favourite!

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: I made this using the milk option, anchovy paste instead of fillets, added the optional Worcestershire sauce.  I didn't thin it at all. If it was just for me, I would have thinned it a little, but my family liked it just as it was. This is quick and easy to put together. Thanks!

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: Mmmmm....total keeper recipe! Just the right amount of seasoning and broth. Loved it! As usual I make some adjustments based on what I have on hand and our preferences my changes were to halve the amount of beans, skip the pasta and substitute finely chopped cabbage in place of the spinach. Delicious and even better the next day. Thanks so much for posting this recipe.

name: moist chocolate cupcakes  super easy  budget
review: What a great recipe! I was a little worried when I saw there were no eggs in the recipe, but I needn't have been because these turned out great. Rich, moist and so decadent. You honestly couldn't tell that these didn't have all the ingredients cupcakes usually have!

name: orange julius smoothies
review: Pretty awesome!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: Excellent chicken. I had no problems thickening the glaze, but I did change the preparation.  I didn't want all of the grease in the glaze so I continued to baste the baked chicken with the glaze.  Very flavorful chicken.  Thank you for the recipe

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: Very good. Thank you for the recipe

name: baked ziti
review: I halved the recipe and did exactly what the recipe says. Amazing! So easy to make as well. My family inhaled the whole thing at dinner time. Great recipe!

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: We really enjoyed this dish.  It was a favorite of my DH. Made as directed but scaled back for two.  Thanks for sharing.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: Delicious potatoes. I used my homemade recipe for the onion soup mix, #110331, and baked them a little longer at 375 degrees Fahrenheit until they were brown and crispy, as suggested.

name: hot german potato salad
review: Yum!  Make sure you temper the eggs or they will be scrambled.  I cut the sugar a bit and it still was pretty sweet.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: This is a great  pasta dish! I added peas. I used 1/2 box of pasta but made full amount of sauce. Delicious!

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: I usually make pizza sauce with tomato sauce but I was out, so I was happy to find this recipe using crushed tomatoes, which I had!!  This was delicious and a perfect pizza sauce!  Loved the flavor, thanks!!

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: I have another favorite chicken wing recipe!  Mine turned out perfectly crisp on the outside and tender and juicy on the inside.  Tossed with some Frank's Red Hot sauce mixed with a bit of butter.  Great super bowl food!  Thanks for sharing!  Made for Favorites of 2015 tag game.

name: eggs with hats on top
review: I've been making these just like this forever!  Only difference is the name, which I LOVE this naming of it.  We usually call them "Toad in a hole".  Delish!!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review:
A tasty muffin but a little too sweet for me, light cake like texture.
Will make again but reduce sugar.

name: cake batter ice cream
review: Wow wow wow! This is perhaps the best ice cream I've made. I think the cake mix helps absorb the moisture so it doesn't crystallize. I followed the recipe exactly, using a yellow cake mix. I froze it in a bread pan with saran wrap on top to prevent freezer burn. I also sprinkled on some funfetti.

name: stuffed green bell pepper soup
review: Like the idea of the recipe but made a lot of changes to make it work so I'm not giving it a star rating. I used beef stock instead of the bouillon and water, I did 1 pound of sweet Italian sausage (since I had a bunch in the freezer) and 1 lb beef, then skipped the brown sugar. I also put my rice in uncooked so it would cook in the soup and not get mushy. Then topped it with chopped parsley. It was great and we will definitely be making it again.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: A lovely rich, moist chocolate cake. I was surprised how easy this was to make and it was certainly decadent! I made 2 9 inch layers and then topped it with chocolate buttercream. This might be my new favourite chocolate cake recipe as it is perfectly soft and delicious!

name: mini tacos
review: I used the round gyoza wrappers and topped them with a bit of sour cream, a wedge of cherry tomato, and some chopped chives.

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: This was excellent.  I used bone in, skin on cut up chicken. Had to omit cilantro to avoid an argument  Had to sub chile and garlic with chile garlic sauce. Also baked on a rack in oven.  This chicken was so juicy and flavorful.  I'm sure marinating overnight would be even better and I intend to do so the next time I prepare your dish.  Thank you!

name: zucchini chocolate cake
review: We loved this cake! I used applesauce instead of oil and chopped snickers in lieu of the chips and nuts. To make it extra chocolatey I topped with a simple chocolate frosting. I will make this again, thanks

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: SO GOOD!!  Mine didn't flip perfectly but Oh well!  I love how some of the noodle crisp up.  Taste great!!

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: I used dried thyme because it is what I had on hand.  I subbed beef broth for the chicken broth and wow the sauce was so rich and delicious.  That's the only two substitutions I made.  Hubby and  I both loved this dish.  We are looking forward to leftovers for tomorrow.  Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: These meatballs were yummy. I will never make a different meatball again. Follow the recipe exactly. Thanks for posting

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: 10 thumbs up!  Used ground turkey and the green enchiladas sauce.  Easy to make and was the best enchiladas I've ever made!  Thx :)

name: detweiler sloppy joe mix
review: Excellent recipe Kurt Detweiler - thank you for posting.  I've finally found a sloppy joe mix both my  husband and I truly like.  I used your basic recipe with a couple of changes. In place of catsup I used chili sauce (I use this for cocktail sauce) as it has a bit more kick than catsup and I also added garlic, dash of Worcestershire and 1 tablespoon of apple cider vinegar (other reviewers suggested these last three ingredients).  I can stop looking now :)

name: chocolate mint candy  fudge
review: Great recipe and super easy! I used white Wilton Candy Melts (as that's all we get here) for the mint layer and it turned out great; easy to spread and flavour/colour! Will definitely be making this again!

name: amazing white trash puff balls
review: I didn't have very high expectations of these but decided to give it a try anyway. I am so glad that I did. I added some chopped sweet mini peppers in the cream cheese filling. It tastes like mini pizza! So good and so easy! Thanks for the recipe.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: Good!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review:
UPDATE: Nov. 6, 2015 Although the first time I made these I would say they were great but the 2nd time, they were by far the best I have ever made. I used frozen butter and let it sit out 10 minutes or so, just enough where I could cut it into chunks. Also the food processor is key I think. They were flaky and so awesome!!

1st Review: My 13 year old granddaughter wanted biscuits and gravy and we picked this recipe. Delicious!! Thank you!!

name: wholly guacamole
review:
Wholly Guacamole...this was good stuff!!!  This will be my "go to" guacamole recipe from now on.  My family had this for a Cinco de Mayo/Supermoon party this year and it was a hit.  Like another reviewer said, they were sold on trying this by the story that went with it.  Loved it!!  I read somewhere that if you put the avocado pit in with the guacamole that it also helps it from turning brown along with the plastic wrap trick on laying it right on the dip.  I put a couple in and the next day it was still beautifully green.  Thanks for sharing a great recipe!!
UPDATE March 4, 2016: I found a new way to keep it fresh and green looking. When ready to store, forget the pit and plastic wrap technique. Instead, push down guacamole to get all the air out and smooth top. Add about 1/2" of LUKEWARM water and close with a tight fitting lid. Sounds weird but it works. On the 3rd day it was still green. Do this every time you get out and use.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: this was delicious. I used a bottom crust as my family and I like it that way. I also added some peas. I was simple to make and not at all time consuming as I used a vegetable cutter to dice up all the vegetables. It was nice because all the veggies were the same size. Thanks for sharing> I will be making the again and again.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Good and super easy. I doubled the sauce and added a few shakes of crushed red pepper. Thanks for the recipe!

name: classic baked ziti
review: This recipe doesn't need another review but here I go!!! I made this for a friend & they just loved it. I used lean ground turkey (1 1/4 lbs), 1/2 cup onion & added some Italian seasoning along with the oregano. I thought about reducing the amount of broth but it was perfect. I needed about 3 cups of cheese & used 1/2 cup parmesan cheese (total). She requested the recipe & I will gladly pass it onto her! Thanks so much for the detailed instructions, too--I had never made ziti before!

name: ground beef gyros
review: Rating is for the meat only; I made these into meatballs and baked in the oven. I think next time I will add a little cinnamon and allspice to include those yummy Greek flavors of the Gyros I love. Served over spinach with kalamata olives, sliced onion and topped with Feta Dill Greek Yogurt dressing. Delish! Thanks for sharing.

name: corned beef and cabbage in guinness
review: I can see why this has gotten rave reviews. It is delicious! The whole week before making this I did research on Guiness and how it tends to make beef dishes bitter. I had decided to try Michelob AmberBock for an Irish stew I'm making later in the week and used that for this recipe because I had it on hand. I will be getting the Guiness Draught for the stew after reading the butcher's instructions. Other than the beer I made this as directed. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review:
I love this cake.

I've tried several variations...my favorite is to add cardamom and a touch of cinnamon to the batter.  Then, after the cake is iced?..a generous amount of cinnamon ontop the icing, along with the walnuts (or pecans or other tasty chopped nuts).

Those additions add considerable dimension to this recipe.

name: granny s banana cream pie
review: YUM!!!  I was a little worried because I messed up and had the order of things got messed up.  I ended up having to do the second cook time WITH the vanilla, bananas and butter.  The bananas kind of cooked away into it.  I was mainly worried it wouldn't set up and just be a puddle of pie when I served it.  But I went with it, poured it into a graham cracker crust and stuck it in the fridge.  went back a couple hours later and it set up nicely!!  It was so delicious!  Perfect with whipped cream.  Yay, thanks!!

name: crock pot chicken vindaloo
review: This recipe is amazing!! I had to give it 4 stars b/c of all the changes I made (read the reviews, which really helped). Used chicken thighs (4), but after I coated the chicken w/ the sauce--I was nervous that there wasn't enough so I made more to cover it. I used a full tbsp chicken curry, 2 tsp cumin, 3/4 tsp ground ginger, reduced the vinegar to 1 1/2 tbsp, added 2 tsp brown sugar, used 1/4 tsp chili powder for the hot pepper, added 1/2 tsp coriander & 1/4 tsp seasoning salt--and 3/4 tsp mustard powder for the mustard seeds. I also omitted the cinnamon & parsley. This is perfect to go over rice, esp with the extra sauce it made! I might try this on the stove top! Thank you for sharing!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Since we butcher our own meat, I used a 4-1/2 lb. (pork) ham roast (with bone in) to make this recipe. I also used 14 ounces of Ginger Ale, and cooked the roast over night for 12 hours on LOW, but by the next morning, the roast was far from being done, so I turned the roast over, covered it, and cooked on HIGH for another 2 hours. By then the roast was done. I cut the meat into bite size pieces, rather than shredding with 2 forks, and just added a few of the cooked onions back in with the meat, and discarded the remaining onions. Since there was lots of meat, I added an entire (28-ounce) bottle of Sweet Baby Ray's Original Barbecue Sauce. (Next time I'm going to use Sweet Baby Ray's Sweet & Spicy Barbecue Sauce, cause we like spicy.) After I added the barbecue sauce, I cooked for about 1-1/2 hours on LOW, so not to dry out the meat. I have noticed, when you cook meat on a LOW setting before serving, it never does get hot enough 'temp-wise', and so the meat was just warm, and not hot enough, but we still enjoyed the sandwiches. I'm reheating leftovers in the microwave. Since I used a bigger roast, I found this made at least 15-16 sandwiches. One thing I did want to mention when making this recipe, I used a 6-quart crock-pot which only has 3 settings, On, LOW, and HIGH. While my husband and I enjoyed the sandwiches, I like the fact you don't need a lot of ingredients to make a delicious pulled pork sandwich. Thank you duonyte for sharing this recipe, it's definitely a keeper!

name: blackberry cobbler
review: Loved this cobbler.  Had it warm and then the next day for breakfast.  Had two 6 oz. containers of black berries.  YUM.

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: You don't need another review!  I tried this with Parchment paper.  I used my mandolin and forgot to soak the potatoes, will try that next time.  I sprayed the parchment with coconut spray, placed my potatoes and tried sea salt and pepper and onion powder, the next batch I swapped out the onion powder with garlic powder, sprayed the top of the potatoes put another sheet of parchment paper on and trimmed around my round microwave plate that rotates inside.  YUM!  Way better than store bought!  Thank you!

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: DD and I typically don't care for cauliflower, but everyone enjoyed this recipe. Can't wait to give it a try with garlic salt, as we love our garlic.

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: I can't wait to make again.  Best fruit salad recipe.

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: This makes a really good fruit salad.  I added the dry pudding in with the fruit and then added some of the pineapple juice until I thought it was juicy enough, didnt need much of the peach juice.  I did not add the sugar.

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: I have made this twice now, and my picky eaters are begging for more. If you are watching calories, using margarine and lite cream cheese works out fine, but REAL butter and REAL cream cheese REALLY makes you stick your face in the pan, like Jeff says. We didn't even put any icing on this, it was so good. (Although my pickiest eater put butter on his and ate it like a slice of bread.) I also baked this a bit longer than called for, about 1 hour and 45 minutes. Thank you Amanda for letting your Dad share this with the world!

name: slow cooked bbq ribs  for crock pot
review: Holy yum, these are good! And so simple! I'm not the biggest fan of pork, so made these predominantly for my fiancé, but I wolfed them down too, so that's saying something! Brilliant recipe!

name: spinach salad with honey bacon dressing
review: This has to be the best salad I've ever made/had! I'm not the biggest salad lover, but this was phenomenal! So much flavour! I wanted soft boiled eggs, but apart from that I made it exactly as the recipe stated. That dressing is to die for!

name: honey ginger grilled salmon
review: We used local wildflower honey and reduced sodium soy sauce.  We started it on the gas grill, but ran out of propane and had to finish it in the oven.  It turned out fantastic. Served with couscous and steamed asparagus.

name: breakfast casserole supreme
review: This is such a fantastic recipe! I used sausage for mine and I'm glad I did; it went so well with the tomatoes and peppers! What a simple, hearty meal; I could not stop myself going back for seconds!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Thank you for sharing your recipe.  We enjoyed the pork chops prepared this way.  Quick and easy to make entree, the pork chops were perfectly cooked and the sauce was thin but very tasty.  What a lovely meal, served with aspargus and jasmine rice. Made for What's on the Menu Tag Game.

name: detweiler sloppy joe mix
review: Very good recipe if you like a sweeter Sloppy Joe. To suit my family's more savory tastes, I tweak this easy recipe by adding diced celery, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper to taste. I agree with the reviewers who said to use 1/4 cup of water instead of the recommended 1/2 cup. The water will make the meat mixture look thin at first, but let it simmer for 15 minutes as you occasionally stir and the mixture will thicken. This recipe is a keeper!

name: ground beef gyros
review: I used ground turkey.  I used the suggestion from other reviewers and slammed the meat mixture on the counter for about 5-10 minutes to make it dense.  WOW, it was a winner in our house hold.  I did spruce up the cucumber sauce.

name: chipotle roast for tacos   sandwiches
review: Surprisingly not as flavorful as I expected. Meat was tender and shredded well, but could use a flavor boost.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Reminds me of a Chi chi's dish from the past. Good, rich, filling, changeable. Needed a bit more spice. A winner.

name: kittencal s perfect prime rib roast beef
review: A great and simple way to make roast beef. This made a delicious Sunday roast last week! It didn't take too long and was incredibly easy to make. A definite winner!

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: AMAZING! I was not expecting this to be so good. A little too much cheese for us so we'll cut back next time, but definitely a winner for the whole family, toddlers included! Used an Old El Paso giant restaurant style burrito tortilla and it made a great amount of crispy crust.

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: The other day I made beef, black-beans and white-rice enchiladas, but didn't have a canned enchilada sauce in my pantry. This recipe came highly recommended by others who made beef enchiladas from this site. I'm so glad I tried this recipe. Not only was it easy to make, but there was plenty of sauce, and I liked how it tasted; especially since this was my first time making enchiladas. One thing I did change about the recipe, I didn't add any salt or pepper, as I already added it to the beef mixture in the enchiladas. I don't think I'll ever buy the canned sauce, as this recipe is definitely a keeper!

name: homemade rice a roni
review: Thank you for sharing this lovely recipe Lisa. The rice was quick and easy to make with excellent results. It had a soft and tender texture with a lovely subtle flavor. I made a very basic version for my dh. Chicken stock, vermicelli noodles and jasmine rice, he was over the moon. We will be enjoying this comfort food often. Made for What's on the Menu? Tag Game.

name: southern fried chicken
review: Delish!! I used chicken tenders for this and made the best chicken fingers! I used some seasoning salt on them when they came out of the fryer and kept them warm in the oven while cooking the rest of the batches. So good! Thanks a lot for a great dinner! ��

name: jalapeno popper burgers
review: Fantastic!! These may be my new favourite burgers! So easy and they tasted great! The burgers turned out so juicy and I loved that fiery hit you got from the middle, just fabulous!

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: Delicious, the whole family LOVED it! I meant to make some homemade vanilla ice cream to go with, but didn't end up having time. It was gladly eaten without though, with happy smiling faces :)

name: yummy creamy rice pudding
review: I was craving rice pudding after watching a show of people eating rice pudding lol, so I had to make some! It was delish! Used Jasmine rice and and coconut sugar and it was perfect. Also replaced raisins with dried cranberries. Topped with a little bit of cinnamon and fresh mango. Yum!

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: After reading the reviews, I added an extra cup of stuffing, next time I may add a little more. My family really liked this. It was easy to throw together in the morning and have it ready and waiting when we got home. The Chicken was fall apart tender and the gravy was good. It didn't have the soup taste I was expecting. In fact, my family like it so much that next time I may make mashed potatoes or rice to serve it over.

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: This is one of the best marinades ever! I used Thai basil which I think is very appropriate here and marinated for about 6 hours. Used skinless but bone in chicken thighs. So flavorful!!

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: Loved it!! Worked perfectly with our beef tostadas :)

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: I am only rating the sauce as this dish did not work for me. The package of meat that I bought said beef ribs but should have said beef boots. And even on low setting they cooked way to fast. I didn't have much of a problem with the grease issue because I trimmed what I could from the meat. If I attempt this dish again I will definetly make sure I have good quality ribs and will prepare them in the oven. Thank you for the recipe.

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: If I could give this 10 stars, I would. It was GREAT! I didn't measure my chicken or flour, but I guess it was about 1.5 lbs. of floured chicken tender bite size pieces. I used seasoned salt instead of the cayenne and salt, but did add a touch of cayenne (hubby isn't happy if he has steam coming out his ears) but otherwise stuck pretty closely to the recipe. I used Penzy's curry powder which was quite fresh, so the spices were wonderful. The raisins are a tasty sweet addition to the other spicy flavors (you could probably use dark raisins instead of the golden ones.) I added about 1/2 red bell pepper to the onion, and that made it pretty much a one-dish meal (if you count peppers as a vege.) A side of rice and sliced tomato was all it took to complete the plate. Yum, yum, yum - don't bother with any other recipe for chicken curry. This is the best.

name: thai chicken breasts
review: Very good. I took advice from other reviewers and cut up the chicken breast into bite-sized pieces and doubled the sauce. Also, I find that chicken breast can get dry and tough when fried, so I changed the cooking procedure to this recipe by first sauteing the chicken pieces and then adding the remaining ingredients directly into the frying pan with the chicken still in the pan. I boiled down the sauce and stirred the chicken in the sauce frequently. That worked out well, as the chicken pieces absorbed some of the sauce and were fork-tender when done. My kids and husband asked me to make this recipe again. There is something missing to this sauce, though--maybe pineapple or orange juice? I'll be making this again and will find out. I served this meal with white rice and black beans (the Goya recipe on the back of the Goya black beans can; it's the best black bean recipe). I will use this recipe often!

name: thick  soft  and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: Great cookie! I used all butter as another reviewer suggested. I believe my cookie scoop is a little smaller than two tablespoons. The first batch I cooked at 375 for 10 minutes and the cookies were too brown on the bottoms. The second batch I cooked at 350 for 10 minutes and they were much butter. Thanks so much for sharing.

name: wholly guacamole
review: The perfect guacamole! :)

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: Made very beautiful muffins, fast and easy. I'm used raspberries as suggested at the end of the recipe. A keeper!

name: uncle bill s green split pea with hambone soup
review: This is honestly the best soup I've ever tried!! I really wasn't expecting to like it as I don't normally like split pea soup, but this tastes phenomenal! SO much flavour! Just delicious! I pureed half of the soup and left half with some small chunks to add texture; it was perfect!

name: quick n easy quiche crust
review: Good, basic, and versatile recipe. I personally found it to have very little taste....and while a flaky, buttery crust (which this is not) definitely enhances any quiche, this did nothing to detract from the quiche I made. If I have time and motivation, I'd opt for finicky my butter-laden quiche crust. But this was quick and easy and fit into my life so SCORE!

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: This is like chicken covered in bubbling artichoke dip! Very delicious, and such a snap to make!

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: These were great! The only change I made was to add cinnamon. Now I don't need to feel as guilty when I want to have potatoes with my pancakes. Thanks!! Update: 6/23/16 - I completely forgot about these, but was searching for a recipe to use up 6 egg whites. So last night for dinner, I made 1.5x the recipe and got fifteen 2.5 inch pancakes. I added mini chocolate chips and used whipped topping instead of maple syrup. Still a winner in my book!

name: leftover mashed potato pancakes
review: So easy and so good, I did follow another reviewers advise and added 1 teaspoon of baking powder and separated the eggs, whipping the whites before adding. Was delicious, topped with the sour cream option. Could make a whole meal out of these. As long as you cook on a medium heat and wait for the first side to cook well (like pancakes) had no trouble with turning

name: herbed pork tenderloin
review: This tasted bland to us.

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: Really good. I used a 15 oz can of tomato sauce (no salt added) and water to equal the remainder of the liquid called for in the recipe (I didn't have 6 oz of tomato paste on hand). I also stirred a little beef base in to the finished sauce. This was really quick to put together and tasted so good. I used cooked ground beef (with a small amount of sauce & shredded sharp cheddar stirred into it and topped it with the remaining sauce & cheese. Served with corn, this time. Wish I had a little sour cream for garnish (with cilantro, lime some black beans and maybe a margarita...;) Anyway, really great recipe. Thanks for sharing!

name: white almond sour cream wedding cake
review: Soooo delicious! Light but rich. I halved the recipe and baked in a 9x13 pan for just shy of an hour. I think I could have taken it out about 5 mins sooner, the edges got a little tough. I cut the cake in half and froze half. I split the other half and iced the center with PB icing and iced the entire cake with buttercream icing. Delicious! I'm looking forward to trying all sorts of variations of this keeper recipe. Thanks for sharing.

name: the best belgian waffles
review: Best waffle I have ever had!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Made these for a bake sale. Wonderful!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: I had 3 really ripe bananas, so this was the perfect recipe to use them up. I made them for DH, as he is the only fan of banana bread/muffins in our house. He wasn't so sure about the crumb topping, but gave the muffins 4 stars.

name: soft italian breadsticks  abm
review: The BEST, that's the comment from my picky eater nephew who likes almost nothing. I have to agree, soft pillow crumb, with the flavors of the brushed on butter n spices. Made it exactly as directed in the ABM so couldn't have been easier, served them with scallops and pasta and it was the perfect bread. I'm betting this one is going to make all our Italian meals in the future

name: bev s macaroni and cheese
review: I was in doubt that this would really be creamy but it is! We loved it and I followed the recipe as written except..(there is always and except) that I added some gouda cheese and did not decrease the cheddar amount. Very good and a keeper for sure

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Wow, was this ever good. We really loved this simple recipe, it was so quick and easy to make with terrific results. Best of all it uses ingredients that are always found in my pantry and fridge. Thank you so much for sharing a recipe that we will enjoy often. Made for What's on the Menu tag game.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: This was great and very simple to make! I ended up using about 3/4 of a pound of pasta (used up some partial boxes) and it was the perfect amount for the sauce. Like other reviews, I would double up on the sauce if making an entire pound. I added an extra garlic clove, sautéed a jalapeño, and threw in strips of a roasted poblano pepper at the end to make it a bit more substantial for a main dish. I also used fresh parsley. It needs a little something "more" so I just threw in some different spices I had on hand to punch up the flavor. Still its a great alternative to the sodium-laden Lipton's Pasta Sides, etc. I'll make this again!

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: i needed a recipe for a chocolate cake,and i had made a recipe of Chef DiSharf's for the Christmas Cookie Bake-Off 2005.so i knew that this one would be a winner and it was.it made a perfect base for Ho Ho Cake recipe#11799. it was very moist,and had a rich but not rich chocolately(if that's a word :))flavor.this is a wonderful cake.thank you for posting. UPDATE ON 7/24/2016: This review is going to be a bit confusing,I first made this recipe on 3/2/2006. I first saw it posted by DiScharf. But her recipe is no longer on this site,but strangely enough my photos which were posted to that particular recipe on 3/2/2006 are on this recipe. So I'm redoing my review. I've made this recipe SEVERAL times over the last 10 years and found it to be the best chocolate cake there ever was. And anytime I need a chocolate this will Be my " go to " recipe. " Keep Smiling :) "

name: soft peanut butter cookies
review: Love these easy and soft PB cookies, made for a bake sale and followed directions, my young nephew even did most of the work. Sold out and folks where coming back asking for more

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: I have made this recipe several times now and just realized I never reviewed it. My husband and I both love the convenience of this recipe as well as the taste. Sometimes I leave out the beans and just use corn. By the way, neither of us are fond of black beans so I always substitute pinto beans. I sometimes chop and add some onion or chopped poblano pepper. This is one of those recipes that is wonderful as originally written as well as being very adaptable to a few changes. Thank you so much for posting this recipe.

name: crock pot ravioli
review: We thought this was a little on the bland but the taste of this is totally going to depend on the quality of the ingredients you use. The flavor of sauces and filled pastas vary greatly. This was extremely easy to throw together and it was wonderful to come home to find dinner ready. We served this with bruschetta

name: grilled cheese  diner style
review: Mayo has always been my go to for grilled cheese when I'm out of butter (when does that happen?). Perfect and yummy :)

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: WOW was this great. I followed the recipe exactly. I did double the sauce. I used day old cold long grain rice and made a quick version of fried rice. I stirred fried the rice in peanut oil adding a few tablespoons of soy sauce and a few drops of sesame oil. Everyone said 10 stars. Next time I think I will add mushrooms. This is a keeper. Thanks for sharing.

name: easy baked potato wedges
review: These are very good, but I do think the cook time is bit long. Mine were done in about 30 minutes. Taste great thought and the family loved them :)

name: easy taco stew
review: Delicious stew with pantry ingredients. Easy and filling.

name: beer  n bbq braised country style pork ribs
review: These were FANTASTIC!! Love the fact they are not just BBQ ribs, but beer braised. Adding the beer really adds something to the finished dish. These disappeared in a flash here!

name: philly cheesesteak sandwich     authentic
review: This tasted great! It made the perfect lunch for two seriously hungry people this past weekend! Quick to make and full of flavour. I'm not from the US, so I have no idea if this is authentic, but to me it was one delicious sandwich!

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: Oh my goodness, this is SO good! I love copycat recipes as it means I can enjoy lots of things we don't get here in the UK! All the layers of flavour together are just sublime. Out of this world! I will definitely be making and eating this many many more times!

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: We used a sweet onion and cut the amount way back. We enjoyed it, but like Bergy, we all agreed we would like it better with a touch of dressing. Over all, a great summer salad, especially when cucumbers and tomatoes are abundant.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: I used the mayo/cream option and used canned peas with carrots. I found that the first 15 min. of baking didn't even heat the mixture...so I allowed a bit more time then placed the cheese and biscuits. This dish turned out bueatifully. The biscuits were not a bit raw I did find that in the future I will add some sort of seasoning but even without them we really enjoyed this. Thank you for the recipe!

name: pepsi pork roast
review: Absolutely yummy!!!! Thanks so much!

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: I really really liked these chewy pancakes! Excellent with butter and maple syrup.

name: kittencal s extreme chocolate brownies
review: Amazing brownies! Easy enough for my toddler to help and feel like he did most of the baking, yet delicious results! I baked mine for about 40 minutes at 160C and they came out perfectly gooey just as I was hoping. Thanks for another star recipe!

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: Football, wings and bacon dip! I served this with wheat thins and tortilla chips. My family seemed to like it better with the tortilla chips.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: We enjoyed this recipe. Not everyone in our family is a fish lover. The ingredients in the sauce is the main flavor that comes through instead of the fish. I served this with steamed broccoli and cheddar bacon bread that I got from the local farmer's market.

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Thank you ~In*Memory*of*Brats~ for posting this recipe. I am not a fan of meatballs, however, my DH loves them so I make them for him. I always try one when I make a new recipe and, until I made and tried these, had yet to find any I'd eat. These are delicious - I made them exactly as you posted them, only I froze nine of them and cooked the other six in the sauce per your instructions. I am hoping the ones I froze taste just as good as the ones cooked fresh. I will look forward to having a meatball sandwich with my DH in the next couple of weeks :D

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: I really like the taste of this and the juice was very nice. I only used 1 t. liquid smoke and I think that was just right for us, as I think it can be over powering. I didn't use as much salt and pepper either but someday maybe I will be brave and make this recipe as it is written. Thanks - I will be making this again!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: I made this soup last week because of all rave reviews. It's good. Not the best I've ever had, but then honestly I haven't had Panera's version so I had no idea what to expect. It is more of a vegetable cheese soup that would benefit from some garlic with the onion and a partial puree. I did not have nutmeg so it was not added. I did add another handful of cheddar to make it more "cheesy". This is a hearty soup that I plan on making again with a few changes for personal preferences. Thanks for the recipe

name: weight watchers mexican chicken breasts
review: OMG!!! I love this recipe - so easy, and the taste is wonderful. A great change from plain old grilled chicken. I didn't have taco seasoning on hand so used recipe #34883 and it was the best. Served with steamed brocolli and brown rice for a very satisfying and deliscious meal. Thanks BC for posting. 9-7-2016 update, continue to make and love this recipe, this time used thighs as that's what I had on hand, even with todays Smartpoints still comes out to a low 4 points.

name: outback steakhouse style steak
review: AMAZING!!!!!!!!

name: amy sedaris s vanilla cupcakes
review: Rating for cupcake only: I thought these had great flavor and were easy to make. Downside is that they did dry out very quickly and were pretty dense. I didn't read reviews or might have added the extra vanilla, but I still thought they were tasty.

name: ginger me up chicken  low fat honey   ginger chicken breasts
review: Delicious, and so easy to put together. Made this for a guest who was dairy and gluten intolerant and served it with jasmine rice. I opted for the skillet preparation and browned the breasts first. Perfect! Thanks so very much for this fabulous recipe (bonus for a company-worthy meal made with things in my pantry)!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I ruined a pan cooking these. Don't know what I did wrong - not sure a dish of potatoes is worth the cost of a $20 pan. Sad.

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: I used yellow and red grape tomatoes and didn't have baguette but did have some pita chips so I served this delicious bruschetta on them :) YUM!!!

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: So easy to work with. Perfect every time!

name: basil pesto
review: Really good pesto. This was my first time making pesto and the family loved it. I used walnuts in place of the pine nuts. Fabulous, thank you!

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: We loved these! Lovely and fluffy and they taste great too! I served with some fresh fruit and maple syrup and they all vanished!

name: salmon and asparagus in foil
review: What an easy way to make dinner. I used a garlic pepper, sea salt blend and put a little directly on the salmon as well as on top of the asparagus. I don't think it would have had enough flavor other wise, so I am glad I did. Clean up is so easy with this because of the foil packets. I would definitely make this again.

name: brown rice and lentil casserole
review: I made this tonight, but used it as a side dish, not a main dish. My kids loved this, which is a miracle because I usually have a hard time getting them to eat any beans or legumes. Thank you for a quick and easy recipe ladypit!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: AMAZING! We used skin on salmon fillet and just broiled it for 5-8 minutes. Really wonderful sauce.

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: Sweet or savory...works for either. Makes 2 crusts.yum.

name: eric s easy grilled chicken
review: This was so simple and so moist. I love when I can find something that I basically throw in a bowl in the fridge and then throw on the grill and it turns out moist and delicious. Thank you for a winner, winner chicken dinner!

name: homemade pie crust
review: This is an amazing but EASY pie crust! I used half butter and half shortening. So simple and perfect for the quiche I used this for :) :) Very happy :)

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
