review: This is a lovely recipe. Quick and easy to make with wonderful results. I love that it uses ingredients always found in the pantry. A wonderful example of how a few ingredients can create a stunning dish. Thanks for sharing, made for What`s on the Menu Tag Game.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Not that this recipe needs another review, but WOW this is good! And it's so incredibly easy. I served it over rice that was seasoned with salt and lime juice and served broccoli on the side. Great weeknight meal. I know I will make this many more times. Thanks for posting a real keeper!

name: christina s killer dip
review: Sure is killer!

name: light and fluffy pumpkin pancakes
review: Yum! Nice balanced flavor. I freeze pumpkin in half cup portions so used it all. I used 2Tbls brown sugar and a couple top of white sugar, 1/4 cup of flour was whole wheat pastry, I'd use more next time. I increased the cinnamon and didn't use nutmeg because I was out. I followed another suggestion and spread the batter a bit so no problem with undercooked. I

name: momma s fair funnel cake
review: Wow.<br/><br/>I had no idea how easy it was to make funnel cake. I made them for a bunch of college guys and it was universally agreed that they're just like the ones from the fair or the race track.<br/><br/>The batter was a little too thick to flow through the funnel though. I had to trickle it from a measuring cup. It makes a lot of 8" servings. A LOT. After the first time I've always added a little vanilla to the batter.

name: spinach   feta stuffed chicken breast  quick   easy
review: This was SO good!! What a fantastic way to cook chicken! The breadcrumbs came out crisp, the filling was so delicious I took the note of the OP and served the leftovers as a side. Really easy and totally delicious, will definitely make again!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Well, I modified the recipe because I don't like cottage cheese (nor ricotta). In fact I don't like a lot of cheese in general. I used bechamel sauce instead (I think my recipe made about 17-18 ounces sauce) in place of the cottage cheese. I also cut the mozzarella in half... it was great and just right for someone who doesn't like cheese. Thanks for a fabulous recipe. : )

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: Fast, easy, healthy, forgiving for subbing ingredients. I left out the Rosemary in favor of oregano and cut down the quantity of pasta and used smaller pasta. Would be just as good without pasta or with some crumbled Italian sausage or diced chicken. My husband asked for crumbled pancetta in it next time. Keeper recipe for sure.

name: tasty buns
review: This is a new favourite for me! I used this recipe to make smaller dinner rolls. (Leftovers made for great tiny sandwiches!) The first time I used all vegetable oil and the rolls were nice and soft but lacking that nice buttery flavour. The second time I used 1/4 cup oil and 1/4 cup butter (melted) and that woke the rolls right up. I much prefer it with some butter in the dough. Next time I may try subbing all the oil for butter, but I really liked it with half butter, half oil! I also like this method of mixing half the flour first and then the rest as it needs it. This made it a lot easier for me to mix than just throwing all the flour in all at once. I let the dough have a full first rise (it took only maybe 40 minutes because my ingredients were warmer than lukewarm; so my dough rose quickly!) and I ended up making 32 rolls! So many rolls! They turned out so soft and delicious, and perfect for our Thanksgiving dinner. It made me smile seeing people keep reaching for them! And they're still soft and delicious the next day. Thank you!

name: perfect turkey in an electric roaster oven
review: This turned out great! The turkey was lovely and moist and the skin crisp. Will definitely make turkey like this again and it makes a ton of space in the oven!

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: Fantastic recipe. I used bread flour and bread machine yeast. Nice talk fluffy loaf, absolutely delicious.

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: Followed this recipe exactly and my family was very happy tonight. I used the sour cream option, instead of milk in this. I like my soup really thick, so I did add about 12 corn tortillas. I served this with tortillas, green onions and sour cream. Thank you for a great soup Eddie!

name: cranberry feta pinwheels
review: I took these to a party and they were a hit, so I'll make them again. But I would like more flavor, even though I was generous with the green onion. Perhaps fresh herbs or a flavored cream cheese?

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review: I forgot to review this when I made it a few months ago. It is outstanding! I added some Worcestershire and some Cajun seasoning to spice it up a bit. Looking forward to making again this week. Thank you!

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: What else can I say that hasn't already been said? Super crispy and even better than store bought or ordered in! I served these lovely crispy wings with Buffalo sauce and a sweet thau chili sauce but we barely touched them...they were so good on their own! Thanks for a 'keeper' recipe!

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: I followed the recipe exactly. It was good!

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Delicious! I took others' advice and used 3 cups sugar and it was plenty sweet. Loved the sweet with a touch of salt.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: Pretty good recipe, very simple to prepare, although I made my dressing mixes from scratch (no dry dressing mix in Aus). The flavour was good, but I still prefer my roast in the oven.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: I have made this a few times now. It's definitely better with a spicier salsa rather than a mild one. It's a very tasty and filling dish, not to mention so easy. I usually serve it with white rice. One thing I do differently is cook the chicken from fresh/defrosted rather than frozen, as one of the other reviews suggested cooking from frozen in a slow cooker is unsafe.

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: This is a great banana cake recipe, Mine turned out tasty, soft and moist. The cream cheese icing is so good! I'll make this again for sure.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: I have made this recipe several times now. The first time that I made it we thought it was a bit soggy, so I cut the butter down to 2 tablespoons after that and the hashbrowns have come out great and to our liking. I follow the recipe besides the butter precisely and these always come out great and get gobbled right up. I made them again tonight for our weekly "Brinner" (Breakfast for Dinner) and they were a hit as usual. Thank you for a great staple in our house!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: I deviated from my regular homemade mac and cheese recipe to try this, and it didn't turn out well for me. I tripled the recipe because I have a large family, and maybe that created an issue. I purchased a higher grade sharp cheddar, and it didn't melt into a smooth consistency. If I were to make this again, I was try a sharp American or another cheese that melts better.

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: Made half a recipe to try it, adding it to my mint coffee. YUM.

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: I used a jalapeno pepper instead of a bell pepper. Also, I drained the beans and used water instead of the bean liquid (personal preference). Very yummy, I will definitely make again :)

name: copycat lipton s onion soup mix
review: This is great. I use this in a lot of recipes, as well as making Dip. Who knew that Lipton's had flour in it? Cheap filler, possibly? It's a no-no for me, since I can't tolerate gluten. This is a great substitute, and it isn't full of unpronounceable ingredients.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I really like the flavor of this, so it gets the 3 stars, but the long baking time uncovered made my chops come out a bit dry, so that my kids wouldn't eat them. I'll try this again, but follow some of the other reviews and cover this for the majority of the cooking time. For 6 chops I made a bit more than double the sauce, but covered to cook it might have been plenty. Thanks for sharing. I'll make this again and use thicker chops that I cover while baking.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: This was a delicious stew that I really enjoyed. Thanks for sharing, Ev.

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: Wow. Very good. I added the pasta uncooked and it turned out really thick, more like a stew. Which is fine because I like my soup thick and not thin. If you want thin soup either add more broth or cook the pasta before putting it in. The flavor is fantastic!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: This was simple and flavourful. My husband loved it!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: I tried this instead of my usual go-to spaghetti sauce one night. I didn't enjoy it, although my kids did, which is why I'm giving it 3 stars. I just can't get around using the sausage instead of ground beef. My go-to sauce is this one http://www.food.com/recipe/authentic-bolognese-sauce-sugo-alla-bolognese-474008

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: A very tasty soup. I had plenty left over to freeze and take to work.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: So tasty! I don't use pimiento, as I can't find them here, but I don't think it matters. To me it's great without them.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: A great carrot cake recipe! Home made is always best!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: I didn't really love this, I don't like Italian sausage in meat pasta sauces, plain ol ground beef is best for me. I prefer my lasagne classic, with a proper bechamel sauce.

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: Good ol kittencal, her recipes are top notch. This one is no exception. A great salad. I love feta!

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: This is my fave veggie soup. It's so tasty but so easy. A keeper.

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: This is very good. I've made it a couple of times. Great with rice, pasta, bread or on its own. Keeps very well.

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: Very tasty ribs. The flavour was perfect! I'll be making these again.

name: our favourite lemon loaf
review: Yum! I took this to work and it was raved about. Mine stuck to the pan a bit, but that was my bad. I may not have greased it well enough and/or took it out too early. I was able to eat all the broken bits myself. Mmm

name: olive garden fettuccine alfredo
review: Delicious! One of my favourite pastas. A nice, creamy, garlicky and slightly cheesy sauce.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Yummy! This is a great mac and cheese recipe, no tweaking needed!

name: poverty meal
review: This was enjoyed by all. I do personally prefer a nice slow cooked bolognese sauce/ragout with my pasta but this will be a good option when I'm short on time. I like the chef's idea of adding fresh herbs.

name: kittencal s best deviled eggs
review: Great deviled eggs, enjoyed by all. A keeper. Kittencal's recipes are always reliable, and whenever I try a new one I know it will be good.

name: best banana bread
review: This is a great banana bread, this is now replacing my previous go-to recipe! This one uses white sugar instead of brown which my other one does, I like the 'lighter' flavour of this.

name: denny s style french toast
review: This is a great French toast recipe. It was easy and tasty. Will keep this as my go-to.

name: soft peanut butter cookies
review: I love this recipe! Delicious cookies. I added peanut butter and milk chocolate chips to the 2nd half of the batch. Otherwise followed the recipe exactly. Thank you for sharing. I will make these again!

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: These are without doubt the BEST Snickerdoodles I've ever had!! Rich, buttery and oh so soft. Pure perfection! I may have eaten 3 in one go!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: It was probably one of the worst meals I've made, and there was nothing we could do to make it taste better. It wasn't so bad that the dogs wouldn't eat it, but it was bad enough that my husband for it to never be made again.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: I can't get canned chopped chillies here in Australia, so I used jarred jalapeños and chopped them up. I only used about half the amount because I didn't want it to be too spicy for my kids but still have a little kick. Other than that, I followed the recipe exactly. My kids didn't love it, they still found it a bit spicy, but they tried it at least. I enjoyed it, but I don't think it will be a regular meal for us. I have had nicer enchiladas made with a kit. I feel I can still give a star rating as I'm not adding or leaving out anything, but rather subbing something that shouldn't change the recipe much in my opinion.

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: These are delicious! Especially when fresh out of the oven. The description is correct, they are chewy and fudgy. I found I needed to chill the dough. This helped keep the cookies from flattening too much, as the dough was very wet and didn't hold its shape at room temp. I also rolled the balls, coated them in as much powder sugar as possible and dumped them straight onto the tray, no flattening. They spread enough on their own. The best thing is they are so quick and easy to make.

name: oreo balls
review: I made these some time ago but only just reviewing now. I don't remember having any trouble making them, apart from making a bit of a mess. I did use chocolate chips to melt rather than bark which I couldn't find. I remember they were very, very rich and tasty and enjoyed by everyone.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: I made these exactly as written. I'd never tried biscuits before, as being from Australia, they are not a common thing. We do have the similar but sweet British scones, which are served with jam and cream. I used the food processor like the author, and found it to be easy. I did find the wet dough hard to work with as it kept sticking to my hands. I'd be grateful for any tips on this. I was also not sure if you are supposed to flatten the dough again between each fold. Like another reviewer stated, the ones I pieced together from the leftover dough turned out better than the first ones, which makes me think that a little kneading may be ok. I may have flattened the dough a little too much before cutting because mine weren't super tall. This may have partly been due to the cutter I used which was a Tupperware double sided one, where it has two different sized circles on each side. I used the bigger side, but it probably pressed the cut rounds down too much. I know an old trick with scones is to actually use a small drinking glass to cut the rounds and keep them nice and high. Mine cooked a little too fast, which I was prepared for as my oven runs hot. The taste was buttery and savoury, which was strange being used to sweet scones, but not unpleasant. This recipe is probably not something I'll make again but I enjoyed trying them.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: I've make this recipe a lot and everyone loves it! The biscuits on the top are amazing!

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: If this was the "worse" one, what was the worst? SMH.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: sorry left comment in wrong spot...

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: Absolutely wonderful recipe! I made these today for tomorrow's Thanksgiving meal. The dough had risen so high in the bread machine, that it stuck to the lid! No problem as it came right down upon taking it out of the pan. I made 20 larger rolls rather than 24. Thank you!

name: moist and tender turkey  or turkey breast
review: Here's another testamonial to this being the most moist turkey I have ever had. I was drawn to this recipe due to its simple ingredients and rave reviews. How could a turkey breast that only has butter, chicken broth and mayonnaise and isn't brined be really good? I followed the instructions and also doubled up on the gravy ingredients, as suggested. I deleted all of my other roast turkey recipes because this is the only one I'll use from now on.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Very yummy, quick and easy cake. My kids devoured it (I chose not to add nuts). Next time I might try the round pans instead of the 13x9, for ease of serving and storage.

name: lisa s swirled chocolate chip cookies
review: Wow! This recipe makes gorgeous cookies! The brown sugar gives them a beautiful flavour. I cooked them at 325 for 9-10 minutes as we like a soft, chewy cookie. I have made these with both milk and white chocolate and actually prefer the milk. I'll try a mixture of both next time!

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: I was apprehensive - campbell's soup with refried beans mixed in? Hmmmm... We made it and everyone liked it - we had company and left over THANSKGIVING TURKEY. It was great. A great use and much different spin on left over turkey. We put Rotel tomatoes and fresh Cilantro in between the layers. (I also used home made taco seasoning from this site). We also let it setup for about 5 min after taking it out of the oven. Dinner was quick and readily assembled. It was good. Everyone had seconds. We topped it with more tomatoes, sour cream and cilantro.

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: These were amazing! So, so tasty. Definitely for the peanut butter lover. We don't have graham crackers here so I used McVite's Digestive cookies which according to google is an acceptable substitute. I was eating the mixture while making them. I used baking paper for ease of removal and cutting, but they will definitely cut cleaner if they are chilled enough so both the peanut mixture and chocolate are solid, but without the chocolate being too hard. Keeping this recipe for sure!

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: Great pancakes, nice and light and fluffy, perfect amount of sweetness. This will replace my previous go-to recipe. The main differences are this one uses butter instead of margarine, and this has more baking powder, giving it more rise.

name: cheese enchilada chowder
review: This made a very tasty soup- one we'll be making again! I made this in the slow cooker and added chicken breasts which I shredded before serving.

name: best ever pumpkin pie
review: Best pumpkin pie I have ever made. Perfection. Used my mother's homemade pie crust.

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: Very tasty. Keeper recipe

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I was a bit worried about this one due to mixed reviews, but my family actually really enjoyed it, including me, the non pork eater. I paid attention to some of the tips. I cooked 6 chops, so I actually quadrupled the sauce. I used a 9x13 dish. The chops were swimming in the sauce. I probably could have done with doubling or maybe tripling, and I did cover them for 3/4 of the cooking time. I think the covering and extra sauce helped them stay juicy and not dry out. I also noticed the thicker chops (mine varied in thickness a bit) were more tender and fall apart. I would suggest nice thick chops. I will make this again.

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: Loved this! Excellent replacement for the traditional (gross) yams and marshmallows at thanksgiving.

name: french dip roast beef for the crock pot
review: Wow!! This came out perfect!! The only change I made was used 1 cup beef broth instead of bouillon (had on hand). Can't. Stop. Eating. Will make many times again!

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: Making cookies for a Christmas party cookie swap tonight. First recipe was a major fail, tasted good but looked horrible. Now I am short on time and still in need of cookies for tonight. So glad I came across this. I had everything on hand. They were quick and easy to throw together and baked up beautifully. They taste good, too! Next time I may try the adjustments that were posted in another review based on a recipe on the side of the cake mix box as my mix was just a tad on the greasy side. Thanks for saving the day!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Perfect! I doubled the recipe. Used a 17.6 oz. bag of Lumaca Rigata (from Costco), grated two 7.6 oz. wedges of Yancey's Fancy Jalapeno-Habanero cheese, added 1 cup of shredded Monterey Jack, and a pound of crumbled, crispy bacon. I omitted the salt because of the bacon, but would probably add 1/2 tsp the next time I make it. This is a great basic macaroni and cheese recipe! I don't understand the negative comments unless you don't know how to make a proper roux. (For all the beginning cooks, look it up! Youtube is a wonderful thing.) So much potential and the ability to make it your own by adding different ingredients. Thank you for sharing, Marie! Certainly a keeper in my house.

name: the best ever waffles
review: These are most definitely The Best Waffles I have ever made. I have made them several times and they always turn out crispy on the outside and fluffy on the inside. Tonight, I made these as "Brinner" (Breakfast for Dinner) and I subbed in buttermilk because I needed to use some up and they still turned out magnificently. Thank you for a great waffle recipe Cooking Creation.

name: amy sedaris s vanilla cupcakes
review: This review is for the cupcakes only. I made these tonight with children (3 and 6) I was babysitting. The family owns neither a mixer (hand or stand) nor measuring spoons. So we were hand mixing and eyeballing all the little measurements. I used all-purpose flour. I did add what I estimated to be an extra teaspoon of vanilla as well as a cup of mini chocolate chips that I had tossed in a little flour so they wouldn't sink. The kids helped from beginning to end with measuring and mixing. It made exactly 24 cupcakes and needed 21 minutes in their oven. The cupcakes rose beautifully, the tasted great, and were moist. And it is a very forgiving recipe since my little helpers were not always that. When they were cool enough to eat, it was the first quiet in the house since I picked the children up from school! Thanks bernrome!!

name: uncle bill s whipped shortbread cookies
review: Can't believe I haven't rated these yet, they are my go to shortbread recipe for the best five years! I always do the thumbprint jam ones as pictured and they are delicious. Just remember to press the thumbprint in before cooking or cookies will crumble. =)

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: Wonderful! Huge hit at our house.

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: I used 2 lbs of meat (1 beef, 1 sausage) so I also added a 15 oz can of tomato sauce. I knew I'd like it better with more seasoning so I also added onion powder, minced garlic, basil, oregano, salt and pepper. I put the cheese on top instead of mixing it and I cooked for 25 mins and then finished with 2 mins under the broiler.

name: breakfast casserole supreme
review: I made this for breakfast for a my family day after Christmas and it was well received. I omitted tomatoes just because at this time of year they are not that exciting and served it with Picante Sauce. I think seasoning the hash browns is pretty important, also.

name: individual cream cheese danish
review: Yum! I'm not a big fan of cresent dough so I used your filling and glaze recipe and puff pastry and it was just what I was wanting. Thanks for sharing your recipe!

name: gingerbread  for cookies or a  gingerbread house
review: 12/13/15 - rated five stars no comments. 12/28/16 - Still five stars, but I want to say this dough was easy to work with, and smelled wonderful for days. There was a little spread while baking, so next time I will reduce or omit the baking soda. Since last year we decided to make creating a gingerbread house an annual tradition for my family, so there will definitely be a next time!

name: homemade pie crust
review: Excellent recipe. Flakey and tender. I used all butter, put into the freezer for about 20 minutes, then grated on a box grater into mixture of flour and salt. Toss dry ingredients into grated butter. Add iced water until dough holds together. DO NOT overwork dough.

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: I made these for dinner tonight. I didn't make any changes and made the recipe as written. I didn't eat any but my family seemed to enjoy them. They gave them 4 stars.

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: I only had a couple hours to marinate this, but it was still SO flavorful! I love the herb combination and just needed to add a pinch more salt. We will definitely be using this recipe a lot. Thank you!!

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: I'm not the worlds biggest pork chop fan, but my fiancé loves them, so I decided to make these for him. However, I actually loved them too!! I deglazed the pan as advised and added a little white wine and chicken stock; it was to die for!! I served the sauce with the chops and mashed potatoes; a delicious filling dinner!

name: easy banana muffins
review: These are delicious. Love how easy they are to throw together and they made a great on the go breakfast!

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: Very tasty. I made these exactly as directed and used Sweet Baby Ray's for the sauce. That stuff is the bomb. We finished the ribs on the grill, time consuming but we don't have a broiler. Will make again.

name: sweet potato curry with spinach and chickpeas
review: We loved this recipe! I made a few tweaks as I was going... I added a red bell pepper as I had one going spare, and frozen spinach. The water evaporated and left it a little dry so next time I'll either make it in the slow cooker or add more water/ tomatoes. I also added more curry powder and cinnamon to boost the flavours. We really enjoyed this, thank you for posting!

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Great cookies. My oven runs hot, and I left them in just a bit longer than I should so they didn't come out as soft as I would have liked but they were still good. My second batch I ruined completely because I got distracted and they burned. No timer on my stupid oven, can't wait to get a new one!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Easy but terrific. Huge hit.

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: Faster than drive thru or take out and much better too! I served it with a salad and cheddar biscuits. Next time I may try it over angel hair pasta.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: I was sceptical about trying this because I don't usually like Italian sausages added to dishes such as spaghetti sauce or lasagne but I gave it a shot because of all the high ratings. The ratings were right, so flavourful and different! I think the quality of the sausages would make a big difference. I used Italian meatballs (made from sausage) I found in my supermarket. I also found the potatoes really absorbed all the yummy flavour and were my favourite part of the dish! I will add this soup to my folder to make again.

name: bestest hamburger soup
review: I pretty much followed the recipe, but used a little less ground beef and a little more tomato sauce (what I had). I also used frozen peas (instead of the split peas) and added a can of corn. On tasting, I felt the soup was a little bland, so I ended up using triple the spices and added 1 1/2 Tbs of worchestershire sauce. I also added about 1 1/2 Tbs of chicken soup base and 1/2 Tbs of sugar. Unlike a lot of reviewers, I did not find the soup overly salty and even added another 1/2 tsp of salt. When cooking, I sauteed the celery and carrots with some garlic while I was browning the ground beef, mixed the seasonings with the sauteed veggies and the beef, before mixing everything together and simmering for 30 minutes. I added the peas and corn with the pasta and simmered for another 15 minutes before turning off the heat and letting the soup sit for another 15 minutes. To finish with my changes, I did not add any parmesan at the end (my kids don't like it). The result was frankly something that we all liked, but didn't love. I am sorry that it wasn't more to our taste!

name: peanut butter no bake cookies
review: These are really good but SUPER sweet. I used natural peanut butter. Next time I will cut the sugar in half.

name: bacardi rum cake
review: Derf, rest in peace!

name: crock pot thai chicken thighs
review: KelBel, thanks for a great recipe!

name: cherry pie filling bread
review: Tastes like cherry cobbler!! Marie, thank you for another wonderful recipe!

name: ginger me up chicken  low fat honey   ginger chicken breasts
review: French Tart, thank you for your lovely recipe!

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: Deeeelish!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: This is a WONDERFUL chicken pie! So comforting and tasty especially for the winter months. The epitome of comfort food. I added some poultry seasoning , but otherwise followed the recipe as written. I love this pie breezer and it will be part of my comfort food repertoire. Than you for sharing.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Deeelicious!

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: This was a really great side dish for us tonight. My husband wanted more and was highly disappointed when I told him that there wasn't anymore. I think this would be fabulous with an Italian meal. I paired it with Picnic Chicken and Suddenly salad and it was delicious. Thank you Merlot!

name: cheese and garlic drop biscuits
review: These were absolutely delicious!! Marg, thank you so much for the recipe, I'll be making this one often!

name: skylike chili   skyline chili copycat
review: Delicious! One of my favorite variations on copycat Skyline Chili! I used a 28 oz can of tomato puree instead of the sauce it called for, and Certified Angus Beef ground beef .... absolutely delish! The second time I made it, I substituted one 14.5 oz. petite diced tomatoes, and one 6 oz. can Cento tomato paste. I made up for the loss of the additional liquid by adding more broth.

name: balsamic chicken thighs
review: So delicious! So simple! So fast! No crazy ingredients. But it tasted so exotic. DH loved it. Thanks.

name: meatloaf barbecue style
review: Wow what a lovely meatloaf this recipe makes Bev. Moist, tender and delicious. Quick and easy to make with excellent results. Thank you for sharing this lovely recipe, which we will enjoy again and again. Made for What's on the Menu? Tag Game.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: Love roasted cauliflower and this was a good variation. Used the ingredients called for. Only changes were to toss them in a bowl instead of a bag, used an ungreased baking sheet, and did not broil. I cooked it for about 20 minutes until it was close to my liking (I like mine really browned), sprinkled with parmesan and back in the oven about 5 more minutes.

name: spicy shrimp in coconut milk
review: Excellent! Omitted the water and used two full cans of coconut milk. Added extra seasonings as we like things spicy and flavorful. It was super quick to prepare and enjoyed by all. Thanks for another winner, MizzNezz

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Really tasty. I used an Instant Pot and pressure cooked it on the meat setting for 35 minutes. No problem using frozen meat that way since it heats up so quickly. I mashed it a bit before serving to smash up the chicken.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: I've made this several times. It's delicious!

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: EPIC!!! While it was in the oven, my husband said, "smells like garlic!" (He doesn't like it). He cleaned his plate!! A few notes to the negative reviews: I 'always marinate b/s breasts in some buttermilk prior to cooking, seems to help them hold moisture). I also cut the breasts in half to make them more equal thickness (doubtful you'll ever get a matching pair, haha!). I also used a wire rack above cookie sheet for airflow and keeping meat out of juices. These are things I do for almost every b/s breast recipe! I take for granted these adjustments. Usually makes every recipe perfect (adjust cooking time down slightly, too) As always, Kittencal's, a winner! Just sorry it took me SO long to try this one!!!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: The meatloaf itself is very good, but the sauce wasn't. The acv is too strong, and my kids refused to eat it.

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: Great recipe and a keeper. I used frozen blueberries that I rolled in flour. I put half my batter in pan spread the blueberries covered with remaining batter and add topping. Don't worry; the batter is very thick, but comes out just perfect.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: Amazing potatoes!! I used this homemade onion soup mix: http://www.food.com/recipe/homemade-dry-onion-soup-mix-110331 So easy to throw together (especially if you have a mandolin) and tasty!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: If I could give this more than 5 stars I would! The best brownies ever!! My additions were chocolate chip and marshmallows. YUM!!

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: These were really tasty and enjoyed by my whole family. They certainly didn't last long. The only downside to making these, is I found it to be a very messy process. There was a lot of cleaning up to do. It was worth it, however I don't think I'd find myself making these again because of how fiddly and messy they are. I'd probably rather buy them from my local bakery.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: Wow, I used this recipe to make cupcakes, and they turned out so tasty, soft and moist. I used kittencal's chocolate frosting recipe for the frosting. Perfect! Everyone loved them.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: Yum, I love alfredo and this didn't disappoint. Very easy and very tasty. I'll be saving this recipe to make again.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Beautiful frosting! Makes a good amount for up to 24 cupcakes. I used it for only 12 but I piled it on and ate some myself, hehe.

name: classic baked ziti
review: Nothing more to say. It's great.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Mmmm, these were divine! So good fresh out of the oven while still warm. Lovely with fresh blueberries, but I'd make these with frozen too when fresh ones are out of season or ridiculously expensive. They were nice and sweet, and the topping make a nice, crunchy coating.

name: yummy baked potato skins
review: I've tried Potato Skins a lot of different ways but these were definitely the BEST EVER!! Thank you so much for posting this. The seasoned oil is the secret -- don't skip it! SO good. Mmmm!

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: Both my husband and I enjoyed this, but unfortunately none of the kids did. Because of that, and the fact it was a lot of work for me (I made my own crescent roll dough from scratch because we can't buy store bought here) I probably wouldn't make it again. I have a bit of the chicken filling mix left because I must have misjudged the amount in the centre of each roll, and I plan on using it in twice baked potatoes because I loved the flavour so much.

name: wonderful salsa
review: Amazing salsa! First time I've made salsa, and I was impressed. I'm glad it makes a lot because it was a lot of work, especially with peeling and chopping all those tomatoes. Better than store bought.

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: OMG! I know this doesn't need another review...but dang!...this makes a great crispy wing...I cooked it as posted and didn't add a sauce...although I will next time...the hardest part of the recipe is making sure the wings are dry...I can't tell you how many paper towels I went through...Made this for the Best of 2016 tag game...Yum!!!

name: crock pot garlic brown sugar chicken
review: The ingredients all sounded good, but the dish came together to be rather bland. Maybe if I combined everything and used the oven instead, then the sauce would have some caramelization and would reduce? (I don't want to use my slow cooker, only to need to reduce the sauce on the stovetop.) We served this with broccoli over rice and had a nice dinner, if not something I would necessarily make again.

name: funky chicken with sesame noodles
review: While my husband and I thought this was nice, the kids didn't go crazy for this. I followed the recipe exactly. The noodles were tasty, but I didn't think they needed the sesame seeds, they were a bit too much for me. I also think veggies are needed, so I cooked some red pepper strips in the pan after the chicken was done. I probably wouldn't make this again as there are other dishes I like more.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Delicious! Loved the depth of flavor but these were sweet not strong. And best of all, this was SO EASY!!! Thank you for posting. (DH loved, LOVED them!)

name: impossible peanut butter cookies
review: The good thing about this recipe is that it's quick, easy, has few ingredients, and has less mess to clean. The bad, well, it tastes like what it is, peanut butter and sugar. While I do like peanut butter, I prefer that real, flour cookie taste and to me it's worth the extra effort, ingredients and mess. Also, I'm not rating this low because it didn't turn out for me, mine turned out ok and stayed together, I just think there's better recipes out there for peanut butter cookies.

name: individual cream cheese danish
review: Divine danishes! Thanks so much for a wonderful recipe ??

name: the best ever waffles
review: These were great waffles. I have a new top of the range waffle maker and this recipe worked well with it. I do find the recipe that came with the machine a bit easier, as it didn't involve beating the egg whites. I know that step made them lighter and fluffier on the inside, but I'd prefer quicker and easier early in the morning. I'm still giving it five stars though because I still think the fluffiness is worth the extra effort if that's important to you.

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: The flavor was good but the texture was tough. Next time I will drain the tomatoes. I will also drain the spaghetti squash strands in a colander after cooking them. There was just way to much liquid and it made for a mushy texture.

name: soft peanut butter cookies
review: We've made these twice and added chocolate chips both times. I've also added a bit more flour to the mix before shaping into balls as it was too sticky to shape. Definitely a winner with us!

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: I was surprised with this dish. I didn't expect such a simple recipe to taste so great and go down so well with the fam. My youngest son had three servings, which is unusual. Great recipe, and a definite keeper. Thank you!

name: eloise s easy sugar cookies
review: We really enjoyed these cookies! I tweaked it slightly by doing half brown sugar and half granulated, and adding cinnamon. I baked ours for 7 minutes and they were golden. Thanks for posting!

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review: These were very good. I thought they could use a bit more salt, but that could just be me. Quick marinating time and quick cooking time. Perfect for a weeknight.

name: sweet bacon wrapped venison tenderloin
review: We hadn't had venison in years. A dear friend gave us some so I was looking for ways to make it. Anything with bacon in the name sounds good to DD. So the outcome surprised me. DH really liked it, but DD didn't care for it at all. I didn't eat any, but as far as the cooking goes, it was fairly simple to make with only a few ingredients. I lined the pan under the rack with foil, so clean up was fairly easy.

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Oooooh yeah! Yum! Thanks for the keeper recipe!

name: gumbo
review: This is our favorite gumbo. No okra!

name: quick spanish rice
review: We loved this quick rice recipe. I added onions and bell peppers but omitted the butter. Definitely one we'll make again!

name: awesome homemade crusty bread  bread machine
review: Awesome is right. The softest textured bread of all that I have tried in my bread machine. I have finally found "the one". Love

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: I have made many times, with rave reviews! I used a rotisserie chicken. Perfect!!!!

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: These are super tasty. I did have to make a few changes based on items I had on hand. I used a dash of orange extract, I reduced the sugar to half cup, added 1/2 cup applesauce and more blueberries. I liked them and so did the kids - thanks

name: best banana bread
review: This truly is the best - I'm sure it's all the butter, but it's delicious!! I cooked a bit longer in a stoneware pan, but as long as the middle didn't come out gooey with a toothpick, I knew when it was done. I let it cool in the pan.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: I've never tried Panera Bread, as we don't have it here (Australia). I made this exactly as written, didn't change a thing. It was absolutely amazing! I love broccoli and cheese so I enjoyed the flavour. The consistency was great. My husband also loved it. I'll be seeing this recipe in my recipe box to make again.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I've been making this for years. I've done it completely on the stove, in the oven (for 40 minutes), with and without a bone. I've passed it onto a friend who makes it on a regular basis for her family. I think the leftover meat would be great in Sue Lau's Chinese Fried Rice.

name: best ever  and most versatile  muffins
review: Not necessarily the best and it is the most versatile

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: The skin was so good.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: This is a good, easy frosting. I also used 3 cups of sugar and felt that it was the right amount of sweetness. I also usually use 1 Tbs of whipping cream instead of the 1 tsp milk. This is my go-to frosting recipe and always gets raves! Thank you!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Not fair for me to rate this yet. I used it as a springboard to mix leftover deli chicken, salsa, black beans, corn, a handful of grated cheddar, and cream cheese in a casserole and heated it in the microwave and served it over rice. Fast and yummy. DH thought it was delicious too. Even my 5 year-old granddaughter (sometimes very picky eater) gobbled it up. I'm looking forward to preparing it as written, at which time I will give it my (I'm sure) thumbs up rating. Thanks.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: Very delicious! Inexpensive to shop for and easy to make; this is definitely a keeper. Thank you for this tasty way to incorporate more veggies in our diets!

name: bakery style chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: These made for some lovely chocolate chip cookies, light, tender, soft, chewy and delicious. I took them to a family event and boy were they devoured. The kids couldn't get enough of this tasty treat. Thanks for making me look like a star. Made for What's on the Menu Tag game.

name: strawberries   cream bread  strawberry or blueberry
best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: I thought I had all the ingredients, but I didn't have the can of cream of chicken soup I thought I did. So my review will not be 100%, sorry. I used can of cream of broccoli soup instead. The casserole was fabulous, I think it was the best I've had in years. I served it with a tossed salad and thinly sliced cooked carrots. Next time I'll use the cream of chicken :)

name: addictive mexican stew
review: Very hearty, sustaining stew. Easy

name: yeast free bread
review: I did feel it was more like an Irish soda bread, but we enjoyed it just the same. I cooked it for 30 minutes instead of 40 because I cut the recipe in half. I put melted butter with garlic on the top after it cooked about half way. Thank you for sharing.

name: thick  soft  and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: These were great! Made exactly as written and used silpat liner.

name: bread maker hamburger buns
review: Update 2: made with ~5 TBL butter, 2C white wheat Flour, 1 C bread flour, 1 C AP flour - added 2 TBL gluten + 1 TBL dry milk powder. makes 12 big buns...(UPDATE 3 - prior notes - make perfect buns.) Update: Made this with just the 1/3 C oil and it was still plenty. Did 1/2 and 1/2 AP flour and white wheat flour + a bit of gluten to help along the wheat. My neighbor who ate these said they were amazing. I thought there were good - but not yet amazing. Original : I made this as written. Next time I'm going to reduce the oil quite a bit and see what happens. I liked this recipe - super simple. Thanks!

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: Needed a basic Salisbury Steak recipe and found this one. I frankly didn't have the canned soup on hand so I significantly deviated from the recipe, cobbling things together with bullion cubes so I will make it the next time as described but my DH loved it on a cool spring day.

name: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
review: These are good but Peanut Butter Chocolate Chunk Cookies (on this site) is a better recipe because those are more peanut buttery.

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: We prefer this recipe because the other recipe we used needed evaporated milk.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Total keeper! I seasoned the flour with a little garlic powder and cayenne, used half cheddar and half velveeta. I did this because those were the flavors I was wanting and just used this recipe as a base recipe. Thank you for the perfect instructions. I'm excited to try different kinds of cheese and seasonings.

name: philly cheesesteak sandwich     authentic
review: Epic FAIL! This is NOT Philly Cheese Steak. Deli Roast Beef - are you kidding me.

name: peanut butter no bake cookies
review: I reduced the sugar by 1/4 c & used light brown sugar. Excellent twist to chocolate no bake cookies. Thanks for sharing.

name: easy banana muffins
review: Whenever the bananas look ripe

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Oh my gosh! NEVER will I buy it again. I always have the ingredients on hand. So simple yet so rich in flavor! THank you for a Blue Ribbon Sauce!

name: cinnamon muffins
review: I quiet agree charlotte

name: berry smash muffins  strawberry muffins
review: Strsawberry fields forever

name: pronto pups aka corn dogs
review: Must try

name: lemon tea cookies
review: Must try

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Wow, I made these with the sauce recipe in the description. Perfection! The meatballs, which were mixed and rolled with the help of my 7 year old son (he had a ball) came out perfectly, flavourful and tender. I followed the recipe to a tee and served them with spaghetti. I don't know why some commenters are so worried about broiling or cooking the meatballs first. You don't need to, it's just a waste of valuable time. Mine stayed together just fine. The trick, I think is to make the meatballs first and let them sit for a bit while you start the sauce so the breadcrumbs can absorb the egg and juices which in my opinion helps bind them together. Also, just gently drop each ball into the sauce and don't stir for a while until they are cooked. The raw meatballs, as I read in another comment are also supposed to help flavour the sauce as they cook. I can certainly agree with that. I am keeping this recipe to make again and I will continue to make it as written. This is one of those very rare meals that pleases everyone in my fussy family.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: I made it mostly as directed, except I used tater tots. That's because you can't get frozen shredded hash brown potatoes in Australian supermarkets and I didn't want to spend the time shredding, rinsing and par-cooking fresh potatoes. It turned out very well though, I really loved the flavour. It was maybe a little salty, so next time I won't add salt, but I will make it again.

name: tilapia
review: I, too, was a bit worried about my husband's reaction to the addition of cayenne....but on previous reviewer's (Jon Edwards) comment,I followed recipe to a "T". He LOVED it! I thought it was a great change of taste for tilapia...will definitely make again! Thanks for giving me a super easy, fast addition to dinner choices!!!

name: buttered egg noodles  best ever
review: Extremely greasy, too much butter. Thumbs down.

name: grilled cauliflower
review: I made this for my family for dinner tonight. Their reviews weren't what I expected. My husband, who really likes cauliflower, just thought it was just okay. My daughter, who typically isn't a huge fan of cauliflower, loved it. And the remaining could give or take it.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: This was great, the italian seasoned meat added a lot. I saved the rest to make the lasagna on a different day...my hubby thought it tasted like it was from Buca Di Beppo's!

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: You must really like your friend Pete to dedicate a recipe for him what a honor

name: the best ever waffles
review: I agree with Sara fish

name: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
review: Alicia have a drink

name: kittencal s scalloped potato and ground beef casserole
review: Kittencal you did it again. A winner

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: This is a great recipe! The cookies turned out perfectly. The only change I made was to substitute coconut oil for the shortening. Otherwise made as directed. Yummy!

name: kittencal s famous coleslaw
review: I'm not the world's biggest coleslaw fan, but my fiancé is so I made this for him. However, even I loved this!! This is amazing! The sauce is out of this world good, so creamy and well balanced flavour wise. Delicious!

name: chocolate mint candy  fudge
review: well om no 100

name: my no roll pie crust
review: Turned out really well and was so easy! I do agree with other reviewers that you can cut down on the salt, which I will be doing next time, particularly with a sweet pie. I made an apple pie with this and it was fantastic!

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: Amazing! I can't believe I made something so good! I followed the recipe as directed and it came out perfect. A keeper for sure.

name: wonderful salsa
review: Joshua look it up on food com

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Perfect basic mac and cheese. The whole family loves it! We used good quality sharp cheddar and a added the milk slowly to get a perfect roux. I also removed it from the heat to stir the cheese in so it didn't overheat and get gritty.

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: These turned out great! I made them as rolls. The dough was the right consistency in the bread machine. They were sweet, but tasty. The kids loved them with dinner and have asked me to make them again.

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Recipe is amazing. I won't toss out my old meatball recipe in case I need meatballs @ a faster rate (I cook mine in the oven), but this will hopefully become my go to! I read a few reviews to help me out. I cut the recipe in half & used 1/2 lean ground turkey & 1/2 chicken Italian sausage. I needed 1/2 cup whole wheat bread crumbs to hold them together. I added Italian seasoning & oregano, and used dried parsely. Recipe made about 14 meatballs, using a cookie scoop I used my own sauce recipe. I seared the meatballs in olive oil, and waited till the sauce was warm (or warm enough!) before dropping the meatballs in! I also tried not to stir for a good 1/2 hour to let the meatballs cook. Amazingly, my sauce was extra tasty as well as the meatballs being very tender & juicy. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: quick and easy pizza dough
review: Wow! I honestly didn't expect it to be this good. This easy. It was. I am so going to put this into a regular rotation. It's just fantastic. My kids could make it. That easy. Thank you!

name: kittencal s pizza sauce
review: So... as a kid I used to peel the cheese back on my pizza, scrape off the sauce and put the cheese back. Not a sauce fan. I am now. I tasted it. Then I went back for another. And another. I could have just poured this stuff in a bowl and gone to town. It. Is. Amazing. My husband and kids know "Kittencal." But this recipe... even blew my Kittencal expectations. Best. Pizza. Ever. Thank you! (I hope you are doing well, Kittencal.)

name: sausage gravy
review: While we thought this was good, it did lack in flavor. Next time I will definitely add some seasoning in addition to the pepper.

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: This rib recipe has hundreds of rave reviews for good reason -. the result is flat-out fabulous. Next time I'm going to double it and use Kittencal's Famous Barbecue Sauce. Blessing on you Beth for sharing such a perfect creation.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: I used this homemade onion soup mix: http://www.food.com/recipe/homemade-dry-onion-soup-mix-110331 My oven was at a higher temperature (400 degrees F) because that was the temp my main dish needed to cook at. Even at the higher temp. my potatoes were not quite done and required an additional 10-15 minutes bake time. But they turned out fine and the family liked them.

name: easy pizza pasta casserole  oamc
review: This is amazing! Love how easy it was to make and it made so much, we're set for months of delicious dinners with it portioned up and frozen!

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: These were sooo yummy. I enjoyed making these. My 7yo son helped ice and decorate them. We used blue icing and sprinkles. I took some into work, and they went fast. I took home an empty container that afternoon.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: This was a good pizza crust. I made cheese, pepperoni and meat pizzas. I could have made it a bit thicker on the edges, but it was still good.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: These were very tasty and easy - no peeling required. Ill definitely make them again.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: This was very yummy, but I probably wouldn't go to the trouble of making it again, a lot of chopping. If I have a craving for it again I will probably order from the Chinese restaurant, lol. It was fun though and worth trying.

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: My husband loved this. I loved the texture but didn't love the flavour of the spices. Mine did break, but I know that was my fault for not allowing it to cool enough in the pan. I'm giving it 5 stars anyway, its a great recipe and nice and healthy. If I try it again I'd probably try my own combo of spices in it.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Thank you so much for this recipe. My husband said they were the best. I followed the recipe & I thank you for such great directions. I used a large cutter so I only got 5 biscuits but they made good sandwiches. I baked @ 400 for 10 minutes & that was enough--not sure what was up with the difference? But glad I watched them carefully. Thank you again!

name: banana oatmeal bread
review: The oatmeal adds such great texture and flavor to this bread, easy and great way to use up those bananas that our turning fast.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: This one is keeper; we loved it. I followed other suggestion; bought the heat up to finish it off as well as a tsp of Sambal Oelek. Thanks for sharing.

name: awesome slow cooker pot roast
review: One of the first slow cooker roasts I learned to make many years ago. Like a reliable old friend.

name: crock pot   style loaded baked potato soup
review: Easy to prepare, everyone enjoyed it! Thanks. I loved that I could toss it in the crock pot, leave for awhile and just dump in a few ingredients, stir it up and voila - the meal is on the table!

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: My husband and I really loved these. My kids weren't super fans... they did like them better after I cut them into small pieces and mixed it with the sauce and pasta... that was a disappointment because they are really great and very flavorful. We did bake them in the oven, and seeing how much oil came off them, I think that would be my preferred cooking method to reduce fat. Also, I'd like to experiment with the baking temp and time, they did seem a titch dry... but hey, 5 stars delicious!

name: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
review: Delicious! I wasn't expecting to like the icing (seemed strange to use flour), but it was really good! I used 2 c. powdered sugar instead of 1 so it is a little sweeter.

name: balsamic chicken thighs
review: Not bad but not our favorite

name: best banana bread
review: Always always comes out perfect!! My family can't get enough. I have to make 2 loafs. I always use frozen (defrosted ahead of time of course) bananas. :)

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: Not bad but not very flavorful

name: thai chicken breasts
review: Fabulous and Fast! Loved the taste and it went together so easily. Made it for a company dinner and was able to prep things so that it was done in a flash and didn't need any of my concentration while visiting with my guests. They all loved it! DH said it deserved more than 5 stars! (Disclaimer: I didn't have white wine vinegar and substituted apple cider vinegar. I thought it was really good but I'll try it the correct way next time.) We'll be making this again and again. Thanks.

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: I cubed my potatoes before cooking. While the potatoes were cooking I cooked the sausage (I used a vegetarian sausage because we have both vegetarian and carnivores in our family.) This came together quite easily and everyone enjoyed it. Steamed broccoli would be the perfect side to this dish.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: Use the lamb....ground or minced if you can! I also added some fresh minced Rosemary. Also mixed some Parmesan cheese into the potato topping. Even those who hate lamb love this.....with the lamb! Lamb adds a subtle sweetness to the casserole. My husband couldn't stop having spoonfuls of the filling "for appetizers" as I was making. (I make full recipes and then portion out into smaller freezer meals because there are only two of us). We have three meals of potatoes, only two of this filling....!!! Use good lamb, good wine and fresh veggies. And the recipe calls for no salt. None needed!!!!

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: Too bland

name: fresh strawberry cake
review: Excellent, easy and fresh. I had to use 1 cake pan because it did not yield enough for two. gonna make it again for July 4th.

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: We inhaled these! It was me and hubby on July 4th. I left out all the sugar and old bay. I also baked at 325 for 3 hours. Next time I will salt the ribs first. I had never made ribs before and very glad I picked this one to try. Will not use anything else! Thanks so much for an awesome recipe.

name: easy cole slaw
review: Just like momma makes!

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Excellent meatballs. I mixed ground turkey and ground beef and they were delicious. First I baked them then put into spaghetti sauce and it all worked great!!

name: easy fried rice
review: Wow, my family loved this rice! I even realized that I was out of carrots so I left them out and it was still delicious! Great, easy recipe :)

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: This was a bit rich for my personal taste. I probably would have preferred the devils food cake mix on its own. The choc chips and pudding made it too chocolatey and heavy for me. Others in the family enjoyed it, but I won't make it again. It was a very easy recipe, and quick to make, I'll give it that.

name: 5 minute vegan pancakes
review: Agree that the baking soda is too much. I won't make these again.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: This is amazing! The tastiest cauliflower I have ever had. Can't cook it any other way now. The roasted garlic and rosemary flavour just goes so nicely with the cauliflower, and the roasting gives it the nicest crispy on the outside but juicy inside texture.

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: These moist muffins have an excellent flavor, especially warm from the oven. I had the batter mixed up by the time the oven had preheated.

name: crock pot ham and beans
review: Wanted something hearty, but did not want to heat up the kitchen in this hot weather. And decided to give this a try. I used a mix of both pinto and navy beans, and soaked over night. Had left over ham so used that instead of ham hocks and followed the directions. Beans were done at the time directed and the flavor was hearty and delicious, We did add garlic and wish I'd followed another reviewers advise and added some stewed tomatoes just because we like them. Served with home made sourdough bread and made for an easy, filling meal and didn't heat up the kitchen. A versatile recipe that can easily be adjust to personal taste.

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: This was delish, and it would have been even better if I had realized I was out of lemon before I made it! Other than that followed the recipe using the mayo option (avocado oil mayo, if that matters to anyone). I missed out on crispy skin because I used the InstantPot for this (it was 105 outside... no thanks), but my bone in chicken breasts were done in about 12 minutes, so it was worth the trade off. Thanks for sharing!

name: chewy granola bars
review: Very good! Made as written with non-hydrogenated margarine (Parkay).

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: AH-MAZING! Made this for a party we hosted & it was a 'hit!' Absolute keeper. Thanks for sharing!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Yummy. I mixed the blueberry with 1 cup of the flour so they didn't sink. Took about 25 minutes in my silicone muffin cups. Made 20 muffins.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: As written it is too dry. I would add lots more tomato sauce.

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: I won't give this a star rating because I changed it by necessity (no cheddar cheese soup available here) I just improvised and used the chicken coup and cream cheese. Turned out nice.

name: best grilled pork chops
review: I'm not a fan of pork, but my family loved these and want me to make them again.

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: I thought this tasted better than KFC. Something special about things that are home made! Will keep this recipe to make again.

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Bound to be a keeper-this one! The whole family found it scrumptious! What a cool combination of flavors-so filling and satisfying! Thank you very much!

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: My husband and I thoroughly enjoyed this delicious recipe. I basically followed the recipe but I had to make a substitution and use shredded Parmesan. I made fresh bread crumbs and just threw the shredded Parmesan into the processor with the bread so it would have a texture similar to the grated. I butterflied our shrimp because they were really jumbo. Lightly battered as directed and put them on a foil lined and lightly oiled pan before drizzling with the butter. I baked them about 13-14 minutes. I will be making this one again and again!

name: thick  soft  and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: These were okay looking and okay tasting. I'll keep looking for my perfect chocolate chip cookie.

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: These turned out very well considering I have an unreliable oven for now. I saved half the dough in the fridge an made them up a couple of days later. Both batches were just as good as each other.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This recipe obviously doesn't need another 5 star rating but I'm going to give it one anyway. It's great! I haven't experimented with different salsas yet but that would be fun. I have used frozen corn instead of canned and that works great. I also typically use reduced fat cc and it tastes wonderful! I often only use 3 chicken breasts so it's more saucy. Serve it on a bed of rice or in a tortilla! Thanks for this gem of a recipe I'm sure I'll be making it often!

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: I thought these were tasty. I reduced the sugar and subbed applesauce for the butter. I will add nuts next time however at the kids request I didn't this time. I also only used 2 bananas I had previously frozen.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: This was really good! It was a bit difficult cooking but that may have been due to the fact I live at over 10,000 feet and nothing cooks the same up here. After about an hour and 15 minutes at 350 it was a soupy mushy mess but I managed to get it out of the loaf pan mostly intact and transferred to a sheet pan and put it back in at 425 for a half hour on and it ended up coming out pretty nicely. Overall we really enjoyed the flavor and will definitely make again with a few minor adjustments.

name: brown rice and lentil casserole
review: Easy, hearty, filling, healthy and yummy. Added just a little salt and pepper. Nothing to it.

name: best albondigas soup
review: Wonderful soup, the meatballs are great! I didn't realize I was out of diced tomatoes which I usually keep on hand, so used a can of tomato sauce and it was still so good.

name: pizza dough and sauce
review: We made the crust part of this recipe (not the sauce). I thought it was good, but my hubby did not care for the half white/half wheat idea, which is what we made. I will try and review again using all white flour and also after making the sauce.

name: crock pot apple butter
review: So good and so easy, using the crock pot makes it so simple, I made a couple of very minor tweaks, but for the most part followed the recipe. So smooth and taste just like I want apple butter with just the right amount of spice. When finished I canned in a water bath and know these are going to go fast

name: easy stir fry sauce
review: I thought this was really good. I used it on stir fried vegetables. Thanks for sharing.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: This was good, very good! I think the topping may be better on chicken, will have to try that next time!

name: basil pesto
review: Entirely too much lemon. Needs salt and pepper. I think I'll stick with the recipe that came with my cuisinart.

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: So very easy & super delicious!!!

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: I happen to love this recipe and from the amount of reviews I, also, come here for the intellectual discourse.

name: 24k carrots
review: too sweet

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: I do love balsamic vinegar and this was very good, but next time I'll just use all balsamic and never mind the red wine vinegar. (I've been known to sneak a spoonful of balsamic vinegar now and then as a little treat!) I didn't have brown sugar, and used "raw" sugar instead. Made for your fabulous football win 2017!

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: Hallelujah the recipe is in the house! Let me say, I've never cared for tuna...anything. In fact, as I child ~ I got ill from it. For some 'odd' reason ~ this hit me like a ton of bricks! I wanted a 'tuna casserole' and this is the one I picked by having so many reviews. And....let me tell you, the cows and goats, and even the chickens were dancing around from the delight of this UN-pretentious, but soul-y gratifying taste. I flowed with the recipe, and decided to add 'peas' to the mix. So ....there you have it, another grand review of a grand recipe. Thank you!

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: This dressing is so quick and easy to make, and very yummy, too! I love that it uses ingredients that I always have on hand. I used a local olive oil company's balsamic vinegar and olive oil. I often use their flavored balsamic vinegars in my salad dressings, so I can't wait to try them with this recipe. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper. **Made for 2017 Football Pool**

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: These were a little tedious to make, but they came out delicious! The chicken was a little bland, so I would recommend sprinkling a little salt on the chicken pieces before wrapping with the bacon.

name: banana banana bread
review: Perfect! I had to bake mine an additional 15 mins.

name: crispy baked chicken leg quarters  very easy  one dish
review: I’ve never cooked with chicken quarters before. This was straightforward and simple, and it had good flavor. All of the kids except our two year old ate this well. I will make it again.

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: Didn't realize that we were out of Dill until the potatoes were already cooking. So, we just left it out. It did take a lot longer than ten minutes for the potatoes to cook. But when they were finally done, they were pretty darn tasty!

name: magnolia bakery s vanilla birthday cake and frosting
review: Review for frosting only: It was too sweet. I've never made a frosting with such a high sugar to butter ratio before, I could taste the powdered sugar rather than frosting. That said, it made plenty, was creamy, and easy to use.

name: opal s pumpkin pie
review: I would give this more than 5 stars if I could! Pumpkin pie is my favorite and this is the best I've ever had. Everyone who ate it on Thanksgiving agreed. I'm replacing my old favorite recipe with this one! Update: 11/22/17 Wow, I can’t believe I’ve been making this pie for ten years now. That’s a true testament to just how good this recipe is.

name: slow cooker beef short ribs
review: Very good, super easy. It's a really tangy sauce from the vinegar, which I liked.

name: easy  festive chocolate holiday pretzels
review: So fun and easy to make. Very festive looking with very little effort! I love the sweet and salty combination.

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: Wow, did we ever enjoy the shrimp prepared this way. Thank you so much for sharing this wonderful recipe that has made it into my Best of Cookbook for 2017. Kudos to you... The shrimp were incredible, perfectly cooked, flavorful and had a wonderful texture. Made for What's on the Menu? Tag Game.

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: Good stuff! Basically brought back someone sick back from the dead.

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: Nice! Not overly sweet like some versions tend to be, and a lovely, cake-like texture. Because we don't care for milk chocolate, we used semisweet chips. We made 3/4 recipe, as we had only 3 bananas, it made four mini-loaf pans, baked for 40-45 minutes instead of an hour. I suspect next time we'll be adding some ground canela ancho chile powder.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Best recipe for cauliflower EVER.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: When I was looking at this recipe my husband said "Nuts on fish? Can you just leave them off?" So I put them in the blender until they were close to the same consistency as the bread crumbs. He didn't realize they were on there until I told him. We all enjoyed it this way.

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: I halved this recipe using fresh tuna and adding a little salt and pepper in order to see if we liked them. I didn't want to waste my salmon in case no one liked them. I liked the salmon patties but found them a bit bland. The husband actually liked them but suggested more flavor. I decided to use up all of my salmon and re-made this recipe adding in chiles, onion powder and a dash of chile flakes. Thank you so much for the recipe!

name: pumpkin pie dip
review: I made this to take to a pot luck lunch at work. It's the first time I've come home with a container that's almost as full as it was when I brought it. I served it with green and red apple slices, graham crackers and fresh pineapple. I have to admit, I really didn't care for it when I tried it myself, and I typically like most things pumpkin. My daughter thought it was okay though.

name: tilapia
review: This was super easy and very tasty. I was a bit afraid the cayenne would be too spicy, but it wasn't. I made the recipe as written, but I did pour the remaining butter/lemon onto the fish for a little extra moisture. The baking time was spot on. This is a keeper for sure.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: I was very happy with them but I prefer my brownies to be chewier so I’m trying to figure out what to change next time. I omitted the nuts and added a cup of milk chocolate chips instead. I also used butter instead of shortening. I used a glass 9x13 pan and baked them for 33 minutes.

name: the cheesecake factory pumpkin cheesecake by todd wilbur
review: I made this to take to a Christmas party this weekend. I had roasted a fresh pumpkin and made pumpkin puree to use instead of canned. I was uncertain of baking a cheesecake without a water bath, but it turned out great! Done perfectly at 60 minutes with no cracking at all!

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: UPDATE 2: I make these every Xmas... I read that cookies put in fridge bake better - and due to timing left in fridge overnight. When I baked them cold - they STUCK to the pan - so need to use parchment if you are going to cool the dough. They were not flat - did not spread and were thicker and chewier due to the cold dough. (which we like). UPDATE: I've made these about 8 times now - and use all the sugar all the time... I've begun to soak and plump my craisins too-- thanks for that suggestion! Everyone LOVES these cookies!!! I used my cookie scooper and had no trouble with flattening cookies or too plump cookies. I got 28 cookies and 12 minutes was a good time - except after the cookie sheets were hot - the second round in the oven (last few cookies) got a bit overdone - probably should reduce a minute or two if using the cookie sheets a second time... UPDATE to the UPDATE - Turn down the oven a bit and cook them a bit longer so the butter doesn't melt and spread out and make flat / ugly cookies....

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: A ripper chicken marinade...fab served with a simple Asian coleslaw. I think everything has already been said...try it, you will not be disappointed! I doubled sauce ingredients and ginger and used 1.7kg thighs. I only had sweet basil but next time will try with Thai basil and add more chilli for an extra kick.

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: These were very good. I followed the recipe exactly and had no issues. I noticed other people said the dough was too wet. I did NOT sift my flour and just scooped it from the bag, so that might have been the difference between the dough being too wet or not. The recipe did not say what to do with your scraps after your first cuts. I balled them up, kneaded them and then rolled it back out and cut again. They came out just as good as the first cuts. Thanks, Brian

name: stuffed green bell pepper soup
review: I did tweak to what I had on hand.. but otherwise would have made to recipe. It ended up been a very nice soup...Will make it again

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: this picture is worth a million words

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: This was delicious and I will definitely make again. The consistency was cheesy and creamy. Next time, I might try adding a few more veggies (Maybe peas?) and a little less cheese.

name: do at home onion rings
review: this iswhat l did

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: Perfect.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: These were amazing! I doubled the butter, used 2 heads of roasted garlic and used light cream instead of milk. Best mashed potatoes ever!

name: zesty italian crescent casserole
review: This was OK, as written it wouldn't have enough flavor. I made as directed with the exception of using pizza sauce and adding pepperoni. I presented it to my kids as "upside down pizza". I added garlic powder and oregano to the topping (melted the butter before brushing on top) and a lot of seasoning to both the meat and the cheese. It was good, but not over the top amazing that I would anticipate based on the reviews. It is a quick meal when you only have a few things on hand, but they were not ready for a repeat. Thanks for sharing, it's always a challenge finding a recipe that everyone, including the kids enjoy!

name: uncle bill s whipped shortbread cookies
review: These turned out so light and delicate. I left out the cherries and added the optional vanilla. I baked one half of the dough recipe plain and the other half I added two bags of chai tea. Both were delicious! Thanks for sharing.

name: thai coconut rice
review: Excellent! The only change I made was using brown basmati, so I double the cooking time. Loved it! Thanks for the recipe.

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: Wow, what a great recipe - Baby Kato was right to include this in her Best of 2017 list! The shrimp were super easy to prepare (and fast!) with ingredients always in stock at my house. This would be a wonderful entree to prepare for guests, or just as an easy weekday dinner like tonight! Thanks for posting!

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: These are so yummy and crispy...I just squeezed a bit of lemon juice on them...they are a keeper...made for "the best of 2017" tag game...

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: Ok, I made this and thought it was just "okay" fresh out of the oven. Then I let it sit in the refrig a few days and oh, my! what a difference! It was so much better after sitting a few days, I could hardly believe it. So much more taste, and it was really good. I certainly shall make this again, but always, always in advance so it has a chance to "ripen". Thank you.

name: sausage gravy
review: This was so easy and delicious! It didn’t look very pretty because I used hot Italian sausage and it made the gravy a weird orange color, but it tasted really good and I’ll definitely make it again sometime.

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: Delicious! Followed the recipe but sprinkled smoked paprika on top for color and cooked at 400*. Used the same pan to boil the cauliflower and then make the sauce. Used 1 cup 1% milk and 1/3cup half and half. Old English cheddar from Trader Joe’s. Even better the next day.

name: kittencal s salisbury steak
