review: This is wonderful. I didn't have I used regular cream of mushroom soup because that is all I had. I did cut way down on the onion soup mix. This is a keeper. It is even better the next day. Thanks again for a great recipe.

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: This is really fabulous. I followed the recipe exactly other than using seasoned bread crumbs (what I had) and not having lemon so dribbling some bottled lemon juice over the top before serving. I will definitely be making these again, especially for company. SO EASY! Going into my Best of 2018 file!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Felt that it needed tomato paste or tomato sauce

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: This was so good! I only encountered one issue and it was my fault. I left out the onions because my husband won’t eat them and I only cooked the carrots for 2 mins before adding the meat. Next time I’ll cook the carrots for at least 5 mins before adding meat because they were too hard. Also I will probably add some fresh garlic.

name: pumpkin gooey butter cake   paula deen
review: Baked in a round springform pan and topped it pecans and caramel when serving.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: Delicious! I have tried many versions of hash brown casseroles and this version was perfect for breakfast/brunch. Very creamy, not overpowering, and not too cheesy or heavy. My husband said it was very close to the restaurants version. I was afraid it would be too dry by not adding in extra liquid, but it came out perfectly. I did bake at 375 and for the last 10 minutes of cooking time I upped it to 400 to get a little browning on top. I didn't have cream of chicken, so I had to use cream of mushroom and added in a few dashes of chicken bouillon. It was great this way, but next time I will for sure make it with the cream of chicken to be more authentic. Thanks for the recipe!

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: For sure one of the best shrimps recipes! The preparation was super easy and the result superb! We enjoyed this over spaghetti!

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: This was good. We weren't crazy about the breadcrumbs on top. Next time I may try panko or leave the breadcrumbs out all together.

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: The wings are not crispy at all.

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: Next time, I may reduce the amount of water. Otherwise, I'd keep everything the same. Served with French green beans and rices vegetable pilaf.

name: old fashioned banana cream pie
review: Amazing!!! I had no idea how simple it was to put together and is a million times better than anything that I could buy from the bakery. Awesome recipe :)

name: my no roll pie crust
review: I am so happy with this recipe. It really was so simple to put together. I made it for a banana cream pie. The slightly salty-sweet crust really complimented the sweet custard so well! Thank you so much for sharing.

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: WOW! These shrimp really did live up to the reviews. I used panko bread crumbs so they would be extra crispy. I'm not a fan of frying foods so these baked shrimp were perfect for us. Definitely will be a repeat at our house.

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: This is even better the next day. I chopped the onion instead of leaving it in rings. Next time I may add sunflower seeds and raisins or dried cranberries.

name: easy creamy sour cream chicken casserole
review: DH loved this! I used leftover turkey breast meat and half the butter. SOOOO easy! But it looked so fancy. Thanks.

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: Absolutely delicious!! I loved this style for cooking shrimp. The shrimp were crispy on the outside and very tasty! Next time, I'll skip adding salt since the Parmesan provides enough. Thank you for a great recipe! A winner for sure!

name: leftover mashed potato pancakes
review: This is very much like the pancakes that my mom used to make for meatless Fridays. Great with onions in the mix, adds a bit of sweetness....but no cheese. Always loved them!!

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: This was yummy! I subbed plain Greek yogurt for the sour cream and garlic for the onions as I can't eat onions. Both my boys ate it!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: This recipe REALLY doesn't need any more positive reviews lol. I made this with hot Italian chicken sausage, ground. I also halved the recipe (it was very easy to cut in half!). I used about 3/4 cup of water even though I did simmer for about an hour. Oh, and I used Italian diced tomatoes! It was very easy, very satisfying and a wonderful meal; thank you!!

name: aloo gobi
review: Great Indian veggie dish, the sauce itself was nothing short of amazing! Those cilantro stems give so much added flavour! Reduction in star rating, since there was far too much vegetables for the amount of sauce there, and it all turned bland after adding all in. I would only use a small cauliflower and maybe 1 large potato for this amount of sauce, and serve it for 4-6.

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: I made this for lunch today and overall, we loved it. I found it a little salty so will use only part of the seasoning packet next time.

name: hamburger noodle bake
review: Hi, I made this for a neighbor and she really enjoyed it. I took advice from other reviewers and used spaghetti sauce for the tomato sauce (added additional seasonings to taste). I used whole wheat elbow macaroni and mozzarella cheese. I baked it, covered for 20 minutes. Layering was a bit difficult (the sour cream mix was hard to spread) so I sort of "dotted" the mixture over the noodles. Thanks for sharing a great recipe!

name: nestle toll house chocolate chip pan cookie
review: Made as directed and used a 13X9 pan. Baked for 25 minutes. I noticed another reviewer used 3/4 cup butter and I might try that next time! Not sure if my baking time was too high (others baked for much less it seems) but they seemed just fine!

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: These look and smell wonderful. I used four small overripe bananas but I wonder if that was too many. Batter was a bit more runny that I would like! I made jumbo muffins and baked for 25 minutes. I thought I had over baked (they were quite brown) but I actually think they turned out fine. I might decrease the time just a bit next time, though, to see what happens.

name: very moist banana nut bread
review: 256 comments! I can clearly see I arrived late to the party so I ate it all...as in, by MYSELF. In memory of this tragedy I request no moment of silence.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: This recipe was a win!! I'm going to list my changes based on our family's dietary needs in case it's helpful. We added more carrot (an extra cup) and I ran it through the food processor rather than shred it. We then partially sautéed the carrots with the onion as we wanted them to be done. We also used frozen broccoli florets as some of the reviewers said the fresh wasn't cooked through. This worked great and we will do it again!! Also, we used dairy free butter and cashew milk (in place of both the cream and milk). We also used gluten free flour and upped it to 1/2 cup and added in an extra couple tablespoons of butter, since other reviewers have said it was too thin. Our soup turned out thick and creamy. The flavor was excellent, and I loved the addition of carrot (who can complain about adding more veggies?! ;). This will be a regular on our dinner rotation.

name: white chili   football soup
review: I noticed the review on making this vegetarian. I had been thinking of making another recipe, but made this instead. I cooked dry beans instead of using canned. From experience I know the mild chiles don't do much for me, so I added a chopped jalapeno to the onions to saute. Used a bit more cayenne. I also added chopped cilantro and a sliced green onion to the garnishes. It was very tasty. Half the recipe made four large soup bowl servings for us.

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: I cut the recipe in half and made 4 good sized biscuits. I did have to add just an additional slash of milk to get the dough to stay together. Next time I may make more of the butter mixture to go on top. Overall they were a very good addition to our meal.

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: Wonderful! I did use smaller shrimp, and they were tail-less. My breadcrumbs were unseasoned panko. I used shredded parm, the kind in the pouch from the cheese department, not the green can kind. 10 minutes was perfect. So glad I tried them!

name: shredded chicken for enchiladas  tostadas  tacos
review: Three cheers for this recipe. I don't know that you need to let the chicken cool before shredding. I used two forks to shred the chicken while hot and that was fine and made for a quicker preparation. I used oregano instead of marjoram (bc it's what I had in the spice rack) and olive oil in place of butter (bc of a lactose allergy). I used half of the recommended cilantro and left out the tomato sauce bc I didn't have it. I served these quesadillas with a side of chopped avocado prepared with salt, black pepper, and lemon juice. My family asked me to make this meal again after the first bite!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: Delicious! I used an organic all natural cream of mushroom soup which is a little thinner, but still wonderful. Just needed a bit more salt with using that.

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: This was great! I liked that this recipe had bbq sauce in it for a different flavor. I did add some green bell pepper in place of some of the celery. Also tripled the brown sugar and added a few extra seasonings like garlic powder and italian seasonings, and used apple cider vinegar. It was a great sloppy joe recipe. Thanks for the recipe!

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: Classic! Wouldn't change a thing. Thank you for posting the recipe.

name: tsr version of applebee s oriental chicken salad by todd wilbur
review: I'm only reviewing the dressing and it's soooo yummy! Thanks for sharing!

name: strawberry strawberry pie from the really good food cook book
review: Perfect dessert for Easter dinner. I followed another reviewer suggestion and used 1 1/4 cups water and a little squeeze of lemon. I wish my strawberries had been more ripe, a little less firm and more flavorful, but they were just about there. I'm looking forward to making this again in the summer and making 1 1/2 or maybe even double the filling so it makes an enormous mound of filling. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: This was the BEST bread I have ever made in a bread-maker. It was also extremely EASY. So when you see the words EASY or BEST in a review you need to make the recipe ASAP. Thanks Kitchencal.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: I really loved this crust! I made a pepperoni pizza with this crust as well as a margherita pizza. I pre-baked the crust for about 8 minutes before adding the toppings. The pepperoni one held up very nicely and stayed crispy. The Margherita got soggy in the middle of the pizza, but I guess I needed to drain the sliced tomatoes on paper towels better or use less tomatoes, so that was my fault. Will make again!!

name: no bake rice krispies peanut butter granola bars  lower fat
review: As I have now made these about 15 times I figured it is time I made a review LOL! I am giving 5 stars because the beauty of this recipe is its versatility--I have used cashew butter, chocolate chips, and dried cherries together, almond butter with chocolate chips and mint extract, and peanut butter with chocolate chips and crushed pretzels. I always use old fashioned oats pulsed in my coffee grinder a bit, and I often use a mixture of rice crispy cereal and plain cheerios (those cereals that languish in the pantry toward the end of the box LOL). You can totally make these in the microwave; I mix the nut butter, honey, and about 1/4 sugar and microwave for about 45 seconds, stir, then pop it back in the microwave for about 20 seconds. Easy peasy and dangerously quick! The only major tweak I make every time is one I highly recommend--if you use natural nut butters, add about 1/2 teaspoon of salt with the dry ingredients. It will make these taste much more like their store bought counterparts. My kids and I inhale these almost as fast as I can make them, so thank you for the recipe!

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: Yummm! Used what I had on hand - campanelle pasta, regular ground pork sausage, and half-and-half (rather than heavy cream). I tossed in some fresh mushrooms and sausage that were wanting to be used (per another reviewer's suggestion -- thanks!) and it turned out so great. Thanks for this wonderful recipe.

name: extremely soft white bread   bread machine
review: Incredible recipe! The softest bread ever. I usually heat my water to 110 degrees F for proofing yeast and that worked perfectly for this recipe.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: Love this casserole! I've had it with cream of mushroom soup, but I have to say that I like the cream of chicken soup better. Every body gobbles this up at pot lucks.

name: berry smash muffins  strawberry muffins
review: Easy and good!

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: I've recently discovered the deliciousness of balsamic vinegar and so I was excited to try this recipe. I used the ingredients as stated and used boneless, skinless chicken breasts. I started them out at 350 degrees for 11 minutes and then realized the recipe stated that the temperature should be at 400 degrees. So I bumped up the temperature. I kept an eye on them to make sure that I pulled them out as soon as they were done. Even with that, they came out dry and very unflavorful. I think the only way to save these is to cover them up with barbeque sauce. This recipe is not for me.

name: cottage cheese roast  vegetarian meatloaf
review: As I'm (forcibly) gaining experience with vegetarianism, I mixed well this odd combo of ingredients with bitter, fearful tears. To my surprise...voilia! A decent meatless end product for my grass-eater (a term of endearment). What veg dish will I make next? Perhaps a leafloaf? ;-)

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Delicious recipe. My only tweak was to use 1/2 c. of brown sugar instead of the 3/4 cup. Great balance of flavors--not too tangy or salty. I served over white rice with artichoke on the side.

name: overnight french toast casserole
review: So delicious! I did use 2/3 cup sugar since I like to eat french toast with syrup and didn't want a sugar overload. It was perfect and so yummy served with fresh berries on top.

name: one minute flax muffin   low carb
review: Well, when life hands you flax, make a one minute flax muffin!

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: This was great, even though I forgot the garlic! I only added 1 teaspoon of chilli, and my kids still thought it was too hot for them! But hubby and I loved it. Great flavours ... I love corriander! I will be making this alot! Update 2018:This is better than my local Thai restaurant ... Well nearly lol, I have made this with beef also, soaking the beef strips in the cornflour/water mix first! Scattering with cashews too!

name: poverty meal
review: Anyone that said this was bland doesn't know have much imagination because the addition of your favorite spices, some Worcerstershire sauce, maybe some crushed red peppers, a small can of tomato sauce and your favorite cheese(s) makes this a great homemade "hamburger helper" type meal. It is a great starter recipe you can easily customize to anyone's tastes. My kids tend to prefer blander foods that don't have too many ingredients so I make it pretty much according to the recipe, but I am able to add green olives, chopped grilled eggplant, etc. to mine. Corn and diced bell peppers are also good in this. Great way to sneak in some leftover veggies, too. And it goes without saying that this stretches a lb. of hamburger meat like nobody's business! This one is a keeper. No, I wouldn't serve it at a dinner party, but that is not the point of this recipe.

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: These were so good and is a super easy recipe! I halved the recipe and it made 5 large muffins. I thought they tasted better as they sat for the next morning. I made them in the evening for dessert and to have a few leftover for our breakfast. They became more moist and flavorful letting them sit overnight. The only changes I made was to add a splash of vanilla in the batter, and used brown sugar for the crumble topping instead of the white sugar. Thank you for the recipe! I will have to make these again sometime!

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: I'm giving this 5 stars for ease of preparation and taste. I was looking for an easy recipe because I knew I'd be getting a late start on cooking dinner. These pork chops were full of good flavor - in fact, I think I'll sprinkle a little less of the salt seasoning on it next time - and were super simple/hands-off. I thought the turning off of heat and covering was a great way to finish the chops. Mine did come out a bit too dry so next time, I'll do it for a little less time. I used boneless chops - that may have been the reason. Thank you for the added tip at the end. I deglazed the pan with some leftover chicken broth and threw in a little butter. Made for Susie's World Tour - PA-Dutch/Amish

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: Fast and easy to do, I forgot to deglaze but it turned out very nice. I had some fresh thyme and that gave it extra flavour. Made for Susies world tour 2018 Made for the Pantry Pirates

name: parmesan zucchini
review: Sorry. The family didn't care for it.

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: Super easy and great results! I did make a pan sauce with red wine and butter which made them extra special with next to no effort. We will be having these often! Made for Susie's World Tour

name: classic baked ziti
review: Yummy. Easy to make. Thanks for posting.

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: Simple and good. The chops were simply flavored and moist. Thanks for sharing, Nan.

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: These were excellent. I cooked them to 142F, deglazing the pan with white wine and fortifying the pan reduction with butter. Served with roasted carrots and Amish cabbage with bacon. Made for Susie's World Tour.

name: copycat  green giant niblets corn in butter sauce
review: Made this as a side for dinner tonight. I reduced the salt, as we have a family member on a low sodium diet. Also sweetened with stevia. I served it with chicken and stuffing. Everyone enjoyed it.

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: These muffins were a little dry. I used gluten free flour because we have a family member with a gluten intolerance. Next time I will add another banana.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: With so many yummy reviews you can't go wrong with this dish...it's easy and tasty...thanks for sharing your recipe...

name: simple baked chicken drumsticks
review: Simplicity is the best.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: This was just okay for us. I thought it needed more seasoning. As other reviewers recommended I used one pound of Italian Sausage and one pound of hamburger meat. Than ks for sharing.

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: Delicious, even for folks who do not like squash

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: This is a GREAT method. I used chuck roast. It was a bit on the small side, so I cut back on the seasonings a little bit, but I didn't need to. I could have taken all of it and still not been too salty, thanks to the salt being kosher salt. At first, when the crock pot heated up, it smelled like heaven, then, when it got closer to the 8 hour time, it started to smell like maybe it was starting to burn or something akin to that, but all was well when I took it out. I did cook it on the low heat setting, so shouldn't have worried. In fact, I highly recommend using the low setting and refrigerating it overnight, so you can remove the fat from the drippings (assuming you plan to add them back to the meat.) There was LOT of fat left in the juices. The taste of this was simply wonderful, but you could easily mix it up with different flavors and have it come out great. I'll use this meat for sandwiches, burritos, even omelets or fritattas. It would be good over rice or potatoes as well. I put a couple portions in the freezer, and will have another for dinner tomorrow. (I did taste it before putting in the fridge.) This is a keeper for sure.

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: Pretty good. Made as written.

name: split pea soup  crock pot    dairy free
review: Made as written. Very good. Used broth, not water.

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: This was pretty good, a little too salty for me though. Although the chicken was very tender, it came out a little dry. Chicken thighs might work better. I also had issues stirring the soup and cream cheese together. I couldn't get the mixture smooth, there were still clumps of cream cheese and that wasn't very attractive.

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Light fluffy and so pretty to look at, and to top it off so easy to make. Everyone at our get together raved about them. I'm planning on following reviewer Viclynn's freezing directions, so that I'll always have some on hand

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: I actually made two separate batches of this for dinnerue to dietary restrictions of family members. The first batch I made with fresh ground mild Italian sausage and gluten free pasta. The second batch was made with whole grain pasta and diced vegetarian Italian sausage. Both times I used a can of no salt diced tomatoes with Italian seasoning, but forgot to drain it when making the first batch. It still turned out fantastic! I also added extra garlic and used garlic salt instead of regular salt. The only suggestion I got from family was one member asked if I could add some more tomatoes next time.

name: classic baked ziti
review: This is only ok

name: jumbo shrimp parmesan
review: I had to use gluten free bread crumbs due to a family member's gluten intolerance, but otherwise followed the recipe. They turned out great and were enjoyed by all. Served with a side of garlic chive noodles.

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: This is my new go to recipe. It is great!! Thanks for sharing. I'm making this again today. Yummy

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: There are better meatball recipes on this site

name: libby s famous pumpkin pie
review: This has definitely been my staple pumpkin pie recipe; I love it! The spices aren't overpowering, it's got a really nice balance of flavours: a bit creamy yet light and still full of flavour. I've made it with a no-roll pie crust (51537) and it works wonderfully. Everyone loves this pie.. it never lasts long in this house! Thanks! [Edit: lately I've made some tweaks. I sub half the sugar for brown sugar, and increase the amount of spices by 1.5 to 2 times the original amounts. Turns out great!]

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Delicious. Won't change a thing.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: I have to say, this is pretty amazing! My whole family was gobbling it up, husband went back for seconds. Very easy too! Served mine over futtucini, not angel hair and topped with grilled chicken, yum!!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: I needed comfort food from a crock pot. I used one one chicken breast for just DH and I. And I shredded it at the end and served it over rice. I also added sliced onions and green peppers. I also added about 1 tsp of cumin because I like cumin and black beans.

name: pumpkin cake bars with cream cheese frosting
review: If you use fresh pumpkin purée instead of canned, l recommend cutting back on the vegetable oil a bit. Other than that, I wouldn't change a thing.

name: very moist banana nut bread
review: Moist and full of flavor, very nice bread

name: cheesecake factory carrot cake cheesecake
review: This cake was amazing!! Everyone loved it! I made the recipe as is and it was a hit!

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: I made half the recipe just to give it a try before the holiday season. I also tried to read as many reviews as possible! I used a full stick of butter (1/2 cup), and used 2 eggs. I reduced the ginger to 2 tsp as well. I didn't let the dough sit just so I could see how it worked and just in case I am pressed for time in the future. Seemed to work out just fine. I used LOTS of flour and rolled the dough on a Silpat. I also rolled the dough to about 1/2 inch thickness. I didn't have gingerbread men---only a big heart shaped one. I baked mine for 350 for 9 minutes. My spouse said they were great. I look forward to using the gingerbread man cutout.

name: simple vanilla cupcakes
review: Followed the recipe pretty much as described. I used jumbo muffin pans and so baked them for 22 minutes at 350. I didn't get to taste them myself as they were for a friend but they looked and smelled as they should. If I get any feedback from her I'll pass it on.

name: kittencal s onion patties latkes
review: I can't eat onion very well, but I had a small taste and they were delicious. Instead of chopping the onions by hand, I put them in the food processor. I think this caused more liquid to be released, so my batter was a little thin. If you do use the food processor, I would recommend draining the onions first before adding to batter.

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: Very tasty soup! I used fresh carrots. I think this would be good with some pasta added.

name: basic vanilla frosting
review: This was incredibly simple and easy to put together. Thank you so much!

name: light and fluffy pumpkin pancakes
review: I had homemade pumpkin purée instead of canned, which has a much thinner consistency. I assumed my batter may be on the thin side because of this. However, the batter was very thick. I was tempted to add more liquid, but decided to attempt it as is. They were so thick that I was afraid they wouldn't cook through. I cooked them at a lower temperature so the outside wouldn't get done before the inside. They turned out fine, very thick and fluffy. It made eight very filling pancakes.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: This is our go to meatball recipe. Turns out wonderfully every time! Thanks for another winner, kittencal!

name: homemade hamburger buns  bread machine
review: OMG, these turned out sooooo good and so much better than store bought, I'll never buy them again. Using the bread machine made it easy and the results - Wow!! I did brush mine before baking with an egg white and top with toasted sesame seeds, the inside of these came out pillowy soft, but still firm enough to stand up to all our hamburger fixings. As I said, NEVER buy store bought again

name: spiced pumpkin waffles
review: I used fresh pumpkin purée instead of canned. The batter was really thin and the texture was softer than we like. They get mushy before you can eat them once you add syrup. The flavor was fine. Next time I will play with the ingredient measurements and see if I can get them closer to a traditional waffle.

name: frizzled cabbage
review: Only ok. We did not like the taste of the butter
